Hold to Skip
Congratulations, you've restored the Witch's House!
Here's a small gift for you.
Don't forget to doll up the place!
Kyla the Strong
Key Item Issued
No room in your bag. The key item will be sent via mail.
Unknown Sender
{theme} {category} Encyclopedia {achievement} Completion Reward
Honorable member of School for Witches
Stock in Storage
Hello, Ellie!
When I was expanding and tidying up my house, I placed things originally in the storage together.
But I find it too messy to cram all kinds of stuff in one single box.
Since I now have multiple storages, I think it's better to tidy them up.
Kyla devoted to tidying up
Your most caring mom
Kent told me about what happened. I'm relieved to learn that you've begun a new life smoothly.
Mom and Dad will always have your back. Feel free to pursue what you want.
When your apprenticeship is over, the three of us shall go on a trip together.
I'll be writing to you often.
PS: You may find Kent a bit weird, but he is totally trustworthy.
My dear daughter
Moved by your sublime sense of duty as a witch, we decided to change your site of apprenticeship from Highlion to Wisteria.
In addition, we offer a gift in praise of your awe-inspiring attitude.
Please retain this attitude and become an outstanding witch.
Miss Ellie Blueriver
We hereby express our recognition of your {achievement_adjective} achievements on {theme}'s study of {category} with your remarkable spirit of inquiry.
Item Distribution Due to Patch
We are distributing items due to the additional and revised systems.
We apologize for any inconvenience caused.
Development Team
A letter from Freddie
They say you're removing prickly vines from the village? Enite asked me to let you know before I return to the forest.
PS If you need me, just come to the Green Forest Waterfall. I'm usually there fishing.
To a Witch Named Ellie
A letter from Enite
Ellie, just like you left a bowl for the cats last time, I've left an extra bowl as well.
After crossing the bridge by the fountain, there's a small bench. I placed it next to the bench, so feel free to use it.
To Ellie
Ellie,
Are you catching any fish lately?
I have a favor to ask. Please fish for me in the village. There are more Blind Fish there. I want 3 of them.
And, watch out for the cats when you fish. They'll snatch your catch in an instant.
Ellie, I discovered something really interesting!
I think it's a toy for playing with cats.
It's by the stairs next to my house. You should come check it out!
Ellie, I've finished making the Cat Cushion.
I left it by the village fountain. Could you check if the cats are using it?
Of course, only when you have time. Haha.
Ellie, the Dangling Cat Toy is ready.
I've placed it at the crossroads down the path from the bridge. If you head over, you should see the cats playing with it.
Go take a look when you have time.
Ellie, I've completed the Cat Exercise Wheel.
It's set up at the crossroads on the path leading to the library. Can you check if the cats are using it?
Just whenever you're free. Haha.
To Ms. Ellie
Ellie, I'm writing because I've got an urgent matter to discuss.
This talk will be one between witches. Please come to me when you're prepared.
PS: Bring the broom you're currently using.
A Request for Ellie's Help
Hello, Ellie. I have a favor to ask of you.
I've heard that you are into house decoration recently, and I happen to have a related issue. Could you help me with it?
Please drop by if you're interested.
Hello, Ellie.
I apologize for the sudden letter, but I need your help regarding the village bridge.
If you don't mind, please check the village notice board.
I hope you have a wonderful day today!
I didn't expect to receive a letter from you.
You mentioned you were working on something fun.
Fortunately, I've got some information that you may find helpful.
Please find it on the next page. You two can view it together.
I hope your work goes smoothly.
P.S. Please update me on any progress.
Content update information due to the [Friendship] patch.
We are sending you information about the newly added content [Friendship] via letter.
For those who have not experienced the content through the normal route, a separate tutorial popup will be provided.
The popup will activate once you close this letter.
I’ve made some <color=#800000>bait</color> that might help when fishing.
It could be really useful when you want to catch specific fish.
If you’re curious about what they are, come take a look sometime.
Witch! Behold!
Many curious life forms can be found around the Green Forest.
It's so lucky for you to have kept all of them to yourself before I came!
Still, you can't have discovered everything there is to be discovered!
Heh, I've found them in Wisteria! Ritorings, creatures you may have never heard of!
You must be itching to learn more. Come to me then, and brace yourself for a big surprise!
It's Rex!
I heard that you've restored the Witch's House.
Could you come visit me when you have time?
There's something I want to give you in person.
How's everything going?
You're always full of energy, Ellie.
Even I feel more lively when I see you.
However, you should also rest from time to time.
Come over for a break if you're tired.
I'll welcome you with pies.
Enite the pastry chef
It's been a while.
Have you been eating properly?
Rubrum often forgets to eat when he's lost in games.
Do follow a fixed eating schedule even when you're busy.
If there's any dish you crave, just let me know.
Granny Enite
Are you eating properly?
The other day, Rubrum talked about you in great excitement.
He was so radiant that it brightened my mood as well.
Please drop by from time to time to tell us about your latest adventures in person.
Enite, who always welcomes you
I hope you're doing well health-wise.
The temperature suddenly dropped last night.
Is it warm enough in your house?
Tuck yourself in at night, so that you don't catch a cold.
Good health is always one's best treasure.
Enite, who wishes you well
I played in the woods again today!
There were so much to see.
Come with me next time!
It'll be super fun!
You can have everything I find.
Rubrum, who had a good time
I sometimes have bad dreams at night,
but I feel less scared once I think about you.
Thank you for protecting me in my dreams, Ellie!
Here's a gift for you!
Rubrum, who stays strong against bad dreams
This is Rubrum.
There are things that don't work out.
I try hard, but I keep failing.
I almost gave up, but then I decided to finish what I've begun.
Ellie, I will succeed in the end!
Rubrum saddened by the collapsed sand castle
I've been treasure-hunting in the woods a lot.
The woods are full of treasures!
There are pretty stones, sweet fruits, and flowers good for making tea!
They are all treasures to me!
And so is Ellie!
Thank you!
Rubrum the treasure enthusiast
It's Arden.
Today's soup is good.
Come if you want some.
Take this.
I've got many of it.
I woke up from a dream,
and couldn't fall asleep after that.
Doesn't matter though. I can get more sleep tomorrow.
Kyla keeps talking about you.
Drop by when you have time.
Kyla will be glad to see you.
Hello, Ms. Witch,
I sometimes experience bursts of inspiration when striking iron.
It's a mixture of good and bad ideas.
When it happens, I keep the good ones and forget the bad ones as my hammer falls.
That's how life is, right? You keep the good, and discard the bad.
Kyla the strong and handsome
Are you getting enough free time lately?
When I find my hammer too heavy,
I'll drop my work and spend a whole day on recreation. This way, I can come back with full stamina on the second day.
Give it a try, Ellie.
You can only work hard after you've played hard.
Good morning!
Ellie, what do you do when you run into a problem at work?
I will focus on what I can do at the moment.
Strike once, and strike again.
I'll complete a great item before I notice.
Take this, and I'll make another masterpiece for you later.
This letter is about something important!
Actually, I can't remember what that thing is.
I feel like there's something important
and I should write to you about it, but...
Anyway, receiving a letter always lifts one's mood, right?
Ah, this may be exactly the important thing.
Or maybe not. It doesn't matter.
Anyway, take this gift!
Hello, I'm Roy.
Ellie, how's everything going?
Flowers in the village seem to be thriving today, and they remind me of you.
Come visit my shop if you have time.
If you don't, at least accept this.
Have a lovely day.
Roy of Wisteria's flower shop
A precious flower withered the other day.
It upset me even though I knew flowers would wither sooner or later.
I want to tell someone about my sorrow, and you seem to be the best person to go to.
I'm feeling calmer as I write this letter.
Ellie, you can also write to me if you need any emotional support.
Thank you for reading the whole letter.
Whenever night fell, I used to ask myself
whether I was nice to people that day.
That was kind of an embarrassing habit.
Recently, I've quitted my self-reflection and moved potted plants to the windows instead. (Flowers like sunshine. It's really easy to be nice to flowers.)
Tomorrow, I will be a better me.
Ellie, do you want to place a flower by the window too?
Yesterday, I wanted to see the blooming process, so I stared at a mature bud for hours,
but nothing happened.
I kept gazing at it
until I dozed off. I only woke up when the sun had risen.
When I looked up, the bud has bloomed in the morning sun.
So, flowers can also be shy?
How is your day?
Mine is wonderful.
The temperature is mild, and the meals are delicious.
I'm painting smoothly, because the paint is vivid.
The evening sky is as stunning as ever, and the evening breeze is cool.
Here's something I've been hoping to tell you:
Ellie, let's always be friends.
I'm glad to have met you.
Scents of painted flowers
Here's an idea that occurred to me when I was painting.
Paintings are actually incomplete imitations of reality, since they only contain visual elements.
For example, flowers in a painting don't have scents, do they?
However, just as I thought about it, I sensed fragrance!
Flowers made of paint are more real than you'd expect.
Sniff the scents of painted flowers.
World of love
When I was young, I thought the world was full of love.
As I grew up, I felt like love was draining.
Now, I can't find love anywhere.
However... although the world isn't filled with the love my younger self imagined,
it still contains something warm. The world is filled with warmth.
What exactly is this warmth?
How to paint well
When I draw, I sometimes find myself in the zone,
and I'll draw non-stop.
There are also days when I can't seem to get it right,
but I draw non-stop anyway.
However, when I look at the paintings afterwards,
neither situation yields a satisfactory painting.
Vinch in a slump
It's Arin.
I'm writing to share some nice sentences from books I was sorting.
"Have you seen the maiden in the stream?
Her feet separate the crystal clear water as she runs.
Her smile is bright as her hands
stretch out innocently at me.
Have you seen the maiden in the stream? Please give this to her for me,
for I was once saved by her."
From Arin to the maiden in the stream
Hello.
Books should be kept with care.
They need the right temperature and humidity. They should be aired out frequently, but can't be exposed to intense sunlight.
That said, I think books are to be read.
Being read by numerous people gives a book more value than being kept in great condition.
Therefore, the best place to keep books should be somewhere they are easily accessible, right?
Which book shall I read today?
Hello, it's Arin writing.
Today, I was chatting with Rex when you suddenly came to my mind, Ellie.
You resemble Rex in many ways.
Both of you are doers. I'm usually slow to take action, so I keep telling myself that I should learn from you.
I don't think I can ever catch up with you two,
but it's okay.
I like it this way.
Please always set an example for me.
When sorting the books, I found some sentences I want to share with you, Ellie.
"Oh, my love. Take one step forward.
Oh, my love. Take one step backward.
Just stop there.
No, stop at that street.
Let the evening clouds flow by between us.
Please stop just at that street."
Always two steps away.
Hi there! I'm Rex!
You seemed to be worrying about something the other day!
Worry as much as you want!
Until you're tired of worrying!
After that, eat, work out, and sleep to your heart's content.
If your worries don't go away when you wake up... repeat the process!
Rex the currently carefree
This is a letter of fortune!
Ellie, be delightful!
You've been hit by luck.
Luck for you!
Go ahead and open it!
I've brought stuff from home today, and I'm sending some to you.
Whenever I go on a trip, Mom and Dad always stuff my luggage with supplies,
so I've got you some supplies too.
Wait, does that make me your parent?!
I'm your dad!
Ellie, help!
Arin yelled at me today for being too loud.
But I'm not loud... Was she mad because of something else?
Because I messed up the books she'd sorted?
Because I knocked the candle over when sleeping and burned all her translation scripts?
Or because I was too into my adventure and missed the dinner she cooked me?
I don't get it... Ellie, do you have clues?
Was it because I injured myself during my last trip?
It's Alvin writing.
Everyone is the protagonist of their own life.
This statement sounds like a cliche?
I'm talking about the efforts.
A protagonist has to work hard, both on and off stage.
The audience, however, only sees the spotlight they are in.
So far, you're doing well as a protagonist. Keep up the good work.
If you're expecting a compliment, you may be disappointed.
Was today a nice day for you?
I hate it when people say "Have a nice day" to me.
How do you define a "nice" day? A day that gets 70 out of 100? Does getting only 65 make it "not nice"?
That said, I have to reply "You too." since that's the custom.
However, such a conversation seems to make the rest of my day actually nicer, by up to 5 points.
How many points does your day get, Ellie?
Have a nice day.
It's a fan letter.
Last night, I dreamed about you leaving the village.
It felt like a play I enjoyed was over.
Or rather, like I'd come home from a trip?
I can still taste the pleasant sweetness at the tip of my tongue, but the sense of lacking is also intense.
It's not that bad though... but I wish there were a curtain call.
I want to applaud.
Do complete the curtain call.
My eternal sun.
That's my favorite line from the plays I took part in.
"My eternal sun."
However, the sun fell at the climax.
That was the best part of the play.
The line, which appeared early in the play, foreshadowed the sun's fated doom.
It was so passionate, yet so ironic.
Ah, my eternal sun.
Mother,
Mother, how have you been?
My child has been born. My sweet little daughter.
I wish for her to inherit your brilliance, your talent. So I hope to name her after you: Lisa. I beg your blessing.
I will await your reply. Please, take care of yourself.
—Your daughter, Dosca
Ellie, how are you doing?
There's something I want to tell you.
As you know, one of the village cats is particularly fond of you.
Come to me if you want to further enhance your bond with the cats.
A Flyer of Arden's Restaurant
Dishes cooked from quality ingredients and generously seasoned with pepper!
Drop by Arden's Restaurant and treat yourself to a delicious meal after <color=#800000>a long day of work</color>!
Find the establishment right to the south of Wisteria's fountain.
Distinguished apprentice witch Ellie,
Your reliable assistance has saved the witch society from yet another crisis.
Your retrieval of The Silent Guardian will usher in a brand-new chapter for School for Witches and historical records alike.
We are looking forward to your future growth and journey with sincere anticipation and best wishes, and we will contact you again when we confirm your readiness. Yours sincerely.
PS: Please do not reply to this letter. Any attempt to locate the sender is strongly recommended against.
Hello, Ellie. I'm writing to tell you something that might make your life in the Witch's House a little easier.
By now, your adventures must have filled your packs with odds and ends you don't really need. From now on, you can place them into the <color=#800000>Gold Coin Pouch Trading Chest</color> beside my shop.
Deposit 10 spare collected items or materials, and you'll receive a pouch of coin in return. I hope this proves useful to you.
—Aurea
To the owner of the Witch's House,
With your activities resuming in full, we wish to offer our support. Starting tomorrow, a <color=#800000>Luna Coin Pouch Trading Chest</color> will be installed in your garden.
Place any surplus collected items or materials within. For every 10 items deposited, you'll receive 1 Luna Coin Pouch.
We hope this will be of service to you. The Witches' Catalogue will continue to assist you wholeheartedly.
—Witches' Catalogue Department
Ellie, I’ve left another cat bowl down on the lower side of the village.
Head down past the withered wisteria and you’ll find it. Please take good care of the cats.
On Time I Can’t Handle
When I follow my routine, sometimes the work finishes too quickly.
Preparing ingredients, baking, even cleaning—when everything ends too neatly, I’m left with an empty stretch of time.
In those moments, I just don’t know what to do. I start wondering, did I forget something? Did I make a mistake somewhere?
Having idle time feels really hard for me. What do you do when that happens?
If you have good advice, please share it with me.
How about a donut?
Aren’t you living a busy life? Delicious donuts are always prepared for you.
Make your sweet days even more special!
How about tasting them at our Chuity Bakery?
So, what do you think? This is an ad I made. Since I decided to do it, I wanted to do it properly. You should come by and have a taste.
From Clala, waiting for you
I wanted to write you a letter, since you’re always helping me so much.
It’s nothing big. You’d probably say, “You could just tell me in person!” but… that’s embarrassing, isn’t it?
So, I’ll share my feelings with you through this letter instead.
Thank you, always.
That’s all I really wanted to say. Hehe.
Don’t come and say it to me directly. I’ll get too embarrassed.
Ellie, hi hi!
Hehe, the moment I woke up, I wanted to write you a letter.
But now that I’m writing, I don’t really know what to say. I just want to talk with you every single day!
You’re coming to see me today, right? I wait every day, wondering when you’ll show up!
There are so so many things I want to tell you when we meet!
Sis, listen to me!
Clala scolded me again today, you know? Her nagging is the worst, the absolute worst!
It feels like she’s never satisfied with anything I do.
I’m sure the nagging demon king has possessed her or something.
If only you, Ellie, were my sister instead… (sigh)
From Dana, sulking a whole lot
I’ve got a problem.
I’ve got waaay too many things I wanna do, and that’s my problem!
When I do this, I wanna do that too, and when I do that, I wanna do something else again!
You know that feeling when you just can’t choose what to do?
Even today, I was stuck wondering which doll to play with!
Ellie, what do you do when you have this kind of problem?
Can’t you pick for me next time?
Sometimes I get kinda jealous~
That hat of yours… I mean, a talking hat? How hilarious is that?
What if there’s also a talking book or even a talking plant?
Ooh~ just imagining it cracks me up!
I’d really love to see that one day.
Can’t you whip it up with your magic?
There’s something I want to tell you.
I was always thinking that I’m grateful to you. Ellie, you’re a wonderful witch, and everyone likes you.
I wanted to be like you.
Someday I could be like you… haha, no way.
If I stayed a little kid like you, I’d be in trouble. Unlike you, I’ll grow taller and taller. Hehe.
You didn’t actually believe that, did you?
Got leftovers.
My mom and dad sent me a gift again.
I keep telling them I don’t need stuff like this, but they send it every single time.
Since I’m living alone, I don’t need so much of it. Geez.
If I just let it sit around, it’d be a waste, so I’ll share the extras. You can even bow in thanks if you want. Hehe.
From Theo, cleaning up his stuff
My collection has grown recently.
The other day, they were selling a limited-edition bookmark with a cute cat on it.
It was so adorable that I couldn’t help but buy it the moment I saw it. Hahaha!
After all, cute and lovely things are the ultimate truth!
I can’t tell you how glad I am that the artist decided to sell it.
I wonder if they’ll release something else. I really hope they do!
From Bjorn, feeling happy
Ellie, listen to me!
While I was fishing, I suddenly remembered the times when everyone gathered to fish together.
Back then, everyone grabbed a wooden stick and turned it into a fishing rod to play.
And of course, we argued over who caught the biggest fish. Hahaha! Thinking back on it now, it was truly fun!
… Living in this village brings back so many nostalgic memories.
It’s nothing special. Don’t worry about it.
I’ve been trying to write an essay, you know? But hmm, it’s really hard. I want to write something grand, like the words of the great people I’ve read about.
But nothing particular comes to mind.
“As long as you live, chances will come”?
“Opportunity is equal for everyone”?
They’re all just sayings I’ve picked up here and there. If you have a better answer, won’t you tell me?
From Bjorn, full of worries
Additional Brewing Quest Delivery
We are sending you this letter with information about the additional Brewing Tutorial Quest.
For those who could not experience the content through the normal route, we are providing the tutorial quest separately.
Once you close this letter, the quest will be activated.
Notice on Bug Fix for Encyclopedia Completion Reward
If Ellie’s stats (Fatigue, Stamina) are suddenly reset after loading your save,
you may receive a Letter with the Reward on the next in-game day.
If you are not affected by the bug, no Mail will arrive.
We apologize for the inconvenience.
