After completing the quest: [Kyla House Moving Finished]
One day after completing the Arden Villager quest: [Prologue: Everything Is Here for a Reason]
One day after completing the Arden Villager quest: [Act 1, Part 1: They Who Cursed a Dragon]
One day after completing the Arden Villager quest: [Act 1, Part 2: The Person in a Dragon's Memory]
After completing the quest: [Everyone's Stage]
One day after completing the Arden Villager quest: [Act 2: A Cursed Promise]
Arden has lost his night light, which always kept him company at night.
Ellie helps Arden find his missing night light, as he struggles to sleep.
Arden believes that the pepper he bought is cursed.
Ellie investigates the curse on the pepper.
Arden still can't sleep well.
Ellie looks into the items Arden has lost.
Arden keeps having the same dream, convinced he's been cursed.
Ellie investigates a past lover from Arden's dreams – the Warrior.
Arden wants to understand the last words of the Warrior and asks Ellie for help.
It's said that passengers arriving by train to Highlion must take off their shoes when disembarking.
Hear what others say, then decide whether or not to follow the tradition.
Go to the mountaintop you saw from the train and search for the glowing tree.
Outside the train, there are new sights and interesting things to discover.
The train's sleeping compartments are narrow and uncomfortable, leaving you more tired than rested.
While the train is being repaired, explore the forest and find a comfortable place to relax.
To craft the required potion, you must first repair the {InteriorPropBasicName.WitchJuicer}.
Find a way to replace the broken glass bottle so the {InteriorPropBasicName.WitchJuicer} can function properly.
I spent a night at a witch’s house I stumbled upon.
Let’s return before the train departs and get ready to set off for a new place.
The honey pumpkin is blocking the road into the village.
Find a way to remove the honey pumpkin.
A giant prickly vine blocks the village entrance.
Find a way to clear the giant prickly vine.
A little one named Rubrum is stuck in a spider's web and can't move.
Help him break free from the web and get home safely.
The Bomb Potion can't clear the giant prickly vine.
Use the information from the Prickly Vine Fragment to find another solution.
It seems you've found a way to clear the giant prickly vine.
To enter the village, hurry and gather the materials needed to give it another try.
The broom needs to be repaired before you can fly on it.
Collect the materials, then fix it at the workbench.
Use the quill to sketch life forms you encounter in your Encyclopedia. This will tell you how to gather and track them.
If you want to learn more about something, best record it in the Encyclopedia first, and write down the information you observe.
Record the life form you wish to observe and fill your Encyclopedia.
Once the prickly vine are cleared, you can finally enter Wisteria.
Try talking to all the villagers.
Before the village was destroyed by prickly vines, it was home to a carpenter named Kyla.
After speaking with the remaining villagers, decide what to do next.
To bring back the village's former residents, you must first destroy the prickly vines.
Explore Green Forest, find the prickly vine core, and destroy it to solve the problem.
Embark on your adventure to save the village!
To completely clear the prickly vines, you need a potion infused with lunar power.
Ask about the potion recipe, gather the materials, and use it to clear the vines.
The carpenter, who can build houses, is essential for rebuilding the village.
Write a letter to Kyla, the village's former carpenter.
Kyla has returned to Wisteria.
Discuss how to rebuild the village houses and plan for the future.
You've been having strange dreams every night, but you wake up with no memory of them.
Find a way to remember the dreams and solve the mystery.
Get ready to welcome the villagers who want to return to the village.
Kyla is building houses for them – go help her out!
Enite nostalgically mentions the once beautiful fountain in the village center.
Just like fixing Kyla and Roy's house, go help Kyla repair the village fountain.
The village's Cat Temple was also destroyed by the rampant prickly vines.
To honor the two Cat Gods worshiped by the villagers for generations, repair the temple.
The former occupant of the Witch's House, Lisa, might be connected to the prickly vine disaster in the village.
It's time to learn more about this witch.
Ask the villagers about Lisa and find out what kind of witch she was.
The bridge connecting both banks of the village's river is broken, and it needs to be repaired before you can cross.
Talk to Kyla about what needs to be done and work together to fix the bridge.
Just like the village on this side of the bridge, the village on the other side has been almost completely destroyed by the prickly vines.
Explore Cloud Valley, find the core of the prickly vines, and destroy it to solve the problem.
Just like last time, remove the prickly vine core and save the village.
A weird kid is blocking the way into the giant mushroom.
Find out why the kid is crying and try to comfort them.
To completely clear the prickly vines, you need to craft Moon Tears once again.
Talk to the Cat God at the temple, and craft the Moon Tears.
The bridge is fixed, and the village can now accommodate more villagers.
Prepare to welcome the first villager from across the bridge.
Prepare to welcome the second villager from across the bridge.
Prepare to welcome the third villager from across the bridge.
The previously unused space has been turned into a communal area for everyone.
The villagers say they can take a break for now, but you can't help but wonder what it will turn into next.
Get everyone involved in something meaningful and fun.
A villager suggested building a bridge to the area underneath the central fountain.
This time, work with all the villagers to build the bridge together.
Alvin, the elderly shopkeeper, asks Ellie for help with running his sundries store.
Alvin speaks in a mysterious tone about some strange story – who is he really? Investigate this further.
A quiet librarian named Arin mentioned a book filled with magic.
What secrets could this book be hiding that prevent anyone from reading it? Investigate and find out.
Ellie meets someone who seems cursed, constantly talking about nature.
Though the curse is unclear, a special candy can lift the curse. Deliver the candy to her.
After the previous witch left, the Witch's House has stood empty for a long time, and many things are in disrepair.
Ellie can't fix everything alone, so she needs to find someone to help.
Look for a more efficient way to repair the Witch's House and find someone to assist with the repairs.
The shop is buying candies for various purposes.
Regular candy deliveries could bring in quite a bit of money. Pass the test first.
There are rumors about some cats appearing in the village.
Find a way to befriend these cute cats.
The cats in the village love fish.
Go fishing and give the cute cats some fresh fish.
A villager named Freddie sent Ellie a thank-you letter for helping him return to the village.
Take this opportunity to learn more about Freddie, who loves fishing.
The quiet and thoughtful Roy shared a story about flowers.
The most interesting part of his tale is about rosemary.
Investigate whether this story is true.
The energetic explorer Rex says that every time he visits a new place, he searches for something special to give to Arin.
This "special thing" is a material Arin can use to make bookmarks.
What does Arin like for making bookmarks? Find something that matches her taste better than what Rex found.
The quiet painter Vinch wants new paints to gain inspiration for new artworks.
Help Vinch by gathering the materials needed to make new paints.
The village's core member Kyla says she really wants a specific type of alcohol.
Even though Ellie can't drink yet, she can still help Kyla fulfill her wish.
Diane sells services to enhance tool performance.
Use Luna Coins to improve the tools.
Diane offers services to enhance tool performance.
The elevator inside the giant mushroom in Cloud Valley will be come operational after repairs.
Look for the parts needed to fix the smoking elevator.
The suspended ladder in Cloud Valley will be come operational after repairs.
Look for the parts needed to fix the broken ladder.
The elevator inside the Cloud Valley basin will be come operational after repairs.
The sky boards in Cloud Valley Upstream and Downstream will be come operational after repairs.
Look for the parts needed to fix the smoking sky boards.
Diane says that she can make more candies once Ellie explores new regions.
She'll unlock candy delivery services that earn more money, but Ellie needs to gather materials and pass tests to use the services.
To craft new candies with various materials, collect the materials needed for the test and deliver them.
With the Witch's House repaired, the furniture inside can now be freely arranged.
Talk to the villagers who sell furniture to find out what items they offer.
Alvin says that a real witch must ride a proper broom.
Talk to him about how to do that.
You should be able to learn how to change the color of furniture.
{actor} Friendship Level {level} or Higher
Welcome Party Completed
Two days after completing the Welcome Party
What are the mysterious existences Rex is talking about?
Ask the passionate explorer.
Roy says he’ll give a gift to celebrate the repair of his house.
Let’s go find out what the gift is.
Roy seems to be interested in flower-related legends.
His passion may not have come from nowhere.
Listen to Roy's tale.
From the day they moved in, playful Theo has felt a sense of freedom, away from his parents’ interference.
However, feeling that there aren’t enough sweet foods, Theo asks Ellie if there is a magic that can turn any food into something sweet.
Let’s listen to Theo’s story.
Theo wants to share the Witch's Party Snack Gift Boxes he receives with friends.
Hear him out.
Since the previous incidents, Theo has been leading an eventless life.
Recently, however, a strange animal he and his buddies met during an adventure has caught his interest.
Curious about the animal, Theo now seeks your advice.
Theo has learned about a sweet plant growing in the {Map.StarSeaCave}.
He's taking his party and his new friend Honey Bear on an adventure to collect that plant,
and he apparently wants you to join him as well.
Bjorn is working for the village with great passion.
His first duty is to take care of the cats.
Find out about his plan.
There's something Kyla needs.
Find it for her within today.
Although potions crafted by witches can't be used by non-witches, such concoctions are highly versatile and capable of triggering strong or unique effects. Please craft more potions that will aid your exploration and adventure.
Both the last prickly vine core and Lisa Whitegarden are said to be in the {Map.StarSeaCave}.
Remove the last prickly vine core from the {Map.StarSeaCave}, finish village restoration and find Lisa.
Craft a Moon Tears Potion to remove the prickly vine core.
The White Cat God's attitude towards your exploration of the {Map.StarSeaCave} feels suspicious.
Find out about their true intention before you fully restore the village.
All the villagers have returned.
As the final step of village restoration, revive the village's wisteria tree.
What is this warmth in my heart when I get closer to the villagers?
I should try to find out.
When I asked Roy if he had delivered the flowers from the temple to his teacher, he seemed distracted, almost dazed.
When I pressed him for a reason, he only said it was a long story… Just what has happened lately?
I should talk to Roy.
After the incident with the blue rose field, Roy said he needed time to collect his thoughts.
But when we met again, he acted as though nothing had happened.
Something feels off…
I should talk to him, and find out what he's really thinking.
Diane told me that materials from the {Map.StarSeaCave} could also be used to craft new candies.
But, just like in {Map.RainbowForest}, I'll first need to pass her test.
Deliver the requested materials and make the new candy.
Alvin seems to be looking for something.
Get him what he wants within today.
Clala seems to be looking for something.
Get her what she wants within today.
Enite seems to be looking for a certain fish.
Get her the fish she wants within today.
Vinch seems to be looking for something.
Arden, the cooking dragon, has something to say about food.
Let’s go find him and hear what it is.
Kyla seems to be looking for something.
By restoring the bridge leading down the village, more residents can now live here.
We are preparing to welcome the first resident who will move in below the village.
We are preparing to welcome the second resident who will move in below the village.
We are preparing to welcome the third resident who will move in below the village.
Clala, the owner of the fragrant bakery, shared her memories with her younger sister, Dana.
Let’s help the sisters create new memories together.
Thanks to the atlas Aurea gave us, we can now collect maps.
Let’s travel around the various areas of the Green Forest and gather maps.
In Wisteria, cats’ affection increases when you feed or play with them. Try raising any one cat’s affection until <color=#800000>Pet</color> becomes available.
The WitchStation is a convenient device that allows instant travel to the Witch’s House or a return to the original location.
Try using the WitchStation yourself to return.
Thanks to repairing the Witch’s House, it can now be expanded larger than before.
Use the Lizard and the Witch’s Catalog to expand the house’s space wherever you like.
Candy made by witches is often fun or helpful to ordinary people.
Let’s make more simple candy using the ingredients found in the Green Forest.
Arin, the librarian, has informed us that she has finished the preparations to interpret The Silent Guardian.
Let’s find out together with her what is written in the book.
A threatening letter has arrived for Arin, the librarian, telling her to step away from matters related to The Silent Guardian.
However, Arin has said that she wants to uncover the truth to the very end.
Let’s help her and find out what awaits.
One day after completing the Roy Villager quest: [Prologue: Moon-loving Rosemary]
One day after completing the Roy Villager quest: [Act 1: Pansy Heart]
One day after completing the Theo Villager quest: [Prologue: Freedom]
One day after completing the Theo Villager quest: [Act 1: Pranks]
One day after completing the Theo Villager quest: [Act 2: The Encounter]
After completing the quest: [Who Will Come Back? 6]
Arden is the gruff chef who stayed behind in Wisteria.
Give Arden gifts or try various conversations to raise Friendship.
You obtained a broom.
Let’s ride it and use it until its durability is completely depleted.
{Map.GreenForest} is home to many kinds of creatures.
Try to complete each Encyclopedia research task for specific creatures at least once.
{Map.RainbowForest} is home to many kinds of creatures.
Every potion has a special effect.
Use the potions’ power to gather the creatures of {Map.GreenForest}.
Use the potions’ power to gather the creatures of {Map.RainbowForest}.
Use the potions’ power to gather the creatures of {Map.StarSeaCave}.
{Map.StarSeaCave} is home to many kinds of creatures.
One day after completing the Roy Villager quest: [Act 2: Blue Rose Ocean]
Alvin Welcome Party Completed
One day after completing the Arin Villager quest: [Prologue: Placing the Bookmark Once Again]
One day after completing the Arin Villager quest: [Prologue: The Silent Guardian]
One day after completing the Arin Villager quest: [Prologue: The Weight of Truth]
Brew the requested candy and deliver it.
[{outputItem}] Crafting Recipe
{Common.Ritoring}'s Furniture Basket [{aliasedPoolName}]
This basket grants a random [{aliasedPoolName}] furniture recipe.
A Witch’s Life
<color=#800000>Collect</color> the required ingredients, <color=#800000>process</color> them, then try making a <color=#800000>potion</color>.
If there is anything you do not know, try using the <color=#800000>Quill</color> and <color=#800000>Encyclopedia</color>.
Collecting with Special Consideration
Creatures usually live in <color=#800000>specific habitats</color>.
Explore the forests to discover various life forms.
Use the <color=#800000>Quill</color> and <color=#800000>Encyclopedia</color> to find out about their habitats.
View Encyclopedia/Recipes
You can view life form information and potion recipes
written with the quill in the Encyclopedia.
Next Category/Page
Crafting Potions
In order to craft potions, you need to follow the required
<color=#800000>Ingredients</color>, <color=#800000>Fire Setting</color>, and <color=#800000>Ladle Direction</color>.
Carefully read the <color=#800000>recipes in the Encyclopedia</color>.
Save / Load
You can now save and load from the cabinet on the first floor of the Witch's House.
Naps
You can take naps.
*You cannot take naps at <color=#800000>night</color>.
*You can only <color=#800000>take one nap per day</color>.
Spending Time
Some collected items can only be obtained at <color=#800000>specific times</color>.
If you can't collect them soon, you can take a <color=#800000>nap</color> first.
Notes
You can view your notes to see the <color=#800000>keywords</color> you have.
Change to Keywords
You can go to the Memo Board to view your current tasks.
Open Memo Board
Close Memo Board
Witch’s Encyclopedia and Quill
<color=#800000>Press and hold</color> the Use Quill button to draw.
Once the gauge is full and the drawing is complete, the subject of the drawing will be <color=#800000>recorded in the Encyclopedia</color>.
Change Tools
Use Quill
Press the sprint button to move faster than normal.
Sprinting uses stamina.
Energy
Collecting uses energy.
You can recover spent energy by <color=#800000>eating</color> or <color=#800000>sleeping</color>.
Keyword Conversations
You can initiate conversations using the keywords at your disposal.
Change Category
Use Keywords
Use Potions
You can use the <color=#800000>Potion Selector</color> to <color=#800000>select</color> any potion and <color=#800000>use</color> it.
Open Potion Selector
Select Potion
Tiptoe
Certain plants and animals are highly sensitive, so you must approach carefully.
Pressing the "Tiptoe" button allows you to move more quietly but also more slowly.
You can <color=#800000>sell candies</color> to the merchants.
Merchants purchase different <color=#800000>items</color> and use different <color=#800000>currencies</color>.
You can sell using the <color=#800000>Shop</color> keyword in dialogue.
Deliver Special Potion
Merchants buy extra potions according to <color=#800000>special rules</color>, on top of usual potion sales.
Deliver the requested potions to get <color=#800000>more rewards</color>.
Upgrade Work Tool
You can purchase improved <color=#800000>processing tools</color> like <color=#800000>Extractors</color> or <color=#800000>Witch's Pots</color>.
Better tools allow you to make ingredients or potions <color=#800000>faster and in larger quantities</color>.
Book
You can pass <color=#800000>time</color> quickly by reading a book. This is helpful when you're waiting for something.
Books can be stored on the <color=#800000>bookshelfs</color> at the Witch's House.
Training Activities
The <color=#800000>Candy Delivery Quest</color> is a <color=#800000>Training Activity</color> that you <color=#800000>choose</color> to do as needed.
If you opt to refuse such <color=#800000>Training Activities</color>, you can use the <color=#800000>keywords</color> to <color=#800000>do</color> them later.
Check Ingredient Information
If you want to check <color=#800000>which plants and animals</color> provide each ingredient in the recipe, you can tap the Info button to view it.
You can move faster if you ride a Witch’s Broom.
Ride/Get off
Habitat, time of appearance, etc.
Tools used for collecting
Possible collected items
How to make collecting easier
View details
You can view information about <color=#800000>potion usage</color> in the Encyclopedia.
Try crafting <color=#800000>{potion}</color> using <color=#800000>{ingredient_0}</color> and <color=#800000>{ingredient_1}</color>.
<color=#800000>Ingredients required</color> to craft the selected potion are shown here.
The items you pick up while cleaning are <color=#800000>ingredients</color>, so you can craft potions from them right away.
Gallery
Here you can display the <color=#800000>{0}</color> that you have obtained.
You will receive a <color=#800000>{0}</color> once you complete a research topic from the Encyclopedia.
*{0} can only decorate the top of the <color=#800000>{1}</color> of the appropriate {0}.
Parkour
When climbing walls, you can press the <color=#800000>Parkour</color> button to travel faster.
Traveling faster consumes <color=#800000>Stamina</color>.
To lift the pickaxe, press the Use Tool button.
To lower the pickaxe, release the Use Tool button.
To strike slowly but harder with the pickaxe, <color=#800000>hold down</color> the Use Tool button.
<color=#800000>To move at a slow speed</color>, press a direction button.
To drive the trowel into the ground, press the Use Tool button.
To lift the trowel, release the Use Tool button.
A bigger effect may be achieved if the button is released at the right time.
A Witch’s Bug Net
To get into position to use the net, press the Use Tool button.
To swing the net, release the Use Tool button.
To achieve a larger swing, hold the Use Tool button before releasing.
You may level up your Encyclopedia and receive rewards by pulling off different actions.
On the left, you can read <color=#800000>about potions</color>.
On the right, you can read about the <color=#800000>crafting of potions</color>.
Collected items are obtained from plants and animals.
By processing them with tools, they become ingredients for making potions.
The list of potion ingredients.
The firepower necessary to craft the potion.
The direction to stir to craft the potion.
Challenges you may complete while crafting the potion.
Broom Locker
You can store your brooms in the <color=#800000>Broom Locker</color>.
You may only store <color=#800000>brooms</color> in the Broom Locker.
Drawing life forms with the <color=#800000>Quill</color> in the Encyclopedia unlocks <color=#800000>information</color> about them.
When you draw the same type of plant or animal <color=#800000>multiple times</color>, <color=#800000>additional information</color> will be unlocked.
Swim
You may enter and swim in the water demarcated by the markers.
Decorate the Witch's House
You may decorate the interior of the Witch's House however you wish.
<color=#800000>Operate the decorating bell by the entrance</color> of the Witch's House to begin decorating.
Village Bulletin
Village Bulletin <color=#800000>New side quests will be added each morning</color> to the village bulletin.
If you're at loose ends, have a look to see what the villagers need.
Even a small matter can become <color=#800000>a grand adventure</color> in Ellie's company.
Letterbox
Please read your <color=#800000>letters</color> in the letterbox by the door of the Witch's House.
The letters may come with <color=#800000>unexpected gifts</color>.
Feed the Cats
Take and place the <color=#800000>cat food</color> from your inventory on the ground to feed the cats.
Cats are always very <color=#800000>guarded</color>, so you'll have to be careful when feeding them.
There are <color=#800000>cat food bowls</color> in the village that can be used to feed cats.
Place some food that the cats like in them to <color=#800000>attract</color> cats.
Open Tool Selector
Select Tool
Switch Tool
There's <color=#800000>a cooldown</color> before you can use the quill on <color=#800000>something of this type</color> again.
Work tool placement limit
Some work tools have a <color=#800000>placement limit</color>, while others don't.
You can <color=#800000>only place 1</color> of each <color=#800000>processing tools</color> and the <color=#800000>Witch's Pot</color>.
On the other hand, you can <color=#800000>place an unlimited number of</color> <color=#800000>storages</color> and <color=#800000>Incubators</color>.
Open potion selection UI
The Incubator is a tool that lets you obtain <color=#800000>many materials</color> from <color=#800000>a small amount of gathered items</color>.
You can use the Incubator only on flora and fauna in <color=#800000>regions with an Encyclopedia completion rate of 40% or higher</color>.
You can place <color=#800000>multiple</color> Incubators in the workshop.
Craft Potions
Potion crafting placeholder description potion crafting placeholder description potion crafting placeholder description.
Change fire setting and blah-blah-blah change fire setting and blah-blah-blah change fire setting and blah-blah-blah.
Ladle direction left right clockwise and blah-blah-blah.
You can use the <color=#800000>Witch's Pot</color> in the workshop to <color=#800000>craft the potion you need</color>.
When crafting a potion, you need to <color=#800000>check its recipe in the Encyclopedia</color>, use the required <color=#800000>ingredients</color>, adjust the <color=#800000>fire setting</color> and stir with the <color=#800000>ladle</color>.
During the fire setting phase, you should adjust the <color=#800000>heat intensity</color> as required.
You just need to follow the <color=#800000>recipe</color>'s instructions of the current phase and meet the <color=#800000>heat intensity and duration requirements</color>.
During the ladle direction phase, you should adjust the <color=#800000>ladle direction</color>.
You just need to follow the <color=#800000>recipe</color>'s instructions and <color=#800000>stir in the required direction</color> for the required amount of time.
The progression bar at the top indicates the <color=#800000>quality of the potion</color> you're crafting. If you don't follow the instructions, the bar will shorten.
If the bar disappears, <color=#800000>the crafting fails</color>.
The longer the remaining bar when you finish crafting, the <color=#800000>higher your score</color>.
When crafting, you may encounter <color=#800000>unexpected situations</color> in both the <color=#800000>fire setting phase</color> and the <color=#800000>ladle direction phase</color>.
Handle the unexpected situations and make high-quality potions!
When adding ingredients, you must add the <color=#800000>required ingredients</color>.
You just need to follow the instructions in the <color=#800000>recipe</color> and add the <color=#800000>ingredients required</color> for the current phase into the Witch's Pot.
Displayed on the right is the <color=#800000>recipe of the potion</color> currently being crafted.
<color=#800000>Complete all phases of the recipe</color> without failing and <color=#800000>the crafting will be successful</color>.
Potion Brewing Method
Complete recipe <color=#800000>research</color> for a certain number of times to unlock
<color=#800000>auto craft</color> of the recipe.
Auto craft consumes <color=#800000>Durability</color> of the Witch's Pot.
The lower the Durability, the <color=#800000>higher the failure rate</color> during auto craft.
Auto Craft and Witch's Pot Durability
You can boost speed or dive when swimming. Both consume Energy.
To have a map, you need to draw it.
Find the map sign somewhere in a region to draw a map.
Atlas
Enter New Theme
You've entered a new theme.
Obtain new collected items and use them in various events.
Equip Fishing Rod and press the Tool Use Button to cast the line into the water and fish.
(Not usable in shallow waters.)
When you're fishing, watch the bobber closely and wait for fish to bite.
When the fish bites the hook,
rapidly press the tool button to outpower the fish.
Outpower the fish to lift the Fishing Rod and pull it in.
Choose a furniture from the crafting menu to craft it.
You can only start crafting when you have all the required materials in your inventory.
Collect fishes by fishing.
Color variations and special fishes will also be recorded.
Fish Encyclopedia
Keywords
Keywords is a feature for talking to villagers.
You can use keywords to talk to villagers or ask them questions about specific themes.
There are general keywords and special keywords.
General keywords are permanent keywords that apply to all villagers.
Special keywords are for certain occasions such as quests, and are removed after a certain number of uses.
You can view available keywords from the Keyword page of the Journal.
Open Menu
Select Journal
Wisteria is home to many cats.
Different cats show up in the village each time.
Among the cats, some will come to you, and some will hide.
In order to meet the hiding ones, you need to search carefully.
Cat are vigilant. To get close, you need to lower their guards.
Try to make friends with the cats and get to stroke them.
You can lay items on the ground to feed the cats.
For cats not close to you yet, please stay away from the food so that you don't scare them.
Draw any new cats down on the notebook with the quill.
You can record preferences and view affection of cats in the Cat Notes.
Cats
Select Encyclopedia
Select Atlas
Select Notes
To play with the cat, the cat's affection level must be at least Level 1.
While holding the cat toy, press the tool-use button to shake it.
Nearby cats will react and approach the toy.
When the cat approaches the toy, it starts playing with it.
Shake the toy when the cat takes a hunting stance to make it happy.
Shake it at the right timing to make it even happier.
If you play with the cat until it's satisfied, you can grow closer to it.
Even if you play multiple times, you can only get closer once per day.
Cats will use the furniture when they are near it and in a good mood.
The cat will not be interested in other objects while using the furniture.
The player can touch the furniture to interrupt the cat.
Calling Diane
You can use the <color=#800000>call bell</color> to call Diane at any time.
Diane will return after <color=#800000>1 hour</color>.
Broom Shop
Brooms differ in speed, durability, etc. and feel different when you ride them.
You can tell them apart by looking at the types and shaft shapes.
A broom's theme determines its look and name.
Collect brooms of various themes.
Brooms also vary in design and price.
Remember to check out new brooms of the day.
Customization
By customizing, you change the form of a specified item.
You can view customizable items (e.g., furniture, broom) from the customization menu.
Customization costs certain materials, which depend on the type of customization.
You can usually get the materials from villagers.
Choose the target of customization at the workbench.
Please note that the target must be in your bag (inventory).
After you've chosen the target, choose the type of customization.
It depends on the target.
You can also check customizable items via the "View Info" element.
Interact with villagers to bond with them.
The closer your relationship, the more you can talk about and do together.
Some villagers, such as Enite, Rubrum, and Arden, have been living here for ages, while others, such as Kyla, have just moved here.
Destroy prickly vines and restore the village to increase village population.
You can find villager info and quotes in the Villager Notes.
The notes record each villager's name, personality, likes, as well as other personal details.
After you've bond with a villager to some extent, they will confess their worries or issues to you.
You can help the villager solve such problems and have a unique shared experience, which will be recorded in the Villager Notes.
To build Friendship with villagers quickly, give them gifts.
Each villager has their own likes and dislikes, and react differently to gifts.
Their gift preferences unlock when they receive something they like/dislike.
Every moment you spend with Wisteria's villagers is recorded in the notes.
Check the Villager Notes after interacting with the villagers.
By having conversations with the villagers, you may discover their unique tastes.
The more you become friends with them, the richer the conversation topics will be. Try communicating with them every day through different stories.
The mysterious Ritorings live withdrawn lives in the forest.
Little about them is known to the outside world. They offer a clover-shaped gift to anyone who finds them, which is sometimes elaborately wrapped.
Ritoring Shop
You can exchange Ritoring Coins with Rex for random boxes or recipes he owns.
Feel free to trade with Rex every day.
To craft a piece of furniture, register the blueprint of this furniture first.
Use the blueprint from the inventory to add it to the workbench's crafting menu.
To craft furniture, you need a blueprint.
Furniture can be crafted at the workbench.
When swimming, you may <color=#800000>accelerate</color> instantly or <color=#800000>dive</color>,
accelerating or diving will expend <color=#800000>stamina</color>.
Once a subject has been drawn with the Quill, it cannot be drawn again.
Cat Adoption‌
When a cat's Affection is full, you can adopt it and take it to the Witch's House.
When you have a <color=#800000>Token of Friendship</color> in your bag (inventory), stoke a cat with full Affection to adopt it.
Starting from the second day after adoption, your cat will be living with you at the Witch's House, and a higher phase of Affection will unlock.
You may receive gifts from your cat if Affection increases further.
Food with Effects
Having food restores Fatigue. Some food grants buffs in addition.
Food effects don't stack. Having a new type of food overwrites the current effects.
The effects expire after a certain period, when you run out of attempts, or when you fall asleep.
You can gain effects from food even when your Fatigue is full.
Shop Affection System
Some villagers may increase the stock or variety of items they sell when their Affection increases.
Increase Affection of villagers to get more purchasable items.
You need to provide your adopted cat with constant care by stroking it and playing with it.
If you neglect your cat for too long, it may want to leave the Witch's House and return to the village.
Villager Quest
Wisteria’s villagers each have their own lives and stories.
When a villager’s Friendship rises, you’ll receive special requests based on their stories.
Accepting those requests begins a Villager Quest.
Favorites
You can add your <color=#800000>desired recipes (potions, candies, furniture)</color> to the Favorites for quick access.
You can add items to your Favorites from the <color=#800000>Encyclopedia’s Recipe page, the Encyclopedia’s Theme page, the Witch’s Pot, and the Workbench</color>.
You can also select a recipe on your Favorites to adjust the <color=#800000>target quantity</color>.
The Favorites can be checked on pages sorted by crafting stage, and organized as you like.
If processing lowers the required amount, numbers turn <color=#007AFF>blue</color>; once all materials are gathered, they change to a <color=#800000>check mark</color>.
You can check the conditions and objectives of Villager Quests in the Adventure Log.
Quests are activated when the villager’s Friendship and individual conditions are met.
You must also complete the previous quest to proceed to the next one.
Press this button.
Press to continue.
Select the Quill at the bottom.
In the illustrated Encyclopedia, you can obtain various information about plants and animals.
Check their habitats, gathering tools, and collection methods, then try gathering them.
Complete Research Topics to receive additional rewards.
Using Potions on Plants and Animals
By using potions on plants and animals, you can collect them more easily.
Open the potion selector and choose the potion you want to use.
(Drinking potions are used immediately when selected.)
While holding a throwing potion, hold down the throw button to aim, then release the throw button to throw the potion.
Press the cancel button while aiming to cancel the throw.
When you brew or craft a recipe from your Favorites, the result can be automatically reflected on the Favorites.
If there’s a recipe you don’t need, you can select it to remove it.
