Then maybe I should move here?
Let's think about it after you finish your apprenticeship in Highlion and graduate from the School for Witches.
If I'm still alive by then and not bored to death, that is.
For now, let's just not worry about it.
Wisteria's tea is special.
Stories go with tea the most.
It's not bad, although some parts are boring.
Hi, Ms. Witch. I was going to get off work.
Welcome. Have a look at the goods.
Quality of today's goods is quite high.
I value "how to do it" more than "what to do."
Sorry, I can't put down my pen now. Please go ahead. I'm listening.
I look forward to Ms. Witch's story.
Are you busy today as well, Ms. Witch?
Ah, it's a modest gift.
Take care of it.
Doughs are the perfect food to start the day.
Well, what kind of story do you have for me today?
It must be something unusual.
I don't think I need Ms. Witch's help at the moment.
Have you decided? Ms. Witch.
Yes, Rubrum's words inspired me.
You want to bring all the villagers one by one and have them go onto the stage like in a parade?
How... how did you know? I was planning to tell you in person.
I'm always inspired by the improvisation of protagonists, so I've been observing you carefully.
That's a curious idea, and this form of performance does suit the size of the village better.
Replacing stage equipment with humans, it's a nice idea.
Haha, thanks. It occurred to me when I recalled the festival performance I watched with Mom.
Then, I'll leave the music performance to you, Alvin.
No problem. Ms. Witch, you put so much effort into it, so I'll take it seriously.
Let's see... Do we need to prepare anything else?
Didn't you agree to rest this time?
But I'm not the sort of person that would rest just because they're told to.
Fine, I guess a rat would jump into a jar of rice the moment it sees it.
I've promised to be the emcee, so I'd better put that thing into use.
[em1]Attention Potion![/em1] It can produce a beam of light, so it should make me look like the real thing.
You mean the potion you made many of before the Star Gun Festival?
But will the random ingredient stew really be okay?
You did it at the School for Witches just for fun, but we're in Wisteria now.
I don't know what ingredients the villagers will bring. You may mess up.
Will... we? Yeah, Rubrum's looking forward to it.
I don't want to, but I will prepare some [em1]MSG Potion[/em1] just in case.
It's been a while since I last saw that.
Your mother was a big fan of it.
It can turn any horrible flavor into an acceptable one,
only that I'm fed up with its distinct taste.
At least it's better than any horrible flavor.
Yeah. Okay, let's get started!
Huh? Ms. Witch, why are you here so early in the morning?
We've decided to hold a concert, so I just want to check on you and see how the preparation is going.
Since I've accepted the task, I will give it my all.
But we are all beginners, so it won't be a top-class performance, I'm afraid.
I really want to join you. If only I could play any musical instrument. What a pity.
I tried several times, but I really lack talent in this field.
Not only performers and troupes are allowed on the stage.
You can be our emcee, Ms. Witch. You are definitely qualified.
Emcee? But I'm not that eloquent...
Whatever the others might say, you're the biggest contributor to the village's restoration!
How can the protagonist be missing when even supporting roles like them are allowed on the stage!
Besides, it's not like you have stage fright, right?
I don't when it's something fun... but I've never acted as emcee, so I feel shy.
Any great actor was once a rookie.
Just relax, and after all, we need a host for the party.
Okay... if you insist.
But this emcee thing... what should I do exactly?
If I’m going to say it, I guess it’s better to do it in the morning.
Good grief, it's so noisy.
Aren't you too late? Ms. Witch, time is crucial to music!
Haha, it's because we've got such a big crowd.
Everyone ready?
Now, everyone on the stage!
Sure, didn't I mention it? I'll give it my all once I've decided to do it.
One~ Two, three!
You mean that young painter? I know him.
He's talented, but he is not sophisticated.
So, his works lack that captivating appeal.
But I can sense some subtle... desire from them.
Ms. Witch, you should spend some time to appreciate the his paintings when you have the time.
Sometimes, non-humans have a better understanding of humanity.
As long as the script is interesting.
What would you like to discuss with Alvin?
It's nice here. Very quiet.
I especially like the lack of noise here.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Alvin"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Violin
It's my favorite instrument.
Because it's inherently elegant, suitable for both solo and accompaniment.
That's something I made out of my own interest.
As long as there's music, anywhere can be a stage.
Stage
Ms. Witch, have you watched any plays?
The stage is a representation of life. In other words, life itself can also become a stage.
Take the opportunity to experience it. It helps expand a young witch's horizons.
Sundries Store
It's called a sundries store, but the goods are of high quality.
Consider it a pastime for an old man like me.
Are you wondering why people don't ride brooms around the village?
We ride them when necessary. You just haven't seen it.
Village fountain
Places that attract people shouldn't be treated as mere venues for gathering.
Wherever people gather, positive interactions happen.
Now that you mention it, people always say that most witches are picky eaters.
Ms. Ellie, is it true for you too?
That said... even I myself was once so into the spiciness of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_SalmonTuna_Name"))][/em1] that I overate it.
I guess I just revealed an embarrassing anecdote about myself.
Many villagers have jobs that involve making things by hand.
I also enjoy work that brings out full potential of materials.
However, I don't think materials such as [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rock_Name"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Mud_Name"))][/em1] have any worth until processed.
Witches
I've spent most of my life living in big cities.
I only stayed in places like Witch's Houses during my apprenticeship.
It can be said that I mainly stay on the border between witches and humans.
Trends
All trends eventually become old-fashioned. Things with true value must possess unique traits unrelated to trends.
At least that's my standard for deciding what to sell at my sundries store.
Stage props
Nothing gives me a greater sense of achievement than seeing my carefully-made props join a great script in delivering a perfect show.
But this joy can't be shared with others,
because the audience only sees the final product.
We are aware of each other's identity as a witch,
but we haven't talked much.
So, for Ms. Ellie, both Lisa and I are still actors-to-be. It takes a play to know what performance we can offer.
Leading actor
Nothing excites me more than seeing a talented leading actor guide the entire show.
I'm quite impressed by your feats too. I can't wait to see the whole picture of your play.
Troupe
Me and a friend founded a troupe from scratch, and eventually took it to the peak.
It's an experience I will always be proud of.
Forge
Kyla's forge focuses on conveying essence rather than grandeur.
Of course, that doesn't mean its value is superior.
Doesn't it mean that even a useless [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowRock_Name"))][/em1] can be given the life of [em1]usefulness[/em1]?
It already had a unique ecosystem. But after the plants grew larger, it became even more peculiar.
Moreover, the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Kirby_Collect_Name"))][/em1] contains more mushroom spores than other regions.
I'm thinking of processing it a bit and selling it as a fragrance item.
It’s not particularly special, but its stable and peaceful ecosystem is impressive.
Thanks to Miss Ellie removing the thorny vines, the ecosystem feels richer than before.
I sometimes use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BushBug_Water_Name"))][/em1] to clean miscellaneous goods, and it feels like the quality has improved.
A cup of hot tea adds fragrance to life.
Read more, Ms. Witch. There is wisdom in books.
If there's anything you desire, do let me know anytime.
[lua(GetItemName("Reform_BroomStick"))] exchange
Welcome. Always feel free to trade with me for our mutual benefits.
Nice to see you, Ms. Ellie.
If you need a [em1][lua(GetItemName("Reform_BroomStick"))][/em1], bring me [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] or [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect_Unique"))][/em1].
As you probably know, [lua(GetItemName("Reform_BroomStick"))]s are costly.
However, you can still exchange for as many as you can afford.
So... just give me [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] or [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect_Unique"))][/em1].
Let me know when you are ready to trade.
I'm organizing the stuff I can place.
Feel free to look around as much as you like.
Purchase
Miss Ellie, I intend to make a small change to meet your expectations.
I plan to make some [em1]various brooms[/em1]. I’ve also increased the stock of certain items, so please take note.
Well, I don't know.
Ms. Ellie, do you have a moment?
Let me see, around [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowBranch_Name"))][/em1] should be enough. Can you do it?
It's a piece of cake.
Hmm, don't take too long.
I'll leave it to you, then.
Yes. What's up, Alvin?
I'm a bit curious about the story behind the [em1]broom[/em1] you ride, Ms. Ellie. Could you tell me more about it?
This? Um... this is probably just an ordinary broom.
No story?
Oh, I'm sorry. I shouldn't have assumed.
Right. It must be hard to find a decent broom in such a remote village.
Huh? I think this broom is pretty decent...
Ms. Ellie, besides bread, there's no such thing as "pretty decent" in life.
Once should strive for excellence for everything.
But I can't find a better broom...
Well... Can't argue about that.
Can I ask you for a favor?
Favor? What kind of favor?
I want to make something, but don't have enough materials.
Could you please go to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] and collect materials for me?
Since the broom is a symbol of a witch's honor.
"Pretty decent" is not enough.
Would you collect materials for me?
It's nothing.
Just collect 3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Name"))][/em1] in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
Do you want to give 3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowBranch_Name"))][/em1] to Alvin?
Insufficient items.
I've got the materials.
Let's talk about it later.
Excellent.
I should give you something in return, right?
No really, it's not a big deal.
There's no need to be courteous. This benefits both of us.
I asked you to help me collect materials because my [em1]crafting tools[/em1] were damaged.
Now that I have the materials, I can make necessities for you.
What necessities?
An "excellent" [em1]broom[/em1].
Wow. You can make Witch's Broom?
Haha, I hope my skills haven't rusted.
Of course, it's not free. Quality goods don't come cheap.
Alvin, are you a [em1]witch[/em1]?
You don't have to be a witch to make a Witch's Broom, right?
I need to repair my work tools first. Come find me tomorrow.
I'll tell you when I'm ready. Please come back then.
Nothing particularly special, I guess.
Huh? Virgil, have you heard anything?
I think this guy is just a retired actor with excellent skills but a bad personality.
Don't you remember what Arden said?
There must be something wrong with Alvin.
And he might even be a witch.
I'd be really strange if he really is a witch.
Exactly. It's chilling to think a witch might have been an actor.
With the personalities of witches, they could never be actors.
But what if a witch pretended to be an actor to hide something...
He's hiding it pretty well, if that's the case.
Let's investigate whether he's really a witch.
How do we investigate?
People said that he's never at home every [em1]night[/em1]. Let's take a look inside during that time.
Break into someone's house? At night?
It's fine, I'll just take a quick peek and then leave.
Very well... Looks like nobody's around.
Let's search for evidence that proves his [em1]witch[/em1] identity.
What's this...
Oh, he seems to own some expensive items.
Don't talk like a thief.
What thief?!
Hold on, this intricate clock, it looks like something from the Clock Alley in Lucerine Ortu, right?
Even if it is, it doesn't prove he's a witch.
Clock Alley also opens to ordinary people.
But their clocks are super expensive!
I wonder why he'd use something like this.
But this clock is quite common...
So, that's a dead end.
Why is there a stack of papers?
Important information is usually written on paper.
Hmm... looks like receipts or something.
It's not clear exactly what they're about.
Take a closer look. Maybe it's a lead.
Wait a minute. I recognize this.
It's a receipt from the Red Cauldron!
I recognized the seal. This is legitimate evidence.
Besides making witch tools, the Red Cauldron also makes regular tools.
Alvin might just be buying stuff from the Society of Witches to sell.
Hmm, at least it shows he's somewhat related to the Society of Witches.
Let me see...
Is this... a [em1]key[/em1]?
It looks quite peculiar.
Seems like it would be quite difficult to make.
Yeah. It probably isn't meant for ordinary locks...
Don't take it with you.
I know.
By the way, I can't see anything here that needs a key...
Anyway, let's make a note of it for now.
Just a few ordinary boxes.
Can't open them. I'll just peek through the cracks...
Oh? There seems to be something behind the boxes.
Don't forget that we're trespassing.
Moving the boxes might leave a trace.
Nothing unusual here.
Just some ordinary stuff.
I feel like you're up to something.
I haven't said anything yet, have I?
You want to move the boxes, don't you?
Because we have yet to find any conclusive evidence.
Does that mean Alvin isn't a witch?
No, there must be something I haven't found yet.
I want to move the boxes.
Let's stack them on that [em1]carpet[/em1] first, so we can place them back easily later.
Wow, look at this, Virgil.
It's [em1]Luna Coin[/em1].
Lunar Coins...
And this brooch...
It's a [em1]witch brooch[/em1].
Just as I suspected, Alvin was once a [em1]witch[/em1]!
The suspicion just got a lot stronger.
Plus, there's this door deliberately hidden behind the boxes.
What could be behind this door...
Seems to be locked, hmm...
Need any help, Ms. Witch?
Yikes! Alvin...
Seems like you're looking for something.
I, I left something at the sundries store...
Is that so? Did you find it?
Uh... yes. Found it.
But besides that, do you have anything else to say?
Um, yeah... ahem...
Alvin, you're actually a witch, aren't you?!
The clock and receipt in the drawer might not count for much, but this brooch is concrete evidence! Stop denying!
Wait? What...
I am indeed a witch. I didn't intend to hide it...
You had the Clock Alley products and workshop receipts, yet you didn't use them as evidence, which shows your cautiousness. That's good.
Then, there must be something under that hidden door, right?!
You wouldn't pile boxes on top if it was a frequently used room!
I stacked them there when I moved here, and I forgot about it.
It's my [em1]personal workshop[/em1] down there. Would you like a tour?
Huh? Okay...
Even now, you're not showing any fear. I'm impressed.
I haven't finished tidying up yet.
Been busy with moving and my tools got broken.
It's just an ordinary workshop, huh...
Now that the tools are fixed, it's time for a thorough cleanup.
It's late, why don't you go back for today?
Ah, sure...
Oh, can I ask one more question?
Go ahead.
Alvin, you're clearly a witch. How did you end up as an [em1]actor[/em1]?
I heard that witches wouldn't be interested in acting at all.
Is it still the case now? Witches really never change.
I'm not an actor.
Huh? But...
I did work with a theater troupe, making stage props.
I wouldn't want to take the stage myself.
Ah... so you're not an actor.
Young and brave people like you, Ms. Ellie, make good actors.
I'm terrible at acting.
And I never wanted to be an actor.
Hah, witches are probably all the same.
But, Ms. Ellie.
In some sense, everyone is an actor on the "stage" of the world.
We are all actor, but some are leads, some are supporting roles.
I've stepped down from this stage.
Now, you, Ms. Ellie, seems to be the main character.
I'm not that great, really.
No, Ms. Ellie is an excellent lead. Show confidence in your performance.
It's quite late. Time for the curtain call.
Feel free to visit anytime. Next time, there's no need to sneak in.
Of course! I'm really sorry about today. I'll visit again soon.
Take care.
Phew...
Glad it ended smoothly.
Alvin really is a witch.
What a surprise.
But let's not dwell on it too much.
The things Alvin said at the end...
Since he's stepped down from the stage, it means he [em1]once stood on it[/em1], right?
Seems so.
When Alvin was on stage, what happened? Why did he step down?
People at his age usually have done something important in their life.
There's no point pondering about all this. It's time to sleep.
Do you find anything strange?
Whenever you say that, something bad happens.
I mean about Alvin.
Don't you feel something's off?
He is indeed unusual.
Maybe he's a [em1]witch[/em1].
He doesn't have to be a witch to make brooms.
That's true, but...
It's not really a bad thing even if he's a witch. You're a witch too.
Well, you're more of an exception.
Hey!
Anyway, my gut tells me something's not right.
Your hat tells you to stop overthinking.
Let's investigate. Let's ask the villagers.
Other villagers might know something.
Doubt we'll find out anything meaningful.
See who is here? It's been a while since we last talked.
Hmm... A library wing? You're always looking for strange stuff.
Do you know anything about it?
Have you heard of the room with no door?
The room with no door?
There's no door to enter or exit it.
Those in it can't get out, and those out of it can't get in.
Then it's not a room. It's just... a space I guess?
But it's a "room" with no door.
Figure it out yourself.
Hmm, a room is supposed to be somewhere people can enter and exit. If it's a room even when it lacks a door...
There must be a way to access it other than a door.
You know the way to access the wing?
It's not a door, so it's not installed on the wing. I suggest you have a walk [em1]around the library[/em1].
By the way, you aren't planning to enter the wing, are you?
I am, since I'm looking for books for Arin.
Well, be cautious then.
That's also what Enite said.
I don't know what's in there.
But remember this: Preventing intrusion may not be the only reason that a room has no door.
Hm? What is it?
N-nothing. Don't worry.
Phew.
It's by no means appropriate to ask the person directly.
It's the same old style.
Brad's pranks haven't changed at all. Let me see them.
Which letter shall I show him?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Red_Name"))]
Canes are the mirror of a gentleman's character.
One should not blindly pursue a gorgeous design or use luxurious materials,
but pick a cane that perfectly matches them.
A cane is like a stage prop. It must set off the actors while staying out of their way as they move around the stage.
Brad is among the few that know how to achieve this. It's a pity that he's not coming back.
I hope the two youngsters he sent are as accomplished as he is.
Thank you for delivering the letter.
You're welcome. I'm glad I've found a recipient.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Red_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Blue_Name"))]
Portraits are most beautiful when they conform to established sizes and styles.
Unfortunately, I'm not interested in this portable mini portrait thing.
Besides, I prefer still life and landscape over portraits.
If you read carefully, the focus of this letter seems to be leaving a [em1]legacy of memories[/em1] instead of values of paintings.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Blue_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Yellow_Name"))]
[em1]Merchants[/em1] are most likely to ponder over packaging.
Ah, I'm not talking about myself. For me, packaging is only a means to highlight a product's value.
I don't care about the feelings conveyed.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BradsLetter_Yellow_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Alvin! Why are you so calm when a friend of yours is drowning?
No big deal. The "friend" is just a figure of speech.
Don't put it this way in the poster then. You gave me a fright!
C'mon, I wouldn't be so calm if it really were a life-or-death occasion.
By friend, I mean [em1]a sculpture I made[/em1].
A sculpture you made?
Right. I sometimes take one of my sculptures with me when I go for a walk in the evening.
Why would you take a sculpture for a walk?
Sculptures are memories, and mementos.
To put it in a way that you can understand, Ms. Witch, they are media that remind an old man of the past.
Like... diaries?
Kind of.
How come it fell into the water, then?
Well, it was at [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "RainbowForest_Basin"))][/em1]. I was on the footbridge, stroking the sculpture and lost in thought, when I dozed off and dropped it.
And it fell into the [em1]water[/em1] among all places. As I can't swim, I can't rescue it myself.
Do you remember the exact location?
It's a significant sculpture worth being called a "friend!"
I can swim. I'll go look for it.
Your help is the best thing I can possibly expect, Ms. Witch.
Hmm... It was a bright place, probably near some [em1]glowing flowers[/em1].
I think I saw [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Raspberry_Name"))][/em1] when I looked down from the footbridge,
When I walked [em1]up[/em1] from the footbridge, I found a [em1]long ladder[/em1] leading to a vast lake.
Alright, I'll look for this place.
I'm counting on you. My friend can't swim either.
Give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ThornlessRosePiece_Name"))][/em1] to Alvin?
Alvin! Is this the sculpture you lost?
Ooh... yes, it is. Ms. Witch, you must be a great swimmer.
Heh, it's nothing. I can dive too.
You brought my friend back. I'll pay you.
Ah, but before that! I have a question.
Curiosity is a virtue for a protagonist. Ask away.
Why is it in the shape of a rose? Is there significance behind the shape?
Yeah, an old friend of mine liked roses.
I made this sculpture to honor parting with her.
Honor parting? But don't people usually honor meeting and other special days instead?
Parting isn't necessarily a bad thing.
That was when a grand performance of hers turned out to be a success.
I gifted her roses, a flower she liked.
I also plucked all the thorns so that they wouldn't hurt her hands.
Without thorns, roses are elegant and fragile. Anyone can easily hold them.
And we only parted because I left the troupe, so a sculpture is good enough for a memento.
I see. If so, you must miss your friend a lot.
Memories of my life in the troupe often come back to me.
Why did you leave then, Alvin? Did that performance have nothing to do with you?
I'm a wizard. Sooner or later, we would have to part ways.
So much for a geezer's boring stories. Ms. Witch should get her reward.
Speaking of which, would you like to have this sculpture as your reward, Ms. Witch?
Huh? But isn't it a precious memento of yours, Alvin?
A rose with no thorns doesn't pick its owner.
I've kept it for a long time. I should let go now.
I believe it more meaningful to give it to Ms. Ellie, protagonist of this village.
Ah... Can I really have it?
Sure. I made this rose for a friend who used to be the protagonist of a play.
Now, I hope it can start a new life in the hands of Ms. Ellie, another protagonist.
I've got plenty of sculptures and mementos, so I'd appreciate it if you could take it.
Hm, I see. I'll take good care of it.
Great work.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FullBagByEllie"))]
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ThornlessRosePiece_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Alvin said that he the sculpture fell [em1]off the footbridge[/em1], and there were [em1]glowing flowers[/em1] around.
I don't see any [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Raspberry_Name"))][/em1] here...
The [em1]ladder[/em1] here is kind of narrow... but I'll check it out anyway.
I'll look for it.
<wave>Hmm...!</wave>
What have you got?
A rotten leather sack.
Alvin's sculpture isn't here.
This place matches Alvin's description the most.
Let's search it.
How was it?
Got it! It's the sculpture!
Let's see... A rose? It's a sculpture of a rose?
Why would he carve a flower?
Maybe he wanted a flower that wouldn't wither?
Maybe. I'll ask Alvin later.
Now, I just need to get the sculpture to Alvin.
And there isn't a [em1]ladder[/em1] either... but I'll check it out anyway.
Oh, something is glittering...!
Who left a glass bead here?
Doesn't surprise me. Various stuff lie at the bottom of waterbodies.
There's a letter from Alvin.
A talk between witches? Do I sense a hidden message?
I hope everything's okay.
What? Have you caused any trouble again?
Not this time.
But, "a talk between witches"... That's quite appealing.
Alvin, I'm here for the "talk between witches"!
Hello, Ms. Ellie.
It's a serious talk. Have you considered the definition of a [em1]proper[/em1] broom?
Hm? I thought it was gonna be something about witches.
Exactly. A broom qualifies as a symbol of the witch's status, prestige, financial resources... everything.
Do you remember the time when you repaired my workbench for me?
Sure. I saw that you had a wide collection of magical equipment.
Most of it is for making brooms.
Does it... take that much equipment to make a witch's broom?
That's too much trouble for you. I can make do with my current broom.
I've got to remind you that you shouldn't "make do with" your broom.
Usually, you're supposed to find your own equipment under a master witch's guidance...
But it's been years since the last time Lisa was around, and you don't have a new master witch yet.
Huh? Alvin, you know Lisa too?
That's not the point. The point, Ms. Ellie, is that you need a proper broom. Let's put everything else aside.
A good actor needs a suitable script. Similarly, a good witch needs a suitable broom.
The best I can do is to guide you to the starting point of your equipment hunting trip.
What do you say? Do you want to find your own broom?
I certainly can't miss a chance like that.
Alvin, my senior witch, you promised to craft the broom for me!
Ms. Witch, I need to make it clear that I'm not going to act as your master witch.
Just consider it a little thank-you from an old man.
Come to my workshop.
May I go later?
Sure, but remember that lost time never comes back.
Ms. Ellie, I'm waiting for you.
Whoa... This place has also become so neat.
So, you haven't sneaked in since the last time?
O-of course not!
You've been planning to, haven't you?
It doesn't hurt for a young witch to have curiosity.
But there's no need to be stealthy. Just let me know when you want to get in.
Alright, let's get down to business.
Have you ever made any brooms?
No, I only learned to repair them at school.
As a sundry seller, I'm only capable of combining materials made by craftsmen.
So, no need to be ashamed just because you don't have a certain skill.
But combining magic items is an arduous task in itself.
I'm glad you say so.
I will do everything within my power to craft a fine broom, so that the craftsmen's work won't go to waste.
So, Ms. Ellie, could you tell me a thing or two about your family?
I'll start from their names. My mom is Aria Blueriver, and my dad is Aiden Blueriver.
Oh my, you're Aria Blueriver's daughter?
I was wondering if you were a Blueriver... So you really are.
You know Mom?
I can't say I'm a big fan, but she does deserve her reputation as "the most [em1]open-minded[/em1] witch."
I suppose you got your brave, positive character from your mother.
Heh, I guess I did. I get that a lot.
I doubt that it was a compliment.
No comment.
Back to the topic... Do you share your family's [em1]passion for inquisition and adventures[/em1]?
I'm still new to Wisteria, but I've explored every inch of this area!
Right. There’s no place in the village without Ellie’s footprints. And there’s no space filled with books either.
I expect to see such energy in a young Blueriver.
I see. That's a curious piece of information.
Does the broom have something to do with my family?
Every family has different preferences for brooms.
As far as I know, the Bluerivers are more fond of innovative ones.
There's a rumor about the Bluerivers buying all the accessible Solarhorse tail hair.
Ah! You mean those hairs on Dad's broom that emit a red glow.
Which ended up being pulled off by his daughter to make a doll.
It's a doll made after Dad, and he loves it.
Since you're also a Blueriver, I want to use Solarhorse tail hair in your broom too, but I don't have enough in stock, so I'll add it later.
The next question will reveal how well you know yourself.
Since each witch takes in magic differently, the thread used to tie the broom together also differs.
I need to know how you use your power as a witch.
The question is... why have you chosen Wisteria over Highlion?
I've told the others about it too.
Seeing the smiles of villagers makes me happy.
I've chosen to stay in Wisteria for my happiness.
Happiness, I see... I need a thread strong enough to carry the warmth of your kindness.
In that case... Hmm... Threads made of Rainbowffalo horns would be the best choice.
Rainbowffalo horns change color every day, and contain a different power based on the color. Yellow horns suit you well, as they hold the power of happiness.
What I said seems to have helped?
Whatever your answers are, they can't be wrong, because I'm tailoring the broom to you.
I didn't know that to make my broom, we need to have such talks. This is magical.
It's pointless to use even the most precious materials if not on a broom that meets the witch's needs.
That's why we need such conversations.
Unfortunately, my hands have gone rigid as I age... making it harder for me to weave.
Now that the thread is ready, let's talk about [em1]your life as a witch[/em1].
Tell me what has excited you the most since you came here.
Or, you can tell me about what you enjoy the most on this stage named Wisteria.
I like everything going on here. Everything about this place excites me so much.
It's almost impossible to pick just one... But, now that I think about it...
Fill up the Encyclopedia
I enjoy everything I do here, but the best part is to see and record what I've only read about in books.
It also reminds me of all the things I've accomplished since I came here!
If so, I suppose you need a broom for easy travel as you observe and explore the surroundings?
Considering what this land offers, I suggest using head hair from Leafbeavers for the brush. That way, you can see your surroundings clearly even during travel.
We are using local materials from Wisteria too?
This land provides fine materials, but only skilled witches can put them to good use.
But it's been a while since I collected materials myself. I only have underdeveloped ones here, which is a shame.
Had I known this, I could have brought my own materials.
Materials crafted by a young witch... I'm curious... We can give it a try the next time.
By the way, you know yourself better than I expected, Ms. Ellie.
Hahah. You're just asking about what I enjoy. That's not tricky.
It takes some witches days to answer even questions this simple, because they've never thought about what kind of witches they are...
I hope they had more confidence in themselves.
Here's the last question. I'll say a few [em1]words[/em1]. I want you to pick the one you find the most catchy.
Spiderweb, leaf, cold charcoal. That's it.
Hm? Is that all?
It is. Pick the most catchy one.
Well... the most catchy one...
Spiderweb
It reminds me of [em1]Rubrum[/em1] caught on a giant spiderweb.
Rubrum gave me a reason for coming to this village... I'm obliged to him.
So, Rubrum is the major cause of your stay.
You picked the word by association. That's a good approach.
Now I know what kind of broom you need.
I'll combine the best materials in my own way.
And I also need... Right, Moonhare whiskers are crucial.
Ms. Ellie, your broom's ready.
Mmm... It's been a long time since I made a broom. It really takes me back.
My goodness!
I believe it's gonna be an awesome broom!
Here you are. Check it out.
It's your custom-ordered broom. I haven't worked so hard in ages. It's put a strain on my shoulders.
I can see that it's nothing like my current broom.
It's a refined piece of work by a craftsman.
I'm glad to hear that, my hat friend.
Still, Ms. Ellie, you shouldn't be content with a single broom, since a witch's condition changes constantly.
Just like how the same script can give birth to different presentations, each attractive in its own way.
But... Alvin, aren't you the only villager capable of making brooms?
And it never came to me that I'd be selling witch brooms in an isolated village.
I'll consider stocking more witch brooms. It's for you, but not only you.
<wave>Aha!</wave> Does that mean I would be able to buy brooms with [em1]Luna Coins[/em1]?
Yes, since I'm currently a [em1]sundry seller[/em1].
Okay, I'll put your broom to good use.
Thank you for making it!
Cold charcoal
It reminds me of the first time I saw [em1]Kyla[/em1] build a house.
Kyla began to strike iron the first day she moved back. She was soaked with sweat, but she seemed to be enjoying herself.
The idea that "every villager would be this glad when they moved back" delighted me so much.
So, Kyla is your best assistant in bringing the villagers back.
Leaf
It reminds me of the [em1]bitter grape tea tree[/em1] on top of the hill.
It was a fleeting sight during my train ride... but I've gotten used to seeing it every day. It's such a miracle.
So, the bitter grape tea tree is a symbol of luck for you.
Go on adventures
I enjoy everything I do here, but the best part is to remove prickly vines and help the villagers.
At first, I only climbed the vines by the railroad out of curiosity...
But before I know it, I've visited so many places. It could never have happened back at school.
If so, I suppose you need a fast broom that takes you to the sites of new events in no time?
Considering what this land offers, I suggest using sticky hair from Shroom Raccoons for the brush. That way, you won't fall off no matter how fast you go.
Listen to villagers
I enjoy everything I do here, but the best part is to listen to everything the villagers have to say.
It's not a big village, but the villagers have their share of happenings in life.
It feels meaningful to learn about all those happenings and empathize with the villagers!
If so, I suppose you need a balanced broom for you to associate with the villagers and become part of the village?
Considering what this land offers, I suggest using Bellody flowers for the brush. That way, you can hear what's going on here more clearly.
O Witch, help those in your reach.
Alvin, as a witch yourself, you know what this saying means, right?
Sure. I can sense your ability of sharing happiness.
If so, the Lavablooms will suit you well. These flowers from the Volcano Island never melt or tear.
When woven together, their leaves make the most enduring rope. The high cost is the only shortcoming.
I thought it would be more fun to stay here.
My heart started to race the moment my train accidentally stopped by the village.
I see. You need a thread resilient enough to cope with your energy and curiosity.
This is Demonspider's thread. Despite the daunting name, it's the smallest spider that exists, capable of producing the most resilient spider silk.
That said, I hope the thread were thicker... It hurts to have it sink into my fingers when weaving.
Because I want to be a real witch just like my parents.
That's why I thought it the best to be an apprentice at this village.
A witch that follows the right path should get materials from the Azure Island.
Let's see... Right, it's home to a plant called Cloud Tree. Its roots will be the proper material for you.
Cloud Trees are giant trees that grow all the way into clouds. Threads made of their roots are strong enough to last a lifetime.
I'm actually quite ordinary.
Ordinary?
I am far less unruly than Mom.
That's right. You take after Aiden too, in that you don't act recklessly.
Aria is as enthusiastic as flames; Aiden is as steady as a forest. You've got both traits in you.
I'm not that great.
I'm only fond of curious things that interest me.
Right, Ellie is just allergic to adventures in books.
That explains it. You prefer to create your own path instead of following your family's.
Every stage prop should have its use. Every element should contribute to the final product.
Similarly, I don't want my work to violate the author's purpose.
By the way, why are you asking?
Because I got a request and I wonder if I can manage.
A client of Aurea's wants to change the color of his furniture.
She's tasked me with the color changing.
I see. You want to know how to change the color of items.
Right. The buyer should be allowed to make the furniture their preferred color.
After all, the furniture is owned by its buyer, not its maker.
The lack of audience renders all performances meaningless...
You've brought me new insights. I'll try to provide useful suggestions in return.
Really? Thank you.
Firstly, as you may already know, it's within a witch's power to change the form of things.
[em1]Customizing[/em1] furniture is similar to crafting potions.
You need to apply several thin layers to the materials, and spread the materials so that they don't stick.
Mmm, so, customizing furniture color is as simple as crafting potions, but it still needs to be done with care?
Correct. The point is to understand the item.
As long as you achieve that, you can change anything into the form you want.
Besides furniture, you can also try to customize [em1]brooms[/em1].
Brooms too?
[em1]Brooms[/em1] too. And it's not just the colors. You can even change their powers.
That's all the suggestions I can provide. I hope they are helpful?
They certainly are. Thank you!
To customize brooms, you need a [em1]Broom Customization Kit[/em1]. I can offer it at my sundries store if you want.
A flower sculpture that looks real?
Planning a new stage prop, Ms. Witch?
Uh... not quite. It's actually an assignment from the Black Cat God.
A divine trial, is it? Now that is a curious tale.
And how will you pay the price?
Uh... is there something you need?
Haha, I jest. Just tell me the story afterward. That'll be enough.
Hm. I don't quite have enough materials on hand.
To make even one sculpture, you'll need to bring me [em1]one [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1].
That's easy enough! I can bring as many as you need.
Then what shall I craft for you?
First, I'll fetch that [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1].
I've learned the meanings of all the flowers. I can make them now.
Let's tell Roy and bring them to the Black Cat God.
Rosemary.
Please craft a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfRosemary_Name"))][/em1]!
One moment.
Here it is.
Now I just need to take this to Roy to meet the Black Cat God.
Daphne
Please craft a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfDaphne_Name"))][/em1]!
Are you sure that's the right flower?
I'm sure!
Adonis
Please craft a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfAdonis_Name"))][/em1]!
Please craft a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfWisteria_Name"))][/em1]!
Check crafted items
Curious to see what sculptures I've made, Ms. Witch?
I've crafted a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfRosemary_Name"))][/em1].
I've crafted a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfDaphne_Name"))][/em1].
Do they match what you needed?
I've crafted a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfWisteria_Name"))][/em1].
I've crafted a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfAdonis_Name"))][/em1].
Nothing's been made yet.
Well now... I've only ever seen roses like that used as [em1]props[/em1].
Props? So, they're fake?
Hm. Fake and real... Depends on how you look at it.
Tell me, Ms. Witch, do you know the [em1]meaning of a blue rose[/em1]?
It stands for [em1]impossibility[/em1].
But to those who've seen one with their own eyes... it would be a [em1]miracle[/em1].
You sure know a lot about the tongue of flowers, Alvin.
Not really. My knowledge is shallow at best.
But if I were to point you to someone who knows more...
It'd be someone who can [em1]paint[/em1] the false so real it deceives the eye.
Alvin! Could you make me a flower sculpture again, like last time?
Hm. Another task from the Black Cat God?
Ah, no, not this time.
Then shouldn't you settle your last debt first?
Debt?
You promised to tell me your story in return for that sculpture.
I don't normally allow debts. Twice would be pushing it.
Oh! Right! I did say that... But this is kind of urgent.
And what flower sculpture do you need now?
A [em1]rose[/em1].
Just one bloom? That'd cost you a little extra, but manageable.
Not just one. More like... a lot.
How many exactly?
Enough to make a whole flower field...?
Whew. That's no small request.
Is it impossible?
How could I turn down a request from you, Ms. Witch?
Really? You'll do it?
Yes. But as I said, I won't be extending your debt again.
With so many roses to craft, I'll need you to help as my assistant.
That way, you'll also pay off what you owe from last time.
That's fine by me!
<shake>Ughhh</shake>... okay, maybe not fine at all.
Already complaining? That's not a line worthy of a protagonist.
The road is long. Keep your hands moving, or you'll never reach the ending you want.
Now, what became of that Black Cat God's task?
Oh, that.
Roy wanted the [em1]flower from the temple[/em1], so he went to ask the Black Cat God's blessing.
The god said, "If you desire the promised flower, then bring me an [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1], nestled among [em1]living flowers[/em1]."
They also said, "Living flowers bloom in the [em1]heart[/em1]."
Quite the riddle.
So you came to me, hoping I could fashion this ever-blooming flower.
Exactly. Even if it's artificial, it has to look real for the Black Cat God.
But what of the living flower in the heart? What was the answer?
It was Roy's [em1]pansy brooch[/em1]. He always wears it close to his chest.
He even prepared a massive bouquet of pansies.
Oh, and the Black Cat God said something strange.
"No flower can bloom for a hundred days."
If only they'd speak a little more plainly.
Even the brightest hero must leave the stage when the curtain falls.
A flower that blooms out of season has no fragrance. Just like a hero who refuses to step down.
You sound just like the Black Cat God...
Heh. I'll take that as a compliment.
So, the task is done. Now, what's with this sudden need for a whole bed of roses?
Well... that's a long story.
Hm. The miracle of a blue rose...
I never imagined there'd be a witch who wanted to make such a garden.
Oh, but don't tell Roy! It's a [em1]secret[/em1]. I want to surprise him once it's complete.
He'll be happier if he sees it with no clue beforehand.
Understood. But keep your hands moving while you talk.
So far, you've only managed a bouquet. You'll never meet your deadline at this pace.
Ugh...
So, are you trying to bring about a miracle yourself, Ms. Witch?
Huh? I wouldn't go that far. It's not that grand.
Considering the meaning of a blue rose, perhaps it isn't far off.
For most, its meaning is [em1]impossible[/em1]... yet to those who've seen it, it becomes [em1]a miracle[/em1].
And miracles are things only the young truly believe in.
I suspect this stage will be quite the spectacle.
And look, our work is done! Your tale made the time fly.
Wow, they look just like real roses!
For props in the witch's play, I gave them special care.
Thanks, Alvin! With these, I can really make a whole field of flowers.
Then I look forward to a splendid finale.
And one small piece of advice, so I don't spoil your performance...
Don't assume that a seasoned actor is any more prepared for tragedy.
...Is that a riddle?
No. Just a reminder. A florist lives among the living.
And those who keep life close sometimes lose it against their will.
So if you're set on the ending you want, don't delay.
Now, I'll excuse myself. I have a journal waiting to be written.
Okay! Thanks again!
Now... where should I make this field of roses?
How about in front of the temple?
That's the temple entrance... I can't just claim it for myself.
Well, you didn't break into the headmaster's office just to decorate it, right?
I only went in. I didn't use it!
Still, finding a more [em1]secluded spot[/em1] might be better.
Yeah. No need to attract attention.
Hmm... somewhere hidden, with space for a flowerbed...
Got it! We'll plant them where the [em1]Green Forest prickly vine core[/em1] used to be!
It's quiet there, so Roy can enjoy it in peace.
A gift? I'll pretend to be curious.
<Waiting for a gift>
[em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]? You know me quite well, Ms. Ellie.
Thank you for your gift.
A [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]? It's a nice gift.
[em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]...
I'll take it if you don't need it.
Ms. Ellie, have I ever said that life is about pursuing the [em1]great[/em1] stuff?
If this performance is part of the process, I'll teach you this one time.
This is a [em1]sorry excuse[/em1] for a great gift.
Actually, Ms. Ellie, I'm kind of surprised.
Conversations with you have somehow brought me back to... I mean, thank you.
I'll cherish this [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] for the rest of my life.
Your life as an apprentice witch has many more impressive aspects than most witches.
It seems that you are embodying the saying, "A witch should help those closest at hand," better than anyone else.
It meant that seeing one can reveal ten. I will gladly accept the gift.
Winning someone's heart is the most valuable thing.
The many things contained within the gift—I have received them well.
There's no need.
I've received enough. Excessiveness isn't desirable.
Welcome. Perfect timing.
I've got you this. Here you are.
Everyone uses it in their own way. I hope you will discover your way.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Alvin"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
Oh, wait a second.
I hope you like it.
Welcome, Ellie. I have something to tell you.
I'm an actor that has long left the stage. My play had a nice ending.
The current play is your play, Ellie, and you're doing well in it.
I was meant to be watching, but before I knew it, I'd joined you on the stage.
I'm not supposed to do so,
but I simply couldn't resist the protagonist's charisma.
I will probably keep joining you in the performance. Please forgive the arrogance of a mere audience member.
Consider this a flower I throw on stage.
I thought you might like it, so I prepared it for you.
Ellie BlueRiver, I suppose it's time to acknowledge it.
Even a single prop, depending on how it is placed and used, can change the course and direction of the play.
You have sincerely directed the play of life on the stages of Wisteria and reality.
In that sense, the gift you gave me as a prop seems perfectly fitting.
I pay my respects to your [em1]play[/em1].
Accept this. It's in place of a bouquet.
From now on, as an audience of your play, I look forward to it.
[em1]A copy of Book of Memories[/em1]? Why would you want such a thing?
It's for Roy. I want to make a [em1]Book of Memories[/em1], the graduation photo album of witches.
With a Book of Memories, I can show Roy what an extraordinary life he has lived so far.
Alvin, you're a trader of rare items. I was wondering if you would have a [em1]copy of Book of Memories[/em1].
I do. Those photo albums are always sought after.
But tell me, what do you offer in exchange for this copy?
I'm afraid I'm not going to charge a small amount.
H-how much are you charging then?
A bag of Equus Gold Coins.
That's outrageous!!
It's common knowledge that the more convenience an item provides, the more expensive it is. In addition, this copy I have is for the general users.
I do have a cheaper one, but it wasn't made by the witch society, so let's forget about that one.
I... I guess I'll have to make some money first... Wait for me, Roy...
She's doing it for Roy? I suppose it has something to do with that incident.
You want to rewrite the story and give it a [em1]happy ending[/em1]?
Of course! I won't let it end as it is!
I want Roy to return to his former self.
But the flower shop owner has already stepped down from the stage.
Then I'll just drag him back on stage.
Interesting... If miracles exist, they only happen to those who take action.
I happen to have a copy that's usable but not suitable for sale. You can have it.
But weren't you going to charge a large amount? Are you sure you want to give it away?
I'm interested in the adaptation you're going to compose.
You've brought about countless miracles, but will you be able to turn the tides of a story already falling apart?
I do wish to see how this story will unfold.
You're baffling me. Can I really have it?
You need it, don't you?
Just think of it as me paying to watch a performance. However this story ends, I won't complain.
I'll take it then. Thank you, Alvin.
I look forward to seeing the ending you give to this story.
Ms. Ellie, thank you for coming.
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("OneEyeFrog_Powder"))][/em1] for me?
Really? That is reassuring.
Can you finish it [em1]today[/em1]?
It's no big deal. I need a witch to help me with something, so I put up a poster.
It's for the sundries store. That's why I'm asking it of you.
I want to experiment with that item.
It's been a while since I did any witchcraft, but I'm in the mood for it.
I'm afraid I can't explain its purpose in detail, but I do need it.
I want to match it with items offered at my store.
Bjorn said that he needed something special, which requires some preparation.
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("BubbleLizard_Water"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("MoonButterfly_Water"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("CaveLizard_Jelly"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Reaver_Powder"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("LeafOtter_Water"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("WaterDragonfly_Jelly"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Gboolnori_Powder"))][/em1] for me?
Could you craft 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Powder"))][/em1] for me?
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("OneEyeFrog_Powder"))][/em1] to Alvin?
Alvin, I've got you the items you want.
I'd expect no less of Ellie.
You've granted my request perfectly. It's time for me to repay you.
I hope you can create value with this.
1x [lua(GetItemName("OneEyeFrog_Powder"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("BubbleLizard_Water"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("BubbleLizard_Water"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("MoonButterfly_Water"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("MoonButterfly_Water"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("CaveLizard_Jelly"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("CaveLizard_Jelly"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Reaver_Powder"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Reaver_Powder"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("LeafOtter_Water"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("LeafOtter_Water"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("WaterDragonfly_Jelly"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("WaterDragonfly_Jelly"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Gboolnori_Powder"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Gboolnori_Powder"))] will do.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Powder"))][/em1] to Alvin?
1x [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Powder"))] will do.
Alvin, did you ever borrow a flag from Vinch?
A flag? Ah! You mean the one from the parade.
Yes, that's the one.
Indeed, I borrowed it from him.
Could you give it to me? I need it for something...
Seems that flag has quite a few admirers.
I know, right? I don't understand why everyone's so obsessed with it.
Then you'd best go find [em1]Rex[/em1].
...Huh?
I gave it to him not long ago. He asked me for it.
Ah... got it.
<shake>I've got a bad feeling about this...</shake>
Worried Rex might have broken it?
What I'm worried about is Rex lending it to someone else.
But now that you've said that... I guess I'm worried about both.
Anyway... let's go find [em1]Rex[/em1].
Alvin, I came to pick up the flag as promised.
Ah, I see. Here it is.
How was the investigation?
Hm, yes. To put it simply, there was nothing special.
It was just decent-quality cloth. Nothing unusual.
Seems it was just my mistake.
Lately I’ve been having such mistakes more often. I’ll have to be careful.
That can happen.
Oh, I’m heading to Cloud Valley to plant the seeds now, but you and the others will need to come along.
Please bring the others with you at that time.
Understood. I’ll pass the word along.
That name brings back memories...
I was shaken, too, when the vines began to grow and she was gone.
It all felt... too predictable.
Today I came to ask about Lisa as she really was, day to day.
Day to day?
Not the grand events. Just... what kind of person she was.
Very well.
Her hair was a silver as smooth as marble.
Her eyes, large and aquamarine, gave her a kind impression.
Altogether, she had a soft, approachable look to her.
But when she was alone, her brow would knot, her lips would twist, and her face would brim with discontent.
But the villagers all said she was kind and gentle.
She was. With them, she was always courteous.
She'd wear a slightly [em1]awkward smile[/em1], and she usually granted whatever they asked of her...
So, of course, they remember her kindly.
Do you think she disliked doing that?
I don't believe so.
This is only my guess, but...
It wasn't that she disliked people. More like she was weary of them.
Weary of people?
Anyone who came to her with a request, she'd bristle at them, almost by reflex.
But truth be told, I think she enjoyed helping the villagers.
If she hadn't, she never would've stayed here for so many years.
The ending... wasn't the best.
It's not over yet.
You're right. The play isn't finished.
I hope it ends in happiness.
Then let's work for that together.
Your stories help. Thank you, Alvin.
Think nothing of it. Come by anytime.
So... you've got something on your mind.
Whoa... You noticed right away.
When you're watching a great play, sometimes you can read everything in the actor's eyes.
Then I'll just say it straight.
I need to find the torch that was used in the very first graduation ceremony.
Heh, now that's an intriguing relic to hunt for.
In your play, I'm but an observer. In truth, I'd rather remain in the audience forever.
But... When it comes to finding the torch...
That much I can do. I'll count it as just another prop.
Thank you! Alvin, you really are the best shopkeeper there is.
To be called "the best" for such a small kindness... Truly, I'm humbled.
Very well. To meet your expectations, I'll see to it right away.
Ah, and do pass along my regards to Diane.
The [em1]torch[/em1] will be ready whenever you wish to hold a graduation.
So put your worries aside and focus on preparing the rest.
It was a family that baked bread with true sincerity.
They were a very passionate couple.
The eldest daughter seemed to have inherited her parents’ character just as it was.
The younger daughter... I don’t remember exactly. Honestly, I rarely went down to the lower part of the village, so I hardly ever saw her.
Why did you open a sundries store?
Well, I can't say it was due to some remarkable opportunities or anything.
With abundant funds, there's no need for excessive effort, but lollygagging all day isn't for me either.
So, I needed a job that could keep me appropriately busy.
Plus, a sundries store doesn't look out of place no matter where it's opened.
Right, whether it's a village or a big city, there are always sundries stores.
And, you get to meet people of all shapes and sizes.
Where there are people, there are stories.
I see you enjoy interacting with people.
Yes. Observing all sorts of people is quite fascinating.
Originally, I didn't plan to return to Wisteria,
but when I heard about a great witch who was actively saving the village and overcoming crises, I became interested.
Oh, I'm not that amazing.
No need to be modest. In my eyes, Ms. Witch is an interesting heroine.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Alvin"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Ms. Witch, do you like music?
I only enjoy listening to them.
Because I lack the talent for singing or playing instruments.
Ah, that's truly a pity.
The closer you get to music, the more you'll find it to be a good friend.
It seems like music is a good friend to Alvin.
Hmm... music enriches our lives.
Ms. Witch, why don't you try learning to play an instrument?
Instruments, although complicated, are very honest. They always follow your fingers and breaths.
The feedback is exact and is incredibly elegant.
Hmm... but becoming proficient must be quite difficult, right? I'm already busy with my apprentice witch duties...
All the more reason to practice playing an instrument. Cultivation leads to excellence.
Um... It feels like being back in school...
Ms. Ellie, do you have a strong bond with your broom?
I suppose so?
You don't seem to be certain enough. Being familiar with your tools isn't enough. As a witch, you should establish a bond with them.
In other words, you should think of them as a part of your body.
Hmm... But I've been used to my current tools since my schooldays... Are you saying that it's not enough?
My point is, you should not overestimate yourself.
When I was young, I also once lived on my broom.
But surely, I didn't do it to establish a bond with my broom. I did it because I had to.
You lived on your broom... Is that even possible?
Haha, Ms. Ellie, that's just a figure of speech.
During early days of the troupe, I was as busy as a bee.
To get on and off the stage and decorate it faster, I did most of the work on my broom.
And I did it subconsciously. It took me quite some time to realize that I was on my broom.
That's just an example. Everyone has a different approach, and you should find yours.
Alvin, where did you serve your witch apprenticeship?
Oh, I haven't talked about that.
Had my train delayed like yours, Ms. Ellie, I'd probably have stayed at Wisteria.
What do you mean...?
I was assigned to Highlion, your former destination.
Unlike you, I spent quite some time at my Witch's House before I could graduate.
How's life in Highlion? I heard that witches there are very busy.
As you know, there are three Witch's Houses in Highlion. I stayed at the HQ — the one inside the palace.
If memory serves, in my first few years, I was making [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))][/em1]s all the time,
because we needed [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))][/em1]s to create vast open space for laying train tracks.
Wait... "first few years"? But shouldn't your apprenticeship last only three years in total?
During my schooldays, each witch should be an apprentice for ten years.
I thought it was mentioned in witch history books. You weren't aware of it?
No... I didn't know it took so long.
Alvin, you used to work in a troupe?
Why did you turn from an apprentice witch to a troupe member?
I've always been interested in cultures born from witches and humans,
and Highlion can be considered the best place to experience such artistic cultures.
Musicians sing on every street. Performances are given on stages of every size.
Poets and novelists discuss literature in every tavern. And all of these render witches inspirations to create items.
It sounds so fun...! You've made me even more curious.
However, everything will cause greater hunger if oversupplied.
I gradually grew tired of cultures that pursued stylish improvisations.
Just when my frustration was accumulating... I ran into a small stage built in a basement.
An actor, whose name I had never heard of, was playing a monodrama there.
To be honest, it was not a fancy performance. I could hardly hold back my laugh when I saw those wooden props patched with paper.
However, that actor knew what he was supposed to do on the stage.
It was an original play, but his perfect delivery surpassed all the famous plays I'd watched.
It was a eureka moment for me. I thought I could build an unprecedented stage for him.
(Replay the previous story?)
About music
Sundries store
Brooms
Back
Apprentice witches
I always carry a quill and a catalogue with me.
Even a cup of tea can make ordinary moments special.
Alvin, don't you make potions? I didn't see any in your shop.
Potions, eh... It's been so long I can't say exactly when, but at some point I simply stopped making them.
Aren't useful things supposed to be... good?
Mm... that sounds complicated.
Convenience isn't always the right answer, you see.
It's not a conviction, mind you. I haven't sworn off making or using them. If needed, I would.
Then do you remember the last potion you used?
Yes. It was a [lua(GetItemName("HeatPotion"))].
I used it to warm a basement as cold as ice... funny how sometimes I even miss that chill.
These days, I take pleasure in discomfort. Standing on the border between witches and humans, and savoring that tension.
As you said, potions are indispensable tools for witches. But that's all they are. Tools.
To me, a witch should be able to handle many tasks, with many different solutions.
So think of this as the stage where I'm exploring those possibilities.
Where have you been? I haven't been seeing you.
Goodbye.
The specialty here? The stew I've been making since I opened the restaurant, of course.
There is no special recipe for cooking.
I always have plenty of pepper ready.
Nothing has changed today.
There's nothing better for killing time.
I have this feeling that it will remind me of something.
Feels refreshing to see it.
And,
Eat this.
This is for you.
Do you have something to say?
Say it.
I'm a [em1]dragon[/em1].
I'm also a [em1]cook[/em1].
I wouldn't have known if you didn't tell me.
Then, what more do you want to know?
Well, [em1]why[/em1] is a dragon working as a cook?
Hmm, well...
I forgot.
How can you forget that?
I guess it wasn't so important.
That doesn't seem so.
How would I know when I have forgotten?
Because you're a [em1]dragon[/em1].
And also a [em1]cook[/em1].
Well, of course.
What’s the problem?
The problem is that you [em1]forgot[/em1].
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Arden"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Do you hate witches?
Yeah.
I don't have any good memories about them.
Didn't the witch at the Witch's House help the villagers?
She helped us a lot.
Then those are good memories.
Now that you mention it, they are.
I still don’t like them though.
Then, what about me? I'm also a [em1]witch[/em1].
Come to think of it, you really are.
You don't like me?
I can't say whether I like you or not.
It hasn't been long since I first met you.
It depends on what you do from now on.
Um.
Do you know about dragons?
I know as much as what I learned from school.
I didn't study any further.
What do you know?
That they live a thousand years as giant lizards that breathe fire from their mouths.
You know a lot.
I surely do. I was quite the honor student.
But they are all wrong.
A dragon doesn’t live a thousand years.
But aren't you called thousand-year dragons because you live for a thousand years?
We don't live one particular life for a thousand years.
We live many lives.
Hmm... What's the difference?
Have you been using your [em1]night light[/em1]?
Oh, yes.
It's the first time I've seen a lamp without a wick.
Was it made by witches?
I've helped you find it. Shouldn't you at least tell me about it?
I really don't know.
I got it at some point and have been using it ever since.
Could it be something legendary?
You've got a fertile imagination.
That's because you're a dragon, Arden!
Well... I've had it for a very long time. Maybe it's got a long history.
It's really too old now and isn't that valuable.
But... it's something I've gotten accustomed to.
I suppose I've reached a point where I'd feel lost without it.
Arden, what kind of dragon are you?
What kind of dragon? Asking obscure questions again, huh?
Come on, I'm not! Stories usually depict various kinds of dragons, don't they.
There are righteous dragons that fight alongside knights, and evil ones that loot the world for treasure.
Well... I don't quite remember my past.
But didn't you mention guarding treasure in a mountain?
Maybe I did...
You really did. Be more certain.
Right, villagers were scared of me.
The first time I went to that mountain, I had a cold and couldn't stop breathing fire. I ended up burning down an entire forest.
Do dragons also catch cold?
I suppose so. I, for one, have caught a cold.
Anyway, after that, villagers started to enter the cave I lived without permission.
I don't think they were there to see you.
They would bring all kinds of stuff and leave them in the cave... Probably all treasure, now that I think about it.
If so, wouldn't adventurers and thieves also visit your cave frequently, in search of treasure?
Yeah, humans came and go all the time. One day, I became so annoyed that I flew down the mountain for a word with them.
However, every human that had met me had passed away.
I guess the villagers back then already had much misunderstanding about you.
Right. And I didn't bother to resolve it.
Self-introduction
About witches
About dragons
Things here for no reason
Past self
Pepper's the best condiment.
I've been running a restaurant all this time. I think I used to guard a treasure trove.
Tobacco
Stubbornness
Dreams
Memories
What are you staring at?
Why are you so obsessed with pepper, Arden?
Do witches dream too?
Enite's changed a lot, hasn't she?
Losing memories doesn't mean you lose all of them.
Nonsense.
I use pepper because it makes food taste better, that's all.
So it's not just some chef's stubborn streak, huh?
Or do you just like spicy food?
That part's true.
I don't remember exactly, but... back when I first opened this place, a customer told me something.
Said my cooking was missing something. Told me not to hold back on the pepper.
If you actually listened, that must've been one sharp-tongued customer.
Wrong. I was so pissed off at being told what to do that we argued. I remember that clearly.
I can't follow this conversation at all.
So... they said your food was lacking, you got mad, right?
So, I dumped pepper all over it just to spite her.
She loved it. And when I tried it... I liked it too.
So, your taste for pepper wasn't even your own idea?
Who knows when it started...
But yeah. I just got used to it that way.
...Can't say for sure.
You really smoke a lot, Arden.
Doesn't your throat hurt?
Never felt that.
Well, dragons breathe fire, so I guess cigarettes are nothing in comparison.
Why? Thinking of trying it yourself?
No way! I hate the smell.
My grandma smoked, and it had this weird, fishy stench. Ever since then, I can't stand it.
A "fishy" smell, huh? Then it must've been tobacco from the northern witches.
Wait... How would you know that?
Because that stench comes from a plant that only grows in the far north. It's too damp there, so the smell never dries out.
I remember it well.
You talk like you've smoked it yourself.
I have. Still do, sometimes.
Really? It's a very long way from here.
Hmph. There are peddlers in town. Why would I bother traveling that far?
<wave>Right?</wave> I figured as much.
Tsk. You're awfully simple.
I'm not about to close my restaurant just to buy tobacco.
What was Enite like when she was young?
Of course I dream.
Just last night, I dreamed I was swimming in a chocolate fountain.
So... what memories do remain?
I just know some memories stay, and some vanish.
Why? Do you wish you could dream of other things, instead of just nightmares?
Then what's your oldest memory?
You must've been a child once too, right?
I don't even remember my parents' faces.
Really? That's sad.
...But I remember having a younger brother.
We lived together for decades, at least until we learned to fly.
Arden's little brother? Now I'm curious. Do you still keep in touch?
No. Don't even know where he lives.
That's cold...
Even so, if I saw him, I'd recognize him. Funny thing. Family you can always recognize, even after centuries.
I actually ran into him once, decades ago.
Just said hello, asked how he was doing.
And then?
We went our separate ways.
Dragons really are... incredible, in every sense.
She wasn't as calm as I am now.
Used to drink and sing in my tavern all the time.
That's hard to picture.
Enite's so quiet and kind now.
When she came back to the village, she'd changed.
Come to think of it, Enite mentioned something like that.
She said she was grateful you stayed in the village until the end.
That's all you've got to say?
If Enite hadn't returned, maybe I would've left too.
Running a restaurant in an empty town makes no sense.
So you two really needed each other. Enite and you.
Seems that way.
But even after you came back, you stayed the same, Arden.
Yeah. I had my reasons.
Witches can enter dreams, right? I wondered if maybe I could too.
You probably mean [lua(GetItemName("RememberDreamPotion"))].
Want to try it? You could do anything in your dreams.
I do dream of more than nightmares... but I never remember them.
What happens if a dragon drinks it?
A dragon?
I guess if a normal person uses it, it works as intended...
Not sure. Should we find out?
I'd love to see your dreams, Arden.
Maybe it'll be events from centuries ago.
Hmph. Planning to sneak into my dreams, weren't you?
Forget it. I'd rather not know.
Are you flying in them? You are a dragon, after all.
That'll be interesting.
Still... as long as my memory lasted, I've kept this restaurant. It's all I have now that matters.
Dragons don't cling to blood ties. What matters is who you choose to stay with.
Like the people of Wisteria. And me, right?
...Hmph.
Come again if you're hungry.
I’m not open for business now.
Thanks to you, the restaurant's been having more customers.
To feed everyone, I plan to cook more food and increase my [em1]stock[/em1].
I've put [em1]extra efforts[/em1] in some of the dishes. Try them and you'll see.
You came.
I don't know about that story.
I’ve never heard of it.
Heh, you're a witch.
Yes, I’m Ellie, an apprentice witch.
I'm [em1]Arden[/em1], a [em1]dragon[/em1] and a [em1]cook[/em1].
You helped Rubrum? You're pretty kind.
Don't mention it.
Are you going to stay here for a while?
Tell me if you're hungry.
Although it's not for free.
Okay, sure.
This is for helping Rubrum.
This one's free. Take it.
It’s the last one remaining.
... Why are you staring at me like that?
Ah, I'm sorry. It's my first time seeing a dragon with my own eyes.
Makes sense. Normally you wouldn't see one.
Even Mom said that she seldom met a dragon.
That's why I wasn't sure... but you're a real dragon.
I never thought I would meet a chef dragon in a place like this.
Since dragons have no reason to mingle with humans...
I think I was like that too.
I can't tell you the reason even if you look at me with those eyes.
Because I don't remember myself.
Thank you. I’ll enjoy it.
The witch from before... What kind of witch was Lisa?
She wasn't a bad witch.
Is that all?
She was kind and quiet. She listened to everything people had to say.
She didn’t come out to the village often. It seemed like she was usually doing something at home.
You don’t know what she was doing in the house?
Of course I don’t.
I told you. Lisa was quiet.
Alright. Let me know if you recall something.
I don’t know anything.
Ask someone else.
The prickly vines of the village?
Yes, just in case you know something.
Well, I don't know much about the prickly vine.
I just feel the [em1]malice[/em1] filled in it.
[em1]Malice[/em1]?
[em1]Prickly vines devoted to destroying houses[/em1]? It's so unnatural.
If it’s not someone’s [em1]malice[/em1], what would it be?
Is there someone who would do such a terrible thing?
I don't know. Well...
Heh, I'm not sure. I don't know anything.
How about searching through the [em1]witch's house[/em1] at least?
Hey you. Did you promise to get rid of these prickly vines?
Yes, that’s right.
But will you be able to do it?
Of course. I'll bring the village back to its former appearance.
That's some confidence.
Did you find the bag?
Yup, here.
Ah, thanks. I needed that.
What’s in it?
Hmm, curious, are you? It’s my secret recipe.
Woah, really? What is it?
Pepper.
Pepper?
Yeah, black gold, the king of spices.
But I thought pepper is pretty cheap these days? Anyway, I don't really like pepper.
Here, have a taste. This is true cuisine.
Ugh. The taste of pepper is overwhelming!
Strange. People used to like it back in the old days.
Man, I was looking forward to this secret recipe of yours.
Just how long ago were the "old days"?
Did you say that you kept having weird dreams?
Yes... probably. Although I’m not sure, because I don’t remember...
Do you also feel some kind of disorientation when you wake up?
Like you have forgotten something important?
Yes, that’s right. It’s exactly that.
Do you know something?
No, I’m also like that.
You too, Arden?
It's not that serious, but I feel like that from time to time.
That I'm forgetting something...
I'll let you know if I find a solution.
There's no need for that.
What? But...
There would be a reason if I forgot.
Don’t worry about it.
Well... Like I said before, I can roughly remember, but I don't exactly know who it was.
Still, wasn't there any kind of trace left?
I searched the inside of the restaurant after you left, but there was nothing in particular.
Hmmm.
Come to think of it, there are things I put outside because I'm going to throw them away.
Take a look at them.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Accept"))]
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Decline"))]
I'm up to something else. I'll come back later.
Do what you want.
Why would you throw them away?
Because I don't know why they are here. They seemed to have just popped up.
I've thrown away quite a few things like this in the past.
Some of them seem to have been taken by other people.
If you see something you like, you can take it.
It might be cursed though...
Never mind then.
You're here.
Yeah! How was it, Arden?
Still the same. Even after eating that candy or something, I couldn't sleep because of the dream.
Hmm... You still recall nothing about the curse?
Let's find those items.
I've thought about it, but I have no idea who would curse me.
I think there were some cursed treasures as well.
Where are these treasures?
I don't know. Must be somewhere else since we can't find them here.
If they were treasures, I think someone probably took them already...
Even if they were cursed.
Because you can't tell from the outside.
Should I give the dragon figure and drawing to Arden?
Arden! Take a look at this!
Isn't this me?
It really is what you looked like?!
Wasn't that what you expected?
Still, I was surprised... No, that's not the point.
Arden, take a look at this as well! This came out of the dragon figure.
My love.
It is written here in dragon language.
Arden.
The reason why you keep dreaming is not because of a curse, Arden.
It's because you've forgotten someone.
So maybe, that's the reason why you keep dreaming about that person?
I promised to run a restaurant together.
With whom?
A warrior who was after my treasure.
Yeah, I loved her. That's how it was.
What happened to her?
She died...A long time ago.
It's okay. I don't feel anything.
Thanks. I think you're right.
I don't know why she popped up in my dreams, but I may find out once I dream again.
Hmmm, I did it, right?
Yeah, thanks.
It's still too early to thank me! I'll also help you find your other memories, Arden!
That wouldn't be necessary if I can sleep but... Do what you want.
Anyway, thanks for your effort.
Is love supposed to be this desolate?
That depends on the person.
But it feels... more indifferent than what I read about in books.
If you don't even remember you loved, doesn't that mean you never loved much?
No no.
He said he kept having dreams... Maybe he forgot something he didn't want to?
If Arden is even forgetting his feelings, I want to help find them for him.
Because you’re a witch?
Because of your self-esteem?
Because you feel sorry for him?
Yes. Helping others is the witch spirit!
Of course. Ellie the witch will finish whatever she has started!
Yes, it would be very sad if he forgot the person he loved so much like that.
I should go fetch the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DragonPiece_Name"))][/em1], [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DragonPiece'sDraft_Name"))][/em1].
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Arden"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
I wasn't expecting much, but see what I've found! I'm a genius!
The box is a treasure chest.
Let's take a look at the inside.
You remind me of your mother because she used to open every chest she found.
Only Arden would put food ingredients in a treasure chest.
But still, food ingredients shouldn't be put in a treasure chest!
It's up to the owner to decide what to put in it.
Why are there so many radishes?
I don't think radish is needed in stews.
It's not radish, it's parsnip.
It's an ingredient often put in stews and pies.
Aha.
No, I searched all the way to the bottom and found nothing but radish.
I told you that it’s parsnip.
Radish hell!
You're not listening to me, right?
I am. You say it's radish.
House repairing? Do I look like a carpenter to you?
My tools are a knife and a spatula. Not a saw and a hammer.
Should I ask Kyla instead?
Of course. Kyla is good at this.
But it's a Witch's House.
Well…
Well, I suppose Kyla can do that too. Just ask her in person.
A restaurant decorated with weapons feels scary.
It will make people want to curse it.
Look at those cracks.
What's there to look at? They're just old, broken sword and shield.
Maybe there's something written on them.
There’s nothing!
I said they're just old things.
The wretched soul of a treasure-seeking warrior downed by the dragon's flames has possessed...!
Nope.
But what on earth is this?
A collection of Kyla's failed works?
They're too old for that.
This is really...
Surprising.
Just junk. Nothing but junk.
Because the world is not your oyster.
Why do you sound like it's someone else's business?!
It can't be like this!
What are you going to do?
Arden said some of the things thrown away seem to have been taken by other people.
I should go ask the villagers.
It would be much better than just looking through junk!
This is a dragon, right...?
It looks a lot different from Arden, though.
Maybe it's Arden’s appearance in the past?
Ahhh!
What's this?! A curse?!
The neck has been separated.
What a horrible curse...
No! Something’s inside.
Drawing? A person? What a terrible drawing.
There are strange letters too. Is this also a drawing?
It’s dragon language. The dragon scripts.
You know, Virgil.
This isn't a curse.
Arden just forgot someone.
Apron, teacup, wine glass, and dragon figure...
Oh, can you read it?
That I don’t know.
He's dreaming because he threw away a bunch of stuff. Since he can't remember.
Because he's a dragon?
Because he's a dragon that has lived many lives.
Let's take it to Arden.
I don't remember anything special.
I've told you everything.
Roy?
I heard he ran a flower shop in the village.
He didn't come to the restaurant very often, and I never met him much elsewhere.
So, I don't know him very well.
The [em1]burned box[/em1] in the village. Was it you?
How’d that happen?
I was lighting the candle with my breath...
...but a [em1]cough[/em1] came over me.
And that was that.
Why don’t you just use a [em1]match[/em1]?
How do you expect me to use such a tiny thing?
All I have to do is just breathe on them.
You'll burn down every box in this village if you do it this way.
I’ll be fine if I’m careful.
Come to think of it, can't you just breathe fire into the streetlamps and light them?
I'm sure I can.
Then it's settled.
But there's nothing to burn in the streetlamps.
And each only has a small glass bottle in it. There's no room for [em1]Firewood[/em1].
I thought so too.
But the streetlamps would melt away if you light [em1]Hot Flames[/em1] in them.
You need [em1]Cold Flames[/em1] for that.
[em1]Cold Flames[/em1] that don’t require fuel...
Why, do you think you're up for the task?
This is quite hard.
Yeah, before you end up burning down every single box in this village.
Alright, go give it a shot.
Now, what to do...
Dunno. Hmm... [em1]Cold Flames[/em1]...
How about we use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))][/em1]?
Light that bright would end up blinding you.
Something softer... with a prettier color... <bounce>That's it!</bounce>
<rainb>Twinkle-Twinkle Juice!</rainb>
Oh, it's not everyday that you get a good idea...
I need the [em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice recipe[/em1].
[em1]<wave>For the sake of this village</wave>[/em1]!
Oh please, you just want to drink that [em1]junk[/em1].
It has a [em1]soft glow[/em1], it's [em1]cool to the touch[/em1], it's perfect! Sure it tastes kinda [em1]sweet[/em1], but that's just a bonus.
[em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice[/em1] should do the trick!
It's the village's streetlamp, so go ask the villagers.
Alright! Let’s decide after asking them [em1]their favorite colors[/em1].
Um, since they will be put in the village streetlamps, it'd be boring to make just ordinary streetlamps out of them.
Let's use a color different from that of ordinary streetlamps!
Do you have a color that you like, Arden?
I don't really mind either way, but if I have to choose, it'd be [em1]silver[/em1].
[em1]Silver[/em1]
I’m surprised it’s not gold.
Gold is good, too.
Black, like pepper, is also fine.
But [em1]silver[/em1] is better.
Why do you like the color silver so much?
Not too sure. Can't remember. But why the question about color?
I'm asking around to decide the color of the light coming from the streetlamps.
Ah, right.
I don't really mind either way, but if I have to choose, it'd be silver.
I've got it right here.
Oh, thanks.
Fine. You want to know [em1]how to breathe fire[/em1], is that it?
I wasn’t too sure myself, so I thought it through step-by-step to teach you.
Alright!
First, [em1]breathe in[/em1].
Then, heat up the innermost [em1]crimson tooth[/em1].
Okay...?
Then squeeze the [em1]pouch[/em1] in your throat to release the liquid.
I'll teach you step-by-step.
Spray the liquid as you exhale, and flames will come forth.
How does that sound?
It won’t work!
The breathe-in part seemed fine.
But I don't have a [em1]crimson tooth[/em1] to heat up!
Have you properly heated up your tooth?
I see.
What do you mean "I see"...
After all, you're not a dragon.
My lifelong dream...
So what if you can’t breathe fire?
<shake>It’s not as simple as that!</shake>
All it does is hurt your throat. Not really useful at all.
Treasure?
Here, you did me a favor, so have this bread.
Okay…
Back in the old days, I used it to threaten the humans who were after my [em1]treasure[/em1].
But nowadays I just use it to increase the heat when I'm boiling a stew.
Where is the treasure now? Did you hide it in a secret cave?
Can't remember.
What happened to the people who were after your treasure?
Can you really forget something so important?
It happens.
Hello, Arden.
Arden?
<shake>Arden!!!</shake>
Oh! You scared me.
Why sneak up on me and shout like that?
I've called your name countless times!
What were you so occupied with that you couldn't even hear me?
I was just dozing off.
Come to think of it, you do seem a bit tired.
I haven't been getting much sleep lately.
There was this night light I kept next to me when I slept, but I lost it.
I went out at night with it one time, using it as a lantern, but I forgot to take it back.
I went back to look for it after I remembered, but it was gone.
Did someone take it?
I don’t know.
Try looking for it on your way.
What does it look like?
Sorry, I’m a little busy right now.
Sure. You can look for it whenever you’re free.
It's a special silver color, and it doesn't have a wick or candle, even though it's a lamp.
I went to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] lake[/em1] far from the village and spent some time there.
Alright. I’ll look for it.
It wasn’t there when I went to look for it, but you never know.
That area is filled with the [em1]scent of flowers[/em1] at night.
I don’t see anything by the lake.
Arden did say he couldn’t find it.
Since it's an open area, we would see it if it were here. Maybe we should go search somewhere else?
Why don't you go ask another kid who prances around in the woods like you?
I'm not just prancing around. I'm here because I have work to do!
But I guess it won't hurt to ask around.
This must be the place Rubrum mentioned.
Let’s look for the night light.
Found it! This is the location marked on the map.
I just need to take it to Arden.
So, you found the time to look for my [em1]night light[/em1]?
Arden, I found it.
Oh, where was it?
Rubrum found it first, but he forgot to bring it back to you.
Good work.
But how'd you end up taking a night light all the way to the lake?
Just ‘cause.
Again with that "just ‘cause"
I’ve always visited the lake from time to time for no specific reason. That's all.
The urge just comes up sometimes.
And when it does, I go and gaze out on the lake for a while.
A fond memory, perhaps?
Who can say… Just a habit of sorts.
In any case, thanks for finding it.
I am a bit tired, but it's not urgent.
Bring it back to me if you find it.
Sure thing, let me know when you’re available.
Return the night light to Arden?
It wasn't there when I went to look for it, but you never know.
I found it near the Bitter Grape Tea Tree.
It’s best to avoid that crazy bird.
Wait, is there such a [em1]potion[/em1]?
I really need to get through.
Hmm... Have some [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))] while I think.
Wow, that looks delicious.
[em1]40 Gold Coins[/em1].
You said you had to get past a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "Gaga_Name"))], didn't you?
I don’t have money for the stew.
Actually, it's difficult unless [em1]you can't hear it at all[/em1].
Well, you are a [em1]witch[/em1] after all. I thought you would have come up with something before asking me.
Okay then.
One [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))] costs 40 Gold Coins. Is that okay?
There’s something I need in that bag.
Please bring it back to me if you find it.
Give Arden the bag?
I haven't gone out of the village lately...
So, I must’ve lost it here in the village.
Ah, thanks. I can't go without that.
Still, I can finally make [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] again.
Come find me if you get hungry.
I lost an important [em1]bag containing ingredients[/em1].
I think I lost it somewhere [em1]near the water[/em1]. Please try to find it for me.
I remember carrying it back to the village.
My throat gets sore after spewing too much fire.
I asked Rubrum to brew me some tea. Could you do me a favor and get it for me?
Give Arden the tea?
I see. You want to know [em1]how to breathe fire[/em1], is that it?
I wasn’t sure myself, so I thought it through to teach you.
Once you exhale, eject the liquid as well, and flames will come forth.
What's the big deal about breathing out fire?
With that cigar in your mouth, you look like you're puffing flames.
Is that so.
Hm? Do you have something to say?
Actually, it's my first time seeing a dragon in the flesh. You can imagine how intrigued I am.
I suppose there aren't many dragons that mingle with humans.
How do you breathe fire?
Why? You plannin’ on learnin’?
It's my [em1]<wave>lifelong dream</wave>[/em1] to be able to breathe fire!
Pretty simple for a lifelong dream.
I won’t need your soul, but if you do me a [em1]favor[/em1] I’ll teach you.
A favor?
There’s something I asked of from [em1]Rubrum[/em1].
If you asked Rubrum, I'm assuming it's tea?
Yeah, he claimed to have [em1]tea that soothes your throat[/em1].
I can't leave my pot alone.
So why don't you go get it from Rubrum?
Then you'll teach me how to breathe fire?
Sure. But there's no guarantee you'll be able to do it.
I’d sell my [em1]soul[/em1] if I could breathe fire.
I said I would go in the [em1]morning[/em1].
Alright... Grind this well and...
It worked!
It's strange to have such a bad taste when there isn't any smell.
You wouldn't have had to eat it if you didn't go into places that were forbidden.
Don't you know that curiosity and passion for inquiry are required for a witch?
The problem is that you're applying them to things you shouldn't do.
Time to put pepper on it~
They said that the powder glows when it's on a curse but...
Surprisingly, nothing happened.
Still, it's now clear that there is no curse.
Arden seemed to be convinced somehow...
Hmm... Something feels uncomfortable.
Because Arden might not believe it?
Well, rather than that... I wonder what could be the cause of the inability to sleep.
Then, you'd better make some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] before you go.
It would work even if something other than the pepper was cursed.
I should try that for now.
Is it delicious?
Yes. I did a good job of preventing you from putting in a bucket full of pepper.
So what's the meaning of the saying that dragons live multiple lives?
A dragon lives a thousand years. That's like accumulating an enormous amount of memories.
Wow, do you remember all of that?
We can't, because we'd go crazy if we do. So it disappears at some point.
That's why it is said that you live many lives.
Oh oh...
After hearing what you said, I felt that someone might have cursed me in the past that I can't remember now.
Can you recall anything from your previous lives?
I can only recall fragments of it but...
Burning the hair off of a guy who was after my treasure with eternal fire or...
Breaking the waist of a drunken man causing trouble at the restaurant and throwing him out or...
Flying around with a guy picking a fight tied to my foot for three days.
I guess you do deserve some curses.
It was self-defense.
Anyway, a few things came to my mind, but I still don't know the exact cause.
Did you happen to have some kind of incident with another witch?
You said you hated witches.
That might be the case.
Something feels uncomfortable about witches.
Hmm... Could it be a curse that is triggered when certain conditions are met...?
Can I ask you a few things?
Reason for running a restaurant
About your past
Reason for staying in Wisteria
I don't know. I've just always been doing it, since the moment I remember.
Since when?
Well... Even before Enite was born?
I protected some treasure just like other dragons.
Treasure!
I want to say that I will give you one if you take care of the curse, but I don't know where it is now.
At that time, all kinds of people came to visit. Maybe there were witches too.
What are you curious about?
Because of passion for Wisteria flowers.
Your passion for Wisteria flowers?
No, I don’t know whose passion it was.
You don't know whose passion it was, yet you remember the passion?
Wisteria flowers have strong vitality. Thus the passion.
I wonder who it was...
So much for my questions.
I really can't remember a thing.
Speaking of which...
Hmm... Then should we start by recovering your memories?
Why are you helping me this much?
Because I'm a witch
Because my fighting spirit calls for it
Because I feel sorry for you
A witch is always ready to help people, starting from those around her.
This is my creed.
Since I've already done so much, I want to keep going until I see some result.
I'd also have to get rid of your prejudice against witches.
It's sad to be cursed by someone you can't even recall.
I guess that's why you've become so withdrawn?
I was harsh earlier. I apologize.
Humph. The water's already been spilled.
But, I'll forgive you since I'm curious about your past.
Alright, next would be...
Let's stop for today. My head hurts from thinking about all of this.
He kicked me out!
At least he only kicked you out after filling up your stomach.
I'm already in it, so I'll make sure that I find out the secret!
Do you consider what you can't remember a secret?
Everything that hasn't been revealed is a secret!
Alright. Let's gather more clues first.
Give Arden the Curse Lifting Candy?
Candy?
Can you find out what the curse is and lift it?
I think that will take some time and I'm a little busy right now.
Is that so? Alright then.
Where did you get the pepper?
I bought it from a green-haired lady who often comes to the village.
Aurea?
Exactly. I smelled a strange curse from her last time.
I'm guessing she touched something strange somewhere.
I'll try to find out.
I've been unable to sleep, and I think it's because of this new pepper.
The color is reddish and it has a subtle, sweet taste.
I've always slept well when my night light is with me.
It must be some kind of curse.
Yes, it’s [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1].
I asked you to remove the pepper's curse.
I checked with Aurea and also tried using [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1], but there was no curse in the pepper.
They say the reason for such color and taste of pepper is because it’s red pepper.
I think there may be a curse somewhere else. But even if not, it's a delicious candy.
That's why I brought it.
Heh...
This is only a temporary fix. It won't solve the problem completely.
Anyway, witches get drunk on their feelings and butt in with this and that saying it’s a good deed...
They are rarely truly of help. They just want to feel good.
Arden, isn't the reason you aren't able to sleep because you keep saying mean things?
I worked hard in my own way because I wanted to help you.
Does it make you happy to talk like that?
Maybe it's not because of the night light or the pepper, but because you yourself are cursed?
That might be so.
If you know me better, you may be able to tell whether I'm cursed.
Do you know the meaning of the saying that dragons live multiple lives?
Oh, you cruel belly clock.
Would you like a bowl of beef stew before you leave?
I’ll also tell you what that means.
Alright. But it's by no means because I'm hungry.
But because I'm so broad-minded that I'd like to hear you out.
Said the belly clock.
<shake>*stomach growling*</shake>
I should go fetch the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Arden, are you sleeping well?
Huh? What is that?
The smell... Is it pepper?
Why are you giving me pepper all of a sudden?
Don't you find it strange?
Uh... It's just pepper.
Wrong. If you look closely, you can see that it's mixed with strange colored particles.
Now that you say it, it does look a little dark red in color...
I keep having dreams that I don’t even remember.
I even sleep with a night light by my side but it’s useless.
The only new thing in the restaurant is this pepper, and it has a strange color and a subtle, sweet taste.
I'm sure this pepper is cursed.
A curse on pepper...?
There is nothing strange about it, since there's even a curse that keeps you praising nature.
If you're a witch, you'd also be familiar with curses.
I don't care.
You've never seen something similar?
'Tis a [em1]key[/em1].
Older dragons are quite keen on those.
We have a natural preference for precious metals and stones, but some also like to collect those.
They aren't valuable in and of themselves, and there usually exist [em1]corresponding devices[/em1].
Seems that there was a fellow into this stuff.
Do you have any clues?
Well, let's see. Those fellows usually prefer [em1]large trees[/em1] or [em1]old caves[/em1]. It would do you well to search there.
I should go fetch the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PrayerStone_Name"))][/em1].
Lisa? Who's that?
She's the witch who used to live in the Witch's House. Don't you know?
Oh, so her name was Lisa? I didn't know that.
You really don't care about anyone else, do you?
I'm not that close with witches.
Arden, you've lived in this village the longest. How was Lisa as a witch?
Just like any other witch.
You know, pretty much your standard witch.
The kind you never know what she's up to all day, but ends up making a huge mess for everyone.
Not every witch is like that!
Maybe, you do seem different.
Do you know any places Lisa frequented or what she did a lot?
I don't venture outside the restaurant much, so I'm not sure.
But I used to know a witch like that.
She sacrificed the whole village so she could live a long life.
Sacrificed... the whole village?
The whole village was reduced to a ruin and the witch who lived there became immortal and ageless.
Isn't that something a witch can do?
If you try anything like that these days, you're going to be dragged away in chains!
Yes, I suppose that's changed these days.
Arden, do you really think Lisa was behind the prickly vines in the village?
I don't know. I know nothing about Lisa.
I only know that there was a witch who sacrificed her entire village.
Do you think I'd look at the flowers while walking around?
You've lived here a long time after all, Arden.
I don't know. I just go where I'm supposed to. Why would I bother about these things?
Anyway, I [em1]haven't seen[/em1] it [em1]by the water[/em1].
What to discuss with Arden?
Restaurant
Business is always slow at the restaurant.
It's always just the usual crowd after all.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Arden"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Isn't this place really boring for young people?
I've been living here without dwelling on it much myself.
Pepper
You can never put in too much pepper.
So, it's the right amount no matter how much you put in.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))]
I've always put the same ingredients into my stew.
After all, it's nice to stick with familiar flavors.
Hometown
I don't remember my hometown.
Actually, I don't even remember the mountain I used to live on before coming to the village.
Cooking
I've never studied any recipe.
When I cook, I just follow my intuition.
Hobbies
Humph, everything interests you.
I guess smoking can count as my hobby.
Night light
Despite the name, it's too dim to illuminate anything.
Maybe it has been worn out by time.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RoughStone_Lamp_Name"))][/em1] will make a better night light. It's reliable and enduring.
Sleeping
I've been a light sleeper.
Back in my days in the cave, I often had sudden wake-ups.
The treasure hunters were usually so loud that I couldn't get any proper sleep.
Treasure
One should not be obsessed with treasure.
At the end of the day, it will become useless. Better consider it useless from the beginning.
Fire-breathing
Not all dragons breathe fire.
Some breathe poison.
That's a pointless skill, but some are actually proud of it.
Well, time doesn't have much impact on dragons.
If I have to mention any, my teeth gaps are widening. It's a headache.
Because of that, I have to brush my teeth with stuff such as [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowBranch_Name"))][/em1] every day, which is troublesome.
Warrior
I once loved a person deeply.
After she passed away, I never had that feeling again.
Other dragons
I've probably met some,
but as you'd expect, such meetings don't stay in a dragon's memories.
Age
How old am I?
I don't know, and no one keeps count for me.
Why would I do that?
If I catch something ugly, such as [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_YoungCat_Name"))][/em1], it will only ruin my mood.
Flower shop
You didn’t actually think I would go buy flowers, did you?
Of course, Roy shares good insights about plants. I learned how to use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PlopRadish_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
Coating meat lightly with [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PlopRadish_Water_Name"))][/em1] reduces the fishy smell significantly. That’s why I use it often.
The things Kyla makes are certainly sturdy.
Except for toothbrushes. I've never used one of his toothbrushes for more than a month.
So it's just easier to use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1].
You also think Alvin is an inscrutable person, don't you?
Even when Kyla persistently asks, he never properly shares his story.
Come to think of it, he resembles [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_OldCat_Name"))][/em1].
He has great skills, but he hides them.
If you've got time, you should visit someone else.
The soup is good today.
Nothing of that sort.
Come on, think about it, please.
I haven't received anything of that sort.
Are you sure you haven't forgotten?
Maybe I have.
I say, try thinking about it again, Arden.
Oh, how about this?
Is this a scarf?
Yes. Enite gave it to me a few days before you appeared in the village.
And she told me to remember the village even if I left.
But here I am, so this scarf's no longer needed.
Hmm, I guess so.
No matter what happened, I never thought of leaving this place, though.
Though you usually act like you don't care, you love this village, don't you?
Are you going to use my entire home here for bricks then?
Though that would be really fun, all I need is your scarf to make good bricks.
That’s a relief.
I don't have anything else.
Fade out and summon Arden who fades in
Lines for when character forgets after taking it
I think this is it, but I'd better ask Arden.
Content: I'll go see the bridge once it is repaired
Villager model fades out and disappears, villager fades back in normally
Then go ask the adults who can imbibe.
I'm not selling.
But I haven't said a single word.
Aren't you here to get me to sell [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))]?
Don't be like that, why have you stopped selling it? Did you lose the recipe?
There was never a recipe to begin with.
Wait, no, I think there was, but now it's gone.
I've never said I wouldn't sell liquor anymore.
Since the prickly vines sprouted, the water's changed and no matter what I do, the flavor's just not right.
Kyla's just being unreasonable.
Then why not try making new kinds of liquor?
That's too much of a bother.
Do you know anything about liquor?
I'm an expert when it comes to Twinkle-Twinkle Juice... Uh, I've helped to brew moonshine before.
You're no help at all.
I haven't reached the drinking age, okay?
Which is to say, Kyla won't like the new taste of the wine?
Maybe?
How about this, I'll go find some wines Kyla might like.
And you make it, Arden.
So the adult you were looking high and low for is me?
After all, you're an adult, Arden.
I suppose if we're talking body size.
So Arden, what's a good wine to you?
Hm... A [em1]sweet wine[/em1] seems good.
Hm... Really?
There's a saying that the harder a person's life, the sweeter the wine...
I thought you wouldn't like sweet wines.
I don't know where you got that from.
I just have this feeling that there used to be someone very fond of sweet wines.
Hm, sounds like a good chance to make some fruit wine.
There's plenty of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1] growing around the village, which would be a good ingredient.
I'll go look for the ingredients, go ask around about their compatibility or whatever.
Arden, I've brought you the ingredients for winemaking.
Is there enough? I can get more if needed.
Oh, you've even brought the ingredients.
I'm certain your restaurant does not stock these.
That's right, it doesn't.
I knew it, you're always selling the same things.
It's fine as long as it tastes good.
Will you be able to make new wines using these?
Yes. Hopefully everything goes well and no one comes pestering me again.
How about preparing some drinking snacks to go with the wine?
It's said that the flavors of the wines will change with the food they're paired with.
Hm... What else is there to do? Let's go take a look.
You don't even drink, how would you know all that?
Dad and Mom often snuck me a few bites of the drinking snacks they paired with their wine.
Stringy fries with cheese pulling long when being picked,
roast sweet potato that melted in the mouth with an explosion of butter... *drool*
Yes. We should be good with [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))].
You've been offering that all along!
Don't familiar things taste the best?
It'd be a waste of all those wines if you paired them with those foods!
Then what would be a good pairing?
Hmmm, certain pairings tend to be more compatible.
Don't you need someone who cares about those things?
Don't bother telling me about that.
Tell [em1]Kyla[/em1] to come with you the next time.
And since you're going, bring them [em1]when Kyla is working[/em1].
Always going on about how wine after a day of hard work tastes the best.
It's [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))].
Surely you know how to make other dishes than [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))], Arden?
These are my specialties.
I don't make that.
Even if you don't, you may have a recipe for it.
Do I look like I do?
No, you don't...
Then why did you ask?
Just in case you turned out to be the answer to my problem.
I'm a dragon, not an answer.
Was that a joke?
Not at all.
Ugh... I'll be going then.
If you want something sweet, go look for someone else, not me.
I'm not the only one who cooks [em1]food[/em1] in the village.
On the surface, he seems to be a clean-cut old man.
But I can feel a sense of bitterness in him.
I don't think he had a peaceful life.
That old man might be annoying, but his translation skills are really impressive.
I gave him the strange book rolling in a corner of my house, and he translated it after just one read-through.
Thanks to him, I got some great recipes.
Oh, by the way, just now [em1]Roy[/em1] came to buy [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))], and was looking for you.
He said he wanted to talk to you about the [em1]librarian[/em1]. You should go meet him.
I haven't talked to him much and don't know much about him.
How would I know any story of Wisteria?
But, Arden, haven't you been living here for long?
I have.
You've never heard about any myth or folktale?
I certainly have, but I can't recall.
I'm not the only one who [em1]has lived in the village for long[/em1].
What are you dilly-dallying for?
It's okay. I don't need your help.
Arden! They say you're struggling with the party menu?
Who are "they"?
Somebody!
I am struggling... but you don't look like you understand.
Of course I won't understand if you don't tell me!
I'm wondering how much pepper I should put on the [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))].
See? Isn't that difficult?
<shake>I should have known it.</shake> You make nothing but these two dishes.
What do you have to complain about? Aren't they good? Maybe you need more pepper?
Usually, people would expect something different for a party menu, you know...
So much trouble. If so, just ask them to bring their own ingredients and toss them into the pot.
What kind of dish is that... <shake>Oh, right!</shake>
<wave>[em1]Random ingredient stew party![/em1]</wave>
What an irresponsible name.
What do you mean irresponsible? I used to cook such a stew with my friends back at the School for Witches!
You are actually going to cook that horrible dish?
It's the best for a large party.
Arden, you always cook the same stew, don't you? Just cook that for the party.
And let the villagers each bring their own preferred ingredient.
That's nothing new. It's just a potluck.
No, no, they are different. My stew requires everyone to toss their ingredient into the same pot.
Are you so eager to remind everyone that you are a witch with all your grotesque ideas?
You are only proposing such plans because you believe every mess can be handled with [em1]potions[/em1], huh?
Usually, only in your dreams can you make a tasty dish by mixing random ingredients together.
But I'll agree as long as you stop complaining about my [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))].
Sure, I will never say another word against them.
Hehe, it amuses me just thinking about it. I haven't cooked this dish since my apprenticeship began.
I've sworn to never eat that dish again, though.
Have you forgotten already? It tasted like boots soaked in mud.
This is this and that's that.
Let's see... I've checked on everyone except those that're going to play musical instruments.
Then, I should talk to [em1]Alvin[/em1].
We'd better go to Alvin [em1]in the morning, when he's resting[/em1].
The parade thing doesn't interest me.
But you've closed your restaurant tonight to come here!
That doesn't mean I have to join the parade.
C'mon, just join us. It's a party for everyone to have fun.
Arden, you're not coming?
It's the only occasion for us to spend time together.
Join us pleeease.
Give me a break. You guys are such an annoying and talkative crowd.
I will only be walking behind you. That's all.
He's not like ordinary people.
He exudes the aura of [em1]those people[/em1].
What kind of people?
Those who can completely change others' lives.
... What do you mean?
Literally what I said.
On the bright side, they can love and care for others, heal wounds, or impart incredible knowledge.
And on the dark side?
They can harm others. Physically or mentally.
It's that kind of aura.
But I might not be entirely accurate.
Enite said that she lent you the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SewingBox_Name"))].
Yep. I wanted to patch up my ripped apron.
You want to mend a doll?
Yes, it's a stuffed doll. About this size.
Arden, do you know how to mend dolls?
Tsk. Give me a break.
Wait here. I think I have a doll in my restaurant. I'll go get it.
Watch closely. I'll only show it once.
Wow... Your stitching is so neat.
So, did you get it?
Where did you learn those skills? From Enite?
I asked if you get it or not. Don't change the subject.
I didn't learn this from Enite.
Then who? You seem quite familiar with sewing.
Don't know. Having to deal with all kinds of stuff when running a restaurant, you just pick up skills over time.
Hmph... There's no harm telling me about it.
Here's the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SewingBox_Name"))]. Go, don't bother me again.
There's not much thread left, and the needle is worn out. It can only be used once.
Thank you, Arden!
Doll mending? Why are you bothering me with this?
Does this place look like a doll shop to you?
Library? Wing? Are they a thing? I don't know.
Haven't you been living in the village for a long time? You never heard about it?
I never heard that the library had a wing.
But Enite knows it.
Okay, then it's probably a thing.
Come on...
Then, do you know anything notable about the library other than the wing?
The old man at the library used to come to my place a lot.
Oh, really? Did you chat with him?
I don't remember. They were just small talks, I suppose.
Anything not a "small talk"?
Pfft, he once mentioned storing books.
Storing books?
That he used to store books in a place with good [em1]ventilation[/em1], but ventilation at the library was poor, or something.
That previous place... can it be the wing?
Good ventilation... meaning that the old storage place had a [em1]vent[/em1]?
If so, maybe I can locate the true wing by listening to the [em1]wind[/em1] going through it.
Thank you, Arden. You're a great help.
Do I look like I've got pen pals?
Why, maybe, you'd never know. Just have a look, please!
Tsk, so much trouble. Hand it over.
I'm not that old. I don't need a cane.
For a person to want a portrait... they should have [em1]a long past[/em1], or have [em1]lost someone[/em1].
Arden, you've also lived in the village for a long time. Don't you have such experiences?
Can't think of any, and why would I tell anyone about it?
I run a restaurant. What does packaging have to do with me?
That's right. It's a [em1]curse[/em1].
What? Why all of a sudden?
I've been [em1]dreaming[/em1].
But haven't we talked about it?!
Arden, the cause of your sleep disorder isn't any curse, but your [em1]forgotten memories[/em1].
That's what I call a curse.
I went to the green-haired merchant for the pepper I ordered.
She asked me to wait for a moment because she was sorting a newly arrived shipment.
So I stood on the side watching the goods as I zoned out.
Then I noticed the [em1]hair ties[/em1].
There was a package full of colorful hair ties.
They were of all colors and designs... but strangely enough, I was strongly attracted to a green piece made of silk.
[em1]Green[/em1]... Exactly, a piece of green hair tie, just like what the Warrior in my dream gives me.
Whenever I fall asleep, she appears in my dream and hands me the hair tie.
"[em1]At least remember this one thing[/em1]."
She always says so.
That's when I will wake up, but I have no idea what she means by [em1]"this one thing"[/em1].
I have that dream more and more often these days, and I can hardly get any proper sleep.
What can it be if not a curse.
Well... But weren't you sleeping fine before you lost the night light?
Some curses only trigger when [em1]conditions are met[/em1].
I suppose losing my old night light is also one of the conditions.
That explains why the curse isn't lifted even though you've retrieved the light for me.
And...
What? Why are you staring at me? Are you suspecting me again, just because I'm a witch?
I've been helping you since the very beginning! Why should I curse you now!
It may not be your fault.
But witches are inherently ominous existences.
I'm not blaming you.
That's called blaming me!
I'm aware of your recent hard work.
I just want you to know that my prolonged sleep disorder is caused by a curse.
So, you think the [em1]Warrior has cursed you[/em1]?
If not, I can't see why she keeps visiting my dreams and repeating [em1]the same words[/em1].
Forget about it. I'll try to fix it myself.
Hmm... I'm not quite convinced.
And I somehow feel wronged...
Also, I wonder if Arden is really cursed by the Warrior — someone he once loved.
Shall I reinvestigate Arden's curse?
By the way, what on earth have you forgotten to deserve a curse?
Do I look like I have the answer?
Well... no.
But... even if it [em1]really is a curse[/em1], can I lift it?
Not even [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))] works on it.
Are you throwing the towel already? Didn't you feel wronged and unconvinced?
I am not! I mean, if [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))] doesn't work, it can't be an [em1]ordinary curse[/em1].
If candies prove ineffective, we must follow the standard procedure.
Try to reveal the curse's true nature.
Well... To decipher a curse, I should first know the [em1]person who placed it[/em1] and [em1]its medium[/em1].
Arden was in love with the Warrior... which means the Warrior could have loved him back?
After all, they used to run a restaurant together, and Arden made a sculpture for her...
What curse would one put on their loved one?
Wait, why would someone curse their loved one in the first place?
There are more reasons than you'd expect.
Love isn't always wonderful.
Love, hmm... That's complicated...
Done chatting with your hat?
We weren't chatting! We were discussing how to identify the curse.
There must be something important among [em1]things Arden has forgotten[/em1].
According to the procedure... I should learn more about the [em1]Warrior[/em1],
and look for [em1]the medium of the curse[/em1] at the same time.
Let's start from the basic information... Arden, what was the Warrior's name?
I can't remember. I only know that she was a warrior.
Trouble already.
<shake>A-another question then!</shake> How exactly does the hair tie in your dream look?
I'm not sure. Just that it's green and silver.
Do you still have it?
I don't wear hair ties, so I've probably thrown it away.
Then... Arden... How long has it been since the Warrior passed away?
Let's see. That was long before Enite was born... Probably more than 150 years ago.
<shake>Ughahhh!</shake> Nobody of her time could still be around then!
Try to summon Enite's great great great grandmother.
Where from!
To find clues about the curse, I need Arden's memories...
No, the curse was triggered exactly because Arden had no memories.
What can I investigate then? Do I really have to summon Enite's grandmother...
Come over.
Show Arden the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "AccessoryOfBrave_Name"))][/em1]?
Arden! I've found something that may be the medium.
Have you? Test it then.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DiaryOfBrave_Name"))][/em1], [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "AccessoryOfBrave_Name"))][/em1], [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
What with this place?
See what's underneath.
Gosh, so much dust, <shake>cough! cough!</shake>
It's... a chipped bowl, a tea cup, and withered flowers...
What are these?
I don't know. They were always at the restaurant.
I was going to throw them away,
but Kyla said that they could brighten up the gloomy restaurant, so I kept them.
Kyla is such a lifesaver...
Alright, let's check for clues. This bag... is full of stones.
Not this one... Hmm, a [em1]leather journal[/em1]...?
May I read it?
That's what I've brought you here for.
Okay, let me see... There should be some clues written in it.
No... no way!
What's it? Some secrets concerning Arden's background?
<shake>It's written in an unknown language!</shake>
Arden, can you read this?
Well... I...
I can't.
<shake>NOOO</shake>! It may be the only clue we have. We can't give up!
Oh right! Shall we ask Kent for the translation service of the Society of Witches?
Unfortunately, they only translate the ancient witch language.
<shake>Oh, shoot!!</shake> Why are there so many languages!!
Calm down. Someone in the neighborhood may know it.
It's neither a dragon language nor a witch language. For human languages, you should ask a human for help.
Languages... Do I know a language expert?
I do go to Enite for all kinds of matters concerning the village... but I've never heard that she's a language expert.
Alvin is knowledgeable, but he doesn't seem to be interested in languages.
Arin once said that she was studying languages!
Arden, can I borrow this?
Suit yourself.
It's worth trying! Let's go find Arin!
Which page shall we read?
10-Mar
The restaurant has been in business for three months. I thought we would close in no time, but we've gradually gotten on track.
Despite all his complaints at first, Arden has become a fixed component of the kitchen.
He didn't put enough pepper in today's stew. I told him to add more.
Stews only taste great when they have much pepper! Oops... The thought alone has made me hungry again.
Oh and, there's a place we usually go after a day's business.
There's a [em1]cascade[/em1] a short walk beyond the [em1]cliff[/em1] deep in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))].
It's normally hard to reach, but Arden can carry me on his back, haha!
The serene and vast [em1]lake beneath the cascade[/em1] is great for relaxing.
I taught Arden how to [em1]skip stones[/em1], but he's hardly as good as I am yet.
I've promised to grant Arden a wish when he beats me in stone skipping, but he still has a long way to go.
This entry is about Arden and the Warrior taking a break at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] [em1]lake beneath the cascade[/em1] after a day's work at the restaurant.
24-Apr
On our days off, me and Arden take walks in the forest surrounding the village.
Usually, it's me pulling Arden around by force, but despite all his complaints, he comes along anyway.
When we [em1]go deep into[/em1] the forest, we'll reach a dark area.
Most of it is dim, but if we look carefully, we'll find a patch of sunlight leaking through the leaves. This scenic location is our secret base.
There's a huge rock among the bushes. I've [em1]flattened its top[/em1] to use it as a chair.
Although Arden complains about the long trip, he seems to like the spot.
I've been carving a sculpture of Arden. I usually become so lost in my work that I forget he's beside me.
Arden will then start to gather fruit from nearby trees.
Today, I brought painting tools so that we could paint together.
Hahaha! Arden sucks at painting. I fell to the ground laughing the moment I saw his painting of me.
Arden immediately started fuming. He tried to snatch the painting back and burn it, but I didn't let him.
It's my treasure. I finished the Arden sculpture today, and I'll put the painting in it for safekeep.
This entry is about Arden and the Warrior hanging out [em1]in the depth of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))][/em1].
03-May
Me and Arden revisited the place in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))][/em1] where we planted the Flower of Love. Arden called the name childish,
and clucked his tongue when he saw me digging the ground with my sword, but he walked over to help me anyway.
They say that the more sincere you are, the [em1]bigger your Flower of Love[/em1] will be. I can't wait to see my flower bloom.
Bigger flowers take longer to bloom, but once they do, they don't easily wither.
Arden dismissed the saying as "nonsense that only children would believe." He knows nothing about being romantic.
That's how he is. Once I asked him to consider me a gemstone and say something sweet,
and this wooden-headed dragon said, "A gemstone is just a precious ore. What sweet things can be said about it?"
To keep the Flower of Love companied, I've [em1]surrounded it with other flowers[/em1]. Even if they wither, their seeds will sprout into new flowers.
A day may come when we can't come here together anymore, but I hope this flower will always be here as a mark.
A mark that me and Arden were once here together.
I don't think this [em1]cliff[/em1] gets a lot of visitors, so the flowers probably won't be stepped on.
I don't feel lonely now, because I've got Arden. I hope the Flower of Love feels the same.
I can't wait to see the flower bloom.
The Warrior received the [em1]hair tie[/em1] at the place she [em1]planted flowers[/em1] with Arden.
We'd better check out this place.
This entry is about Arden and the Warrior planting a Flower of Love on the [em1]cliff of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))][/em1].
04-May
We went to see the [em1]Flower of Love[/em1] again. Arden didn't think the flower would bloom so quickly, but he wanted to see it anyway, so we went together.
Just when we were heading back, he pulled out something and handed it to me. It was a [em1]hair tie[/em1].
"Didn't you want to celebrate your birthday? Here's your birthday present," he said.
My birthday isn't just any random day! Still, I'm quite happy.
I've been so busy with the restaurant that I haven't got a chance to trim my hair. It sometimes gets in my way.
This hair tie features a green ribbon, probably because I, thinking of Arden's appearance, said I liked green.
It also has a silver gemstone that Arden likes. It's so cute of him to pick this color.
Arden is very shy, but after I repeatedly begged him,
he finally tied my hair for me under the [em1]old tree that overlooked the Flower of Love[/em1].
I hope he could do it every day. I want to show off to the customers.
The hair tie described here resembles the one in Arden's dreams.
Arden always leaves things in random places. The hair tie must be lying somewhere.
This entry is about Arden giving the [em1]hair tie[/em1] to the Warrior.
29-Nov
Today was supposed to be the greatest day of days.
I finally succeeded in making a packed lunch, and even added the trendy [em1]mushroom[/em1] as a surprise!
Such [em1]giant[/em1] Earthgem Shrooms, cultivated with witch technologies, are said to be very delicious.
I bought a [em1]purple mushroom[/em1] collected from the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1]. It's only as tall as my calf now, but they say it will grow.
I planned to show Arden the mushroom and the packed lunch I made, but my plan was totally ruined.
Before I set out for the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1], I heard something from a customer that I wish I never found out.
Even worse, I heard it from someone else instead of from Arden.
I thought Arden was known as a "thousand-year dragon" just because he had a long lifespan.
But by saying he had lived several lives, he actually meant that he had been [em1]losing his memories[/em1]...
I questioned Arden why he didn't tell me earlier about such an important fact.
He said he didn't find it important, which made me madder.
I can't help but think, Arden will naturally forget me when I die.
Forget... me.
This entry is about a [em1]purple mushroom from the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1], and how the Warrior heard about the meaning of "thousand-year dragon" from a customer.
The last page
My health is deteriorating.
I didn't expect it to happen so fast... Fear is consuming me.
I thought it was a minor ailment, but it turned out to be incurable.
Arden will probably still be alive long after I'm gone...
And since he is a thousand-year dragon, Arden will forget me.
The time we spent together feels short even for me. Maybe it's just the blink of an eye for Arden?
Whenever I think about it, my chest feels tight.
What words should I leave for him to remember me?
I hope Arden can remember every detail about me, no matter how trivial and insignificant.
If only the Black Cat God could pity me and give me more time...
In this entry... the Warrior found out about her illness. No other location is mentioned.
I can't understand a word. I'll have [em1]Arin[/em1] translate it.
This seems to be a location mentioned in the journal.
It's where the Warrior and Arden used to rest after a day's work at the restaurant.
Arden actually skipped stones here? I can't picture that.
I feel like we were here before.
Of course we were. It's the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))].
Well... but now you mention it, this seems to be where Arden lost the night light.
By the way, he likes waterbodies, doesn't he? He always goes to waterside for breaks.
I can't find any lead here. Let's check somewhere else.
It's Arden and the Warrior's secret base.
They... painted portrays and made sculptures for each other here.
This place is so remote. Not even I have considered exploring it or doing anything here.
Sometimes, "with whom" matters more than "where."
Oh, that is the rock. I thought it was flat naturally... The Warrior surely had much strength.
Cutting off the top of a rock with a swish! That sounds so fun.
Don't try it, or you will break your arm.
Tsk, shut up.
On the cliff... According to the journal, it should be a field of flowers surrounding one large flower.
The more sincere you are, the bigger your flower... Flower of Love.
Hey, over there!
There's something by that large tree.
Doesn't it look like a [em1]green ribbon[/em1]?
But how can I get up there?
If you go straightly up, you may see the Warrior.
That'd be awful...
There's [em1]some ladder kind of thing[/em1]...
That's not a ladder, but a stick.
And it's broken from the middle.
Hmm... Can it be repaired?
I need to find a way.
This is where the Warrior learned about thousand-year dragon's meaning...
She thought Arden was just forgetful... but he actually had to forget.
I want to remember all the happy stuff no matter how long I live.
But you can't choose what to remember.
Everyone has their share of suffering.
For me, it's not being able to choose a better head to sit on.
You don't have to say the last sentence...
Is this the mushroom the Warrior bought?
So, it used to be calf-high? But see how large it's become. This is amazing.
That said, the mushroom seems to be the only thing notable here. Let's check somewhere else.
Just fly over.
I'm not a dragon.
Find something in place of wings then.
There are plenty of [em1]vines[/em1] and [em1]trees[/em1] there. Just use those.
That thing seems to have been ripped off and reattached.
Just get [em1]plants[/em1] and figure out [em1]how to use[/em1] them.
Well, I guess I can plant it beneath the ladder?
And wait for a moment...
There you go!
Whoa, it grows so f-
and [em1]withered[/em1] before I could finish.
I can probably revive it with some [em1]fertilizer sort of thing[/em1].
Let's try to breathe life into it.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Roy'sFastGrowSeed_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Whoa! It worked! It's back to life!
But it will soon wither again. I must hurry up.
Let me climb up the vine and see what the [em1]thing dropped there[/em1] is.
A green ribbon with a silver gemstone... It matches the hair tie described in the journal.
But... doesn't it feel a bit weird?
It does surprise me that Arden picked such a plain item.
That's not the point. I mean, why is it at the [em1]location mentioned in the journal[/em1]...?
As if someone has left it here on purpose...
But hasn't Arden thrown it away? And he can't read the journal.
The other locations mentioned in the journal... are also places Arden [em1]discarded things[/em1].
Or was he really "discarding" them...?
Take it to him and you'll find out.
Alright. And I'll check if the hair tie is really the medium.
And take a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Hmm... I feel like I've missed something.
Arden, did you gift this hair tie to the Warrior?
I suppose I did.
W-what's going on! Why are you crying?
What are you talking about? I'm not.
Arden is crying!
Don't be ridiculous... Tsk.
"I don't want to die. I want to live longer."
That's what she said... in her final moment.
This reminds me of her. She held on to it until the end.
She must hurt, a lot. She was always... bustling around, and wouldn't stay still for a second, but she spent her last days in bed.
Her hair had grown so long. She was supposed to tie it up, but she couldn't, because she was lying all the time.
But I... I'm just a dragon who's lived a long life alone. I couldn't do anything for her.
She must be complaining... about my uselessness.
I didn't realize why she kept appearing in my dream to give me this.
But it must have been [em1]a sign of complaint[/em1]. She wants me to remember her.
Arden...
Aren't you going to verify my guess? You've brought an item that can identify curses, right?
Oh right, I've brought a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))]. If I crush this...
Don't tell me you're going to grind and spread it. You'll dirty the floor.
Hm? I'll clean it afterwards. You know how awful this candy tastes?
It's a restaurant I'm running.
Come on... This is no time for cleanness. You're being unreasonable.
Arden is a geezer.
I hear you.
Fine, I'll have to swallow it while holding my nose... <shake>Gulp!</shake>
Ugh, it really tastes like mucus from when you catch a cold... <shake>Yuck!</shake>
Now, the hair tie...
Huh? The hair tie doesn't carry any curse. If it were the medium, there would be a strong sign...
What's been cursing Arden then... Hm?
Why does that [em1]pot[/em1] show a [em1]sign of curse[/em1]?
I'm not seeing things, am I?
Go and have a closer look.
Yeah, I can see it clearly. It's a [em1]sign of curse[/em1].
On the closest of all things.
Arden! Where did you get this pot?
Come on, Arden, you must know something!
I need to inspect the pot. It may have the maker's signature or a mark of the curse on it.
Arden, put out the fire please!
Ouch, it's still quite hot.
Maybe there's something at the bottom.
"A.A"... "The restaurant is finally open!"
Huh? This is more like a doodle than a mark.
There was a similar mark on a [em1]wineglass Arden threw away[/em1].
There are more words. "We've got our 100th customer, awesome"... "May stews earn us a fortune."
These are curses...?
Arden, look at this!
Now I remember it.
[em1]I've put the curse on myself[/em1].
What? What do you mean?
Arden? Don't just fall silent again. Explain it.
And what's this crystalline substance on the ground?
It's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1].
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s crystalize as time goes by.
As for the curse... As I said, I placed it on myself right at this restaurant.
I actually forgot this as well.
Why...?
The hair tie... She held on to it until her last breath.
She was hurting, and afraid. Rather than death itself... she might have been more scared of me forgetting her.
So I promised her that I would keep everything in mind.
However, I wasn't sure about it. We dragons live a thousand years, so we have to [em1]forget periodically[/em1].
Otherwise, we could go insane due to our brains being overloaded...
I sat on the bed she used to lie on and cried forever, feeling helpless.
I needed a means, be it a curse or anything, to [em1]keep my memories[/em1].
So, for one thousand nights in a row, I cursed myself at the restaurant.
If I ever forgot, I would [em1]have the same dream[/em1] repeatedly.
Which means, your sleep disorder is...
Caused by myself.
It's a method taught to me by that witch, so I never expected it to be sensible.
But I almost forgot the curse as well, if not reminded by the witch in front of me...
A curse I put on myself.
Who's "that witch"?
So much for the investigation.
There's no need to investigate the curse further.
Why? We've come this far, and it's possible to remove curses placed by oneself.
It's okay.
Arden! Do you know how much work I've put into this?
You can't simply dismiss me like that. You must at least tell me your reason, don't you agree?
I even resorted to a curse, but I still forgot.
All I hoped was to [em1]remember this one thing[/em1], but not even such a humble wish was granted. I haven't recalled it so far.
Still, if I keep dreaming, I may remember it one day.
The curse... is all that I have now.
My previous affection and sadness have faded...
But I want to grant her last wish.
I know you've done a lot for me. You need to do no more.
It's kind of weird...
We've proved the existence of a curse, but it's placed by yourself.
If so, what about [em1]the Warrior's feelings[/em1]?
On the last page of the journal, she found out about her illness. She wrote no more after that.
Arden, did the Warrior really hold a grudge against you?
I really like Wisteria, and my parents' house.
I don't like studying... but I like the school me and my friends used to study at.
Therefore, even if things go wrong for me...
I will hope that people I like can keep creating happy memories in those places.
At least... I won't want them to live on with a curse.
Arden, do lift the curse.
And find another way to retrieve your memories.
Such as what the Warrior meant by "[em1]At least remember this one thing[/em1]."
Hi.
I've been thinking about what you said.
I've got a favor to ask. Could you help?
What is it, Arden?
I've been dreaming.
It's still that same dream. She gives me a hair tie, and says "[em1]At least remember this one thing[/em1]."
I want to find out what "this one thing" is, and I've tried various methods to no avail.
I've read the journal you helped translate, and visited the places... but it didn't help.
I want to recall [em1]"this one thing"[/em1] she didn't want me to forget.
And I've realized that... dreams from the curse alone won't be enough.
See? I told you that the curse wasn't the solution.
Let's get started at once and find [em1]a way to retrieve memories[/em1].
Hmm... Where shall we begin? A strong impact, such as falling from heights...
Are you planning to kill Arden?
Arden is a dragon. He can certainly withstand this with ease, right?
Well, well.
That's not the favor I want to ask of you.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]? What do you want that for?
As I said before, [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s crystalize as time goes by.
And they are a precious ingredient coveted by witches. if I'm not mistaken.
I stared at the tear every day, until an idea struck me.
When she fell ill... I tried every means to cure her,
but she only went worse.
I consulted every person I could, until a witch came to me.
She said that she needed [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s to develop a cure.
Therefore, I cried every day
and my eyes became swollen and red.
Now that I think about it... my look would only worry the sick more.
Later, I found out that the witch only wanted [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s to test her own potion.
And of course, I didn't receive any cure.
Oh no, my goodness, I would never do such a thing.
I didn't even know that [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s crystalize.
I know. I'm not suspecting you. There's no need to prove yourself.
You and that witch are different individuals, Ellie.
The point of my nonsense lies somewhere else.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s, which that witch craved, contain a power known to few.
The witch came to me because she knew it.
What kind of power is that?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s contain the [em1]power to reflect memories[/em1]. [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s from the same dragon [em1]resonate[/em1] with each other.
Every night, I turn on the night light to read her journal.
One day, I remembered that I wasn't trying to discard those items.
Well, I did throw some away due to not remembering them... but some were placed on purpose at locations with [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s[/em1].
Go there with the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] I gave you, and [em1]other [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s[/em1] should resonate with it.
Fill this tear with [em1]memories[/em1].
In that case, wouldn't it be better if you see the memories yourself?
The owner of the tear [em1]cannot see[/em1] the memories.
After all, we lose memories to stay sane. We can't have our tears remind us constantly.
If so, why do you keep the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s away? It's not like they will show you the memories.
There are things you [em1]feel compelled to do[/em1] even if you know they won't help.
Even a dragon may hope for... [em1]miracles[/em1].
Alright. Leave it to me.
I love and shine at finding hidden stuff.
Nice hobby.
Here, take her journal. Thank you in advance.
Just go to the [em1]locations mentioned in the journal[/em1]. There are [em1]4[/em1] in all.
On it.
Now, let me take stock of the situation.
Arden wants me to fill the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1] with [em1]memories[/em1].
The [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] [em1]resonates with [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s from the same dragon[/em1], so I need to take it with me.
Before I set out to find the other [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s, I should browse [em1]the Warrior's journal[/em1] again.
Alright, just let me know when you're available.
Give the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s you've gathered to Arden?
Tada! Arden, I've brought you the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s.
The [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] from you also contains memories.
Arden? How is it? Are you remembering anything?
Arden? Say something. You should be able to see the memories this way, right?
You're so talkative...
Ellie, actually...
A place has come to my mind.
If I'm not mistaken... a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] can be found there as well.
Are you coming with me?
Sure! Where is it?
What's wrong? Is it far away?
How fast can you walk... Forget about it. Just get on.
On... where?
My back.
I should come back with [em1]5 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s[/em1].
Which page shall I read?
Arden will then start to [em1]gather fruit[/em1] from nearby trees.
Refer to the [em1]journal[/em1] and look for locations [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s may be placed.
Arden says that the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] [em1]resonates with [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s of the same dragon[/em1]. I mustn't lose this one.
Something's shining here. It looks like a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]!
I found it! It's a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]!
Hm? What is this?
The surroundings feel a bit strange.
So, this is what "[em1]reflecting memories[/em1]" means.
This must be [em1]Arden's memory[/em1]?
I think so. It happened the moment you got the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1].
Arden? What are you doing there?
A human? Why does she look colorless?
Is Arden's memory lacking?
That white shadow-like figure must be the Warrior.
Oh, does that mean we can see a younger Arden too?
But where is Arden?
Is she... mistaking me for Arden?
I suppose that's why dragons can't use [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s themselves.
To watch the memory, you should play along with it.
But how?
You should [em1]pretend to be Arden[/em1].
Act like Arden, or [em1]recreate Arden's actions[/em1].
What, Arden, why walk into water?
Don't worry. It's a bet. I won't break my word.
Come here. I've brought leftovers from the restaurant. Let's eat together.
This is good! Is this beef bread new?
We're doing great. Despite our hard preparation, I thought the restaurant would soon go out of business.
Now that we've got repeat customers, we should be able to rest a bit.
Arden, you were so reluctant to open a restaurant.
But look at the dishes you cooked today. You've become a real chef.
Don't forget that I was supposed to be the chef. You only got the position because I let you.
And adding a ton of pepper in the beef stew is also my suggestion, remember?
<wave>Ohhh!</wave> It feels great to sit side by side in the breeze.
Come on, I told you to relax. Business is good today. You can have another shot.
Arden, remember what I said? I'll grant you one wish if you beat me in stone skipping.
My stone skipped eight times. Yours should skip more than that.
You can do this, Mr. Dragon!
Hmm... What now...
Apparently, you should do what the Warrior and Arden [em1]did together[/em1] here.
I need to go through [em1]the Warrior's journal[/em1] again.
I will make an exception and give you one more chance today.
Remember what I said? I'll grant you one wish if you beat me in stone skipping.
Haha, it's just throwing stones, but it's fun.
Opening a restaurant is my wish... Thank you for helping me realize it.
I've always wondered what such a life will feel like.
Following the same ordinary routines, complaining about all the hardship after work...
drinking and eating with a loved one, and living on with a relaxed mindset.
It's a life I didn't dare to dream about when I first met you, Arden.
You've granted my wish. I want to grant yours too.
Whenever you make a choice, go for the largest option.
Stone skipping is about making the stone bounce on water, not sink into water.
Stones that big won't skip well.
But... it looks like it can bounce. There you go!
See?! That counts as a success, right?
Oh my, that's not bad! Looks like what I said reached you.
But you're still far from beating me. Just keep trying.
Alright! This stone looks like it can fly.
Hey, only once?
At this rate, I wonder if I'll ever grant you any wish.
It's not a large area. I should check every [em1]nook and cranny[/em1].
Oh, I've caught something!
Now, I just need to get close to this [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]...
Oops, my bug net caught something, but I've got no room in my bag.
It's brightest here.
Ughhhh, but it's too high. I can't reach it even if I stretch my arm!
Why are witches capable of so many things?
Because they can use [em1]tools[/em1].
But I am wrapping the spiderweb on my hand.
Don't get too far away.
Our secret base is as lovely as ever.
Loot at this. Isn't it great to have such a flat place to sit on.
I always plan before I act. Stop calling my actions a waste of time!
Okay, I'll continue with the sculpture.
It's a precious day off. Arden, go ahead and enjoy yourself.
But the memory doesn't seem to be ending...
You probably should act accordingly.
When the Warrior was making a sculpture, [em1]Arden would be[/em1]...
Ah, it disappeared.
The memory has entered the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))].
Alright, let's search another place.
We've got all the memories. Let's take them to Arden.
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BraveFruit_Name"))][/em1] to the Warrior?
Let's see... They are all perfectly ripe. Our chef is getting more discerning rapidly.
Arden, doesn't this look like the cave you used to live in?
Haha, the first time I saw you, you were sitting on a large pile of gemstones, like a typical villain dragon.
Although I was the one in the wrong.
I mistook you for another dragon and was there to catch you... Now that I think of it, that encounter was a blessing in disguise.
The dragon I wanted to take revenge on was already gone.
When I found out the truth, I couldn't accept it, and went to you for fights every day.
Haha, we actually ended up sitting in a remote forest, eating fruit together.
Ah, it's all gone already. Time to finish this sculpture.
Arden, you should also develop your own hobby instead of taking care of me.
<wave>Tada!</wave> That's why I've got you this.
The kind Miss Warrior has got you tools for you to take up painting!
Give it a go.
It will be great to record the beautiful things with your painting brush during such occasions.
Draw something you like, or something you find beautiful.
Oh? You've picked these again? You really like them.
Pick more then, so that we can share.
Arden did something for the Warrior. Look around.
Hm? You've really drawn something?
Let me see... Huh? Arden, sorry... but what is this?
What? Me? But it doesn't look... <shake>Hahahahaha!</shake> Ah, are these my clothes and apron?!
Oh my goodness, in the name of my sword, your drawing is awful!
Alright, alright, I'm sorry... <shake>Chuckle</shake>... Oh no, I can't stop it.
<shake>Ahahaha</shake>, Arden, you're blushing. You're a red dragon now!
Is this painting for me? Hey, you don't take back a gift you've given away.
Since my sculpture is also ready, I'll place the painting in it.
But didn't I ask you to draw something you like or find beautiful?
You've drawn me. Does that mean you like me very much? Hm?
Haha, alright, no more messing with you. Would you like to try making a sculpture next time?
Oh! There's something in it.
But why's it so [em1]slippery[/em1]...
<shake>Ahhh!</shake> I can't grab it!
It's just normal for such a large mushroom to have more slime.
Yeah, but it makes things hard to pick up.
Here it is! A [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]!
Ohhh!
And here's my [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]...
Arden, come over. I want a word with you.
Don't you have anything to tell me?
From the look on your face, you never planned to tell me about it.
I heard it from Mr. Tatton, one of our patrons.
So, "thousand-year dragon" wasn't just about your lifespan?
Why didn't you tell me earlier? That you will lose your memories. Why?
Er, what's wrong? Why isn't she talking?
You're supposed to answer, aren't you?
I see, I need to [em1]pretend to be Arden[/em1].
How should I reply to the Warrior?
I'm sorry
Isn't this the answer?
We are in a memory. Your reply should match what the [em1]owner of the memory[/em1] would say.
Well... Let me check [em1]the Warrior's journal[/em1] again.
I didn't want to upset you
It doesn't matter
Huh? What matters then?
How much pepper to add to the stew? How many flower petals are there on the new plates? What color is the table cloth?
These things were meaningless, until our relationship gave them meanings.
What's the point of doing these things if you won't remember them...
If I go on a trip one day, and my return gets postponed due to sudden injuries or sickness...
you may have forgotten me when I come back.
Why should I hear it from someone else?
At least, at least... you should tell me yourself.
My life is much shorter than yours in the first place...
Are we not close enough for me to know it...?
I hate you, you stupid dragon.
So... Arden has always been like this.
I thought he would act differently in front of his partner.
Perhaps he really found it unimportant.
Sigh, Virgil, you're a hat after all. You don't understand human feelings.
I'm a hat with a heart.
But amnesia is a serious issue. How can you dismiss it as a trivial matter?
Suppose I go home to find my parents not recognizing me... That's terrifying!
Arden is hundreds of years old. He may not share a little girl's opinion.
Or, he thinks he can handle it.
Hmm, he's a dragon hard to understand.
We're here again...
Hm? Something's shining over there!
There's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1] somewhere.
But... I don't see a thing.
It may be in the wall or the [em1]ground[/em1].
Oh, my shovel hit something!
It's a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]!
Well, I've hit it, but I can't dig it out.
Use more strength, and dig [em1]properly[/em1]. It may have been caught in something else.
Ah, and the flower's gone too.
The flower probably didn't bloom during the Warrior's lifetime.
Arden, what are you waiting for?
This... should be when Arden gave the hair tie to the Warrior.
It's a present from you. <wave>You should help me put it on! Chop chop!</wave>
I guess I should approach the Warrior.
Oh, that's swifter than I imagined.
Hmm... That's quite skillful. When did you prepare this?
I was finding my hair too long and considering a haircut. Now it's nicely kept off my neck.
But aren't you forgetting something?
You are supposed to say something sweet to accompany such a gift.
Come on, don't zone out. <wave>Just say something!</wave>
I like you so much
Hey, why the silence?
You're like a gemstone
This is embarrassing
Sigh, this is very you. I knew it would end up like this.
I just want some sweet words. Is it that hard for you? Even harder than breathing fire I guess?
But at least you're giving me gifts now. That should count as an improvement...
Thank you. I'll wear it often.
But I thought you would find an excuse to justify it. "It's your birthday" or something.
How can you make up a birthday for me? That's not how it works.
Haha, you do have a point. By the way, when is your birthday, Arden?
What? You don't remember? Well... maybe you don't.
A warrior who never knew her birthday, and a dragon who's forgotten his. Aren't we a perfect match?
Right, I can assign a birthday to you.
And I will celebrate it for you every year. Look forward to it!
This flower... If only the Warrior could see it bloom. She would have been so glad.
At least her wish has come true.
"The more sincere you are, the bigger your flower"...
Arden must have seen the flower when he came here to drop the hair tie.
I hope Arden could recall the scene we just saw...
Alright, let's look for the other [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s.
All the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s are here. Let's take them to Arden.
The inside of the mushroom's cap is glowing.
I'll examine the glowing area with my [em1]hand[/em1].
Urr... <shake>Urrahhhh</shake>, this is hard.
I thought I wouldn't have <shake>dragonback motion sickness</shake>...
Wasn't it a thrilling experience you'd always wanted?
It was indeed!
And I got here in no time. Dragons may even be faster than trains.
You're tougher than I am after all.
Say, where's Arden?
Let's look for Arden.
It should be around here.
Do you have any digging tool on you?
Sure. Witches always have all kinds of tools on them.
That's reliable.
I'll get the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] out. Dig where it resonates.
Please dig where the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] resonates.
Oh, it's the resonance! This is the place!
Arden! I've found a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]!
Okay, take this too.
Hm? Isn't this the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] I gave you? Why...
Oh! This is —
Arden! Arden! The Warrior is right ahead!
I've told you that a dragon can't see it himself.
Huh? Then...
You've filled that tear with memories, so I can sense a bit of it.
Shall I put this piece of memory in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] too?
No...
She never stops talking, right?
Unlike the first impression, she's really talkative.
I need you to repeat her words to me.
And my words... to her.
Sorry for the trouble.
You've already caused me quite some trouble, you know?
Well... my apologies.
I'm just kidding. I'll do as you said.
Whoa... It's been ages since I last came here. Lying all day long was driving me crazy.
Don't push yourself too hard.
Okay, okay, but I feel good today, Arden. No need to worry.
And the breezes today feel comfortable. I'm glad we've come out together.
Say, Arden, you remember what I said before? The [em1]"Don't ever forget me"[/em1] thing.
I do.
I'm taking it back now.
When I first found out what "thousand-year dragon" really meant, I was really mad.
Later, I learned that my days were numbered... and was terrified.
Arden, you will live for centuries, right? Haha, you'd probably outlive me even if I had five lives.
The time we spent together is just a flash in your life.
So, I think my death won't have a lasting impact on your life.
Every day, you will get up, open the window, and smoke in the morning breeze...
You will make stews deftly, go for a walk after a day's work, and chat with someone over a drink...
And one day, when you don't even remember [em1]why you opened the restaurant[/em1],
the time I spent with you will no longer mean anything to you.
I'm destined to die before you. I used to find it unfair, and I was afraid that you might forget everything about me.
But the more I thought about it, the more I felt sorry for you, Arden.
I will become a thing of the past for you...
It will be exhausting to keep thinking of me for a thousand years.
And it will feel so lonely and painful... So, you'd better forget it all.
I'll remember you.
No, there's no need, Arden. I don't mind.
Alright, just [em1]remember this one thing then.[/em1]
Arden, you've made me very happy, so I hope you can [em1]always be happy yourself[/em1].
I want the rest of your life to be peaceful and content, and free of pain and illness, just like now.
Don't cry over the happy memories you had with me, and don't be tortured by them.
Just recall me for one time. Got it?
I remember.
Alright, I will absolutely remember it.
Are you sure you want to use "absolutely" so casually? Doesn't every word of a dragon contain power?
I'm not using it casually.
Alright. Don't you dare forget it.
And here's a gift.
This is a strange looking lamp.
It's a [em1]night light[/em1]. I had a witch I know make it.
You sleep a lot, so I asked her to make [em1]a lamp that rids the user of nightmares[/em1].
I love you, Arden. I wish you eternal happiness.
Arden, when I die, scatter my ashes in the [em1]cascade[/em1].
Water goes everywhere, so I want to be in it.
Shall I scatter you in the sea instead? I can fly over in no time.
No, I prefer the cascade. The sea is the final destination, and it's way too far.
And... I may be attracted to this place when I want a break, and end up arriving at the [em1]village[/em1].
That way, I can check on you, Arden.
Fine, you know nothing about being romantic.
That...
That's why Arden stays by the village cascade a lot...
I miss you.
After you were gone...
I kept reminding myself of you.
At first, I pretended that you were still around, and carried on my old life.
However... The time still came when most of my memories faded over one night.
I couldn't figure out why I left all the gemstones behind to open a restaurant here...
And why [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s were scattered all over the place...
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))]s don't work on me, but I kept them anyway, thinking that they might become handy one day.
I went with the flow and kept running the restaurant. Strangely enough, I carried the tear with me wherever I went.
I was such an idiot...
I couldn't even grant one single wish of yours...
Ellie, could you do me one last favor?
I want to grant her last wish.
I won't be able to face her again if I keep living with a curse on me.
I've been telling you so all this time: Let's lift the curse!
Now, let's get over there.
<shake>W-whoa</shake>... This is fun, but it makes me cold and sick.
Arden, this place...
It's where I'm going to see her off.
Here.
It's her.
What? This... this is tiny. Isn't she...
She's dead. These are her cremains.
Why give them to me? And why do you have them in the first place?
They were stored inside the dismantlable bottom of the night light. I struggled for a long time... and finally decided to bring them here.
<shake>But, but what am I supposed to do with them?</shake> And why were they stored in the night light?
Because I couldn't let them go...
I would have nothing left if I scattered them into the cascade.
I couldn't stand that, so I kept them.
However, I think it's time to move on.
Ellie, you've helped me a lot. I hope you can see her off with me.
Have you ever paid any last respects?
Nobody close to me has passed away, so...
You're young after all.
No need to overthink. Just say what comes to your mind.
I'm doing well.
You're gone, but I'm enjoying my life as promised.
I know it was stupid of me to put a curse on myself.
I... won't do it again.
I can't help forgetting again, but I will retrieve my memories when it happens.
You are the most beautiful, most dazzling, and [em1]cutest... gemstone[/em1] I've ever seen.
I love you, Angelica.
Your memories will keep me happy in the future.
I will never forget you.
It's your turn.
What? Ah, alright!
Hmm... What should I say?
Stone skipping
Arden is now a master of stone skipping.
Thanks to your coaching.
I once heard that the body might remember things the mind had forgotten.
Arden is doing fine. You can rest in peace.
What? Are you going to call my words pointless?
They are fine.
What's going on? You are nothing like your usual self.
Hm.
What now? Arden, do you need more help lifting the curse?
What do you think?
No, you don't.
Right, I'm really fine now.
You won't regret it?
I will.
And I knew I would from the very beginning.
I decided to make [em1]a choice that I would regret for my whole life[/em1].
But I [em1]would do the same[/em1] even if I got to choose again.
I knew I would forget, but I couldn't let go.
I didn't want to give up 50 years of happiness, even if it meant 500 years of regret.
It's a new experience for me.
I used to hate witches.
But I think I'm able to get rid of my dislike now.
I know I will forget everything again as long as I live.
To remind myself, I will leave a record,
and place it somewhere eye-catching in the restaurant.
Because I've promised her...
Ellie, you are the [em1]best customer[/em1] our restaurant has ever had.
Thank you, indeed.
Arden is still running the restaurant.
He can be a complainer, but he's getting along with the villagers.
The village had a crisis, but things are back to normal now.
Flower of Love
The seed you planted with Arden has grown into a huge flower.
It's always as fresh as when it just bloomed.
I believe it's the largest flower in the Green Forest.
The memory has apparently entered the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))].
So, Arden opened the restaurant for the Warrior's sake...
He probably never expected himself to be a talented cook.
But now that the Warrior's gone... why's the restaurant still in operation?
Just ask Arden if you are curious.
I think he won't know a thing, like always.
But... maybe he knows it now.
Nothing happens anymore even if I hold it in my hand.
What was that?
Arden isn't here, but I can hear his voice!
Are the memories leaking because you're approaching other tears?
But, didn't Arden sound like [em1]he remembered the Warrior[/em1]?
If that was Arden [em1]before his amnesia[/em1], it may be a clue.
[em1]Go to the shining place and use the[/em1] [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))].
Nine times. Exactly nine.
It went farther than your stone, all the way to the [em1]center of the lake[/em1].
I've been practicing the way you told me.
Your best record was eight... I've beat you.
The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1] has flown farther than any stone in this area.
Now, you should grant my wish.
You promised me... didn't you?
Hardly anyone comes here even now.
Which means the rock you flattened remains untouched.
When I sit here... I can almost hear you laughing.
[em1]The tree behind the rock[/em1] used to bear lots of fruit,
but that's no longer the case.
You liked the fruit so much and couldn't have enough of it... I guess you've taken it with you.
This mushroom has grown a lot.
[em1]Its cap[/em1] is now big enough for me to lay my gift for you on it.
But it probably can't bear its own weight any more.
I should have talked to you properly.
I used to believe that there were things more important than these.
I've got much to say to you.
The seed has finally sprouted.
I knew there wouldn't be a flower soon, but even sprouting took so long.
What were you thinking when you planted the seed?
I played along with the [em1]sowing[/em1], without understanding your purpose.
I wonder how long the flower will last.
I hope it will still be here even after I've forgotten you.
Hm? Look, Virgil, I'm glowing!
You had Twinkle-Twinkle Juice again?
No, I didn't! What's going on?
Ah! The light's coming from the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))][/em1].
Arden said it would [em1]resonate when near another[/em1] [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))].
I suppose I can take the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] out of my [em1]bag[/em1] and [em1]use it[/em1].
With the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "TearOfDragon_Name"))] and the Warrior's journal, Arden won't forget the Warrior again.
This dragon sculpture... has a broken neck.
Arden's painting of the Warrior is stuffed in it.
Arden's love... has always been hidden in here.
This is the night light the Warrior left Arden.
Arden won't have nightmares any more.
It says... "[em1]eternal[/em1] owner of this restaurant."
There's Vinch's signature.
Arden, do you know the [em1]cats[/em1] that sometimes come to the village?
Cats? You mean those small animals that walk on four legs?
Yup, the ones that have a nose and ears, and go "meow."
This explanation is unasked for... Of course I know those annoying creatures.
So, you don't like cats, Arden.
I'd say I'm uninterested.
Not even when you see them wandering the village?
Those brats sometimes steal my pre-cut fruit.
They can eat a bit of unprocessed ones if they have to, but the pre-cut ones, that's cheeky.
Well... I'm afraid you can't expect cats to know manners...
But it sounds like you do pay attention to them, Arden.
I've been telling you that I have no interest in cats. Find Rubrum if you want to discuss cats. I've had enough.
The [em1]impossible[/em1] flower.
A flower [em1]you'll never find[/em1].
It means there's no such thing as [em1]miracles[/em1] in this world.
I'm not sure what you're trying to say.
Whatever you're hoping to find, it's not what you think it is.
Have you ever seen it yourself?
I've searched for it, but I've never seen it.
Then why? What made you look for it?
I don't remember.
Either way, the flower's useless, even if you did find it.
But if you really want to look... ask about the [em1]Garden of Empty Words[/em1].
I thought... maybe if I found it, I could spend a little more time with her.
What? You have a gift for me?
You want to give me this [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
It's not bad. Thanks.
You're giving me a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
A [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]...?
Hmm... Is this a gift?
I don't need any [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
Don't ever give it to me again.
I feel like I used to like this a lot...
But I can't recall why.
Thank you. I believe it's been a long time since I received any [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
You remembered what I like?
Witches really are peculiar beings... Thanks.
There's nothing better than a gift that's needed right away.
I needed [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] right now.
Thanks. I'll use it well.
I don't need that.
Stop giving it to me.
Don't need it.
It's been quite some time since you came to the village, hasn't it?
And you're still so excited about everything here.
I've been seeing a lot of you recently.
Come here whenever you're hungry. I've got more food than you can eat.
During my hours of operation, that is.
I believe we've known each other for some time.
I've met many beings,
including all kinds of witches.
They've given me a good reason to hate everything except myself.
But you... you feel a bit different.
Drop by anytime.
When you first came to the village, I just thought you were an overly meddlesome witch.
I thought you would pass by just like the countless witches and humans who came and went before.
But… you treated not just me, but all the villagers with sincerity.
Thinking about the gifts I've received from you… anyone could see it.
Here, take it. This is my gift to you.
I don’t really like just being on the receiving end all the time.
And... come to the restaurant more often. I can always serve you some [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))].
It's a flyer from Arden's restaurant.
For someone so gruff, he sure takes running it seriously.
Still, with all the work we've got here, we'll probably need the food he's talking about.
But what's this about "never skimping on pepper"? Isn't that just an ingredient?
Guess we'll just have to go ask him.
Arden, I came after seeing your flyer!
The flyer was surprisingly... welcoming. Did you write it yourself?
Not really. I just found a stack of old ones lying around the place.
Figured since there's a newcomer in town, I'd send one your way.
Oh... then does that mean you don't actually sell this [em1]"helpful food"[/em1] the flyer mentioned?
Of course I do. If I'm handing out flyers, I'd better be ready.
Used to make those dishes back when the village was full of workers... but with everyone gone, there hasn't been a reason to.
You're a witch, and you've got your hands full with all sorts of things. The food will help.
These meals are [em1]made with extra care[/em1]. They'll give you [em1]different kinds of boosts[/em1].
Not for free, of course.
I see. And what's with that "never skimping on pepper" part?
Oh, and Rubrum's tea can help too. You should drop by.
As for the pepper... It's simple. Food tastes better with a heavy hand. That's all.
Hah, that's... a pretty underwhelming answer.
Hmph. You sure fuss over the smallest things.
What? Again?
But Arden, you've been here longer than anyone.
You must remember something.
Anything at all!
Hmph.
You really don't remember anything?
...She was picky about food.
Not long after she moved into the village, she came to my tavern with some other folks.
Tried my cooking, then made this face like she'd swallowed poison.
Still cleaned the plate, though.
Later, I found out she couldn't stand mushrooms.
Idiot. If you can't eat something, just say so.
With the way you are, it's no wonder she didn't.
...After that, whenever she came by, I left the mushrooms out.
But never the pepper!
Hmph. Anyway, she kept coming back every now and then for a meal.
Then, about ten years later, she asked me something.
Asked you what?
About the [em1]Plant That Never Dies[/em1].
The... what?
Probably why she came to me in the first place.
Took her ten years to work up the nerve. Foolish.
I don't think so.
Maybe she just wanted to get close to you, Arden.
You even took out the mushrooms for her.
That one...
Nothing. You're looking for Lisa, aren't you?
Yeah, I've been searching for a long time.
If you find her, tell her this. "Thanks... for back then."
Back then?
She'll understand.
Alright. Thanks for telling me all this.
Cold food that tastes good?
Once food goes cold, what flavor's left?
Count me out.
But there are dishes that taste good cold...
If a meal's in front of you, you eat it before it gets cold. What kind of fool lets it sit there?
By Bjorn, do you mean a boy about your age?
He was a sickly kid. He could barely finish even one [lua(GetItemName("BeefStew_Lv1"))].
And… I remember he didn’t want to leave the village. Even on the day they moved, he whined for a long time.
Was it the couple who ran the bakery?
They had two daughters, both small as the palm of my hand. I don’t remember much else.
He’s coming instead of Nana?
Who’s Nana?
Welcome...
The library's gate... is always open.
It's better if you don't come too close... because of the dust...
I need to do cleaning every day.
If they aren't sorted, I'll have trouble finding them.
"I am not where you are." "An apple between the eyes" "I am blooming"...
It's so fun to translate sentence by sentence.
Emm... let's see... ah, I'm sorry. I didn't notice your arrival.
Emm... wanna taste this...?
There's a warm fire here. I like it.
I like silent nights.
It's an adventurer's fantasy to sit still and stare at flames, isn't it?
And... I had a little bit of ingredients left.
This is a gift, Ellie.
Bring them to Rex in the future as well.
Clala's donuts are sweet and delicious.
Birds chirping and the sound of children playing around... are like soothing white noise.
Under the shade of a tree is the best place to be.
Sorry... I'm afraid I may not be of help.
I usually make bookmarks out of plants rarely found elsewhere... Plants that only grow in one place.
But I'm not familiar... with the geography here...
We'd better ask someone [em1]familiar with the local ecosystem[/em1]...
Every place has items that bear local stories. It may not be anything special...
But a story alone is enough to make it precious...
But I am also still searching... We'd better find someone who [em1]has lived in the village for a long time[/em1] or [em1]knows the village's history well[/em1]...
Good, I'm armed to the teeth now. Rex won't scare me whatever he brings.
Let's take it to [em1]Arin[/em1] now.
Which plant should you give Arin?
This flower is called [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))]. It's only found in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
You can only get the flower if you smash into it and knock its crust off.
Yo, you've got something cool on you.
But I'm not empty-handed either!
Here's what I've brought! It'll leave you slack-jawed!
<shake>White prickly vine!</shake>
According to my research, it resembles the prickly vine that used to overrun the village.
And this mysterious plant vanishes once exposed to moonlight!
It's only found around Wisteria.
You actually found this. How lucky of you...
C'mon, Arin! <shake>Time to make your choice!</shake> Follow your heart and choose away!
Arin! I'm staking my best friend Virgil!
And I'm staking <shake>my pride as the best explorer</shake>!
Well... both of you brought interesting plants, but I choose...
YES!!!
...My apologies.
Ellie, I prefer... Rex's plant.
Yippee! That's my Arin! My partner surely has a good taste!
No way! Mine is more unique in every way!
Wahaha! Just admit your defeat, Ellie! Or you'll only look miserable.
<shake>You!!!</shake>
I requested Enite to prepare something for me. Could you fetch it for me?
What? Oh, sure. Just ask. I'll be faster than a gale!
Leaves from the Bitter Grape Tea Tree on top of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))]?
Enite the chief of Wisteria sun-dried it herself. They were only used in rituals, they say.
This is [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RattanPetal_Name"))]. Black Cat God gave it to me.
The village is named after this flower, and it's planted in the temple.
That's so fast...
Ellie... I'm sorry.
This is no pleasantry... Ellie, what you brought is also great.
It's actually called [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))]?...What a beautiful name.
And the way to gather it is also unusual... I'll note it down and keep it safe.
Still... I'm sorry for not picking the item you brought, Ellie... I'm really sorry.
I must do this... so I wanted to stop you.
Yet you brought something so nice... I'm so embarrassed.
Well... Actually, I was a bit upset.
But it's fine as long as you're happy, Arin.
Ellie... you are so nice.
Would you accept this... as a token of apology and gratitude?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fiction_Long_001_Name"))]...?
It's... one of my favorite books. Since you're a witch, Ellie... I suppose you enjoy reading?
Oh... oh, yes...
It may be too simple for a witch like you... but I hope you like it.
And, do accept this too...
I found this in a village I visited, and bought it because it looked nice... I want to give it to you.
Are these gifts too childish?
No, no, they are lovely! They're great! But Arin, aren't they your favorite items? Can I really have them?
Because I like you very much, Ellie... It's like what you did, getting things I like for me...
I don't have much presentable... These are all that I can offer...
Thank you, Arin. I love them.
Ah, besides these, I've got some other stuff.
I found them for you in the first place, so just take them all.
<shake>Rex the great explorer! Back like a hurricane!</shake>
Already?
I know that Wisteria used to be... known for its tea.
But I didn't expect... to receive such special tea leaves.
Did you just mention a god? The Black Cat God... I wish I can see him with my own eyes.
Perhaps you got such magical and fun stuff because you're Ellie...
Humph... Did anyone comfort you when I was away, Ellie?
I wasn't that sad...
Huh, you forgot it already? Didn't you ask me to take over your old friend?
Talking hat! I want to explore the world and discuss life with you!
<shake>Ahhhh, someone save this poor hat!</shake>
Oh, I really did. I staked Virgil... Now I remember.
Why are you so calm? Aren't you too much?
What, do, I, do... I'm, so, sad...
<shake>Wahaha!</shake> Competitions are cruel in nature! Face your fate, losers! Hat and Ellie!
That's enough, Rex.
Ellie is the witch who restored the village and helped us settle down here.
We should be repaying her instead of taking her friend.
Ahem, I was just joking. Don't take it so seriously.
Then, treat us to dinner at Arden's restaurant instead...
Okay, okay, it's just another joke, alright?
Oh, so you're not going to take Virgil?
What? You're disappointed?
<wave>How come~ That's great~</wave>
Ellie... What did Rex bet?
Well, he promised to tell me what he was [em1]looking for[/em1].
Stop staring at me like that. I promised because I thought I would win!
And I really won!
...C'mon, tell Ellie.
Why? I'm the winner!
And I'm the judge, and it was not a fair bet in the first place.
Tsk... Fine, telling you won't cost me anything.
We're looking for something called the [em1]Book of Stars[/em1]!
Book of Stars? Doesn't sound so awesome after all?
Humph, how can you judge a book by its title!
I tell you, that's a mythic book, said to be able to grant any wish.
Really? Never heard of it before!
Of course, it's only known to a few. Arin only found out after much research...
I haven't... figured it out completely. I just thought this was the right place to focus on my research...
That's it!
Waaaah, I though it was nothing, but it turned out that you guys are looking for something quite interesting!
Hey, you're so rude!
If it wasn't for Ellie... we wouldn't have made it here.
Thank you, Ellie... We're forever in your debt.
It's me in your debt. I managed to keep Virgil, and I heard some interesting news.
Don't hesitate to tell me if you run into any difficulty in your research or investigation!
Humph, let's have another bet next time, Ellie!
Bye... Take care.
Witch...
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))] is a material for making potions...
Witch is...
What book... are you looking for?
What would you like to discuss with Arin?
It's a quiet place... I like it.
I've long dreamed to live in such a place... Now it has come true. Lucky me.
Rex... brings me lots of stuff.
Without him... I wouldn't have seen, heard, and felt them.
Pie
The day I moved in, Enite brought me... a huge pile of pies.
Rex enjoyed them... but I'm not a big fan of desserts.
Villagers
During the welcome party... I caused the villagers much trouble.
I was worried that they might reject us... but it turned out that I was wrong.
Temple
Hmm... I've been there. It's a serene and graceful place.
Sometimes, I wonder why... people can be so pious.
Ellie, you're the first witch... that I've had a proper conversation with.
We occasionally had witches visiting the mansion... but they were all taciturn.
Even if Rex tried to talk to them... they would only smile at him.
Every time I do cleaning... I feel calm and peaceful.
Does that count as a hobby...?
It's safe there... and I like it. Rex finds it boring, though.
I can easily gather [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFlower_Water_Name"))][/em1] there.
Oh, it's used to treat minor injuries. Rex needs it a lot...
It has recently been renovated... so it's functioning alright.
But... the small tables and chairs haven't been replaced. They hurt my back.
I'm thinking about replacing them with [em1][lua(GetItemName("SimpleWalnut_Chair"))][/em1]. They are comfortable, and smell good.
I hardly ever cooked when working at the mansion...
Because there was a cook who had always worked there.
On my first day there... the cook prepared bread and soup for me.
Family
Both my parents have passed away...
Rex is my only family now...
Campfire
I feel calm when I stare at a flame.
I heard that ancient people would build fires in caves... Do witches do that too?
According to Rex, there are many points of interest there.
But... I find [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "JingleBug_Water_Name"))][/em1]s... kind of scary.
Rex always comes back with a lot of them on his shoes... It takes me a week to remove them.
Childhood
I spent my childhood in a village smaller even than Wisteria.
During the day, I chiefly worked in the fields with my mother... or did weaving.
My family had many books... but I couldn't read for too long at night, or I'd use too much lamp oil.
Love
Ellie... have you ever loved someone romantically?
Me? I... I can't tell... Please don't tell Rex.
It sounds nice... but I don't think I'm capable of that.
I like romance and... detective novels.
Is that weird?
At night... reading a book seems like a good idea.
Of course, I can't keep the lamp on all night... so I frequently use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Moondelion_Powder_Name"))][/em1].
There's no worry about fire... and one bundle is enough for a night's reading.
I've never tried it...
Rex fishes with a spear or his bare hands... so I’ve never thought of trying to follow him.
But I’d like to catch a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Vwitch_Name"))][/em1].
It looked... pretty.
Roy seems to be truly knowledgeable about flowers and plants.
I also once asked if there was a way to grow [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Raspberry_Name"))][/em1] at home.
I couldn't find a method in books either...
Oh, [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Raspberry_Name"))][/em1] can still only be found in the wild. That was disappointing.
I usually... clean the area in front of the library gate, to keep it tidy.
If I have a chance... I'd love to learn about the village's history too.
Arin, you've always been a librarian?
Not exactly... I was only in charge of the study in the mansion...
Mansion?
Yes, the mansion of Istakipper... It has a huge study.
It's a large residence, so it needs many people to maintain... And there is a study.
It was just that I spent a bit more time there. I dare not call myself a librarian.
It must be a giant house, since it has a room devoted to books.
Yes, because the Istakippers... are a relatively prominent family in that region.
The former head of Istakipper is also a renowned explorer...
Who is this former head of Istakipper?
Oh, that's Rex's grandfather... Also known as the former head of Istakipper.
Sounds like a dweller of another world...
So you discovered your passion for books when working in a study?
I don't know how to put it... It may be familiarity instead of passion.
Because, all that I know and seek... are in books.
Arin, I think you're born to be a librarian. You're the perfect librarian of Wisteria!
I'm... glad to hear that.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Arin"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Ellie, you... remind me of Rex a lot.
What? How?
You are energetic... laugh a lot... and like places of wonder...
So does Rex... Whenever he learns about a place of wonder, he insists on visiting it himself.
That's how I came to see many sceneries — he took me to various places.
You have a point... but I'm actually one of Rex's kind?
By the way, Arin, you go on adventures with Rex?
When I'm alone... I don't feel like leaving the house at all...
But whenever Rex sees me reading, he approaches me and talks.
He asks me... if I want to go to a certain place.
Although I don't accompany Rex everywhere,
we have indeed... travelled to many places together.
Didn't expect that. To me, Arin is totally Professor Library.
Professor Library...?
Ellie... I'm so sorry for what happened last time.
Huh? What was it?
The bet Rex threw at you... It seemed to have troubled you a lot.
It didn't. Actually, I found it fun. It woke the long-forgotten desire for victory in me, and brought me new friends.
By the way, where did you learn about the Book of Stars?
Oh... Somebody told me about it...
Ellie... You've never heard of it?
No, not until Rex mentioned it.
I rarely read anything other than text books, after all... Haha.
Actually... I've never had such a long conversation with a witch.
You haven't been to anywhere with a Witch's House?
I have... but I hardly ever chatted with them...
Never mind, I guess it's better to stay away from Witch's Houses if you don't have business.
Yeah... So I thought you would know, Ellie... but turns out that it's only known by a few people.
It may not be enough to repay your favor, but I will inform you once I have any clue.
A book that can grant wishes! This description alone is enough to arouse curiosity!
Ah... okay.
But please... keep it a secret.
I heard that there're some bandits who target ancient books only... We'd better be prudent.
Arin, when did you learn the ancient witch language?
I first ran into the ancient witch language...
when reading a book at the mansion of Eastchip.
It was a detective novel, and some sentences were in the ancient witch language.
A detective novel? Written by a human?
Right... so I gathered all the detective novels by the same author.
After reading about 80 of them...
I remembered about 30 ancient witch words.
I'm more surprised by the number of books you read.
Why? Doesn't it only take one day to finish an average novel...?
<shake>WHAT?</shake>
Ellie... are you and your mother close?
Sure! I followed Mom around all day long before I went to school.
What about you, Arin?
My mother... always wore a smile.
She said she once aspired to become a soldier, just like her father.
After she married my father... she became an ordinary housewife.
Nevertheless... she didn't waste her time lamenting that. She stayed energetic all her life.
By the sound of it, you don't share your mother's personality, Arin.
No. My mother also said that I have my father's personality.
I guess your parents interacted pretty much the same way you interact with Rex.
Rex's personality is more like your mother's.
Oh... I suppose you're right.
I didn't spend much time with my mother though...
She was too busy with her work to tend to me much...
She would occasionally chat with me in the evening while weaving. That was all.
Librarian
Rex and Ellie
After the bookmark
Ancient witch language
About mother
I spend most of my day... in the library.
I want to read... all the books kept there.
Highlion
Kids
Family History
Ellie... do you ever imagine things like that?
I mean... Could it be that you're part of Theo's adventure party too?
You're from the Blueriver family, right?
I was just imagining what it would've been like if you had gone to Highlion.
I don't think I've done that much recently.
Though I'm sure some fun things happened there, too.
Still, I think staying in Wisteria was definitely the better choice.
You've never been to Highlion, right?
No... I've only been there once, following Rex. Just to take care of some family business.
But I do wonder, sometimes, what life in Highlion is like.
Even books and newspapers give hints about life there.
Especially... I read that there's a place called a [em1]university[/em1] for ordinary humans.
A place where you can study all sorts of subjects.
So, like a school for normal people, similar to the School for Witches.
Exactly. They say the tuition is expensive... so I probably couldn't afford it.
But I'd still like to see it, even if just for a little while.
Ah, don't tell Rex. He said he never wants to go back to the city because there are too many people...
I'm part of the adventure party. I was forced to join.
No, it's really just that I sometimes go along with them.
Actually... I was recently forced to join too.
Theo's adventure party. As an honorary advisor...
Haha, that's funny.
Honorary advisor... what exactly does that involve?
I think it's mostly about gathering useful information for adventures... or offering advice.
Theo sometimes comes to the library to ask questions about this and that.
Doesn't he ever invite you to go on adventures with him?
Now that you mention it... he hasn't invited me.
But sometimes, just hearing the kids talking about their adventures sounds fun.
Theo, you mean?
Well, you're already in the guild. If you wanted to go along, he'd probably enjoy it.
Then... maybe I'll ask him next time.
I had no friends when I was little, so I always played alone.
Then just tell him you want to go along.
Hmm... for now, the first things that come to mind are:
Mom, Dad, Grandma, Grandpa... everyone's Blueriver.
Isn't that obvious?
Other than that, I don't really know. As for the relatives, I don't know what kind of people they are until I meet them.
Could you tell me about your family?
Well, if you look at my family... everyone's really lively, like me. Not many stay at home doing research like other witches.
Except maybe Aiden.
Right. Everyone except Dad.
That's fascinating. It's interesting to see how different families have different personalities.
Blueriver seems the opposite of our [em1]SilverRain[/em1] family.
Most of our family... are absorbed in books and research. They barely even ride brooms.
So we don't have many famous adventurers, but there are plenty of people who make books or potion recipes.
Kent told me all of this, though.
Kent is incredible... to know all that.
Oh, and Mom is very famous too. Almost everyone in the witch society knows her.
She's so energetic, causing commotion everywhere she went. I was worried Aria's hair might catch fire one day.
What about you, Arin? Have you learned anything about your family?
Actually... they've been arranging for me to meet members of the SilverRain family.
So I'm really looking forward to it.
When I finally meet them... I'll tell Ellie too.
Valuables
You sometimes wear glasses... do you actually need them?
And your relatives... they're also Blueriver, right?
Right. But I don't really know much about the family.
I heard there's a mansion where a few SilverRain witches live together. It even has the largest library and research lab among witch families.
I've heard about it. There's a mansion with such a huge, maze-like library.
Glasses?
Ah! That's not glasses, it's a magic lens.
A magic lens?
Yes. Not ordinary glasses. It's a tool witches use.
The lens amplifies magical power, making things clearer. It's essential for witches.
My vision is incredible! I can even see from Arin's library to Kyla's house.
I envy that... my eyesight was never good except when I was very young.
I had to live with poor eyesight until I became an adult.
That must've been difficult.
I'm not sure if saying "you get used to it" really helps.
Yeah... it was inconvenient, but I didn't even realize how inconvenient it was.
I got the glasses after meeting Rex.
It was amazing to finally see people's faces clearly... I really liked it.
So now you can't even imagine living without them?
Of course, the most important thing is that they make daily life easier.
Sewing was the hardest. I kept pricking my fingers because I couldn't see well.
They're one of my most valuable possessions... I have to take good care of them.
To get them fixed, I'd have to go all the way to a big city.
Welcome, Ellie... Are you looking for something?
I am! I'm looking for something you like, Arin!
Something... I like?
Yeah, actually, I had a deal with Rex. Here is it...
Oh... I'm sorry... Looks like I've caused you some trouble.
You haven't. If anything, I brought it up myself.
I haven't had a bet for a while, so I was kind of worked up.
But I don't know you very well, Arin.
So I'm here to find out about your likes.
Err... Well, hmmm... Ellie... I'm really sorry, but...
If that's the case... you'd better give up...
Huh, why?
Although I appreciate it very much that... you offer to find something... for me...
I can only... choose the item Rex finds...
Is the reason something private?
Well, alright. But still, could you tell me what you like?
After all, a bet is a bet, and I don't want to give up halfway.
Usually... I like [em1]three kinds of[/em1] things.
Something special that [em1]can only be found... at a certain place[/em1].
Something related... to the local [em1]history or myth[/em1].
Or something that is [em1]important[/em1] to people living there.
The items... are all different. Although Rex brings various items based on the situation,
they basically fall... into these three categories...
Okay, I'll strive to find something you like too!
Sure...
Let's sum it up.
Firstly, a [em1]special item that can only be found[/em1] in Wisteria.
I'd better [em1]walk around[/em1], or ask [em1]someone familiar with plants in the forest[/em1].
Then, something related... to Wisteria's [em1]history or myth[/em1].
I should find [em1]someone who's lived in the village for long[/em1] or [em1]someone familiar with such stories[/em1].
And the last one: [em1]something significant[/em1] to people who live in Wisteria...
I think I know who to go for that.
You've thought up someone?
We've met them. Existences that have been in the village for longer than anyone.
Here's a hint: They're not humans.
The [em1]Cat Gods[/em1]...!
Exactly. We can pray to the Cat Gods and try ask them.
Won't they be mad because the question is too trivial...?
Wow, Virgil is actually providing me with a hint today before I even ask. Are pigs flying?
Because I don't want that potato-like guy to wear me.
Please be quiet... You're in a library.
I don't need help... at present.
I appreciate your care... but don't push yourself too hard please.
Give Arin the plant for her to make a bookmark?
Arin! I've brought you something awesome.
Rex isn't here yet?
<shake>Humph, I'm here!</shake>
What? Where's he shouting from?
<shake>I'll go find you!</shake> See you at the library!
You want about [em1]2 vacant slots[/em1] in your bag.
Bring [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))][/em1], [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RattanPetal_Name"))][/em1], and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BittergrapeTealeaves_Name"))][/em1].
Hello, Arin!
Oh, hello, Ellie. What's up?
Actually, could you do me a favor?
Me? What is it...
Arin, you study languages, don't you. Please tell me what these books are about.
Well... I need to have a close look before I can tell you.
It will take some time... Would you like to come into the library?
There are many precious books here... You can read when you're waiting.
Oh my, that's indeed a lot of books.
Is that all you've got to say when faced with a sea of books?
Could there be a hidden door or something among the bookshelves?
Okay, now I know that books don't interest you.
H-hello... Do you have a minute?
Firstly, as for the language the books are written in...
It went extinct a long time ago... It's very old even for an ancient language, so it cannot be interpreted at all.
I can try if you aren't in a hurry... but it will take a couple of years at least.
A couple of years?!
But thanks to the pieces of paper between the pages... I somewhat figured out their themes.
All of the pieces share the same handwriting... They're probably notes left by someone who tried to interpret the books.
The first book is [em1]Facts and Misunderstandings About Prickly Vines[/em1]...
Why should they write in a dead language if it's just a book on plants? I don't get it...
The second book is called [em1]When Life Meets Life[/em1].
It's a curious title, so I browsed a few pages... It's probably about how to combine plants.
Besides plants, there seems to be something else, but I can't understand a word... What a pity.
Lisa has made a combined prickly vine, right?
Maybe there's more to it.
And the last book... It's a bit... weird.
The title is [em1]The Simplest Immortality[/em1]...
Ellie, I want to ask you a question first.
Why do you want to learn about... these books?
The notes in the books... Did you write them?
My goodness, no it wasn't me.
It's a long story, but to put it simply...
So... There used to be a witch named Lisa here in Wisteria.
She suddenly went missing... and giant prickly vines appeared in the village at the same time.
And these books are what that witch was studying...
Yes, and I'm looking for Lisa.
I see. If so... I'll go on with my explanation.
The Simplest Immortality.
It's about [em1]forming a contract with an evil god[/em1] and offering [em1]sacrifice[/em1] in exchange for [em1]immortality[/em1].
Use a life form summoned from the evil god, and offer a scapegoat...
According to what we currently know about the books, this witch named Lisa...
Attempted to sacrifice the village in exchange for immortality...?
That's... probably not the case.
According to the villagers I asked, Lisa was quite helpful.
She wouldn't have been like that if she was planning to sacrifice the village.
In addition, Lisa didn't summon the prickly vines. She created them herself.
She must have her reasons.
I'm not so sure about that.
I-I mean... Sorry, I'm just...
Because witches... usually do absurd things.
There are many eccentric witches, but we're all taught to help others.
So, I don't think Lisa did... horrible things like that on purpose.
Yeah... we shouldn't jump to such a conclusion.
I wasn't a great help... but please drop by whenever you need me.
You already saved the day, Arin! Thank you.
What really did Lisa want to do?
I want to meet her so much if she's still alive...
There are things in the world that you'd better not know.
What's that supposed to mean! Aren't well-hidden truths more worth revealing?
Normally, no.
Anyway, we've got some new clues, right?
Although the situation isn't hopeful yet, at least we know that there are traces of Lisa left around the village.
There must be something nearby! My instinct is saying it!
Which means, we've got more work to do besides restoring the village.
You're simply doing it because you think it fun, no?
Yeah, why not?
Let's do what we can for now!
This is my first time here. So... I don't really know.
I have... nothing to sell right now.
Ellie... It's been a while. How's everything going?
I came after seeing the bulletin. Some books here were lost?
N-no... not lost...
I was sorting the books based on a catalog from the previous librarian...
And found that the catalog and the holdings don't match.
Maybe some books were moved to another place when the library collapsed?
Yeah... that's likely.
But there's a huge gap. It's much work...
I'll ask the villagers for you.
I'll ask Enite first.
Alright... thank you. I'll see if the previous librarian has left any other clue.
[em1]Wing[/em1]...
Have you heard of it?
No, my predecessor didn't mention a wing when I took over.
But...?
He said something like this:
"Don't worry if the actual holdings don't match the catalog. The books are not lost."
"And don't worry about the [em1]small building[/em1] beside the library."
That should mean the wing.
But why did he say [em1]don't worry[/em1]? Shouldn't it be "don't enter" or something?
Maybe he thought "don't enter" would arouse my curiosity.
But this wing here is the one Kyla restored.
It's probably not a full restoration.
Oh my, I can't be more curious!
Do be careful. I'll keep looking for anything left by my predecessor.
And there was nothing in there when I entered...
Please take this [em1]lamp[/em1] with you just in case.
You may be going to somewhere dark...
Thank you, I'll use it.
Ouch, I hit my butt.
But the floor isn't so elevated.
What did I say? The floor is visible.
But I can't see a thing now.
I hope your eyes can emit brighter light.
I don't have such a function.
Wait, I'll light the lamp Arin gave me...
Where... is this place?
At least you should have escaped the maze of bookcases.
Let's walk around a bit.
This... looks like hand-drawn...
It's too dark. I can't see clearly.
Shall we get closer...
I didn't expect to find this beneath the wing.
I was here for books, but I found something unusual.
Ah, here are your missing books, Arin.
They were piled at the place connected to the room with the portraits.
I'll check them out later.
Be careful when you're in there. The passages in it change.
Thank you for everything you did for me...
You found the books for me.
It's nothing. I had much fun.
Ah, this lamp was very handy. Here you are.
Okay, the wing will be open regularly. Drop by whenever you feel like it.
Alright, I'll come often.
Goodnight, then.
Goodnight, Ellie.
I've asked everyone that may have clues.
Are you really getting in there?
But everyone keeps saying that it's dangerous.
Yeah, that's why I can't hold back.
Your way of thinking really baffles me sometimes.
How can I stay away when I've come such a long way to gather information.
Alvin said that the entrance is not on the building, but somewhere [em1]around the library[/em1].
I'll probably find the entrance if I follow the [em1]wind[/em1] from the vent like Arden said.
And don't forget what Vinch said about Janifer.
But they say that the wind is only audible at night.
That should be none other than "Janifer's voice."
Right, Janifer will show us the way into the wing.
Even if Janifer will, don't ignore Alvin's story.
About the "room with no door"?
It can be a [em1]treasury[/em1], or a [em1]jail[/em1].
Hmm... From what Arin said, the previous owner also wanted to hide it.
There must be something in there.
Exactly, and doesn't that make the place even more attractive?
Your way of thinking really baffles me a lot.
Based on these clues, I just need to go [em1]near the library[/em1] [em1]at night[/em1] and find [em1]the source of wind[/em1].
The [em1]real wing[/em1] is really somewhere else.
It should be around here. I can hear wind.
You heard Janifer?
Shh, be quiet. It's indeed scary at night...
Wait, is that it?
Here, this should be the entrance.
Are you sure you want to get in?
Maybe... sometime later. Tomorrow evening, or the evening after that...
Shall I enter now?
Of course I will enter now.
S-something has come up.
Now that we know the location, we can come another evening.
*door opened*
Emm... it's a bit too dark...
Okay, I can see the floor.
Let's go find "our root"!
By the way, is this place really for storing books?
It feels like...
A maze?
Maybe because there aren't brighter lights.
There seems to be a passage ahead. Let's proceed.
Look closely at your surroundings.
What... is this? A bronze statue?
Are there usually statues where books are stored?
And this statue looks creepy.
But this doesn't seem to be the problem.
The existence of this statue is a problem.
You've reached a dead end.
For the end of a maze to be a dead end, it doesn't feel good.
Well... okay then.
<shake>T-time to get out from the vent.</shake>
This makes me feel that I can jump higher now.
Alright, get out quickly.
Okay, I'll get out from the vent and report back to Arin.
This place is full of books and weird bronze statues.
I hope we can get out without an issue.
Hmm... Virgil?
I don't remember passing this place...
This seems to be where we entered from.
Calm down, we'll be fine.
But... the vent is gone.
Okay, we won't be fine.
<shake>What the heck is going on?!</shake>
<shake>Where is my vent?!</shake>
Now calm down again and walk around the place.
<shake>We're stuck here!!</shake>
There is a passage.
Right before you.
Isn't that the passage we followed at the beginning?
But we got here via a passage that didn't exist earlier.
Maybe we can find a new passage beyond it.
Yup, you've got a point.
Alright, since there's a passage, let's go.
This is the statue from before...
Wait.
I've covered my ears. You can scream now.
<shake>Isn't this the statue we saw at the dead end!!</shake>
There can be duplicate statues placed at different locations.
We went down this passage at the very beginning! There wasn't anything here!
Hmm... wait a second. This means...
At least it means the passages are changing.
Right, it's better than being stuck in a dead end.
I'll keep going. There should be new passages ahead.
Is it just me... or is the passage narrowing...?
I think you'd better hurry up.
Hell yes!
Hmm... this I didn't expect...
Books are no longer put on bookshelves nowadays.
Did anyone drop them when cleaning...
Janifer?
<shake>Ah.</shake> Don't tell horror stories here. I beg you.
Anyway, since there always is a passage, let's get out fast.
I can finally catch my breath.
But this place... is full of books!
Looks like we're at the right place.
Then...
Don't tell me you want to leave now?
Our task is to find the books, isn't it?
You actually want to linger around?
Virgil, can't you see that vent? It's too high to reach.
We need to find another exit.
You just want to explore the place.
Heh, let the exploration start!
Everyone says that this place is dangerous. Be more watchful.
<shake>Okay!!</shake> Let the dangerous exploration start!
Lamp! My lamp!
Calm down and light it again.
How am I supposed to calm down!
Phew... Thank goodness.
And there's the passage.
Okay, let's keep going.
<align="center">Comment
"A starry night"</align>
<align="center">Y_Liz0331
"I am always with you, in happiness and in sadness"</align>
<align="center">tvanitidtv6258
"Ms. Witch, I'm here. Please pull me out!"</align>
<align="center">JJ
"Any symptoms?"</align>
<align="center">MOMO
"You're here meow? Melcome!"</align>
<align="center">RYURI
"I feel a bit nervous."</align>
Eek!
Ah...
Arin?
Ellie...? Why are you here...
I happened to find the entrance to the wing...
I passed a maze-like place, and arrived here.
I... I found a key and a hidden passage when looking through my predecessor's stuff, and here I am.
Oh... So this place is connected with that wing.
This... looks like a portrait.
Portrait?
Whose portraits are these?
Our root...
Sorry?
It's what Enite told me.
The previous librarian used to say that "our root is stored in the wing."
I thought the "root" meant books, but I was wrong!
It meant these people.
Root... So these are the founders of the village?
Or someone even greater.
I'll go see the other portraits.
Please let me know when you're done and want to get out.
All the portraits are different. I can't find a clue...
They can't be nobody since their portraits are kept here...
You done?
You can come again. You don't need to check everything today.
Alright
Alright, I'm going.
Yup, it's already late...
I want to look around more.
Sure, no problem.
I'll check out the portraits first.
Arin! I heard that you got some letters for unknown recipients?
Arin! I've identified all the recipients.
Great work!
Another letter arrived when you were away...
Hm? Arin, did you just chuckle?
Oh, hmm... sorry, I recalled something that happened before I came to the village...
Back then, Rex was teased a lot by Grandpa and Mr. Brad.
Before sending this letter, Mr. Brad originally planned to state in it that the recipient must send out 70 such letters themselves.
Yeah... The sender is Mr. Brad, but the recipient isn't specified.
Is Mr. Brad the former librarian here?
Yes, he is a good friend of Rex's grandpa, and is also the person who advised us to... come here.
Hmm... Since the letter is delivered to the library, I suppose it's for you and Rex?
I think... Rex should join the conversation too.
Rex, do you have a minute?
What? But I've just handled the previous letters?!
Ah... Don't worry. This letter has the recipient's info on it.
It's... for you, Ellie.
Huh? For me?
But I don't know Brad...
Still... it has your name on it, Ellie.
Here you are...
What's going on? Anyway, if it's for me... I'll just open it.
Hmm, let's see...
"This is a letter of fortune from Highlion.
It goes around once a year, bringing good luck to everyone that receives it.
It has brought good luck to you now.
You must send a total of 7 letters of fortune, including this one, to people who need them within 4 days.
Please note that you will have good fortune for 7 years in a row as long as you send the letters, but if you don't...
<shake>Ughaaaaah! Isn't this a letter of fortune!</shake>
Go back to the Witch's House and grab a pen.
Do I look like an idiot to you?! Some letter this is!
It says something else below.
<shake>You can't fool me!</shake>
It's the truth. Ms. Ellie Blueriver, you got a fright?
Nnngh, if I read all of it, I will have to write letters myself...
Haha, don't worry. This is not a real letter of fortune.
Hello, Ms. Ellie Blueriver. I am Brad.
Check what else it says.
Ugh... I've left the school. Why would I receive one of these...
I heard a lot about you from Enite and Roy. Arin and Rex told me much too.
I'm sorry about not being able to return to the village.
Still, I hope that these two kids, who are like grandchildren to me, can fit in with other villagers well.
I played this little prank in the hope that they could use it as an opportunity to make friends with the villagers.
I think Arin would seek help from others because she couldn't make the decision.
Rex would open the letters as long as someone's there to help him.
As a result, you would probably learn about these recipient-less letters, Ms. Ellie,
because you are Wisteria's problem solver.
Sorry for bothering you with the wish of an old man, but it would be my honor if this incident has entertained you.
I hope you could become a good friend of Rex and Arin.
In addition, as a former resident of Wisteria, I also want to extend my thanks to you for restoring the village.
Ms. Ellie, I wish you lasting happiness and good luck.
Brad
PS Please consider this pocket money from a grandfather.
Use it to get beef bread from Arden's restaurant and enjoy it with the kids.
Hahaha.
Now I get what Rex meant.
And I also understand why Brad became a friend of Rex's grandpa...
Could it be... a letter of fortune?
The first part looks like it, but the rest is just an ordinary letter.
Rex came with ink all over his hands and dark circles under his eyes. He miserably said, "Arin, help me..."
Haha.
Ellie, you helped me identify all the recipients... Thank you so much.
It's nothing. I had fun and received pocket money.
I'm glad to hear that... And I'll let Rex know.
Here are the letters...
There are a red envelope, a blue one and a yellow one. Three in all?
Yup, Mr. Brad said that he sent them as early as last year.
But he got the wrong address... so the letters ended up being returned to him.
But that geezer then decided to just send them all to us.
What's more, he changed the envelopes and didn't specify the recipients.
Huh? Why would you know?
It's obvious. Brad looks serious-minded and mature, but he plays a prank every once in a while.
You'll know why he became a friend of my grandpa just by looking at this.
Hmm, so these letters were not actually for you and Arin?
No, he sent us other letters.
And in those letters he asked us to identify recipients of these letters.
We've been wondering what to do...
Hmm... I can't tell who the recipients are just by looking at envelopes of different colors.
Huh? Hey, these letters are not sealed?
Which means... anybody can open them and read.
Ellie... are you...
Since the recipients aren't specified, the only way to find out is to read the letters.
That said... these are other people's letters...
I'm for Ellie.
Rex, you too?
See, our letters are both properly sealed.
That these envelopes are left unsealed means he wanted us to check the content.
Indeed. I would never know who to give the letters to only by staring at the envelopes.
Also, he wouldn't leave the letters like this if they contained anything important or private.
You've got a point... Let's read them.
Okay, let's start from the red envelope!
Have you got a [em1]new cane[/em1]? I got a very satisfactory one.
Many canes these days have unique handles. Some even have gems inlaid. They look gorgeous and dazzling.
Still, my favorite are ebony wood canes with silver ornaments. They are simple and graceful.
Speaking of which, new commodities at <Slumbering Tree> are quite good.
A catalogue is attached. Just let me know if you're interested in any of the items.
After all, this is the only place you'll find [em1]canes[/em1].
Brad doesn't only like books, but also likes to collect [em1]nice stuff[/em1].
Hmm, let's read the other letters too.
Recently, portraits small enough to fit into bags and be carried around are popular in large cities.
Many people have portraits painted to show off.
But when it comes to [em1]someone you miss[/em1], any keepsake from them would be precious.
If one can at least keep the portrait of [em1]a loved one who's deceased[/em1],
it may help them cope with the loss.
If you want such a portrait, please contact me. I'll introduce a good painter to you.
This letter is about [em1]portraits[/em1].
Mr. Brad is a patron of painters, you know...
Aha... There's one letter to go. Let's read this one too.
I recently received a gift — it's an extremely rare ancient book.
But that's not my point. Instead of the book, it's the [em1]packaging[/em1] that impressed me.
We usually wrap the card in the packaging with the gift, right? But the card of this gift was hanging from the packaging.
On the card was a quote from a myth about hyacinth.
What a curious way to convey the sender's feelings.
Since you were wondering [em1]how to pack items[/em1], how about trying this style?
This letter is about [em1]packaging[/em1].
Brad often exchanges gifts with people.
Hmm... These alone are not enough clues.
Arin, Rex, what do you think?
Hmm... I can only conclude that the letters are about topics they discussed before.
Beats me too. How are we supposed to know what others talk about in private?
Hmm... Arin, can I borrow these letters?
Did anything dawn on you?
I'll ask someone who may know! And look for the recipients on my way.
Thank you, Ellie. I'll leave it to you.
Damn... There's no room for me to shine.
Heh, I'll find the recipients. Just you wait.
Okay, we'll reread the [em1]letters[/em1] if we don't know what to do. And we'll ask the [em1]villagers[/em1] too.
Which letter shall I show her?
Mr. Brad also used a cane. He has good mobility, but he's attractive with a cane.
This letter should be for a fellow cane enthusiast... Maybe this person also wants to be [em1]stylish[/em1]?
Elder members of the Eastchips — which is Rex's family — usually have portraits drawn. Maybe they were once in a same portrait.
I heard that people who have [em1]family members[/em1] and are affluent usually have portraits drawn.
I only wrap books to preserve them... That's it.
Sending gifts isn't part of the work at the library either.
Many people have portraits painted as an act of self-importance.
If you want such a portrait, please contact me. I'll introduce a suitable painter to you.
Alright, I've found all the recipients.
Let's get back to [em1]Arin[/em1].
Arin! Do you know what language this is?
Hmm... It's the language used on the Eastern Continent.
Many folklore and legends are written in it... I spent a long time gathering them.
Rex is a big fan of those hero stories.
Really? Can you read this?
Well... If there aren't too many uncommon words. Do you need me to translate all of it?
Er... That'd be great, but first of all... Wait...
Oh! Firstly, please look for any text that mentions a [em1]hair tie[/em1].
Alright, on it...
Ah... This looks like a [em1]diary[/em1]. May I know who the owner is...?
Well... It seems to be Arden's late partner...
I've asked Arden, and he's given permission!
So... you need to know what's said in here. I'll try.
Yeah... This really is a diary.
It doesn't follow a strict format. Some entries are dated, while others aren't. She probably wasn't bothered by trivial matters.
And by the look of the dates, she didn't write every day...
You want to learn about a hair tie? Just a second...
Here it is. A [em1]green ribbon[/em1] with a [em1]silver gemstone[/em1]... It was a birthday gift she received.
This keyword appears a lot. She mentioned it frequently.
And in the last part, oh... well.
What's it?
You'd better read this part yourself...
Could you give me a minute?
I don't know if it will help... but I've translated the dated entries first.
They seem to have some significance.
Whoa, thank you!
Hmm, is this the last page?
You said that this was Arden's late partner...?
Are you looking for something? I hope this will help.
I don't know what happened, but I sort of understand how it feels like...
to not want to part with my loved ones.
Ah, am I babbling too much... sorry.
The hair tie... was mentioned on [em1]May 4[/em1].
There's no need to apologize. You're a great help! You've found me clues!
Back to the journal now.
First, content on the [em1]hair tie[/em1] Arden received in his dreams.
Arin said it was mentioned on [em1]May 4[/em1]? I'll read the [em1]adjacent[/em1] entries too.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DiaryOfBrave_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Hello, Arin.
Seems like she's lost in thought.
Ah...! Ellie?
When... when did you get here?
Just now!
I... I'm sorry. My mind must have wandered somewhere else.
You were bowing your head like that... What were you thinking about?
Ah, I was... reading a book.
Ah! I see a book in your apron. What book is it?
Well... do you know anything about [em1]enchanted books[/em1]?
[em1]Enchanted books[/em1]? That's my specialty!
Of course... since you're a witch.
We shouldn't talk about that book from last year, the one where all the letters on it vanished... right?
Don't worry, Arin. There hasn't been a single letter disappearance since then.
Really...? Then would you take a look at this book for me?
Shouldn't be a problem.
Hmm... hmm... hmm...!
What's wrong? Is your instinct refusing to open it?
I'm just examining the book from the outside first.
Look at this. From the spine to the corners, it feels like they used extremely high-quality materials, completely seamless.
I can see it. Even the decorations carved into it give a sense of something special.
Exactly. Even the paper inside looks like soft silk...
Huh? Eh...?
Arin, this book... won't open.
Yes... That's the problem.
Rex even tried opening it with strength... but ordinary force couldn't do it.
A book you can't open... sounds like it's sealed with magic.
The author... is a witch named [em1]Parks[/em1]. Do you know him?
There's a small engraving at the bottom of the back cover of the book.
I see. Is there no surname?
If [em1]Parks[/em1] is a witch, knowing the surname would help identify him precisely.
I'm afraid only the first name is written.
...Then, do you remember the [em1]Book of Stars[/em1] that Rex and I have been searching for?
You mean the one said to grant any wish?
Yes. Parks was a witch who searched for the Book of Stars before us.
She left a lot of writings and clues related to the Book of Stars...
But this is the first time we've found something recorded in book form.
So this book could be a crucial clue for you.
It might help you in some way with what you two are doing.
If you're not too busy... could you help me?
This book is essential for finding the Book of Stars.
Exactly...
I'll look into a potion that can break the book's seal.
It might take a little time to make the potion. Can you wait?
Waiting isn't a problem... thank you.
I'd love to, but... I have other things to do.
I see... that's fine.
Come by anytime when you're not busy.
Ellie, I don't think I can break the seal on this [em1]enchanted book[/em1] on my own...
The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1] is ready, so let's go break the book's seal.
Arin! You've been waiting long, right?
You didn't have too much trouble... because of me, did you?
Trouble? Not at all! I'm just as curious about a sealed book as you are.
Just place the book on the ground.
I brought a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1], it should be able to open the book.
Then... what should I do?
Don't worry. It won't damage the book.
Understood.
The opening ceremony is now concluded.
It's more interesting than I expected...
Right? But it seems like the book itself hasn't changed.
Did you use the wrong method to break the seal again?
But the book clearly said to prove that we're [em1]new students[/em1] of the School for Witches.
No, Ellie, the book...
Something... is happening!?
Maybe the book didn't see the dance the freshmen performed. The book has no eyes, after all.
Just like what happened after using the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1]... Nothing.
Then just repeat after me, and follow the next steps.
Easy, right?
Let's begin.
We pursue learning with the burning passion of the sun.
We communicate and unite, like a comet in flight.
We understand everything, like water flowing under the moon.
We embrace all, like our land, and grow together.
Give Arin [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EnduranceUpCandy_Name"))][/em1]?
Arin, I brought [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EnduranceUpCandy_Name"))][/em1]. Let's dance together!
Dance...? Wasn't this supposed to be a ceremony?
Actually, it's not really dancing. Just walking around in a circle.
I'm... ready.
I... I'm not so sure.
Just eat the candy and follow me. Even the younger freshmen do it.
Ellie, do you remember all the steps?
Of course. I've memorized them to teach the new students every year.
Now! Let's start!
L-Let's... start...
You don't have to repeat that.
Oops! I forgot about the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EnduranceUpCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Arin and I each need one, so I should grab two.
I... [em1]Awakened<shake><font="Astronomicon SDF">'</font></shake>[/em1]. [em1]Awakened<shake><font="Astronomicon SDF">'</font></shake>[/em1]. [em1]Awakened<shake><font="Astronomicon SDF">'</font></shake>[/em1]. [em1]Awakened<shake><font="Astronomicon SDF">'</font></shake>[/em1].
The book... It's speaking, isn't it?
I... [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">?@</font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">#</font>[/em1] to [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>[/em1].
As the silent guardian... it allows only the [em1]worthy[/em1]... to hear.
Arin, you understand this right away?
I-I'm barely keeping up...
I... [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">?</font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">U</font>[/em1].
It grants the [em1]power to break the silence...[/em1].
To think... I have met a witch who understands my words...
Since my awakening, it is the first time.
A witch... the first ever... established by witches...
Suddenly asking questions now?
You... [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">[</font>[/em1]. If [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">?</font>[/em1], I will [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">?</font>[/em1].
Looks like the book's "eyes" are closing already.
Ah, ah!
Highlion!
N-No! Lucerine Ortu.
Stay focused, Ellie. If you answer wrong, the book will fall asleep again.
Answering on your behalf...? The answer is correct at least.
Then, the witch who awakened me... is it truly you, with hair silver as moonlight, radiant enough to make even the moon jealous?
...Me?
With eyes like an unfathomable lake, hiding endless curiosity, you...
Have awakened me.
Uh... I did awaken you, but not alone...
I am the Silent Guardian. Only truth is just; falsehood must remain silent.
Witch who seeks the hidden truths beneath the surface... What truth do you seek, and what lies must remain silent?
Oh... Mr. Book... Silent Guardian, before that...
You speak with respect, continue.
The one who awakened you... Is the witch named Ellie, standing beside me.
Yes. I woke you.
To be precise, we performed the school ritual together, Arin and I.
Impossible... your form does not convey the intellect to understand me.
Yet, do not despair at my words.
The passion in your eyes will bloom like weeds, no matter how trampled.
Virgil... I think this book has a worse personality than you.
I, guardian of the mind, agree with the words of the guardian of silence.
Yes. You, who stand on the edge of a great witch, have succeeded in awakening me.
How long do we have to endure this?
Arin, the book seems more interested in talking to you than me. Don't you want to ask it something?
Then... I will speak to the Silent Guardian.
The one who created you, [em1]Parks[/em1]... what truths were you instructed to protect, and when were you commanded to remain silent?
A pointed question...
But I cannot answer. To reach the truth...
Then... what must I do?
[em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>[/em1] must [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">K</font>[/em1]. To [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">T</font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">K</font>[/em1]. That's [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">¶</font>[/em1].
Arin, what is it saying now? I still can't understand.
I... I don't know. I've never heard anything like this...
It seems like a... language.
It refuses to be understood, huh? Truly a nasty book.
I guess... We'll have to translate and decode its words.
Look, the [em1]front pages[/em1] have unfolded so we can read them.
I see. I guess the book opens little by little as we understand its words.
Ellie, if you don't mind... Let me research a bit more.
And we can continue working on it... Would that be okay?
Of course. I'm curious too why Parks made such a cantankerous, difficult book.
Thank you...
Then let me know when you're ready to speak to the [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1] again.
Got it. Thank you for your help, Ellie.
Lucerine Ortu!
I... I can almost hear it in my mind.
You must [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">g</font>[/em1] [em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">[</font>[/em1].
It's asking... the first [em1]city built by witches[/em1].
If I do not answer... it will close its eyes and remain silent forever.
Arin, what first time are you talking about...?
Meeting someone who understands its words... It says it's the first time since it was created.
I see. Are you the [em1]child awakened by starlight[/em1], invited for this ritual?
Huh? I'm not a freshman. I'm a witch about to be fully initiated.
I thought we agreed to call that an apprentice witch.
Congratulations on beginning the great task of understanding me.
To read me, you must gather [em1]more languages and truths about people[/em1].
Virgil, want to be sealed next?
Your teal eyes hold the innocence and purity of freshly sprouted leaves.
Leaves? You mean weeds?
Come, Arin. Just follow me.
After we sprinkled the potion... it feels like something tried to happen, but then stopped.
I see. Looks like the seal wasn't broken after all.
We should tell Diane that the potion didn't work.
The book... still won't open.
But... some symbols appeared on the cover that weren't there before.
[em1]<font="Astronomicon SDF">'</font>[/em1]...
Huh? What did you just say, Arin...
Ellie... you're a witch, so you understand, right?
You're reading ancient witch language right now, aren't you?
Yes... I read what's written on the cover.
Did I... pronounce it correctly?
I only understood the word "school"...
So the text on the cover basically says, [em1]"act according to what you've learned at school."[/em1]
Arin! That's something only someone who went to School for Witches could figure out. Amazing!
I've never heard of anyone self-studying ancient witch language with that proficiency.
Really...?
Even for an ordinary human to be able to read that much text in ancient witch language would shock the Witch Association.
I'm trying to study and translate different languages...
Virgil, it's good she can read it. Why the doubt?
So, Arin, you can actually interpret it too, right?
The rest of the sentence... I can't read it yet. Too many unknown words.
But if I knew some of the words, I could.
Then I'll try reading the words I know first.
Potion, ritual, performed in front, starlight... I don't know the rest.
Then... it probably says something like... "There is no magical potion to open this book. Any attempt at a seal-breaking ritual is [em1]powerless[/em1] in my presence."
"The first page will only be revealed before the [em1]child awakened by starlight[/em1]."
[em1]Child awakened by starlight[/em1]...?
Does that word have... some special meaning?
That's what they call a [em1]freshman[/em1] just admitted to the School for Witches!
They undergo a ceremony at the entrance and officially become students.
Then... only a freshman can open this book?
Freshman? Outside the school, no freshman is called a child awakened by starlight.
Then... there should be freshmen at the school. Maybe we could show the book to them?
No! If we send the book to the school, it'll be years before they return it under the excuse of "examining" it.
Then... What kind of ritual did they perform?
A ritual? It's simple. Eat a sour candy, repeat what you're told, and that's about it.
Oh! Should we try it together?
The preparation is simple too. All we need is [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EnduranceUpCandy_Name"))][/em1].
So... we're tricking the book by showing it what freshmen at the School for Witches do?
Exactly. I thought it would be fun for you to do it too.
Think of it as... experiencing it firsthand!
But... I'm not even a witch. Is it really okay for me to perform the ritual?
Wouldn't we need the school's permission... or follow some kind of witches' rules...?
<wave>Don't mind that.</wave> What's the harm? We're not doing anything wrong.
...Alright. I'll do it.
Perfect! I'll go get the candy right away.
Why don't we pour the whole bottle of potion first and see what happens?
But... what effect does the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1] actually have?
Diane is the witch administration officer who recommended it.
She said the book is sealed with powerful magic, and this potion should weaken that force.
Fascinating... So, witches share knowledge about potions that way.
How about we get started already? Don't you want to see if the potion works?
I was just about to.
Haha. It's not like witches know every potion, after all.
Alright then, I'll pour the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1] onto the book.
Arin! How's the translation going?
Ah... you're here. I was just debating if I should contact you.
I thought I'd reach out after digging through more sources, but... I've hit a wall.
Then I showed up right when you needed me.
Ellie, do you happen to know what these words mean?
[<font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>] takes [<font="Astronomicon SDF">U</font>] [<font="Astronomicon SDF">+</font>].
[<font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>] takes [<font="Astronomicon SDF">F</font>] [<font="Astronomicon SDF">,</font>].
Heh. Sorry, no clue.
Do you have to sound so cheerful about that?
What can I do if I don't know?
Look at this. Aside from [[em1]Give Up<font="Astronomicon SDF">+</font>[/em1]] and [[em1]Promise<font="Astronomicon SDF">,</font>[/em1]], I can't read a single character.
Ellie, did you just say [em1]Give Up[/em1] and [em1]Promise[/em1]?
Yeah. I've seen these symbols of ancient witch language over and over in history books.
I see... it's only a hunch, but...
Thinking about what I've translated so far... Silent Guardian seems to be a book about history.
Which makes me wonder... do you know any witches who are well-versed in history?
There's a history teacher at the school...
But, she's always busy, constantly running off to research something.
I see... too bad.
If it's a researcher you need, don't you already know one?
Huh? <wave>What?</wave> <shake>Ahhhh!</shake>
Kent! Kent could definitely help us!
Kent...? Who's that?
He's a public official who goes around villages doing population surveys.
The first time I met him, he was gathering information on Wisteria. So he probably knows plenty about history too.
Then... This may sound a bit abrupt. I'd like to ask Kent for help.
Would you reach out to him for me?
Of course! I was about to suggest contacting him myself.
I already have his address, so sending a letter won't be a problem.
Kent's always traveling. Who knows when he'll even get your letter?
Well... you're right.
But maybe Diane could help.
Kent works with the witch administration, so she'd know how to reach him quickly.
Then I'll leave the letter to you, Ellie.
And I'll put [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1] on the library shelf so you can read it too.
Got it. I'll make sure to read it.
Arin, could you wait a little longer? I have something else to take care of first.
Since I'm the one asking for help... I can wait as long as you need.
Just let me know when you're ready.
I'd really like to continue the translation work...
Kent replied sooner than I expected.
Well, he's used to gathering info from every village under the sun. This is right up his alley.
True. Arin's going to love this.
Look at this! He even sent along piles of research notes with his letter.
Wait... Did I just forget Kent's [em1]letter[/em1]?
Pull yourself together, Ellie. Arin needs that letter and the research notes that came along with it.
Arin, Kent sent us both his research and a reply.
Yes, he did... These notes are incredible.
They contain such a clear breakdown of the ancient witch language.
Does that mean you can pick up the translation again?
Yes. For example... There are two words for "witch": [Witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>] and [Witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>].
That clears up so many confusing passages. I'll annotate them all.
It suddenly feels like I'm back in school.
So... you've realized [Witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>] is the witch of the past, while [Witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>] names the living witch of the present.
Whoa! Where'd that voice come from?
And I'm not even holding the book! How are you talking to us?
At least while you're in this town, my voice will always reach you. Fear not.
The power of magic... It's truly astonishing.
And yet, while you weave far greater works, you marvel at such a trivial wonder. Almost charming, in its smallness.
Well... I'm no witch. I rarely experience things like this at all.
Silent Guardian... are you, in fact, a history book?
A book exists to be read. What I am depends on the one who reads me.
That's just a cryptic way of saying "figure it out yourself."
I only hope your efforts will surpass my pride soon.
Ha! Count on it! I may hate books, but I'm unbeatable at quizzes.
That's one way of hypnotizing yourself.
Still, thanks to Kent's notes, I think I can translate a few more pages without trouble.
I've even spotted plenty of new glyphs.
I'll translate what I can right away.
And, [em1]mark[/em1] any particularly useful symbols so they stand out.
Those same symbols may appear in [em1]untranslated pages[/em1] as well... so be sure to watch out for them.
Got it! Let's try our best.
Whew... translation is a lot harder than I thought.
Any work takes time to get familiar with.
But you've been doing this for a long time, right, Arin? Must be second nature by now.
Being familiar with it... doesn't mean it's easy. That's the frustrating part.
Arin! I did it!
I think I've finally deciphered the last of the pages!
I thought you but a frivolous apprentice witch...
Yet, are you born with boundless curiosity and resolve?
Hehe, thanks for the compliment.
But hey, why are you called the Silent Guardian anyway?
Do you think reading mere words upon a page means you've grasped their meaning?
Ah... this is some kind of a ritual.
When the sun glows endlessly upon the sea...
...the mystery of magic reaches out to you.
As expected, you remembered.
Of course. That was the last ritual I performed.
Then prove yourself once more.
Arin, this is the ritual apprentice witches perform before leaving the school.
It only needs simple materials: [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1] and five textbooks.
Textbooks... what are they for?
We throw them behind us with all our strength!
...Excuse me?
It means we've mastered everything in them.
And, we'll never need them again once we've graduated.
I... suppose that makes sense?
I left my textbooks at school... So, let's use whatever books we have.
Finding books we can throw... that's quite the task.
But I'll do my best to prepare.
Strange... nothing in the text explains your name.
As expected... You never fail to impress.
Why would a student ever...?
How many times must I tell you? Answers must be found, not asked.
Give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1] to Arin?
Ta-da! I've made the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1]!
Doing this ritual with you almost makes me feel like I'm becoming a witch in school myself.
It would've been fun if you'd attended the School of Witches too.
Anyway! Shall we throw the books? Let's pretend we're back at school!
You just want to throw books, don't you?
Arin, I'll make the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1]. Just gather about five books.
Five will be enough?
Yep. Seventh-years had exactly five textbooks.
And this library is overflowing with books. There should be plenty of books we can throw away.
Do you realize the librarian can hear you?
Oops! I forgot to bring the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1].
We'll need 2x [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1]. One for me, one for Arin.
If I had gone to the School for Witches with you, I think we'd have shared so many memories.
But I've never set foot in one, so it's hard to picture.
All the work we're doing now is practically the same as the lessons I had in school anyway.
And the ritual's no different than before. Should be easy enough.
As moonlight colors the darkest night...
...so too does the essence of magic flow into you.
That's... great.
Exactly. Let's begin.
Hah, it's easy!
Now it's your turn, Arin. Once you eat the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MuscleUpCandy_Name"))][/em1], you'll be strong enough to fling books like feathers.
It might be even easier than last time.
Nice work, Ellie. Not even an enemy could be thrown that far.
Forgive me, books... but I'll try.
My hand slipped. I’ll do it again.
Is it... Okay to damage books like this?
What? Didn't you pick out books we could throw?
Such books don't exist... I only chose the sturdiest ones...
Arin! If you want to be a true witch, you must throw without hesitation!
Some master witches even toss apprentices off cliffs!
What... really?
No, the right answer was "that's insane."
Would it... be okay if I switched books?
Sure. Do you need a minute?
N-no... I'll do it.
There... I did it too.
Is it normal for this ritual to leave your heart pounding so hard?
Nope. No one's ever said that.
But wow, you're strong! Must be from all the things you do in the adventure party.
Must I ask whether you intend to keep chatting or resume?
Hey, Mr. Book, would you stop popping in like that?
After the war between witches and humans ended, peace returned. Just as you've read from me.
Tsk. Ignoring me now?
But... is the seal on you finally broken now?
No one has ever spoken of where this task ends.
So there's more?
You're worse than Professor Lewis!
Ellie... another page has appeared.
If you dislike a path with no end in sight, you may turn back anytime.
No way! Not knowing what's next is half the fun.
Indeed... my judgment was not mistaken.
This new page... the word Heblin appears again and again.
I don't know who, but it seems tied to a family's story.
If it's a witch's surname, then the SilverRains must be a major house—enough to appear in history books.
Should we ask Kent again? He also did some research on the Whitegarden family.
And he did say he was curious about how our work was going.
I see... Yes. We should ask him once more.
Alright. I'll go ask Diane to send another letter.
A pleasure to meet you. My name is Kent.
Thank you. I'm Arin, the librarian.
Heh. Thanks to you, I've gathered fascinating stories and information.
What kind of stories, Kent?
You're undertaking quite an unusual project.
First, I investigated the author of the Silent Guardian. It was a witch named [em1]Parks[/em1].
His full name was [em1]Pax SilverRain[/em1].
SilverRain! The Pax SilverRain?
Do you... know him?
I knew I'd seen it before! He's the one who wrote our textbooks!
Indeed. For a brief time, Parks also served as a professor at the school, known as the Witch of Books.
Wow... So, the creator of Silent Guardian was one of our own. Amazing.
Not only that. He was also a brilliant cryptographer and found the ancient relic known as the [em1]Book of Stars[/em1].
He accomplished... quite a lot.
Yes. And now that I know his name, I've been able to gather much more material.
But before I share it... May I ask a question?
You've already helped us so much. Please, go ahead.
Thank you. Then I'll be blunt.
Uh...?
There's meaning even in asking this. But you don't have to answer.
...Yes. My name is [em1]Arin SilverRain[/em1].
Wait, what!? Arin, what does that mean?
Your surname's the same as Parks'... but you're just a normal person...
Ellie, my father was Pax SilverRain. But my mother was...
A human. So you are indeed a [em1]half-blood[/em1]. Heh...
You knew the book's secret, didn't you?
...I never meant to deceive you. I just... needed to be sure.
I'm sorry, Ellie, for hiding my true name while asking for your help.
No, Arin. I understand.
Honestly, I've never met a half-blood before. It's amazing.
Now that I know this, I can uncover far more material.
If you'll allow me, may I examine the book as well?
Of course. Right, Arin?
Yes... I'll set it out so we can all read it together.
Funny how you never studied your textbooks, but you remember every word of this.
Hey! I skimmed them before tossing them at the ritual.
So, Arin, is your surname [em1]SilverRain[/em1]?
Wow... that means Arin's been translating her own father's book.
Heh... so this is the Silent Guardian.
Usually, when it's opened, it speaks of the page it reveals...
But nothing this time. Shy, maybe?
[Silence <font="Astronomicon SDF">?</font>]. [Witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">R</font>]. [Worthy<font="Astronomicon SDF">t</font>].
It says... someone not worthy stands here.
Ah, so the book won't speak to me.
That's too bad, Kent. This book's the strangest talking creature I've ever met.
Am I only in second place now?
It's fine. I only wished to see what it looks like.
May I stay in touch about this matter?
You've been a great help... I'd be glad if you do.
One more thing: I've heard... though it's uncertain...
Pax SilverRain was once part of a group tied to the old [em1]war[/em1].
The war... the one between witches and humans?
Yes. I'll need to confirm it, but I thought it was worth telling you now.
Then I'll take my leave. You should expect a letter soon.
Thanks to an unworthy helper, you've gained some sort of a clue to the translation.
Well? Young witch. Are you ready to read me yet?
I'm always ready!
Then, witch and her assistant, come... Read me. The final page awaits.
Yes! It feels like we're finally nearing the end.
Let's sprint to the finish line.
If you ever manage to read the final page, please tell me.
Arin... I did it. I managed to read the last sentence.
That's wonderful news. But... why do you look so troubled?
Because... I think you should see this part too.
Perhaps you're right. I can feel the Silent Guardian reaching out to me already.
William SilverRain met a sudden [death<font="Astronomicon SDF">L</font>]...
Those who hunted the [Dreamers <font="Astronomicon SDF">B</font> of Eternity <font="Astronomicon SDF">z</font>]... claimed William SilverRain was among the group.
Ellie... You said you've never learned this before, correct?
Yes... This definitely isn't in the textbooks.
I've always wondered what kind of man my father really was.
All I ever heard was that he loved books, was meticulous and considerate... and was a good witch.
Arin...
But the truth... turned out very different.
He only wrote and sealed this book to hide a shameful past.
Didn't Parks say the book was sealed before the truth was revealed?
If we try to uncover the truth again, we might find other hidden stories.
What more... could I possibly learn?
The truth is this... My grandfather branded a villain, and my father sealed history to hide it.
And a half-blood like me left as their legacy.
But... maybe your grandfather wasn't really the criminal the book describes.
Even if that's the truth... I don't have the courage to face it now.
This is... harder than I imagined.
Silent Guardian! Is there nothing more after this?
This can't really be the end, can it?
Young witch... it seems your assistant has lost the will to explore me.
Thus, I have nothing further to show. If you wish, I will return to silence.
How... irresponsible.
Yes, this must truly be my father's work.
My mother... She left the city for the countryside, suffering her whole life.
For the greater cause, sacrifice is sometimes required.
Afraid to even write down whether he was the one who started a war... and you call that the greater cause?
B-but, Arin... We uncovered so much that isn't in any history book.
That means what we've done together truly mattered.
And besides... This was the first time I ever felt like I was adventuring while reading a book!
That much... I can admit. It had meaning.
There's no way this is really the end!
So... so... um...
Why don't you take a breath? You're not ready to stop. You just need time.
Y-yes! That's exactly what I meant to say.
Anyone would feel shaken after all this.
But if you still want to go on, Arin...
...Thank you, Ellie.
I don't want to be a coward either.
But for now...
I'll wait as long as it takes. When you're ready, just tell me.
Would it be alright... if I put the book out of sight for now?
Of course. It's your book! Do as your heart tells you.
Thank you, Ellie... Then... let's wrap things up for today.
I will always be there for you!
For reasons I'll never know... my mother rarely spoke of my father.
He wanted us to live quietly in the countryside. But... it was all just so he could create this book...
Which page should I look at?
1) The Witch and Mankind
According to legend, the [witches <font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>] once became [stars <font="Astronomicon SDF">S</font>] before returning to this world.
