H-hello.
Ellie... I have something to tell you.
Rex has been the only friend I have.
I struggle to make friends, probably due to my personality and the environment I am in...
You've been nice to someone like me, Ellie.
This means a lot to me... as if I've made a new friend.
No, not "as if." you are my friend, Ellie.
Please take this. Thank you.
Ellie... could you listen for a moment?
Suddenly, I found myself reflecting on it.
The things Ellie has done for me.
Except for Rex... no one has ever cared for me this much before.
So... I sincerely want to repay you.
Would you accept it?
And... I look forward to your continued support.
Ellie… do you have a moment?
Arin? Sure, what is it?
Do you remember the book you once asked me to translate?
Oh, you mean Lisa’s book?
Yes… that’s right.
I remember. It was about thorny vines, wasn’t it…?
There was a book about thorny vines, another about synthesizing plants, and one about immortality.
But Ellie… why are you planning to go to [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]?
Of course, to clear away the thorny vines in the village.
And also to look for Lisa.
Yes… I…
I’ll put my trust in you, Ellie.
Actually, among the books I received back then, some parts were [em1]already translated[/em1] before I worked on them.
And in those translated passages, there was one line about a [em1]“Fallen Star.”[/em1]
If it was already translated, then maybe Lisa had seen it.
And by “Fallen Star,” do you mean [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]?
Yes, probably. The line was [em1]“At the Fallen Star, you can obtain anything.”[/em1]
That means…?
This word “anything” can take on many meanings depending on translation.
The most common is simply “anything,” but…
It can also mean energy or life—in other words, [em1]“eternal life.”[/em1]
Eternal life…
Wait, then the sentence becomes [em1]“At the Fallen Star, you can obtain eternal life!”[/em1]
Then Lisa is in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]…
It’s only speculation, just one possible interpretation.
As I said earlier, there’s much we don’t know about [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
Please be careful.
I understand. Thank you, Arin.
I’ll be careful, I promise.
Shortly after I moved here, you asked me to help translate a book.
It was a book written by someone who used to live here, Lisa Whitegarden.
Arin, do you remember the flag I carried during the parade?
Yes, I remember.
Did you ever borrow that flag?
Yes, I had it until not long ago.
Until recently? Then you don't have it now?
That's right. Someone else asked to borrow it... So, I no longer have it.
Do you remember who that was?
I think I lent it to [em1]Vinch[/em1]...
Alright. Then I'll have to go see [em1]Vinch[/em1].
Thanks for telling me.
No problem.
Yes, what... is it?
That parade flag... Did you get it from Rex?
Yes, that's right.
I borrowed it from Rex and then passed it on to Vinch.
Why do you ask...?
Ellie...?
Hold on a moment. Her mind is still loading.
O-okay... I understand now.
Virgil, I feel <shake>incredibly</shake> confused right now.
That's perfectly normal.
It's the information you've heard so far that isn't.
I need time to sort my thoughts.
Let's move somewhere else for now.
Arin. Do you know which books Clala borrowed?
Clala?
Yes. She's been quite busy, so I offered to get the books for her.
I see... There are ten in total. Can you carry them all?
What? Ten?!
There's no space in my bag. I'll have to empty it first.
I recommended books that could help with her work... and she said she wanted to borrow them all.
How about splitting them into more batches?
You might not believe it, but I'm actually strong. I can manage.
Come to think of it... Clala seems very diligent.
I get it.
She told me she plans her entire day out in advance.
Even her reading time is scheduled. Unlike me... I just read when I feel like it. It made me reflect a bit.
Really? She's more methodical than I thought.
She said she feels at ease only when she follows steps and recipes, just like baking.
Even from the titles, you can tell they're all work-related.
"In Search of the Legendary Bread," "The Complete Guide to Growing a Shop," "Miscella and the Toy House"...
Huh? What's [em1]"Miscella and the Toy House"[/em1]?
That book... contains illustrations and descriptions of dolls from a famous doll workshop.
So it's work-related too? Maybe she plans to decorate her shop with dolls.
I didn't recommend that one... but if it's in the stack, then she must have intended to borrow it.
I see. I just asked because I feel like I've heard the name [em1]Miscella[/em1] somewhere before.
I'll have to ask Clala about it.
Yes... I don't really know who that is.
Let’s come [em1]when Arin is at the library[/em1].
Ellie? What's wrong?
Arin, do you know anything about this plant?
Ah... this is the one I told Rex about. I received a commission about it.
Actually, Theo was the one who mentioned it to me. I've been looking for it since then.
If you use it that way... the sweetness seeps inward and lingers in the fibers.
It's different from sugar. More of a faint sweetness.
There's a book that mentions this herb... I'll track it down.
In the meantime... Maybe we should [em1]check[/em1] on the Honey Bear?
But how did Theo even know about this plant?
Uh... Well... The thing is...
Oh, just tell her! Theo overheard that.
Hey! You didn't have to spill it all like that!
Rex said he felt someone sneaking around...
So, it was Theo after all.
That herb is called [em1]Sweetleaf[/em1]. Usually, it's boiled, dried, and ground into powder before use.
What happens if you just eat it raw?
It would be [em1]poisonous[/em1]...
Whatever the recipe, it always has to be boiled first.
[em1]Poison?![/em1] But the honeybear ate it and seemed fine!
Some poisons... take time before their effects appear.
What?! Really?!
Okay. Be back in a second!
Ellie is... like that too...
So, you came here with Theo.
Arin, you were right. The herb really is [em1]poisonous[/em1]!
Well, well... the infamous troublemakers who keep turning this village upside down have all gathered.
If it's the book you seek, I have it right here.
Alvin? Why are you holding that book?
Because that sweet-tasting herb you've been chasing, [em1]Sweetleaf[/em1], was the ingredient I asked Arin and Rex to find for me.
That plant isn't just a food additive. It's used in medicine as well.
<shake>Forget that!</shake> We need to find an [em1]antidote[/em1], fast!
Oh! Right! This isn't the time to stand around!
As it happens... Alvin and I already looked into an [em1]antidote[/em1].
Really? What ingredients do we need? I'll gather them right away!
Sadly, it's [em1]not that simple.[/em1]
What? Why not?!
Most of them grow nearby, that's true.
The problem is with the [em1]rare ones we can't find here[/em1].
Come on, Alvin! You run a sundries store! Can't you just source them from somewhere else?
That too is difficult. Hardly anyone ever asks for them, so they're scarce even in trade.
So... there's really no way?
<shake>Liar! That can't be true!</shake>
Reality is harsh, boy. You're still young. You don't understand yet...
<shake>Don't give me that!</shake> Just because I'm young doesn't mean I don't get it!
Forget it! I'll handle this myself! I'll find the antidote on my own!
Hey! Wait! Theo!
He bolted with the book in hand.
That's the thing with side characters' lines. You only grasp their true meaning if you hear them through to the end.
Alvin, what do you mean by that?
The antidote can be substituted with [em1]other ingredients[/em1].
Not flawless, but it will keep the worst at bay.
What kind of ingredients? I'll get them right now!
[em1]Cleansing Herb[/em1] and [em1]Glowpetal Bloom[/em1].
Both grow in the area, but they're [em1]difficult to harvest.[/em1]
Best ask [em1]Enite[/em1]. She knows this land inside out.
Good idea. I should also reassure Theo later so he doesn't worry himself sick.
Ellie... you really go out of your way for Theo, don't you?
Huh? Arin, what do you mean?
Honestly... I don't like Theo very much.
He once flung Rex off a couch with some prank.
Rex laughed it off as childish mischief... but still.
Lately, his pranks have only been getting worse.
And yet... he [em1]never takes responsibility[/em1].
So, why do you keep helping him? What's your [em1]reason[/em1]?
Yeah... I get it.
He's a real brat right now. Snapping, sulking, throwing fits...
But Enite once told me...
She, too, was nothing but trouble as a kid, until she grew up enough to realize and change.
That doesn't always happen... Some people never change, no matter how much time passes.
Theo could be like that. Do you really believe he'll change?
He might not. Maybe he'll stay exactly the same.
But I still believe he'll change someday. Because... so did I!
I might not look it, but back at school, I was notorious. I broke every rule, went everywhere I wasn't supposed to.
I could talk all day about the messes I caused!
But since coming to this village, I've met people and faced trials.
I think I've changed, at least compared to back then.
Looking back, my family, teachers, friends... even when I caused trouble, they stayed by me.
That's the only reason I'm still here now.
And Theo has [em1]us[/em1] by his side, doesn't he?
I want to be that kind of person too—to support someone the way others supported me.
You make it sound noble, but honestly, you haven't changed all that much.
Anyone who saw the prank you pulled in the last village would agree.
...Virgil, can you not ruin the moment when I'm trying to sound inspiring?
Even so, that was a fine speech. It deserves some applause.
Alvin, when you say it like that, it just sounds like teasing.
...Heh.
So that's why you stay at Theo's side... I understand now.
Thanks for answering me, even when you're busy. I'll keep searching for another solution too.
Yeah! Thanks, both of you! I'll head over to [em1]Enite[/em1] right away!
Arin, when should we start the [em1]witch graduation ceremony[/em1]?
Right, everything seems ready. Shall we begin?
Arin, you’re ready too, right?
Then let's hold the ceremony together!
I'll be back later.
Oh, it has to take place at night.
Should I wait with Arin until night falls?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Together_Yes"))]
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Together_No"))]
I didn't bring the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirstGraduationCeremonyForm_Name"))][/em1] or the [em1][lua(GetItemName("FirecrackerPotion"))][/em1]. I should go get them.
Perfect timing... I just finished preparing all the graduation certificates.
I referenced the books the witches wrote when making them, but... I've got a question. Mind if I ask?
If everyone writes just one more line on their own graduation certificate, we'll be ready to start.
Of course. What is that?
Each graduation certificate has a space where the witch writes [em1]what kind of witch they are[/em1]... am I right?
That's right. It can be filled by either the parents or the witch themselves.
Even though these are just fake certificates for reenacting the ceremony... I feel like they should be made with sincerity.
That's what I thought... I'm thinking of writing down what my mother once told me.
I'll prepare the graduation certificates.
Please handle the rest.
Other than what's written on the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirstGraduationCeremonyForm_Name"))][/em1], we just need someone to keep watch over the village.
Alright. I've made the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))].
Let's tell Diane that all the preparations are done!
Let's wrap up the rest, too.
Diane! I made the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1].
I've gathered everything we need. We can begin the graduation ceremony anytime.
Ellie, your initiative is remarkable. I didn't think you'd complete the prep work so quickly.
So then, when do you plan to begin?
Since you're ready too, Diane, I think we just need to check with Arin.
I'm sure Arin's ready by now as well.
Very well. Once you're ready, we can start.
Everyone, allow me to introduce Diane, who will help us reenact the graduation ceremony.
Greetings, everyone! I'm Diane, from the Witch Administration. It's an honor to be part of such a meaningful event.
Alright, is everyone gathered?
Don't we have to do something too? Like dance or something? Hehe.
It would be nice if we could lend a hand while we're here.
Haha. Well then, shall we begin?
Yes!
Teacher! Arden isn't here. Hehe.
It's fine. Watching the ceremony is voluntary, so no pointing fingers, Theo.
Now then, everyone, today we even have a special guest here for the ceremony.
You both have the certificates and the items for the torch, right?
I, Diane, am a witch who treats everyone with kindness and enthusiasm.
Haha, there's nothing in particular. Everything is prepared, so all that's left is to enjoy the ceremony with us.
I would like to explain this to the villagers: a graduating witch must prove she is worthy.
That judgment falls to the magical torch before us.
Normally, one throws in items obtained during apprenticeship, but now you must also cast in your graduation certificate.
What...
If the torch deems you unworthy, the certificate will burn to ash.
It's only a fake certificate, so don't worry! It doesn't matter if it burns.
Still... It feels a little sad...
Now then, Ellie, you're next. Just toss it into the torch [em1]accurately[/em1], just like the way I did. You understand?
Wow... The torch burns with such strength.
What a waste, watching it burn away...
Dana, it's a sacred rite. I told you there's a reason for it.
That's right. To become a true witch, one must be ready for this.
So now Ellie and Arin both throw theirs, right?
That's right, Rubrum. Looks fun, doesn't it?
Alright then, I'll start.
I, Ellie, am a witch who always loves adventure and stands with pride.
I can feel it... the certificate burning within the torch.
That's an amusing way to put it. "Feel it burning."
Haha. Arin, you're sounding more and more like a witch yourself.
You've never attended the school, yet you've experienced everything, from admission to graduation.
You're right. If there were a next life... I'd wish to be born a witch.
Dreaming of a completely different life... That's a fine wish indeed. The best line of the day.
Was... it, really?
Then I want to be a witch too!
Me too, me too!
Becoming a witch isn't something one simply chooses.
More importantly, Ellie, the [em1]thing[/em1] you prepared. Launch it into the sky, and the ceremony will be complete.
Ah! Of course.
Some of you may have seen it before, others may be seeing it for the first time.
The one thing no witch festival is complete without: the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1]! Here it goes!
A place where [life <font="Astronomicon SDF">i</font>] dances endlessly, harmonizing with the [earth <font="Astronomicon SDF">Y</font>].
The source of [potions <font="Astronomicon SDF">u</font>].
Arin said the town fountain fits this description best, right?
Then we should ask [em1]Enite[/em1] if we can hold the graduation ceremony there.
Something special
Worthless in [daylight <font="Astronomicon SDF">Z</font>]. Can only be born from [death <font="Astronomicon SDF">L</font>].
The [spell <font="Astronomicon SDF">G</font>] of the [stars <font="Astronomicon SDF">S</font>] has taken root in this land.
According to this, we need to find someone to obtain the [em1]torch used in the first witch graduation ceremony[/em1].
Something edible
Outside [time <font="Astronomicon SDF">z</font>], composed solely of [desire <font="Astronomicon SDF">y</font>].
That shouldn't be too hard.
We just need someone to make a [em1]cold, tasty dish[/em1].
Information on paper
It can prove someone is a [witch <font="Astronomicon SDF">></font>], and shows they have the [power <font="Astronomicon SDF">U</font>].
Record your [history <font="Astronomicon SDF">§</font>] on something and place it in the burning [truth <font="Astronomicon SDF">Y</font>].
I should ask Arin to translate it first.
This refers to the certificate. [em1]Arin[/em1] will prepare it.
I... want to give it some thought.
Arin, have you made up your mind?
Ellie... come.
I just decided.
I plan to send the Silent Guardian to the Witch Administration through Diane.
Do you think that's alright?
Of course. This isn't a decision you made lightly.
But... are you sure? That book is the only keepsake left by your father.
I hope more people can know the truth, rather than me keeping it to myself.
Just as my father wished.
If that book becomes known to the world, the Witch Administration will be busy for a while.
Textbooks and histories of witches will be drastically revised.
Maybe... even you, Ellie, will end up in the textbooks?
[em1]That would be amazing.[/em1]
Can't even tell a joke, huh?
Arin doesn't joke.
It was a joke...
Ellie, thank you for accompanying me on this journey.
Witches say, [em1]"Witches are supposed to help those in their reach."[/em1]
Right. That's something you hear all the time at witch school.
I've lived my whole life with... prejudice against witches. I couldn't even believe those words.
Thank you for breaking the prejudice for me.
Ellie, you're the second person to truly change my life.
I'm just happy I could help.
That's nice, but... now I feel like I can reach out first.
I look forward to what we will achieve next.
I got a letter from the [em1]Silent Guardians[/em1] too!
Why did they tell you not to reply and not to find the sender? That's... intimidating.
Hehe. But they said they'll contact us again when we're ready. Can't wait.
Alright. Everything's perfectly prepared.
Wow, it's Ellie! She's here!
The graduation ceremony is incredible!
Huh? Rubrum, Dana... What are you talking about?
How did you do that? Magic? You and Arin disappeared and then appeared out of nowhere!
Disappeared and appeared? Us?
Yes. You vanished from where you were standing... Then reappeared.
Ellie is a witch, so disappearing makes sense... But Arin too? Magic is amazing.
The flow of time in the book... must be different from that in real life.
Hm. Interesting. Can you tell us exactly what happened? To everyone?
Okay... I'll explain what happened.
You went through something incredible. Well done, Ellie.
Ah, sorry. I was lost in thought...
Everything that just happened feels like a dream.
Don't worry. The Silent Guardian in your hands is real.
My mom always says, "Leave tomorrow's worries for tomorrow."
Got it. I'll think about what to do with the book tomorrow.
Good night, everyone.
Arin meeting her father was truly miraculous.
Sometimes, reality can be more surprising than any play on stage.
This must be one of those moments.
It all seems like a big coincidence... How fortunate.
I disagree. Parks risked his life. There's no such thing as a coincidence with that kind of resolve.
No matter what you think about it, it's still the result of heartfelt effort. In the end, Arin's feelings matter most.
Arin... was it good? Meeting your dad?
Yes, Rubrum... I'm glad I'm alive to see this.
It's a bit of a complicated story, though.
Hmm... I'd want to see my mom and dad too.
Arin, it's okay to cry if you want to.
You just finally released something from your heart.
Yeah. If you need some drinks, tell me. I'll drink with you.
Everyone... thank you so much.
Arin, stay strong.
Stay strong...
...Good work, Arin.
I made it this far thanks to all of you...
I'm looking forward to meeting everyone tomorrow with a brighter face.
Everyone must be tired, so let's wrap up for today.
Arin, Rex, and I will clean up. Thank you all for helping.
Especially Diane.
Not at all. It was great. Call us again next time.
We didn't bring the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirstGraduationCeremonyForm_Name"))][/em1].
Let's get it from Diane.
Arin, I talked with Diane.
Looks like you have to do something else as well.
We borrowed the document needed to prepare the first witch graduation ceremony.
It's the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirstGraduationCeremonyForm_Name"))][/em1]. Want to read it together?
It's written in Ancient Witch Language, so I would like your help to translate it.
I see... There are certainly a lot of ambiguous sentences.
The document was written by my father.
It really is! It says [em1]Pax SilverRain[/em1] as the author.
Feels like we're following the path my father laid out.
Yeah. Everything seems planned in advance.
We'll just have to follow instructions, I suppose.
I'll try translating the ancient witch language... and we can check together what items are needed.
It also says only graduates of the School for Witches can borrow this document.
Of course, since I'm not a witch, I wouldn't have been able to borrow it anyway.
Ellie, have you been well lately?
Of course. I've been doing fine as always.
How about you? Feeling better since last time?
Yes... much better.
I received a letter... from someone unknown.
It seemed like whoever sent it knows exactly what you and I have been working on.
You mean our translation of the [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1]?
That's right. I was going to show you the letter, but...
The moment I read it, it burned to ash in my hands. That's why I suspect it came from a witch.
Do you remember what it said?
Yes... It told us to stop digging into the book.
To stop breaking the seals. Otherwise, they said... "They'd step in themselves."
Good grief... if they said [em1]"they,"[/em1] that means it's more than just one person.
Arin! You're not hurt, are you? You only got a threatening letter, nothing worse?
Have you told Rex? Or Kent?
No... You're the first. I only received it yesterday.
I was torn about who to confide in. The threat felt too serious to dismiss.
So you intend to face that fear?
At this point, your sudden interruptions don't even surprise me anymore.
When you speak of fear... You mean, was I afraid of the threat itself?
No. That doesn't scare me. What I truly fear...
...is the regret if I never saw this through.
So you choose not to remain silent.
If you abandon the work now, I shall forget my existence as a book forever.
Even if there is no turning back. Are you prepared?
Arin!
You've decided to continue the translation, right?
Yes... I've been thinking about it ever since you left.
About my father, and my family, whom I've yearned to know all my life.
I need to learn the truth. Whatever awaits, I'll see this through to the end.
You'll help me, won't you?
Of course! I've been waiting for you to say that.
Mr. Silent, tell us what we must do next.
The festival of all festivals. The rite that proves one has become a witch. [em1]The first graduation ceremony of the School for Witches[/em1]. Reenact it before my eyes.
The first... School for Witches graduation ceremony?
Another ritual about the school? Is there a special reason for this?
Because I must witness that [em1]ceremony[/em1].
Strange... A book crafted by witches demanding to see a graduation ceremony?
Yeah, I figured you wouldn't explain.
The first ceremony must've been ages ago.
Which means the best way is to dig up old documents, right?
Ellie, I should warn you. Alvin said he can't really help with matters involving the [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1].
Wait... You know Alvin is a witch too?
Yes. After we broke the first seal, he visited the library.
He encouraged me, then told me to continue my work with you. Said he'd rather remain a supporting role himself.
He even told me it was fine to mention he's a witch, since you already knew.
That's true. Alvin told me from the start he had no intention of hiding it.
We should ask Diane for help.
Diane? She's not that old though, is she? I'm not exactly sure either.
But since she works in the Witch Administration, I thought she might have access to old public records.
I don't have any Luna Coins... But I will find some way to cover whatever fee may incur.
Ha. You really are getting familiar with the world of witches now, Arin.
Anyway, I think it's a good idea.
I'll head there right away!
And of course, we'll do it together.
...I'll need to prepare first, so give me a little time.
All right. I'll keep researching in the meantime.
I'm afraid... but I'll see this through.
My mother once told me she watched a School for Witches graduation ceremony.
The year my father graduated from the school... was the year they married.
He [em1]secretly[/em1] invited her to the ceremony.
For an ordinary human to step into the school is nearly impossible.
That's why her story stuck with me. She said it was [em1]the most beautiful sight[/em1] she'd ever seen.
That part's true. It is a spectacle.
Of course, we won't be able to recreate it as grandly as the real thing.
But what made the first graduation ceremony different, I wonder?
He risked expulsion for it. Why he went that far, I'll never know.
And still... that wasn't the very first graduation.
The path here is blocked, just like in the previous maze.
I’m glad you’re here, Arin.
No… if it weren’t for you, Ellie the witch, I wouldn’t even have been able to open the book.
How heartwarming~
Indeed…
Shall we read the book then?
According to legend, the first witch had ten disciples, and thus only the ten witch elders mediated and guided the witches.
The elders swore by the power of the stars. They guided the witches on the right path and helped the humans.
The Ones Who Live Forever
Dreamers of Eternity
Arin, you read the book to open the wall too, right?
Yes… it had what I’d read before written there, so I just read it as it was.
I found it a bit confusing, though.
Thus, until the evil witch appeared, witches and humans were able to live in peace for a long time.
Those who followed the evil witch.
Because of them, one could say everything began and ended.
Shall we read it this time too?
The war waged by the evil witch left both witches and humans devastated.
Pax Silverrain was the one the evil witch obsessed over.
Eternal Life
It was written that because of that one thing, everything changed.
Infinite Power
That is also why all witches at the Witch School are forbidden from researching that subject.
George Goldenbaut, who became the leader in place of the ten elder witches, felt that a city for witches was needed.
He decided to reclaim the land that had once been used by the Dreamers of Eternity as their final stronghold.
Countless witches gathered and fortified the newly built city, protecting it with the magic of stars and night.
At the most tranquil heart of the city, they raised the most important building high.
It was the Witch Administration.
It was the Witch School.
Because George Goldenbaut regarded it as a building that symbolized a new era.
Arin, doesn’t the book blocking the path seem a bit different?
It feels like someone is just speaking their own thoughts.
I felt the same way.
The one we briefly encountered earlier… maybe it was written by that person.
Hmm~ we’ll only know once we reach the end, right? I’ll keep reading.
What is it that distinguishes the witches of the past from the [em1]new witches[/em1]?
It is none other than the unique ritual of the Witch School.
The witches of the past regarded proving what they were as a disgrace.
Four rituals
Only after proving themselves through those may they be awarded the [em1]Witch’s Brooch[/em1].
Three rituals
But for witches of the Witch School, they must perform the proper ritual each time they become something new.
Every student has a set number of rituals they are required to undergo.
From where does a witch’s power spring forth?
The only way to know that is by proving one’s own abilities oneself.
But at the Witch School, one item is presented so that they may take pride in that skill. That is—
The Witch’s Staff.
The witch brooch.
The item itself has [em1]no power[/em1], but it is proof of having overcome every trial.
In the new era, it is the Witch School, not the family, that presents the item, making it a proof of the new age.
Thus, it can be said to be the very tool that proves the witch’s power and ability.
The Silent Guardian is the name of the book, and the intent of its creator still remains unknown.
Huh? The book’s contents…?
It’s… a different format than before.
I’ll keep reading.
Ellie Blueriver and Arin Silverrain were the first to break the seal placed upon the Silent Guardians…
They plunged into the maze to break the complete seal of [em1]the Silent Guardians[/em1], the history book written by Pax Silverrain.
If the two of them cannot find what they truly sought within the maze, then with all their hearts…
They will regret it.
I think they’ll regret it!
Huh…?
I could have done better!
If I had studied harder at school, I could have understood the truths hidden in the book much better!
This is when Virgil should pop out and say something <shake>like this!</shake>
How long is he planning to just keep thinking like that?
Haha… that’s such an Ellie-like regret.
But I never expected a question like this.
It only ever kept asking whether I was translating the book correctly.
Still… the path has opened.
Shall we go then!
They will not regret it.
Huh? Arin read it…
Yes. I will not regret it.
Just the fact that we were able to make it this far is enough.
I mean… I’ll feel a bit of regret, of course.
I’ll read it again, since it says they will regret it.
I’ll read it again, since it says they will not regret it.
When the path is blocked and there’s just a single book lying there…
I guess we have no choice but to read it, right?
It is said that the first witch accomplished many things with the knowledge and power borrowed from the stars.
The next sentence is split into two parts.
Which means we have to choose one of the two to read…
The Book of Wishes
Oh, did one side just open?
The Book of Stars
And with her power, she created a book said to grant every wish.
It is said to have been created, but no one has ever confirmed its actual existence.
I know this story well too.
It’s a book, huh?
Shall we give it a read?
According to legend, a single [em1]star[/em1] that shone the brightest in the sky fell upon the earth, cutting through the [em1]night sky[/em1].
That star shared its power with the one who gazed upon it and earnestly made a [em1]wish[/em1].
That is said to be the beginning of witches.
It’s the story of the [em1]first witch[/em1]. I remember it well since I often heard it from my grandmother.
Pax gave up on seeking the [em1]Book of Stars[/em1].
The world must not know that he is writing the book.
Because he decided to devote his life to writing a history book.
For a long time, witches lived freely. They built their homes where their hearts led them and followed the paths they desired.
But that time did not last forever.
Along those paths always stood the ten elder witches, like moonlight, guiding the witches on their way.
Because the war waged by the evil witch and the Dreamers of Eternity brought everything to an end.
Among them, witches like Katherine Coralcloud and Lily Embersteel gained renown through their infamy.
They all died as villains, unable to let go of their desire to live forever.
The evil witch discovered a way to turn human lives into her own life.
The [em1]Dreamers of Eternity[/em1] followed that power and gathered as a group.
With George Goldenbaut elected as leader, the reborn city came to be called Lucerine Ortu.
On the vast and vibrant land, countless witches gathered to make their home.
It is a bustling city, filled with countless buildings—the Witch Administration, markets, and villages where witches live together.
But the most important facility in this city is undoubtedly the [em1]Witch School[/em1], protected at its very center.
The Witch School was established with the purpose of nurturing witches of the new era.
There was so much new knowledge to be taught. As a result, the students had to remain at the school for a long time.
Looking back, it feels like that period might have been excessively long.
The new witches who underwent the [em1]Entrance Ceremony[/em1] went through 20 years of school life.
And after going through the [em1]Rite[/em1] of becoming an apprentice witch again, they spent 10 years in the Witch's House.
Only after this can they undergo the [em1]Graduation Ceremony[/em1], which allows them to be recognized as true witches.
There are many items that a witch must handle with great care.
The diploma that proves she is qualified as a witch
Things like the staff that will walk countless paths in her stead.
But the most important item is undoubtedly the [em1]Witch’s Brooch[/em1]. Without it, it would be considered a disgrace as a witch.
Although it's a [em1]witch brooch[/em1], a tool of the witch, it holds no power.
It is merely an item that a witch carries for life to prove her own existence.
The Witch School gives a brooch to every graduate, but in conservative families, they still require the use of a self-made brooch.
I do not [em1]regret[/em1] making this book.
Even if the seal of this book is broken someday, I will not [em1]regret[/em1] it.
The three [em1]rituals[/em1] of the school—Entrance Ceremony, Apprentice Certification, and Graduation Ceremony—determine sincerity through magic unknown to the students.
Thus, if the process has been properly carried out, the ritual is designed to be passed without fail.
That procedure is nothing more than a formality, yet I deemed it a journey that would bring a sense of accomplishment.
My father, William Silverrain, was a war criminal.
Through this book, I reveal that this fact is the truth.
In a few minutes, my life will come to an end.
There are things I could not leave in this book, but I entrust them to the witches of the future.
Lastly… not being able to see my family’s faces before I breathe my last will be my only [em1]regret[/em1].
The witches were free. And so, they lived to achieve what they desired.
Within that freedom, one witch realized what it was she truly needed.
[em1]To live forever[/em1]. But it was something impossible with her own power.
In the end, it was something that could only be done by taking the life of another living being.
In Lucerine Ortu, countless buildings stand.
To the north lies the Witch Administration, and to the south are the shopping streets and witches’ houses.
In the west, various buildings stand centered around a grand library.
And at the very center of Lucerine Ortu stands the [em1]Witch School[/em1], facing the great river that runs through the continent.
Even after the war ended, some of the [em1]Eternal Dreamers[/em1] survived.
The witches and humans pursued the wicked beings to the very end and condemned them.
William Silverrain is a representative figure of this.
The Silent Guardian, is it?
The Silent Guardian has fallen down again.
It feels more and more like… finding and reading this book is the way forward.
<shake>Kyaaah!</shake> I’m being sucked in!
Right? Then I’ll try reading it once more.
What a relief. Though it feels like we wandered a bit.
Hmm. Then let’s move on to the next.
Why would it be lying here...
I know, right. Such an important book, just lying on the ground...
Huh? Wha—what?
Ahhh!!! I feel weird!
Ellie, you’re really good at finding the way.
I just thought, if I keep walking, there’s bound to be an exit somewhere.
I… see.
Even before reading the book, my stomach feels queasy.
Arin, look at this.
The table of contents... it’s written here too.
The first floor is called the Floor of Myths.
If there’s a first floor, that means there must be more after it?
I’ll try reading it for now!
So this must have been the second floor.
The Floor of History… since the book here was about history, that makes sense.
That means… reading the Silent Guardian on each floor must be the way to reach the next one.
Then… soon to the next floor…
But I wonder… how long will this maze go on?
There’s a table of contents. The third floor was The Witches of the Future.
Well… I’m not sure.
It feels like most of what we read in the book has already come up.
But we won’t know for sure until we make it all the way to the end.
Ellie's certificate has also vanished into the flames.
<shake>Arin~! You can do it~!</shake>
My ears! That's Rex, isn't it?
Haha. He must be watching from afar, worried about Arin.
Hehe! Instead of keeping watch, he's staring over here?
Alright then! I'll lend Arin my strength too! Ah—
Stop it, Bjorn. Arin's trying to focus.
Now it's Arin's turn, isn't it?
Arin, whenever you're ready, go ahead.
Even though it's only a fake certificate, the flames devour it so fiercely.
If it were the real thing, I'd certainly hesitate.
Haha, I felt the same way myself.
I... Arin... am one who always seeks truth and has high hopes for the future.
<wave>Phew~</wave> I was too nervous to throw it. I’ll try again.
Welcome. The child of stars and the child of earth have found their way out of the maze.
Arin, we did it! We made it out!
Sir... could you let us go now?
Before that, is there a question you would like to ask? Such as lifting the seal on the book, or revealing the truth.
Right... I almost forgot our original goal.
I have so many questions... But first, who are you?
I am merely a memory of one who guards the book.
However...
To those who have unsealed it, I speak as the memory of Pax SilverRain.
Ah...!
So Arin's father left a memory inside the book.
Are you Ellie Blueriver and Arin SilverRain?
Names unfamiliar. Born after the war, you are the ones I truly waited for.
The name Arin SilverRain... is unfamiliar?
That's your daughter's name...
When Pax SilverRain was still alive, there was an unborn daughter. Her name was not in the memory.
Then you must remember your wife, Stella.
In my memory, Stella is a shining beacon.
She always said that "the ten years we had together were the happiest of her life."
Then... you didn't know my mother lived through hardship after you left.
To make some sort of fake history book, she was taken to the countryside and couldn't leave.
Incorrect. It was Stella who suggested hiding in a village to avoid the world's eyes.
She said there's no need to feel shame about what the family did, but to record the true history and convey the truth.
She urged me to document the crimes of my father, [em1]William SilverRain[/em1], in a book for the world to read.
What???
But if that's the case, why would Parks seal the book himself?
I accidentally ingested poison prepared by an unknown killer.
With my last strength, I sealed the book.
To prevent anyone from altering its contents.
So... you didn't seal it deliberately to hide it.
Correct. Only graduates from the [em1]School for Witches[/em1] can unseal it.
Only they hold the knowledge to lift its seal.
The witches who started the war... and grandfather... You wanted to protect the book from them, right?
[em1]Dreamers of Eternity[/em1] were witches from the past. Future generations are not supposed to be involved.
Exactly. New graduates of the witch school are unrelated.
Then Arin's father... he only failed in delivering the truth.
What memory do you have of your unborn daughter?
My father used to talk to me while I was in my mother's womb. Parks must have similar memories, right?
Those memories remain in abundance.
One day, when preparing to hand over the completed book to my colleagues, Stella told me she was with child.
She said we now had one more reason to live.
But I was afraid of the danger my actions might bring.
Stella said that if I use my memory as the book's guardian, it would also serve as protection for our daughter.
That way, the truth could reach her undistorted. I agreed.
All of this... Spoken without a single emotional inflection...
But I understand now...
If your doubts about me are resolved, and desire for the truth, satisfied, I would like to ask...
I would like to plead that you two join the [em1]Silent Guardians[/em1] and reveal the truth to the world.
Can we really join you?
You are worthy. Once the book is unsealed, my colleagues who are still alive will send a letter.
Ah! The threatening letter.
That must be from one of Parks' colleagues.
Firstly, young witch, will you join us?
I'd love to brag to my mom and dad about joining such a legendary group...
But... it has to be a secret. I'll hold it in for now.
Then you cannot join us.
What? Why the sudden change of attitude?
We are the Silent Guardians. You will be allowed in when you can truly stay silent.
Tsk. Stiff rules, huh?
Still, I can help Arin even if I'm not a Silent Guardian.
Th...thanks, Ellie.
Next, the librarian, will you join us?
I... understand my father's will... my mother's sacrifice...
I am grateful for everything that brought me here.
So... I will join the Silent Guardians.
That's okay.
The Silent Guardians are Arin's legacy.
I helped... but joining a secretive group seems too much.
Worried you'll blurt it all out?
What, Virgil, you're awake?
Besides, I've got other things to do.
You helped unseal the book with the librarian. That alone proves your resolve.
Joining or not is only a matter of choice.
Haha, thanks.
Arin! Something weird is happening!
The book is closing. Time is short.
Father... is there nothing more you wish to say?
No. I wished to tell you countless things...
But in my memory, duty comes first.
The book, [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1], will return to being just an ordinary book.
Its fate now rests with you, young witch and my daughter.
I hope the truth will no longer be silenced and reach all witches and humans.
And... stepping back from my role, there's one thing I must tell my daughter.
You are the light of my life...
It's okay, Ellie.
I've... lived my whole life under a misunderstanding. No, I chose to misunderstand.
I was sure my father had abandoned us.
But... now I know that I know the truth, I feel relieved.
Goodbye... Father...
The induction ceremony is quite the spectacle.
I... don't feel any different, though.
Arin SilverRain. I detect witch's blood in you.
A being half-human, half-witch.
Naturally. I am your daughter.
Again. I cannot independently verify this yet.
That's right. No one alive can prove I am your daughter.
Mother always told me stories of your youth.
I want to hear them from you directly...
About the [em1]Book of Stars[/em1] that shaped my life...
About the [em1]story of your engagement[/em1] at the graduation ceremony...
But... I should be satisfied that I made it this far.
Stella sneaking into the graduation ceremony at the School for Witches...
No one knew of it.
I thought you knew Arin is Stella's daughter.
Now you know.
My memory exists only to guard the book.
Yet I still want to confirm. Stella... at the graduation...
She said it was the most beautiful thing she had ever seen.
And we...
You announced your engagement. Not as a witch and a human... but as two people in love.
I See... Arin SilverRain... I ask you. May I... remember you as my...
...Daughter?
Of course... I've waited for this my whole life.
...Arin... My daughter.
It was you all along.
Yes... It's me.
In my dying moments... I wanted to see your face.
I'm sorry I had to leave you...
I saw him just now!
Ow... ow...
Where am I?
Arin? Virgil?
No answer...
Guess I'll have to find my own way.
Ah! Arin! And... who's that?
Come forth, child of stars and child of earth.
Uh? Hello.
I thought only the Silent Guardian lived here. Didn't expect to meet someone.
Why... why have you called us here?
You both wish to bring forth the book of silence into the world.
You may desire it, but it will not come easily.
This is the Maze of Letters. Fail to comprehend it, and you will wander forever.
Arin, did they just say... a maze?
Yes. They said we'd be lost in the [em1]Maze of Letters[/em1].
At least tell us your name before vanishing—!
Didn't even let me finish my sentence.
Still... I'm glad you're here with me, Arin.
...This won't be easy.
Huh? Why not?
I glanced at the writing in the book in front of us. It's filled with things no ordinary human could comprehend.
"The unheard heartbeat of the moon... was the first cry that summoned the stars"?
Do you know what that means, Ellie?
Well... Moon and stars are terms witches often use, but I'll have to think about it.
And you, Arin?
If it's about stars... I remember reading that "the first witch became a [em1]star[/em1] and then returned."
But how's that related to this, I'm not sure.
Ah! Witches believe their power grows stronger at night. Sometimes they say their hearts burn hotter.
I've even felt it myself.
Maybe that's what they meant by the heartbeat of the moon!
Things only a witch could know... fascinating.
If we keep doing this together, maybe we can escape the maze.
I sure don't want to stay here forever.
You're right. We need to return to the ones we cherish.
Do you not seek to reveal the true history sealed within this book?
I do. I want to break the seal and uncover everything written inside.
And... I want to know why my father wrote it.
This maze must be tied to the ancient witch language, just like everything else we've encountered.
One question, though. Why seal the book in the first place?
Books are usually meant for all to read.
But this one is bound shut, locked away. Why?
I do not believe what you said.
So... You wanted to hide the truth?
To bury it, so no one could ever find it?
Whether that is so, you will see for yourselves at the maze's end.
We've translated the ancient witch language before. We can do it again here.
How was it, Arin? Perfect, right?
Truly... it was beautiful. I almost cried.
Witches who get to hold this ceremony every year... they must be really happy.
Right? Even witches rarely get to see a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1].
How about everyone else? What did they think of the graduation?
Everyone... is so quiet.
They are probably too moved to speak, right?
Rubrum, what about you? Was it as fun as you expected?
Ellie... don't you think something's strange?
Everyone... is frozen in time.
Hmm... Virgil, say something. Anything.
No response from Virgil as well...
Mr. Book. What's going on? Did you freeze too?
You conducted the ceremony splendidly, young witch and librarian.
I invite both of you, fully prepared, to my library.
An invitation?
Indeed. You only need to read me.
Is this... another task?
I clearly said it is an [em1]invitation[/em1].
What happens if we don't accept?
Will you stop being a book?
Not for such a trivial reason.
You will spend this space with those frozen until death.
Wh-what?! Hey! That's not acceptable!
Then this isn't an invitation... It's a threat.
You opened the doors to my library. I never said you [em1]had to accept[/em1].
Ellie... It seems we have no choice.
Fine. We've come this far, so let's see it to the end. We'll manage if we go together!
I... trust you, Ellie. Let's accept the invitation together.
Which chapter should we translate?
It lists [em1]locations[/em1] suitable for a graduation ceremony.
Hmm... so we need a place in the village that meets these conditions?
Considering these conditions... the most fitting spot is...
The fountain
Near the fountain, right? It's full of life because of the water and is placed on the ground.
And water is the base material of potions.
That seems to match the conditions best.
I'll check with Enite if the fountain is okay for the graduation ceremony.
Looks like we've gathered everything we need.
There's... a lot to prepare.
We'll need help from the villagers.
If they help, I'd be truly grateful...
Feels like we're preparing a village festival. The village will be lively for a while.
Then... The person who sent the threatening letter might notice too?
Totally forgot about that.
We should find someone to [em1]keep watch over the village[/em1] when the ceremony begins.
We're not warriors. If danger arises, we run.
Good idea, Ellie.
I'll gather the necessary items. Arin, could you prepare the graduation certificates?
Under the wisteria tree
Near the wisteria, right? Lots of living organisms thrive there, and it's rooted in the ground.
But it's not a source of [potions <font="Astronomicon SDF">u</font>]... It seems not related at all.
True... The tree might be used as an ingredient for some potions, but calling it a source of potions seems pretty far-fetched.
The stage
Near the stage? People dance there, and it must be on the ground.
Special items
The document describes the [em1]special items[/em1] required for the ceremony.
Any ideas?
The ceremony is held at night. That's probably why they are worthless in daylight.
Spell of the stars probably refers to tools only witches can use.
Then what can be born only from death...?
Hmm... Let's think about the essential items for the ceremony...
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_2_Name"))]
Firecracker Potion? It's a magical item and can't be seen clearly in daylight.
But it doesn't seem related to death at all.
Yeah. Just sparkly and pretty.
The podium
Graduates speak on the podium...
Seems unrelated to the things mentioned here...
Yeah. It's really not special.
Torches
Torches, maybe? We had to put magical items into torches, and you don't use them during the day.
Yes... I think it's probably torches.
To light a torch, one needs to set something on fire, destroying it in the process.
Makes sense!
But what makes these torches different from regular ones?
Hmm... I guess we have to ask someone who knows this process from the inside out.
We'll have to ask around the village to find the right stuff.
It says something edible.
What... could that mean?
This is pretty easy.
Graduates eat only [em1]cold[/em1] food. Not sure why.
Cold food can be eaten any time... seems reasonable.
And "desire" just means it must be delicious. No bland food.
One tradition at the graduation ceremony is that no bad food is allowed.
Fun but... strict rules.
Right? Witches usually like warm stews.
As long as it's as tasty as that bread you had, it works.
Someone can make something just as good for the ceremony.
Sounds like the graduation certificate.
I think I can make that. Saw a template in a recent book.
Then what does [em1]putting it in the burning [truth <font="Astronomicon SDF">Y</font>] means?[/em1]
It likely refers to how the graduation certificate is used at the ceremony, but I'm not exactly sure.
Let's think about that after preparing everything.
Food that tastes good at room temperature isn't that common.
It reminds me of the bread from my childhood.
Sugary, cold... but still tasted great.
There are plenty of talented cooks in the village.
Maybe that's what "born only from death" means.
I'll ask everyone for help!
That's quick!
Of course. This is basically the description of a graduation certificate.
The graduation certificate is the only thing that proves a witch has gained enough power.
Then I should make them.
Where does the School for Witches hold its graduation ceremony?
The ceremony is held at the largest sports field at the school.
A stage is set up around the lake.
The stage is covered with decorations, creating an unforgettable sight.
So... that's why my mother was moved by the ceremony.
If we translate the document...
Do we need a lot of special items for the ceremony?
From what I recall... not really.
If we just read the text...
The description is quite clear.
Students need their broom and proof of their apprenticeship.
For the stage, we need torches, the podium, chairs and the flag of the School for Witches.
Sounds like... I still don't really know what counts as a special item.
Let's read the document.
See you next time.
Yes, I’m listening.
Well, I'm not familiar with that story.
I don't have any information on that.
Repairing the Witch's House? Did you ask the Witches' Catalogue Department?
Yes... But isn't there another way?
Things made by witches are special.
But I heard that besides witches, craftsmen who are skilled can also make special things.
Yeah, so I think Kyla can probably do it.
I think I should go ask her myself.
Hello. Do you live in the village?
Wow, what a lovely view.
Aren't these trees beautiful? Their green leaves are so pretty in the sun...
Oh... Sure...
Nature is so breathtaking.
You must love nature a lot.
I suppose no one dislikes nature, since it's so charming.
Okay, I'll be back.
Walk under the vast sky and feel the charm of nature!
That was an enthusiastic fan of nature.
So enthusiastic that you can't have a proper conversation with her.
You should respect her interests.
I think it's more of an obsession.
Something didn't feel right about her.
You think she's [em1]cursed[/em1] or something?
A [em1]curse[/em1] that makes her praise nature all the time?
A [em1]curse[/em1] by a nature lover? Well, maybe.
Many witches are quirky, after all.
Alright, let's make [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] to lift the curse.
Oh, but we can't use the processing tool now.
I must process what's been collected to make candies. What should I do?
You picked up several ingredients at the [em1]workplace[/em1] earlier, didn't you?
Those would be enough to make [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1].
And did you see the thing beside them?
Beside them? What?
There's a glass bottle that would be perfect as an [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ExtractorGlassBottle_Name"))][/em1].
There really is!
The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] that can lift the curse... It should be among the basic recipes...
And to receive that glass bottle as a reward.
That would be nice.
Didn't you make a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] just now?
I guess I can simply give it to her.
Alright, now let's lift the curse.
First, let's check on the [em1]candy that can lift the curse[/em1] in the [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1].
I love this forest.
The trees here are always green, as if not affected by the changing seasons.
Ah, nature is so incredible!
Have you ever listened to the stream flowing?
That beautiful subtle sound...
Nature is full of fascinating secrets.
Let's look for the mysteries hidden among the giant trees!
Long live mother nature!
A Ritoring? First time I’ve heard such a thing.
It's like an acorn, but with arms, legs, and a face.
Oh, you mean the Spirit of the Forest.
A Spirit?
They say it grants the finder good luck...
... Or grants them special powers...
... Lots of rumors like that.
You’ve seen one before, Aurea?
No, unfortunately I've never seen one myself.
But you hear things here and there as you do business as a merchant.
I have a product to recommend today. How does that sound?
A nice processing tool that just came out. Let me introduce it to you.
It's an affordable new product from <Yellow Windmill>.
They say it was made to [em1]process larger quantities at once[/em1] by increasing the capacity.
I also have the Roaster.
So we don't have to do it one at a time now?
If you buy this processing tool, yes.
The new Extractor by <Yellow Windmill> will save you half of the time.
Let me know if you're interested.
The Extractor is 10 Gold Coins and the Roaster is 15 Gold Coins.
The advertising text is pretty cool too.
Oh, the owner of the flower shop, right? I know him, yeah!
I used to buy seeds and seedlings from him. I even ordered flower bouquets.
He was pretty good. He wasn't a master in this field, but had good hands.
Above all else, he always kept his promises.
No way. that’s a taboo word.
No, Aurea. I don't mean pepper.
Really? The mention of a curse just makes me shudder. Ho Ho.
I heard that you saw Arden throwing away stuff.
Can you describe the situation?
Hmm... It was not long after you removed the prickly vines...
I saw Arden carrying a huge package.
I saw him on my way to the village...
I think he was heading towards the forest.
Are you looking for the thing that curses Arden?
I'm not sure if it's a curse yet.
Cheer up. Prove the innocence of my pepper.
I don't have any items ready now.
Come by anytime.
Sell
Trade with [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))]
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect_Unique"))][/em1] have many uses.
But it's hard to always have everything you need on you, don't you agree?
I can get [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] or [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect_Unique"))][/em1] ready if you want to exchange for them.
They tend to fly off the shelves, so I usually have them in stock.
You can bring me any unneeded [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] to exchange for items you want.
But I'm a merchant after all, so I will charge a small fee for the exchange. I hope you understand.
Ellie, you want to trade with [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1]?
And if there are any gathering items you've collected during your exploration that you don't have immediate use for.
I’ll exchange them for [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] and others.
Aurea, do you have any house blueprint?
Yes, of course I do!
Is it for the other villagers' houses?
Which villager is moving back this time?
A villager named Roy.
Roy... Ah, the owner of the flower shop.
I happen to have the flower shop blueprint too. I'll put it up in the shop.
Aurea, do you also sell food ingredients?
Usually only for the requested items. Do you need something?
Oh, I got this from Arden, but...
He said he bought this pepper from you and there was something strange about it.
Hmm? No way. Shall we take a look?
Hmm... This is red pepper. It's a pepper with a mild sweetness that is proud of the unique flavor.
I gave it to Arden to try it out, but I guess he didn't listen. He never does.
Well... Arden thinks this pepper is cursed.
What? That’s nonsense.
I’m very sensitive to curses.
The mention of a curse makes me shudder. I would never sell something with one.
Right. I also thought it was weird.
I have my pride as a merchant.
I'm serious with what people eat.
The pepper is not weird. It's just a different species.
I think Arden was just mistaken.
Hmm, but there are cases where a curse is hidden. Shall we look into it a little more?
What was it again? The thing that tasted terrible.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1]?
It's not really a memory I'd like to recall, but...
I should ask Diane if I can get a recipe.
Wait, I forgot [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Arden'sCursePepper_Name"))][/em1].
I have a favor to ask today.
Wow, thank you.
Yes? What is it? Tell me.
Can you take this letter to Kyla?
Although I don't usually do it for free...
I'll think of it as payment for getting rid of the prickly vines.
I guess I’ll see Kyla again after a long time.
Where’s Kyla now?
I think Kyla always wanted to come back.
Last I heard, she was helping out at the old smithy she used to work at, and she never settled down anywhere else.
I hope she comes back soon.
I'll give her the letter as soon as possible. You may get the reply as early as tomorrow.
Yes, I’ll be waiting.
Wait, I forgot [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "KylaLetter_Name"))][/em1].
The Prayer Stone? Hm... Don't think I've heard of it.
This here. Have you seen anything similar?
Oh, goodness. This is very valuable. Where did you get it?
I borrowed it from Enite. Apparently it's an artifact that is passed down by the village chiefs.
That explains it. it's not exactly the same, but I have seen similar stones elsewhere.
They are made by pouring [em1]wishes[/em1] into rare ores, so they're also called [em1]Wish Stones[/em1].
So do they grant your wishes?
No, not that magical, but they can be ingredients of certain [em1]mysterious items[/em1].
Some stones can carry unforgettable promises, so they are also called [em1]Pledge Stones[/em1].
However, they say that the devices would be placed [em1]somewhere noticeable[/em1] or [em1]remarkable[/em1] near the village.
They're placed in noticeable places when they're supposed to be hidden?
If it really contains a wish or a pledge, will its maker want others to know?
[em1]Fries[/em1] with BBQ sauce fried with bacon bits are delicious too.
Oh my. You're not old enough to drink, are you? Ellie.
I'm helping Arden to look for suitable drinking snacks.
Oh, I see. You've definitely asked the right person.
There aren't many people like me who've tried all kinds of wine and every food pairing.
Wow, could you give me a few recommendations?
Though I like [em1]bitter wine[/em1], it doesn't go down easily if it's over the top.
These go well with spicy soups or savory drinking snacks.
A [em1]shakshuka[/em1] with chunks of meat and pepper would be great too.
I'd recommend pairing [em1]bitter wine[/em1] with [em1]shakshuka[/em1] and [em1]french fries[/em1].
Oh, perfect timing. I've just had some new items delivered.
Are the new items pieces of furniture?
Looks like news really gets around a small village like this quickly.
I'll be bringing [em1]rugs, wallpaper and flooring materials[/em1] that will be from the [em1]same theme[/em1].
I'll be selling products from [em1]different themes daily[/em1], so keep an eye out.
If you do have any theme you really like and want to see more of, just let me know.
I'll keep the products [em1]constant for 3 days[/em1] for you, Ellie.
If you're lucky, you might occasionally find some [em1]rare furnishings[/em1], so be sure to come take a look often.
Well... Wisteria's specialty is, of course, tea leaves.
But what is it for?
Making bookmarks.
Emm... There're some strange plants around here. Let me see which ones can be used for bookmarks.
Ah, right, what about [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))][/em1]?
It looks nice and has pretty colors. It should make a good material, right?
I may sound like boasting, but I've been to many places, yet I've never seen those flowers elsewhere.
If the well-traveled Aurea says so, it must be true.
Hehe, thanks, flattering me won't get you anything, though.
Enjoy your free time.
Oh, is this a fragment of the prickly vines?
Yes. Do you know something about it?
No idea at all.
But I have something that might be helpful.
Something that might be helpful?
Tada! [em1]<wave>Universal product identifier</wave>[/em1]!
Wow! What’s that?
It's a tool made by some witch.
With the [em1]power of the moon[/em1] of the moonstone embedded here, you can find out [em1]the identity[/em1] of any object.
Really? Then hurry up and try it!
Alright. Here it goes.
The prickly vine fragment... has disappeared?!
That's strange... Why did it disappear...?
I don't usually do this for free, but since you lifted my curse...
Just this one time.
Wow, that's great.
No [em1]plant gets killed by sheer moonlight[/em1], right?
This tool just emits [em1]moonlight[/em1] and analyzes the reflected light.
A plant that withers once exposed to [em1]moonlight[/em1]...?
Oh, I remember now!
Maybe because of a grudge against nature?
Well, I don't think so.
I see, this prickly vine is definitely [em1]afraid of the moon[/em1]! That's why [em1]it withered once exposed to the moonlight[/em1].
I'm glad the tool is working fine.
Thank you. I think we can get rid of the prickly vines now.
No, I'm the one who should be thankful. I'm counting on you~
Think, Ellie. This is something you learned in school.
I think I've also heard of plants like that.
[em1]Afraid of the moon[/em1]! They're plants that get killed by moonlight.
<shake>Ugh, it seems like something's coming up in my mind...</shake>
I should go fetch the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ThornPiece_Name"))][/em1].
That's my specialty, y'know.
I will put them in my shop, so if you see anything you want, just buy it.
The selection's different each time, so it's best if you buy it than wait.
Oh, try asking Kyla.
She's quite skilled with wood, so she could make a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "DisplayItem"))] or [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "DisplayTable"))] for you.
Here, for you.
Wow, for me? It's so cute.
Yes, to support your effort of decorating the gallery.
I've added things to my shop, so take a look.
I heard that you passed the candy delivery test.
I knew you could do it.
I offer a candy purchase service similar to that of the Witch Association.
Come to me if you want to earn some Gold Coins.
From now on, you can deliver candies.
Usually, the delivery list refreshes every [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Monday"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Thursday"))][/em1], but since it's your first day, I'll make an exception and refresh it now.
It will follow the regular schedule from the next time.
Please note that the order that spawns today should be completed before the next refresh day, no later than this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", GetGlobalVariable("$711")))][/em1].
If you make and deliver potions well, you will get the chance to deliver more advanced potions and in larger quantity. I look forward to your good work.
The delivery lists refresh every [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Monday"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Thursday"))][/em1].
<Calling Delivery service>
Do you want to use the delivery service?
Fulfill this delivery order?
Oh, you chose this one.
OK, remember to deliver before [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  GetGlobalVariable("$711")))].
Take your time.
Thank you. Potions delivered.
You want to cancel this Delivery order?
Looking forward to working with you again.
If you need anything, just ask.
The harder you work to make and deliver candies, the more candies you can deliver. Hang in there.
These are the delivery orders you chose.
An overdue means a failure. Be careful.
The goods on this delivery order need to be delivered before [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", GetGlobalVariable("$711")))].
If you can't make it, or wish to switch to another order, you can cancel it.
But you've reached the [em1]delivery limit[/em1] of this candy theme. Cannot deliver anymore.
The delivery has been completed.
Select another delivery.
Should I write down the items to deliver in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("UI", "Wishlist_Name"))][/em1]?
Alright, I’ve written them down in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("UI", "Wishlist_Name"))][/em1].
Check special greetings
Ellie, have you been busy lately? It’s nice to have a chat after so long.
I've passed the candy delivery test.
That's impressive, since you've just begun your apprenticeship.
It's nothing. I was a model student.
I basically offer the same services as the witch society.
Except that I have different items on my purchase lists and I trade in Gold Coins.
Then, I'll get ready, so that you can start your delivery from tomorrow.
There're changes to the delivery orders. Check them out.
You've still got an unfinished Delivery order.
Sorry... The order has expired and cannot be completed.
Check out the new Delivery orders.
The delivery lists that spawn today can be completed before this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", GetGlobalVariable("$711")))][/em1].
Note that all current content will be removed upon the next refresh.
[em1]Candy deliveries[/em1] refresh today.
Aurea, I need more house blueprints.
No problem, I have all the blueprints you need.
Ah, since you put it that way, can I buy multiple at once?
You need the blueprints for the houses across the bridge, right? I'll put them in the store right away.
How did you know? You're amazing, like a fortune teller.
Hehe, don't you know? Mind reading is an essential skill for merchants.
For merchants, information is the key to success.
Alright, they're now available. You can buy them anytime.
It's disturbing how merchants are well-informed sometimes...
What would you like to discuss with Aurea?
Money and Happiness
Some people can buy happiness with money, but others can't.
So don't worry about how much money you've got. You can be happy regardless.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Aurea"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Ice Strawberries
There is an ice strawberry found in the forest at the northeastern tip of the continent.
It's a pinky-sized silver bead, and it fills you with refreshing sweetness the moment you put it in your mouth.
It's more expensive than gold of the same weight, but it's worth it.
The Jungle
There are more frauds in the jungle than in the desert.
Because you can't hide in the desert.
In the jungle? You disappear after only five steps.
You must be careful in a deep forest, because everything there is cunning. Not just humans, but also animals and plants.
Arden's Soup
Have you tried the soup that Arden has made?
Ask him to remove the pepper next time.
Arden wouldn't like it but quite a wonderful soup will come out.
Curse
Curses often appear when you least expect it.
Always be mindful of the things you encounter for the first time.
I think I’ll be lucky today.
A career as a peddler can be quite eventful.
Do you have any special memories?
An old man sold me a cursed wooden statue of a monkey.
Can’t argue with that.
It’s a joke.
There was an old woman selling pottery.
She was selling some handcrafted potteries in the most inconspicuous location of the market.
When I passed by, I accidentally met her gaze.
I looked at the pottery placed in front of the old woman who smiled bashfully while avoiding my eyes.
I still clearly remember the shape of that pottery.
It was a long, white water bottle with its spout open like flower petals.
The soft blue lighting gave it a mysterious air, and the fish engraved around its midsection were full of life.
I had never seen such a water bottle, and I fell in love with it at first sight.
I decided to buy it even if it would cost all the Solaris Gold Coins I had, and I asked her how much it was.
How much do you think she asked for?
Well, you can buy 10 water bottles with 1 Solaris Gold Coin, right?
Wouldn't she accept it if you offer 1 or 2 Gold Coins?
Only 2 Equus Silver Coins.
Equus Silver Coins... Even the shoes I’m wearing are more expensive than that!
That’s what I’m saying.
It's so lucky of you!
I got upset and told the old woman off.
"I will not buy it for less than 12 Solaris Gold Coins," I said.
All of a sudden it's more expensive than the house I live in!
So what happened?
In the end, I couldn’t buy it.
What? Why not?
She said, "Even a kid can make something like this out of mud. It's worth 2 Equus Silver Coins at most."
She was good with her hands, but terrible at appraising her own work.
But don't you regret it?
It could have been very profitable.
Being too expensive is a problem, but it can't be too cheap either.
Good things should be given good prices.
I never do business with people who don't know how to properly value things.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Aurea"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Do you know what's the happiest moment for a peddler?
I'm assuming it is when it's profitable?
When I spot good stuff.
I feel the best when I find something precious among the things laid out randomly at the country market.
Then isn't it a big gain? You can buy it cheap and sell it.
I can't do that. A good product must be bought at a good price.
But the seller didn't know.
But I knew.
What if you're wrong?
Then I have only my poor eyes to blame.
Aren't you being too nice in doing business?
It's been a really long time since I've heard that I'm nice.
Don't worry. It's a matter of my convictions rather than how nice I am.
I earn enough to get by.
My love, my beautiful love.
I look for you in the morning sun broken by the waves.
Oh my love, my dazzling love.
What kind of song is it?
It's a song that sailors sing.
When I sing, it’s nice to feel like I'm back in those days.
I look at you between the sails blown up by the breeze.
Oh my love, my warm love.
Tell me anytime if you want anything.
You were once a sailor?
Sailor? Well, yes. Why?
Since you were singing a sailor's song...
I was on a ship for quite some time.
Those days were really fun.
Wow, it's my first time meeting a sailor.
How did you end up getting on a ship? And why did you get off?
It's a long story.
I'll tell you about that next time.
Ummm... This unique smell. It resembles a fart of a squirrel, and also the heavy smell of soil after a rain.
It matches the trait of [em1]Earthgem Shrooms[/em1]. Thank you.
This mushroom is called an Earthgem Shroom?
Yup. It means "a gem growing out of soil."
It smells weird, but it seems tasty.
Well, I guess it has a distinctive taste.
Errr... but is it that expensive?
Gems aren't popular because they taste good, are they?
Okay?
Anyway, you kept your promise, so I should keep mine too.
[Hand over the item]
Wow! Thank you, Aurea, you're the best!
It was nothing. Trust is the foundation of business.
Here are the options a peddler has when the path is blocked.
First, find another path.
Second, find another means of transportation.
Third, get rid of some luggage if the first two don't work.
To be specific, reduce the size and [em1]lessen the weight[/em1].
That way, [em1]what didn't work would usually become effective[/em1].
I think I can help you with that problem.
But I won't help you for nothing.
I heard that there's a unique and precious mushroom in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
Although it's been missing from the marketplace for long, it used to be a renowned local specialty.
The mushroom is small and hard to spot, but please do this for me.
Small and hard to spot? If so, I don't think...
C'mon, you are a witch who has solved bigger problems. You can do this.
Just pay me with that instead of Gold Coins.
I wish you a smooth journey.
There are all kinds of mushrooms growing in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest")].
And that kind of mushroom has [em1]pink caps[/em1] and [em1]yellowish pink stalks[/em1].
And it's said to have [em1]white markings[/em1].
Aurea, you're looking for an expert in curses?
So, you got here first, Ellie.
I thought Arden would be the first again.
Yeah, the Arden you know. He sometimes examines unknown items for me.
I didn't know Arden is familiar with curses.
Everyone picks up some unique skills over the years.
Exactly. He has good judgement and has helped me a lot.
Although he only came to pick up pepper or other ingredients he needed, and helping me on the way.
Is that so? Arden actually has such a skill?
He would say things like "This one may be dangerous." or "That one's fine. You can sell it." Conclusions only. No explanations.
Anyway, Ellie, since you're a witch, I suppose you're also familiar with curses and rare items?
Here, I want you to examine these 4 books.
Where did you get these? The titles sound curious.
From a secondhand bookstore no longer operating.
The books have magic on them that prevent reading, so the owner [em1]asked[/em1] me to help handle them.
As you know, collectors are fond of such magical books, so they can fetch good prices.
I don't know that, but I'm willing to pick up such a profession.
It sounds so fun!
Heh... It is, isn't it?
I can only classify the books when the magic in them has been addressed. Do you know anything about these books?
Well, firstly, this 1001 Transfiguration Spells of Circe the Genius Witch is fake.
As far as I know, that witch isn't generous enough to write a book for others' benefits.
By looking at the content, this obviously wasn't written by any witch. It's just an enchanted work of fiction.
In short, it doesn't have much worth?
Right. Then there're Elf Flame and Prophet of the White Salt Kingdom. These two... are notable in a way.
Elf Flame has elf powder all over it, while one gets a salty taste in their mouth when reading Prophet of the White Salt Kingdom.
Both are weird spells, but they match the respective books.
They are both taught at school.
They are not curses? That's good to hear.
Yeah, but as for this [em1]Burning Bakery and Anxious Staff[/em1]... I'm not sure about it.
It's just an intriguing fairytale.
Isn't it strange for a 20-page fairytale to be so extraordinarily intriguing?
M-maybe?
I've read it 27 times, but I still can't resist it. Whenever I open this book, I can't help but finish it.
I was also somewhat mesmerized when reading... It seems to have a certain magic.
To find out whether it's a curse, we'd better try a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1] first.
You've got a point. The examination needs to be as precise as possible.
I'll pay you well.
Okay, Aurea. Could you give me a minute?
Sure, take your time.
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1] to Aurea?
Aurea, I've brought you the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Shall we start the examination?
Alright, and could you please examine the other books too just to be safe?
No problem. I'll check them all.
It's just like I expected... The other 3 are fine, but...
But what?
[em1]Burning Bakery and Anxious Staff[/em1] is really cursed.
A look at the cover alone gives me a burning sensation. No doubt it's a curse.
I think the curse triggers once you open the book.
What kind of curse is it?
Well, probably... a curse that forces the person to read all the way to the end?
Even if the book is boring?
I need to lift the curse to know its type for sure.
Come to think of it, a curse that makes you feel entertained is a hilarious idea in itself.
No, in many cases, entertaining stuff can lower people's guard, so it may count as a curse.
Still... it isn't that dangerous a curse.
Not for a fairytale.
I need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] this time. I'm counting on you.
Again, thank you for your help.
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] to Aurea?
Aurea, I've brought you the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Lift the curse at once?
Sure, the book is here.
Crush the candy with your hands like this... and gently sprinkle it on the book.
The cover has begun to change, and the title... is fading away.
Candies actually have such an application. Witch products are magical indeed.
Done. It's lifted.
However you look at it...
It's no longer a usual children's book, right?
Let's see. The title... is in a handwritten font.
We were really trapped. This is [em1]a book disguised as a children's book[/em1].
Apparently even the title was affected by the curse.
Look, the content is completely different now. The fairytale is gone, and it's all gibberish now.
I come across cursed items from time to time, but I've never seen anything like this before.
It must have been made for a purpose.
I suppose the maker used it to [em1]practice cursing[/em1].
Practice cursing?
Yeah, because the book's content is quite basic.
The more complicated a book's content, the more difficult to put a curse on it. This curse is simple, so it only needed a thin book.
How scary, to think that a fairytale book carries such a curse.
If so... the book can't be sold.
But it may be good news for you, Ellie.
Would you like to have this book?
I don't think you would put curses on anything, but it doesn't hurt to learn about them.
This book can be your first step in understanding the structure of curses.
You'd better have one of these.
Alright, I'll take it, although I don't know how I can use it yet.
And here's your reward for helping, with a bit of bonus.
Wow! Great, Thank you.
It's been fruitful for myself too. Have a wonderful day.
I need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1] this time. I'm counting on you.
Cursed items can't be sold.
Ellie, what's up?
Oh, Rubrum, hi!
Nice to see you, Rubrum.
You too, Ellie and Aurea. I overheard what you guys were talking.
May I see that children's book?
You mean [em1]Burning Bakery and Anxious Staff[/em1]?
Yup! I love bread. Granny makes the best bread in the world. Nobody can beat her.
But what does "anxious staff" mean?
It's the story in the book. You want me to recount the story? But that wouldn't be fun.
Ah! Ellie, don't. I want to read it myself.
But, Rubrum, do you know what a curse is?
Curse?
I know, something only baddies would use.
You're right, and this very book has been cursed.
If you read it, something super scary may happen to you.
What kind of thing?
Well, all your teeth will fall off.
Aurea, don't scare the kid.
Rubrum, if you open this book, you'll have to read all the way to the end. That's the curse.
But that's what reading a book is about. Granny said that good books must be finished.
Hmm... Can't argue with that.
Ellie, you heard that?
Humph, I know.
Aurea, what do you say? Shall we let Rubrum read the book?
Nothing went wrong when we read it, so I don't see why Rubrum can't read it.
Well... alright? Since it was fine before.
Good, Ellie, read it to me.
Rubrum!
Yes?
You're ready to listen until the end?
Let's go sit on the bench over there then. I'll read [em1]Burning Bakery and Anxious Staff[/em1] to you.
I didn't expect the whole village to come listen to you reading a fairytale.
Neither did I. The curse seems to be much more powerful than we thought.
We can sell it the way it is... but it would probably cause serious trouble.
Yeah, I can sell it for a good price, but that would be unfair for the buyer.
After all, however intriguing the book it, that's because of the curse.
Ellie, sorry to bother you again. Could you please lift the curse on this book?
Lift the curse? Wouldn't the book just disappear?
If it was a normal book, listing the curse may return it to a normal book.
It makes sense. Let's give it a go.
To lift the curse, we just need to grind a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))][/em1] and sprinkle the powder on the book.
1 should suffice. I'll make it right away and bring it here.
Alright, Ellie. I'll keep the book by my side for now, just in case.
I can't read it anymore!
I've already read it nine times!
When did everyone show up!?
Ahem... I'm sorry, Ellie. The book was just so much more entertaining than I expected...
Ellie, you really have a talent for reading storybooks, huh?
Hoho... I came because everyone else was gathered here.
Ellie... Could you read it one more time? I came in halfway and missed the beginning.
Granny, it's fun, right?
It's just as fun no matter how many times I hear it.
I see... It's much more entertaining than the books at home.
It's fun, sure... but I think we should stop now.
I haven't told everyone yet, but this book is... cursed!
A curse... I haven't noticed any strange effects yet, but we'll have to read it again to be sure.
Right, Ellie. Let's read it together again and figure out what this curse is all about!
How about one last time, Ellie?
This is getting worse and worse.
Yeah, Virgil... It really is a cursed book. Everyone just can't resist it.
Anyway, that's it. Everyone, please go home.
If you want to read it again, come back after we lift the curse.
Whyyy...
It's a beautiful day today.
Ellie, you are... reading a children's book, huh?
Yep! Roy! Let's read together!
It's so fun!
Hey, Roy. This book I'm reading to Rubrum is cursed.
We're on the last bit now, so you can listen in if you want.
It's pretty fun.
Really...? Alright then, I'll give it a try.
Wait, what's going on?
Everyone's here... and now Roy too?
What is this? That's not going to impress me easily.
Not at all, Kyla. This is a book worth reading.
Read it with us, Kyla!
Ah, so everyone's here.
I brought some fresh pies...
What is everyone looking at?
Enite, this is serious. Not the time for pies.
Granny Enite, let's read the book together.
Let's read it together. It's really fun. Pies can wait.
Everyone... Ellie, can you just start where you left off?
Aurea, do you have any [em1]cat food bowls[/em1] for sale?
Cat... food bowls?
That's right. I'll take one if you have any.
People do come to me for bowls often... but I never had any bowls for cat in stock.
Really? That's unexpected.
Is it? I don't think anyone will buy them.
No demand, no supply, haha.
That's a shame, because I want one badly.
Why do you want a cat bowl all of a sudden?
Well, because I want to make friends with the village cats.
I want a bowl to feed them fish with. I guess they'll come to me if they know the fish is from me.
Hmm... Offer cats food repeatedly to form a friendly relationship.
That's a good idea.
I didn't expect you to want a cat bowl, but... Okay, it's decided.
I've got a bowl here that I don't know what to do with. Would you like to use it for feeding the cats?
It's too small for humans, but just the right size for cats.
Woah! Great!
You can have it for 30 Gold Coins. Deal?
30 Gold Coins?
It's of top-class quality and very enduring, as long as you find what to do with it.
And I'm giving you a discount because it's been eight years since I last dealt with such bowls.
What do you say, Ellie?
Sounds like a good deal. I'll take it!
Good. I'll add it to the catalogue then. You can buy it anytime.
Thank you, Aurea.
Haha, I should be the one saying thanks.
Now, where should I put this bowl?
I'd like to put it in the village, but I should ask for permission first.
Dear me, you're actually being prudent. That's not very you.
Well, it struck me when I was talking to Aurea.
That makes more sense.
I suppose I should ask someone in charge of the village, say, Enite?
I'll take the bowl and go ask Enite.
The bowl is in place now.
The last step is to fill it with fish, but what kind of fish?
Just place a random kind, since you don't know the preferences of cats.
Will that work? Alright, I'm off fishing.
I forgot the cat bowl. I should get it.
The fish is ready. Will any cat come to eat it?
Fair... but I can't stay here and stare for a whole day.
I've done everything within my power.
So you have, and this place is easily accessible for cats. They'll probably come.
In that case... Let's see which cat will be the first to arrive!
You can come back and check tomorrow.
Okay!
Why isn't it tomorrow <shake>just yet?</shake>
Oh, you've brought the [em1]customized[/em1] furniture.
I guess you rushed over the moment you finished painting?
Huh? How did you know?
Because the furniture has the sheen of fresh paint.
Don't worry. It won't peel off, since you did the finish well.
How is it? Will the customer like it?
Well... I can't present this to the customer.
What?! H-have I messed up?
It's such a perfect customization that I can't stand to part with it. I'd rather keep it.
<wiggle>What?</wiggle>
Hahah, just kidding. I'm certainly not going to keep it.
Come on, you scared me.
The customization turned out much better than I expected. I believe my customer will like it too.
It has breathed new life into the furniture. You must have enjoyed the process too?
Exactly. I was so happy when I managed to apply my ideal color.
I've tasked the right person indeed.
Thank you for your hard work.
And as always, good things deserve good prices.
Whoa! Thank you, Aurea! You're the best!
I'm also glad to try something new.
See you next time then, Ms. Witch.
Hoho, Vinch happens to be making some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reform_Coloritem_Name"))][/em1]. You can ask him.
I need to bring the [em1]chair I was commissioned to remodel[/em1].
I've got a letter!
House decoration, hm? That sounds kind of fun.
But why you, instead of Kyla?
Well, I'll find out once we meet.
Alright. I think I've finished asking.
What's your plan?
To accept the request, of course! It feels so fun.
I knew you would.
Let's talk to Aurea.
Isn't it beautiful?
I guess I'm gifted in [em1]customization[/em1] too.
As your first attempt in customization, it's not bad.
Don't you agree? I'm gonna rework the furniture at home too.
Before that, why don't you deliver the customized piece to Aurea?
Oh yeah! I should show it to Aurea at once. She will like it, right?
Aurea, I want to take your work request. Is that okay?
Sure, I've been waiting for you.
I have to be patient, since I'm the one asking for a favor.
Have you asked the villagers for advice? Think you can manage?
Yup. I have all the [em1]customization[/em1] tips in my head.
Hoho, that confidence is reassuring.
Ready to get started?
Yeah, I'll strive to satisfy both you and your patron.
Good. Here are the furniture of question and the material for customization.
Good luck.
But... you don't seem to have enough space in your bag.
Please empty 2 slots in your bag before you come to me again.
Ellie, how's the furniture [em1]customization[/em1] going?
Hi, Aurea, I've come to help you.
Oh my, I'm glad that the letter interested you.
Ellie, what do you think about [em1]furniture coloring[/em1]?
Furniture coloring?
When I was little, I once painted all the furniture in the kitchen orange with my mom.
You mean, when Aria failed to stop you and had to give in?
Hoho, I've got a similar task for you — furniture [em1]customization[/em1].
In other words, I need you to turn the furniture into a different color.
It's a request from one of my patrons.
And it's not just any color. He wants an unconventional color that can catch people's eye.
When I pondered over the task, it struck me that I could entrust it to an unconventional person.
That's an odd description... Still, I'm glad to hear you say so, and the task seems fun.
But I have no experience in this trade... so there's no telling whether I can handle it.
Just relax. My patron is also quite unconventional. I don't think he will object.
And, I believe you're the right person for this task, Ellie.
Hmm... I don't know.
May I ask the villagers for input first?
Some of them know furniture or colors better than I do.
Sure. I love that idea.
There are a painter and a sundry seller in the village if I remember correctly? And a carpenter too.
They may have useful tips concerning [em1]customization[/em1].
Could you wait until I've talked to them?
Sure. I'm the one asking for a favor. Take your time.
Of course I've heard of it.
It's just a [em1]rumor[/em1], after all.
People have [em1]seen[/em1] it, but no one actually [em1]owns[/em1] it.
Uh... but someone does have it, actually.
Oh my, really? Then acquire it for me, won't you?
I'll make it worth your while.
They only have one rose, so that might be difficult.
I see... I was hoping to see the rare treasure in person.
[em1]Treasure[/em1]?
It's not alive.
But, it looks very much so. That's why they say it's priceless.
There's even a rumor that it brings incredible luck and wealth to its owner.
Ah, what a shame. If the owner ever changes their mind, be sure to tell me.
So, there's nothing else you know?
Hmm... well, it's an old rumor.
Anyone who's [em1]lived long enough[/em1] might have heard of it.
Thank you, but I'm fine.
You mean people whom the flower shop owner has benefited.
Heh, right. And it just so happens that I want to spend Roy's tip.
Tip?
Roy's excellent skills often earn him tips.
But he wouldn't accept them, no matter how I persuaded him.
I ended up keeping the money as a fund, and helping him with it when he needs money.
It has accumulated into a large sum, and I was wondering how I should spend it.
Don't get your hopes up, though. I'll try to ask them, but they may not write it.
They will, because Roy's flowers can touch people's hearts.
Can't argue with that. I've seen many people whose days were brightened by those flowers.
Alright, I'll do my best.
I know those customers. I just need to send the requests?
Right, could you do it for me?
I'll use the fund to pay the postage for these letters.
[em1]Gold Coin Pouch Trading Chest[/em1]?
Basically, it's those places where you exchange unneeded stuff for pouches of Gold Coins.
You can finally put whatever is rotting in your backpack to good use.
Indeed, I can take the opportunity to organize my backpack and storage, and even make some money at the same time.
Aiden would have burst into tears if he heard the word "organize" coming out of your mouth.
Aurea, I need the house blueprints again.
Buy anytime you like. Hoho.
Good news for everyone.
Actually, I had already prepared the blueprints that might be needed.
Fast!
Hoho. While you were clearing the village's thorn bushes, I was making preparations too.
Information is life for a merchant. I’ve already told you that once, haven’t I?
Aurea, do you know the festival is coming up?
Of course! Everyone's buzzing with excitement.
I've already received quite a few orders as well.
Merchants always follow the festival crowds, so this is perfect timing.
Then, how about Aurea joining the festival too?
Am I invited as well?
It's the villagers' festival... is it alright if I join?
Of course. You've helped out so much already.
I usually don't enjoy these things too much...
But if Ellie personally invites me, I'll be happy to participate.
Oh, and could I also ask you to deliver this invitation?
I met this person on the train. He used to live around here.
He's a bartender on the train.
Since I was invited, I'll deliver it free of charge.
I should be the one saying thanks.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FestivalInvitation_Name"))] [/em1] Chapter 2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Got the invitation. I will definitely go.
Welcome, it's been a while.
I suppose it hasn't been that long.
Is that so? Perhaps it's been a while since I last came here.
Did you remove them? The prickly vines?
Yes, it's nothing special.
Is that so? You're humble.
But you did really well.
This village has been really gloomy for the past few years.
I'm just getting started.
That's a big start, because the disappeared hope is reviving.
So, never give up on this village.
Okay, don't worry. I'll never give it up no matter what happens.
You sound reliable.
By the way, did you happen to bring the thing you promised last time?
Are you talking about yacon melon?
No!
You promised the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RoasterHandle_Name"))] for the Roaster.
I’m kidding. Of course I brought it.
But since this guy broke his leg...
I don’t think I can bring proper products for a while.
Oh really? I feel sorry for him.
Thank you for your concern. But don't worry. It will get better soon.
I don't have any great item in stock, but I do have a good offer for both of us. Do you want to hear it?
Sure, what is it?
As you can see, Wisteria is not the best place to shop...
I'll make it better soon!
Yeah, but I didn't mean it that way.
However, there is a good witch here, and I want to use that to our advantage.
Is there such a witch here?
That's what I'm saying. I can't even see one from up here.
I'm positive I have an eye for both people and things.
So Ellie, I want to entrust you with some work. What do you think?
Naturally, you will also receive proper wages, since good things deserve good prices.
Really? You mean me?
Really? You mean her?
Yeah. The work will usually be [em1]potion[/em1] crafting or [em1]life form gathering[/em1].
Of course I like it!
Naturally, I'll also look at the quality of products properly.
After all, only good products can fetch good prices.
Listen carefully, Ellie. It means bad prices for bad products.
Just like the talking hat said. Therefore...
It's Virgil. A hat that deserves a bad price, I suppose.
I'm counting on you then, Ellie and Virgil.
Okay, we'll work hard.
Since I'm not a witch, I only want [em1]candies[/em1] edible for even non-witches.
I'm always purchasing all kinds of candies. Come to me whenever you want.
Yeah, okay.
Then, can I talk about work right away?
Since I’m not a witch, I will only sell the [em1]candies[/em1] that can be used by non-witches.
Potion Deliverys refresh every [em1]Monday[/em1] and [em1]Thursday[/em1].
After you accept a Delivery order, you need to deliver the potions before the next [em1]day of refresh[/em1].
For example, Delivery orders accepted on Monday must be completed no later than Wednesday, and those accepted on Thursday must be completed no later than Sunday.
I've got more time than I expected.
Crafting takes time, after all.
I'm always purchasing. Come and sell potions whenever you want.
But the potions in Delivery orders can fetch a higher price, so think twice.
But you must deliver once you [em1]promise[/em1].
That’s because [em1]trust[/em1] is important.
So can I ask for a favor right away?
There is no potion that can lift the curse now.
I can probably make them with the ingredients I picked up at the workplace earlier.
Shall I give her the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UncurseCandy_Name"))]?
Would you like to try this?
May the blessings of nature be with you...
Hello...?
Yes, hello.
Am I speaking [em1]properly[/em1] now?
Yes, I think so.
Wow, thank you so much. To hell with nature.
I guess it really was a curse.
I met an old man in the jungle west of here. He was apparently suspicious.
I simply couldn't ignore such a well made wooden statue of a monkey.
After I bought it, I could only talk about praising nature...
I tried to speak sarcastically, or write, but all that came out were praises for nature. Pure torture.
I hope nature just rots and dies.
Still, I'm glad the curse was easily removed.
Oh, thank you so much! My name is [em1]Aurea[/em1].
<shake>How long has it been since I said my name...</shake>
My name is Ellie. I'm an apprentice witch.
Oh, did you come to this village to be an apprentice?
I was on a train, but I got off for a moment and It left without me...
Oh dear...
I wanted to enter the village, but it was blocked off by some prickly vines.
Damn nature.
Thankfully, we found an empty witch's house nearby, so I've been staying there.
An empty... Oh, yes there's a witch's house here. That's good.
I've business in the village too, but the vines stopped me. Nature be damned.
I'll be here for a while, so let me know if you need anything.
Oh, then... Can I ask you a favor?
Not a favor, but a [em1]fair price[/em1].
The tools were broken when I was trying to use the Dispensary at the Witch's House.
Do you have any tools or parts?
What kind of tools or parts do you need?
I need a glass bottle for the [em1]Extractor[/em1] and a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RoasterHandle_Name"))] for winding the [em1]Roaster[/em1].
Wait a minute... I’ll look for them.
But Ellie, do you have any money?
I do. Mom gave me pocket money when I came out.
You think you'll be able to buy witch tools with just enough pocket money to buy a snack or two?
Oh, yeah?
What if I don't have enough money?
Since you have tools, make and sell potions or something.
You can also sell candies now.
Only if there are people to buy them.
I'm back.
Here you are.
<shake>How much is this?</shake>
Oh, nevermind. This is return for breaking my curse.
Wow, thank God.
Unfortunately, I don't have any [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RoasterHandle_Name"))] for the Roaster.
Will you be staying at the village? If so, I'll bring it next time.
I'll charge you for it then, however.
Good, please bring it then.
Okay. I’ll write [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RoasterHandle_Name"))] in the memo.
Oh, and take this too.
Since the worth of the bottle earlier wasn't enough, you can have this as well.
It's an [em1]atlas[/em1], including maps of the surroundings.
But it's not complete. Please find time to fill in the missing part.
I've included maps of the surroundings. You can check them out later.
I almost got lost. Thank you!
This is to repay the medicine fee you gave me. No need to thank me.
This is a bonus. Now you can thank me.
Haha, alright, thank you.
Sure, looking forward to your next visit.
Now we are finally able to fix the Extractor.
But are you really going to stay in this village?
I should until the train comes.
I have no choice.
No, I mean, are you really going to leave when the train comes?
As for that question...
I'll decide when it does come.
Let's just fix the Extractor first.
Something on your mind?
Want some water?
What’s up?
Hello, Mr. Bartender.
Hey! Want a drink?
No, I don't drink alcohol. Do you have any tea?
Then I'll have a cup of that.
The tea has alcohol, though. Is that okay?
But then that's just alcohol. Alcohol with tea.
Potayto, potahto.
You know your way out, right?
The [em1]exit[/em1] is [em1]next to the sofa[/em1] down there.
I knew that.
... Then can I ask you a question instead of a drink?
Anytime.
Do you know why the train stopped all of a sudden?
I saw a [em1]mysterious tree[/em1] outside the window.
Let me know if you need anything to drink.
I've been here with you the whole time.
I know as much as you.
Does the train stop often?
No. Never.
Time is money. If there's no good reason, [em1]it never stops[/em1].
Once they fix the problem, it will leave [em1]right away[/em1].
The crew member just said we'll be leaving [em1]tomorrow morning[/em1].
Oh, then I guess we're leaving tomorrow morning.
A [em1]mysterious tree?[/em1] What did it look like?
It was a [em1]gigantic shining tree[/em1].
A [em1]shining tree?[/em1] I've never heard of such a thing.
I suppose large trees are not that uncommon here, though.
Huh... like the one I just mentioned?
Hm, but that tree wasn't shining.
It was just a [em1]large tea tree[/em1].
Where was the tree?
I'm not sure whether there's a path leading to it...
You'll see it if you climb to the [em1]highest point of the mountain[/em1].
I'll go have a look. Thank you.
Don't forget, the train will leave once the problem's fixed.
I wonder what’s out there?
I took a look outside since the train had stopped...
...And it looked similar to the [em1]village[/em1] where I used to live.
There's a [em1]village[/em1]?
It's nowhere to write home about.
Nothing compared to a sprawling city like Highlion.
At least it should be better than a boring large Witch's House.
I suddenly have a bad feeling about this.
Why are you working here as a bartender, and not at a bar?
I may not look the part, but I used to be quite the big deal back in the day.
What sort of work do you do here?
Cocktails are my specialties.
I like making drinks, but I like drinking them as well.
I'm mixing my life and changing the alcohol.
Wait, I think it's the other way around.
I'm just an average [em1]bartender[/em1] working in the most expensive place in the world.
What brings you to this very expensive train?
I thought you were listening to our conversation?
I stopped listening when it got boring.
I'm going to be an [em1]apprentice[/em1] at the Witch's House in [em1]Highlion[/em1].
After working as an apprentice for [em1]3 years[/em1], I will able to [em1]graduate[/em1] from the School for Witches.
Wow! [em1]Highlion[/em1], huh? That's a busy place, isn't it?
So they say.
That's probably why you got the train ticket for free.
You must be someone special.
I don't really care about that kind of thing, though.
[em1]"That kind of thing"[/em1] is what's important at the end of the day.
It's best to just suck it up. You'll be glad you did later down the road, you know.
Yeah, [em1]"later"[/em1]...
I used to own a [em1]bar[/em1].
In this area?
Sure did. My wife and I, the [em1]two of us[/em1]...
Woah, you’re both bartenders.
I met her at work, after all.
We had to move due to circumstances, though, so here we are now.
I hope a time comes when you two open up a bar again.
Anyone ask?
Virgil, shut up.
You must've been very popular.
There were customers who’d visit the bar just to see me.
Even to this day, I still take pride in these [em1]eyelashes[/em1] of mine.
After all, even my wife said she fell in love with them first.
Woah...
A romantic tale that starts with eyelashes...
We only sell alcohol at the moment.
Can you take a look at my shoes?
Your shoes? What for?
From what I've heard, you have to take your shoes off before you step foot into Highlion Station.
You work at the train so you know what I'm talking about, right?
Oh, that story.
Alright. I've seen plenty of [em1]confused[/em1] passengers who were all dressed up for Highlion, only to find themselves in the wrong shoes.
If you're wearing shoes of that sort, I'd advise you to untie them in advance.
"O ye who reacheth Highlion, look first upon thy shoes!" Or so that's how the saying goes.
See, Virgil? I was right!
These slip-on boots Mom gave me tell me just as much.
Those are some nice boots.
Right? Mom bought them for me when she found out I was graduating magna cum laude.
It sure is amazing you're graduating magna cum laude despite your antics.
You gonna keep up with that attitude of yours?
Haha. Hearing the two of you speak, I have a feeling that boredom won't be an issue.
Nope. It's so boring.
Aren't you bored, Mr. Bartender?
I've gotten used to it.
But it's certainly gotten less boring, thanks to your chat with your hat.
You've been listening?
Other passengers would've all heard about your arson at the School for Witches by now, if there were any.
I didn’t set it on fire!
Uh, sure, there was a fire, but that was because I shook a potion five times and made it explode.
Potions must be shaken three times only. Even a non-witch like me knows that.
Exactly!
How can you not try shaking it four times having heard that?
But you said you shook it five times.
Nothing happened on the fourth time, so I shook it once more.
An inquisitive mind. You've already got the makings of a fine witch.
Thanks for the praise.
I wasn't praising you.
I should be on my way then.
Alright, have a fun trip.
You can't act like a country bumpkin once you're in the city, got it?
You're not going to ask just one person, are you?
Whatever research you do, one sample is never enough, you know.
Not even the greatest detectives can reach the truth based on a single piece of evidence.
Hmm... You have a point.
Let's ask the others too.
If there is anyone else on this train, that is.
Trains are pretty rare, you know...
So the constructors began to receive all kinds of feedback the moment they built the first station.
That's why we ended up with these strange rules.
Let's ask passengers in other cars too.
I should have torn up that stupid [em1]ticket[/em1] right then and there.
Check out this idiotic patterning. It looks like it has armpit feathers of a phoenix in it!
Although not from the armpit, it definitely has [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Phoenix_Collect_Name"))][/em1] phoenix.
It's to prevent people from [em1]counterfeiting[/em1] such expensive tickets.
You're such a know-it-all. No one asked.
Are you enjoying the most expensive train ride in the world?
For a fine witch such as yourself, I'll give you this instead of the usual spiked tea.
After all, a bartender should never let a customer leave empty-handed.
Wow, it looks delicious. Thank you!
Enjoy your trip, little witch.
I can't believe it! It's here!
Are you really a god? This is my first time seeing a god!
O Black Cat God, could you tell me where Lisa Whitegarden is?
They call it a god, but it's probably just a very long-lived fairy.
Shush.
But why isn't the God speaking?
Isn't it because you didn't ask him the right question?
Is that so?
O Black Cat God, may I know where Lisa Whitegarden, the witch formerly lived here, is now?
Lisa Whitegarden.
Yes! Lisa Whitegarden. Do you know where she is now?
She is in Wisteria.
Wisteria also includes the forests around it, right?
Well, at least we know she's nearby!
She is in the forest.
She has climbed up a tree.
The thunderbolt strikes the swaying branches.
She returns home after falling into the blue river.
Uh... What does this mean?
But I've never seen her in the village...
I don't get what you're saying...
But thank you all the same.
It is natural that humans do not understand the gods.
The gods do not understand humans either.
Doesn't that mean it's pointless to get an answer anyway?
I don't even get what you're saying...
Oh! The [em1]White Cat God[/em1]!
The White Cat God was much easier to talk to when it came into my dreams.
Wasn't that just because it was a dream?
Maybe. But we should give it a shot.
Since the Black Cat God comes out during daytime, let's pray at [em1]night[/em1] then.
Then we won't be able to track Lisa down...
Wouldn't it be better to ask the villagers...
Though I don't really understand what you're saying, thank you, Black Cat God!
Lisa didn't seem to mix much with the villagers.
Even Enite, who lived with her a long time, and Kyla, who was good friends with her, didn't really know her well.
Apart from the villagers, there isn't anyone else we can ask...
Greetings, Black Cat God.
I wish to know which plant has special importance to Wisteria. Could you tell me please?
Oh no... So it's not a proper question after all?
You're not mad... are you? I hope not?
It looks insignificant, but it's crucial... Huh? What is this?
Your prayers ring true. I grant you the flower of the heavens.
P-prayer? Although I did pray...
After so many years, the ruins have regained vitality.
Bless the visitors, and reward the generous with vitality.
Saying something I can't understand, again.
But since it's from a god, it must have some meaning.
This is the source of root. Whoever questions the bloom will fall.
Of course, of course. I'll take it with gratitude.
We'd better ask the [em1]White Cat God[/em1] for the meaning.
The meaning you already know.
There won't be a second chance.
Greetings, Black Cat God! What a lovely day! Haha!
Um... If you don't mind, may I take some of the water in the temple?
I need [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))] to make a potion that can remove prickly vines from the village.
Ellie Blueriver.
Y-yes?
Is that your prayer?
Well... I guess it counts as one...? Because I want some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))]...
If so, show me how eager you are.
Huh? Eager..?
The utmost eagerness can split even the hardest rock.
Ellie Blueriver, you're the one who makes the flowers bloom.
You just need to show me your eagerness.
But how do I show it exactly?
Bow down at the temple 100 times? Or pray piously for 100 days? Isn't it too hard...
I don't think that's necessary.
I guess... I'd better ask the villagers.
By the way, Black Cat God... If...
If I manage to show my eagerness, can I take one more bottle of water?
Hey, are you bargaining with a deity?!
Deities are not someone to haggle over a price with.
I mean! I really need it! I won't abuse it!
You messed it up.
Maybe you now need to devote yourself to serving the Gods to repay.
It... it can't be! Black Cat God may be a fan of riddles, but he isn't greedy!
<shake>R-right?</shake>
<shake>I-if it's no deal... it's fine.</shake>
What? Oh, sure! I will show it clearly, sir.
I know you're ignorant and reckless, but I didn't expect you to be such a daredevil.
Well, I need to repay Diane, after all.
You've got a point, since we can't expose Lisa's "treasure."
Although it was just Virgil's fake "guarantee."
As long as we get it.
It will pay the debt, and we will be able to craft [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonTear_Name"))][/em1]. Kill two birds with one stone.
Without further ado, I'll show my eagerness to the Black Cat God now.
I need to see nothing but your eagerness.
Black Cat God!
How was it? Do you like it?
You... you don't like it?
Phew... That's a relief.
A lasting promise must be accompanied by trust.
I've received Ellie Blueriver's eagerness.
Yeah, sure. Thank you so much, Black Cat God!
I'll use it to remove the prickly vines all over the village.
Now, go to Diane to repay the debt, and buy the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))] recipe[/em1] too.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNotTea_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
To restore the village, I need [lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))]. May I have it?
The stars yet linger in the dark celestial vault.
I don't quite follow you.
‌[lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))], I cannot offer.
From them must you obtain it.
You mean the White Cat God?
When shadows descend, the truth shall unveil itself to you.
Asking the White Cat God may not be the ideal approach for me... Black Cat God, could you directly give it to me?
Please help me this one time, will you?
Hello?
The east is the cradle where...
Alright, alright, you want me to go to the White Cat God.
I'll figure it out. Thank you.
May the deepest night be with you.
Good grief...
I can't remove the prickly vine core without [lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))]...
Anyway, I'll go see the White Cat God.
Gotta wait until night again...
Black Cat God, there's something I hope you could enlighten me about.
Whenever I think I've deepened my relationship with a villager, I feel warmth filling my chest.
I don't think it's just an emotion. But what else could it be?
Prepare yourself to receive the blossoms.
Blossoms?
Blossoms start from tiny droplets.
Could you explain it further?
[em1]Drop of Emotion[/em1].
[em1]Drop of Emotion[/em1]?
It's a visible form of emotions, materialized through distillation.
But I've never experienced this feeling before.
It's not like I didn't have friends!
Drop of Emotion flows between connected hearts.
Wisteria houses powerful bonds.
Well... basically, you're telling me that the village is a special place?
Woah, is this a Drop of Emotion?
But why am I only seeing it now?
Because you've learned about it.
Existence follows awareness.
It's because you've told me about it?
What can I do with it though?
Collect the drops, and the flowers will bloom.
Flowers? But how?
Water them in the village where the bonds are the strongest.
Where the bonds are the strongest...
Shall I go to the fountain?
The bonds are the key.
I see. Much appreciated, Black Cat God.
May you have a night of deep blue.
I told you that it was something magical.
It wasn't just affection. I've got a sixth sense.
You were right, I'll give you that.
Let's go to the fountain.
Why the fountain?
Because that's where the villagers often gather. We've even held parties there.
That will make strong "bonds."
Do you know how to use that droplet though?
No, but I may find out when I reach the right place.
And the spirit is at the fountain.
I can show the drop to it.
Make the flowers bloom.
At the places your heart longs for.
<shake>Caww!</shake>
<shake> Caww!</shake> Spit it out!
Busy! <shake>Caww!</shake> No small talk! <shake>Caww!</shake>
Maintain security! <shake>Caww!</shake> Secret! <shake>Caww!</shake>
Don’t know! <shake>Caww!</shake>
A crow?
[em1]Witch![/em1] <shake>Caww!</shake>
It spoke?
It's a witch's crow.
Oh, it’s a witch’s crow.
The Witch returns! The Witch returns!
This is my first time coming here, though.
[em1]<shake>The Witch Returns!</shake>[/em1]
Not exactly a listener, is he?
Goods and services! <shake>Caww!</shake> Goods and services! <shake>Witches’ Catalogue!</shake>
The Witches’ Catalogue!
I've always wanted to try it out.
You need to head towards Highlion, young lady.
But I can't just starve until I reach the village.
And after I find the village, I will be staying there for a while before I go to Highlion.
Limited time only! Register now for a [em1]gift[/em1]! <shake>Caww!</shake>
Try the [em1]Witches’ Catalogue[/em1]! Try the Witches’ Catalogue!
They’re handing out [em1]gifts[/em1] as well! Plus it’s [em1]limited time[/em1] only!
Multipurpose glue? Kitchen accessories? A Spork?
In any case, I need the [em1]Witches’ Catalogue[/em1].
You can buy [em1]ingredients[/em1] or [em1]potion recipes[/em1] from them.
Alright, let's register for now.
Thank you! <shake>Caww!</shake> Thank you! Visit Employee! <shake>Visit Employee!</shake>
<shake>Caww!</shake> [em1]<shake>Visit Employee!</shake>[/em1]
<shake>Caww!</shake> [em1]<shake>Gift!</shake>[/em1]
I guess it wouldn't hurt to stay here for a while.
[em1]<shake>Closed for the day!</shake>[/em1]
So suddenly?
It's not easy getting the message across to witch's crows.
Hmm, then I guess I should keep searching for the village.
You never know when the Witches’ Catalogue will show up.
Let's stick to the plan and find the village.
Work finished! Work finished! <shake>Closed for the day!</shake>
Goodbye!
This is Diane who brings happiness.
Do you have any questions?
My goal is to get off work on time.
It’s my first time hearing it.
Do you want to repair the Witch's House?
Yes, the floor boards are broken.
That's a big problem.
Hmm, by the way,
does the master witch also agree to it?
She says yes.
Then if I go apply today...
A repair witch will probably come within three days.
The master witch must be present when she arrives. Is that ok?
Oh, now that I think about it, I actually like the flooring as it is!
It's my dream to live in a house with broken flooring!
I...Is that so?
But you could get hurt or something. Repairing it would be...
It's okay! I’m tough!
Hmm... Alright, got it.
Okay, it's up to you to decide. Just let me know if you change your mind.
Yeah, okay!
Well done Ellie.
You refused so "naturally."
I certainly did.
I told you I'm good at acting.
Ha, right.
Ellie! A moment, if you will...
Sniff... Sniff...
Why are you smelling me...?
This scent is unmistakable.
<shake>But I took a shower today!</shake>
You've had an encounter with a [em1]Ritoring[/em1]!
It's a creature that looks like an [em1]acorn[/em1] with a face and limbs.
Have you seen such a creature?
Yeah, I have.
I was picking flowers when a strange acorn appeared and surprised me.
It certainly is quite the sight at first glance.
Ritorings plant [em1]seeds[/em1] in the ground in order to preserve the forest.
They would plant anything that looks like a seed in the ground.
That's why they sometimes even plant [em1]other Ritorings[/em1] or even plant [em1]themselves[/em1].
Themselves?
They say that if you save a buried Ritoring, it'll give you a [em1]gift[/em1] in return.
That [em1]gift[/em1] is very important.
Gifts from Ritorings are in high demand as [em1]ingredients[/em1].
<shake>You're not trying to tell me in a roundabout way that I smell, are you?</shake>
Of course not. Ritorings are creatures you can only find in the forest.
Besides, you smell nice, so there's no need to worry.
I smell [em1]<shake>nice</shake>[/em1]<shake>...?</shake>
In a [em1]good[/em1] way.
No, I don’t think I’ve seen any.
Considering you have the scent of a Ritoring on you, I'd say you passed by it without noticing.
<shake>A scent...</shake>
That's why I'm exchanging [em1]Luna Coins[/em1] for the gifts.
Woah, really?
2 Luna Coins for 1 Ritoring's Gift.
Let me know if you want a deal.
What do you wish to know about Ritorings?
Description
Where to Find Them
Exchange Gifts
Tell me more about the Ritorings.
Where can I find Ritorings?
No, not at the moment.
A Ritoring is a creature that resembles an [em1]acorn[/em1].
They look like cute acorns with a face and tiny arms and legs.
It's still unclear as to whether Ritorings are [em1]animals[/em1], [em1]plants[/em1], or something else.
Some people believe them to be [em1]Forest Fairies[/em1] that preserve the forest.
But upon closer inspection, you'll find that they don't exactly do that.
All they do is just plant [em1]seeds[/em1] they find into the ground.
They plant [em1]anything that looks like a seed[/em1], if we're being precise.
Other Ritorings, tiny balls, pebbles, even themselves.
And so, if you save a buried Ritoring, it will hand you a [em1]gift[/em1] before it leaves.
They usually have a [em1]tall flower[/em1] in their hands.
Ritorings can be found in the midst of forests like these where people rarely visit.
[em1]Bug nets[/em1] cost 10 Gold Coins.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFairyCake_Name"))][/em1] costs 1 [em1]Ritoring’s Gift[/em1].
And many believe a [em1]Ritoring Village[/em1] exists somewhere in the woods.
Woah, a Ritoring Village!
But you’ll find that Ritorings aren’t that different compared to other creatures.
Perhaps us humans simply thought them to be intriguing?
You're smarter than I thought, Diane. I guess first impressions aren't everything.
Just what exactly did you think of me before...
I haven't really seen any lying around.
They're probably [em1]hiding[/em1] here and there.
Ritorings are often [em1]buried in the ground[/em1].
They can also be in [em1]trees[/em1] or [em1]bushes[/em1].
They tend to hold a [em1]tall flower[/em1] in their hands, so you'll be able to find one by looking for that.
Alright. I’ll try to find one.
You don’t have enough [em1]Ritoring’s Gifts[/em1].
Alright then, that'll be 10 Gold Coins.
You can find Ritorings in the forest.
Pay careful attention to the flowers.
Is there anything else you need?
Okay then, let me know if you've changed your mind.
I have it here.
Payment received.
Here’s your [em1]Bug Net[/em1].
Thank you for your business.
Alright then, that’ll be 1 [em1]Ritoring’s Gift[/em1].
I need to think it over a bit more.
Here you go.
Here’s your [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFairyCake_Name"))][/em1].
Alright, I'll be here whenever you need me.
Is there anything else you want to discuss about Ritorings?
I want to go!
The [em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice Recipe[/em1] costs 1 [em1]Ritoring’s Gift[/em1].
A [em1]Witch's Bug Net[/em1] is a tool used by witches to collect creatures.
It’s used to collect small creatures like [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FairyButterfly_Name"))], and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "ShadowFrog_Name"))].
You’ve heard of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFairyCake_Name"))], right?
You betcha! My mom will buy one for me at the end of the week if I've been good for a whole week.
Our wares include the famed Nubicula products.
Nubicula Cupcake! I've never tried one before! The lines were always too long...
I'll give you one as a freebie.
Woah, really? Thanks!
What I have right now is the same thing used in the School for Witches.
Oh, those...
You must've used them recently, since you've just graduated.
I'd always get splinters, so I'd have to sand down the handle before using it.
We make sure they go through an extra quality assurance check, so you needn't worry that much.
So I’ve hardly ever had a chance to eat one.
This is the Twinkle-Twinkle Juice?
Correct, this is the Twinkle-Twinkle Juice.
I've always wanted to have the recipe for it.
After all, no one would be able to study if half the class is shining brightly like a star.
This is the juice that makes your whole body shine brightly.
We'd always gather around the alley behind the school in the evening, and drink it in secret.
But it’s one of the concoctions the professors would never teach us.
Obviously we'd all get caught, since we were all glowing.
Well, now that you're an apprentice witch, you can make it without any worries.
Of course, with it comes great responsibility.
Here’s the [em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice recipe[/em1].
It should've been automatically added to your [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1]. Go check it out.
The [em1]Bug Net[/em1] has been unlocked.
The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))] Recipe[/em1] costs 1 [em1]Ritoring's Gift[/em1].
The recipe for the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))].
Here’s the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))] recipe[/em1].
It was meant for therapeutic uses, but in reality the potion is widely misused for entertainment.
Entertainment?
That's right. You can fool around in your dreams.
After all, you can have all kinds of experiences safely in your dreams.
But be warned, for it is precisely this reason why it can be addictive.
Alright, got it.
You don’t have enough Gold Coins.
You’re here to exchange Ritoring’s Gifts!
[em1]1[/em1] Ritoring's Gift will be exchanged for [em1]2[/em1] Luna Coins.
How many do you wish to exchange?
You don’t have any Ritoring’s Gifts at the moment.
You can exchange them whenever you want.
Thank you. I’ve exchanged them for you.
Please, take all the time you need to think it over.
Thank you. I've exchanged them for you.
Do you wish to exchange more?
I'll be here whenever you need me.
[em1]3[/em1] Ritoring's Gifts will be exchanged for [em1]6[/em1] Luna Coins.
[em1]5[/em1] Ritoring's Gift can be exchanged for [em1]10[/em1] Luna Coins.
[em1]10[/em1] Ritoring’s Gifts will be exchanged for [em1]20[/em1] Luna Coins.
So far, you've exchanged a total of...
[var=System.RitoringPresentNumber] Ritoring’s Gift(s).
You're just getting started. Keep it up!
Wow, you gathered a lot!
Amazing! Just a bit more and you'll find them all!
I believe you've found all of them in this forest. Congratulations.
Gather what results from throwing the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NutritionPotion_Name"))][/em1] at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))][/em1].
I should go to [em1]Diane[/em1] if I run out of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NutritionPotion_Name"))][/em1].
Just throw the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NutritionPotion_Name"))][/em1] I gave you at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))][/em1].
Out of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NutritionPotion_Name"))][/em1].
Oh dear. I can give you more, but please save it.
My stock isn't infinite.
Diane, can you read what's written on this note?
A note? Let's see.
Hmm... This is ancient witch language.
See? You're the only one who fell asleep in class.
Hmm... Moon’s...
Moon’s...?
Moon’s...
I can only read up to this.
I've forgotten everything I learned at school.
I forgot everything because it's been a while since I've learned it and I haven't used it either.
That's because Diane graduated a long time ago. What's your excuse?
It hasn’t been that long since I graduated either...
Then, is there any way to decode the ancient witch language?
Of course there is a way!
Ancient witch language is definitely a subject you learn in school.
So, there must be knowledge on the ancient witch language in your head.
You lack not the knowledge but the intelligence to use it.
That hurts a little.
Truth hurts.
That's why I recommend the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "IntUpPotion_Name"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "IntUpPotion_Name"))][/em1]!
It raises your level of intelligence, like memory, deduction, and language.
[em1]Deciphering[/em1] ancient witch language’ll be easy with better memory and deduction.
Sounds like a drug peddler.
This is real. I only sell the recipes approved by the Witch Potion Association.
Careful though, long-term usage can cause minor sequela such as headache, vomiting and intellectual decline.
They don't sound minor...
Don't worry because there will be no problem at all if you use it once or twice only.
I'll add the recipe for [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "IntUpPotion_Name"))][/em1]. Feel free to purchase it if you need it.
Wait, I forgot the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UnreadableMemo_Name"))][/em1].
Did you say you couldn't get much sleep lately?
Because you had some kind of dream?
That’s right.
Hm, well...
A fainting pillow! The moment you lie down, you fall asleep as if fainted, hence the name.
No, I...
This is the work of Herencia, who is called the master of sleep and the queen of the night.
Even if you drink [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))] beforehand, you'll sleep like baby and not even remember your dreams. Try it!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))]!
Would you like to buy a fainting pillow?
I need to craft a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))].
Alright, got it. I'll also put [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))] on the list.
And also give me the pillow.
Thank you. Please order the pillow through the Catalogue.
Diane, can you also get me the recipe for [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CurseWatchCandy_Name"))][/em1]?
Sure. I'll add it right away, since I happen to have it in stock.
Are you going to use it yourself?
Uh... that's right, but is there a different version with improved taste?
You're lucky. This happens to be an improved version.
It used to taste like rotten grilled fish left at room temperature for 3 days...
They say it has now been improved to taste like nasal mucus from when you catch a cold.
If you feel uncomfortable eating it, you can also consider grinding and sprinkling it.
Was there such a method?!
I told you to read the book to the end.
Shush...
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1]. It's a potion I've always wanted to try making.
You too, Diane?
Sure. It's the highlight of the [em1]Star Gun Festival[/em1].
Right. I liked the fireworks on the last day the most, too.
There's somewhere I want to use it in this time. Can I get the recipe?
Hmm... It’s not hard to register the recipe in the Catalogue but...
Ellie, as you likely already know, it's forbidden to craft a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1] while enrolled in the School for Witches.
But I’m already an apprentice!
In that case, you can, but there are conditions.
You have to report how many and for what purpose to the Witch Administration.
<shake>Th.. the.. Administration...</shake>
Ellie, you are like an unfinished hat.
Still haven't found the recipe?
T... They say I would have to report it to the Administration...
Oh, you can just use the master witch's name.
Please fill out the master witch’s name, your name, the intended purpose, and how many, right here.
Okay, I will add it for you.
Phew... My heart pounds out of my chest every time something like this happens.
Stop acting, it's terrible. You'll get caught.
But I have no choice.
I wrote down [em1]Mom's name[/em1] because it was the only name I could think of... That should be fine, right?
I’m really getting worried.
Before the laws, a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1] would often blow the butts off people or burn down houses...
My name is Diane. Thank you for coming today.
Let's go make a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1], since we've accomplished our goal.
<shake>T-the master witch's name...?</shake>
What? Ellie, you little furball!
You're writing MY name with your hellish handwriting?
It looks like your master witch has quite a temper.
If you'd like, you can also put the name of someone else.
<shake>T... Then...</shake>
<shake>Aria... and Ellie. Just 1. For the village party...</shake>
I like [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DangleMango_Name"))] sherbet[/em1]. It tastes refreshing and would be a great match.
Oh... A glass of [em1]sweet wine[/em1] after work with a dessert is the best.
A slice of heaven to reward a hard day of work!
I think I understand how that feels, that's me when I eat a Nubicula cupcake.
Wonderful! I'm glad you understand how happy sweets can make a person, Ellie.
Do you have any recommendations for the menu, Diane?
Hm... I like sweet wine with desserts, but some people think that's too much.
I often pair [em1]sweet wine[/em1] with [em1]cheesecake[/em1] or [em1]dark chocolate[/em1].
Donuts are best when there's a layer of cream spread on them or fruit toppings.
I once went to a shop which served donuts with a chocolate coat. Crack the coat
and the glorious chocolate cream filling would ooze out of it. The donut was really chewy and the fruits served with it were fresh. It was a match made in heaven.
<shake>No, no</shake>. I'm looking for a recipe for donuts, Diana!
Oh, you wanted recipes?
Well, though the Witch's Catalogue contains everything on anything under the sun...
But I don't think the Witch Potion Association would have any recipe for donuts...
I'm really sorry I couldn't help.
Why not have a look close by?
Recipes are usually stored in [em1]homes[/em1] after all.
If you ask [em1]longtime village residents[/em1] or [em1]people who have always cooked[/em1], you should be able to find what you need.
That's a great idea. Thank you, Diane!
Though there isn't a Donut Association, I'll be sure to use the Witches' Catalogue!
It's a promise, Ellie.
Thank you for dropping by, this service was provided by Diana.
Too bad the Witch's Catalogue only sells recipes that the Witch Potion Association has approved.
Exactly. <shake>Why on earth</shake> is there no witches' association for donuts?
It's too bad. It would have been really helpful if it existed!
I think part of that's just my personal preference, but... yes.
Ellie, are you interested in [em1]making a large sum of money[/em1]?
Making a large sum of money?
Of course I am!
Hey, isn't that a typical line to start a fraud?
Now that you mention it...
It's not like what you're thinking... What I want to say is, do you want to earn more money...
That is... also a typical speech of a scammer...
Don't tell me...
I mean clean money...
Well... Let me rephrase.
Ahem...
Ellie! We're offering a service that's yet to be listed in the Witches' Catalogue. Are you interested?
Are you sure it's a legal service?
It's a [em1]legal and official[/em1] service that helps deliver candies specified by the Witch Administration.
Known as "visiting candy delivery"!
Candy delivery?
But isn't the Association purchasing candies all the time?
The candy purchase service will provide a fixed list. Submit the listed candies and the Association will buy them at higher prices.
Since the prices are higher than daily purchase, the service is quite popular.
Sounds pretty nice, huh?
Most Witch's Houses are participating.
But to be qualified for candy delivery, you need to prove your skills first.
Prove my skills?
After you've passed the potion making test, you can deliver potions.
I'm confident about my test taking skills, you know!
Ellie, your expression doesn't match your line.
I graduated magna cum laude from the School for Witches.
And I didn't win this honor with rock paper scissors.
You won it with talents, last-minute cramming and by chance.
The witch's broom test was a good example...
Ahhhh!
But I always got full score in crafting.
Then there's no problem!
I'll give you a test list then.
Make all the candies on the list successfully and you pass.
Show me what you're capable of, magna cum laude graduate.
Are you here to deliver candies?
We're now purchasing this candy.
I've checked the candies you delivered.
And the candy quality is far better than I expected.
You really deserve your honor!
I certainly do.
That means you've passed the test.
Great!!
Then, I'll brief you about the candy delivery [em1]rules[/em1].
The potion delivery list [em1]refreshes[/em1] every [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Monday"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Thursday"))][/em1].
You can deliver any time before the next refresh day.
But note that if you fail to deliver before the next refresh day, this order will become unavailable.
In the beginning, you'll only get one list at a time.
Then, I’ll get the list ready so that you can start from tomorrow.
Thanks a million.
Take your time. No need to hurry.
Oh, and there's one more thing.
I hope you could go find the merchant for humans in this village.
You mean Aurea?
If that's the name of the person purchasing candies in the village, yes.
Wha do you want Aurea for?
Most merchants of the human society also purchase candies,
and they usually follow the rules of the witch society too.
Since you've passed the test, you can deliver candies in the human society too.
Okay, I'll ask Aurea about it.
The number of lists and items required will increase as you complete more orders, so keep up the good work.
You've passed the test, so you can deliver candies from now on.
Usually, the delivery list refreshes every [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Monday"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Thursday"))][/em1], but this time, I'll make an exception and refresh it today.
Hello, Diane.
*Zzz*
<shake>Diane!!!</shake>
Hello! This is the [em1]Witches' Catalogue[/em1] that gives you the most inexpensive products of the best quality!
This is Diane to bring you happiness... Oh, it’s you, Ellie. Welcome.
I’m sorry, that was unprofessional of me.
Did something happen?
Hmm... I'm not sure if it's okay to tell you this, since we just met.
What is it? Maybe I can help.
Hmm… did you know that you can also sell potions via the Witches' Catalogue?
Oh, really?
The Witch Administration sometimes bulk buy potions for massive use.
And we buy [em1]potions on the delivery list[/em1] of the day at a [em1]higher price[/em1].
You can select one out of three in the list provided and deliver [em1]within 2 days[/em1].
Since we're [em1]buying at a higher price[/em1], don't lose this [em1]nice opportunity[/em1].
And there's also the [em1]Visiting Special Potion Purchase Service[/em1]!
Some witches also sell potions via the Witches' Catalogue.
Recently there have been frequent complaints of bad potions.
Trust in the Witches' Catalogue’s potion quality. Trust in the Administration!
As a result, the Administration issued a notice to each Catalogue sales person to test the suspicious potions.
The problem is that it also concerns some potions I purchased...
As you know Ellie, potion quality is also a matter of a witch's confidence.
You can’t do it yourself, Diane?
I need a witch to accompany me in the test, for certification.
I've prepared a small reward… some [em1]Nubicula Cupcakes[/em1].
[em1]Nubicula Cupcakes[/em1]!! My mom will buy one for me at the end of the week if I've been good for a whole week.
So naturally, I've hardly had any so far...
If it's alright, may I ask for your help?
Alright, I’ll help!
Thank you. Please take this first.
A bird cage?!
To test as quickly as possible, I also caught a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))][/em1].
Just throw the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NutritionPotion_Name"))][/em1] I gave you to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))][/em1].
Then, I’ll record the details like the date, weather, time, wind direction, etcetera.
It feels... very formal.
Also, please let me know if you make a bad throw.
When the [em1]results[/em1] appear, please [em1]gather[/em1] them and take a close look.
Hmm... It looks like there's no more room in your bag.
Please come back once you’ve organized your bag.
I was planning to use the potions I had saved for the event this time as well, but...
Since it’s an event organized by the administration, mistakes must be avoided.
Hello! This is the [em1]Witches’ Catalogue[/em1] that gives you the most inexpensive products at best prices!
This is [em1]Diane Greenwind[/em1] who brings happiness. Nice to meet you!
Yes, hello. I’m Ellie, an apprentice witch.
Yes, nice to meet you, Ellie!
What I must help you with today is... Oh, you're [em1]registering[/em1] for the first time!
It must have been inconvenient for you to not be able to use the Witches' Catalogue.
Just a minute... Okay, thank you for waiting.
So, I need to see the [em1]master witch[/em1] before you register. Is she inside?
M...
The [em1]<shake>master witch</shake>[/em1]!?
Yes, I need the [em1]master witch's signature[/em1] to register you on the Witches' Catalogue.
<shake>Oh, that’s... Um... I’m...</shake>
[em1]<shake>Hey Ellie!</shake>[/em1]
Fooling around while I'm out? You didn't forget to register on the Witches' Catalogue, did you?
<shake>Eh...Huh?</shake> Oh, no, I didn’t forget. Of course not.
Oh, I guess the master witch is [em1]away[/em1] now?
Are you talking through [em1]that hat[/em1]?
<shake>Y...Yes!</shake>
Stay quiet, Ellie. You [em1]unfinished dumb hat[/em1] of a little rascal.
Why can't you even do such a little thing properly?
I told you to tell me when the Witches' Catalogue employee came!
I'm sorry, I was just about to tell you.
Oh... Okay. Then I guess Ellie can just [em1]sign[/em1] instead because the master witch is here!
You'll also receive a [em1]gift[/em1] if you join now.
Woah! A [em1]gift[/em1]? What is it?
A [em1]Witch's Broom[/em1] that makes your life much easier.
A [em1]Witch’s Broom[/em1]! Finally!
You can just sign here and here.
Okay, just a minute...
Yes, that’s it. Then I’ll explain [em1]how to use the Witches’ Catalogue[/em1]. Would you like to hear it?
Listen to the explanation.
Yes, please explain.
Every morning, a Witches' Catalogue employee will come. In this case, it will be me.
I’m planning to be here from 8 am to 6 pm.
You can just purchase the items you need from me during that time.
We do not accept Gold Coins and only accept [em1]Luna Coins[/em1].
What is that thing called [em1]Luna Coin[/em1]?
[em1]Luna Coin[/em1] is the currency used in witch society.
It is called Luna Coin because it is made of an ore with the power of the moon...
Don't you already know that since you were also raised in a witch society, Ellie?
I think I learned it in school... It's just that I don't think I called money something else in my life.
After all, only Luna Coins are used in the witch society.
But how do I earn Luna Coins?
I guess you don’t have enough Luna Coins!
What...? Basically yes.
That's exactly why the Witch Administration is running a [em1]candy purchase service[/em1]!
Please let me know at any time since we purchase regardless of the type.
So do you have any more questions?
No, not anymore.
Alright, then feel free to talk to me if you need anything.
Yes, go ahead.
The gift...
Right, I’ll give it to you now.
Wow, thank you!
Finally! My own broom!
Have a nice day. This has been Diane Greenwind of the Witches' Catalogue.
Do you think it went well?
Yes, it looks like the urgent fire is out.
How was my [em1]acting skill[/em1]?
You? I'm the one who did the acting. All you did was stutter.
The stuttering was all an act!
This might become a problem later on.
I told you I’m good at acting.
No, not your poor acting skill but the fact that you lack a [em1]master witch[/em1].
The [em1]master witch[/em1] must be at the witch's house. We can't just have an apprentice witch.
Can't you just keep acting?
How long will it work?
And there's still the matter of the [em1]witch who was originally here[/em1] at this witch's house.
It would be nice if we know who that witch is.
Let's ask the villagers later on.
The [em1]witch who was originally here[/em1]...
Could also be [em1]someone with malice[/em1].
Let me mount my broom and go sell potions right away.
You need to get to Enite.
Oh, you're right, but no need to hurry.
Do not listen.
I don't think I need to hear it.
Are you sure?
Ellie! You unstitched fur hat! You're clueless about all this! Listen!
Listen carefully!
Okay, okay! I'll listen!
You want to deliver the candies of the selected order?
This is Witch Administration's candy delivery service.
Do you want to fulfill this delivery order?
Although it's your own choice, you'd better double-check it.
Thank you for your cooperation. The deadline is [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  GetGlobalVariable("$711")))][/em1].
Please think carefully before you decide.
Thank you for your cooperation. Potions delivered.
[em1]Cancel[/em1] the Delivery order?
Come back anytime.
This isn't a delivery order you chose.
Make sure you deliver before the deadline, or you will fail.
Just deliver all goods required by the delivery order before [em1]this [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  GetGlobalVariable("$711")))][/em1].
If you can't manage, or wish to switch to another Delivery order, you can [em1]cancel[/em1].
You've reached the [em1]delivery limit[/em1] of this candy theme. Cannot deliver anymore.
Delivery completed. Cannot be selected.
Please select another delivery.
Diane, can the underground workshop be expanded?
Sure, the Witches' Catalogue offers [em1]workshop expansion service[/em1].
But the materials need to be provided by the Witch House, which means you should [em1]pay the commission and provide materials[/em1].
Witch's House expansions usually rely on the power of home spirits, though...
If the home spirit isn't powerful enough, or the expansion is not possible due to other reasons, Witches' Catalogue will help.
That's usually the case for underground spaces.
Yes, and it's true for the underground workshop here.
In this case, Witches' Catalogue will work with the home spirit to expand the place.
Oh, and you can now purchase [em1]work tools[/em1]. Let me introduce the service.
Work tools?
From now on, you can buy the tools for processing and crafting from the Witches' Catalogue.
With better tools, you can hopefully enjoy a more comfortable witch life.
Which means I can have multiple Roasters or Witch's Pots, right?!
Well... not really.
Tools placed in each witch's workshop must [em1]strictly[/em1] adhere to the rules provided by the Witch Potion Association.
You can only place [em1]1[/em1] of each [em1]processing tool[/em1] and [em1]crafting tool[/em1].
It's a matter of safety. Please do keep these rules.
But don't worry. There's no limit to tools other than the processing and crafting tools.
You can arrange the storage and Incubator in the style of your choice.
Oh, and one last thing.
To encourage all the witches to [em1]upgrade their tools[/em1], Witches' Catalogue purchases second-hand tools.
If you've bought better tools, you can sell your old tools [em1]to the Witches' Catalogue[/em1].
We buy for higher prices than the market average, so do sell your old tools to the Witches' Catalogue.
Hello, Diane! I'd like to order some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))]s.
Welcome, Ellie! Feel free to use Witches' Catalogue anytime.
What recipes are you looking for?
I need [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SeasoningPotion_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SpotlightPotion_Name"))] [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))]s.
So, you're preparing for the party!
But you want [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SeasoningPotion_Name"))]...
I suppose you're going to make [em1]that[/em1].
Diane, you know [em1]that[/em1] too...?
Sure! Random ingredient stew is an event for every boarder of School for Witches.
But I haven't heard that term for a while since I graduated.
And I've never made it outside school.
Have a great party!
Satisfaction guaranteed with superfast service! Adding it right now!
Check the refreshed delivery orders and choose one to fulfill.
I noticed that you have a failed Delivery order.
Unfortunately, you cannot fulfill expired Delivery orders.
The good news is, you always get new orders to choose from.
Just forget about the failed orders and check the new ones.
The delivery lists that spawn today will last until this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", GetGlobalVariable("$711")))][/em1].
I’m well aware of the [em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice[/em1].
Do you sell [em1]recipes[/em1] as well?
I sure do. [em1]Recipes[/em1] are in stock as well.
Please check the Witches' Catalogue.
Oh, and you can get gifts if you buy the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] recipe now.
If you're going to buy the recipe, I'll get you the gifts right away.
Gifts?
Yes, it's a latest trend in the witch society to use [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] for decorative lighting.
Witches' Catalogue is seizing the opportunity to launch a "buy recipe, get [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColoredBeads_Name"))][/em1]s for free" event.
Add the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] you craft into a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColoredBeads_Name"))], and it'll emit light of the corresponding color.
Wow, that's exactly what I'm looking for!
The gifts are yellow, pink, or silver [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColoredBeads_Name"))]s.
Which color do you want?
Your free [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColoredBeads_Name"))]s. Here you are.
Pink
But isn't silver its innate color?
It is, but this silver is brighter than the innate one.
I believe you've already bought a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] recipe?
Yes, but I wonder how I can change the color.
Oops, sorry, I almost forgot to give you the gift.
Let me get the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BrokenIncubator_Name"))][/em1].
Diane, could you check this out for me?
Oh, it's an [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))].
Wait, this is...!
What's the matter?
This [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] is a model that has been recalled long ago due to a fatal defect!
Why didn't you apply to Witches' Catalogue earlier?
I'll give you a replacement at once!
Well... What's the fatal defect?
It seems that neither you nor the master witch has experienced it, Ellie.
Umm... Should I tell someone who hasn't experienced it about such a scary happening...
I-is it that bad...?
Ellie, do you know what an [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] is for?
Er, nope.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] is an advanced witch tool only for witches that have mastered collecting.
If you use it, you can get [em1]a lot of ingredients[/em1] out of [em1]just a few collected items[/em1].
Does that mean only veteran witches are allowed to use it while apprentice witches are not?
No! Ellie, you've got the [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1] issued by the School for Witches, right?
Only plants and animals with a sufficient level of [em1]regional Encyclopedia completion[/em1] can be used in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))].
Which means, you can become skillful at using the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] if you work hard to complete the researches in the Encyclopedia.
Wow, this will spare me the efforts of collecting items from the wild.
Exactly. It's especially favored by witches who need to [em1]travel a lot collecting items[/em1].
And you can place [em1]multiple [/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))]s in your [em1]workshop[/em1].
I'll register the new model in the [em1]Witches' Catalogue[/em1] for you this time.
Wow, thank you, Diane!
So, what on earth is the fatal defect?
Sigh... I was trying to distract you because I didn't want to talk about that scary happening.
As I just said, you can get [em1]materials[/em1] if you put [em1]collected items[/em1] into the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))].
Of course, it takes [em1]a while[/em1] for it to process the items.
But as for this [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] model you brought...
A witch once added collected items into it. When she went to the workshop to check it on the next day, she found...
Found what...!
A full pot of salty fried food!
They say that the witch was a fried food researcher. She went into the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] workshop by mistake, and caused the accident.
It'd be fine if the collected items turned sweet, but anything put in that Incubator turned salty... Isn't that scary?!
I don't think that's the point...
The new [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Incubator"))] won't go wrong, will it?
Ahem, sure. After all, Witches' Catalogue has strengthened supervision of product quality since then.
You can use it with confidence.
Wow, thanks a million!
Huh... But a pot of fried food doesn't sound so scary.
Just imagine materials such as [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Phoenix_Collect_Name"))] fried in oil.
Witches' Catalogue, always at your service.
I don't have any request now.
Feel free to talk to me about anything.
Please use the Witches' Catalogue to submit candies.
Looking forward to your next visit.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "EncyclopediaRank"))]
You really worked hard for the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "EncyclopediaRank"))], didn't you?
This is a reward from the School for Witches.
I'll check the other pages, too.
There seems to be nothing else.
Come to me once you’ve raised your [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "EncyclopediaRank"))].
There’s no reward you can receive at this moment.
Be sure to let me know when you get your [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "EncyclopediaRank"))] to the highest level, because you'll get a reward.
The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))][/em1] you requested is over here.
Come take a look again.
There is no registered [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))][/em1].
Please order general goods via the Witches' Catalogue.
I have something to show you!
Alright, I'm coming.
Wow, what's that next to you?
That's why I called you here, Ellie.
This is the [em1]Witches' Catalogue[/em1].
Finally!
From now on, you can use the Witches' Catalogue.
It works [em1]the same as before[/em1]. There's no need to worry.
Ah, so you won't be coming anymore, Diane?
Not exactly.
I'll leave the [em1]call bell[/em1] next to the mailbox, so feel free to use it whenever you need me.
Can I call you anytime I want to see you?
Of course! Using the call bell makes it easy to come and go, so it's no problem at all!
Hmm... But I'd prefer you not calling me too frequently.
Okay, got it.
By the way, now that you have the Witches' Catalogue, you can [em1]purchase work tools[/em1].
Work tools are also purchased from the Witches' Catalogue.
I should be on my way.
Call me anytime you need me.
Okay, see you next time.
Also, you might want to buy [em1]better work tools[/em1]...
Better work tools! I want them!
I'm sorry, not now.
Huh... why not?
You'll be able to purchase work tools once you have the Witches' Catalogue.
What? Am I not using the real Witches' Catalogue?
The Witches' Catalogue originally refers to a physical "Catalogue", consisting of papers and a quill.
What you're using now is the [em1]service provided by the Witches' Catalogue[/em1], abbreviated as "Witches' Catalogue".
Since the real Witches' Catalogues are often in short supply...
Therefore, for new witches joining the Witch's House or when the catalogue is out of stock, the staff will provide services personally.
I'm here because the catalogue is constantly out of stock here.
So, the Witches' Catalogue staff aren't actually responsible for the services?
You're correct. The actual service provider is the "Witches' Catalogue".
So, when will the Witches' Catalogue be officially issued?
As I said, it's always in short supply...
Just be patient. I'll urge them to [em1]replenish the stock[/em1].
Once it's ready, I'll let you know immediately.
But what does that have to do with work tools?
Because when the Witches' Catalogue is officially issued, I can easily travel through it.
That way, I can bring heavy work tools to you.
You must have been busy. It’s nice to see you!
Now, please choose the direction you want the workshop to expand in.
Left
Right
Down
Cannot expand anymore.
You want to expand the workshop?
Then the following materials are needed.
[Deliver]
Thank you. I'll begin the expansion right away.
Let me know if you need anything.
What would you like to discuss with Diane?
And, of course, I graduated from the School for Witches as well.
When I was in school, I dreamed about graduation. Now, I just want to turn back time.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Diane"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
This currency is highly sought-after because only a handful of witches can process it.
A special material, Lunar Stone, was used in the casting, making it exceptionally gorgeous.
If possible, I'd like to have more of it.
Witch's Broom
Having been a regular of the Witch Administration, it was only natural to become familiar with it.
This is the broom I spent a hefty amount on when I joined Witches' Catalogue Department. We always keep each other company.
A Witch's House best reflects the personality of the master witch.
This one is considered less eccentric than most.
Lucerine Ortu
The place is bustling with witches no matter what time of day.
Especially in the Administration department, it's always crowded... I'd rather not talk about it.
It's another nice day.
I’m Diane Greenwind.
I'm currently working for the Witches' Catalogue Department of the Witch Administration.
What does the Witch Administration do?
We manage and distribute the finances and produce of the Witch Society.
The management of Witch's Houses and the Witches' Catalogue is also an important task of the Witch Administration.
Wow, that’s impressive.
It is, isn't it? The Witch Administration is the department that employs the largest number of witches.
And it's the only building where indoor flights are allowed.
Wow, being able to ride a broom inside a building really sounds fun!
Not if a flying encyclopedia knocks you out while you're blinded by the peanut butter from a flying sandwich that lands on your face.
It sounds like there's a lot of stuff flying.
Be wary of the flying encyclopedia. This is what we say all the time.
It's very heavy, and don't let your guard down even if you evade the first, because the second and third might be on the way.
Speaking of it, I've always been evading encyclopedias.
Do books fly around at the School for Witches too?
No, I just don't like reading.
I like it because it's peaceful here.
It makes me want to just come here.
Do you go to other Witch's Houses too?
Hmm, I think I normally go to three or four places a day.
Wow, it must be hard for you.
Other witch's houses are battlefields.
You must be fast and accurate in handling the orders that are rushing in.
It must be tiring.
Does this village happen to have any bakeries?
Bakery? Not yet.
Not "yet"?
Oh, I didn’t tell you.
The village has been badly destroyed by the prickly vines and the people are all gone.
Oh, I see.
That's why I'm removing the prickly vines and restoring the village.
It's nothing special.
But why a bakery?
It is my hobby to try unique desserts of every village I visit.
I was looking forward to the desserts of this village. What a pity.
There was probably a bakery in the village originally.
I'll let you know if it is restored.
Thank you. It's a deal.
Keep up the hard work today!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Diane"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Diane, do you happen to sell an ingredient called [em1]sacred water[/em1]?
Yes, I have it. Should I put it in the Catalogue if you need one?
Yes, please do that.
Alright, but it's [em1]a little[/em1] expensive. Is that okay?
<shake>How expensive...?</shake>
It costs 150 Luna Coins.
That’s too expensive!
I can't help it because it's a precious ingredient.
Can you... sell on credit...?
Selling on credit is kinda...
I really need that ingredient now. Please!
I will definitely pay you back... The master witch will also stand surety.
[em1]Surety[/em1] is not possible but [em1]guarantee[/em1] is possible.
Just a minute. Let me think about it.
<shake>Would she do it...?</shake>
At times like this, third-class merchants refuse.
Second-class ones just accept.
Then what about the first-class?
They would make you promise to give something bigger.
To rake it in...
That's kinda scary...
I’ve made the decision.
I’ll give you the sacred water [em1]on credit[/em1].
She’s second-class.
Doesn't first-class usually come out here?
I don’t know what you’re talking about...
Don't worry about it.
So, are you really giving it to me on credit?
Yes, I usually don’t, but Ellie is my valued customer.
Since it's an emergency, I will give it to you on credit this one time.
But note that I'm doing it because I trust you and the master witch is standing surety...
I'm only "guaranteeing."
...is guaranteeing. Please don't betray my trust.
Of course! I’ll be sure to pay back. Don’t worry.
Alright, got it! Thank you for your business.
<wave>Ellie~</wave> Hello!
I've got something important today!
Something important... What is it?
Did they find out about my true identity?
W-what? No, no way.
Can you lean over a bit?
<shake>Eek!</shake>
Stop hiding and go ahead. Don't be intimidated.
It's not like this is a match.
Are you here to deliver collected items to use the candy recipe purchase service?
I'll show you a list of the collected items you need to deliver.
[em1]3 candy recipes for delivery[/em1] are available today.
I've checked the potions you delivered.
They are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ToothDecayHealingCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DejavuCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1]
and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "UnluckCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1].
No problem. You earned them, Ellie.
Here, take this too.
Whoa, can I really have it back?
Sure. I only took the item to test your skills. You can't make candies without ingredients.
I've examined it. Now you can take it back.
I see...!
If you want to deliver again, you'll need more [em1]candy recipes[/em1].
I'll sign you up for the [em1]candy recipe purchase service[/em1]. Please feel free to use it.
[em1]4 candy recipes for delivery[/em1] are available today.
The collected item list also includes life forms that only inhabit [em1]shadow areas[/em1].
If you can't enter [em1]shadow areas[/em1] yet, you may [em1]not get all the items soon[/em1].
The good news is, collected item delivery [em1]has no time limit[/em1], so relax.
And don't hesitate to hand in the items, because they will all be [em1]returned[/em1] once they are examined.
Okay, show me what you're capable of from now on, Ellie!
They are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BlahblahCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "AntidoteCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CryingCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1]
and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SatietyCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1].
Oh my, that's a lot!
Now you can make more new candies.
Yahoo!
I'll sign you up for another [em1]candy recipe purchase service[/em1]. Please feel free to use it.
[em1]5 candy recipes for delivery[/em1] are available today.
This will be the last examination. Just collect one of each item.
The collected item list also includes life forms that only live in [em1]water bodies[/em1].
If you can't enter [em1]areas with much water[/em1] yet, you may [em1]not get all the items soon[/em1].
They are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "CleanBubbleCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GrandmaWisdomCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EnduranceUpCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1],
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SweetDreamCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1]
and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RemoveRunnyNoseCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1].
Congrats! Now you've got all the obtainable new candy recipes.
One last thing: Please take this.
That's more than I delivered, no?
It's a small gift from me, so that you can deliver more in the future.
Thank you for the efforts so far, Ellie!
I look forward to future deliveries from you.
This has been Diane of the Witches' Catalogue. I hope you have a nice day!
Hi, Diane, I've got a question...
Wait a second. Let me guess.
Umm...
You've come to me because you need a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Manufacture_Kneader"))][/em1], is it?
What? How did you know?!
Because I'm always watching you, Ellie...
No... don't give me that look. I was just kidding...
No wonder I feel someone's gaze whenever I'm in the forest...
I said I was kidding!
It's just a simple deduction. You entered a new forest, there is no [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Manufacture_Kneader"))] in the workshop, and you've come to me...
That sounds like nothing but a stalker's doing.
I prefer to be called "a considerate salesperson that pays attention to her client's needs."
Anyway! I've brought you a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Manufacture_Kneader"))][/em1]!
Wow! Thank you.
You've gotten used to taking things for granted, huh?
Well... H-how much is it?
It's for free, of course!
Why tease me then!
There was one left in the storage, so I took it.
Thank you all the same.
If you need better work tools, check out the Witches' Catalogue!
Oh, and there's one more thing!
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))][/em1] to Diane?
Hehe, Diane, guess what I've brought!
Hello, Ellie. Look at that wide smile!
Hehe, I've got something amazing for you, Diane.
For me...? I want to see it. Is it from the village bakery...
Er, I'm afraid not.
Oh... what a pity. But since it's from you, Ellie, it must be great stuff.
Ta-da! It's [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))]!
Wow! Great timing. I was about to write the report.
Various problems will emerge if payment is delayed for too long...
I've been wondering whether I should remind you of the master witch's surety.
Umm... What if I failed to make the payment?
Fortunately, you didn't betray my trust.
I had faith in you, Ellie.
Why zoning out? There's one more thing you need.
What? Ah, right, Diane, I also need the recipe for [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))].
What... do you need it for?
Well... I need lunar power to remove prickly vine cores...
She needs to drive Bluemoon Butterflies away.
Oh my! I was about to say that...
Oh, actually, we've [em1]stopped selling[/em1] [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))] recipes.
What?!
Because the maker is involved in recipe copyright disputes...
Copyright...
Don't worry though, because the Potion Association has issued a potion recipe of similar effects for temporary use.
It's also called [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))].
Is that okay? Aren't there copyright disputes in the first place.
The disputes lie in the crafting process. Despite the same name, this recipe has a [em1]completely different crafting process[/em1], so it's okay.
By the way, you can find the required ingredients in [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1].
Okay, please give me the recipe first.
I'll get it registered for you. If you need it, feel free to visit my shop.
Ellie may not be so talented, but she's a kindhearted girl.
Come to think of it, I also need to buy the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))] recipe.
Oh~ Sure. I'll put it in the Catalogue for you right away.
Please use the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_WitchCatalog"))][/em1].
<shake>...</shake>
Nothing. I just somehow got goose bumps on my arms.
Err, let's craft [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))][/em1].
Ellie! I heard that you went to a new location!
Oh, from whom?
Heh, I have my source of information.
A new location! You must have found new ingredients there.
Which means, you can craft [em1]new candies[/em1] now!
<wave>Congratulations, Ellie!</wave> I'll enable a [em1]new delivery[/em1] for you, so that you can make more money.
Phew, thank goodness it wasn't about Virgil.
Ah, I mean, Virgil-flavored candies must be tasty, <shake>hahah</shake>!
Ah... Wait, candy? To deliver new candies... I need [em1]new candy recipes[/em1].
I need to buy candy recipes too.
Don't worry! We have a [em1]candy recipe purchase service[/em1].
Woah! Can I use it?
As long as you meet a few requirements... Ah, you can use the Witch's House here.
The candy recipe purchase service is offered by the Witch Administration to encourage deliveries!
Therefore, Witch's Houses that hardly delivered can also enjoy the service.
As you know, Ellie, it's been years since this Witch's House delivered anything.
Ah... Yeah, right.
Anyway, does it mean I can get free candy recipes?
You can, but there are conditions!
<shake>Huh?!</shake>
The purpose is to encourage deliveries, so we need to make sure you are capable of deliveries.
Of course I believe you are, Ellie, but...
I have paperwork to submit... Please understand.
What should I do then?
Collecting is the basic of crafting! Just collect the ingredients I name.
However! Since you're new to the delivery service!
I'll make an exception and give you [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ManaDetectingCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1]
and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "NoiseCandyRecipe_Name"))][/em1] in advance.
You said there are conditions.
You're a distinguished client of mine, Ellie, so I'll relax the rule a bit.
But to get other recipes, you still need to complete the delivery and pass the test.
The collected item list also includes life forms that only live in [em1]giant mushrooms[/em1].
If you can't enter [em1]giant mushrooms[/em1] yet, you may [em1]not get all the items soon[/em1].
In addition, [em1]two new items[/em1] have been added to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_WitchCatalog"))].
One is a [em1]new potion recipe[/em1].
Now that you've gained access to a new location, you'll need more potions!
Chat with the Witches' Catalogue to buy [em1]new potion recipes[/em1] [em1]from the shop[/em1].
The other is [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchTicket_ReturnHome_Name"))][/em1].
It must be exhausting to go home when the new themed region is so vast, right?
Just use a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchTicket_ReturnHome_Name"))]. It sends you back to the Witch's House directly.
Note that it's relatively expensive and in limited supply.
Now, you can buy new items from the [lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_WitchCatalog"))].
Feel free to use it~
There's one more thing!
Diane! Could you get me the recipe for the Colorful Potion?
Sure. Is it for the witch coloring game?
Recently, there are many coloring books for adult witches on sale.
And there are some marketed for apprentice witches too.
I can get you one if you're interested.
Thank you, but the paint isn't for my own use. I only need the recipe.
It's a pity. If you change your mind, just let me know.
I'll add the recipe to the catalogue.
Diane, do you happen to know a potion that can open a book that won't open?
If it won't open at all... then something must've sealed it quite firmly.
Exactly. No matter how I try, it won't budge, like it's clamping its mouth shut.
And the only writing on it is a name [em1]Parks[/em1].
Hmm... So you can't open the book itself, which means you can't access its contents either.
Yes, that's exactly it!
Well then, Ellie.
Right now, there are thirty-one different potions listed in the Witches' Catalogue that can undo seals on books.
T-thirty-one?!
Of course. Witches tend to love books, so naturally, there are many enchantments, and many countermeasures.
Some seals keep unfinished books from being read, others only allow the worthy to open them...
Every witch has their own ways of protecting what's written.
So if there are many kinds of seals, there must be just as many potions to break them.
Precisely!
Then... Could you recommend one for me?
In that case, my suggestion would be the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WeaknessPotion_Name"))][/em1]?
If the book is sealed with a powerful spell, weakening that spell should do the trick.
This potion has no side effects of damaging the book itself. That's why so many witches use it.
Wow, that sounds perfect! Can you prepare one for me now?
You must really want to read this book, Ellie. Are you sure you're not secretly a bookworm yourself?
I didn't expect you to make such a terrible joke...
The truth is, the village librarian asked for my help.
Ah, I see. Then this librarian is... a human, not a witch?
Right. Her name's Arin. Just an ordinary human.
You sound curious about her.
Naturally. I'm a member of the Witch Potion Association!
Which means, I'm invested in anyone who needs the help of a witch, and how potions are used!
Don't worry, I'll be very careful while handling it. Just give me the recipe, please.
Very well. I'll register it for you immediately.
Hm... There are so many options, I feel lost.
That was a joke.
Why are there so many anyway?
Ellie, are you sure you're a witch?
Hey, I'm more of a hands-on type than a bookworm, alright?
Haha, I'm not much of a reader either.
Still, if we knew more about how the book is sealed, we could rule out a lot of options.
For instance, did you feel a chill down your spine when you touched it?
No... nothing like that.
In that case, it's probably just locked by sheer magical force.
Thank you again for using our service today!
When you touched the book, did your hands smell like cilantro?
Uh... no?
Diane, I have a favor to ask today.
Anything! Just say the word.
The Witch Association and the Catalogue service are ready for any request.
Could you send a letter to Kent for me?
Kent... you mean Kent from the [em1]Witch-Human Information Exchange Department[/em1], right?
That's right. Since he travels from village to village, it might take forever if I send it the usual way.
But I figured you'd know a better method.
Indeed. Normally, a letter to a human would go through the Exchange Department, but Kent is... special.
Exactly. Here's the address I have.
Oh! With this address, you don't need to worry at all.
Huh? What do you mean?
This is an [em1]Anywhere Address[/em1]. It follows the recipient wherever they go.
Since Kent works with the Witch Administration, he's been issued a [em1]Dimensional Letterbox[/em1] with a pre-allocated address.
That way, he can receive mails no matter where he is.
Just a side note, only letters and Luna Coins can be delivered. Nothing else.
Whoa... That sounds incredible. How much does one of those cost?
I'm afraid both the [em1]Anywhere Address[/em1] and the [em1]Dimensional Letterbox[/em1] aren't for sale.
They're only issued to officials working directly with the Administration, especially those who spend over three hundred days a year on field operations.
Yikes... Yeah, I definitely don't need one of those.
Hahaha. So, shall I send your letter for you?
Yes, please. Send it to Kent.
Done. He'll probably receive it instantly. Expect his reply in a day or two.
Diane, I need your help again.
Ah! I think I can already guess what it is.
Then should I just go ahead and ask?
Wait, Ellie... You're supposed to shout "What is it?!" for a more dramatic effect...
Come on, you already know what I've got in my pocket, don't you?
It's a letter. For Kent, right?
Correct!
Phew... Twenty-four years at the Witch Administration wasn't wasted, then.
Then I'll leave the letter in your hands again.
Of course. The Witches' Catalogue always serves with sincerity.
Blue roses? I've never actually seen one.
Really? I thought with all your experience, you might know something.
Most of my work deals with potion ingredients, so I'm not very knowledgeable beyond that.
Are you in need of a blue rose right now?
Not just a rose. I'm looking for an entire field of them.
Hmm... Perhaps one of the wandering witches, always seeking unusual ingredients, might know.
Or one of those making experimental potions.
I'll ask around the Witch Administration and see what I can find.
Thanks, Diane. I'm counting on you.
About the blue roses...
I've done some research, but the information is all over the place. I'll need more details.
Do you know anything more?
"Garden of... Emptiness"?
Hm. Nothing in my notes matches that.
Wait... I think I heard something similar from [em1]Arden[/em1]...
Garden of Empty Words
Oh! Yes, I found a document on that exact place!
Let's see... where was the owner's name...
Ah! Found it. The [em1]Garden of Empty Words[/em1] belonged to Amber Redleaf.
Her predecessor was obsessed with the color [em1]blue[/em1]. She made everything blue, her house, her belongings, even her garden.
They say she was an eccentric witch who brewed potions no one else would even imagine.
Whoa... So, could I meet her?
That would be impossible.
Why not?!
Because she's already passed away.
But don't worry. She left her recipes to her daughter.
And the current Redleaf has officially registered 366 potion recipes with the Association.
<shake>Three hundred and sixty-six?!</shake>
Since you're looking for blue roses...
It must be among the garden- or flora-related recipes.
Give me a moment. I'll search.
A fictional flower field
Ah, here we go. There are only thirteen recipes related to gardens.
I guess that's... good news?
A whopping ninety-seven percent reduction!
True, but pulling them all out at once is going to make a mess.
Ellie, could you hold these?
Ah! <shake>Whoops!</shake>
Aaaah! They're scattered everywhere!
Just looking at this mess makes me dizzy. Feels like your bedroom, Ellie.
Oh dear... It's all mixed up now.
Still, this might make the search easier.
You really are clever, Ellie!
H-ha... Yeah, I guess so.
Then let's see what we've got.
And I'll double-check to make sure I haven't missed any recipes.
Okay... Since it's about blue roses, it should be [em1]flower-related[/em1].
If I can recall [em1]what Vinch said[/em1], I can narrow it down further.
Alright, let's look through them!
...Nope. Definitely not this one.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))][/em1]?
Diane, what's this potion?
Oh, that's the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))].
It's used on [em1]sculptures[/em1], making them look like a real, living flower.
Wait... on a sculpture?
Yes! The former Redleaf loved [em1]roses[/em1] most of all.
Since no blue rose existed...
She used a [em1]potion[/em1] on the sculpture.
You just need to use the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EveryBluePotion_Name"))][/em1]!
She really loved blue...
So in the end, the blue roses were...
The result of much trial and error.
She experimented endlessly, trying to reproduce the exact blue hue she'd painted on her house...
But she never succeeded.
Then the rumors of blue roses...
Likely came from people stumbling across her [em1]experiments[/em1].
Oh! Then does that mean I could make them too?
Of course. These recipes are officially registered. You only need to purchase them.
Ugh... Of course it comes to that.
I'm afraid the sale and distribution of potion recipes are tightly regulated. I can't just give them away.
But since it's you, Ellie, I'll waive the research fee this time.
Wait, that service isn't free?!
Depends on the scope of the search. And this one took quite a while.
Anyway, please make use of the shop! Thank you for choosing Diane's services!
Well, at least I found a way forward, even if it took some work.
But if a witch made it, shouldn't Virgil have known?
Sorry, even one Blueriver is more than I can handle.
If only the hat on my head were a little smarter...
If only the witch beneath it were.
Anyway... next step is...
Making the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))][/em1] and the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EveryBluePotion_Name"))][/em1].
Then, use them on the [em1]rose sculptures[/em1] to create a [em1]field of blue roses[/em1].
I'd better finish them before Roy departs.
If Roy and his teacher can see the miracle they thought was lost, it'll surely give them strength.
Alright, let's buy the [em1]recipes[/em1] from [em1]Diane[/em1]!
So, you decided to [em1]make them[/em1] yourself.
And you want to make flowers that would [em1]never wither[/em1], right?
After all, petals change color as they fade.
Oh, but I found the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))][/em1].
Will this potion turn the flowers blue?
I'll organize the scattered recipes.
Thank you, but I'll just accept the sentiment!
Diane, can I hire an instructor via Witches' Catalogue?
Hire an instructor? Is there something you want to learn?
Yeah, there's a subject I'm not so good at, and I want more practice in it.
I guess that's what made you magna cum laude! You're so eager to learn.
Unfortunately though, Witches' Catalogue doesn't provide such services.
No? That's a pity.
I want to practice carpentry. My master witch teaches all other subjects well, but she hates carpentry...
E-Ellie! I'm not ever doing woodworking again!
Y-you heard her.
If the master witch says so, it can't be helped.
You want to learn woodworking because of the recent Witch's House restoration, I suppose?
Yup. Diane, you know about that tradition too?
Sure. After renewing your Witch's House, [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Craft"))][/em1] [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] will be stacked full on your bookshelves.
I believe you want to try making the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] you received as a gift, don't you?
I do. I've got a sofa recipe that lets me make a nice [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Craft"))][/em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1].
In that case, you can receive some advice from Diane Greenwind, who got the best score in carpentry every single time.
Wow! Diane, you always got the best score?
I did. My classmates even called me "Diane the Bed Manufacturer." "Lillia the Shelf Manufacturer" was the only person who could rival me.
The secret to my success is that I used [em1][lua(GetItemName("CopycatMarionette"))][/em1]s.
Copycat... Marionettes? That rings a bell... Oh, I've probably heard about them in the broom lessons.
Haha, now you remember. Do you recall what they do?
They are puppets that follow orders, aren't they? Orders such as [em1]"remain on the broom" or "stand there in the teacher's place."[/em1]
That's right, but marionettes don't just follow orders. They learn techniques.
To be more precise, people with remarkable skills can infuse them with [em1]craftsman's aura[/em1].
For example, a marionette infused with the aura of an outstanding carpenter can perfectly recreate all the movements of that carpenter.
It's hard for the puppets to actually work on wood though. Since they are no bigger than a fist, they barely even have enough strength to lift a wooden spoon.
So, you were always the best performer because you learned woodworking by observing marionettes?
Right. And it was a laborious task to infuse aura of all the witch carpenters into the puppet at a Witch's Workshop.
You can't get to any Witch's Workshop yet, but you can have this marionette from me.
I made it myself as a pastime. You can consider it a housewarming gift for your restored house.
Really? Thank you!
Just a second. I'm gonna infuse it with my aura.
<shake>Hyaa! Hoo!</shake> <wave>Eigh!</wave>
Woah, to infuse the puppet, you need to yell like that too?
Well... I was trying to make the process more fun to watch...
In fact, you just need to place your hand on it while thinking about the techniques you want the marionette to learn.
Oh, there's more: Marionettes can be infused with the aura of humans too.
Yeah, because [lua(GetItemName("CopycatMarionette"))]s are fueled with the magic of witches, not the aura.
I'll ask all the villagers to provide aura then. The more the better.
The problem is... You don't have anyone to guide you since your master witch is absent, right?
Right. Even if I want to learn something, I don't have anyone to learn it from.
May I ask which subject we're talking about?
Carpentry, I suppose...? The chairs I make always have uneven legs, and it's the same with other furniture.
I'll put it to good use, Diane!
Diane, I want to make a Book of Memories. Can you name the potions I'll need?
Sure. Making a Book of Memories only requires one potion: the [em1]Reminiscence Potion[/em1].
It's a magic that keeps precious mementos in the book.
It's usually used to make graduation albums, but can also be used on various other albums.
You're very familiar with it.
Because Diane is an alumnae.
I am, and I still fondly keep my Book of Memories.
What does it feel like to browse through it?
Shocking, like "Did I really do such a thing?"
After all, it's made from a collection of items from close friends at school.
It carries a wide range of memories, from embarrassing ones to joyful ones. It really brings you back to the school days!
But are you making a Book of Memories on your own? I thought it was made and issued by the school.
This one's not for me. It's a gift.
Can I make one by myself?
The quality may be subpar, but it is possible.
Much preparation is needed, though.
Done already!
Is that one of those copies available in stores?
That will save us time. Place the copy at the bottom and lay all the items neatly on top of it.
Then, simply sprinkle the pile with the Reminiscence Potion, and we're done.
It's simpler than I thought.
Although it's a witch product, it can't be too complicated because it's also sold to ordinary people.
Since you've got all the other materials, you just need to craft a [em1]Reminiscence Potion[/em1]. I'll add it to the catalogue.
I hope you have a nice day! This has been Diane Greenwind of the Witches' Catalogue.
<wave>Ellie!</wave> I need to talk to you! Right now!
Could you hear me out if you're not occupied?!
Now?
Yes! I think it will benefit you.
I'm saying it now! Please come closer!
Ellie, do you remember what I said after your first trip to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1]?
About the new deliveries.
Sure. I received a lot of candy recipes.
Good. I've got a task of the same kind for you.
Word has reached me that you've been to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1].
That will give you access to all sorts of new materials.
In other words, time to rake in a fortune!
You're giving me new candy recipes?
Business has flourished ever since you settled down at the Witch's House,
but for a new area, I'm afraid you still need to submit collected items for a qualification test. It's our standard procedure.
I suppose you know it, since you've done it last time?
Sure. I'll have my collected items back in the end, so it won't be a problem.
I'll give it my best shot, as always.
Your passion always reassures me, Ellie.
I've got you two recipes in advance for you to earn some Luna Coins.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandyRecipe"))][/em1] and
[em1][lua(GetItemName("WarmComfortCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Great! I'll bring you the products as quickly as possible.
Look at you, you're so motivated!
Of course I am. That's an awesome place and I can't wait to explore.
Now that you mention it, to explore a new region, you'll need new buff potions.
I'll add [em1]new potion recipes[/em1] to the Witches' Catalogue. Feel free to [em1]purchase[/em1] them.
I look forward to any lucrative opportunity in the new area.
The first batch of items needed are as follows.
Bring me collected items, and I'll give you candy recipes that utilize these items.
Here are the candy recipes.
Firstly, [em1][lua(GetItemName("DontMoveCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetItemName("ForesightCandyRecipe"))][/em1] and
[em1][lua(GetItemName("CoolHeadCandyRecipe"))][/em1]. Here you are.
You've delivered products for 4 candy recipes.
Like before, the ingredients will be returned to you.
By completing all the quests perfectly,
you've proved that you can be entrusted with work.
The next collected items I need require you to venture further into the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1].
Like before, there is no deadline. Bring them to me whenever you're ready.
Once I've received the items, I'll give you [em1]4[/em1] candy recipes.
As always, I wish you the best of luck, Ellie!
[em1][lua(GetItemName("HeavyPressCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Okay, here's the recipe for the candy.
Firstly, [em1][lua(GetItemName("CalmStomachCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Then, [em1][lua(GetItemName("LightStepCandyRecipe"))][/em1] and
[em1][lua(GetItemName("WhisperCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Also, [em1][lua(GetItemName("DeepVoiceCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Last but not least, the collected items you brought.
That's a lot of new candies made with items collected from the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1].
What do you think of the qualification test? Does it bother you or bore you?
It's fine. I can manage.
Glad to hear that. You seem to be enjoying the tasks.
Onto the last task then!
Just deliver 2 of each collected item.
There's no need to put off your adventure. You can collect the items in your free time, and you always have my support!
Got it. <wave>I'll do my best!</wave>
Firstly, [em1][lua(GetItemName("SharpEarCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
And, [em1][lua(GetItemName("QuickReflexCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
Then, [em1][lua(GetItemName("SoftGripCandyRecipe"))][/em1],
and [em1][lua(GetItemName("TickTockCandyRecipe"))][/em1].
You've stuck it out until the end!
Oh my, this is a lot!
Your efforts deserve a generous payment!
Well done, Ellie. It can't have been easy.
It's nothing. These new candy recipes are well worth my efforts!
I hope I was able to provide more candy recipes, though.
Ellie, good luck with all the future delivery tasks assigned to your Witch's House.
And the Witches' Catalogue service will stay available. Feel free to use it. Have a lovely day!
Diane, do you have a potion that can help find someone?
Yes, of course.
I knew it!
But potions for finding people are subject to various restrictions, since they can be abused.
Restrictions?
Did you get the person's consent first?
No... If I could ask them, I wouldn't need the potion.
Then did you get their family's consent?
Ugh... no.
Can you prove to the witch society that the person is missing or in danger?
I could, but... If I did, I'd probably get kicked out of here.
Are you trying to find Lisa Whitegarden?
You know my situation... Is there really no workaround?
Well... Like I said, there are different potions, but they always come with restrictions.
If I help you, there's a good chance it'll reach the ears of the witch society.
That... would be risky...
Exactly. These potions are handled very carefully, even among witches...
Since it's related to Lisa Whitegarden, helping you would be even more dangerous.
I see... Alright.
I'm sorry I can't help you this time.
Don't be. You've already helped me so much.
I'll handle this one on my own.
If there's anything else I can do, please tell me anytime.
I'll always be on your side, Ellie.
Thanks, Diane.
Diane, do you have a recipe for the Sunlight Potion?
Are you dealing with another prickly vine core?
Yup, probably the last one.
But how did you know it was for a prickly vine core?
I've overheard Kent's explanation.
And all of the village's latest news finds their way to me.
By the way, the Sunlight Potion recipe I used to sell has been banned.
Again? Is it because of another copyright dispute?
No, this time, it's for safety reasons.
The authority spotted a problem with the recipe that would menifest under certain circumstances.
The good thing is, a new Sunlight Potion recipe has been developed, so rest assured.
New recipes come out in no time!
After all, Sunlight Potions are in high demand.
The rapid development of new recipes has probably caused the inflation of the prohibited items list.
But what can we do? The Witch Potion Association can't afford to examine every single item.
I'll list them at the shop then.
Diane, I've prepared everything you asked for.
We're ready to start anytime!
You're quick to take action.
In the meantime, I did some digging into the very first graduation ceremony.
Aside from a few minor changes, there was one major distinction.
Did you know the ceremony used to include throwing your graduation certificate into the torch?
Wait, what???
Supposedly, if the flame judged you worthy, it wouldn't burn your graduation certificate.
But many witches hesitated, afraid it might burn anyway.
Losing your certificate would be awful! People would mock you and call you a disgrace.
And without it, you couldn't even claim your own [em1]Witch's House[/em1]!
The ritual was considered too cruel, so they abolished it the very next year.
So... Did some witches really lose their certificates?
Records say four of them did.
Those four...
They had to spend another year as apprentices.
That's... horrible. Just imagining Virgil going up in flames is terrifying.
Hey, what does that have to do with me!?
Fortunately, the graduation certificates we'll be tossing are fakes that Arin will make for us.
Right. Once Arin makes them, we'll be all set.
Have you and Arin agreed on when to hold the ceremony?
I'm ready whenever you are.
Arin will probably say anytime is fine.
I'll let her know we're ready.
Once everything's prepared, come see me.
First, you'll need to make the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_2_Name"))][/em1].
And make sure to finish the preparations listed on [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirstGraduationCeremonyForm_Name"))][/em1].
The big difference in the first ceremony was that the graduation certificate was one of the items thrown in the torch.
Right, along with other things showing you'd completed your apprenticeship.
Diane! I need help from the Witches' Catalogue.
Calm down... It must be something big.
It is. I really need your help this time.
It's a bit of a long story... please hear me out.
Recreating the [em1]first graduation ceremony[/em1], huh? That's quite a hassle.
Exactly! No one around me graduated that long ago, so I don't have a single clue about it.
Is there really no way to learn more information about it?
Fortunately, I think I can help.
It reminds me of when I joined the Witch Administration.
My first post was in the records department, filled with piles of dusty old files no one ever reads.
Among them were documents on every single witch school graduation ceremony.
Seriously!?
I didn't read them thoroughly myself, but...
I can get you the records. Just be aware, they won't be easy to decipher.
Then we'll definitely need translations.
That's fine. Arin, whom I'm working with, is good with ancient witch language.
That's a relief.
Still, it's the second biggest school event. Recreating it properly might be too much for just the two of you.
True... I'll have to talk it over with Arin.
By the way, I can only lend you the original documents for a fee.
You'll also need the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1], right?
It was part of the tradition.
Could you prepare the potion recipe and the original documents?
I'll get them ready. Once you've finished preparations for the ceremony, let me know.
I'll also check if there's anything else you'll need.
But be warned, the documents are very old, and many of them are in ancient witch language.
And honestly, you'll probably need help from the whole village to pull this off.
Also... If you lose the documents, the penalty will be quite severe. Handle them carefully.
Uh... Does this mean you'll be watching the ceremony too?
Well, since the book specifically said "the first graduation ceremony," I assume that has something to do with witches.
That's... intriguing.
Alright then! Once everything's ready, I'll let you know, Diane!
The Witches' Catalogue Department said that they would install a [em1]Luna Coin Pouch Trading Chest[/em1]...
That will get me some easy Luna Coins!
You should make honest money, young lady.
I'll make use of the chest then!
<shake>Shower Gold Coins on me!</shake>
Diane! I'd like to invite you to the village festival!
A festival?
Yeah, to celebrate the village being completely restored.
Oh, that's wonderful news!
Thank you for the invitation, but I'm afraid I'll have to decline.
<shake>Wait... what? Why?</shake>
<shake>W-Well, I'm not really a villager...</shake>
I only helped out because it's my job...
Don't say that!
You've done so much for me and the village!
D-Do you really mean I can join?
Alright then, I'd be happy to attend!
Then why did you say no at first? You scared me!
I... thought you were just being polite...
That was a sincere invite!
<shake>I-I'm sorry...</shake>
Oh, and could you deliver this invitation to Kent as well?
By the way, have you ever heard of "Meteor Fall"?
The older witches used to talk about it like some sort of heroic story.
Are you planning to make it?
Yeah, it sounds fun! And they say it's safe if it's diluted.
Then you'll be needing a [lua(GetItemName("FirecrackerPotion"))], right?
Should I put it under "Lisa Whitegarden"?
Yes, please. And I'll also need a [lua(GetItemName("SpotlightPotion"))] for the festival.
Got it. Please check the shop.
Will do.
Yeah?
Thank you for inviting me to the festival!
And... um...
Is there a bakery in the village?
There is! A new villager runs a famous donut shop.
Perfect. I'll be looking forward to the festival!
I'll be looking forward to it!
One... two... three...
So many Birdflowers are blooming!
Hmm... Moderate temperature, mild wind, and low humidity...
Great. Fortunately, the potions here seem normal.
It went well, right?
Yes. We can relax a bit now, as at least one of them is normal.
This is the reward I promised you, a [em1]Nubicula Cupcake[/em1].
I requested this as a test this time, but I hope you've realized that [/em1]using potions to collect[em1] makes things much easier.
Witch's Houses supply the most potions every year, which also means witches are big potion consumers.
Have a nice day, Ellie.
Tips about using potions can be found in the [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1].
Welcome. The sun feels as nice as always.
Once you've made it, it will have a red color, bright and pretty.
I used to read fairy tales whenever Rubrum didn’t want to go to sleep.
Should I weave a hat for you?
Time flies when I do this.
There are many pretty bookmarks in the forest.
Put a handful of sour strawberries from the bushes into the pie and take a deep breath.
There is no set recipe. I learned it by watching elder family members make it.
The village chief has controlled the sharing of information in the village for generations.
I've been at it for so long I'm used to it.
The breeze is so comfy here.
Heh, and cute too. It sings beautifully.
Oh right, I have some leftover ingredients at home.
Let's share them.
I never thought I'd see this tree again. It warms my heart.
It's been ages since I've had time to just relax like this. Hoho.
Have you eaten? Make sure you keep your strength up.
Hoho. There was a time we'd sit and chat for hours.
I’m listening. Tell me.
Talk to Rubrum if you need some tea.
I don’t have any that I’m selling.
Welcome, Ms. Witch.
You’ve done a great job with helping my grandchild. Thank you.
No, I’m the one who received help.
Many witches don't look their age...
Alright, I shall save the formality. Welcome to Wisteria, Ellie.
I'm [em1]Enite[/em1], chief of this village.
What happened in this village? What are all those prickly vines?
I’m Ellie, an apprentice witch.
Have you taken a look around the village?
Yes, I saw the houses covered with prickly vines.
They didn't look like ordinary prickly vines.
At first, they were saying things like [em1]god's punishment[/em1], [em1]monster[/em1] or [em1]witch's curse[/em1]...
It happened three years ago.
People had no place to live and could only leave the village.
What happened to the villagers?
Wipe off your drool, Ellie. It's a serious story.
Nobody was hurt.
Now, only [em1]Arden[/em1] and I remain in the village.
Don’t worry now. I’ll help you.
Thank you so much for saying that.
All the houses have been ruined already and everyone has left.
Ellie, you should also leave now. It's better to go to the place you were originally planning to go.
I'm not forcing you. You can stay in the village for as long as you want.
But it’s too late now.
Instead of a village, the current Wisteria is more like some [em1]ruins[/em1] housing two seniors reluctant to leave.
Leave when the train comes. This place is... not a village anymore.
Why did the prickly vines started growing all of a sudden?
There were lots of rumors, but no one actually knew why.
They started growing all of a sudden without any explanation.
<shake>I won't give up yet!</shake>
Highlion is boring as hell!
Virgil! Language!
The [em1]villagers[/em1] are all gone. Even if the prickly vines are removed, what's the meaning?
This is still a [em1]village[/em1]! The villagers will be willing to come back!
Even if the prickly vines disappear, why would they come back to a remote village like this?
Everyone would want to come back!
But Ellie... People left and time has passed.
No. They would definitely want to come back!
It's a wonderful village that you have been developing all your life, [em1]Enite[/em1].
Those prickly vines started to grow all of a sudden and destroyed the houses one by one.
Actually, these are not the first prickly vines growing in the village.
I'll remove the prickly vines and bring the villagers back.
Both the village chief and the village are in bad shape, though.
The village used to have [em1]White Prickly Vines[/em1] growing at its entrance.
But the prickly vines that appeared 3 years ago look completely foreign to us.
I know that prickly vines grow fast, but they aren't supposed to be fast enough to hurt anyone.
Please relax. It will be fine.
Yeah... You're right but...
I don't think those driven out by the prickly vines will ever want to come back to these ruins...
I won't let these [em1]weird prickly vines[/em1] take over the village.
Phew... Let's call it a day and continue tomorrow.
Don't be too hard on [em1]Rubrum[/em1].
Yeah, okay. Get some rest.
You too, Enite!
I'm...
You look tired too. Rubrum looks like he needs to rest as well.
I’ll think about it. Let’s talk again [em1]tomorrow[/em1].
Yes, see you tomorrow!
What do you want to talk to Enite about?
Though it's a small village, it's got everything we need.
I've lived here for a long time.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Enite"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Tea
The village was once famous for its tea.
So I've gotten into the habit of having tea.
Rice
Young people especially need to get proper meals.
Don't neglect mealtimes just because you're busy.
Village Chief
My parents were once village chief too.
When I was young, I thought there were many things cooler than being village chief...
It's hard to predict where life takes you.
There shouldn't be anything too dangerous.
I used to go around picking tea leaves like Rubrum.
I don't usually go to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))][/em1] though. It's too far away, and I don't want to see those [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "OneEyeFrog_Name"))]s[/em1].
Village events
When I was a kid, the village would hold a celebration whenever tea was harvested.
Lots of tourists would come to join the celebration and buy tea as well.
It's a memory that I recall fondly from time to time.
I enjoyed dancing when I was young.
I used to dance with my husband in my favorite yellow dress shoes.
It never occurred to me that I'd pick up pie-baking as a hobby one day.
Fountain
The fountain was a popular place for villagers to gather and drink tea.
To make their preferred tea, people would come with various ingredients.
It was the same for me. [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))][/em1] was all I needed to make my favorite tea. It was so convenient.
The Cloud Valley used to attract many people due to the various mushrooms growing there.
Mushrooms there were great as tea ingredients, so the villagers would often visit too.
I myself usually went to gather [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Tails_Powder_Name"))][/em1] and other silk materials.
Village bulletin
When the village population was over 20, the bulletin was always full of posters.
Oh, there used to be a villager called Brad. He would put up a poster for every trivial matter, so I told him off.
A villager once planned to build a school beside the stage.
There were four kids in the village, and he aspired to provide them with good education.
But the plan went up in smoke because of the prickly vines.
I haven't met many witches... Lisa has defined the witch in my understanding.
She was a big fan of my pies, although she didn't have a large appetite.
Lisa would thank me and give me presents in return every time. She was a nice witch.
Cat Gods
The Cat Gods may not have much power any more, but they have contributed a lot to the village.
Before the road to the temple was blocked by prickly vines, everyone used to receive plenty of advice from the Cat Gods.
Rubrum is the last remaining treasure in my life.
My only wish is to stick around until Rubrum can take care of himself.
Do you know how picky Alvin is when it comes to evaluating items?
Once, he wanted high-quality thread, so I spun [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PumpkinTerrier_Powder_Name"))][/em1] into thread for him. I’ve been using it just fine myself.
ut he declined, saying the thread thickness was inconsistent.
Of course, I enjoy spinning [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PumpkinTerrier_Powder_Name"))][/em1] into thread and using it, so I continue to do so.
Rather, the inconsistent thickness of the thread makes it feel nice to the touch.
Did you know that [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))][/em1] won't grow if planted in ordinary soil?
Long ago, the village was filled with flowers. I planted plenty of my favorite ones.
But [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))][/em1] was the only one that never grew and always withered...
I can still vividly remember Roy’s flustered expression as he explained it.
When I recall the city's nightscape... it feels completely different from this place.
Ah, I suddenly remember. A painting I saw by chance.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("Basic_PictureFrame_NightView_MatSquareM"))][/em1] looks exactly like the scenery from that time.
Looking at that painting... I couldn't help but remember walking through the city at night.
I enjoy both making and eating.
But my teeth have become much weaker than before, so I can't eat hard food well.
That's why soft fruits like [em1][lua(GetItemName("DangleMango"))][/em1] are nice these days.
Don't forget to eat well.
Your health comes first, don't push yourself too hard.
Are you talking about Lisa? She was a very nice person.
There's probably no one here who hasn't received help from Lisa.
But she disappeared all of a sudden.
Was there something different about her before she disappeared?
No, nothing in particular.
Since she was often immersed in her research, I thought she was being her usual self.
Do you know what kind of work she was doing at home by any chance?
She usually didn't talk about herself.
So I’m not sure about that.
Oh, Vinch might know. He used to talk with Lisa often.
I see. Thanks for letting me know.
He left after the village became like this.
Vinch is a painter who used to lived in the house at the upper part of the village.
When they first appeared, we tried very hard to get rid of them.
I tried an axe and also set them on fire, but it was useless.
No matter what we did, they regenerated in no time.
That resembles the [em1]White Prickly Vines[/em1].
Exactly. But White Prickly Vines disappear when there is a [em1]full moon[/em1].
While these vines don't.
As strong as White Prickly Vines, but not afraid of moonlight? That's strange.
We thought so too.
It's okay. You already are a great help.
I believe it is the providence of nature that if there are strengths, there are also [em1]weaknesses[/em1].
This is all I know. I'm sorry I couldn't be of much help.
Well... I don’t have anything else to tell you.
Try asking other people as well.
Oh, that's a problem.
Is it a problem?
Sure it is.
You need to sleep well to be healthy. Are you eating well?
Yes, I am.
Sleep's not a problem though.
What do you mean? To sleep well is very important.
At your age, you must be sure to sleep eight hours a day.
Or you won't grow taller or become smarter.
Why Virgil? Did you remember something?
Keep in mind that the reason you're dumb is not because of sleep.
You're just dumb.
Shut up, will you?
If you can't sleep well, how about trying a potion?
No, it's not that bad...
Witches easily fix problems with potions. Isn't there also a potion to cure insomnia?
There is, but...
Wait, a potion?
Let me tell you. There are also potions that make you smart.
Do be quiet and let me finish.
Wouldn't there be a potion to help you remember a dream?
There can be one. Ask Diane.
Thank you, Enite. I'm inspired.
Are you? I'm glad to be of help.
Anyway, make sure you sleep well and eat well.
I can fix small furniture, but a house is too much.
I don't remember if I've ever repaired the Witch's House.
Okay, thank you. I'll ask Kyla.
Wouldn't it be better to leave such a big task to Kyla?
Enite, the box with the candles at the village entrance has burned away.
It's okay. I was thinking about replacing it.
But why're you leaving the candles there like that?
A [em1]Firekeeper[/em1]?
It's [em1]someone who takes care of the flames[/em1] in the village, especially [em1]wild fires.[/em1]
It's a bit inconvenient, but I'm afraid that until the [em1]Firekeeper[/em1] returns, this is the only solution.
So the candles fell over by themselves?
No... Usually it's [em1]Arden[/em1].
Huh? Arden?
I think it’s best if you ask him yourself.
I don't think it's safe to keep using candles like that.
But it's dark at night and no one is lighting the streetlamps for us. So this is all we can do.
Then I'll try and light the streetlamps for you.
You would do that?
Sure, I won't be as professional as a Firekeeper, but I can give it a try.
It’d be great.
Leave it to me!
Ever since the [em1]Firekeeper[/em1] left the village, we couldn't use the streetlamps.
So we took turns lighting candles to illuminate the roads when it got dark.
Then I’ll leave it to you.
First, I should go see [em1]Arden.[/em1]
I have to find out what happened.
[em1]A burned box[/em1]?
Wasn't there a [em1]candle[/em1] placed on top? What happened?
Either the candle toppled over, or someone screwed up while lighting it.
That's what you get for placing a candle on a wooden box.
Why would they leave it like this? It's not safe!
Let’s go see [em1]Enite[/em1] and ask her why.
Even I know that.
Now Arden won't be burning any boxes.
It's dangerous to leave it like this. I have to do something about it.
So this is the [em1]burned box[/em1] Enite talked about.
What color do you want the [em1]streetlamps[/em1] to glow in, Enite?
I'd like them to glow in a pretty pink color.
I’m not sure... I just want people to take a stroll at night without getting hurt.
But if you had to choose, what color would you like?
Hmm, let's see now. If I had to choose, I'd like it to be [em1]pink[/em1].
Pink?
What’s wrong? Is that too strange?
No, just unexpected.
Might as well be pretty, wouldn't you agree? I myself prefer pink.
Of course. Got it.
[em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice[/em1], complete!
Don’t drink it.
Wasn't gonna.
I’m gonna make some [em1]extra[/em1] for myself later.
I should give this to [em1]Enite[/em1].
Hello, Enite!
Oh, it’s you, Ellie dearie. Keeping yourself well fed, I hope?
I came here today because I wanted to ask you something.
Oh, anytime. I’ll answer as best I can, dearie.
Do you know about the White Cat God?
I sure do. The White Cat God has been the guardian of our village for ages.
Can you tell me more?
There's a mural of the tale up north in the village...
But you'd best not go there.
It’s a dangerous place. Do try to stay away from there.
Maybe once more people return...but it’s too dangerous now.
I have a bad feeling about this.
No doubt about it... Who wouldn't go there after that?
She said dangerous, not mysterious!
An exciting adventure is just waiting for us out there!
Like mother, like daughter. Guess that adventurous streak runs in the family.
Let’s go!
Enite! Whose house is the one south of Kyla's?
Ellie, you're working so hard, even though Kyla has just come back.
Seeing that Kyla likes it, I want to make sure the other villagers return soon.
Yes, I understand.
The house south of Kyla’s belongs to [em1]Roy[/em1].
Roy!
He was a very kind and upright young man that ran a flower shop.
A flower shop! Must be pretty.
He was diligent and kind, and used to take care of the plants in the village as well in his free time.
After Roy left, the flowers in the village started to wither.
The village will become prettier once Roy returns.
It surely will.
Oh, also, I saw a broken [em1]bridge[/em1] over there. Is the other side also part of the village?
Yes, there used to be many people living beyond the bridge.
That bridge also needs to be repaired.
I'll write a letter to Roy right away.
I can't possibly have him stay at someone else's house when he returns, though...
Understood. I'll talk to Kyla.
Ellie, I want you to go to [em1]Kyla[/em1] and ask her to help rebuild Roy's house.
After the prickly vines destroyed the houses, they tore the bridge down as well.
I’ll leave it to you.
Roy was kind and diligent.
No one asked him to take care of the flowers, but he did it anyway.
As a result, the village looked a lot better when Roy was here. There weren't any weeds either.
It's hard for me to go and see you, Ms. Witch. Thank you for visiting me often.
Someone who would curse Arden?
Who would curse a good dragon like Arden?
Good... dragon?
Ellie, that wasn’t the case with you?
He was mean when talking to me!
I suppose there's some kind of story behind it.
Speaking of a story, have you ever received anything from Arden?
He was about to throw away a bunch of good stuff. So I took one.
Isn't it a little small for Arden to wear?
No wonder he wanted to throw it away.
Maybe there used to be someone else at the restaurant?
This is the thing that Arden threw away.
I'm not sure about the curse, though.
It's a spooky story.
Wait a minute, Ellie.
I heard that Arden threw away another bunch of stuff recently.
I heard about this from Aurea. Would you like to go have a look?
I don't know what you're looking for, but I hope it goes well.
Ask only after you've spoken to Arden.
Oh, Ellie. Thank goodness you're here.
Hello. Something wrong?
I'm baking a pie, but I've ran out of the final ingredients.
Would you kindly do me a favor?
Sure thing! What do you need?
Could you get me [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "SilverStarFlower_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]2 Birdflowers[/em1]?
No problem. I'll be back in a jiffy.
I would go myself, but my body isn't what it used to be...
Thank you, dearie.
Sorry, I’ve got things to do at the moment.
Oh, I guess it can't be helped then. Try not to push yourself too hard.
Are you done with your work, Ellie?
One minute!
Then I'll go first with Arden. Come to the front of the fountain with the others.
You can use the [em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1][/em1] at night.
Should I spend time with Enite until it's nightfall?
I should make a [em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1][/em1].
Kyla said that it would take a day to repair the fountain.
Let’s talk to Enite tomorrow.
Enite! I heard you were preparing something.
Oh my... I guess everyone in the village knows already.
But we don't know what it is.
And I've also prepared something.
I'm sure it's something wonderful if you prepared it, Ellie.
Could you call the villagers?
You can do that later if you have some work left.
There's something I would like to tell you.
Kyla hasn't started repairing the fountain yet.
Tell Enite about it [em1]the day after tomorrow[/em1].
Enite! We got rid of the prickly vines!
I saw it! Indeed... You really did it.
Thanks to you and other villagers. You told me about their characteristics!
Still, you're the one who did it! Good job, Ellie!
Now let's call the villagers back and bring the village back to normal.
Okay, Ellie. I think we can achieve anything as long as you're here!
Then, are you going to contact Kyla now?
Yes, I wrote the letter in advance.
Let me send the letter then.
You would? Thank you. The peddler also happens to be at the village during [em1]daytime[/em1], so please hand it to her.
Okay. Oh, and can I send my letter as well?
Of course. Can I ask what you wrote?
"I want to see you soon."
"I'm waiting for you."
"You're always welcome."
I wrote that I wanted to see her soon.
I wrote that everyone was waiting.
I wrote that she was always welcome.
Kyla would be happy too. Then, I’ll leave it to you.
Okay, don't worry.
Since the village became what you see now, the mailman stopped coming, but you could give it to the peddler instead.
I thought about it yesterday.
But I'm still not sure.
The villagers...!
I don't know why you're more confident than me when I lived my whole life in this village.
Even so, I decided to believe in that [em1]happy vision[/em1].
If you [em1]get rid of the prickly vines[/em1], I'll [em1]contact[/em1] the previous resident of that house.
But if that resident refuses...
Don't worry because it won't happen.
Ellie, you are so nice.
Everything will be fine. Do not worry.
Yeah... Yeah, I guess so.
Yeah, you mean they would want to come back, right?
The house at the [em1]upper left[/em1] side from the central fountain of the village belongs to [em1]Kyla[/em1], who is a carpenter.
Let's do it this way: If you get rid of the prickly vines, I'll contact Kyla.
Thank you, I'm counting on you.
So who should we get first?
Was there a [em1]carpenter[/em1] in the village?
To fix houses, I think the first person we need is a [em1]carpenter[/em1].
Then it would be better to remove the prickly vines from [em1]Kyla’s[/em1] house first.
Hello, Ellie. Did you sleep well?
Alright, let’s get this started.
Keep in mind that we don't have [em1]information[/em1], nor do we have any [em1]phoenix feather[/em1].
The first thing to do is to [em1]collect information[/em1].
Let’s look around [em1]Kyla’s house[/em1] once and collect [em1]information[/em1].
Let's think about the phoenix feather later.
Oh, right, take this with you.
It's the [em1]village map[/em1].
Thank you very much.
So much has changed due to the prickly vines.
But now that you're here, Ellie, there is hope.
If you need anything at all, you need only ask.
Wow, what a vast space.
I think Kyla has finished with the repairs.
It's not a village.
Oh!
Huh? What's wrong?
I just sensed something dangerous.
You know, every time you say stuff like that I get goosebumps.
This seems to be the [em1]temple[/em1] Rubrum mentioned.
It feels a bit eerily cool to the touch, see.
Whoa. You're right.
It's been passed down for generations, yet I know little about it.
After the first chief left it behind, it became a symbolic item that was passed down to each following chief.
And is it dedicated to accessing the temple device?
They say a long time ago, it was used in rituals as well.
Have you seen the [em1]Bitter Grape Tea Tree[/em1] at the peak?
It's supposedly where the [em1]Cat Gods[/em1] dwell.
Since you're trying to help the village, it might be a good idea to pray to the Cat Gods. They may open a path for you.
<shake>Why is it so cold up here?</shake>
Right, you're shivering a lot.
<shake>What are you talking about? I'm not shivering...</shake>
<shake>Oh my, look at this!</shake>
<shake>The [em1]Prayer Stone[/em1] is glowing!</shake>
<color=#4b49a5>Will you go to the Place of Promise?<color=#4b49a5>
<shake>Virgil, do you hear that?</shake>
What, I don't hear anything.
<shake>There's someone... asking me if I want to go to the Place of Promise.</shake>
<shake>Oh... Um... Yes!</shake>
Do you know what you're answering to?
<shake>It's too late!</shake>
It didn't light up before, did it?
Something's off... I can feel it.
<color=#4b49a5>You won't forget your promise, will you?<color=#4b49a5>
What's this mural about?
As far as I know, it tells the legend of the tea tree.
What was the legend about?
I asked my parents the very question when I was young.
But the legend was so scary that I never asked about it again.
Really? What made it so scary?
Well... In the end, the girl fell off the tree to her death, if I remember correctly.
Every time I heard a thunderclap, I would recall the legend and get chills down my spine.
Still, no matter how scary it was, it was a long time ago.
I'm not frightened now. It's just a legend, after all.
It'd be nice to recover those missing pieces of the mural, though.
I'll look hard in the forest whenever I go through it.
Did you say the statues were of the Cat Gods?
Right. They are the gods of the [em1]giant tea tree[/em1] and the [em1]guardians of the village[/em1].
And I'll tell you this in confidence: as a child, I found the Gods absolutely adorable.
I have to admit I'm the same.
Haha, are you really?
When there were more kids in the village, I loved the Gods so much.
I'd tell the statues about what exciting thing happened that day.
Really? I was very talkative as a child, too.
Apparently, I would talk to the desk, the pot, and I'd even lie on my belly and talk to the carpet.
How lovely that must have been.
The same with Rubrum. I made him a cotton doll, and it overjoyed him.
There was a time when many people came to worship the Cat Gods.
What's the difference between the White Cat God and the Black Cat God?
It is said that the White Cat God is merciful while the Black Cat God is capricious.
Few people have been coming since access became so difficult.
If I could make another wish, I'd wish for all the villagers to be healthy.
To be free of illness and disaster for a long, long time.
The more I look at them, the closer I feel to them.
That's wonderful to hear.
I'm sure that the Cat Gods welcome you here, Ellie.
Whoaa... What is this place?
No way? As I go further in, I see a tiled chamber with pillars, and statues of unknown subjects... Finally a giant door...
Stop being dumbfounded at everything. You'll wake horrible demons. First figure out where we are.
Hmm... The Place of Promise?
Seriously, what the heck is this Place of Promise you've been saying?
Some voice said so.
The voice you recklessly said "yes" to?
I couldn't help~ There could be danger around here, so I'd better take a look around now~
Can't wait to explore, huh?
There's something strange!
Don't say that like you struck gold.
We arrived here after the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PrayerStone_Name"))] started to glow. The [em1]waterway device[/em1] may be here...
What a majestic space.
Hmm... There are pictures on the [em1]steles[/em1] on either side.
There is also something up above.
Huh, where?
Ah, maybe a mural? There seems to be a faint groove...
I want to take a closer look, but there isn't a path.
Do what you can for now.
Alright, I'll look around here for now.
Whoa, incredible!
What a huge building.
Attack!
Let's check!
Did giant prickly vines grow here, too?
Was it a covert laboratory? Secret rendezvous point?
I have no idea how you're coming to those conclusions.
There are strange paintings and statues!
Seems like a normal temple to me. Now it's in ruins.
Oh hello, Enite!
You've looked around, haven't you?
Do you have the time for a chat?
Wow, all the pillars have gone up!
Oh, but the upper floor's the same.
The sign's gone... Is it still being repaired?
But they've all collapsed.
The lock doesn't look very sturdy... Ugh!
What, why is it so hard to open?
Stop trying to open every darn thing you see by force.
Isn't it natural to want to open a locked chest?
You really lack a sense of adventure, Virgil.
You and Aria are simply too much.
Hmph, there's probably a key for it. I'll take it to Enite and see what she can do.
The waterway device is working now, after all.
Now that the prickly vines have vanished, I thought the rituals might take place again.
But I guess it was wishful to think the temple where the Cat Gods are enshrined would be spared.
Ask? Isn't it obvious?
Enite, I'll come up with a way to restore the temple!
If it ever feels too difficult, know that you can stop anytime.
I've got to go now. See you around, Ellie.
Enite, are you the only one who comes here?
This place is perfect for people looking for silence and contemplation.
Perhaps to wish for something from the Cat Gods.
I've brought Rubrum here, but I don't think he remembers as he was too young.
It is indeed quiet in here. The only sounds are our voices.
That's actually what I find to be bizarre...
It has always been quiet here, but I used to hear some insects or small critters at least.
I wonder if it's because the Cat Gods left after seeing their space had disappeared.
The destroyed statues are of the Gods, aren't they?
Careful, you'll be cursed if you get too close.
It pains me, but I suppose it hasn't been that long since the vines disappeared...
We'll have to wait for the people to return before we can start tidying the place up.
If it weren't for you, Ellie, I wouldn't be standing in here after so long, though.
Thank you so much.
Don't.
I haven't even said anything!
How about we do something to help out here?
You may have a natural talent for destruction, but this is too large-scale even for you.
Who's talking about destruction? Where there's a will, there's a way!
And this place is so unusually quiet.
It's the first time I've had a close look at the temple.
So what's so interesting about it?
Do understand that I appreciate your intentions, Ellie, but isn't it too dangerous?
Even if I can't restore it directly, I will find another way.
Alright, but it'd be hard to do it all by yourself. Why don't you have a chat with Kyla about it?
I will. Don't worry.
I'll have you know that I listened closely to the human society lectures.
Yeah, only what you wanted to hear.
Anyways! I do have heard of the Cat Gods.
If I can restore that damaged mural, maybe I will find more clues?
Don't do it. Gods aren't something you can approach.
You're talking as if you knew one yourself, Virgil.
Maybe. Anyway, what's your plan?
What, Enite?!
Why are you here?
I saw you going to the temple with Kyla.
The "repairing" sign was gone, too. So I got curious.
Haha, I'm glad you came, Enite.
What do you think? It's so clean now you couldn't tell it had been in such bad shape.
Oh, and I found something that looked like an entrance at the bottom, but I couldn't get through it no matter what I did.
Whoa, what is it?
It's a stone that passed down the generations of chiefs. It's called the [em1]Prayer Stone[/em1].
There used to be a path that led to a waterway device underneath the temple.
One can only access it using this stone.
But the door hasn't been working since the [em1]prickly vines[/em1] took over the village.
How wonderful! An adventure!
Calm down and find another way! We need to get out.
Trust me. I'll get the job done!
Alright. You look for a way, and Enite and I will figure out how to raise the roof.
Right, so I'll have to find a path that we can take the [em1]Prayer Stone[/em1] through.
That means we need another path leading to the device, right?
With the [em1]Prayer Stone[/em1]?
Yes, there may be a secret passage way... or just another entrance.
I'm good at... uncovering such secrets!
I trust you... If you could deal with the prickly vines, you'll probably find a way to resolve this too.
But do be careful with the stone. It mustn't be lost, or we'll have serious trouble.
Serious trouble... Will there be an explosion?
Haha! I like heat, but my restoration so far will be ruined if there's an explosion.
That's probably the way to the waterway device.
A waterway device, huh.
If the path inside is blocked, there will be no other way.
[em1]Stellar Stones[/em1] for transporting the device are stored at the entrance.
So even if we get the path opened, we won't be able to unblock the waterway.
Hmm... I imagine a place like this would have other paths built in, just in case.
But there's only one entrance as far as I know, which is the one beneath the temple.
We don't have to go further. Where are you going?
What? You told me yourself.
Enite, do you have any other clue?
Well... There is this...
Oh wow! I've never seen anything like this!
Ellie, you can feel the buzz of magic coming from the stone, right?
I wouldn't get involved with it if I were you.
Then all the more reason I should!
Ellie, come on...
Enite, could I borrow the [em1]Prayer Stone[/em1]?
If I can't find it, I'll just have to ask the [em1]villagers[/em1].
What a curious structure.
Yes, we used to make tea with this water and perform rituals.
After the ritual, the tea would give off a mysterious glow and smell sweet and refreshing.
I wish you could see it for yourself one day.
Sounds like something Rubrum would enjoy.
Yeah, he does enjoy a good cup of tea.
Will water flow out if we activate the waterway device?
Yes. But how did you do it without any Stellar Stone?
I used Twinkle-Twinkle Juice like I did for the streetlamps.
Twinkle-Twinkle Juice is a potion that makes its drinker glow.
That must have been the beautiful, mysterious light I saw.
I drank the potion, crawled to the device and found it activated.
How in the world did you think of that idea!
You're a genius, Ellie.
Aw shucks, it wasn't that difficult, really.
There were many coo... interesting things in the cave.
It's said to be another manifestation of respect towards the Cat Gods.
It's said the two Gods represent the sun and the moon respectively.
The color of the water is amazing.
I think I now understand why Kyla likes it so much.
Enite! What brought you here?
I came after seeing that the prickly vines blocking the path to the temple had disappeared.
Exactly, this is the [em1]temple of the two Cat Gods[/em1].
They are the gods of the giant tea tree and also the guardians of the village.
Before the prickly vines appeared, we held rituals and offered tea as tribute every year.
But because of the vines, we haven't come for a very long time...
I feel sorry to see what it has become.
The village's guardians...
Indeed. It's all in ruins.
But I called you over since you're here, Ellie.
The temple?
Hand over the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MemoryBox_Name"))][/em1] to Enite?
What is this? Looks like a [em1]Memory Box[/em1].
[em1]Memory Box[/em1], huh...
You must know as well as me, Ellie. It is a box holding the [em1]things its owner cherishes the most[/em1], their wishes and hopes.
But why was it there?
What's strange is that [em1]it looks familiar[/em1] yet I don't remember it.
Maybe it was something you made with [em1]your family[/em1]? As a child, I made one with my mom.
Hm... I suppose so. Let me take a good look at it.
Thank you for bringing it, Ellie.
Let me know what it is once you figure it out.
The water in the temple really changes the ambiance, doesn't it?
It's all because you helped us get the waterway device working again.
Thank you very much, Ellie.
The temple has returned to its old self, and villagers are returning.
Kyla, Ellie, the restoration wouldn't have gone so smoothly if not for you two
Oh, the mural. Is it going to stay like that?
Some parts of the mural seem to be missing.
As the prickly vines grew and disappeared, they took the illustrations with them.
I see... That's a pity.
Is there something you'd like to know?
Yes, could you please tell me about everything? The painted walls, the Cat God stone statues and the waterway device!
Well, well, let me go through them one by one.
Why don't you go look at something you'd like to know more about?
Huh, we’ve entered the temple.
I thought it’d go deeper.
Oh, how I love the Sun!
<shake>Enite!!!</shake>
My, isn't that Ellie. Why have you shown up here?
I found where the waterway device is!
Does that mean you've activated it?
Yeah, and speaking of which...!
Enite, what brought you here?
I came since Kyla mentioned the [em1]roof repairs[/em1] had been completed.
Then I've come at the perfect time.
Wait, is that water I hear?
Looks like water's coming out.
Wow, it's so clear!
That's why we'd make tea with it.
I haven't seen this for so long, but just the sight of it makes me calm.
Bravo, Ellie. You're amazing and talented at solving problems.
Speaking of which! When I brought the Prayer Stone to the Bitter Grape Tea Tree, I heard a voice speaking.
I responded to the voice and I was able to go into the cave where the device was.
Incredible! I've never heard of such a method.
It was called the Place of Promise.
I suppose it's called that because our ancestors made a promise to the Cat Gods in there.
To be honest, to always remember the favors they received, and to be sincere to the Gods.
It's incredible that you can heard that voice. It must mean you're a precious guest of this village.
Hm, could it have something to do with this? Since I came out after the device was activated.
Let's see here... Why don't you come a bit closer so I can see?
I tried opening it, but it's locked up very well.
Have we... Have we done it?
I suppose, for now.
Wh-what do you mean!
Sh-shut your trap! I'm still alive and kicking!
V-Virgil, look over there!
The water’s rising!
I’m glad it’s not a demon summoning.
Oh, hey. There's a [em1]box[/em1] floating over there.
I think it's come loose after the device was activated. Let's take a look.
Lisa started to live in the Witch's House before I was born.
She's helped the villagers and me so many times. She can't possibly be behind this wicked deed.
Lisa was a woman of few words and rarely ventured out.
We don't know what Lisa was doing in the Witch's House.
But I'm sure Lisa was not a bad person.
Even if she was behind this, I'm sure she meant well.
There must be more than meets the eye...
I understand. I don't think Lisa's an evil witch either.
May I know if anyone can translate books written in ancient languages in the village?
If it's books you need help with, you can go to the [em1]library[/em1] across the river.
The old librarian there's really smart and should be good with translation.
No problem, I'll fix the bridge and house right away.
The [em1]bridge[/em1] across the river's been destroyed and so has the library.
Looks like some villagers do suspect Lisa was behind the prickly vines.
I've heard the same legend before.
Really? Have you seen it?
It was a long time ago... So things are a bit hazy.
I once pestered my husband to hunt for the gold rosemary everywhere.
I found a path to the cliff, but the [em1]cave[/em1] was too dark and I didn't go any further.
Oh... I see.
If I find it, be sure to come take a look.
Of course, I'm looking forward to it, Ellie.
Fade out and summon Enite who fades in
I think this is it, but I'd better ask Enite.
Open a bottle of the sparkling wine so that the garden's filled with its aroma.
Liquor's just like tea, it only goes down well when it [em1]smells good[/em1].
A good aroma makes everyone feel better even before drinking.
Seems like anything that's delicious smells good.
Yes. So it isn't really that novel to make wine with tea leaves.
Make wine with tea leaves?
Some people will use anything they can get their hands on to make wine with.
It worked pretty well when I tried it with some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "SilverStarFlower_Name"))][/em1] I found in the Green Forest.
All this reminiscing is making me misty-eyed.
When I was young, I thought that only liquor with high alcohol content was the real deal and downed a lot of it.
But after I returned to the village with my husband, I started making milder drinks.
Or [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFlower_Collect_Name"))] salad[/em1] topped with lemon juice.
I haven't had drinking snacks in a long time.
Since my husband was gone, I haven't drunk either.
Don't you like wine, Enite?
I don't really like or dislike it, besides, I have Rubrum now.
But I get a little nostalgic thinking about it...
He loved [em1]sweet and sour drinking snacks[/em1] with his wine.
Such as [em1]baguette slices[/em1] with tomatoes, basil, olive oil, and garlic.
He said nothing tasted better than [em1]fragrant wine[/em1] plus [em1]bruschetta[/em1] with [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFlower_Collect_Name"))] salad[/em1]. He had it a lot.
Do you want a donut, Ellie?
Oh, I'm not the one who wants it.
Roy really misses the donuts he had in Highlion.
If it's a donut from a place like that, it would be hard to find in such a rural place.
There used to be a small bakery, but even that's gone now.
Hm, they don't have to be authentic, as long as they are delicious.
Don't you make the best pies, Enite? That's why I thought you might know how to make donuts.
Though I did go through a phase where I was obsessed with making all kinds of desserts when I was young...
I just started baking nothing but pies one day and don't remember much about other desserts.
Oh... Really? I thought you were our best hope, Enite...
Let me see... Where have I put the recipes, let me see.
Yes, Rubrum's going to want to try other pastries when he gets older.
It's best to start experimenting now.
Even if I can't find my recipe book, donuts aren't that difficult to make.
Awesome! You're the best, Enite!
Hehehe, you're an easy child to please.
Desserts should be sweet, so let's make some cream first. I haven't done that in a while.
Add some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MapleHerb_Water_Name"))][/em1] for color and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SilverStarFlower_Water_Name"))][/em1] to enhance the aroma. That'll probably make good donuts.
I haven't been this busy in a while.
Oh, I'll find you the ingredients.
Please focus on figuring out how we can make the perfect donut, Enite!
Can I bother you with that, Ellie? I can get Rubrum to go instead.
Although I'm no good at cooking, I'm great at prepping ingredients.
Alright then, over to you.
Once you find them, come back with [em1]Roy[/em1].
Let's share the donuts when they're baked.
I don't think there's anything I can give you now.
It's all fate...
I heard about what happened from Kyla. Take this.
Is this a blanket?
Was this Rubrum's?
Though life is full of trials, the day Rubrum came into this world was especially difficult.
How could I ever forget the sight of him looking up at me with his black eyes, swaddled in his pure white blanket?
There weren't any suitable ones in his home, so he used that white one for quite some time.
So I brought out my sewing kit that I hadn't used for a long time.
It had been a very long time since I knitted for anyone...
His smile was so beautiful when I covered him with the blanket I had knit. I couldn't help but smile too.
Was this Rubrum's first blanket then?
It must hold many important memories for you. I can't accept it.
I made a new blanket some time ago.
A blanket's only going to get old and tattered lying around.
While the memories in my heart will last much longer, like a solid bridge.
That bridge must be really tough. It will not collapse even if overrun by prickly vines.
I certainly hope so.
Well... a plant with a story, huh.
You're looking for something mythic?
It can be mythic, or it can be something that reminds you of Wisteria's history.
In that case, I know something suitable.
Just a second.
These... are leaves from the tree on top of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))]?
Yes, I dried them for tea making.
I didn't dry a lot because they were only meant for the ritual. Good thing I've got some left.
There's an old tale about the Bitter Grape Tea Tree on the mountain summit.
And its leaves are for rituals. I suppose that qualifies them as objects with a story.
Yeah... but can I really take such precious items?
It's okay, since you're Ellie.
You saved the village, and restored the temple.
The Cat Gods won't mind doing you such a little favor.
I suppose... you're also looking for something for someone?
It's indeed a huge matter in my life as a hat.
Haha... Thank you, Enite. I believe its receiver will love it.
I hope so, and I'm very pleased to be of help.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BittergrapeTealeaves_Name"))] is the only one that remains.
How quiet and peaceful. There's nothing going wrong.
Oh, it’s such a pretty pink color!
I made it pink, the color you like the most.
You've picked such a pretty color.
Through all my years, I've always thought this village to be beautiful...
...but it's simply dazzling today. Thank you.
Now Arden won't be burning any more boxes, right?
That's right. Thanks to you, we'll be safe at night until the Firekeeper comes back.
You went though a great deal of trouble for us.
Have you seen everything?
I remember the first time I was taken to the temple by my parents.
I only found out what a chief's duties were when I reached your age, Ellie.
And I thought it a boring job.
But you're the chief now, aren't you?
Yes, indeed. I guess you never know what will happen...
However, if I hadn't stayed in the village as the chief, I wouldn't have met a [em1]lovely girl[/em1] such as yourself.
I'd be happy if you came with Rubrum.
I wish [em1]he[/em1] could have come with us.
Oops... The elderly really like to talk to themselves.
Nothing's more important than a good diet and ample sleep. I mean, look at you, you're so thin...
Th-thin... huh...
Sure. At that age, eating properly is top priority.
Since the temple has also been restored, we can meet here like before from now on.
I'm glad we had this talk, Ellie.
Enite! What's on the party menu? How's everything going?
Hi, Ellie. It wouldn't be fun if I tell you now.
Rex says it's only fun when there's suspense.
Well... He's got a point, but I can't help being curious!
Just wait a bit longer. This time, Arin is also helping, so it will probably be smooth.
Although she can't tell sweetness from saltiness, she's really skillful with her hands. She's been a big help.
I really look forward to the food, since it's you in the kitchen.
To be honest... Arden worries me the most.
But Arden has been running a restaurant this whole time.
But he seems to be scratching his head this time.
You mean Arden is being indecisive about the menu?
Yes, but he didn't seem to want any help, so I didn't poke my nose in it.
But Ellie, maybe he wouldn't mind if it's you.
If you have time, would you check on him?
If Arden is pondering over some new menu, I'm very interested!
I'll go ask him!
Before starting the party, get the [em1]Attention Potion[/em1] and [em1]MSG Potion[/em1].
Now, go to Enite to start the party.
Enite, how's the preparation going?
I'm all ready!
So are we.
I've heard it from Roy and Rubrum. They say you put much work into this event too.
Doing nothing is too boring.
What a kind and honest girl you are.
Then, please tell the villagers now.
I will go with Rubrum once I've fetched a few items from my home.
The concert had better be held [em1]in the evening[/em1].
Should I spend time with Enite until it nightfall?
Quite the varying tastes.
Enite likes [em1]pink[/em1], Arden likes [em1]silver[/em1], and Rubrum likes [em1]yellow[/em1]...
What color do you want, Virgil?
[em1]Turquoise[/em1], just like my glowing eyes.
Ellie, what color do you like?
Hmm, let’s see...
I like Enite’s [em1]pink[/em1].
It’s cute and fancy.
I like Arden’s [em1]silver[/em1].
I like Rubrum’s [em1]yellow[/em1].
Oh, come to think of it...
Silver is probably best to really light up the night.
A mellow yellow would fit this village best.
First thing’s first, let’s get the [em1]Recipe[/em1].
Go see [em1]Diane[/em1]. She may be selling it.
I could just give her a pre-made one as well.
It just struck me that I've only ever made [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] of one color.
Are you sure you want to waver over the colors first?
Can't the color be changed?
How about asking Diane?
Enite! I got you something that'll light the streetlamps.
Oh, what's it?
It’s [em1]Twinkle-Twinkle Juice[/em1].
It's a potion that makes your body glow. It'll light up the streetlamps if put inside.
Wait just a second, dearie.
The light is a bit weak, but we can make do with it until the Firekeeper comes back.
Is it night?
(Do I give the Twinkle-Twinkle Juice to Enite?)
How's the streetlamp lighting going, Ellie?
Don't overwork yourself now. Your health should be your top priority.
It’d be great if you could do that for us.
Using [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))] at night can help you see better.
Find [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColoredBeads_Name"))][/em1].
The temple's repairs are complete. Now we can ask the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1] for help.
We've got to come back during the [em1]day[/em1].
Enite! The Prickly Vine Core in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] have been eradicated as well!
I see the prickly vines on the other side of the bridge are gone too.
Who are the residents over there? When are they coming back?
Haha, Ellie is so proactive.
Why don't we go take a look together, and I'll tell you about the residents on the way?
Seeing it again still feels amazing.
Those overwhelming thorn vines disappeared in an instant. Impressive.
Hehe, I actually take joy in it.
Enite, please tell me about the people living here.
Sure, let's start with the house up there?
In the topmost house lives a painter named Vinch.
A kind young man who's very good at painting.
But he rarely ventures far from his home.
In the house by the river lives a stylish old man named Alvin.
He's skilled and knowledgeable, running a sundries store selling furniture and novelty items.
This place used to be a library, with a resourceful old man named Brad serving as the librarian.
He loves to chatter and loves to collect, owning many valuable books.
What about these houses below?
Well... these houses are empty.
The residents have settled elsewhere.
We don't need to worry about them for now.
Uh, I'm curious about everyone.
But we can't ask them to return all at once, right?
I can write letters to everyone, but we should prepare the houses first.
Too bad Kyla isn't a superhero with multiple arms.
Haha, indeed.
Unfortunately, it looks like I'll have to contact them one by one.
So, who should we contact first?
Who do you want to meet the most?
I want to thank you for restoring the village.
So, I decided to let you choose the person you want to meet the most.
You can ask around the village before making the decision.
Alright, I'd like to hear what others have to say.
When you make the decision, let me know who I should write to.
Have you decided?
Alright, who should I write to?
I heard that Vinch is a painter. I'm curious.
I've never met any good painters before.
Alright, I'll deliver the letter to Aurea.
Ellie, do you want to ask Kyla to repair the houses?
Yep. We think alike.
I'd like Alvin, the owner of the sundries store, to return.
I'm curious about what he peddles.
The grandson of Brad's friend decided to come, right?
I heard he's very smart, and he volunteered. I'm looking forward to meeting him.
Right, Roy was just looking for you.
He seems to have contacted Brad.
He has something important to discuss with you. Go talk to him.
Alright, I'll give the letter to Aurea again.
I'll ask Kyla to fix the house.
He's a kind and polite young man.
And takes painting very seriously.
People who are fully committed to doing what they love are awesome.
But he don't seem to be eating meals regularly. He needs to take better care of his health.
He's a fashionable old man. A rare sight in a country place like ours.
I'm not sure about the details, but I heard he used to work on theater-related jobs in a big city when he was young.
He currently runs a small sundries store in the village.
Not very nice on occasion, but generally polite and courteous.
But he doesn't seem to be eating meals regularly. He needs to take better care of his health.
I miss the time when we used to have a library.
Granted, most of the books were abstruse but there was no shortage of interesting ones.
I hope we can rebuild it soon.
Brad had an eye for good books.
Yeah, I heard that from Roy too.
I'm looking forward to the guy Brad introduced.
He's a fashionable old man. A bit out of place in our countryside village.
He's not particularly close to the villagers...
But he's not a bad person.
How was Alvin when he first arrived?
At the beginning? Let me think.
He hardly ever talked about himself, so...
Ah, I remember now. He chatted with me when he first arrived.
We talked about all sorts of things.
At that time, he said, "this place is perfect for a retiring [em1]actor[/em1]."
I think he was probably a famous actor when he was younger.
And he [em1]used to sit by the fountain every night[/em1].
Maybe he still misses his past career as an actor.
Give the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))] to Enite?
Enite, I got this [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))].
Great. Let's make tea right away.
What's so special about this tea?
Do you want to know? Then listen to me while I make some tea.
Forget-me-nots bloom in other places too, but [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))] are special.
It is said that a long time ago, when the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] was still bustling, the flowers there were sky blue.
When people left, [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))] started appearing.
Some blabbermouths say that the flowers symbolize a curse, or that the souls of people who died unjustly inhabits it.
However, it was soon discovered that going near this flower, or even picking it, did not invite any disaster.
Instead, word gradually spread that Black Cat God liked this flower tea.
The tea is boiling as we speak. Just a moment.
Wow, it smells so good.
Haha, the Black Cat God's probably gonna recognize this.
Come to me whenever you need anything else.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
They only bloom atop the mushrooms even in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
If you don't know how to clean it, why not bring it here?
Um... it's just too dirty and smelly. I don't want to bring it over.
Hmm... then how about pouring water directly [em1]on the doll[/em1]?
If you can't bring the doll here, then [em1]take water over to it[/em1].
If it [em1]rains[/em1], the doll can be washed clean. Unfortunately, it doesn't rain often here.
Mending dolls? I do it all the time.
Wow, could you help me out?
Of course, I'd be happy to help you.
But Arden borrowed my [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SewingBox_Name"))].
You can go find [em1]Arden[/em1] and learn how to mend the doll from him.
Oh...? [em1]Arden[/em1]? He doesn't seem like the sewing type.
Haha, trust me. Just go find him.
Enite! Can we contact the next villager now?
Haha, Ellie is really enthusiastic!
Have you decided who to contact next?
Um... There are still two houses left.
Well... at times like this, I really just want to be the carpenter and blacksmith.
Haha, no need to rush. You'll get to meet everyone eventually.
If it's difficult to decide, take some time.
The remaining are Vinch the painter
The library is expecting a [em1]newcomer[/em1]. Even if I ask around, no one will know about him.
and Alvin the sundries store owner.
I'll ask the villagers again.
Ellie, you're here. I've prepared the letters.
Enite, your writing speed has improved!
Haha, you were complaining about not being able to ask everyone to return at once.
So, I prepared the letter in advance.
Enite and I are truly on the same wavelength. Actually, I wrote a letter too.
Really? Then I'll give both letters to Aurea.
What did you wrote?
About wanting to meet soon
I asked him to come quickly because I want to meet him as soon as possible.
Your letter will definitely make the recipient even happier.
Hehe. I'm off to Kyla's to repair the house.
Alright, take care.
Saving the best for last
I was worried that he might be unhappy for receiving the letter last. So I told him that I was saving the best for last.
Everything's Ready
I said that the house is cleaned up, waiting for him to come.
Because the remaining person is [em1]Vinch[/em1].
Because the remaining person is [em1]Alvin[/em1].
Because the remaining house is the [em1]library[/em1].
I was wondering if part of the library's books are stored somewhere else.
Library's books? I'm not sure.
Nobody has visited that place since the bridge collapsed...
Where can the books be if not stored somewhere else?
Can I help you?
Arin says that the library's books don't match the catalog. Many are missing.
Books are missing? In that case, maybe...
You've got some clue?
Yeah, but... I wonder if I should say it.
Well... I wonder if I'm supposed to tell you...
Why? What is it?
Actually, the library has a [em1]wing[/em1].
Wing? The small building beside the library?
Yes, and not.
Isn't the current wing a new one rebuilt by Kyla?
It is, but the wing had been collapsing for no reason before that.
Even though Kyla made it so enduring every time.
That may be why there are rumors that the wing is haunted...
The missing books can't be in there then?
The previous librarian was an elderly man. He used to talk about the [em1]wing[/em1] a lot.
He said that [em1]our root[/em1] was kept there.
[em1]Root[/em1]?
Everyone thought he meant the books.
But the wing is too cramped and stuffed with random stuff.
Maybe the elderly man wasn't serious? Did you ever ask him?
He wouldn't have answered even if I did.
But he was into studying mysterious things, so there should be something in the wing.
That is... worth an investigation.
Be careful. Rumors don't come from nowhere.
It's okay. I can handle.
I need to find books for Arin.
And I have this feeling that it will be fun.
Alright, I won't stop you.
Do you have any other clue?
Nothing notable. I only remembered it because the elderly man's pronunciation of "wing" is unique.
Got it. I'll look into it myself.
Alright, I'll leave it to you.
I also want to know the true nature of this "wing."
People on the other side of the bridge may know.
Be careful.
So that's what the Black Cat God said.
Ellie, what do you think?
Errr... I don't know how to put it. Shall I offer some precious... food? Or sacrifice?
Haha, Ellie, remember what I told you when you were restoring the temple?
It was a long time ago... but Wisteria used to be a village known for its tea.
People used to offer the Gods [em1]tea[/em1] made from clear water flowing in the temple.
It then became a tradition, and they offered tea to the Gods during rituals too.
Wow! Can I still get that tea?
Sure. They used to use leaves of Bitter Grape Tea Trees, but I believe you're exploring the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1]?
Then you can use tea leaves there.
Collect tea leaves, and we'll make tea together.
Where can I find the tea leaves?
Did you see the [em1]giant mushrooms[/em1] in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))]?
Some of the mushrooms [em1]collapsed[/em1].
[em1]Red flowers[/em1] would grow on them.
That flower is called [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ForgetMeNot_Name"))][/em1]. Can you pick some for me?
No problem. I'll be back in a jiffy!
I believe those [em1]collapsed mushrooms[/em1] can be found in [em1]remote places[/em1] of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "RainbowForest_Basin"))][/em1].
[em1]Collapsed mushrooms[/em1] at [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "RainbowForest_Basin"))][/em1]...
I guess I'll check the [em1]map[/em1].
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "RainbowForest_Basin"))][/em1] is vast, so I'd better draw a [em1]map[/em1] first.
Heh, the geezer seems to be playing another prank.
One of the letters may be for me... May I see them?
I do use a cane, but I've been using the same one for years and don't know about the trends.
I've been using that cane of mine since forever. It's comfortable to grip... and it's from my husband.
This letter mentioned materials and trends.
You can look for someone who [em1]sees items in a unique way[/em1], or someone [em1]familiar with various materials[/em1].
Hmm... such portraits have been emerging these days.
As I age, I lose old friends more than I make new ones.
And my memories are fading... Sooner or later, I'll forget people that I used to think of so much.
In short, yes, I talked with Brad about portraits.
Enite, you also have people you miss?
Certainly... A lot of them.
Especially my family.
It'd be nice to have a portrait of me and Rubrum.
Thank you for bringing me this letter, Ellie.
I usually make food to distribute to everyone, but I've never worried about packaging.
I suggest you find someone who needs to [em1]pack stuff[/em1], or someone who [em1]would pay close attention to such details[/em1].
Enite, may I ask you a question?
Ho-ho-ho, hello, Ellie. What is it?
I wish to learn about the relationship between the villagers and [em1]cats[/em1].
Cats... What kind of cats are we talking about?
A cat recently came to my door. I wish to know where it lives.
And also... whether there are cat lovers in the village.
I see. As you've probably noticed, there are many cats in the village.
Although they stopped coming after the prickly vines appeared... Some seem to have returned.
Then, does any of the villagers keep cats?
No, no one in the village keeps them. They just roam around as they want.
I thought they were house cats of someone in the village.
They are not, but they get fed from time to time.
I myself also feed them when it strikes me.
The cat at my door probably lives nearby.
That's likely the case, although I don't know those cats well enough to tell them apart.
What a pity. I hope somebody knows the one at my door.
Speaking of which... A stranger seems to visit the village every once in a while to look after the cats.
I've never met him myself... so I can't describe him.
Still, I know he's left some traces.
Traces? You mean, a stranger stays in the village from time to time to look after the cats?
So it seems, but that's all I know.
I see. Thank you for telling me about it, Enite.
Show Enite the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Catbowl_Name"))][/em1] and start a conversation?
Enite, would you please give me some time?
No need to be so formal. I always have plenty of time for you.
You've got a new adventure in mind, haven't you?
Woah... How did you know?
It's written on your face.
Actually, I'm thinking about placing a cat food bowl in the village.
I want to make friends with the village cats, so I'm setting up a dining place for them.
Well... I see.
And!
Is there more to it?
If we can get along, I'll be able to handle things better in case they cause any trouble.
In short, I'll try my best to manage the village cats.
So far, they haven't caused any serious problem...
But there were times when they stole Arden's pre-cut fruit..
More reason for me to do so, right?
Okay, Ellie. I'll entrust the cats to you.
Let me know if something you can't handle alone comes up.
I will, but I'll try not to let such things come up.
The would be great. That's so sweet of you.
Now, I believe you just need to pick a place for the bowl?
Rubrum told me that you two found a cat together and fed it apples.
That's right. I once saw the cats eating apples [em1]before the Temple of the Cat Gods[/em1].
I suggest you place the bowl where you fed them [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s. What do you say?
Nice idea. I'll place the [em1]Cat Food Bowl[/em1] at the place I first fed them apples.
Good, and let me know if you need anything else.
In the end, the bowl still goes to where we found the cat encyclopedia.
It's a nice spot. The cats are already familiar with this place.
Are they? I'm not sure.
But this is a place where the stranger in question may show up.
Do we have to see him?
Why not? He's a cat lover, and he has worked hard on the pictures.
He must be kind and amicable!
I can see that you already consider him a friend.
Hehe, but before that, I must make friends with the cats.
So, let's place the bowl already.
Oops! I forgot to buy the [em1]Cat Food Bowl[/em1]!
Sorry? Ellie, what did you say?
Haha, nothing. I'll be back later.
I have no idea what you're up to, but take your time. There's no need to rush.
I will buy a [em1]Cat Food Bowl[/em1] from Aurea before coming back to Enite.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Catbowl_Name"))][/em1] [lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "NotHaveItem"))]
It's a letter from Enite. You said you placed a bowl of food across the bridge as well, right?
That seems to be the case. It looks like someone put one there before you did.
I'm so excited that there are now two places to feed the cat.
Enite sent a letter.
But you still know what I'm talking about, right?
This must be the bowl Enite mentioned, right?
Yes. Just by looking at the size of the bowl, it seems like it.
Then if we put some fish in here, the cats will come.
Kitties~ I'll take good care of you~
Who put this cat food bowl here?
I don't know. Judging by its good condition, it seems like it was placed here recently.
Probably, right? So it's okay to use it?
Enite! Do you know the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1]?
To some extent. I used to go and pick pretty stones when I was young.
I want to visit the place! Please show me the way!
You're going to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]? Perfect timing.
Hm? Why?
Thanks to you, most of the area beyond the bridge has also been restored.
There used to be houses [em1]to the south of the bridge[/em1] as well.
I've left the bridge unattended since it collapsed completely...
But recently, we've been having a discussion over its repair.
You can access the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] from the [em1]southern part of the village[/em1].
While we're at it, let's go have a look.
We'd better get Kyla too.
What's a discussion over repairment without Kyla.
You're right, Ellie. Let's do it.
Shall we summon everyone? To visit the site of the bridge?
Let's go! I can't wait to see the southern part of the village.
And I'm going to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] too!
Alright, I'll have Rubrum summon the villagers.
Let's go over first.
If we are to visit the bridge site as a large crowd, we'd better wait until [em1]daytime[/em1].
Are you giving me a gift?
This [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] is for me?
So, you're giving me a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
I'd love to accept a gift from you, Ellie.
Ellie, it's nice of you to offer this, but...
I think someone else may need a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] more than I do.
You've prepared this [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] for me?
I suppose I've really aged. I easily get emotional.
I appreciate it. That said, I think your coming to the village is the biggest gift.
Wouldn't receiving a gift always make you happy?
And when you receive something you love the most, it makes your whole day happy.
Thank you for always thinking of me, Ellie.
Ellie, thank you so much for the gift.
It's been a while since I've had such a pleasant day.
Haha, I'm content with having one gift.
It's fine, dear.
You've been here for some time now, Ellie.
I've lost count of how many times I've said "thank you" to you. Without you, the village would have still lied in ruins.
Thank you, and please accept this.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Enite"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
Do you have a minute?
Ellie, you've brought energy to the village.
Removing the prickly vines and bringing back the villagers are both changes for the better.
But you've brought us more than that, Ellie.
Ellie, do you remember the first time you came to me?
Although I wanted to maintain the village, I was about to give up because I couldn't find a means.
You taught me an important lesson.
You made me realize that all the other villagers love the village and want to come back.
And I share the feeling.
Even now, I still imagine from time to time what things would have looked like by now if you never came.
I want to thank you for contributing to the village, and for helping me and Rubrum.
It's great to have you here, Ellie.
Ellie, can we talk for a moment?
It’s not a serious conversation. I just wanted to say thank you.
As I’ve gotten older... I’ve stopped worrying too much about what I like or dislike.
But Ellie, every time you give me a gift thinking of me, it makes me think of many things.
Yes, things like what I used to like, what I used to avoid.
I thought all of that was pointless, but... it wasn’t.
What you’ve done for me, thinking of me... I’m really grateful.
So this time, I’ve prepared a gift for you. I hope you’ll accept it.
Let’s spend happy times together in Wisteria from now on.
Enite, do you know how to turn [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))] into threads?
[lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))]? I don't usually use it because it's hard to come by.
But I do know how to spin.
But what do you plan to do about such threads? I don't think you can weave clothes or carpets with them.
It's for Clala. She wants to make a doll for Dana.
That'd be a nice choice.
[lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))] threads are very thin and only good for tiny items.
To make threads for one doll... bring me 3x [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))].
I know how to spin. I can do it for you.
Really? Thank you so much, Enite.
Those are firm threads often used to make items meant to be kept for ages.
Give Enite 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))][/em1]?
Enite, I brought the [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))].
Hoho. I'll turn this into threads for you.
I've got to make the threads in the kitchen. One second.
Here you go. I made more than I expected, but you can take it all.
It's so soft. If I make a doll with this, I'd want to hug it all day.
Right? It's harder to process than common threads, but it's worth it.
Oh, if you're making a doll, there's one tip I want to share with you.
As I mentioned, the thread isn't very strong. So weave the [em1]thread[/em1] [em1]tighter[/em1].
That way, once you stuff it, it'll hold its shape nicely.
Have you tried it before?
Hoho. I used it to make a pillow, not a doll. Learned from my own mistakes.
Got it. I'll definitely tell Clala.
Alright! Time to take the thread to Clala.
Clala's impressive. Even with all the things on her hands, she still finds the time to make her sister a doll.
Right? I wonder how much Dana will love it.
Wait... Since it's a gift for Dana, should I try to find out what she likes first?
Then Clala can make the doll the way Dana likes it.
Not a bad idea. Think you can pull it off without giving it away?
If you blurt it out in excitement and spoil the surprise, it's all ruined.
Of course. I already have a plan for it. Don't worry.
3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))][/em1] should be enough to make thread.
I'll be right back with them, Enite.
We're fine here. Go on and help the other children.
I forgot to bring the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EmptyBowl_Name"))][/em1] Theo gave me!
I need to go back and get the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EmptyBowl_Name"))][/em1].
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EmptyBowl_Name"))][/em1] to Enite?
This is the bowl I gave Theo.
Ellie, why do you have it?
Theo asked me to bring it back for him.
He could do it himself, but he's always like this.
Sigh... Perhaps he just doesn't want to come here.
[em1]It's been hard to get a hold of Theo lately.[/em1] When I do see him, he avoids my gaze or runs off.
Do you remember the incident where he made a mess of my house?
Ugh, of course. You mean the [em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Box incident[/em1]?
That prank is still in your top five all-time greatest hits.
Ugh, I can't even argue with that...
I'm really sorry about the trouble I caused back then.
Hoho. You apologized, and you learned your lesson. It's all water under the bridge now.
It's just that since that incident, things haven't been the same between Theo and me.
I worry that I was too harsh on him.
Should I talk to him?
I'd appreciate it, but he seems reluctant to talk to anyone about it.
If he doesn't want to talk, please don't force him.
I fear prying will only make things worse.
Are you sure it's okay to just leave it alone?
Hoho. Do you know that Theo's grandmother and I were friends?
The way Theo is acting reminds me so much of her back in the day.
We both caused our fair share of trouble when we were young.
But you eventually learn. Before I knew it, I was the one sitting in the chief's seat.
Theo is still young. He has plenty of time. For now, let's just give him some space.
If you think that's best, then okay!
Thankfully, he seems to be getting along well with Rubrum these days.
I heard they even went on an [em1]adventure[/em1] together not long ago.
Oh, Theo told me about that. Said they saw some [em1]strange creature[/em1]?
Is that what Theo said? Rubrum said he saw a [em1]monster[/em1] and was terrified...
He said something big appeared out of nowhere and scared him.
I was a bit worried that there is actually a [em1]scary monster[/em1] out there...
Hmm, I'll ask Theo about it. I was planning to anyway.
Thank you, as always. Do be careful.
I don't really remember.
...Uh, what was that about?
You forgot already? [em1]What you did with the Witch's Party Snack Gift Box[/em1]?
Oh, that's right! Yeah. I really was sorry about that...
So, that's why Roy's been so bloomy.
That boy takes everything seriously. At this rate, he may collapse from fatigue.
Maybe I should get him some pies.
Enite, you're also worried about Roy?
Heh, it's not just me. Everyone does.
Even more so since Roy takes care of the flowers in the village. I can't thank him enough.
I hope he gets well soon.
And Ellie, you shouldn't push yourself too hard. If you need anything, just let me know.
I'll get Roy some pies when I have time.
We're also wondering what we can do to help Roy.
"We"?
Thank you, Enite! Just send the letters to my letterbox!
Okay, I'll spread the word.
I mean all the [em1]villagers[/em1]. They may not be saying it aloud, but everyone's worried about Roy.
He puts up a cool front, but he's not his usual self.
Something about him is off. Everyone's somehow noticed it.
You guys are so perceptive! I didn't notice it in the beginning.
I thought he was really fine.
It's not too late. And I'm glad to be of help.
I don't know if this will work though.
Heh, have faith in yourself. If you fail, we'll fix it for you.
Theo comes from the city.
Because of his parents’ circumstances, he has to live alone for a while, so he’s planning to come to our village.
I heard he’s a little younger than you.
Rubrum was also very excited that a friend his age would be coming.
Ellie, have you been fishing lately?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_CloudSalmon"))][/em1]?
Thank you in advance.
Could you deliver them [em1]today[/em1]?
There's a fish dish I want to cook. Please help me with it.
Rubrum wants to have a dish made with this fish.
I need it for a dish I haven't made in a while.
I'm craving this fish.
Before he left, Freddie taught me a recipe that uses this fish.
I want to make a dish my mother used to make.
There's a dish I want Theo to try.
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_Cantsee"))][/em1]?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_BigFist"))][/em1]?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_HardLobster"))][/em1]?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_Axe"))][/em1]?
