Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_SparkleFin"))][/em1]?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_Nokyeomo"))][/em1]?
Could you find me 1x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_Skyfin"))][/em1]?
Sure. I'll be right back.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_CloudSalmon"))][/em1] to Enite?
Enite, I've brought you the fish.
That was fast. Thank you so much, Ellie.
I need to repay the favor.
It's a pie freshly out of the oven. I hope you enjoy it.
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_CloudSalmon"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Cantsee"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Cantsee"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_BigFist"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_BigFist"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_HardLobster"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_HardLobster"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Axe"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Axe"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_BigHead"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_BigHead"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_SparkleFin"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_SparkleFin"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Nokyeomo"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Nokyeomo"))] will do, heh.
Give [em1]1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Skyfin"))][/em1] to Enite?
1x [lua(GetItemName("Fish_Skyfin"))] will do, heh.
Enite, it's an emergency!
What's the rush? Is it about Theo?
Huh? Well, yes, Theo is involved. How did you know?
I heard he's been pacing around with a book.
Actually, it was about the Honey Bear. He ate a [em1]poisonous herb[/em1].
Alvin told me about an antidote and said someone as knowledgeable as Enite might know where to find the ingredients nearby.
Do you know [em1]Cleansing Herb[/em1] and [em1]Glowpetal Bloom[/em1]?
So you're worried about Honey Bear.
These ingredients are indeed nearby.
But are you sure? Those ingredients aren't exactly [em1]easy to gather.[/em1]
That's fine! I'm a witch. I have [em1]potions[/em1]!
Is that so? Wait here, I'll write them down for you. That should help.
Thanks, Enite!
Ellie, thank you for staying by Theo's side.
Not at all! I'll be off now!
I was worried something might have happened. Though Theo is probably resting now...
When he returned to the village, he looked like a mess.
He lingered in front of my house and ran off when he saw me.
Which one should I read about?
Biome
An herb buried deep in a [em1]lake[/em1], where [em1]pink petals[/em1] fall like rain.
I believe it was somewhere in Cloud Valley.
I'm sorry, dear. I can't quite remember the exact location.
Characteristics
Since the herb is probably covered by the pink petals, you'll have to swim around the lake to find it.
If you go closer, it will [em1]sparkle[/em1], reflected in the water’s light.
You'll likely have to swim all over that lake. My husband had quite the time with it himself. Hoho.
When it blooms, it's influenced by the surrounding flowers, changing its shape to match theirs.
They say it absorbs light and glows on its own, but only when in [em1]pitch black environment[/em1].
I always thought this bioluminescent flower was quite marvelous. Hoho.
It was reportedly found in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1], where the Star Scouts ventured.
Specifically, it inhabits a [em1]fountain[/em1] where sunlight filters in and the ambiance of day and night exist in harmony.
Good thing I read up on those books about Star Scouts. Hoho.
Enite gave me information about the biome and the characteristics separately!
This makes it easy to find exactly what I need!
The book said it disguised itself as a [em1]flower with purple petals and yellow stamens[/em1] [em1]inside the fountain[/em1].
Lisa? Why? Didn't we just talk about her the other day?
I want to know more about the usual Lisa.
The usual...
I haven't thought about Lisa for a long time.
She was such a kind and gentle soul.
Come to think of it, [em1]Lisa was a terrible liar.[/em1]
A terrible liar?
As you know, Ellie, Lisa has been here since the very beginning.
She was here even when I was born.
She's been here a very long time.
Indeed. A very... long time.
Enite?
Whenever someone in the village fell ill, Lisa was always there to care for them.
She'd always say, "You'll be fine, just leave it to me," and she'd nurse them with all her heart.
But of course, not everyone could always be saved.
Sometimes... We had to say goodbye to those we loved.
Even then, Lisa would tell us it would be okay and to leave it to her.
But whenever she did... She could never quite look you in the eye.
She wore an expression more sad and heartbroken than anyone...
Seeing that look on her face... Somehow, it made me feel a little comforted.
Even though we lost so many people, perhaps having Lisa by our side was what gave us the strength to carry on.
Though the other villagers were a great support as well.
I'm here, too.
That's comforting.
You and Rubrum give me so much strength.
Thank you, too.
I truly wish I could see Lisa again.
I want to tell her we're doing well and that she shouldn't worry...
If I find her, should I give her that message?
No. You will find her, Ellie.
When you bring her back, I'll tell her myself.
I understand. I promise to bring her back.
Enite, how are the festival preparations coming along?
They're coming along nicely, so don't you worry.
I have something to tell you, too. Could you spare a moment for me after the festival starts?
Also, is it okay if I... invite some other people?
Other people? Who did you have in mind?
The witches who helped me... and Aurea... and Freddie, too!
That's so thoughtful of you.
I actually already made invitations for them.
Would you be a dear and deliver them?
Absolutely, I can do that.
Here you are, then. The invitations.
I'll leave it in your hands.
Okay. I'll make sure they get delivered.
I know I can count on you. Come see me when you're finished.
I'll see you tomorrow.
It seems the festival preparations are all complete.
Shall we begin the festival tomorrow, then?
Very well. Leave these things to me. I'll have everything set out in boxes.
To start the festival, we need to prepare the necessary items first.
To recreate this graduation ceremony, you'll need a wide-open space, won't you?
Just like you said, Ellie. The area in front of the fountain seems perfect.
Are you sure? It might get pretty noisy.
If it's for you, of course it's alright. Don't you worry about a thing.
In fact, I'm looking forward to it. It's a festival, after all.
Feel free to start whenever you're ready.
You may begin the witch graduation ceremony anytime. I'll take care of the setup and preparations.
Oh, and Enite? Could you make some delicious cold dishes?
Make delicious food... and serve it cold?
Yes. We'll need food for the graduation ceremony, too.
Hmm... Most of what I make is hearty home cooking. I'm not sure it would suit a cold dish.
Yeah, you're right. I'll ask someone else. Thanks!
Enite! I even got rid of the Thornbush Core that was in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]!
This place can return to how it used to be.
To the right of where we’re standing lived a young tailor named Nana.
At the very bottom of the village, there used to be a wonderful bakery.
This house had been empty for quite a long time. It changed owners several times.
And… the wisteria, once the pride of the village, also catches the eye.
At last, all the thorny vines in the village are gone.
Ellie, you really went through a lot.
Like before, the villagers who used to live here will be able to return, right?
Holhol. For now, let’s go down to the lower village together and take a look around.
There’s a lot I need to tell you.
Many people used to live here too, right?
That’s right. I’ll tell you one by one.
Theo is the child of a couple who were my friends when I lived in the city.
Sadly, that child said she wouldn’t come back.
The couple ran the bakery together… and they had two daughters.
So I’m thinking of giving this house to a boy named Bjorn.
He’s a boy who left decades ago, but he’s a friend who kept saying many times that he really wanted to come back.
But only the two daughters said they would return to the village.
Instead, a boy named Theo will probably be living here alone.
It would be wonderful if we could see its great blossoms bloom once again.
That’s about all I can tell you regarding the lower part of the village.
Holholhol. Who would you like to invite first?
Do you want to think it over a bit more this time as well?
Since all the places in the village that had thorny vines are gone anyway, you can take your time and think at ease.
Uh~ hmmm…
This time, the stories behind people moving in are quite diverse.
I’d like to hear the villagers’ opinions once more as well.
Alright. Then think about who you want to send a letter to first, and let me know.
But since he has to be apart from his parents for a while… they decided to send the boy to the village where I live.
Holholhol. Who would you like to send a letter to?
The bakery.
Who should we send the letter to?
A good choice. As always, I’ll ask Aurea to take care of the letter.
Then I’ll go ask Kyla to repair the house, just like always.
Of course, of course. Just like always.
I hope Theo, who will come instead of Nana the tailor, arrives.
I hope Bjorn, who used to live in the village long ago, comes.
I hope Clala and Dana come.
I’ve always wanted there to be a place in the village that sells delicious desserts.
If someone who remembers the village’s history comes, I think we’ll be able to hear old stories.
Rubrum is also waiting for a friend his age to come soon.
Enite! I want to send a letter to the next villager who will come.
And it’s amazing that already a house has moved in during that time. Time really flies.
Now there are two houses left, right?
It’s really difficult.
Holhol, it seems Ellie is really excited.
This time too, we’ll need to choose who to invite first, right?
In the end, everyone will move in, so don’t be too impatient.
In the meantime, take a little more time to think it over.
Seeing that you’ve come, it seems it’s already time to send a letter to the last villager.
Hoho, just hearing it makes me feel happy. The friend who receives the letter will be delighted as well.
I’ve prepared a letter as well.
Haha, Enite, you had already anticipated it.
That’s right. Let’s send the letter you prepared along with mine.
Now, the only one left is the [em1]bakery[/em1].
Now, the only one left is [em1]Bjorn[/em1].
Now, the only one left is [em1]Teo[/em1].
Hoho, there's only one person left, isn't there?
Finally, a new person is moving into the last house to be repaired...
I’m so excited!
I can hardly even remember the last time every house in the village was lived in.
So I even wrote it in the letter.
Finally, we meet.
I wrote that I want to meet soon and greet them face to face.
I’ve prepared the stage.
I wrote that I’ll help them do whatever they want when they return.
Then, at last, the story finds its closure.
I wrote asking them to return to the village and make the finale shine.
The bakery couple’s two daughters are named Clala and Dana.
Clala really enjoyed helping with the work. Instead of wandering outside, she preferred staying by her parents’ side, helping out in the shop.
When they left here, Dana was younger than Rubrum.
Back then, she was toddling around... I can’t wait to see how much she’s grown.
Bjorn was a child who left for the city with his parents back when I was young.
Recently, I happened to have a chance to see him, and that led us to talk about the village.
As a child, he was small, but now he has grown into a very dignified figure.
He said working as a train engineer was the secret to becoming healthier.
It seemed there was no longer any need to worry about him skipping meals like before.
Have you met Arden?
He's a dragon who lives in our village.
I thought Arden was a human like everyone else when I was small.
Because he really was too normal.
The first time it really struck me he was a dragon was after I returned to the village.
I aged a lot, but Arden had not changed at all.
That sounds... somewhat strange.
That's how I felt at first.
But after my parents passed and lots of things happened in the village,
Arden's brought me some solace because he hasn't changed in the slightest.
Because dragons don't change?
Yes, Arden stayed even when the village was a total mess.
Going about his business as he always did.
Unchanging and a permanent fixture... Those meant a lot to me.
Now he's already a very important family member in the village to me.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Enite"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Baking pies is my hobby.
Well, actually it's more of a habit than a hobby.
Have you always liked cooking?
Not really.
My mother baked the most wonderful pies.
Since I wanted more, I watched over her shoulder and copied her. That’s probably how it started.
I've eaten three fruitcakes Dad baked in one go too.
Rubrum has grown a lot before I notice, and become a little pie glutton too.
Maybe Rubrum will learn to bake pies someday too.
When I lived in the city, I used to work at a clothes shop.
Fancy clothes dazzled me when I was walking in the unfamiliar streets.
So I found the most stylish clothes shop in the city and asked to work there.
You're such a doer, Enite.
Well, I was simply naive...
I was just a village girl attracted to pretty clothes. I knew nothing about how hard a career it was.
I ended up quitting in less than a month.
And you returned to the village?
Certainly not. I didn't want to leave the city, so I went on job hunting again.
I only spent a few years in the city, but it earned me quite some useful experience.
I don't care to go back to the city, but... I cherish my memories there.
What kind of villagers used to live here?
You mean before the prickly vines appeared?
Right. Not everyone has come back. Who else used to live here?
I want to know them better.
Well... I need some time to recall their names.
Firstly, there was Brad the former librarian, who you already know. He loved to make jokes.
There were Mr. and Mrs. Noah, and their two children. Prickly vines were not their reason of leaving though.
Their elder son was a top student. They moved to the city to further his education.
And a wandering merchant called Sparkle also called the village home,
but for half of the time, he was away from the village, doing business.
Before Aurea came, we relied on Sparkle to bring us goods from other places.
I see. We did have various villagers here.
Indeed. Oh, and there was a young man called Haji.
He was as strapping as Kyla. I believe he was amid some sort of training...
He stayed here for a few years because he found this place good for training. Before he left, he was quite frustrated by his inability to conquer the prickly vines.
That's all the villagers I can recall for now.
It's awesome to learn about so many villagers I wasn't aware of!
My husband was born to a prominent family in the city, but he had the temperament of a wild horse.
He left home for a career in music which his family opposed.
How did you get to know each other?
We first met at a New Year banquet held by aristocrats in the city.
Whoa, a nobles' banquet! It must be luxurious and fun.
It was, but I was there to serve food, and my husband was there to play the piano.
We were both too busy to notice the existence of each other.
However, towards the end of the banquet, he suddenly came to talk to me.
I thought he was interested in me... but his eyes were fixed on the plate I was carrying.
Ahaha, even Enite can make mistakes.
Exactly. My husband stared at the untouched steak in my plate, and asked whether he could have it.
He seemed curiously comfortable with the request.
And weirdly enough, I didn't feel offended either. Instead, I found his straightforwardness quite pleasant.
And then? And then?
As I was also hungry... I suggested that we cut the steak into halves.
My husband agreed, so we went to a staircase outside the venue, and had our first conversation as we shared the steak.
That sounds like a scene in a novel...
Pies
City life
Previous villagers
Husband
A cup of piping hot tea and a book is enough to make a person happy.
I wish the village can stay peaceful and quiet forever.
I lived in the city for a few years when I was young.
Fortunately, I landed a job in a tavern where bands performed every day.
I learned to dance and sing, and made many friends. I had a great time there.
He had fierce eyes and usually wore a long leather jacket. His expression was melancholy, but he always stood straightly.
Village traditions
Bjorn left the village before I did.
He left before the prickly vines ruined the place... I can't even remember how many years ago it was now.
Once the village is bustling again, there's so much I want to do.
When did he get back in touch?
It was a few days after you arrived in town, Ellie.
Because the train stopped for the prickly vine, he had to pull into a nearby station and took the chance to visit the village.
Oh? Maybe Bjorn was the driver of the train I was on.
It's possible. Ask him next time.
I see that Bjorn still remembers the way back here somehow.
What do you want to do?
For starters... I want to restore the tea fields near the village.
If we can grow high-quality tea leaves again, we could bring back the tea festival.
Wisteria's tea was once famous for its quality.
There are plenty of people who'd be waiting for our tea. We could expect more visitors.
That actually sounds fun.
Of course! When I was young, the fountain area used to be packed with folks from all over.
There were even witches who came for the tea.
I don't think the whole village has ever been so excited and merry as it was then.
Of course, since you arrived, Ellie, the village's had plenty of bright moments too.
We should do it, Enite! Let's make it happen together.
Hohoho... It'll take some time. Are you sure?
Restoring the tea fields to their former glory could take years.
And for the festival to regain its old fame... That'll take even longer.
Still, I want it done before Rubrum comes of age.
I want Rubrum to see what I've seen in my childhood.
When I got that letter again, I was a bit surprised.
He was shocked by the prickly vine blocking the village as well.
Sounds like his reasons were similar to mine, except I followed the Cat God.
Exactly... When he heard you'd cleared the prickly vines, he rushed straight here.
When I saw him again, the boy who used to be smaller than you had grown to Arden's size. It was really astonishing. Hoho...
When he was a child, Bjorn was too weak even to climb a tree properly.
Looking at him now, it feels like a lifetime ago.
It's hard to imagine him as that sickly kid when you see him now.
Right? Even on the day he left, he quietly held his tears in.
That's why, though many villagers have returned... Bjorn's homecoming felt extra moving.
He's one of the few who shared my childhood.
About the witches
Ellie, you're the third witch to stay in that witch's house while I've been in the village.
Wait, wasn't Lisa always the one in that house?
Not always. After Lisa disappeared, a witch from out of town stayed there briefly.
Really? It's rare for a witch to just turn up like that. Interesting.
I guess I prefer to carve my own destiny.
Hohoho. Indeed. That witch was rather unusual.
She stayed a few days, then suddenly said she would leave, and she did.
I think she was here for the tea.
She came talking about tea... When she saw how ruined the village was, she seemed so disappointed that she left.
What kind of witch are you?
Didn't that witch say anything after seeing the prickly vines?
At first, she poked around like she was investigating things, but she soon looked worn out and lost interest.
She said she'd come because she heard of our tea during her travels.
Ah, so that's why you told me at first to leave the village.
Yes. If a more experienced witch had given up, I thought it was too much to ask an apprentice witch.
That's why I felt so grateful you didn't give up on our village, Ellie.
You saved our village. Thank you again.
I served her what little tea we had left, but she said it wasn't as good as it used to be.
What brings you here?
Just tell me comfortably.
I guess you have time for a chat.
You seem to have a lot of questions about me.
I don't sell anything.
I don’t think I know about that.
Turns out that it's true...
Although it still remains elsewhere, I’m here now.
I'll get rid of all the prickly vines and bring the villagers back again.
Ellie, you're so reliable.
I’ve already brought Kyla back.
I want to see a lively village soon.
I'm also looking forward to it.
So, since you answered all my questions, I should give you a prize.
Tada, I'll give you a candy.
Wow. It looks delicious!
Eat carefully.
Okay! I'll enjoy it. Thank you.
I'm going to leave now.
Yes, I also have to go somewhere else...
I've heard everything that I need from here.
Oh, as the master witch may already know, please let me know if there's a change in village population.
I’ll leave my office address.
See you next time. Ellie Blueriver.
Good bye.
I removed the prickly vines around here.
Already? But you haven't asked many questions yet...
You've provided all the important information well. So as a prize...
I’ll give you one more candy, since you’ve answered all of my questions [em1]without any mistakes[/em1].
The vanished master witch... prickly vines that suddenly appeared, and a village left with only 4 residents...
And Blueriver...
It would be fun.
Look at this, Virgil! I got candy too.
Ellie, don’t eat that.
Oh, why? I got this as a prize.
Didn’t you see his face just now?
No one has ever looked that suspicious.
Virgil, it's a bad thing to judge people by their faces.
It’s okay to judge someone with that kind of face.
And, you also thought he was suspicious at first.
Anyway, be careful.
He seemed like a nice guy. Don't sweat it.
By the way, what is that Exchange Department or whatever? Does it really exist?
Witch-Human Information Exchange Department.
It surely does. There were some difficulties, but it's still running.
What kind of place is it?
It’s a place created to share collected information with human beings.
These days, it seems to be focused on the [em1]census[/em1] of the villages managed by Witch's Houses.
Hmm, so it isn't a strange place.
The strange thing is the people, not the department.
Witches naturally collect information because of the Witch's Houses.
Let’s bring back the villagers first.
We'll meet Kent again anyway.
But is Kent really from there?
You answered everything without even checking on that?
You saw the [em1]moon-shaped brooch[/em1] on the cloak, didn't you? It also serves as a Witch Society pass.
I didn't know that.
And his [em1]red jeweled necklace[/em1] is the [em1]royal seal[/em1] of the human society.
Does that mean he is [em1]royal blood[/em1]?
Could be, but from the looks of it he’s just a [em1]public official[/em1].
I mean, because people who work for the royal family also have them.
Well anyway, that means it's not a lie.
He didn't look like someone who would lie either.
Indeed, It's going the way... Blueriver thought it would.
I guess I'll become a little busy now.
See? He's a nice guy.
What on earth makes you think so? He seemed to be up to something.
Prejudice is not a good thing, Virgil.
You're just happy because you got candy.
The candy is just something extra!
He even offered to find out about the previous witch.
Should be easy for him, considering the amount of info they get there.
Right? We just need to focus on restoring the village!
This is such a quiet place.
Hello. Are you Ellie Blueriver?
Yes, that's me.
My name is Kent. I work for the [em1]Witch-Human Information Exchange Department[/em1].
I think it's my first time hearing of such a department...
It’s a department created by witches to provide information that they find useful to humans.
It's been quite a while since it was created. If you haven't heard of it... are you an apprentice witch?
Uh... Yeah. I only came here recently.
No, I'm not.
Didn't you recently register on the Witches' Catalogue as Ellie Blueriver at this Witch's House?
Uh... Yes, I did.
Then, where is Ellie Blueriver?
Actually, I’m Ellie Blueriver.
So why did you lie?
Because you looked suspicious, I just...
You can trust me.
Ellie, who are you talking to again?
Oh, a... a witch or whatever from the Exchange Department.
Is that a talking hat?
<shake>Oh, the m... master witch</shake> is not here right now, so she's talking through the hat.
The master witch is not here...
Because she's busy. <shake>Haha...</shake>
If he's from the Exchange Department, it must be because of the villagers.
Villagers?
The master witch seems to know well about us.
I know a little bit.
Since I left everything related to the Witch's House to Ellie, you can talk to her.
Right, I'm in charge of the Witch's House now.
Alright, got it. I’ll do that for today.
But what will we be talking about?
Don't worry, I will only ask some simple questions.
If you answer well, there is even a [em1]prize[/em1].
Wow, a prize?
What is the [em1]name of the village[/em1] that the Witch's House you're currently staying at is in charge of?
It’s Wisteria.
Then, [em1]how many[/em1] villagers are living in Wisteria now?
Uh... Hmm, just a minute.
Oh, there are 4. Four people are living there now.
4 people.
... Did you say [em1]4 people[/em1]?
Yes, Enite, Rubrum, Arden, and Kyla, who moved back recently.
This data I have says that [em1]7 years ago[/em1], Wisteria used to have [em1]20[/em1] residents...
Can I go to the village and take a look?
Of course. I'll guide you.
You are reliable.
Since I'm in charge of the Witch's House, leave everything to me.
That’s...
Some prickly vines that destroy houses suddenly appeared in the village a few years ago.
So, many villagers had to leave. Only a few people remained.
2 people
3 people
4 people
5 people
It’s 2 people.
It’s 3 people.
It’s 5 people.
Wake up, Ellie. It's 4 people.
Prickly vines destroying houses...
Oh, that's probably right too.
You registered on the Witches' Catalogue not too long ago, right?
Yes... But why?
But what kind of question?
You don’t need to worry, since they’re formal and trivial questions.
I see... Wisteria.
Oh, it’s here.
Bimbley
Vine Deli
Yegrina
It's Bimbley.
It's Vine Deli.
It's Yegrina.
Ellie, didn't you see the sign? This village is [em1]Wisteria[/em1].
Oh, right. It’s Wisteria.
Hello! Kent, long time no see.
Is the master witch still not here today?
Huh? Yes...! That’s right. Since she’s a busy person... Haha...
It was a joke. You don't have to hide anymore.
It's been a while, Ellie Blueriver.
I’m not sure what you’re talking about...!
I already know that the master witch is not here for some reason.
Actually...
Looks like someone new has moved into the village.
I'm also relieved to see the village being restored smoothly.
Oh, oh, no! She’s here!
I also know that you are supposed to go to the Witch's House in Highlion, Ellie.
Ugh
Don’t worry. I’m just curious.
I wonder what happened.
Please tell me. I will keep it a secret.
... You’ll really keep it a secret?
Yes, he’s a villager who was originally living here.
What's his name?
His name is Roy. He’s running a flower shop.
Is he living alone?
I see... Alright, got it.
So that's what happened...
You seem to empathize with the village, Ellie.
I just did as I was taught.
But, I’m worried...
Wouldn't they be waiting for you at the Witch's House in Highlion, Ellie?
Everything may seem fine, but the School for Witches and Highlion will find out.
When that happens...*Giggle*
Oh, I’m sorry. It reminds me of something from the past...
What should I do?... What if my professor finds out?
I mean I will really be in big trouble if Mom finds out...
That would be really a big problem.
But don't worry too much.
I think we should worry considering Aria’s personality.
Ellie is staying here with good intentions of helping the village.
That is for sure. And it probably won't become known so soon.
As far as I know, the School for Witches does not inform Witch's Houses about sending apprentice witches.
That’s why neither place will think anything is wrong despite your abscence.
Then, that won't be a problem. What a relief.
And um...
Is there something else...?
Um... No, not really.
Then, I have something I want to ask you, is that ok?
Of course. You're free to ask whatever, Ellie.
I want to know what kind of person the witch originally at the Witch's House is and where she went.
I think it has something to do with the village, and probably with the prickly vines also...
Can you help me?
I don't know anything right now, but I'll investigate and let you know next time I come.
I’ll leave it to you then.
You'll keep it a secret, right?
I can't leave this place behind now.
Of course. I made a promise with you, Ellie.
Unless an unexpected situation requires.
I'll head back now.
Alright, see you next time.
Oh, I almost forgot.
Tada! Here is an award for the hard work.
Wow, thanks.
I'm really leaving now!
Hey, isn't that Kent?
Kent!
Oh, you're here, Ellie!
Good day to you, Ellie. I've been awaiting your arrival.
It's about your previous request for me.
My previous request... What was it?
You asked me about who was [em1]the previous witch[/em1] of this Witch's House.
Oh! I remember now. Yes, that's right. Any progress?
Because she was registered as the owner here previously, she was easy to track down.
What are you doing over there?
Oh, just thinking over things.
Thinking over things?
Who was it? The witch that lived here?
Her name was [em1]Lisa Whitegarden[/em1].
A lady 118 years of age.
So this witch is old enough to be my granny.
It's said that she appeared to be [em1]a lady in her twenties[/em1].
Because few witches actually look their age. Granny looks really young too.
Besides, your mother looks younger than you.
Do you know about the House of [em1]Whitegarden[/em1]?
Sounds familiar...
Oh, aren't they the witches who create [em1]witch's gardens[/em1]?
My garden at home was built by Dad, but he received much advice from the Whitegardens.
Yes, it would be accurate to claim that most witches' gardens were built by the Whitegarden family.
A scion of the family, Lisa came to Wisteria, where she was the only witch.
It's said that she came to Wisteria to study the [em1]White Prickly Vine[/em1].
White Prickly Vine?
Why do you think she came here then?
Um... Could she have gotten tired of gardening?
Well, although I am not privy to the details, that does not seem to be the case.
The reason why the Whitegardens are renowned is that they use [em1]white marble sculptures[/em1] and [em1]vines[/em1] to adorn their gardens.
Then her investigation into White Prickly Vines should be related to gardening.
That sounds about right.
But where is Lisa right now?
According to the Witch Society's records, Lisa is still based in this Witch's House.
I've inquired with other witches to no avail.
Hm... Maybe she's really disappeared.
But there is still more information.
Besides, Ms. Lisa often tasked me with the translation of books or requested documents from me.
Those books are mainly to do with [em1]plants[/em1] or [em1]immortality[/em1].
So [em1]Lisa[/em1] must have been behind the prickly vines in the village!
But there's no evidence to prove that conclusively.
And what's her purpose?
That's why I've brought some of the passages that I was unable to translate from the books Lisa passed to me.
Great, if we can figure out these, we may be able to obtain more information.
But this book is written in an unknown ancient tongue and the Witch Society [em1]cannot decipher[/em1] it either.
I'll need to ask the [em1]villagers[/em1] then. Thank you.
We should ask the villagers about [em1]Lisa[/em1] too.
The villagers have known her for so long. Surely they must know some of the places she frequented.
Then I must be going.
May I borrow this book?
Of course. Please return it to Ms. Lisa someday.
I'm happy that I was able to help, Ellie.
Wait, the prickly vines in the village show plant-like traits, don't they?
Book in ancient languages can be sent to the Witch Society to be translated.
Then it shouldn't be a big problem.
But the mention of [em1]immortality[/em1] worries me a little.
Apart from that, there's also a book about [em1]how to meld the traits of plants[/em1].
Thank you for agreeing to help.
You're welcome, I'm happy to help too.
Then, I'll visit you again if someone comes to the village, or if anything comes up.
Sure, have a safe trip back.
I've brought along some candy for moral support.
But the details are yet to be uncovered.
Will it really be like that?
Well... To meld the traits of plants...
In the end, we're still in the dark as to Lisa's whereabouts.
This translation service will return any untranslatable book to its owner.
I haven't gone yet.
Emm, is it the time already?
It seems that he's come again.
What? Yikes! I should hide!
Huh? Why's he back?
It's suspicious.
Shhh.
Good here.
Do this here... *cough*...
I apparently need to do the preparation at midnight the next time.
And I shall call a certain someone too. She's good at this...
This way, I can finally... Ellie... the next time.
I can't wait to see you. Miss Ellie... *cough*
Ahhh! Virgil, you saw that?!
I knew that guy was up to something bad!
You're way too gullible...
He said he would start preparing at midnight the next time! And he would find an expert for help!
What is he going to do to me...
It's okay. At least you found out in time.
Yup, I'll expose him the next time we meet!
Right, since Kent always comes on the fixed day.
The day after a villager moves back.
I need to get ready for that day.
Until then, focus on your original tasks.
That guy will only come if a villager returns.
You're not referring to him by his name anymore?
Restore the village first, so that the villagers can come back.
Wait, she said she has something to hand to the librarian when the library is restored...
Oh, yeah. It's [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "LisasBooks_Name"))][/em1]!
Now that she has come to my mind, I'll take [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "LisasBooks_Name"))][/em1] to [em1]Arin[/em1] at once!
What time is it now?
It's midnight.
<wave>Ho-hum~</wave>
Let's wait on the other side of the door.
I don't know whether it will come, but...
He's not here yet. Was I mistaken?
I should have gone to sleep instead.
That way, you may get into trouble.
Hmm... Let me wait a bit longer, since I don't know when he will come.
<wave>Ho-huuuum~</wave>
Was I overthinking?
People aren't usually that evil, are they?
There are evil people out there.
But Kent has a righteous appearance.
I don't think anyone who's ever seen Kent would agree on that.
Wait, someone's coming... I can hear the footsteps.
Shh, he's approaching.
I can't hear what he's saying...
He seems to be chatting with someone else.
Shall I peep through the window?
Don't. You're too close.
If you can see them, they can see you.
What on earth... Ellie also... *cough*...
He seems to be planning something...
You're indeed an expert... It's so...
What do I do... Shall I jump out and expose him right now?
Not now. It's too dark.
Wait until the sun has risen.
If so, all I can do now is wait.
Get this... from here...
Remember to wake me up... if I... fall asleep...
<shake>They really came before sunrise...</shake>
<shake>Ellie!!</shake>
Hmm... emm...
<shake>Ellie! Get up! It's morning!</shake>
Hmm... What the heck...
What's so great about morning, Virgil...
What's this mess.
And why are you whispering?
You forgot what you said yesterday?
You said you would get out at sunrise.
Huh...? Ah!
Noooo!!
<shake>The school! I'm late!!</shake>
<shake>Ahhhhhh!</shake>
Congrats!
Congratulations.
What...? Diane? Kent...?
*cough* I was right in getting an expert to do it.
Ahem, right? I'm an expert in creating surprises.
Ellie, you were surprised, weren't you?
<shake>Yeah... To the point that I almost fainted...</shake>
*cough* Then it was a perfect success. Thank you, Diane.
Of course I will join the celebration for Ellie.
But what's... what's the celebration all about?
Well, Kent will explain it.
The method I told you last time went smoothly...
The Society of Witches has issued a formal permission.
Which means...?
Ellie, you can now officially start your apprenticeship here.
*cough* Congratulations again.
Hooray! Congratulations!
So, Kent, the preparation you talked about last time...?
You heard it? *cough*
To be honest, I knew it would go smoothly, so I was planning for a celebration party in advance.
I decided to start preparing at midnight, so as to give you a surprise.
But I should admit that I couldn't probably have managed without the help of Diane the expert.
Yeah. I wanted to use fireworks too. The banging noises will create a festive atmosphere, right?
Oh... I didn't know this, and I got you wrong...
Hm? What did you say?
Nothing, I mean, thank you for the celebration... haha...
But I'm actually a bit disappointed.
Ellie, you actually lied to me of all people. I could have helped you too if you had told me earlier!
<shake>Haha... Kent?</shake>
Yes, I also told Diane about the master witch.
I think we can trust her.
You surely can.
Phew, it's great that the problem is solved.
Sorry, Diane. I was at a loss what to do.
It's OK. I understand, Ellie.
Now that I know it, I'll keep the secret for you and help you in every way I can.
No problem, haha. You're making me shy.
I should get back to work now. Bye.
Let me know whenever you need anything!
Okay, see you.
One to go.
Congratulations again, Ellie.
I'm sorry, Kent.
For what?
I've been suspecting you until just now.
I overheard you last time...
Oh, it's okay. I'm used to it.
Getting misunderstood can have its benefits, so I don't hate it.
For example, it can make such a surprise party even more surprising.
But how did it work? The Society of Witches really believed that letter with the fake signature?
Yeah, I'm great at imitating other people's writings. *cough*
Members of the Society of Witches were deeply moved by what you've done for Wisteria, Ellie.
Good to hear that. I still feel a bit guilty, though.
Don't be. Although the letter was fake, your goodwill is real. *cough*
It's so nice of you to say that.
Oh right, I've also got a message from Ms. Aria.
Wow, from Mom?
"I'm glad to learn that you're in good health."
"I'll be writing to you soon."
"PS: Run away if you can't take it anymore. Mom will always have your back."
Mom...
Should I feel moved?
As mentioned, Ms. Aria will be writing to you soon, so the message isn't so long.
I see. Please tell Mom that I look forward to hearing from her.
Oh, and there's a new face in the village.
Yeah, I'm glad that the restoration is going smoothly.
Good work, Ellie.
Haha, Kyla should take the credits. She built the house.
Utilizing my letter delivery trip, I also investigated other Whitegarden witches.
Whitegarden is the family Lisa belongs to?
My investigation shows that most Whitegarden witches are in the witch society.
Only two have wandered off: Lisa Whitegarden and Kate Whitegarden.
They say Kate Whitegarden left the witch society to build [em1]her own garden[/em1].
If so, did Lisa come here to build her own garden too?
You can say that.
Could you please ask around in the witch society for Lisa's whereabouts?
I'll tell you what I find the next time I'm here.
By the way, how's the translation of those books going?
What books?
The books that Lisa handed to the Society of Witches for translation, but were returned because they couldn't manage.
Oh, those books! I forgot it because I was overwhelmed by village affairs.
[em1]Arin[/em1] said that she was studying languages. Let's show them to her.
So there's someone you can go to right among the new residents, *cough cough*.
And, the last thing.
Here's one more gift for you from Ms. Aria, full of her love.
I'll be on my way now.
<shake>That really gave me a scare...</shake>
He's really nice.
What did I say?
I knew on first sight that Kent was a righteous man.
You were calling him "that guy" though.
That was a misunderstanding...
I wonder where Lisa has gone, though.
The villagers' image of her didn't sound like a villain to me.
You can't judge a book by its cover though.
Yeah... So she's in hiding after all?
Or six feet under.
Witches disappear when they die, you know. They don't leave a single trace.
Since they live reclusive lives, some witches may even die a sudden death at home alone.
That's exactly why witches wear [em1]witch brooches[/em1].
I searched the surrounding thoroughly but didn't find Lisa's witch brooch.
You "haven't found it."
Hmm... You're right. Maybe it's still lying somewhere.
Then, either Lisa is a baddy, or she's dead. Neither is a happy ending.
Oh, something the White Cat God said just struck me.
According to him, Lisa must be alive somewhere.
If Lisa were dead, the White Cat God would have told me.
Good, so a happy ending is still possible.
Now, let's look for Lisa while restoring the village.
Hello, Miss Ellie.
Wow, Kent, you are so punctual.
Thank you. *cough*
The village has so many dwellers already.
Yeah, it's gradually regaining its vitality.
You're so impressive, Ellie.
As I promised last time, I asked around in the Society of Witches for Lisa Whitegarden's whereabouts.
Not very fruitful, I must say.
Most people in the Society of Witches who know Lisa thought she was still in Wisteria.
Hmm... I should keep searching the surroundings then.
But I also came across a curious tale.
A curious tale?
Yes. It's about gods. It feels similar to what's going on in Wisteria, so I noted it down.
Wow! What's the tale about?
A witch that studies deities told me the tale. It's what she discovered during her research.
It says that, in a village that worshipped gods, there was a witch coveting divine power.
The witch used a certain method to drive all the villagers out of the village.
How would that help her get divine power?
Because divine power is the power of faith. It's the power of the followers.
Come to think of it, White Cat God also said something similar.
The witch attempted to snatch the power from gods when the latter were weak.
Did she succeed?
The remaining villagers told another witch about it and sought her help.
According to the second witch, when she arrived on the site, the first witch had almost succeeded.
It's a perilous tale. Not even the witch that told me the tale knows the details. We have no clue who the evil witch was, or what method she used...
Wisteria has two cat gods, and displaced villagers, just like the village in the tale. That's why I want you to know this tale.
Thank you, Kent. This is helpful.
*cough* I'm glad to hear that from you.
If you need help, just let me know.
I will, thank you.
Ah, and I got you a letter from Ms. Aria this time.
Really? A letter from Mom!
It's in the letterbox. Check it out when you have time.
Thank you for everything you did for me.
That's all for today. I'll come again.
Please take care... *cough*
Virgil, what do you think about what Kent said?
It surprised me that Aria would write a letter.
That's not what I'm talking about!
It's the story about the gods.
Well, there are all kinds of witches.
Can divine power be taken away?
Yes, in various ways.
For example, turning a god into a slave is also one way to take his power.
So, there are ways, no matter what the form is.
But why would a human want divine power?
It's normal for people to seek power.
Just like they seek water when they're thirsty.
They will seek power if they lack it?
If a person wants to become stronger, but can't get the power he needs,
he will consider various means.
Is it possible that Lisa was also longing for power?
Are you thinking about her motivation?
But we don't know Lisa well enough yet.
All we know so far is that she's a witch who wants to build a garden.
Or to become immortal.
We don't have clues for that yet.
Sigh... Pondering on it will get us nowhere.
We'd better find Lisa and ask her in person.
*Cough*...
Oh... Kent.
Do you have something exciting to share?
Yes. *cough* I do. Something interesting.
The village's got a new resident?
Yes! Prickly vines on the other side are also removed, so there will be many more.
That's great.
Yes, I suppose the village will soon be restored.
I still haven't found Lisa...
Are you looking for Lisa?
Yes, White Cat God said Lisa is in the Rainbow Forest.
That's curious.
I went to [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))]. There were traces of Lisa, but she wasn't there.
Oh, and the prickly vines in the village were in deed caused by Lisa!
I found her diary, which recorded how she spliced plants.
Is that so... The White Cat God and Lisa Whitegarden... curious.
I came today because I have something important to tell you.
It's about Highlion.
Highlion... Could it be...
Did they find out I that haven't been to Highlion?
I overheard the witches talking at the Witch Administration.
I heard that Highlion has been in contact with them.
They are complaining about no apprentice witch being dispatched there this year despite serious labor shortage.
Witches of the Administration are confused, since they did dispatch the second best performer of this year.
The magna cum laude at the School for Witches...
That's me, right?
There was actually only one witch better than her. The School for Witches is doing far worse than before...
The witches calmed the complainer down, saying that they would check it out. I believe it wouldn't take much time.
They will soon find out about you once they contact the train and ask the crew.
Then... what do I do?
Will I be captured?
You would probably be sent to Highlion if you don't do something.
Is there... any means to avoid that?
Ellie, you're now facing two problems.
First, you've come to Wisteria instead of going to Highlion.
Which isn't so big a problem.
Why? Isn't that the bigger problem?
*cough* Because all witches are overly sympathetic.
As long as they know how you care about Wisteria and what you've done for this place, you'll be fine.
What about the second question...?
Second, there's no master witch here.
That's the bigger problem. Ellie, you're an apprentice witch. They will think it inappropriate to leave you here alone.
I can handle it on my own!
But the Society of Witches values education. They won't agree.
So, what should we do? I couldn't find Lisa in the Rainbow Forest either...
So, I brought this.
A letter written by Lisa Whitegarden herself.
It clearly states why Ellie Blueriver should stay here instead of going to Highlion.
And with Lisa Whitegarden's signature.
Did you find Lisa, Kent?
No, I didn't.
Huh, then what's this letter?
This is a letter I wrote for Lisa Whitegarden.
For?
Because I believe that if Lisa Whitegarden had spent time with you, she would have written such a letter.
Isn't this forgery...
*Cough* I would call it "ghostwriting."
Ever since I entered human society, I've often written documents or signed on behalf of others.
It only takes one glance at a document or signature for me to copy it.
And Lisa wrote many letters to translate books, so I... *Cough*.
Sounds a bit risky...
But also very interesting!
It's my first time forging official letters!
Indeed, it's a novel experience.
*Cough* Not bad for Ms. Aria's daughter.
Hey, Kent, how do you know my mom?
I've received much help from your mother, Ms. Aria.
I'm really curious about what happened.
I'll tell you next time we have the chance. *Cough*
So, before this matter gets out of hand, I'll go deliver this letter.
Oh, I almost forgot about this.
Thank you for the candy.
It might be the last candy. *Cough*
Well, goodbye.
Let's meet again when the next villager comes.
People who forge official letters usually aren't good folks.
But this is for a good cause and is okay.
And it's also quite fun.
But what he said today was a bit cryptic.
Cryptic?
"It might be the last candy."
Um... yeah...
If things go smoothly, why would it be the last candy?
Indeed, we can't rule out the possibility of things going wrong...
Maybe he's waiting for an opportunity.
Like now, a decisive opportunity.
Of course, I'm just offering one possibility.
After all, he looks quite cunning, and you're too trusting...
Alright, let's quietly follow him.
He never seems to go straight back, let's follow him and see.
See if he really has bad intentions.
Whoa, I didn't expect you to come in person, Kent.
Indeed. Corresponding by letter felt somewhat lacking.
You sent me two letters with truly fascinating content.
Right? Isn't it interesting?
I uncovered some intriguing details about the witch society and history, which prompted my visit.
Did the [em1]Silent Guardian[/em1] have some big secrets?
It's not about the book, per se. It's more of a story about a person named Arin.
For the details, wouldn't it be better to speak with Arin herself?
Alright. Arin should be in the library, so let's go together.
I became so fascinated by the story connected to Arin that I had to come see for myself. Hehe.
Hello, apprentice witch.
I'm swinging my hammer diligently.
It'll take some time, but I'm working hard.
Enite has made tea. Shall we have some together?
It's nice to have some rest once in a while. A good blacksmith must know how to enjoy life.
Delicious food and cold drinks. A day's bliss.
The hard stuff always tastes great after a good sweat.
There’s a specific sound that comes from wood well trimmed.
I'm willing to craft anything.
Can you hear the song of the hammer? It's my favorite song.
It's a sound that resonates with my soul, hahaha!
Getting firewood and training at the same time, killing two birds with one stone.
Argh! One! Two!
Oh right, Ellie, as a witch, you must need a lot of ingredients, right?
Just in case, I kept some. Hehe.
I’m listening.
What’s going on, witch?
A weird dream that I don't even remember... How strange.
It's really getting on my nerves.
It's a big problem. You can't sleep well if you keep dreaming, can you?
Not that bad. I sleep fine.
Then you don't eat well?
No, I also eat well.
What? Then you're healthy.
But I'm still concerned.
When that happens, I tend to work more.
When I hammer, the trivial thoughts disappear, and I can sleep better when I'm tired.
Hmm, is that so?
Ask Enite if you’re worried about something.
Enite is a problem solver.
Or you can ask Arden for a drink.
I can’t drink yet.
It's no big deal.
A curse... Interesting.
I wouldn't be surprised if Arden is cursed.
After all, he's a dragon with a long face. Hahaha!
That's right. He’s so cold.
He really isn't very easygoing.
Kyla, have you ever seen anything Arden threw away?
Oh, yes. I've got this one. He actually threw away such a nice wine glass.
There are letters engraved?
Yup. There are two conspicuous A's engraved.
Maybe it means "A curse on Arden"? Hahaha!
This probably isn’t the only thing that Arden threw away.
You know the merchant who often comes to the village?
She also said she saw him throwing things recently. Try ask her.
You mean Aurea? Thank you, Kyla.
So, am I holding an object that curses Arden?
Oh, I don't mean to curse him. Don't get me wrong. Hahaha!
I've seen plenty of lamps for sure.
It's not your average lamp.
It's a silver lamp that glows gently, with no wick or candle.
I think I've seen Rubrum holding something similar.
He said it was Arden’s, and that he was going to return it to him.
I should ask Rubrum then. Thanks!
Did you gather the materials?
Great, I'm super motivated.
You can take your time, but it has to be within today.
It’ll be useless if the house is already complete.
I'll do my best to make a good one!
Hello. You’re Kyla, right?
Oh, I guess you're the witch who helped Enite. My greetings, ma'am.
I'm Ellie, an apprentice witch. You don't have to be so formal.
Really? Then I'll talk casually.
I mean, witches are often older than they look.
I’m just as old as I look.
You came back so fast.
That's because there is a witch who wants to see me quickly.
I came in a flash since everyone was waiting.
If I’m welcome at any time, I’m also welcome today, right?
I really looked forward to seeing you.
Of course. You're welcome anytime.
Enite told me that an apprentice witch had come to the village and wanted me back.
What do you say then?
I only managed to come back because of your generous help.
Thank you for coming back too.
Whoa, it's the flying carpenter.
Sorry if I let you down, but I can't fly.
This is my friend, the talking witch hat named Virgil.
Nice to meet you, Virgil.
You don’t need to thank me, carpenter who can’t fly.
From now on, you will have to swing your hammer as much as flapping your wings.
Haha, don't worry. My arms are stronger than they look.
Are you fixing your house?
I’m making a new one rather than fixing.
It might take some time.
Wow, can I come and watch?
Of course. Come anytime.
It looks like you're about four arms short. Will you be okay?
Two arms are enough according to my experience so far.
Of course I wanted to come back. I like this village.
I can work here more comfortably than anywhere else.
I might need your help, Ms. Witch.
Let me know at anytime.
Sure. Everyone missed you.
Don't you need House Blueprints?
Usually, I do.
But this is my own house, so it's okay.
You need one to build houses for others, then?
Yes. To build a house, I need a [em1]House Blueprint[/em1] and [em1]Foundation Materials[/em1].
The [em1]Blueprint[/em1] can be purchased by talking to [em1]Aurea[/em1].
[em1]Foundation Materials[/em1] can be found in the forest. Those found in the forest around here are pretty good.
How long does it take you to build a house, Kyla?
I’m going to start building tomorrow and it should take about a day.
Hey! You're not working!
It’s break time.
Is it going well?
Yeah, no big deal.
Is there anything I can do to help?
Let’s see. Hmm...
Alright then. Can you do me a favor?
Rubrum borrowed my shovel and hasn't returned it to me yet.
I think I have to use the shovel a little bit later. Would you find Rubrum and get it for me?
Bring it to me if you find it.
Is that so? Come back if you change your mind.
Oh, you’re here. Can you help me?
Sure. What shall I do?
I have an idea: I want to add some [em1]decorations[/em1] to the house, but it requires some [em1]special materials[/em1].
Can you gather these [em1]materials[/em1] for me by [em1]today[/em1]?
Great, this is really motivating!
Please note that I need these materials [em1]today[/em1].
It's okay. I can build a lovely house even if I just follow the blueprint.
Do tell me if you change your mind.
Oh, did you change your mind?
It needs to be done before the house is complete.
Ellie, when I talk with you these days, I strangely feel a surge of creative inspiration.
So starting tomorrow, I’m thinking of selling some [em1]varied furniture[/em1]. I’ll also increase the [em1]stock[/em1].
Still preparing.
I’ll have everything ready as I said starting tomorrow, so be sure to check it out. Haha!
She... She really came.
Why wouldn't I? Haha!
Now, now, let's get down to business.
Well, well, no matter how I look at it, it's all in ruins, isn't it?
Look over there, Ellie. The structure is rather unique. If the water there flowed out and covered the floor...
You wouldn't need to drink to see a mirage! Haha!
You said just now that the view would be the perfect drinking snack.
But it's all in ruins now.
Seriously, Ellie. Where's your imagination as a witch?
You'll get what I mean once you see the completed structure.
Hey, not bad. Guess we won't starve.
<shake>Phew... This was... a piece of cake...</shake>
But your voice is shaking, and your hands are quivering.
Haha, then, leave the rest to me.
Repairs are going to take [em1]a whole day[/em1].
The size of the debris can pose a danger, so I'll close off the streets.
<shake>Okay. I'll leave it to you.</shake>
Can you clean up the [em1]debris[/em1] around the temple and bring it to me?
Oh, there you are.
Is the top floor still being repaired?
You've come just in time, Ms. Witch.
As if you can sense that I need you!
So, you need me?
Yes. As you can see, it's not just one or two places that require fixing.
It's going to be hard for me to restore with what I've got now.
But I know there's an adhesive that you witches make. It can stick anything together in just 3 seconds.
Well, you mean...
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GlueCandy_Name"))]!
<wave>Shake and shatter, break and batter, smooth and slick, so you will stick!</wave>
<wave>The fallen head, the torn window, and the ripped pages. Repair them before I can notice.</wave>
Huh? How do you know this song, Kyla?
Well, the witches always sang it when I went to the Witch's House to request that stuff.
So eventually I picked it up myself, haha!
And they told me that every witch who knew this song was probably a troublemakers at the School.
<shake>Ahem! Ahem!</shake> [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GlueCandy_Name"))], right? Leave it to me!
Troublemaking was the least of it. I could go on about her past...
<shake>Shut it, you!</shake>
Haha, good luck with the task.
What did you say all that for?
Just telling the truth, that's all.
Alright, whatever. I have to make the [em1]candy[/em1].
Kyla! Where did you go?
Oh, see, I was working and started craving food. So I fixed myself a little snack.
That's that.
Wow! It's perfect!
It happened all so very quickly again this time...
Ellie, come up here!
So, what do you think?
What did I say? It's a magnificent building.
Oh wow... So that's how it's supposed to look!
Actually there used to be a gorgeous dome top.
I wanted to get that restored too, but that project's too big for now.
Oh dear, I was off with the fairies.
The materials should be collected first, and as a result, the workbench should be cleaned up first.
Can you gather some of those pebbles for me?
Pebbles, you say?
It's alright if it's too much work. I can do it myself once I finish the work at hand, haha!
I've never seen you work too much.
You just cause destruction every day.
What?? I glued things together!
Alright, let me help you, Kyla!
What do you need me to do?
Oh, you're up for the job?
Could you gather more of the pebbles you see in front of the wagon?
Sorry for such a tedious task. Thanks! Haha!
Oh goodness, that one's all destroyed, too.
You knew about it, Kyla?
Of course. I'm not from here, so I didn't go to pray or anything.
But the atmosphere at night was fantastic enough to replace any drinking snacks.
I remembered it on my way to the village, so I went there.
Great. Enite told me it'd be a good idea to check in with you.
By all means, I'd love to help out.
But as you can see, my own house is in such a state...
I need a place to sleep and eat first of all, so I'm going to repair my own house first.
My house is fixed. Let's talk.
Oh, I see... Then, let's get moving, why don't we?
What? Right now?
Strike the iron while it's hot, as they say.
The temple is not in great shape now, but it used to be a quite fascinating building.
I've always wanted to touch it, but I may be punished by heaven for doing that! Haha!
As I said before, I don't know him that well.
I guess he is nice and sincere?
I wonder if he enjoys drinking. We can have a nice chat this time. Haha!
Lisa? Of course. We were friends! Hehe!
Friends? Really?
Sure! We were thick as thieves.
Will you tell me about Lisa then?
Sure, now listen closely.
Lisa hated bread that tasted too sweet because she considered it a main course.
She hated mushrooms too, saying they belonged in the garden.
Strange, I know. Mushrooms are delightful.
So do you know anything else apart from this?
Anything else? Hm... alright. This is a secret but...
Lisa said she had to have her back against the wall to go to sleep.
No! That's not what I meant!
Then what would you like to know?
The places Lisa used to go to a lot or what she was studying...
But she didn't mention these things to me.
Ah well...
Oh, she said this to me before.
She asked me what it felt like to have to [em1]repair[/em1] a house that I had built.
Repair it?
Yes, she looked very serious when she asked, so it's stayed with me till now.
What was your answer?
I said repairing it was my duty since the house would only need repairing because I didn't build it well. Haha!
Though Lisa looked like she disagreed strongly, she dropped the subject.
That's about it.
Hm... Alright.
Oh... Kyla. How would you react if Lisa was behind the prickly vines?
Lisa? Haha!
Lisa would make a terrible villain.
If she did it, she'd be beside herself with outrage.
Got it, thanks.
The only things that friends discuss when they're drinking are their grievances. Haha!
But Lisa didn't drink.
Wait... what?
Didn't you... ever talk about anything more serious?
Very good, you've found everything. Go on back to Kyla.
Now we're going to begin the repairs properly
Move to the bridge and begin repairs
Content: There's still one piece missing
Content: Speaking of which, I also took one away
So go help me bring it here.
I think this is it, I should bring it back.
Now we're going to begin the bridge repairs properly
Is the wine made out of that any good? Hahaha.
Fine wines? There are plenty of them.
What's your poison of choice, Kyla?
Wines with a bitter aftertaste that lingers on the tongue...
Mild wines should be enjoyed in a nice moody setting.
Sweet dessert wines aren't really my thing... but they are good once in a while.
I'm starting to think you just like drinking as long as it's alcohol, Kyla.
You got that right, hahaha!
But if I had to pick one, I'd go for wines with a bitter aftertaste.
Well, Enite mentioned that the leaves of the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "PlopRadish_Name"))][/em1] are especially bitter.
I spend all day sweating by a fire. A mouthful of that would be like heaven.
I can almost feel my mouth watering.
Ta-dah! Welcome to Ellie and Arden's winetasting party!
Hahaha, you've got the attitude. Very good, bring it over.
Here, this is the first glass.
It's a [em1]fragrant wine[/em1] made from melted [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SilverStarFlower_Collect_Name"))].
I've prepared a few snacks, take whatever tickles your fancy.
Which food goes best with [em1]fragrant wine[/em1]?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFlower_Collect_Name"))] salad
Cheesecake
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DangleMango_Name"))] sherbet
Shakshuka
Hahaha, this tastes good.
Hm... Though this is good, they don't seem to go well with each other.
We're serving up the second glass of wine.
It's a [em1]sweet wine[/em1] made by adding [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))] to other fruit wines.
Which food goes best with [em1]sweet wine[/em1]?
Bruschetta
French fries
Dark chocolate
Coming up, the third glass of wine.
This [em1]bitter wine[/em1] was made with fermented [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "PlopRadish_Name"))] leaves.
Which food goes best with [em1]bitter wine[/em1]?
This [em1]deeply aromatic wine[/em1] is best paired with a [em1]refreshing salad[/em1].
[em1]Sweet wine[/em1] and [em1]a dessert with a slightly bitter flavor[/em1] work best together.
[em1]Bitter wine[/em1] paired with [em1]savory drinking snacks[/em1] is sure to make anyone go "oh!"
Ugh, I'm sloshed...
Ugh, I can't drink like I used to.
Do you want to give Kyla more wine and drinking snacks?
That's true, it must have been a tall order to prepare such a spread.
Ehehe, feels so good...
Ugh, I can't help being talkative whenever I drink...
I... didn't say anything weird, right? Ehehe...
Let's recap.
The [em1]fragrant wine[/em1] was paired with bruschetta and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFlower_Collect_Name"))] salad.
The [em1]sweet wine[/em1] was paired with cheesecake, dark chocolate and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DangleMango_Name"))] sherbet.
The [em1]bitter wine[/em1] was paired with shakshuka and french fries.
What are you going on about.
Arden, more wine and drinking snacks over here!
Nothing to give to you...? Oh, Ellie, give me your hand.
This is wine I received as payment before coming back.
Uh... But I don't drink.
But it's pretty, even as a [em1]decorative piece[/em1].
Hehe, hehehe... Oh, I must have overdrunk... I can't stop grinning...
Feels like the old days when a glass after hammering and making things all day made it all better.
The sword I forged was so shiny, shiny...
The smooth side of the blade reflected me, sweaty. I looked really cool...
Wahaha, so embarrassing... Why am I thinking about that now, hehe.
The swords I forge now are shiny too! Super cool!
Oh, Kyla, you're forging swords?
Yes, mm, unrivalled masterpieces~
A weapon for chopping
A tool for protecting someone
A pretty ornament
Yes, that's a sword... Simple, right? Ehehe...
If only... But you can do this with weapons other than swords, right?
Yes, it's very pretty. The ones I forged were especially splendid.
What kind of sword are you working on right now, Kyla?
Ahaha, what are you talking about? I don't forge swords.
Huh? But you just said you were forging swords...
Wahaha, no, no. I would never forge a pathetic sword like that.
Oh my, haha, wahaha, this new wine's not bad.
Oh my, I'm mashed. I can't even talk... Looks like I can't drink like I used to.
This goes down really easily. Oh? Muhaha!
Though the new drink was a little disappointing... Arden's cooking was really good.
I wish I could cook as well as Arden, and become a master in my field, haha!
Haha, I'm really drunk. I'm going to head out.
What an irritating fellow.
Wahaha, yes, I drank all the wine before.
Hey, Ellie, what do you think a sword is?
Hm, speaking of which, shouldn't we do something for Ellie, who's been working so hard?
Yes, Arden's cooking is always delicious.
Oh, wonderful, wonderful...
Wahaha, hm, very good, it really is very good~
Wine would be the cherry on the cake, hahaha!
I didn't know Arden could make other foods...
It's long overdue for a few editions.
Too troublesome.
Hahaha, if Arden weren't so averse to taking the trouble, he'd have made his name in the neighboring village.
No need for that.
It's enough to sell just [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))].
I often went drinking with my friends like this back when I was working in the city.
What friends do you have here?
Wahaha, not any yet, but I'll make one sometime.
He can make anything you ask for, yet he insists he doesn't want to because it's too troublesome…
Bahaha
Ellie, you mentioned you were an apprentice witch, right?
When you become a full-fledged witch, we're going to toast to that.
Long ago, I was invited to an old nobleman's party. Now that was a sight to remember.
It was full of expensive wines and rare delicacies.
But this tastes much better. Yes, hahaha. It's true.
Better than the food at the party?
Wahaha, yes. [em1]Something that made my stomach churn[/em1] happened there too.
Though it's a bit embarrassing for me to say so, my swords are really good.
Yes, really good~ But some people just won't stop judging, and it kills the appetite.
What happened there?
Oh, it's too embarrassing to talk about~ Nahaha!
No, she's completely wasted.
Kyla, I heard you wanted to see me?
Oh yes, come quickly, Ms. Witch.
Nothing important, I heard you helped Rubrum look for [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]s?
Yes, it was pretty fun and I made a wish.
What? You made a wish? Oh dear, I wouldn't have asked you here if I'd known, hahaha!
Why? What's the matter?
Actually, Enite and I hid those [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]s.
Enite and you, Kyla!?
As you can see, the children in the village haven't got much to entertain themselves with.
So this was a small activity we planned for Rubrum.
These apples are known as Harvest Apples and are a specialty of another region.
Aurea helped us get hold of some.
How can this be... I thought it was an age-old legend.
Hahaha! I'm sorry, really.
We didn't really know if it would work and gave it a try. Turned out Rubrum really took to it.
But I left the village for some time, didn't I?
So Enite was doing on her own and couldn't venture far. So there weren't that many hidden.
But thanks to you, Ms. Witch, I'm back and we can start the game anew.
It was pretty fun hunting for them.
Oh, the Blue Apples are just painted with [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))]. I'll take care of them.
Thanks for playing with Rubrum. Here's something Enite wanted me to pass to you.
Though it isn't a legendary apple, it's really good, haha!
Thanks! Please tell Enite I said thank you.
You're welcome.
I hope your wish comes true too, Ellie.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FullBag"))]
But the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))]s will scream even during the production. Can you handle that?
Haha, that's why I got another kind of potion.
Tadah~ [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EarPlugPotion_Name"))]!
<shake>Isn't this just wine!</shake>
Nahaha, don't you know that wine's an excellent medicine?
*gurgle gurgle*... Hahaha, excellent stuff!
No one can stop a drinker like you...
Otherwise why would there be stories of alcoholics who drank their families into ruin and despair?
I'm a repairman of houses, so my house won't become ruins, hahaha!
Ohoho, wonderful~ Let's get started on what we need to do.
Now, add the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))]s!
<shake>Oh no! Their skin fell off!!!</shake>
Oh my, you've <shake>got a really loud voice</shake> for such a tiny critter!
So Ellie, can you hear this happy song? Hahaha!
So this is the reason... why the professors say not to make illegal potions...
Especially if it's just a potion by name.
Come, try a glass... *gurgle* Mm, hmm... This taste...
Na... hahaha, the rush is coming! This energy... <shake>Whoaaaaaa</shake>!
*gurgle gurgle*... I'm Kyla, the strongest person in the world, hahaha~ I believe I can fly!
Should we stop her before this gets out of hand?
Forget it, the Potion of Courage's starting to take hold.
Hey, pretty Ellie! Come have a glass... <shake>Oh right, you aren't old enough</shake>!
Well then, let me see, let's eat some drinking snacks then.
This... is some chocolate I've been keeping for a special occasion, here. For you only, Ellie.
Mud... chocolate?
This does take gumption to eat.
And also something... more solid. Here, have some of this spud.
Bleh... *cough cough* Kyla, my tummy's full to bursting.
<shake>What?</shake> That won't do, of course it won't do.
Then take this home for after! Dried meat I cut and made myself!
Eat much and grow up fast so we can be drinking buddies, little Ms. Witch, <shake>hahaha!</shake>
Oh, now I've made a potion, am I a witch like you, Ellie?
Haha, maybe.
Ah! Great, great! It's all thanks to you, my witchy friend.
But it's best to leave the potions to us witches, Kyla.
What, uh, I suppose witches are the pros. <shake>What about me?</shake> I'm a craftsman of wine!<shake> Haha!</shake>
Does it... really work?
<shake>Nahaha! </shake>Delicious!
I'm not asking you what it tastes like...
Doesn't seem to have much to do with courage...
Nahaha! Ellie! The most important thing about wine is the <shake>taste</shake> of it, the <shake>taste</shake>! Everything else isn't important!
<shake>*gurgle gurgle*</shake>... *gurgle* Ahhhh!
Though I'm a little worried about the effects of the potion.
Ugh... The whiff of liquor's far too strong.
I've got to go, Kyla.
Hah~ Do you have to leave so soon? <shake>Alright then</shake>, until next time, my witchy friend!
Donuts? Why do we have to eat something so sweet?
You hate sweets, Kyla?
Though I don't really hate them, I wouldn't go out of my way to have them.
Sweets don't go well with wine after all.
But I'm an expert when it comes to making drinking snacks.
I can make good pork and chive stir-fry and clam soup. Would you like some?
Ermmm, lovely, but I'm looking for a recipe for donuts.
Really? In that case, we happen to have a [em1]Pie Queen[/em1] in our village.
You can go ask her.
What would you like to discuss with Kyla?
Arden's Restaurant
The stew there is good. You must try it.
I must eat it to feel at home.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Kyla"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Blacksmith
If you don't mind a bit of colorful storytelling, I was holding hammers as soon as I could walk.
The hammer was my best friend and kept me company.
Carpenter
It's different working with wood as opposed to metal.
If the sound of metal being struck makes the heart beat, then that of wood being trimmed makes the fingers dance.
This is a place filled with good people, fresh air and clean water.
The only thing it lacks is more pubs, haha!
Liquor
It's a good friend second only to my hammer.
Liquor makes me doubly happy.
Build houses
Building houses is more fun if you do it while imaging what kind of people will live in them. Don't you agree?
When I visit houses I built, I usually find my imaginations correct.
On fine days, villagers used to party at the fountain.
Time would fly when we chatted over tasty wine and dishes.
Oh! How about we throw another party and invite everyone?
You can find a lot of fine timbers and ores there.
And it's fun to gather [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "LittleMandrake_Collect_Name"))][/em1] in the depth of the forest.
It goes with every wine, you know? Hahaha.
I've tried it with Freddie's fishing rod.
Freddie says it requires a good sense... I don't have it in me yet.
I've heard about a super powerful fish called [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Stone_Name"))][/em1]. I hope I can catch one of those. Hahaha.
Everyone in my family is either a carpenter or a blacksmith, so I've never considered a third job.
But my younger brother is an exception.
He always asks me to make desks and chairs for him. He never tried to do it himself.
However, one day he suddenly became a poet. We both enjoy drinking, and as we drank, he came up with lyrics for the tune I was humming. Hahaha!
Drum
Beating a drum is actually quite fun.
It's just like how I hit the table with my cup when I'm tipsy and merry.
Drinking? Hahaha.
Just kidding. My true hobby is thinking.
My work requires concentration, so I can't let my mind wander when at work.
After work, though, I think about how to improve my skills. Hahaha.
Blacksmiths don't visit the place so much anymore.
It used to provide the best ores, but you can't mine anything valuable now. Just mushrooms everywhere.
But there are other items a blacksmith can use, such as [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Kirby_Powder_Name"))][/em1]. It can be added to abrasives.
Unlike what one'd expect, witches are not so great at repairing.
Just like you, Lisa used to bring broken furniture and items to me.
I mean, It's good news for me. I will lose my job if witches are experts in every trade.
It's good to have a sundries store in the village,
but don't you find Alvin's prices a little high?
Sundries stores should offer inexpensive snacks. Don't you agree? Hahaha.
Legend
I've seen a legendary sword used by a warrior.
The sword didn't look as refined as I expected,
but it must have been sharp and easy to use, or it wouldn't have been chosen by a warrior.
So, I suppose inner values are indeed more important than physical appearance.
During the day, I have so much to do that it feels like I just work through it all without realizing it.
Of course, there are days off, but I feel like I’ve worked only when I work while the sun is up.
When that happens, I have to quickly grab a meal, so Arden's [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefStew_Name"))][/em1] seems like a great choice.
Ellie, have you ever heard any strange sounds when you went to [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))]?
Sometimes, I go to the forest to cut trees even at night.
I was walking and heard a strange sound, and when I turned around, I realized it was the sound made by [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "BubbleLizard_Name"))][/em1].
I was really surprised when I first heard the sound, you know?
I laughed so much. Ah, I remember I quickly grabbed [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BubbleLizard_Water_Name"))][/em1] because I was told it works well when added to alcohol.
It's the perfect weather for hammering.
Tell me if you need anything.
She even looks giddy when she walks.
Will Kyla be fine?
People go to another world when they are drunk.
The winetasting party ended in a hazy blur.
Like you said, liquor sold very well when paired with drinking snacks.
Hehe, told you so.
Yes. It's thanks to you one of my problems' been solved.
I'm tired. Let's call it a day.
You should go home too.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Kyla"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
Although she kept complaining, she's drunk so much today, so she shouldn't come pestering me for that old wine anymore.
Oh, welcome. Are you here to look at the furniture?
I chiefly sell beds, chairs, bookcases and other [em1]large furnishings[/em1].
And I'll sell them according to specific [em1]themes[/em1].
The themes [em1]change daily[/em1], so be sure to drop in often.
If you really want furnishings from a certain theme, let me know. The furniture I sell for the next [em1]3 days[/em1] will be from that theme only.
Well then, be sure to come by often!
Ahem, yep. I do know some rumors and jokes among village folks.
Do those not count? Haha.
Those are not stories of Wisteria.
But it's surprising. I thought Kyla wouldn't care about such trivial stuff.
I don't, I just find them interesting.
Some folks would babble on beside me when I'm blacksmithing.
That's how I got to know those stuff.
Now that I think about it, there're no such people in Wisteria, haha!
Let's see, if you want to do some research on village stories,
you should go to the [em1]village administrator[/em1]. Haha!
Usually, village administrators get to know everything going on in the village every day.
The dark's not great to work in. Come again during the day.
Great, this weather's perfect for doing some work.
Let's go have a look at the bridge!
Hm, these bricks are special indeed.
Then what about the remains of it? Is it intact?
Most of it appears to be here.
Good to hear.
But we'll need some extra manpower.
Even if I'm the best worker ever, it'll be difficult for two people to handle all these.
Where should I go to look for helpers?
If it's helpers we want, don't we have a lot here?
Hey! You, c'mere.
Hello, Kyla and Ellie.
You, are you strong?
I suppose I'm average. May I know why you're asking?
Mmhm... Not bad.
What are you doing?
Haha! I've been itching to try that out.
Kyla and I are repairing the bridge in the village and we need help.
Ah, if that's the case, I'd be pleased to do whatever I can.
Mmhm... A good attitude too!
Are you really going to continue like this?
This is my first time helping to repair a bridge, please feel free to give me any advice on how I can do better.
Very good, let's get this done before mealtime!
C'mon, just say whatever's on your mind, hahah!
Oh, I don't need anything at the moment!
Forget it. You have no idea how busy I am at the moment.
I want to use my feet as a second pair of hands if I could.
Oh, Ms. Witch, would you like to help?
Did you find the shovel?
No, not yet.
Take your time. We still got time.
Should I give the shovel back to Kyla?
I've got it.
That's pretty quick. Did you meet Rubrum?
Yes. I think he was playing in the sand with the shovel.
He hasn't changed. He's always loved playing with sand.
Thanks for finding the shovel. Now I can finish up the house.
Is there anything else I can help you with?
Nothing in particular but... Oh, do you have a favorite shape?
A shape? Why?
I'm contemplating the shape of the second floor terrace door. Pick one for me.
Rectangle
I think rectangle would be nice.
A rectangle is the classic shape for doors after all.
Okay, thanks for your help.
Come take a look once it gets finished.
Alright, I'll be sure to come see it.
Arch
I think arch would be nice.
An arch type goes well as I expected. You have a good eye.
Triangle
I think triangle would be nice.
Yes, a triangle type would also be pretty.
Heart
I think heart would be nice.
It would be cute.
No, I only found the shovel in the forest.
I guess he forgot about the shovel and went somewhere to play.
I should go fetch [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "KylaShovel_Name"))][/em1].
Kyla, do you remember the fountain at the center of the village?
Of course. I used to go there at night from time to time to sip on wine. The view there was nice.
Enite says she wants the fountain fixed.
That's a good idea. It needs some work, though.
Aren't you tired of building houses all the time?
No. I'd just be impatient if I stay still.
It's also fun to see the village being restored bit by bit.
Let’s see. Then the materials we have now... wouldn’t be enough.
I’ll work on the foundations. Can you get me some materials?
I’ll need 10x [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rock_Name"))], 10x [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Mud_Name"))], and 10x [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Name"))].
Are you delivering it to build Roy's house?
Right now, this is what's needed.
You've gathered everything already? That was fast.
Alright, I’ll start working on it tomorrow.
If you have the time, drop by when I'm building. I have something to ask you.
Hmm... That's perfect.
Oh, come to think of it, little Rubrum told me something.
Enite and Arden might be up to something.
I don't know. Rubrum said Enite wouldn't tell him even when he begged.
Anyway, they're definitely getting ready for something. Maybe a party or something.
I wish I could just get hammered... but I guess that would be difficult with two little kids, hahaha.
I’m not a little kid.
Right. You're a cool witch.
Hmm... A party... I wonder if I have anything to prepare.
Come to think of it, don't you have something like that?
I saw witches gather at Highlion Square and put something down during the Harvest Festival.
When night fell, those things gave out light and it was spectacular.
Uh... That sounds like...
A [em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FirecrackerPotion_Name"))][/em1][/em1].
Exactly! Why didn't I think of that?
Crafting those was prohibited at the School for Witches, but I'm an apprentice witch now.
If they allowed that, the School would have needed to be repaired at least 10 times.
It wouldn’t be that bad.
I don't know what you're talking about, but I guess I was helpful. Hahaha.
Right. I'm inspired.
Then do your best with the repairs, Kyla! I'm going to go now. Something came up.
Okay. Okay. Let’s all cheer up.
If it’s a recipe, we could ask Diane about it, right?
Rubrum will love it.
It will take about a day to repair the fountain.
You want the fountain repaired?
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GlueCandy_Name"))][/em1] to Kyla?
Yes! That's the one! It's really good.
I'll be able to get my work done in no time.
I need a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GlueCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Let's go pull off some ox horns now.
You have to give Kyla the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GlueCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Are you here to deliver the materials needed to repair the Witch's House?
No, I'm busy.
Oh, then I’ll be back later.
Hya Hya! I was just kidding. What's going on?
I'm sorry to ask this of you as soon as you're back, but...
I want to have the other villagers return like you did.
So I was hoping you could build the houses for the other villagers.
Hya Hya! I was wondering what you were going to say.
Of course I'll help. I was going to ask you the same thing.
Is there something I can help you with when you build the house?
In order to begin, I need a [em1]House Blueprint[/em1] and [em1]foundation materials[/em1].
Talk to [em1]Aurea[/em1] for the blueprints. She’ll sell it to you.
[em1]Foundation Materials[/em1] can easily be found in the forest.
So, if I bring the [em1]Blueprint[/em1] and the [em1]Foundation Materials[/em1], we can build Roy's house?
Yes. You can deliver a little at a time, so just let me know when you bring any.
Is Roy the next lucky villager?
The only one still left in the area is Roy's house.
You know Roy?
I certainly knew him, since we lived in the same village. Hya Hya!
What kind of person was Roy?
He was a good-looking, kind friend. A bit lacking in terms of brawn.
And... Hmm...
Thinking back, I guess I didn't get to talk to Roy much. Hya Hya!
If you’re curious, ask around.
Oh, you can first give me what you already have.
I'll take some on my way.
Great, then this should do the trick, I guess?
Sweet wine, bitter wine, fragrant wine...
There are so many kinds of wine.
This is why wine aficionados get wasted everyday.
But will Arden's restaurant have so many ingredients in stock?
Arden only sells meat dishes.
Maybe he's got a secret menu.
Doesn't look like it.
Let me see... A sweet wine... That would be [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1].
The bitter wine would be [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "PlopRadish_Name"))][/em1] and the fragrant wine would be [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "SilverStarFlower_Name"))][/em1].
Go on, take more. Take [em1]3 each[/em1] of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))], [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "PlopRadish_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "SilverStarFlower_Name"))].
Kyla, what's this poster for?
You aren't a witch, so why are you brewing potions?
What? Oh, you mean the potions.
Hahaha, don't worry. I'm just an ordinary blacksmith.
So what's all this about a Potion of Courage?
Oh my goodness, you're really quite green, Ms. Witch.
Haven't you heard of the potion that fills anyone who drinks it with courage?
No I haven't...
Hold on, Sally said something along those lines to me too...
Could it be moonshine!?
Hahaha! We're not at school, Ms. Witch. Relax.
So we don't have to make wine in secret~
It isn't moonshine, it's just the name of a wine that contains a special ingredient.
What? Why would you call it a potion then, that's so confusing.
It wouldn't be good to put up a notice about wine on a bulletin Rubrum can read from, right?
But what about me knowing it?
There's no reason for me to hide it from you, Ms. Witch! Hahaha!
So what's the special ingredient that gives the wine its name?
Oh, don't be too shocked, but it's [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))][/em1].
You should know how loud the shrieks of a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))] can be, Ellie.
But if you put [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))] in distilled spirits, it actually begins to sing.
And the flavor is unimaginable. How should I put it? You start getting really excited,
then filled with confidence like you can take on anything in the world!
That's why I call it the Potion of Courage, hahaha!
That's the first time I've heard of it...
I used to think it was some kind of code...
Don't be like that, aren't you curious, Ellie?
Like you said, this name shouldn't be given to just any stuff.
Hm, alright. Feels like it will be an interesting story to tell my friends.
Wonderful, excellent. I'll get the distilled spirits ready. You get [em1]2x [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))][/em1], please.
Would you like to pass [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))][/em1] to Kyla?
Kyla, here are two [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))]s.
Oh, thank you! I knew I could depend on you, Ms. Witch.
I've tried to do it on my own a couple times, but I couldn't manage.
I thought I was going to go deaf, hahaha!
I'm just more surprised you did it knowing what would happen...
Are the distilled spirits ready?
Of course, I've also gotten the special item ready.
Oh, does it need other items?
Of course. Now we have all we need. Let's get started.
Come back when you've got [em1]3 slots[/em1].
I'll leave procuring the [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "LittleMandrake_Name"))]s[/em1] to you.
You're going to see what the Potion of Courage is for yourself, hahaha!
Witch's House?
Have you ever repaired one before?
Witch's Houses are normally repaired by witch craftsmen.
I have only repaired simple tools there.
Wow, that’s great too.
You're too nice to me.
Have you talked to a witch craftsmen?
For some reason, I can't go there...
Is that so? Hmm...
Alright, I'll help you since I owe you one.
I'm not sure if I can but I'll do my best.
I don't need payment, but there are materials I can't get. So you have to get them for me.
I'll list them on a note.
Once you bring me the materials, I'll get started on the repairs.
Good, it looks like a new house.
You like it?
Oh, yes! Thank you, Kyla!
Haha, don't mention it. You helped me a lot, too.
If you need more furniture, come look for me.
I'm considering whether I should start selling furniture again.
You can make furniture too?
Sure, the pieces I make are really sturdy and lasting.
[em1]Aurea[/em1] and [em1]Roy[/em1] are also preparing to sell related goods. Go have a look if you're interested.
Feel free to talk to me if there's anything else you need.
Though this comes a little late, here's a housewarming gift.
I've put the stuff that was in the warehouse into the [em1]mailbox[/em1]. Make sure to check it out.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "DisplayItem"))]? That's asking for a lot.
I just can't make cute little things like that! My hands are far too big for that! Haha!
But I can make dressers or picture frames for you if you ever need one! Just let me know.
Here's a gift. Do take it.
It's a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "DisplayTable"))]. Someone commissioned it but didn't pick it up. I'm sure it'll be in good hands.
If you need a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "DisplayTable"))], take a look at the shop.
The other villagers are excellent with their craft, too.
Feel free to browse their wares. There are lots of quality things. Haha.
Hahaha. You're quite busy, aren't you?
Plenty of food here that looks great.
They don't have to be paired with wine. They'd taste great on their own.
So you've been asking around about the things you want to eat?
Not at all, I've been making inquiries seriously.
Now I'll tell Kyla. Then the winetasting party can start right away.
Arden asked me to bring them when [em1]Kyla is working[/em1].
Will you help me ask whether [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))] will be sold again?
Oh, Ellie.
Perfect timing. This is for you.
Hm? Why [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))]?
Hahaha, have you forgotten? I promised to treat you.
So I bought a few extras when I went to Arden's restaurant.
But hear me out, Ellie.
The [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))] Arden used to produce was superb.
It was unrivalled, but he insisted he would never make it again.
If only I could enjoy a glass of it after a long hard day of hammering!
Why has he stopped making it?
Oh yes, that's right. I'll savor it.
He said no matter how he tried, he couldn't reproduce the same flavor, so he told me not to get my hopes up.
Right? Although he sells other kinds of liquor, they're nowhere near as good as [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))].
I encouraged him to keep making it when I went to buy [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))].
So I've been trying to persuade him, but he just won't listen.
Is this wine really so good?
That's a given, it tastes marvelous!
Ah... Just thinking about it is making me crave it.
The thought of wine makes my arms run too weak to hammer.
Everyone who loves to drink seems to think the same way.
That's because they've all fallen under the spell of drink.
Hahaha, it's not as bad as you think.
Oh, it's still not working.
Ellie, if you ever visit Arden's restaurant...
I'll be sure to ask for you.
We'd be in a hole if you went on strike because you weren't getting enough wine.
Hahaha, atta girl, Ellie! I knew I could count on you.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "RequestDecline"))]
It's too bad, I would have left it to you if there were a chance.
That wine is really good stuff.
It's a pity you can't drink with me, Ellie.
If Arden ever says he's going to make it, you've got to tell me right away.
Do you wish to invite Kyla to the winetasting party?
Kyla! I talked over things with Arden.
Oh, is Arden finally going to sell me some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))]?
He's decided to make something even better than [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))].
What? But what I want to drink is that...
Oh come on, you could at least give it a try.
We've got snacks with the drinks! It's a tasting party like no other! Now's your chance!
Hahaha, you're killing me. I get it, I get it.
Though I won't listen to anyone else, I'll listen to a witch like you. I'll go try it out but I won't get my hopes up.
I gathered the ingredients personally and studied the choice of drinking snacks.
Kyla! How's the stage repairing going?
Hey, Ms. Witch! Told you to have some good rest this time.
Haha, you've become an essential part of Wisteria!
But after doing such work every day for so long, it feels awkward to start idling all of a sudden.
You should learn to enjoy your free time.
I can empathize with you.
When I was an apprentice, I did nothing but drinking in my free time. I couldn't think of anything else to do.
Isn't it the same even now?
Oops, so it is! Hahaha!
Isn't there any material you lack?
Sorry to disappoint you, but Roy has promised to get all the materials for me.
And the other villagers have provided funds for the blueprint.
...A-absolutely nothing left for me to do.
Hahaha! We've told you to have a break.
But since you're so bored, Ms. Witch, let me tell you some latest news.
I feel like Rex mentioned that he would bring something special, or maybe I'm just imagining things.
I'm not sure, haha!
So that's how it is... I see. Thank you, Kyla!
I didn't tell you anything, haha!
Give Kyla the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ConstellationRock_Name"))][/em1]?
Kyla... Here you are. It's Constellation Ore.
Hahaha, Rex gave me some too just now.
I'll start repairing tomorrow. It'll probably take one day.
I will use this ore. Thank you guys for getting it.
We really deserve some thanks, but does this ore really contain mysterious power?
Haha, whether to believe it is up to you.
The first man to discover this ore was a wine merchant. He lived 200 years and made a huge fortune.
Then he went to heaven and became a constellation, but he is still looking for this ore up there.
It's the first time I've heard of this story...
Blacksmiths tend to be interested in ores.
Anyway, it's a good thing. And it has motivated me a lot, hahaha!
Ellie, you've brought me good materials. I'd like your input too, haha!
Go get the Constellation Ore.
Hi, Kyla!
How's the stage repairment going?
You've come at the right time. I finished it just now.
Now it's time for Roy to decorate it, but he seems to be in two minds.
I told him that since we'd decided to build a stage, we should build an elegant and stunning one,
but Roy thought it didn't match the style of the village.
I was like, "Since we are not decorating a weapon, it's outside my field of expertise. Maybe you're right."
Go have a look if you're curious.
To celebrate the completion of such a good stage, I plan to have a drink, haha!
Haha, I've been waiting for you!
I was so surprised when Rubrum told me about the parade.
I'll show you guys the rhythm skills I learned with wine glasses.
After Kyla, it's [em1]Roy[/em1]'s turn, Ellie!
Hey, Ellie. I knew you'd come.
Oh? How did you know?
I saw the area across the bridge cleaned up, and you were asking the villagers about the people who used to live there.
Obviously, it's time for me, the carpenter-slash-blacksmith, to step in.
Exactly, I have a job for you.
Haha, I'm always ready.
I'll get the tools ready. I'll leave the materials to you, Ms. Witch.
Great! I'll go find the blueprints first.
I'm impressed, Ms. Witch. You're so decisive.
Blueprints, huh? I should ask [em1]Aurea[/em1].
Are you here to deliver the repair materials?
You’ve gathered everything already? That was fast.
You mean the sickly painter?
That guy hardly ever leaves the house, and I've never spoken to him. So, I don't really know him.
Ah, I know that old man.
He's better than me at making small and delicate things.
He made a lot of amazing machines, like boxes that can play music and stuff like that.
And he always wears gloves no matter what he's doing. Quite eccentric.
Because I hardly ever go to the library. He seems like a nice guy though.
The house really looks amazing.
It feels like I’m back home.
Though I haven't even lived here for long.
As long as you like it here, you can think of this place as your home village.
Haha, I'll do that if I'm born again.
Also, check out the second floor terrace. I used the design you chose.
After all, the rectangular door looks more stable.
After all, I think the overall harmony of the arched door is better.
The triangular door feels like an entrance to a secret base. Interesting.
It’s a little... dramatic, but I like it because it’s cute.
I'm glad you like it.
It's because you chose well. Thanks.
That's because you made it well.
Let me know if you need any help. I’ll be glad to help.
Oh, I just remembered that I forgot your shovel, what happened to it?
Rubrum brought it.
He said he forgot while building a sand castle.
Oh, that’s a relief.
Thank you for your concern in many ways.
There was an extra shovel in the luggage.
It's a pity that I have to send you back empty-handed though.
Oh, don't worry. It's something that I also wanted to do.
Hmm. What should I do?... Oh yeah, have you been to Arden's restaurant?
Arden's meat dumplings with a drink are awesome.
Uh... I can't drink yet.
Oh, you said you look just like your age.
I need to clean up my house and equipment for a few days. Could you come back in a day or two?
I'll treat you to a pot of dumplings or something at least.
A pot... How generous.
Alvin? Hmm, I'm not quite sure.
Is there anything strange about him?
Strange? Haha! Everyone is unique in their own way!
Alvin's [em1]craftsmanship[/em1] seems quite good.
But I haven't seen him using his skills to help [em1]other people[/em1].
Help other people?
Yeah. I've never seen him make, sell, or repair anything for others.
I've no idea where he got most of the items in his sundries store.
Weird, right? Normally, a skilled craftsman would want to showcase their skills and help others.
How to show your eagerness to a deity?
Why such a philosophical question all of a sudden?
Kyla, you said that you went to the temple a lot, right?
Well... I don't go to the temple to offer prayers, though. I'm just a fan of the tasty wine there.
Speaking of which... How about offering the Gods wine?
Haha, I'm just kidding!
But it's not entirely a joke.
Isn't the temple a place for [em1]rituals[/em1]? And wine is usually an essential item during rituals.
But food offered during a ritual varies from village to village, or from region to region.
You'd better ask [em1]someone who has held a ritual[/em1] as to what was offered here.
One house repaired,
two to go.
Ms. Witch, you really should take some rest!
But Kyla, you said that wine is best enjoyed after a hard day's work.
Haha, you're right about that. Looking at the repaired houses, I feel really proud of myself.
My tools are ready.
Of course. I'll go prepare the blueprints and materials.
I'm impressed, Ms. Witch.
It's too dim now. I can't work.
Come again during daytime.
Ta-da! I prepared this specially for you, Ellie.
I borrowed it from Enite, haha! It's so fluffy to sit on, isn't it?
Indeed, it's so fluffy and soft.
Alright, let's clink glasses before the liquor gets cold.
To the beautiful temple, peaceful village, and the happiness of Ms. Witch!
Cheers!
Hah~ Delicious!
Yeah~ Delicious!
I brought beef bread to go with the drink. Let's share it.
Well... It's too late to say so, but is this appropriate?
Drinking alcohol in front of god statues.
Why not? Alcohol is used in rituals as well.
And nothing has gone wrong so far. Maybe the Cat Gods like alcohol too, haha!
I don't think they do...
That aside, Kyla, has something slipped your mind?
Huh? Liquor, snacks, a friend...
Haha! Don't give me that look. I didn't forget.
Interesting stories, isn't it?
Let's see... It was a long time ago. Ah, don't tell Enite, okay?
Enite used to come to the temple regularly to worship.
There was one time when she mixed up the containers and brought liquor instead of tea.
She was like, "The tea for the ritual got a new taste. How mysterious."
Back then, I usually accompanied Enite here.
After the ritual, we drank the supposed tea... and I found that it was liquor.
But Enite was already drunk when I realized.
Enite can't tolerate alcohol?
I suppose so, haha! She clung to me, and said,
"Oh my... The Cat Gods have grown so much... I need to bring more tea from now on."
"But... is it just me or have your colors blended?"
She just kept babbling, hahaha!
Hahaha, and then?
I was younger and naughty, so I wanted to mess with her.
<wave>Touched by your piety, we've merged into one.</wave>
<wave>However, we're embarrassed to let you see us in this form. Please head home posthaste.</wave>
Hadly had I finished when Enite dashed off.
I had to follow her with our stuff and Rubrum.
Enite doesn't remember it at all, hahaha!
Haha, I can hardly picture that.
Right? Not from her current village chief demeanor.
Are there any stories about other villagers?
Hmm... other villagers?
Who do you want to learn about?
Enite is the person I've met the most in the temple.
Do you know that Enite is actually quite talkative?
The fountain and the temple can be called the gossip hubs of the village!
Gossip hubs?
I invented this term, hahaha!
Rubrum used to be so tiny, you know?
He's still a little guy, but there was a time when his head was only as big as my hammer's.
There were several times where I carried him in my arms when Enite was praying.
He was comfortable around strangers, and would giggle in my arms. It was so adorable.
I often thought of Rubrum even when I was away from the village.
I never saw Arden here at the temple.
According to Enite, he came once when the temple was covered in prickly vines.
Would the prideful Arden also seek gods' help? I don't think so, haha.
There were a couple of times when I forced him to come with me. He rattled on even when drinking.
"I'll get mad if this goes on!" Hahaha!
Come to think of it, I've never met Roy here.
I believe he comes as often as Enite does, though. Hahaha!
Oh, by the way, didn't some yellow flowers appear here all of a sudden?
Roy may be glad to hear this.
No one else
Satisfied now, Ms. Witch?
Hmm... alright. Let's come here and drink again when you've come of age, Ellie.
Hahaha, I wouldn't usually say something so cringe...
Ellie, thanks to you, I can see this beautiful view again.
It's because you restored the temple, Kyla.
Right. And I only managed to return because you came to this village, Ms. Witch.
Hahaha, this very moment is the best snack to savor today.
<wave>People get drunk with not alcohol but their own emotions...</wave>
Oof, I finished a whole bottle before noticing.
Let's come again sometime, hahaha.
By the way, won't the cushions get wet if you just lay them on the ground?
Ah, don't worry. Enite has knee pain, so she specially made these to use at the temple.
She said it is a water-resistant fabric that dries fast.
Enite would share the tea with me after the ritual ended, which tasted nice.
Rubrum was very young back then, so I would carry him here for Enite.
I was standing at a distance, so I wouldn't find out...
Enite just thought the tea's taste changed after the ritual. She didn't suspect it.
Because Enite frequents this place the most!
Oh! So the geezer is doing well?
I've never communicated with him via letters, so it can't be me, but I can have a look.
Hmm, we may have talked about the sound made by quality wood, or which log has the best grain for furniture.
But I don't recall discussing canes with him.
For tools like this, you'd better ask [em1]someone who actually uses one[/em1].
Painting is not my thing. I don't think it's me.
Packaging? I know nothing about it. For me it's just extra trouble, hahaha.
Well, the ladder isn't hard to repair, but there's a problem.
As you may know, a ladder must be placed on solid ground.
But the top of the cliff can be unstable. It's too dangerous.
You need something to support you as you [em1]climb up and install[/em1] the ladder.
I don't think metal or wood will work... It'd better be a [em1]plant[/em1].
I'm sorry I couldn't help. Hahaha.
Oh, this is the stone. Well done, Ms. Witch.
It's the wrong one. Give me another stone.
Give me the smaller stones first.
Good. Ms. Witch, you nailed it.
This will be the base...
Kyla, this is it. It was already broken when I found it.
Hahaha. It broke in quite a subtle way.
So, Kyla, do you know how to use it?
Hmm. Rubrum explained it to me on the way.
But I'll need to try it out myself to figure it out.
The one on the floor looks pretty simple. I think I can fix it.
Wow! Really?
The design is straightforward. Just need to hammer in a few nails, haha.
But... the one that looks like a fishing rod is a bit tricky.
Huh? I thought it looked simpler, like it'd be easy to fix.
Well, I've never made a fishing rod before. Hahaha.
I'm a pro when it comes to metal and woodwork, but this is a different field.
I can give it a shot, but I'm no expert, so who knows what it'll turn out like. Hahaha.
Really? That's too bad.
*whine*
Ah! Since it's a fishing rod, maybe we can ask [em1]Freddie.[/em1]
Freddie?
Oh, Freddie?
That's a good idea! From what I know, Freddie makes fishing rods himself.
Right? He even gave me an extra one last time.
So, handing it over to Freddie seems like the right call.
Okay. I'll stay here with my assistant Rubrum to handle the other broken items.
Assistant? Kyla, am I your assistant?
Yep, Rubrum. There's a lot to do. Think you can handle it?
Mm! I'll give it a try!
Ellie, leave this to me and Kyla!
Alright! I'll go find Freddie.
Kyla! Are you planning to make more [em1]cat items[/em1]?
Oh, yeah, that's right.
Remember when I fixed the scratching post last time?
Of course, I even saw some cats playing on it.
Yep, I saw them too when I passed by.
That got me thinking.
Maybe I should make a [em1]Cat Cushion[/em1]! Sounds like a good idea, right?
Oh yeah, now I'm excited for it!
I've got the general idea of how to make it, but I still need some materials.
Ellie, could you help me gather 6 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Mongsiri_Collect_Name"))][/em1]?
Is that all I need to get?
Actually, 5 would be enough, but... just to be safe. Hehe.
Alright. I'm looking forward to seeing the Cat Cushion. I'll go gather the materials.
I think every cat has its own personality and preferences.
Yeah, some cats love to run around, while others just sleep all day.
Exactly! So I thought, maybe I should make something for the cats who like to rest.
Give [em1]6 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Mongsiri_Collect_Name"))][/em1] to Kyla?
Kyla! can we make the [em1]Cat Cushion[/em1] now?
Oh, just in time, Ellie.
I've already talked to Enite, and we decided where to put the cushion.
Wow, what did she say?
We discussed a few places, and finally decided on the [em1]left side of the village fountain[/em1].
Haha, I knew you'd be happy.
It should be quick to make. I'll probably finish it tomorrow.
That's fast!
Hahaha. Once I'm done, I'll take it over. And if you're passing by, you can come check on the progress too.
Oh, and here's a little something as a thank you for helping me with my hobby.
Aww! Thank you.
I might come up with more ideas at any time, so I'll need your help again soon.
Alright, Kyla. I'll be on my way now.
Ellie, about the [em1]Cat Cushion[/em1].
I heard that the cats won't move once they settle in.
After this one's done, let's go check and see if it's true.
Okay, Kyla. I'll go collect [em1]6 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Mongsiri_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
I'll start working on it right away.
(GetGlobalVariable("$615") == true)
Oh, a letter from Kyla!
Probably a reminder about making the Cat Cushion.
Just like the letter said, the cushion's all set up.
It looks so cozy, doesn't it?
Do you ever not think things look great?
(GetGlobalVariable("$616") == false)
This must be the Cat Cushion, right?
Seems like it. Kyla did mention putting it by the fountain.
I can't wait to see the cats lounging on it.
You're not planning to sit by the fountain all day just to catch a glimpse, are you?
Guessing it's to say the Dangling Cat Toy is ready now.
Just like the letter said, the Dangling Cat Toy's been placed.
Just seeing it there makes me so happy!
Too bad, Ellie. If only you were a cat, you'd get the full experience.
This must be the Dangling Cat Toy, right?
Looks like it. Kyla did say she'd put it by the bridge.
I bet the cats will love it!
It seems that the Cat Exercise Wheel's completed.
Just like the letter said, the Cat Exercise Wheel's set up.
It looks like so much fun, doesn't it?
Don't tell me you're planning to hop on and take it for a spin.
This is the Cat Exercise Wheel, right?
Yep. Kyla mentioned it would be placed along the path to the library.
Watching the cats play on this could make the whole day fly by.
Do you really think they'd run on it ALL day?
Yo, Ellie, are we ready to build the bridge?
The construction takes time. If you have any other task at hand, you can finish it first.
What do you say? Shall we summon the villagers?
Let's get going!
The villagers would prefer to work [em1]during the day[/em1].
Hahaha, your curiosity has kicked in again.
Coloring furniture isn't hard, but there's one step you shouldn't forget.
You must remove the old paint before you can apply any new color.
As long as you do that, the task is half done.
Aha! I thought I could put on the new paint directly.
No. Color changing is actually more complicated and demanding than you'd expect.
I, for one, prefer to make a new piece instead of customizing an old one.
Ellie, when we are at it, shall I teach you how to make furniture?
Well... I need to fulfill Aurea's request first.
Hahaha. A gift for me?
A [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] for me?
Thank you so much, Ms. Apprentice Witch.
I didn't expect to receive a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1] from you.
Anyway, thanks!
Ellie, I appreciate it, but...
I'm afraid I'm not a big fan of [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
You may give that one to someone who needs it more, okay? Hahaha.
Oh my, Ellie! When did you prepare this?
I'm already deeply in debt to you, y'know?
Thanks a million!!
Hehe, Ellie really is sincere about everything, huh?
How did you know what I like again?
Thank you so much for the gift!
Wow, this is exactly what I needed!
You're really giving this as a gift, right?
I'll use it well, Ellie. Thank you!
Hahaha, you've already given me a gift today.
Ha ha! I’m good for now!
Oh, hi there.
It suddenly occurred to me that I'd never given you any gift, Hahaha!
Hi, Ellie. We've been meeting a lot lately.
Life at Wisteria may be slow-paced, but it's more meaningful.
Without so much work, I now have more time for what I really want to do.
And I owe it all to you, Ellie. Here's something for you.
It's kind of embarrassing, Hahaha!
Oh, hello Ellie. I happen to be looking for you.
Hmm, well... What was it, urr...
I had a cool line ready, but it has slipped my mind. Hahaha!
To be honest, I wasn't so sure about whether I should come back to Wisteria.
But I made up my mind after reading your letter, Ellie. Thank you.
It’s a good one. There will be plenty of places to use it.
But don't hesitate to use it. The more you use it, the happier I am. Hahaha!
So, I’ve prepared it. Here, take this.
Ellie, it's something I've always been thinking about.
Aren't you being too nice to me? Hehe.
Now that I think about it, you remember my preferences perfectly.
I think I've realized just how much you care about me.
And gifts, they only have meaning when given and received, right?
I’ve also prepared a gift for you, Ellie <wave>just saying~</wave>
I hope you like it. Hehe.
And if you ever need anything in the future, just let me know! We're close, after all. Hehe!
Witches do have amazing powers. To think that you can make puppets that move exactly the same way as I do!
Indeed. I didn't know it could be used in such a way until I heard it from the witch that gave it to me.
Hahaha. I've been hoping to introduce you to the fun of furniture making, Ellie.
What should I do? Make some furniture right in front of the marionette?
There's no need. Just hold the marionette while imagining the technique you want to teach me.
Really? That sounds like a very convenient way to learn things. I want a marionette like this too.
I'm sorry... but marionettes run on magic. Only witches can operate them.
That's a pity.
Come on, all that a marionette does is imitating. You don't need it since you're a great craftsman already.
Am I? I guess you're right. Hahaha.
That's it? I'm not feeling anything though.
I think it's done. Thank you. I'll make some fine furniture. I promise.
I forgot to bring the [em1][lua(GetItemName("CopycatMarionette"))][/em1].
Go ahead and make something amazing!
The spirit of the craftsman?
Huh? I don't see Theo anywhere.
That's weird. He said he'd go wait at my house.
You don't think he got impatient and ran off, do you?
Should we go outside and look for him?
Maybe we should.
...Hehe...
Hey, I just heard a [em1]sound[/em1] from...
Should I give Kyla 2 [lua(GetItemName("Nail_Collect"))] and 2 [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))]?
Kyla! Is this enough?
Ellie, thanks for your hard work!
To make what Theo wants, it'll take me [em1]until tomorrow[/em1].
Okay, I'll come back tomorrow!
I haven't gathered everything yet.
Ellie, hi there!
Check it out, the sofa's all done.
Wow, it looks super comfy!
Really? Great. I hope Theo likes it.
I'll go find Theo!
Thanks, I appreciate it.
Kyla said the [em1]sofa would be ready tomorrow[/em1].
I should come see Kyla tomorrow.
Ellie, you're a bit late! I was waiting for you.
Well, now that you're here, shall we get going?
Well, I'm not entirely sure myself.
Theo came running up, saying he had something to tell us. He said he'd tell us when you got here.
But, he got tired of waiting and said he'd go to my house first.
Really? You don't think he's planning some kind of prank, do you?
Heh, your guess is as good as mine. Let's just go and see.
<shake>Ahhh!</shake>
<shake>Whoa there!</shake> What's going on?
Teehee, hahaha! You should see your faces!
Lisa?
Hmm... Well, Lisa hates mushrooms.
You told me that last time.
Ah, did you ask me about her before?
Did I tell you the bread story, too?
Yes. That she hates sweet bread, and that she sleeps on her back.
Looks like I've told you almost everything.
Isn't there anything else? Even little stories are fine.
You're really interested in Lisa, aren't you?
I'm just curious about what she's like.
Heh, now that you mention it, Lisa had a pretty quirky side.
A quirky side?
She'd leave her stuff all over the surrounding forest and the whole village.
There wasn't a bench in town that didn't have a Lisa's book on it.
She said she just left them where it was convenient to read, but I think she just forgot half of them.
She's a weird one, right? Hah!
She really is.
Ah, there's more. When she drank, she'd often talk about her daughter.
Is her name Dosca, by any chance?
Oh, right! How did you know?
She's cute, she's kind, she's capable... She'd do nothing but brag about her all day.
She said something else, too.
She said that whenever it happened, if she ever had a grandchild, she wanted them to have her name.
She'd try her best to stay alive to see that day.
She wasn't usually the type to say stuff like that, so it stuck with me.
It makes me want to try harder, too.
Why all of a sudden? You got a daughter?
It's nothing. Thanks for telling me.
Don't mention it! Haha!
Ellie, can I ask you a favor?
Could you get me 3 [em1][lua(GetItemName("Branch_Special"))][/em1]?
I need to make a tool in a hurry, and I'm short on materials.
Could you get me 3 [em1][lua(GetItemName("Rock_Special"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 3 [em1][lua(GetItemName("Mud_Special"))][/em1]?
I'll make it worth your while. Thanks! Hehe.
Can you get them by the end of [em1]today[/em1]?
Just bring me 3 [lua(GetItemName("Branch_Special"))].
Give [em1]3 [lua(GetItemName("Branch_Special"))][/em1] to Kyla?
Kyla. I brought the things you asked for.
That was fast! Thanks, Ellie.
Here, as promised. Thanks for the help.
Just bring me 3 [lua(GetItemName("Rock_Special"))].
Give [em1]3 [lua(GetItemName("Rock_Special"))][/em1] to Kyla?
Just bring me 3 [lua(GetItemName("Mud_Special"))].
Give [em1]3 [lua(GetItemName("Mud_Special"))][/em1] to Kyla?
You know, I don't think I've ever gotten a request for something used in a witches' graduation ceremony.
I heard they don't use things you can normally get your hands on.
Yeah, that’s right. As far as I know, they use a few [em1]items ordinary humans can’t make[/em1].
That's a shame.
If it were something I could make for you like usual, I'd help in a heartbeat.
So the whole bakery family isn’t coming back? Only the two daughters are?
I used to buy and eat the donuts they sold there quite often.
They also sold a few donuts that weren’t too sweet but still tasted really good.
I’m looking forward to it, aren’t you?
So now the daughters are taking over the bakery and running the business.
Hey, Ellie. You're starting again this time, right?
That’s right. It’s the beginning once again.
I mean the move-in of the new residents.
This time too, we really need Kyla.
Alright, then shall we get started right away?
Let’s do it the same way as last time. You prepare the blueprints and the materials, and—
I’ll take care of the tools. And I’ll loosen up my body too. Haha.
Alright. I’ll go get the materials we need right away!
I hope the new resident moves in soon.
Right? The day when the village returns to how it used to be isn’t far off, so let’s keep going strong.
Which house should we repair next? I’m done warming up, so just say the word.
Alright! I’ll go get the blueprints and materials ready.
Then the two remaining houses won’t be a problem, right?
Of course. My shoulders feel light when I’m hammering away.
I even feel like I want to hurry on to the next house already.
Then shall we pick up the pace a bit?
Working like that will make the taste of the drink even more special.
Haha. Now you really know it well too, Ellie.
Anytime’s fine to start, partner.
Now only the last house is left, right?
Alright. Partner~
Good, good. This time, don’t forget that we need [em1][lua(GetItemName("BlueprintClalaHouse"))][/em1].
Good, good. This time, don’t forget that we need [em1][lua(GetItemName("BlueprintBjornHouse"))][/em1].
Good, good. This time, don’t forget that we need [em1][lua(GetItemName("BlueprintTeoHouse"))][/em1].
Once this repair is finished, the village will return to how it was before the thorn bushes appeared.
Heheh. It looks like you’re feeling a bit strange, doesn’t it?
Of course! I never even imagined the village would be restored like this.
It’s all thanks to you!
Heheh. Thanks for the compliment.
Then shall we go and restore the village to how it was before the thorn bushes appeared?
Partner?
Kyla, could you have a look at this blueprint?
Hmm? Are you building something? Let's see it.
Oh my, is it Rubrum's artwork? He's a genius, hahaha.
Not Rubrum. It's a blueprint made by Bjorn.
Bjorn? Then that's a different story. I can't see much talent in him, hahaha.
And... is this a castle? And there are cats in it.
Right. He wants to build a castle for the village cats, and this is the blueprint he shows me. Kyla, what do you think?
It's hard to build a structure of such a scale. I don't think there will be enough space even if we demolish both the library and the stage.
I figured as much. And it's not like Bjorn has built a house before.
I see. He's just doing it [em1]on a whim[/em1].
It's good to be ambitious, but he can't afford a failure if his plan is too grand.
So, building such a castle is unrealistic, right?
If you ask me...
A test?
Right, if you want to do something for the cats,
try to first make something they like. That way, you'll know if your plan is realistic.
As the saying goes, success is the sum of small efforts, hahaha.
If you say so, Kyla. I'll talk to Bjorn about it.
I think Bjorn should start with smaller tasks before he challenges something this ambitious.
Hmm... maybe he should consult an expert?
If you throw it too close, I can’t catch it.
Throw it from a bit farther away.
Kyla, have you been to a city?
Yes, I stayed in a city for quite a long time.
Do you know Highlion?
Absolutely. That was the place I was going to originally.
Oh, really? I was in Highlion before I came here.
How was Highlion?
It was easy to get materials, and many people would go there to shop.
There were many people who liked fancy decoration.
Lots of strange people asked me to add flowers, or lion sculptures for decoration, and it was not even in a garden.
It was on a garden shovel.
How were other things? The street... or the food?
Sorry, I wasn’t interested in things like that.
If you were just beating iron, there's no difference between here and there.
Haha, yes Virgil, you're right.
But this place is quieter. That’s why I like it better.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Kyla"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Can I try lifting the hammer?
Yeah, try lifting it.
*Grunt*
I can’t lift this.
You will be able to lift it if you burn your flesh a little more.
Do you get stronger if you burn your flesh?
No, haha.
That's what my master always said. It means you need to put in much effort.
But my hammer seems to be getting lighter these days, so I'm thinking of making a heavier one.
I think it’s heavy enough.
It seems the weight has reduced after using it so often.
Do hammers also get lighter as you use it more and more?
Yeah, that's what my master said.
What kind of person was your master?
He could make a flower by bending steel plate with bare hands.
Wow, I don't know him, but that sounds incredible.
Why do you like drinking, Kyla?
Well, do I need a reason to like it?
I've never really thought too hard about it.
But isn't there usually a reason? Like liking the taste of wine or some kind of memory to do with it.
Hm... well. If you really want to delve into it, I probably picked it up from my father.
Was your father also a blacksmith?
Yes, that's why I was born to the sounds of metalworking.
When I was an apprentice elsewhere, I'd also go have a drink with my friends after we were done for the day.
I guess that's how I got started with drinking.
Besides, it tastes good.
I suppose it's my way of rewarding myself for a hard day of work.
Oh, if that's the case, I think I understand.
I also buy some pumpkin cookies whenever I finish an assignment.
Right? That's how you find some happiness in life.
Kyla, you said you were from a family of blacksmiths?
Why have you become a carpenter then?
Hahaha. The village I grew up in was full of various craftsmen.
It was a village where blacksmiths, carpenters, and potters gathered to craft.
That's why I got to see many other jobs besides what my family does.
What a wonderful village. I want to see it with my own eyes.
Yeah, it would wake up before sunrise, and be filled with all kinds of sounds throughout the day.
There was a carpenter's workshop right beside my family's smithy, so I naturally learned to process wood.
I basically love any work that involves making things by hand. Hahaha.
My father always says that I should concentrate on one trade, though.
Have you considered any other job, then?
Hmm... I don't think so.
My current goal is to forge the best sword. I should focus on that.
Kyla, where were you before you returned to Wisteria?
Before I came back to the village?
I was staying at a Witch's Workshop in this area.
Really? A Witch's Workshop in another village?
Right. I was helping witches there build a giant tower beside the workshop.
I don't know what the tower is for. I passed by and saw them recruiting, so I volunteered. Hahaha.
And I returned to Wisteria before the tower was finished.
Really? Why didn't you finish it?
There wasn't a particular reason, and it had nothing to do with money. I came back because I wanted to.
Assisting your adventure has turned out to be more fun than building a tower. I think I've made the right decision.
Hammer
About wine
Two jobs
Before returning to the village
There should be something special about a tower if it's commissioned by a Witch's Workshop.
All I did was basic work such as laying the foundation and building the frame.
But the witches there seemed to like my work. They wanted me to stay and go on with the construction. Just when I was drinking and thinking about it, however...
I received Enite's letter. Hahaha.
Working for a Witch's Workshop should pay well. What a pity.
Enite wrote about how you removed the prickly vines. It excited me, and I immediately decided to come back.
Master
Kyla, when did you make that hammer you always carry around?
This? My Master made it for me right before I became an adult.
Huh? You didn't make it yourself?
Heh. It's a little embarrassing, but [em1]this hammer[/em1] is way better than anything I could make.
So I just kept using it. It's ridiculously sturdy.
I guess that's why he's the Master.
Yep. His skill is honestly the best I've ever seen. He can drink me under the table, too.
If only he could tame that fiery temper, they'd be perfect. Haha!
You didn't get along well with your master?
Huh? I wouldn't put it this way. My master is my father.
Oh, did I never mention that?
You've talked about your master and your father.
You just never said they were the same person.
Sorry. Guess I skipped over that important detail.
My mother had her hands full because of him.
It's nothing major. My father was just a man who was useless at everything except his work.
He'd sell a ton of expensive items, then mess up the calculations and take a loss.
Can I ask what happened?
One time, he miscalculated so badly that he spent a whole week's grocery money on a new pair of gloves.
I can picture the scene, and I wasn't even there.
My mother chased him around all day with a feather duster. Haha!
Right? That's why I worry about running a shop myself. It's embarrassing, but I think I'm bad at math, just like him.
My books have never balanced once! I'm always thinking, "What am I gonna do about this?!"
But sometimes Enite checks the ledger for me, so I think I'm still breaking even. Haha!
I've got something too. Listen up.
When I first came to Wisteria, I'd been wandering from place to place.
You said you were wandering?
Haha, I was young back then.
Then I fell in love with how quiet the village was, and decided to stay for some time.
But I didn't plan on making this my home.
I look more suited to a bustling place, right? Haha!
Back then, it was because... I was facing a lot of problems.
I just wanted a quiet place to catch my breath.
But then you ended up staying.
Yeah. You know who caused it?
Eh? Arden?
I was starving when I came to the village, but I didn't have a penny on me.
Train tickets were expensive, and I spent all my money on one.
So I walked about the place and stumbled upon a restaurant with open windows.
Some people were sitting together, eating simple food and drinking wine.
I was hungry and tired, so I just stared at them numbly.
I got it! Arden then came out with free food for you, didn't he?
So you were touched and stayed on in the village?
Hahahaha!
Do you think Arden's that kind of person?
Uh... No.
Arden didn't come out. I went in.
Eh? Didn't you say you had no money?
I've got a healthy body, hands and legs, so what's there to worry about! If things went south, I would just have found work. Hehe!
Oh, you.
So I walked in, and ordered food and wine.
The food was undoubtedly good, but that goblet of wine...
Was it [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))]?
Yes! It was [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))]!
A wooden goblet-full of wine, so full that the foam on it was gurgling out.
That coolness and warmth went right to the heart. Sweet as honey but with a hint of bitterness.
Was this wine really so good?
It was marvelous...
So marvelous that it made me cry...
Anyway, the wine was really too good, and it brought me to my senses.
So I stood up, went to Arden and said,
"I'm sorry! I haven't got any money! I only did it because I was too hungry! Let me work for you!"
I got it this time! Did he say you didn't have to pay?
Hahaha!
True... He's Arden after all... So what happened next?
He asked if I was a blacksmith. I said, yes. He gave me a silver goblet and said...
"Engrave this with something beautiful."
So he did put you to work. Doesn't surprise me at all, though.
Yeah, that's how it was.
To fulfill his request, I put up a temporary blacksmith's stall and even built a small house.
Because that kind of fine craftsmanship can't be completed in a trice.
Oh, then...
Haha! That's right, so I ended up staying here.
I worked for the other villagers and finished the engraving with the rest of the time. Then I returned the goblet to Arden.
He poured some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))] into it and handed it to me, saying, "This is your dedicated goblet now. Remember to drop by frequently."
So I stayed.
This is the goblet I was talking about.
Wow, it's really pretty.
But are you sure you want to give such a pretty goblet to me?
Yes, you can have it.
Even without this goblet, Arden's still going to give me my wine. Haha!
I think it will make an extremely tough brick.
I'll keep the goblet safe for you.
Alright now, come back when you've got all the other materials.
Okay, then let's try to make some bricks.
Oh, if you want to fire some tough and useable bricks, you'll need about a day. So you should come by tomorrow.
It was only sometime later I learnt this was a wine called [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "FlameDrink"))].
Let me know when you've gathered all the materials we need.
Like the aroma of bread fresh from the oven, but also like the perfume of a flower...
Haha, finally! The last of the three houses.
It feels quite surreal. I never expected to return to the village like this.
And now, I've repaired several houses.
Having you around is great!
Haha, you're too kind! It's all thanks to you, Ellie.
Now you're practically my partner, Ellie.
Wow, it's my first time being a blacksmith's partner!
Haha, and it's my first time having a witch as a partner!
My tools are "hot" and ready.
I'll be back with the materials before your hammer cools down.
Okay, remember that we need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BlueprintVinchHouse_Name"))][/em1] this time.
Okay, remember that we need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BlueprintAlvinHouse_Name"))][/em1] this time.
Okay, remember that we need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BlueprintArinHouse_Name"))][/em1] this time.
Emm, the way to make a wood plank float.
Usually, you erect enduring pillars beneath the bridge deck to support it.
But I don't have that much strength.
Haha, it requires both strength and skills, so it can be hard for you, Ellie.
I even attached a windsock to it, but it won't work.
Why don't you make the windsock [em1]larger[/em1] then?
After all, everything becomes stronger when it [em1]increases in size[/em1], hahah!
Kyla, I heard that you were looking for someone to accompany you to the temple. Why?
I stated it in the poster that the person should accompany me to the temple first.
C'mon, just tell me...
Haha, just no. Sometimes I need a drinking buddy.
What the heck. All you talk about is drinking.
It's not like I can drink.
It's okay. I just need someone to clink glasses with me.
The temple has the best liquor in the village.
And if you have a friend to chat with when you drink,
even water would taste like wine.
What do you say, Ellie? Get your favorite drink and come with me.
You're coming, right?
Will you tell me some interesting stories then?
Leave it to me. Ellie, you just need to prepare your own drink.
We'll go in the [em1]evening[/em1].
Why evening?
'Cause the temple has a unique vibe in the evening.
Now, see you later, haha!
Hmm, what should I take...
Something to drink in a place of a unique vibe...
<rainb>[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice_Silver_Name"))]</rainb>, of course.
You enjoy the taste of that junk so badly?
The charm of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice_Silver_Name"))]'s taste lies within [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice_Silver_Name"))] and nothing else.
It's just like bread sold at the canteen of School for Witches.
Okay, I'll take [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice_Silver_Name"))].
[em1]I'll prepare [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StarJuice_Silver_Name"))][/em1] and come back in the [em1]evening[/em1].
Go to the temple with Kyla?
Kyla! I've come with my drink!
Oh, good. Let's go.
What are the interesting stories you're going to tell me at the temple?
Kyla! What kind of [em1]cat item[/em1] are you planning to make this time?
Haha, Ellie, you got here fast!
Have you noticed the [em1]cats[/em1] roaming around the village?
Yep! They're always running around, looking so lively.
Right? But there are some that like to just sit and watch.
I even saw one cat wagging its paw, trying to shoo away a butterfly!
Haha, maybe it was woken up and got annoyed.
Maybe, but it looked pretty happy.
So, I thought of a new idea.
How about a [em1]Dangling Cat Toy[/em1]?
A dangling toy? Sounds fun!
What can I help with this time?
I've got the design ready. Ellie, all I need are some materials.
Could you help me gather [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Bellody_Collect_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Moondelion_Collect_Name"))][/em1]?
Just from the materials, I can't quite picture how it'll turn out.
Haha, well, you'll just have to wait and see!
Alright, I'll go collect the materials right away!
Eager as ever, aren't you? That's great!
Give Kyla the [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Bellody_Collect_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Moondelion_Collect_Name"))][/em1]?
Kyla! Are these enough to make the [em1]Dangling Cat Toy[/em1]?
Yep, the materials you brought are in perfect shape.
Great, now I can get started.
I've already talked to Enite, and we decided where to place the toy.
You know the bridge beyond the fountain? We'll put it at [em1]the crossroads underneath[/em1].
Wow! That's a great spot.
Haha, right? I bet the cats will love it too!
It should be done by tomorrow. I'll put it out once it's ready.
You work so fast, Kyla!
Haha, feel free to stop by and check the progress if you're around, Ellie.
Oh, and here's a little thank-you gift, like last time.
Thanks a bunch.
I'm already brainstorming some new ideas. I'll need your help next time too.
Ellie, about the [em1]Dangling Cat Toy[/em1].
I heard that once the cats get used to it, they just can't stop playing with it.
Alright, Kyla. I'll gather [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Bellody_Collect_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Moondelion_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
Ellie, thank you for coming right away.
This time, I'm thinking of making something a bit more active.
I got the idea after watching the cats running and jumping around the village.
Did those cats inspire you? What is it?
Yes! I want to make something that lets cats run freely and safely.
A [em1]Cat Exercise Wheel[/em1]! Sounds cool, doesn't it?
What do you need me to do? Gather materials as usual?
Haha, I knew you'd be up for it. I'm counting on you again.
I'll need [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowRock_Special_Name"))][/em1].
Is that all you need?
Haha, yep! I've got the rest of the materials ready.
Alright then, I'll go gather everything as quickly as I can.
Give Kyla the [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowRock_Special_Name"))][/em1]?
Kyla, are these enough to make the [em1]Cat Exercise Wheel[/em1]?
Haha, you're the best, Ellie!
I'll get started right away.
By the way, aren't you curious where we'll place the Cat Exercise Wheel?
Where did you decide to put it this time?
This time, we chose the [em1]path leading to the library[/em1].
Wow! That's a great spot!
Haha, I knew you'd like it, Ellie.
It should be finished by tomorrow.
I'll definitely come by tomorrow to check it out!
Haha, once it's set up, you're welcome to swing by anytime!
And here's a little thank-you gift for all your help.
I'm always happy to help out.
Ellie, about the [em1]Cat Exercise Wheel[/em1].
I heard that once the cats get used to it, they just run around non-stop on it.
We should definitely go see how much fun they're having.
Alright, Kyla. I'll gather [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RainbowRock_Special_Name"))][/em1].
Wahaha. It's nice seeing you, Ellie!
Whoa! You scared me. When did you come?
My goodness, that place seems fun too. Maybe I'll go there next time?
Have you had your meal? I have!
You won't have energy for adventures if you don't eat. I'll go even farther next time.
*yawn* Ah... There seems to be a sleep spell on this book...
My goodness... Arin's been staring for hours.
Good timing. Take a seat and I'll pick a song for you.
Try not to get overwhelmed by my performance!
We sometimes bake food from Enite and eat it here.
Oh? Would you like to sit by the fire too? I'm great at making fire.
See you next time!
Witch! It might be sudden, but here's a gift.
Here you go!
What is it? You want something?
I don't understand a word you're saying!
What would you like to discuss with Rex?
To be honest, life in the village is kind of boring, isn't it?
Still, I think this is a lovely place. It has an ideal natural environment!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rex"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Arin and I have known each other since we were little.
We're great buddies, sticking together all the time!
Well... You mean the place with lots of books, right? Arin likes to go there.
Books are food of the mind. You must read more too, Ellie!
The first thing I did after arriving at the village was to explore the Green Forest!
The forest itself is ordinary, but it is inhabited by some interesting guys.
The welcome party was great! This is not a large village, so we can invite everyone, which is so fun!
And everyone is nice, <shake>wahaha!</shake>
I want it to be more dangerous and thrilling.
That said, I like those giant mushrooms.
But those taste horrible. Don't ever try them!
Exploration tools
You mean besides the thingies from Arin? All I need is a pair of binoculars, a compass and some enduring ropes.
Exactly. [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Pompom_Powder_Name"))][/em1] has many uses.
It's light, resilient, and versatile. By the way, this is a piece of intel only an expert like me can provide!
I've never had sleeping issues ever since I became robust.
My only complaint is that I can't take my bed at home with me when I go on an exploration.
My [em1][lua(GetItemName("StarryNight_Bed"))][/em1] is soft and comfy. It's a wonderful bed.
My grandpa used to be a renowned explorer.
I've long dreamed of experiencing everything he told me about when I was little.
So I promised Grandpa that I'd be the best explorer!
Have you arm wrestled with Kyla?
I never lost in contests of physical strength until I met her...
Maybe I should also pick up blacksmithing?
Exploration earnings
Dad handles most of the valuable items I bring back from explorations.
And Arin manages the money I earn.
An explorer doesn't bother himself with bookkeeping!
I'm not picky about food.
An explorer should gulp whatever food they have!
Ah, except for [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Weak_Name"))][/em1]! It will deprive my strength.
StarSea Cave
It's a perfect spot for explorations!
My favorite activity there is to hang a rope from the cave ceiling and swing back and forth on it.
Don't tell Arin though, or she will talk my ear off again.
Dating
I-I've never gone on any date yet!
I may travel around with A-Arin, but those are <wave>adventures.</wave>
That said... do girls all like to roam around with guys?
Bookmarks
I want to make bookmarks out of phoenix feathers, but Arin won't allow me.
She says ordinary humans will burn if they touch a phoenix.
I'm an explorer though! Why buy feathers from shops when I can earn them with skills? I'll catch a phoenix one day!
Arden's restaurant? It doesn't seem like a bad place, but... doesn't the menu feel a bit lacking?
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BeefBread_Name"))][/em1] is delicious, but... it's hard to eat a lot of it.
Of course, it's perfect for carrying around, so I tend to bring it along on my explorations.
During the day, there are many creatures with good eyesight, so there are times when I need to hide my body.
Did you know that just gathering some feathers and covering your face can be effective in those situations?
If it works, I'll show you the method too.
Around here, I've been trying to use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Pompom_Collect_Name"))][/em1] to cover my face.
Food here is tastier than I expected!
And the villagers are all hardworking! I can't be the only idler!
Spit it out, man!
Phew, I can do this by myself. But if you need help, just ask!
What are you doing, witch!
Told you it's Ellie, Ellie Blueriver!
Oh, right. Okay, Ellie! What brings you here!
You said you were an explorer?
Yes! I am Rex the explorer, who will become prominent one day! Remember my name!
You're exploring this place?
Well, a brief casual exploration. Arin needs a research site with few restrictions, after all.
I happened to find some clues. I believe there's something I need here.
Something you need?
Ahem, I just wanted to try that line. Anyway, I need to get back to my business.
A great adventurer will be stopped by no difficulty once he's set a goal! Nor will I!
You are busy with something else too?
Of course! I am always busy!
I'm looking for plants for Arin!
Isn't Arin a librarian? Why would she need plants?
We've been to many places.
Whenever I visit a place, I look for uncommon items and take them to Arin.
Since I don't know when, Arin has been making those items into bookmarks.
"To record our journeys with bookmarks," she says, wahaha!
I don't quite get what's on her mind, but as long as she enjoys it, it's great!
Wow, that sounds unique and cool!
Wahaha, you finally realized that I am cool?
No... I mean Arin...
Yep! Arin indeed is cool!
So, I'm as busy as a bee every day.
What are you looking for this time?
I need to look around to find out!
It'd be great if there are golden mask leaves wet with rain, or
rainbow hydrangea leaves from the Desert Oasis.
Wow, those are all rare plants.
Huh? You know them too? But I would expect no less of a witch!
Sure. Every witch must learn to craft potions, and the first step to potion crafting is knowing plants and ecosystems.
Although someone starts crying once she opens a book.
Can't you stop raining on my parade?
Wahaha, what an interesting hat. It can talk!
Knowing about plant gathering and actually gathering them are completely different.
Let me handle it this time.
But I know the local environment better.
And I've even been to the principal's secret library and the forest where you mustn't close your eyes.
The problem is, the school regulations prohibit visiting those places.
My goodness! You've actually been to those places? They sound so challenging!
So you're actually like each other.
When it comes to finding plants for Arin, I can also do a great job.
It's okay! I've always been doing it by myself!
Are you worried that I may find something more special?
In your dreams. I'm an expert in this field!
I'm far better at it than a witch who locks herself in a dim room every day, crafting potions.
My mother once said that action speaks louder than words.
What! My grandpa says speaking loudly is a manifestation of confidence!
Okay, time for a bet then!
Let's see who can find a plant that satisfies Arin more.
Deal!
Wait. Since it's a bet, we should bet something on it, right?
<shake>That hat.</shake>
I like that hat on your head! Just bet that hat!
You say you like... this?
I feel offended by your wording.
What do you want? Just say it, Ellie!
Well... I want you to tell me what you're looking for.
What...? That's your condition? You're a tougher opponent than I thought.
Hm... Hmmm... Hmmmmm...
Alright! It's a deal. Just keep your words.
Why has it become a bet anyway.
Because you provoked him.
Because he looked so reluctant. I can never resist the temptation of secrets.
Some habit...
Humph. Now, what shall I choose?
Although rare plants can be found at [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))], those don't feel sufficient to guarantee a victory.
To win, I must know myself and my opponent.
And, since it's a gift, I must prioritize its receiver's preferences!
The best way to find out is to ask the person in question.
Let's ask [em1]Arin[/em1] directly.
Humph! She actually fled from our competition!
Just you wait! What I find will leave you slack-jawed!
<shake>Tada!</shake> How is it? You weren't aware of this place, were you?
<shake>You... you're killing me. I thought I was going to die.</shake>
Come on. It's just climbing a few cliffs. What's the big deal.
Hey! How is it not a big deal? Falling off means an instant death!
But you've arrived here in one piece. Besides, some cliffs alone can't intimidate a great adventurer.
Ah, just in case, don't ever try to come here on your own.
The thought of having to take that route back makes me want to cry...
Wahaha! Stop crying and cheer up now!
You see this ore here? It's a Constellation Ore.
No wonder I find it familiar. I've seen this in a document.
Huh? You enjoy reading too?
No way. For me... books are like potions to induce sleep.
I only came across it in documents when trying to figure out the building structure of the School for Witches.
This ore is rare and hard to spot, but it can bring prosperity and good luck.
That's why they are only used for buildings with unusual significance, right?
You know a lot! Exactly, and it's the first time I've seen it since Grandpa showed me one.
This used to be a large deposit, but most had gone when I found it.
Fortunately, enough has left for us to build a stage.
Where has the rest gone?
Who knows? Maybe people who used to live here used it to build their significant buildings?
Now, you've rested enough? Then let's start digging.
This is a pie Enite gave me. Have it when you're hungry from digging.
We need at least [em1]3 pieces[/em1].
Simply digging is boring. Let's see who can mine more!
I need to emphasize this in advance: You must mine a decent amount! Don't let me down!
Oh, you're back? Show me how much you've mined then. For your information, I've mined quite a lot.
Show Rex the Constellation Ore you've mined?
Wahaha, if you're afraid of competing against me, I can wait for a bit longer!
Woah, really? You mined so much by yourself? Don't tell me that the hat helped you with digging.
I can give eloquent speeches with my mouth, but certainly not mine with it.
<wave>Yo!</wave> Ellie! I'm impressed! You are quite capable.
Among the witches I know, you have the most physical strength!
Hehe, how many witches do you know then?
Only you! <shake>WAHAHA!</shake>
Then what's the point...
<shake>WAHAHA!</shake> To celebrate your victory, you can have my treasure.
<shake>*Grunting*</shake>... Adding my ore to your pile... Good, that should be enough. Let's go back.
Oh, you mined as many as I did. That's amazing.
Looks like I should no longer consider you fragile.
You thought I was fragile?
Not anymore! These are all for you, so forgive me!
Just 3 pieces? Well... fine.
You did a good job for a witch.
<wave>Wow!</wave> We're at the village in no time!
<shake>My... my legs...</shake>
Yup! After spending so much time in a cave, the village air feels so refreshing!
Now, let's give the ore to Kyla!
<shake>An all-out race is on!</shake>
I... I never agreed <shake>to participate!</shake>
<shake>Hey, hear me oooout!!!!</shake>
Hmm? <shake>Whaaaa!</shake> What are you doing? Ellie!
Why so scared? As if you were up to something fishy!
What do you mean fishy? I never have anything to hide!
I'm making a special something to be placed on the stage.
How special can it be? I bet it's just some pretty ore at best.
What? Who do you think I am!
I've found [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ConstellationRock_Name"))][/em1]!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ConstellationRock_Name"))]? I think I've seen them somewhere.
You wanna take a look? I can make an exception and take you there.
I've been wishing I had a company.
We need to take some ore back, so remember to [em1]make some room in your bag[/em1] before we set out.
What do you say? Are you going?
Good. The route I take may be a bit dangerous. Keep up even if you're tired!
Huh, no?
You're going to mine Constellation Ore?
Your bag looks so full. Make some room first.
Hey, Ellie! Where are you going? What about the mining?
A resident here? No, I don't know him.
Selling? I'm only responsible for finding it! Because I'm an explorer!
Come visit anytime.
What? You’ve already found Ritoring?
Crafting Recipe Exchange
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))] Exchange
If you have extra crafting recipes, I’ll trade with you.
You need something?
It's been a while. Got more exciting stories to tell?
Canes remind me of a trauma. I don't want to talk about them.
Portraits? You know what kind of torture it is to sit still for hours to have them drawn? It hurts my butt.
Anyone interested in portraits must at least be able to sit still for ages.
They say that a pleasing appearance adds to an item's value.
There was a time when many would hang a card on their gifts with a poem on it.
Does this village have a resident who is this [em1]sentimental and perceptive[/em1]?
You need a performance? Then you’ve come to the right person!
When it’s flute playing, it’s Rex! And when it’s Rex, it’s flute playing!
I’ll play as much as you want—hahaha!
You don’t have to go that far…
Ah, but what about [em1]that guy[/em1] when it comes to performing?
Personally, I’d say he’s the [em1]toughest person[/em1] in the village to deal with…
But his [em1]violin[/em1] skills are absolutely top-notch!
So, there’s someone you find difficult too…
He’s the best—no doubt about it!
You've got a gift for me?
<shake>Thank you!</shake> My witch friend!
Thank you for your [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]!
Well... Alright, I'll take it.
My dear witch! You aren't so great at picking gifts, are you!
You're giving me a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]...? Seriously?
You... didn't get this idea on a whim, did you?
Really? This is my favorite! Did Arin tell you about it?
Well... <shake>Many thanks!</shake>
Witch, you are a witch who understands the value of gifts!
Anyone would be happy to receive a gift like [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
Thank you for the gift!
It's something I really like!
You're really a good person, huh?
I'm good!
Two gifts in one day is too much for me!
If it isn't Ellie.
This is for you!
Use it whenever you want!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rex"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
If it isn't Ellie. We're meeting so much these days.
Hey! You aren't following me around, are you?!
Humph, you can actually keep up with me. Not bad...
Consider this as a reward for you.
Try to keep up the good work!
Ellie! Great timing. I've got something to tell you.
It seems... that you've been quite active recently.
You've even been to many interesting places not even I've visited... so... my point is...
I acknowledge you as my rival explorer!
Quite an honor, isn't it? After all, I've only acknowledged two explorers so far: Grandpa and Arin.
Here's a token of our rivalry.
Keep at your explorations.
And tell me about them from time to time.
Ellie! I have something to say to you, so let's talk for a moment.
I’m sure you're curious about what it's about... <shake>First of all, thank you!</shake>
What I’m thanking you for is... you always give me this and that.
Gifts, I mean.
Seeing how well you know what I need... I can tell you've put a lot of thought into it.
So! I’ll give you a gift too, thinking of you.
I look forward to working with you in the future!
I can almost hear his loud voice as I read the letter. That can be called an ability, can't it?
But... I think I've heard the name [em1]"Ritoring"[/em1] before.
We've just talked about Ralph and you've forgotten already?
Oh, those little guys living in the woods! One even got me a clover-shaped gift.
Yeah. So, Rex won't surprise you.
Hello. What can I do for you?
Haha, brace yourself for a surprise, will you?
Sure. I've thought up three poses to show my surprise.
I doubt that's the preparation you need.
I won't expect anything less from the witch that has impressed me. Let's get to the point then.
Have you heard of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s?
<shake>You have?</shake> Damn... You win.
What? Is that what you wanted to say?
Right, I asked you to come because I wanted to tell you that there are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s in this area.
Meh. What's so great about finding some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s?
Of course it's great! There are two kinds of people in this world. Those who can see [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s, and those who can't.
There are people who can't see them? Why can't they?
Because they don't have the passion for adventures... or because they aren't children at heart... I suppose?
"Suppose"?
I-it's a piece of unverified information! I need to do more research.
But one thing is for sure. There are people or witches who can't see [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s!
I don't know the cause yet... but since I've discovered this before everyone else...
You're gonna rise to fame?
You're quite impressive too. Seeing [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Ritoring"))][/em1]s is a feat in itself.
Is it? They've given me a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]. They are some nice friends to me.
What, you've even got a gift?
Oh? What does a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] do?
<wave>Haha!</wave> I see. You don't know much about [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]s!
In that case, here's an exploration quest for you. Bring a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] to me and I'll reveal its true nature to you!
Alright! It's a deal!
Good, it's decided. Bring me a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] wrapped in a leaf, and I'll admit my defeat.
I've beat you once, and I'll beat you again.
Sure. I've met them.
They run around carrying clovers, and they give me gifts.
Only sharp observers can see Ritorings.
Give [em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] to Rex?
Here. It's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]. See?
Great job, my rival witch. The victory is yours.
Now, are you ready to learn about [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]s?
<shake>Yes.</shake>
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]s are actually...
Fruits of which no special power has been discovered.
... Don't tell me that is all.
It isn't.
For the general public, they are just a symbol of luck, but they are interesting in a few ways.
And what ways are those?
Fruits offered by Ritorings living in different areas have different aromas. Are you aware of that? The seeds inside also smell subtly different.
There's more. They may have non-local fruits in them, which is really [em1]curious[/em1].
You may open a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] found in a desert and find seeds that only grow on freezing snowfields.
It may seem plain, but it's a [em1]valuable subject of exploration[/em1] for adventurers.
Well... The way you put it has made it feel amazing to me as well.
I'm glad to hear that. Those facts were all discovered by my grandpa, a great explorer.
However... they've drawn little attention due to not having any practical use.
So far, people are only collecting them as a pastime or for good luck.
There's no demand, so they don't fetch a good price.
After all, they don't seem to be doing anything.
Haha! I will make them useful.
How about I pay you with [em1]recipes[/em1] I found during my adventure? These recipes don't have much value in themselves.
I'm trying to find out whether [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1]s can contribute to adventures.
And since you witches are fond of making stuff, I suppose it's a good deal for you too.
Sounds good to me. It's a deal then.
Oh, and if you want, you can trade with me for recipes every day.
1 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RitoringPouch_Name"))][/em1] is no big deal. I will find it in no time.
When I'm away, decide on the expression you will make when you admit your defeat!
No need to remind me! I've been trying to master facial expressions!
Like I said, I doubt that's the preparation you need.
I saw him! I happened to see him during my exploration!
There's a path in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] that leads further into the depths.
I saw him taking that path.
The path in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] that leads further into the depth[/em1]...
I don't know if it has anything to do with the blue rose, though.
Maybe not. You'd better ask the others as well!
Ellie, if you find Roy, tell him I said cheer up!
Being depressed doesn't suit him. I'm counting on you!
I saw him taking the path in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common",  "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] that leads further inside.
I don't know if it has anything to do with the blue rose, though. Try asking someone else.
I'm not a cat expert.
<wave>Hey</wave>, at least ask me why, will you? Don't you just walk away!
Fine, why aren't you a cat expert? Don't you love cats?
I only explore creatures strong, dangerous, unique and magical.
Weaklings like cats, whose only advantage is a cute look, have no place in my adventures.
In addition, due to those dudes' habit of holing up in tight spaces when they rest, it's hard to observe them with a telescope.
Hm? Is it just me or are you actually quite into cats?
Humph, it's just you!
Come to me whenever you have any questions!
I have nothing to say about cats, though!
Rex!
<shake>What? Why? What is it?</shake>
You remember that flag we used for the parade?
Oh, that awesome flag? Of course I remember.
Alvin said you borrowed it from him.
Right. I borrowed it from Alvin.
Ah, I don't have it on me right now, though.
You lent it to someone else!?
<shake>How did you know!?</shake>
Who did you lend it to?
[em1]Arin[/em1] asked to borrow it, so I gave it to her.
What? <shake>Arin!?</shake>
Huh? Why? Can't I give it to Arin?
Okay. I see.
What in the world...
Finally! A job I can do for Arin!
All that talk about the Silent Guardian or whatever... I couldn't make heads or tails of that book stuff!
It's a pity I'll miss the ceremony, but it's for Arin!
I'll patrol the village outskirts! Not even an ant will get near the fountain!
Shouldn't you be watching the village outskirts, not just the fountain? That's what patrol usually means.
Oh! Does that mean I'll miss the ceremony!?
Took you long enough to figure that out. You really are just like Ellie.
I'll patrol the village outskirts!
It's a pity to miss the ceremony, but ensuring Arin's safety is more important!
Agh, fine, if I have to...
Bjorn…?
Sounds like a name I’ve heard somewhere before...
Are you talking about the train engineer who used to drive the train?
My father used to say that whenever he rode the train, there was a very loud engineer shouting.
I also heard he was a really big man.
Hearing that he’s moving here makes me look forward to it.
Ellie, I can tell you're quite frail just by looking at you!
What? <shake>Frail?</shake> I'm not!
Are you a picky eater? That's bad for you. To be healthy, you need a balanced diet!
I used to be sickly when I was little, but look how strong I've become!
A balanced diet is the first step to good health!
Sickly? You?
Exactly! You may not believe it, but as a child, I used to be feeble.
Yet you managed to become an explorer? That's quite impressive.
Thanks to the help of my gramps.
When I was sick in bed, Gramps came to see me.
Gramps is a great explorer who travels the world.
He told me about many amazing places he'd ventured to,
such as a cave stuffed with Rainbow Crystals,
and a cliff where each step was accompanied by a melody.
Stories like these certainly make you want to visit the places yourself, right?
Wow, do those places really exist?
Of course I want to visit them, then! I'm already itching to go!
<shake>Wahaha!</shake> Surely you are! Just like myself back then!
So I started to eat properly, keep a healthy bedtime routine, and exercise regularly!
A great explorer must have abundant stamina! You should eat properly too!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rex"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Hey, you seem to be holding something interesting.
You mean the collection tool?
Right, that's it! I often see other witches use it.
It always seems so magical, making me eager to try it myself!
Well, but it's a tool exclusive to witches. I can't lend it to you.
What a pity...! But it's okay. I have many cool tools myself!
Let me introduce you to the Rex Knife! It's a versatile tool.
What a strange-looking knife. It's a combination of scissors, an awl...
a knife, and a spoon... Why would you put all of them together?
Let me tell you, Ellie. That's because you never know what you will run into during an exploration.
A qualified explorer needs to bring all kinds of tools to cope with various unexpected situations!
And this is a gift Arin specially bought me before I went on an exploration trip!
You mean, Arin picked it?
When I went on my first exploration, Arin was so worried.
She packed so much baggage that I needed a carriage to pull it!
Then I said, this knife was all I needed.
To pack smaller, I did some modification to the tools Arin bought and made this multi-functional knife.
Since then, I've been carrying it all the time!
This is a one-of-a-kind treasure.
What! Why are you staring at me like that!
How did you find out about the Book of Stars?
Emm, actually, I'm not sure!
What? Why do you assume such an air of confidence then!
Because Arin is an expert on books! Whatever I find, I just give it to her to investigate and analyze!
In short, you don't know a thing.
As long as I know it's a book that grants wishes, what's the problem?
Arin has been looking for it for so long. It must be amazing!
So you've been searching for it? Without knowing what it is?
Maybe it will turn out to be nothing special when you find it.
No! It must be an amazing book!
After all, they say the harder it is to find a treasure, the more precious it is.
And there's also the saying "After suffering comes happiness," which means the same.
Why are you so determined? Is there a particular wish you want to make?
Well?
It's a secret!
A wish won't come true if you tell people about it!
How were your adventures like before you came to Wisteria?
Nothing special. I'd stuff everything I needed in a small horse-drawn carriage, and head for my destination.
Once I arrived, I'd stay there until I ran out of food.
Therefore, my goal was straightforward: Find what Arin wanted in 1 month!
Some simple and naive adventures, huh?
Urr... It couldn't be helped. Arin would worry if I was away for too long.
What? Didn't Arin go with you?
Arin had things to do at home. She could go with me if it was somewhere near, but...
Anyway, I couldn't take her with me every time.
Therefore, whatever Arin wanted, I'd bring it back for her!
I see. I suppose making your loot into bookmarks is your way of reassuring Arin.
Let's go, Ellie! You've finally grasped the [em1]essence of adventures[/em1]!
Should I take that as a compliment?
How does it feel to have a family of explorers? "There's nowhere we haven't been"?
Where did you get that idea? I'm from a family of merchants.
Most of my family members trade precious foreign goods, or trade with witches.
Me and Grandpa are the only explorers.
The Eastchips started to trade with witches a long time ago. That you didn't know is the true surprise for me.
You should have known since you rode here on that red bird train.
What? That train... was manufactured by your family?
No! My family provides food on that train!
What? <shake>Really?</shake>
Those super delicious meals served on the train! They were provided by your family?!
They are course menus designed by my father, using tasty ingredients and dishes from all over the world. So, you like them too!
You get to eat those every day?
I don't eat those. We've got our own cook,
who makes us food several times more delicious than what's sold on the train!
My goodness... My mouth is watering already. I hope I can try it.
Just drop by then.
I'll treat you to incredible meals!
Book of Stars
Previous explorations
Rex's family
Exploration is life! Once you've set a goal, you must force through all obstructions to reach it!
I'll find you a more interesting destination.
Acrophobia
Hey! If you flew on a broom, how high could you go?
On a broom?
If it's on a broom, high enough to not get hurt if I fall. But it's still pretty high up.
Want me to show you?
N-No! That's quite alright!
What's with the sudden interest in flying?
Just curious. Don't worry about it.
Worry? Why would I be worried?
Don't tell me~ Are you, maybe, scared of heights?
<shake>N-n-n-no way!</shake>
W-well, the truth is... I saw a really tall tree growing nearby.
Someone as... muscular as me is just too heavy to climb it, you see.
So I was thinking of asking you to do it for me.
Aha, is that so?
I don't see why not. If you're asking nicely.
Yep. Just as long as you tell me why you're so scared of high places.
<shake>I'm NOT scared!!</shake>
It's just... back then, Arin had such a hard time... So I don't go up high much anymore.
I just don't want to get hurt, that's all.
Well, that makes sense.
A long time ago... I fell from a really high place and got hurt.
Luckily, I landed in a river, so I just had to lie in bed for a few days. They said an ordinary guy wouldn't have been able to move for a month.
If I really have to reach high places, I will try to use a rope or something.
Oh... Well, I'll help you out then. No need to do something that would make Arin worry.
It's just... I thought I saw a familiar bird's nest right at the very top.
I need to look for someone called [em1]Freddie[/em1].
Doesn't ring a bell. I don't think that's a witch or a school staff member.
He mentioned Enite and the prickly vines,
so he's probably a former villager, no?
But Enite never talked about anyone called Freddie.
Hmm... but it would have been even stranger if she told me about every single villager in one go.
Do you think he is some hidden villager? Like a villager that appears in a puzzle game or something?
Don't treat people like game characters. That's kinda creepy.
Why, I didn't!
Anyway, didn't Freddie say that he was at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))][/em1]?
Yes, that's what the letter said.
It feels rude to bother someone in the evening when you've never met before. I guess I should go during [em1]daytime[/em1]?
Daytime is better.
But he also said [em1]"if you need me,"[/em1] so you shouldn't bother him either if you don't need him.
I'm going to talk to him about prickly vines, and about [em1]fishing[/em1].
Forgive me for not seeing how these two topics are related.
Because nobody else around here fishes.
I need to see how he does it.
And I can't leave the prickly vine stuff out either.
From your talkativeness, I can feel how determined you're to go.
Exactly. Freddie the [em1]fisher[/em1]...
Let's find him at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))] ASAP.
Sure, since nobody can stop you when you're curious.
Hello... are you Freddie?
What's going on... Who are you?
I'm Ellie Blueriver.
Are you Freddie? I received a letter from you which asked me to come, so here I am.
I didn't really expect you to come.
Ellie's quick to take action. You'll see.
I recall asking you to come "if you need me" though.
Yep! I want to see Freddie, and I have something to say, so I've come.
Aren't them good reasons?
Firstly, I want to know the true reason why you sent me the letter.
Could you talk more slowly? My ears hurt.
Nothing particular. I came back, so I wanted to say hi.
You were a villager here? That's great.
Don't jump to a conclusion. I never lived in the village. I just lived nearby.
Huh? You didn't?
I occasionally had contact with Enite, who told me about you.
She also said that the prickly vines were gone and I could come back.
That's why I sent you the letter. Satisfied?
Why didn't you live in the village? Was life not comfortable in there?
There's no need for everyone to live in a village, is there? And I like to live alone.
Thanks to the prickly vines, the [em1]fish[/em1] population here dropped dramatically, so I moved to a river nearby.
Fish? Speaking of fishing...
Are you a fisher?
I just fish to kill time. I don't do it as a job.
What else do you usually do then?
Nothing... Just fishing.
Nothing? That makes you a fisher then.
Humph... However you put it.
By the way, why are you asking out of the blue?
Are you interested in fishing? Or do you like to eat fish?
Neither. I'm just curious, since it's the first time I've met a fisher.
Is fisher a new profession or something... But I can teach you if you want to learn to [em1]fish[/em1].
It's troublesome, but since you helped the village, I guess I shall return the favor.
Really? Then teach me now please!
Now I understand what the hat said earlier.
You... don't look like you've got a fishing rod.
This is my spare. Talk it.
Firstly, fishing is a skill easy to learn but hard to master.
I'll only explain once. Listen carefully.
Got it?
Hmm... Probably.
I just need to <swing>swoosh</swing> the bobber out so that it <shake>splash</shake> somewhere near the fish, right?
Nobody will get such a vague description.
Kind of...
Yahoo.
Now I'm kind of worried that Ellie may be gifted in fishing.
Anyway, follow my words and give it a shot. You'll get the hang of it.
And reel in right when you see [em1]bubbles[/em1] on the surface, because fine baits will attract rare fishes.
Alright. Have the fish bitten?
No. They're still observing.
If I catch any fish, shall I give you one?
Why give me?
Because you taught me how to fish. And I don't know how to gut a fish even if I catch one.
So, can I give it to you, Freddie?
You surely know how to cause me trouble...
If you have to give me one, give me [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1]. I feel like eating it.
Got it. If I catch any [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1], I'll give it to you.
Good. I'm leaving now.
Oh, long time no see.
I wish I can catch salmon.
Don't underestimate fish in the lower course.
Fishing is not that simple.
Or, the more you fish, the harder fishing feels.
I feel like I'm catching as much trash as fish, but maybe I'm just imagining things.
What would you like to discuss with Freddie?
Fish
Fish are delicious no matter how you cook them.
You're more motivated when fishing once you've had fish.
And fishing itself is certainly fun enough.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Roise"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
I enjoy fishing, because I don't need to think about anything when fishing.
Of course, guessing what fish I'll catch is also fun.
Fishing is the best way to kill time however you look at it.
Stories from the past
There's something Enite told me before.
When the village was known for its tea, fish caught here all had the fragrance of tea.
I'm not interested though. Shouldn't fish just smell like fish?
Acting cool
When you want some taste in your mouth, just chew dried [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))].
Its smell can drive annoying bugs and animals away.
And it somewhat makes you look cool.
Travel
I've been fishing around. There's one single place that I haven't been to, yet I think about it so much.
It's a well-known location called Seafloor Cave in the Sky.
I may find out what that name means when I actually go there.
I don't think the fish are that eager to show up today.
Or maybe I just suck at fishing.
You have to be careful in the woods.
I don't have much to talk about.
Is there anything you like?
Let's see... Cloud Salmon?
Are Cloud Salmon good?
They don't have much meat on them until they become adults, but they taste okay.
Is that why you like them?
Salmon spend their early years out in the ocean... and come back to the rivers once they've grown up.
Yeah, right.
The course back is narrow and dangerous. The flow is turbulent.
Most salmon would fail to reach the destination due to exhaustion or getting lost.
These fish that end up somewhere halfway are called Cloud Salmon.
Because they are like clouds, floating around with no destination.
I took a liking to them after hearing this story.
It's not bad, living in the woods.
How do you live in the woods?
You get used to it.
Isn't it inconvenient?
It's better than before.
Where did you used to live?
In a village in my hometown.
And the woods are better than a village?
There's some inconveniences, but overall it's better.
There's no one to berate me.
That's certainly a plus.
What do you do with the fish you've caught?
Eat them.
You eat everything you catch?
Sometimes I let them go, sometimes I eat them all.
Don't you get tired of eating fish all the time?
I've never really thought of it like that.
Eating the same thing day after day doesn't sound very appealing...
Familiarity is good though.
But there's so many delicious foods out there.
Dunno... I'm not quite interested...
Is fishing any fun?
So-so?
Why do you fish every day if it's so-so?
I don't need to think about anything when I'm fishing.
And you like not thinking about anything?
Because I don't have to worry.
I hate things that gives me a headache.
I just want to live a carefree life.
A life all about living isn't bad.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rosie"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
They say you restored the village?
Huh? W-who are you?
I believe you're the witch that removed the prickly vines?
That's right, but why would he know that you're a witch?
Are you a former villager of Wisteria?
I'm Freddie. I wasn't a villager, but something similar.
Anyway, Enite asked me to give you this. It's a pie. Just eat it.
Enite asked you to give it to me? What is it all about?
You certainly have many questions...
Anyone would if a stranger pops up from nowhere and gives them a pie from Enite...
It's weird no matter how you think about it.
Sigh, I planned to leave once I've delivered the pie...
I'm not a villager. I just live nearby.
The fish population decreased due to the prickly vines, so I left the place temporarily...
Enite wrote to me and asked me to come back because a witch had removed the prickly vines.
So here I am, and Enite sent me to you.
But I've never heard about you, Freddie...
Doesn't surprise me. I hate to be known by people.
I'm not a villager, so neither Enite nor Rubrum should mention me.
Why don't you live in the village? You'll have neighbors, and you can help each other.
I feel more comfortable when alone.
And I would come if I need anything, so there's no inconvenience.
But you used to live nearby, didn't you?
Yes. I had a dormitory at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))][/em1].
But I moved to a river beyond the mountain quite a while ago.
Oh, that means another former resident has come back.
Shall we hold a welcome party? To celebrate your return!
What's there to celebrate about...
Anyway, I've delivered the pie. Goodbye.
W-w-wait.
Do tell me more about you.
About me? There's more you want to know?
Sure, you mentioned [em1]fish[/em1], didn't you?
Is there any chance that you're actually... a fisher?
I just fish frequently...
Fishing is what I do the most. That's all.
That makes you a fisher.
Sigh... Say what you want.
I've never met anyone who fishes.
Doesn't surprise me.
And it's not like you're interested.
No, I asked because I was curiosity. It's the first time I've met someone who fishes regularly.
Why are you curious about [em1]fishing[/em1]? You like eating fish?
It's troublesome, but since you helped the village, I can teach you how to fish.
Um-hum, just try to come to me before dark.
I have something to confirm at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))][/em1]. See you later.
Is it that urgent...
I like to fish there. I'll go and check if the Cloud Salmon have come back.
You can find me there from now on. Come to me if you want to learn fishing.
Hahaha... Understood. Take care.
Virgil, I'm kinda uneasy now.
A sudden pie delivery?
Catching fish sounds cooler than eating them.
Just imagine casting a long fishing rod out with a swoosh and pulling fish in.
Can I go now?
Who are you exactly? Who told you that I am a witch?
About me?
He keeps running around. I wouldn't expect that just by looking at his physique.
Indeed... He ran off in no time.
Anyway, it was my first time seeing a fisher. It's amazing.
Would anything not amaze you?
Hmm... a hat that doesn't talk?
Forget that I asked...
That aside, this can almost count as having another returning villager.
The village population is growing...
It's great! It feels like I've achieved a lot!
This one doesn't seem to like you, though?
That Freddie has this leave-me-alone air all over him.
Maybe the reason that he can't live in the village is because he's too into fishing?
It's the opposite to me. He makes a living by fishing because he doesn't want to live in the village.
There may be more to it...
More to it?
It's just my assumption. You may ask him directly.
Since you'll learn fishing from him.
Didn't you notice the change in his expression?
I did. He got excited whenever he talked about fish or fishing.
I've always wanted to try fishing, so I'm going to seize the opportunity.
I never knew you had such an aspiration. That's quite impressive.
Heh, Freddie asked me to go find him at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))][/em1] during daytime, right?
I will. I'm looking forward to it.
Freddie, here I am.
You promised to teach me [em1]how to fish[/em1], remember?
I didn't really expect you to come...
Not like I'm interested.
Aww, I can't wait to learn fishing from an expert.
I've been dreaming to catch my own fish!
Have you brought your fishing rod?
Fishing rod?
Your skills aside, you at least need a fishing rod.
I thought you would provide me with one, Freddie.
Can't I just fish with a string tied to a branch?
Aren't you oversimplifying things?
That idea's impressive in a way.
Hehehe.
What do I do? Shall I buy one from Aurea?
Oh, Aurea.
You know Aurea?
The merchant? I know that she goes around selling stuff. That's all.
Yeah, and the stuff Aurea sells are quite good.
Forget about it... I'd be kept waiting if you go buy it now.
Handed over Fishing Rod
Here, this is my spare. You can use it.
Could you calm down?
I'm not using it anymore, so just take it.
Yippee!
More specifically...
Skills matter in fishing, but intuition matters too.
Like the intuition of a hunter??
That's probably going too far...
Understood. I'll do as I'm told.
By the way, has you ever caught Cloud Salmon?
Not yet. I've only caught other fishes.
If I catch any Cloud Salmon, shall I give you one?
Then it's decided. If I catch any Cloud Salmon, I'll bring it to you.
Okay, I'll be going then.
And reel in right when you see [em1]bubbles[/em1] rising to the surface, because fine baits will attract rare fishes.
Give Freddie [em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1]?
Freddie, see? I caught [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1]!
Wanna hear the truth?
Well, no.
Okay, I'll take it.
But why do you want to catch Cloud Salmon?
They don't seem so hard to catch.
That's not the point. Cloud Salmon only live in the Green Forest.
Fish have [em1]habitats[/em1] too.
So, you couldn't catch them in the river beyond the mountain, where you previously lived.
No, there were none.
Why does it have to be this fish then?
If you simply want to eat fish, there are other tasty fishes out there.
Is it private?
Are you collecting fishes or something?
How do you collect fishes?
Keep them in a giant fish tank, or do fish rubbing and collect the prints?
Collecting fishes sounds fun.
Many fish species can be found in the Green Forest alone~
You do get to find many life forms here in the wild that you'd never see in the School for Witches.
Yeah, there'll probably be many amazing fishes I've never seen before.
While we're on that topic...
Are you interested in collecting fishes?
Not with a fish tank or fish rubbing, but sort of an [em1]encyclopedia[/em1].
Wow! You really are collecting fishes?
In fact, I've been making an encyclopedia since I came here.
It's a school assignment though.
It doesn't matter as long as I enjoy it.
Neither am I making mine for sale or anything...
It's just a hobby?
Well... right.
Shall we do it together?
We can finish the encyclopedia earlier if we joint hands!
And we can discuss fish in the process, which adds to the fun.
Fishing is... not that simple.
You need to know when each fish is active. Some species only appear once in a century. You won't instantly catch what you want.
I know you want to dissuade Ellie, but she only ended up getting more motivated.
Is it a deal then?
You sure?
Sure, let's make a [em1]fish encyclopedia[/em1] together!
Sigh...
This is the Fish Encyclopedia I made before.
Everyone gets different data, so I've left this one blank.
I can't wait to fill it in!
I'll give you [em1]rewards[/em1] as you fill in the Encyclopedia.
As for what the rewards are, I'll tell you when I've decided.
Wow... great.
Now, anything else you want to say?
Let's see. I've learned fishing and got the Fish Encyclopedia.
Nothing then?
Hahaha. Bye, Freddie.
[em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1] is enough to feed me.
Just 1?
I can have 10 in one go, but I've got other fish, so I need no more.
Alright, I'll bring you more.
Did you ask because you want to strike up a conversation?
I don't need you for anything...
Sell Fish
Let me know if you want to sell anything.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("UI", "FishingNote_Title"))]
Already caught this much?
You're fishing hard. Take this.
Shall we check another page...
The others are still far off.
Catch some more fish and come back.
Still far off.
Let me know if you want to buy anything.
Nothing in particular.
Here's another letter from Freddie.
It basically says he wants to fish in the village...
But feels discouraged because of the cats.
Makes sense. After all, Freddie pays no attention to his surroundings once he starts fishing.
Even if anyone takes his fish, he won't notice.
Shouldn't he be able to sense the noises?
Cats hardly make any noises.
At least that's what he says.
But... do cats like fish?
Well, I guess they do, since they are said to steal fish often.
It's common knowledge that cats enjoy eating fish.
And there's a common saying about watching over a seafood store being the last task you should assign a cat.
Is it that bad?
I think I must find Freddie to hear the details.
I need to ask him how much cats like fish, among other questions.
What? Are you going to ask him how many fish cats have stolen from him?
Come on, it's for making friends with cats!
For heaven's sake...
Freddie!
... What?
Have you started to work on the fish I want?
No, I haven't.
If so... why are you here?
I've got some questions to ask you.
Freddie, you don't like [em1]cats[/em1]?
... I shouldn't have mentioned cats in my letter.
Please, don't say that. I can't help you until my curiosity is satisfied.
Alright, what do you want to know?
Just how much do cats like [em1]fish[/em1]?
How much... How would I know?
Although they do try to steal all of my catch.
So, you've suffered quite some loss? How many times have they stollen fish from you?
Let's see... Once or twice?
Huh... That's not a lot.
They've only actually stollen my fish once or twice, but they usually stare at me when I fish.
And when it comes to throwing my hard-earned catch away, even once is too many.
Speaking of which, some cats only stare at [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] only? They do have a clear [em1]preference[/em1].
Humph, that's why I asked you to fish for me.
Alright. One last question.
Why did you ask me to catch 3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1]?
Because I want to cook a dish with them.
Wow, a dish?
... I've never cooked it before. I'll treat you to it if I succeed.
Alright. I'm off catching [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] now.
... Okay.
Haha, see you later!
Give 3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] to Freddie?
Freddie, I got you 3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1]. Can you cook now?
Yup, I can get to it at once, since I've got all the other ingredients.
I can't wait! A [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] dish!
Well, don't be too positive... I'm not a great cook.
It'd be the best if you succeed, but you can always practice more if you fail.
You're such an optimist.
So I am, now that I've found out that both Freddie and cats like fish.
Speaking of which, I still don't get it...
Why must you feed fish to cats?
Well... because they like to eat fish?
If they like to eat fish, they will like a person who feeds them fish. That way, we will be friends!
To feed them fish, you just need to leave the fish on the ground. They'll help themselves.
That will work, but... I also want them to know that the fish are the fruit of my hard work.
I wonder where you get all these strange ideas.
I never want to make friends with cats.
Anyway, is that all you want to say to me?
Well... for now, yes.
On your way then.
Oh... since you got me fish... you can have this.
Haha, thanks. I'll think about how to feed the fish to them.
3 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] will be enough for my new dish.
I look forward to it. I'll be back soon.
What do you think, Virgil? Shall I feed them fish the way I fed them apples?
Cats wouldn't mind if I place it on the ground, just like if I throw it to them, right?
Like you said, they will enjoy it even if you simply throw it to them.
But you want them to know the fish is from you.
Right, I'm doing this because I want to be their friend.
In that case, you should somehow let the cats know that you are the one providing the fish.
Indeed. They will be more willing to befriend me if they know I'm making the efforts to prepare them food.
Remember what Freddie said about some cats staring at [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1] only?
Uh-huh.
That means... cats also have [em1]preferences[/em1]!
So, if I get them their favorite fish...
They'll be impressed by your sincerity?
All the more reason to fish hard now.
Well that's a good effect.
I suppose... the cats will come over if I fill the bowl with fish they like?
There should be some rules, so that the cats will know the fish are from you.
Nothing will bring us closer then familiarity.
Right. And I need to always place the fish at a same spot, so that the cats will remember it.
I must sincerely place the fish on... a box or something!
Wouldn't a bowl be better than a box? It'll look more decent too.
Yeah, that's the something I was trying to say.
But where can I get a [em1]bowl for cats[/em1]?
There doesn't seem to be any bowl to spare at the Witch's House.
Maybe you can look around the village.
Shall I go to Aurea?
As a grocer, she may sell cat food bowls.
What are you waiting for then?
Just show me your ability of jumping into action.
Hahaha, that's what I plan.
To repair the [em1]broken cat toy[/em1], shouldn't you bring it over first?
Ah, you're right, I'll need to bring it here!
Freddie! Isn't the weather just great today?
What's up with the sudden weather chat?
You don't usually bring that up unless there's something else you want.
Haha, you got me. I do have a favor to ask.
I brought something kind of like a fishing rod and was wondering if you could fix it for me.
Something like a fishing rod?
Looks a bit rough around the edges. And that's not exactly a bobber hanging off the end...
It's actually a cat toy. It reminded me of the fishing rod you gave me — [em1]simple design, right?[/em1]
[em1]<wiggle>Simple design?</wiggle>[/em1] Pfft, Ellie, a fishing rod isn't just some random stick, you know.
The type of rod depends on the fish, the location, and the bait. The rod I gave you was made with all of that in mind! Didn't you know?
If you want to be a real angler, you've got to know your gear. Like for starters, using sturdy wood or bamboo...
Hold up.
Calm down, Freddie! All I'm asking is if you can fix this toy that's similar to a fishing rod.
Oh, I see. Well, unfortunately, no.
Huh? That was a quick "no"!
The rod's split along the grain. Can't fix it. You'll have to get a new one.
Could you make a new one for me, then?
I figured you'd ask that... It's not hard to make, just a bit of a hassle.
Tsk... As you may expect, I'll need you to gather the materials.
Of course! I'll bring what you need!
Alright, I'll need [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Murchin_Name"))][/em1].
I get the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] part, but what's the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Murchin_Name"))][/em1] for?
Just trust me. You'll need it for this project.
Got it! I'll collect the materials and get back soon!
No rush, take your time.
Give [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Murchin_Name"))][/em1] to Freddie?
Freddie! I've brought all the materials you asked for.
Great, hang tight for a bit.
You can't just use a whole branch to make a rod. You've got to use the right parts.
Now, like this... and this... there we go.
Wow! That was really fast!
...Well, it's just a toy, so it should work.
Awesome! Now I can enjoy playing with Rubrum and the cats!
Must be nice...
Hey, you light up whenever you're talking about fishing, right?
I guess we're kind of alike in that way.
...I think I get it. Sort of.
By the way, what did you need the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Murchin_Name"))][/em1] for?
Oh, that? That's just a snack for me.
Wait, what?
I was craving it, so I figured you wouldn't mind helping out with that too.
Haha, of course not! It's only fair, since you helped me out.
And while you're at it, send my regards to Rubrum. Tell him I'll bring some fish over soon.
Got it. Have a good day, Freddie!
Bring me [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Branch_Special_Name"))][/em1] and [em1]1 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Murchin_Name"))][/em1], and I'll help you make it.
But why do you even want a toy that's like a fishing rod?
Because I want to play with Rubrum and the cats!
After all, who can resist a cute kitty?
...I don't quite get it.
Just don't forget to bring what I need if you want me to make a new one.
Freddie, did you know there's a festival happening in the village?
Hm? They do that sort of thing?
Yeah. So, how about coming down to the village for a change?
There are even spots where you can fish in the village, you know.
Hmmm...
You should come. Enite said she's waiting for you too.
Well, I'll think about it.
You have to come, okay? Promise?
Alright, alright. I'll think about it.
Not for me. Give it to someone else.
Freddie sent another letter related to fishing.
If it's bait used to catch [em1]specific fish[/em1]...
Of course, I'm curious about what it is! Let’s go talk about it.
Hello, Freddie. I came to see because you said you made some bait.
You came? I sent the letter just in case. As expected, you're really serious about fishing.
Anyway, as I wrote in the letter, I’ve made some bait that’s useful for fishing.
It’s also easy to use. Once you use the bait, one will be used up every time you fish.
Then, every time you fish, the chances of catching a fish that matches the effect of the bait will increase.
Ah, if the bait is attached to the fishing rod, it will be consumed no matter what, so don’t waste it by casting it into the air.
I’ll give you a few for now... if you think they’re useful, come buy some.
I'm not much of a talker... I don't have anything to say in particular.
What would you like to discuss with Roy?
Train
May I ask... Did you disembark the train in your shoes?
I wasn't teasing you, so please don't give me that look.
Thank goodness you were not hoodwinked.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Roy"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Edible Flowers
Were you aware there are also edible flowers?
If it's okay with you, I'll show you a few next time.
The right flowers are said to make a meal more enjoyable.
Language of Flowers
Each flower has its own language.
A lot of people want to convey the messages behind the flowers when they gift flowers.
That's why I know the meaning of each flower I sell like the back of my hand.
It's a great spot. Quiet and inhabited by warmhearted residents.
I'm so glad Enite looks like she's still in good health.
Rubrum's also... grown a lot bigger.
Way of speaking
Though people around me have asked me not to be so formal when talking to them,
it's not that easy to kick the habit.
Even so, I'm not attempting to be distant, so there is no need to worry.
I like the people, but not the city.
Many things go on in cities every day. I can't get used to it.
If I have to name one, it'd be fishing.
I can catch delicious [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_CloudSalmon_Name"))][/em1].
I've considered picking up an instrument, but I don't have much motivation.
I find the Green Forest a nice place. There are many flowers you can hardly see elsewhere.
Especially glowing [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SilverStarFlower_Water_Name"))][/em1]s. Bouquets made with those are quite popular, so I frequently collet them from the forest.
I usually go there to get books on flowers or plants in general.
Recently, I've also been reading books recommended by Arin.
I've never read any novels or poem collections before, but I've found some fun in them.
Prickly vines
When studying plants, I've also tried to identify those prickly vines infesting the village.
My research showed that they were a new species.
And I just gave up looking for a solution... Fortunately, you didn't give up, Ellie.
The Cloud Valley is home to many giant flowers,
but they've got really short antheses. They wither in less than one day.
I've considered gathering their seeds and cultivating them myself, but due to some past experience, I don't feel like entering the Cloud Valley.
I tried most of the food I'm interested in when living in Highlion.
There's one exception, though. It's so popular that I never managed to get any.
You know [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WitchFairyCake_Name"))][/em1]? I hope I can try one.
Donuts
I-it's not like I have a sweet tooth.
But... after I joined the army, I spent quite some time with no access to sweet food.
As a result, when I finished my training and ate my first donut in ages... the taste was unforgettable.
Friends
I never expected to make any lasting friend.
But...I've made many friends after knowing you, Ellie.
Ellie, thank you for befriending me.
Aspiration
I don't have any aspiration. I just want to learn my current happiness by heart.
Besides that... I hope everyone around me stays healthy and happy.
Is this... an answer you want?
I've hardly fished anywhere outside of the village... so I've only caught limited types of fish.
Speaking of which, I don't think I've caught any [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Gwitch_Name"))][/em1].
There are flowers that only bloom at night... but they’re quite difficult to manage.
I’m human too, so I can’t stay awake all the time.
That’s why I use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "StoneCrocodile_Powder_Name"))][/em1] effectively.
Thanks to that, if I place it on the soil, I don't have to worry about it for several days.
I visit often because there are a lot of good items for sale.
Even though the items Alvin sells aren’t that expensive, they have something special about them.
Since you’re someone who can appreciate good things, I think the shop is filled with quality items as well.
Please let me know if you ever need flowers.
Each and every of my flowers is fresh.
It helps keep the soil moist, allowing water to soak in more slowly than usual.
I've got a gift for you today.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Roy"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
Oh, it's you, Ellie.
I was planning to go to you.
It's a little something from me. A token of gratitude.
Come visit my flower shop whenever you feel like it.
There's something magical about you, Ellie.
Few people try to interact with me like you do...
I used to trouble and confuse people around me a lot.
As a result, I also struggle to interact with others.
However, I feel comfortable in my skin when around you. That's why I can open up with you.
I'll work hard to maintain our friendship and interact more with you.
As my first step, please accept this.
Ellie. I have something to tell you for a moment.
I thought a lot about how to express this, but...
I think it's better to just share my thoughts as they are.
Every time I received the gifts you prepared for me, I felt what true happiness is.
To repay that gratitude, I also want to give you a meaningful gift, Ellie.
Would you accept this? It's a gift filled with my sincerity.
I’m not sure if it’s enough to repay your kindness toward me.
Sincerely... I look forward to continuing our relationship.
A gift for me?
A [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1], for me?
You're giving me a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
It's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
Anyway, I appreciate it.
it's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]...
I don't think this goes with a flower shop... I'll accept it this time, but please give me no more of it.
Ellie... You're always so nice.
Words alone aren't enough to express my gratitude...
I can't thank you enough, Ellie. I'll cherish this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1].
Ellie, you know what I like, don’t you?
Thanks to you, I believe I’ll be able to spend today happily.
It’s a gift filled with sincerity.
Ellie, I’m deeply grateful for always giving me such warm-hearted care.
I will use the gift you gave me well.
I need no more.
One gift is good enough for a day.
It's all right.
Do you have anything to tell me?
I don't have any favor to ask for at the moment.
I do run a flower shop...but as you can see, I’m just a normal passenger at the moment.
I'm still preparing.
Thanks to Ellie’s frequent visits to the flower shop, it feels full of life.
So I’m thinking of placing some [em1]varied furniture[/em1] in the flower shop. Of course, I’ll also increase the [em1]stock[/em1].
The improvements will be ready for you to see starting tomorrow.
Speak.
It's a given that you have to water the plants in the morning.
Good morning.
I'm taking care of the flowers so that they don't wither.
I hope these flowers will delight the others when they come back.
Please tell me what you intend to use it for so that I may provide some recommendations.
What kind of flowers are you looking for?
Though I once fed myself with the fish I caught, I do it for pleasure now.
I often read about the past like this.
So, goodbye then.
Ah, Ellie. I have something for you.
It’s a small gift.
I'm glad I can have donuts every morning again.
I should pick some up on my way back.
Just looking at the trees puts me at ease.
Hi, Ellie, I happen to be taking a break. Can I help you?
I really enjoy days as peaceful as these.
I often borrow books from the library.
Don't worry, I've got my bookmark in. Please, speak freely.
Ellie, it's been a while. How are you?
I haven't seen much of him, so I'm not sure.
I haven't seen it again ever since, either.
After the war, I scoured the area and the place where I saw that field of flowers... but no one else had even heard of it.
Though a farmer who lived nearby said it was a region plagued by constant conflict, where many people died.
Legend has it that the spirits of those who died with grievances left unresolved blossom into flowers.
Ah, perhaps a [em1]witch[/em1] like you might know something about that?
For me, I think the blue flower pot I mentioned previously will do.
The flower pot should be in the shop.
You want to scale a cliff on a broken ladder?
Well... I've got something that may help you. Care to learn about it?
I've got a seed
of a plant called [em1]Hanging Vine[/em1]. It's only found in the [em1]rich soil[/em1] around Highlion.
This plant can [em1]climb[/em1] almost anything, so it's considered a weed by some.
But everyone into container gardening knows it.
It grows rapidly, and is quite enduring. There's only one issue: If you grow it at Wisteria, it will [em1]wither[/em1] in no time.
[em1]Fertilizer[/em1] revives it temporarily, but you can't be adding fertilizer forever.
Therefore, I've been wondering what to do about it.
Ellie, if you want to use it, you may need to prepare some [em1]fertilizer sort of thing[/em1].
I see... May I have the seed?
Sure. It's always better to give it to someone who needs it.
Plant it [em1]beneath the cliff[/em1].
It can climb anything, so I should be able to use the ladder with its help.
But it will [em1]wither in no time[/em1], so I need some [em1]fertilizer sort of thing[/em1] too..
I guess I can climb up now!
I hope the energy I gave you helps.
I just need to stretch out my hands at the marionette...? Like this?
Right. I can feel craftsman's aura flowing into the marionette.
I can't feel anything, probably because I'm not a witch. Still, I'm glad to be of help.
Thank you, Roy!
Could this be the process needed to make the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Craft"))][/em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] I gave you better?
We are. Infusing the marionette with craftsman's aura is an important step towards completing my carpentry task.
I'd love to share my aura with you... but I don't know if I count as a craftsman.
You are excellent in growing flowers, Roy. All flowers thrive when under your care. You've got skills and a sincere attitude. I can't see why you don't count.
And you keep all your tools in order. Just one glance and everyone will consider you a craftsman in flower growing!
That's very kind of you, Ellie. I'm kind of embarrassed. Is that really all it takes to be considered a craftsman?
Nevertheless, I'm willing to offer any help I can.
Are you talking about the spirit of the craftsman?
This story is foreign to me.
Hi there, Roy! Vinch wanted you to deliver the order to his house.
Hi, Ellie. So, I see you're here to deliver a message. Alright, I got it.
Everything is ready. They just need to be delivered.
I heard it's some material for making paint. What exactly is it?
It's cypress tree.
Huh? It's not flower but tree?
Yep. This kind of cypress Vinch ordered has golden-tipped leaves, which is extremely beautiful.
It's still a seedling now, so it's green. Give it time and the color will change.
I see... I thought for sure it was a flower.
May I see it?
I'll come again when [em1]Roy is working at the flower shop[/em1].
I only know a ”method“ that can hardly be called a recipe.
Because I haven't actually studied or really done much research,
I just learned a bit through observation... It's not worth demonstrating.
Since you've agreed to help find a recipe,
I'll get what I can ready.
You need to have a special flower to pluck it, it's very unique.
According to the [em1]legend[/em1], that's the only method, so I looked around for it myself...
It's said to be very close to the moon, so I thought it would be someplace high up.
I went to the [em1]highlands[/em1], but it was nowhere to be found.
Hey, Ellie. I was just looking for you.
Upon hearing that you had cleaned up the prickly vines across the bridge,
I immediately contacted Brad.
I was in a hurry when I left the village and I forgot to return the books.
If Brad could come back to the village, I'd have the chance to return the book.
That's great. He can return now.
Yeah. That's what I thought too...
But Brad said he had a place in mind for a while now, and a spot just opened up.
So? He's not returning to Wisteria?
Right. So he talked it over with a good friend,
And it turns out that friend's grandson is very interested in the village.
The friend mentioned that his grandson is bright and capable, and he'll even bring the books from the old library along.
He hopes that you'll accept him to replace Brad as the village librarian.
I see. Is it up to me to decide on this matter?
I already talked to Enite about this. After all, you're the hero who restored the village.
Although it's a bit disappointing not to see Brad, I'm also curious about this grandson. So, I agreed.
That's great. I'll write a letter to let them know right away.
Then, we can discuss with Enite a suitable time.
The grandson of Brad's friend decided to come and take Brad's place.
He'll also bring the books from the old library, restoring the library's functionality.
I heard he's a smart and capable young man, and I'm looking forward to meeting him.
She often came to buy flowers.
I often saw her in the forest studying plants.
She was especially intrigued by the White Prickly Vines and Little Honey Pumpkins.
Do you remember any places Lisa frequented?
Places Lisa frequented...
Well... Lisa could often be found walking around the forest.
I didn't see her favoring or lingering at any particular spot.
No, I don't think Lisa would have done that on purpose.
Though she wasn't much of a talker, I think she was a good witch.
But... even if it was an honest mistake, her disappearing without fixing it disappoints me a little.
Maybe there's more to the story.
I hope so.
I'll bring Lisa back.
Well, I'll leave it to you then.
If it's a task given by the Black Cat God...
"If you desire the promised flower, then bring me an [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1] in its stead."
"Present that flower among [em1]living flowers[/em1]."
And that "Living flowers bloom in the [em1]heart[/em1]." Right?
I believed the "living flowers bloom in the heart" refers to the pansies on my brooch.
So, I decided to prepare a pansy bouquet.
And you, Ellie, agreed to look into finding an [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1].
I've left a [em1]book with relevant information[/em1] inside the [em1]flower shop[/em1] for you. Feel free to look at it anytime.
You're looking for plants only found around Wisteria?
Yes, even better if they can be made into bookmarks.
Well... in that case, my recommendation would be [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
At [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))], you can find many strange creatures hard to see elsewhere.
And if you want to make bookmarks out of them... [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MushroomWallPlants_Collect_Name"))][/em1] would be your best choice.
Rumor says that it can grant wishes. It makes a good gift.
You wonder how to hold on to slippery things?
I encounter the same problem when moving or changing flower pots.
I would put on gardening gloves in such occasions.
I would apply [em1]non-slip spray[/em1] to the inner side of the gloves.
A little bit of weak [em1]adhesive[/em1] would do the trick too.
Ellie, as a witch, you should know something more practical, right?
Going to gather starlight… is that really possible?
There are many floating starlights in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]. I’m going to collect them.
It truly feels like something out of a fairy tale… Very well. If I can be of help, I shall accompany you.
Ah, if Dana is going, perhaps you might also consider inviting Clala.
Since it is a special experience, it would be even better if the family could join together.
Before that...
You've been staring at my feet for a while, is there some kind of problem?
Oh, I was going to ask anyway. Isn't it troublesome to wear such strappy boots?
It takes some time to put them on and take them off but I'm used to it.
Then it would be hard for you when you arrive at Highlion.
What? What are you talking about...?
I mean, you have to take your shoes off when you get off.
Oh, you were kidding? I'm sorry, I'm rather dull when it comes to things like this...
<shake>Jenny!!!!</shake>
<shake>Mr. Bartender!!!</shake>
At last, mystery solved.
Did I make some kind of mistake?
No, no... I just realized that I was deceived.
Come to think of it, I remember now. It's a joke to make fun of people who visit Highlion for the first time...
Stop. You don't have to kill me twice by giving that much detail.
I’m sorry.
Are you holding back laughter?
...No, I’m not.
He's trying so hard to be considerate of you. Don't ask twice.
Virgil, I hate you even more now.
You don't need to be too upset.
When I went there for the first time in the past, I was also tricked by a colleague and took them off.
That doesn't comfort me at all.
There're a bunch of letters whose recipients are not specified?
It should be a prank if you ask me... Brad's always into making jokes.
Thank you for the trouble, Ellie. Please show me the letters if you don't mind.
Hmm... It's about canes, but I don't use them.
Brad got along with all the villagers.
He was particularly close to [em1]people around his age[/em1]. You can ask them.
Hmm... Sorry, but this doesn't seem to be about me.
I know nothing about painting. Find someone else.
Oh, I know this.
I considered improving packaging when I'd just opened my flower shop,
in order to provide customers with more constructive advice. I sought Brad's input too.
Brad recommended me books about flowers. That's how I learned the language of flowers.
Since then, whenever I plan to try something new, I've been telling Brad about it.
And Brad would recommend methods to me just like this.
Thank you for bringing me the letter, Ellie.
He doesn't go out often, so we haven't met much.
But he occasionally comes to buy flowers.
It appears that he uses them in painting and making paint.
Although he doesn't talk much, I think he's polite and kind.
Also, I can feel that he's really putting in effort in painting.
I think it's very cool that he is committed to something he loves.
I think I've asked just about everyone I can.
So, no one has actually seen it themselves.
Well, it's not a total dead end.
Arden told us to look into the [em1]Garden of Empty Words[/em1].
Vince said he'd heard that an ingredient for a dye with "[em1]Blue Flower[/em1]" in its name is a blue rose...
And Diane said she'd ask the witches she knows who might have info on blue roses.
Let's wait about [em1]a day[/em1] and then talk to [em1]Diane[/em1] again.
Speaking of which, I wonder if Roy has heard anything else?
We have to wait anyway. Why not go see him if you're curious?
Yeah, good idea. I should go meet [em1]Roy[/em1] while we've got the time.
Phew, all done.
Okay, finally... just one last step to go.
Here goes nothing! [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))]!
Whoa, it looks so real.
It's almost identical to the one Roy has, don't you think?
Right! Now we just need to bring Roy here and show him!!
You could leave that right there, and no one would suspect a thing.
He said he'd let me know before going to see his master, so he should still be in [em1]town[/em1].
I wonder if we'll get to see Roy's face light up with a smile?
Let's go get him, quick!
Ah, Ellie. Hello.
I actually have some good news.
Oh? What is it?
Right after I spoke with you, another express letter arrived.
It says my teacher has gotten through it.
They still need to monitor everything, but the prognosis is good.
Wow, that's great news!
Yes. It's really, truly a relief.
By the way... did you happen to learn anything more about the field of blue roses?
We're still looking into it, but I think we've got a solid lead.
I'll let you know as soon as we find out more.
But how did the blue roses save you and your teacher's lives back then?
Ah, that story?
Well... I mentioned before that my teacher and I once went through a life-and-death situation.
It was during the war. My teacher was severely wounded, and I charged in blindly to save him.
We managed to escape the fray, but ended up isolated, just the two of us.
We were running out of food and water. We wandered through the woods, certain we were going to die.
My feet felt like lead, and I almost wanted to give up. If not for the painful coughs I heard from my teacher on my back...
It was a dark night... nothing but the same black trees, no matter how far we walked.
And [em1]then[/em1] it happened. Even now, if I close my eyes... I can see it.
In the heart of that pitch-black forest, a blue lake seemed to spread out before us.
As if someone had cut a hole in the sky right above that spot... a circle of moonlight poured down.
A field of blue roses swaying in the wind, bathed in that moonlight...
The clear scent of water was so strong, I almost believed a real lake had appeared.
And that scent was coming from a small stream running near the field of roses.
We were able to hold out there until we reunited with our allies.
I grabbed one blue rose as we left in a hurry... but when I went back later, the place had vanished, like a mirage.
Whoa, that sounds just like the legends of flowers you told me about before!
Haha, if I didn't have this blue rose as proof, I might have thought it was a dream, too.
So, does that mean you don't have to go there right away now?
Actually, I'm currently trying to purchase some [em1]train tickets[/em1].
Train tickets? You don't mean... that train?
Yes. The very same train where you and I first met.
But I heard the tickets are absurdly expensive...
They are. I'll likely have to use all the money I've saved up.
Even then, the tickets are so scarce that it's really difficult to get one.
Is taking the train absolutely necessary?
My teacher lives quite far from here.
It's too far to go on foot... Even with other transportation, it would take a solid two months.
Fortunately, my teacher's hometown isn't far from a train station.
I want to get there as quickly as I can, in case more news arrives.
Hmm... I might be able to ask around to find a ticket for you.
Let me know if you really can't find one.
Thank you. But I've already asked for so much, I couldn't possibly trouble you further.
I'll keep trying in the meantime.
Okay. I'm sure it'll all work out!
Hmm. It hasn't been long since Diane said she'd look into things, so I should probably wait a bit longer.
I'll talk to [em1]Diane[/em1] again [em1]tomorrow[/em1].
Hmm. I'll bet Diane has found out something by now.
Let's go [em1]ask Diane[/em1]!
Hello, Roy.
Did those flowers you took from the shrine the other day make it to your teacher?
<shake>Roy!!!</shake>
<shake>Huh</shake>, wha? Ah... Ellie. Hello.
Why are you spacing out like that? Is something wrong?
Ah, well...
It's... a bit of a long story. Would you... hear me out?
Well, you see... I received a letter.
It says my teacher's condition is critical.
It says... I might not see him again.
What? Then shouldn't you go see him right away?
I should. It's just...
Is something bothering you?
It's the [em1]field of blue roses[/em1]... I think it'd be nice to show it to my teacher again.
Why the field of blue roses?
It's an old story... When we thought it was the end, that we would die there...
It's the [em1]rose that saved our lives[/em1].
So, I thought that if he could see that field of roses again, it might give him the strength to pull through.
But I've searched for years and never found it again.
I know it's a foolish hope... but I can't stop thinking about it.
Roy...
But you still have that blue rose, right? What if you took that?
Of course, I plan to take it.
But a single blossom isn't enough.
A single flower can't recreate the spectacle of that field...
The [em1]beautiful miracle[/em1] laid out before our eyes. It was fantastical, beyond words.
Well... I still think you should focus on preparing to go see him.
Let me see what I can find out about the field of blue roses!
Can I leave it to you?
I've tried finding it myself, so I know it's no simple task. I know, and yet I find myself hoping.
But you're the one who cleared the village's prickly vines, something everyone thought was impossible...
I'll leave it in your hands, Ellie. Please.
Okay. I'll see if I can find a way.
Try to get more news about your teacher and get ready to leave at a moment's notice.
I said I'd look, but how exactly?
I've never even seen a blue rose at the School for Witches...
You know better than to make promises you can't keep.
But I feel so bad for him.
Maybe someone I know has a clue. Let's just start investigating.
You never know. The answer might be closer than we think.
I see. Please, don't worry yourself about it.
Was it my fault?
You didn't do anything wrong.
But Roy...
I just wanted to see Roy happy...
Roy knows that.
But sometimes, life just takes an unexpected turn.
Call it bad luck.
A witch's potion is powerful, but it can't perform miracles on its own.
I wasn't trying to perform a miracle...
I just wanted to see him smile at a field of flowers...
What was I supposed to do?
You did your best.
Sometimes, all you can do is wait for time to heal things.
Virgil, why are you being so nice today?
Because I'm your hat.
Go home, have a warm cup of cocoa, and get some rest.
That's your only job right now.
Yeah... Thanks, Virgil.
Whoa, that's a really vivid blue.
Next step... "Throw at the object you wish to turn blue?"
"Apply thoroughly until no part remains."
"Warning! Do not use on humans, witches, or living creatures!"
Huh... Okay. So I just [em1]throw[/em1] it. Let's do this.
Yes! <wave>All the potions are done!</wave>
Now I need the [em1]sculptures[/em1] to use them on.
The one Alvin made last time looked so real. I'll ask him.
No matter how good the potion is, it'll just be a cheap imitation if the sculpture is shoddy.
You'll need a lot of them to make a whole field.
Hmm... Someone skilled and quick with their hands...
It's gotta be [em1]Alvin[/em1]!
And since I'm going to the village, I should check in on [em1]Roy[/em1] again.
Going to ask him to help make them?
No. He might have gotten another letter.
And now that I know I can make the blue rose field, I can't help myself. I'm dying to tell someone.
If I give him a little hint of progress, it might cheer him up.
I should hurry to the village and tell Roy.
Huh? Roy!
Ah... Ellie.
Where are you headed? To your teacher's place?
That's... not it.
I have something to show you, Roy! Right now!
Right... now?
Yes! The field of blue roses!
Blue... roses, you said?
Blue... roses...
Let's go together! It's a real field of blue roses!
The exact field you've been looking for!
Very well. Let's go immediately.
Phew, done.
I planted them pretty well, didn't I?
Now, let's see... Diane gave me special instructions for the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EveryBluePotion_Name"))]...
Prepare a full bucket of clean water, then...
Dilute the potion in it. The end?
Wow, that's super simple. Let's do it right away.
Roy! You look better than the last time I saw you.
Do I? I suppose my mind is a bit more at ease.
Fortunately, it seems I'll be able to get a train ticket.
Wow, really? That's great! The train will get you there quickly, right?
Yes. I had to pay a bit extra, but I'm just grateful I found one.
What brings you here, Ellie?
Well. I have good news, too.
I think I can show you that field of blue roses you've been looking for!
Is that... truly?
And it's even [em1]near Wisteria[/em1]!
Truly? It's truly near Wisteria?
To think it was so close all this time and I never knew...
It was in a place that's hard to find by ordinary means.
Ah, that reminds me, how will you show it to your teacher?
Actually, hearing you say that gives me an idea...
I was thinking of asking him if he wouldn't like to come to Wisteria with me after the visit.
It's a quiet, clean town with many kind people. It would be good for his recuperation.
So the town would get one more resident?
If that's what my teacher wants, yes.
If that happens...
We could see the field of blue roses together again.
I don't know the last time my heart pounded like this.
It feels just like when I got the letter from Enite saying I could return to Wisteria.
I'm excited too.
Hey, can I ask you something I've been curious about?
If it's something I can answer, of course.
Does the [em1]reason you became a florist[/em1] also have to do with the blue roses?
Hmm... I can't say it's unrelated.
Originally, flowers held [em1]no special meaning[/em1] to me.
I'd stepped on plenty, but I never had any particular feelings about them.
But when I saw that field of blue roses, I felt something for the first time.
That they were... incredibly beautiful.
It must have been an unforgettable moment for you.
Yes. At first, I thought I was under some kind of spell.
Although I never found a field of blue roses again after that day...
After I retired, I traveled searching for it, and I encountered many things.
I visited many villages and met many people.
And through that, I learned one thing.
Flowers aren't meaningful just because they're beautiful, but because [em1]people[/em1] use them for [em1]special occasions[/em1].
People give flowers during [em1]meaningful moments[/em1].
In joy, in sorrow, for comfort, for celebration, and for love... People give flowers to [em1]someone who matters[/em1].
I thought it was... a warm tradition.
As I mentioned before, I lived a rather shameful life for a long time, so I wanted to do something [em1]meaningful[/em1].
And that... was becoming a florist.
That's awesome, Roy.
Alright! I'd really like you to see the blue rose field before you leave, so I'll hurry things along!
Yes, thank you. I will be sure to inform you before I depart.
Okay, the finish line is in sight!
Let's go see [em1]Alvin[/em1] and make the [em1]rose Flower sculptures[/em1]!
Tada! Roy, look at this!
<shake>It's real</shake>... A field of blue roses.
It's truly, really... here before my eyes.
Just like that day...
Like a blue lake... the scent of clear water...
To think it was... this close all along.
There was a prickly vine core here. That's probably why you couldn't come here.
So, because the prickly vine core disappeared, the roses were able to bloom again?
Ah, no. Actually, I made this!
Hm?
They say true blue roses don't exist.
A witch who loved the color blue experimented with roses because she wanted to turn her favorite roses blue.
So what you saw back then was that [em1]witch's testing ground[/em1].
It took some work to find the recipe, but I finally did it.
Even I think they turned out really, really pretty. What do you think?
I was actually on my way to see the gold rosemary you found for me.
Huh? What's the matter with that?
This morning... another letter arrived.
My mentor's condition suddenly worsened...
It said he... [em1]passed away[/em1].
Wh... what?
R-Roy!
The first time I heard about my mentor's condition, it was from his family, not from him.
<shake>Why</shake>... didn't he tell me himself?
Before it got this bad... back when he first fell ill, just [em1]one letter[/em1] would have been enough.
He said... he thought of me as a son...
He gave me the [em1]pansy brooch[/em1], calling it a [em1]token for his son[/em1], the heart I'd saved...
Why then...
I, uh, maybe there was some... [em1]reason he couldn't contact you[/em1].
Did he... not truly think of me as his [em1]real son[/em1]?
I thought it was a miracle.
That's why it wouldn't wilt like ordinary flowers,
That it would stay unchanged, yesterday, today, tomorrow, and forever after...
I thought that as long as the blue rose didn't fade, my bond with my teacher would remain the same.
But it turns out even the blue roses were <shake>[em1]fake[/em1]</shake>.
I believed... flowers connected people.
So I believed this rose was connecting [em1]my father[/em1] and me...
No. He wasn't my father.
It was all my... [em1]delusion[/em1].
It was just... my own fantasy...
I thought by becoming a florist, I was building connections and helping others build theirs.
Was it really all just my imagination?
What was it that I believed in?
I don't even know what I was hoping for anymore...
<shake>I don't know</shake>.
I'm sorry you had to see me like this.
Roy, wait.
I should go.
Ellie, I know this isn't your fault.
I'm sure you were just looking out for me, as you always do, and trying to help.
So... I don't want to blame you.
You're someone I'm grateful to. I didn't want you to see me like this.
I don't want to be cruel to you...
So please, let me go.
[Stop him]
I'm sorry, Ellie.
[Let him go]
Hmm. Just as I thought, this is the perfect spot for a [em1]blue rose garden[/em1].
Should we get started on making the blue rose garden?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))] [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "EveryBluePotion_Name"))][/em1], [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RealFlowerPotion_Name"))][/em1], and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "PieceOfBlueRose_Name"))][/em1].
Alright, let's do this!
Fade out and summon Roy who fades in
I think this is it, but I'd better ask Roy.
Woah! It has ended up exactly the same as the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] describes.
Learning really fast, am I not?
Can't argue with that. You followed every movement of the marionette's, and the product looks fine.
Although it can be said that the marionette is the real manufacturer.
Hey, I also contributed!
At this rate, I can soon stop relying on the marionette, don't you think so?
<shake>Virgil!</shake>
It's at least 3 years too early for you to say that.
Roy, thank you for your congratulation letter!
Hi, Ellie. Glad to know that the letter arrived with no issue.
As I said in it, there's something I want to give to you in person. That's why I've bothered you with the trip.
Yup, I've come prepared. You won't catch me off guard this time.
Please take this then. It's a gift to celebrate the house restoration.
Whoa, it's a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Craft"))][/em1] [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] for making a sofa?
I've never received a gift like this pretty [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1]. Thank you!
Hm...?
Well... I heard that it's a tradition for witches that have restored a Witch's House to receive [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Furniture"))][/em1] [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] as gifts.
Have I been mistaken...?
No, no. I'm ignorant of traditions. That's all.
After all, Ellie doesn't have a master witch. No one is telling her about such [em1]traditions[/em1].
I see. In that case, it's only normal that you are not aware.
To be honest, I'm not so sure myself. I only heard about it once from a witch customer during my days in Highlion.
My apologies for not verifying the information. Shall I take it back and get you another gift instead?
Oh, my, please don't. I like it very much.
It's so sweet of you to have prepared it for me.
And it means a lot to me, since all witches learn carpentry at school.
I see. I'm glad it's not the wrong gift.
So I am. I'll craft a sofa with it as soon as possible, and when I'm done, I'll ask you over to try it out.
I look forward to it. Have a nice day then.
<wave>Huuufff...</wave>
Why a loud sigh all of a sudden? For a moment, I thought there was an earthquake.
Are you ready to pay the price of lying?
Virgil, how long do you think it will take if I make the sofa by following the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1]?
Well, based on your competence back at school... I'd say 2 years?
Virgil! My estimation is 1 year!
Good for you then, since that's equal to 3 apprenticeships only.
That's still too much time. Roy will have forgotten about this gift by the time I finish.
After that confident front you put up in front of him...
I know, I know... I don't want to admit it, but...
Carpentry is really not my thing.
You do realize that you can make the furniture as long as you follow the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1], don't you?
But Mom always says that I should use my imagination whatever I do. My hands just keep getting carried away by my imagination.
Yeah, you can only do woodworking properly when someone is on the side showing every single step to you.
Where can I possibly find someone like that?
If I am to name an expert in carpentry, Kyla.
I guess I'll have to become a formal apprentice if I want to learn from Kyla. She once said that she would have taken me as an apprentice if I were not a witch.
But all I need is a few pieces of advice. In other words, I need a top performer in carpentry?
Oh! How about I ask Diane?
Witches' Catalogue may provide such a service.
An apprentice witch using Witches' Catalogue to look for an instructor... If you had a master witch, she would have gone mad.
What service?
A service that can get me a carpentry instructor!
Look at this. Can you feel the craftsman's aura gathering in the [em1][lua(GetItemName("CopycatMarionette"))][/em1]?
Whenever someone infuses the marionette with aura, I feel like the marionette is about to come to life.
I can feel the urge to craft something, assumably because of the aura.
Of course you do. It's filled with the aura of great artisans.
Time for the final step: Put the marionette on the workbench and tell it what I want to make.
I will manage to make the furniture as long as I follow the marionette's movements.
How about checking the sofa [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Craft"))][/em1][em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Blueprint"))][/em1] Roy gave you? It might not go as planned.
That's what I was about to say.
Look, Virgil, Roy's written to congratulate me.
So, Kyla's told Roy about your restoring the Witch's House too.
I suppose so. And he says he has something for me... Will it be a gift?
He has given me a sudden gift before.
If he wants to hand it to you in person, it may be something fresh. Flowers, perhaps?
This time, I need to be mentally prepared for a gift.
...Oh. Hello.
Am I disturbing you?
Negative. What's the issue?
Oh, I want to ask you about something.
You’re on the way to Highlion, right?
Oh... it's just that you have a very rigid way of speaking.
Oh my. Old habits die hard, especially when one is deep in thought.
You sound like the janitor from my school.
Well, I used to be a soldier.
So, what brings you here?
What... <shake>huff, huff</shake>, why are you walking so fast?
Oh, sorry. I'm used to speed walking when delivering items.
Sorry for being inconsiderate. I'll slow down.
Let's... <shake>cough, cough</shake>... take a break here before we continue.
Why're you in such a hurry?
Because... trees last longer, but flowers can wither pretty fast.
And when I do deliveries at night, I'm usually anxious because it's getting late... It has become a habit.
Do you usually deliver items at night?
Not that often, but occasionally, yes.
I delivered items to Vinch's house several times too.
So this isn't the first time.
Yes, Vinch has placed many orders.
I think they were all paint materials. He said he liked to make his own paint.
It seems so. He always has much paint placed in front of his door.
He has also ordered several times flowers that only bloom at night.
But he's [em1]rarely at home[/em1] [em1]at night[/em1].
When he isn't, he will leave the [em1]window on the right[/em1] open for me to place the items there.
That's quite unusual. Don't people usually stay at home at night and go out during the day?
Phew, we can continue now.
Okay, I'll make sure to slow down this time.
Now it's way too slow!
Sorry, I kept thinking that I should slow down, and slowed down too much...
At this rate, the sun will set before we arrive!
If we walk around the School for Witches at this speed, we won't be able to visit every place in one day.
So the School for Witches is quite large.
So it is. There are many classrooms, the dormitory is huge, and the cafeteria is also magnificent.
The corridors are so long too... and there are locations with unique structures.
Good thing I won't get lost in Wisteria.
Yeah, it's a small village after all.
Ah, but the terrain may be more complicated than it seems.
As far as I know, there are [em1]houses with a basement[/em1] in the village too.
Alright, shall we continue then?
I'll match your speed this time, I promise.
By the way, it may be a sensitive question, but...
Have you seen any other woman around here?
You mean villagers?
No... It wasn't a familiar voice.
When I passed Vinch's house at midnight the other day, I felt like I heard [em1]a female voice[/em1].
But it can't be.
There are many trees around his house, so I might have mistaken.
Please forget it. I shouldn't have mentioned that.
We're almost there. Hang in there.
Oh, you two have come together?
Yes. Thanks to Ellie, I don't need to do two runs.
Ellie, I'll pitch a [em1]tray table[/em1] in the front. Please put the item on it.
Ellie? Where are you?
Put it on the [em1]tray table[/em1] before me.
Wow, there's a refreshing scent.
It's similar to the smell of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))].
Yes, and it's equally pacifying.
Besides flowers, I also have some saplings in my shop. Just ask me if you need them, Ellie.
Then, I'll deliver them now.
Huh? There're two trees?
Yeah, so I'm going to do two runs.
Isn't it exhausting?
It's okay. My highest delivery record at Highlion was ten trees.
I walk relatively fast, and I'm used to it. I can manage.
Shall I help you then?
Why? I'm really fine.
They are saplings, but since there's soil too, they can be a bit heavy, especially for you, Ellie.
Everyone would think I'm poor at weightlifting.
You look delicate after all.
I may not look strong, but I've lifted rocks in the temple. Carrying a tree is a walk in the park for me.
But remember to tell me some interesting stories on the way.
Interesting stories... I'm not a very expressive storyteller, so they may not sound interesting.
C'mon, you can simply tell me stories about your delivery trips.
Well... okay, but do tell me if you are tired.
We'll set out when you're ready.
Uh-oh! <shake>O-okay</shake>, this is not heavy at all!
I'm ready, Roy.
Okay, let's go then.
Whoa, Roy, that's amazing!
I didn't know that you can build a bridge like this.
There was a time...
when we sometimes needed such makeshift bridges when the river flooded.
I've also helped my farmer neighbors repair their bridges.
Was that before you started your flower shop?
It's not that strong or large, but it should be enough for you and Enite.
Thank you for your help, Ellie.
No problem! It benefits me as well.
Right, I hope it gets used often.
Hm? What's this thing doing here?
Maybe someone was trying to build a bridge?
Maybe. Let's check if the [em1]village bulletin board[/em1] says anything about it.
Is this what Roy mentioned in the letter?
Let me investigate the [em1]village bulletin board[/em1] like the letter says.
What's going on? Kyla never told me about it.
Roy! You want to talk about the village's bridges?
But Roy, shouldn't Kyla be responsible for bridge building?
Oh, so you've seen the bulletin.
Ellie, after you and Kyla restored that big bridge,
many villagers have returned, to Enite's delight.
She's so happy that she's been baking more pies than ever.
Enite is indeed a big fan of pies.
And a master in baking them.
She's baked a lot to share with everyone,
but it takes a large detour to cross the bridge and reach all the other homes from her place,
which is quite inconvenient.
Oh, it's indeed a long trip from Enite's house.
Yeah. Usually, Kyla would be the one to sort this out,
but her workload is already heavy, having to build the other bridge and all the houses.
So, I was thinking that I could do it myself if it was just a [em1]small bridge[/em1] for a couple of people at a time.
Un-huh? Did you run into any problem?
I got all the basic materials...
But when Kyla saw my bridge, she said that it wouldn't last long.
And she was right. I only ran back and forth on it a few times before it collapsed.
You aren't hurt, are you?
No, fortunately.
When Kyla found out, she laughed and said,
"One layer of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reaver_Collect_Name"))][/em1] from the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1] will be enough to enhance this bridge."
According to her, that ore can support the bridge
because it's quite enduring and can withstand wear and tear.
Therefore, I need someone to mine the ore for me.
And the person that came to my mind is our reliable Ellie.
Heh, just leave it to me. I can get you anything you want.
It's [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reaver_Collect_Name"))] that you want me to get?
Right, [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reaver_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1] would suffice. Thank you in advance.
Do you wish to give [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Reaver_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1] to Roy?
Ta-da, Roy! I've got the ore you need!
Thank you. I'll use it right away to build the bridge.
Please get me [em1]2 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reaver_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1].
There's a letter from Roy?
Oh, I've read about it at the village's bulletin board.
He says he wants to talk to me about the [em1]village's bridges[/em1].
He wants me to check out the [em1]village's bulletin board[/em1]. On my way then.
Amazing, you've brought so many.
I've heated up my oven so we can start making donuts at any time.
Are you ready, Roy?
I'm ready. Thank you for sparing me some time, Enite.
Well, aren't you a polite child! Let's start by making the dough.
That's right, you're doing well.
Now knead it into a ball of dough so we can stretch it into a thin sheet.
Put what Ellie has brought into the cream.
Sure, let me try that.
Once they're ready, you can put them in the oven to bake.
I'll teach you how to regulate the temperature.
It can't be too hot when you bake it and you must keep the temperature constant.
Hm, it already smells like the real deal.
Rubrum, come get ready to enjoy some donuts with Ellie.
Yes, Granny!
<wave>Donuts~ Donuts~ Rolly-polly pies~</wave>
Wow, is this a donut?
Looks so interesting! It's a pie but with a hole!
I'm going to dig in!
Me too~
Whoa...!
Is something wrong?
<wave>Delicious!</wave>
It's really delicious!
It's baked through evenly, no bitterness and just the right doneness.
The cream's very sweet and it's scrumptious.
Here, let me have a bite...
Oh... It really is delightful, I can't believe I made this.
You were a quick study. Just keep in mind what I said and you'll be making even better donuts.
You're too kind, it's thanks to both of you, Ellie and Enite.
Since they've turned out so well, you should take some home with you.
Granny, me, me, me! Me too!
Alright, alright. Hold on while I pack some for everyone.
Wow... You've packed so many for me, Enite.
Roy, when did you make this many?
I baked a few more since both you and Rubrum were enjoying them so much.
Is that why you were walking to and fro in front of the oven?
Yes. I thought making another batch would help me remember better.
Were there enough ingredients to make another batch?
I gathered enough ingredients while you were looking for the recipe.
I was only planning to make them by myself...
If not for you, Ellie, I wouldn't have gone to ask Enite.
Not at all, I've had such yummy donuts thanks to you.
Rubrum's also smiling from ear to ear.
Yes, I'm very pleased too.
Although I still have room for improvement, I'm glad everyone liked it so much.
Oh and here's a little token of my appreciation, Ellie.
I must be going. If you need any help, please let me know, Ellie.
Roy, are you okay?
Hello, Ellie! What's got you looking so flustered?
You must have seen the notice I put up then.
Was there a fire?
...Yeah, there was a fire, but it wasn't that serious.
I burnt something I was cooking. That was it.
Wow, I didn't know you could cook.
I've lived alone for a long time, so I do often cook for myself.
It's not a big deal.
Then what happened this time?
I wanted to try something different... and cooked it over too high a flame.
What were you trying to cook? Maybe I can help.
Do you know how to cook too, Ellie?
Nope! After I blew up the coal stove for the third time, Dad forbade me from stepping into the kitchen ever again.
But I found out why the first soup Dad ever made was forming green bubbles.
Now that I think about it, I think I'm a master problem solver.
I totally agree, because you've solved all the problems in our village, Ellie.
Hehe, so tell me all about it.
Well... Although it's a little embarrassing, this is what happened.
I actually wanted to bake donuts.
Donuts? Do you like donuts?
Yes. When I lived in Highlion, I used to go to a shop for their donuts daily.
Though it's great to be back in Wisteria, I still miss the taste of those donuts once in a while...
I've tried but never really succeeded in reproducing them.
Even though I did manage it after much effort, I couldn't lie to myself and say they were delicious.
I would have shared some with you if I had succeeded. It's such a shame.
Hm... How do you bake good donuts?
Don't worry about it, I'm sure I'll succeed someday as long as I keep at it.
But you want to eat it now, don't you?
Once in a while, I miss the food Dad and Mom used to make for me too.
If I'd known, I would have bugged Dad till he let me back into the kitchen!
That's how I feel sometimes.
The food... in your memories?
Yes, though it may not be exactly the same as what you ate in Highlion,
if you just want to bake tasty donuts, maybe someone here will know how to.
Roy, go on and prepare the ingredients for making donuts.
I'll go find you a recipe!
You really don't have to, Ellie. You must have a lot on your plate.
I'm just doing what a witch should.
But if you do make yummy donuts, be sure to leave one for me.
Alright then. It would be remiss of me to keep turning you down.
I'll leave it in your capable hands.
I will make sure I have the basic ingredients ready.
It's no rush at all.
Would you like to give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MapleHerb_Water_Name"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SilverStarFlower_Water_Name"))][/em1] to Roy?
Roy, I've brought you some ingredients!
Ingredients? I thought I was in charge of preparing the ingredients?
Enite told me about some ingredients perfect for adding to donuts.
Enite's looking for her recipe, so I'm here with the things.
I'm sorry to have bothered you so much.
Not at all. Let's go find Enite!
Enite told me to bring you to her along with the ingredients.
Sounds like she did locate the recipe.
Sure, let's go then.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FullBagByEllie"))][/em1]
Roy said this was the flower he found when he was on the brink of life and death.
It's amazing how it looks as fresh as if it just bloomed yesterday.
He said it's [em1]very precious[/em1] to him, so I shouldn't mess around with it.
This must be the [em1]book Roy mentioned[/em1].
Okay, let's... take a look.
The Tongue of Flowers
Rosemary
A woman who threw herself into a pond in her sorrow once said
"There is rosemary for [em1]remembrance[/em1]."
"Pray, love, remember."
"And [em1]please, do not forget me.[/em1]"
People remembered that woman for a very, very long time.
The woman who left this world, her arms full of rosemary.
Hmm... The Black Cat God mentioned "[em1]ever-blooming[/em1] flowers'.
The clue must be in one of the [em1]flowers[/em1] from this book.
And it has to be [em1]artificial[/em1], right?
Don't tell me you're planning to make it yourself?
If it were just a gift, maybe... But this is for the Cat God, so it has to be well-made.
Oh, that's it! [em1]Alvin[/em1] is really skilled!
Let's find out what the '[em1]ever-blooming[/em1] flower' is and ask Alvin to make it.
A monk from a distant continent climbed a mountain to rest and briefly fell asleep.
In his dream, he encountered a flower with a powerful scent unlike any he had ever known.
The fragrance was so profound and beautiful that the monk became desperate to find it.
He searched and searched for the flower, but could not find it before he awoke.
Upon waking, the monk named the unknown flower '[em1]Immortality[/em1]' and searched for it endlessly.
Even when his hair turned white, he could not forget the scent that lingered in his heart.
A god fell in love with a beautiful youth.
The god adored the youth and was always by his side, until one day duty called him away.
Another god, jealous of their love, transformed into a boar and took the youth's life.
And so, the youth's name became the god's eternal, [em1]sorrowful memory[/em1].
A pair of twins fell in love with the same person.
Realizing this, they were tormented.
Their bond was too deep to choose love, yet their love was too deep to choose bond.
In the end, they made the same choice, becoming trees intertwined as if [em1]embracing[/em1] one another.
They comforted each other, saying that [em1]being intoxicated by love[/em1] is a bittersweet fate.
Close the book
Let's pray.
I was just thinking about you. It's good to see you.
Oh? What about me?
Do you remember that flower legend I told you about before?
I remember. It was about the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))][/em1], right?
Why do you ask about the legend?
I was wondering if you might be interested in other flower legends?
Hmm... Well, I hadn't really thought about it before you mentioned them.
In that case, could you spare a moment for me?
Do you have another interesting story?
Yes, a story I'd like to tell, if you're willing to listen.
You know, you seem really interested in legends and such, Roy.
Is there a special reason?
Well... Partly it's for recommending flowers to customers, but...
This is a bit off topic, but...
Do you have any [em1]treasured possessions[/em1], Ellie?
Hmm. Let's see... The boots from my mom, or the fountain pen my dad gave me for my birthday?
Oh, and I treasure Virgil, in my own way.
I doubt you know the meaning of the word.
Hey, name another witch who looks after her hat as well as I do!
I see. Those are all wonderful things.
I have something like that, too.
I don't normally show it to anyone, but...
Since it's you, Ellie, the one who helped me return to the village and open this shop. I think it would be okay to show you.
What is it? What is it?
I've left it in my room, so I'll need to go get it.
Would you mind waiting inside the shop for a moment?
I understand. Please let me know if you change your mind.
That was when I told you about the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))][/em1].
Would you accompany me to the temple to ask about the flower that bloomed there?
We can meet the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1] during the [em1]day[/em1], so it would be best to go to the temple together then.
Right, the Black Cat God can be seen during the [em1]day[/em1].
Roy! I've brought the sculpture of the [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1].
It's incredibly detailed and looks just like the real thing.
Right? I had Alvin make it.
You've gone through so much trouble. Thank you.
I've also picked the freshest pansies to make a bouquet.
Shall we go to the temple together?
Great, let's go to the temple.
Time to bring Alvin's [em1]flower sculpture[/em1].
This flower is the one that [em1]was so special[/em1] to me.
Is this... a [em1]blue rose[/em1]?
I've never seen a blue rose before!
I imagine not. They're not a common sight.
If they're so rare, how did you get one, Roy?
This flower... I [em1]found it during the war[/em1].
I had a [em1]teacher[/em1] in the army, someone I looked up to like a father.
He helped me become a soldier, with no strings attached.
He's also a comrade I served with for a long time.
My teacher and I once faced a [em1]life and death[/em1] situation during the war.
And what helped us survive that ordeal... was this very [em1]blue rose[/em1].
You must have taken really good care of it.
It's still so fresh... How old is it?
It was before the prickly vines appeared, and I left the village...
In fact, it was long before I first settled in Wisteria.
And it hasn't wilted?
No. It's a miracle.
Wow, that sounds like something out of a legend.
Haha... yes. I didn't mean to talk about myself so much, but... it is.
We survived, but my teacher lost a leg in that battle...
He was discharged soon after. I left not long after that, too.
As I said, my teacher is like a father to me, so I've kept sending [em1]letters[/em1].
He is always a stoic person, so I've only ever received one reply.
However, none of my letters have been returned, so I believe he's doing well.
I always live by the saying "no news is good news."
So, the reason you're interested in legends... is because of what happened back then?
Yes. That, and I'd like to have something interesting to write to my teacher.
My daily life isn't very special, so I share those stories as a way of keeping in touch.
I bet he's really happy every time he gets a letter from you.
Actually... That's why I have a favor to ask you, Ellie.
I'd like to send the [em1]flower from the temple[/em1] to my teacher.
But to do that, I think I'd need permission from the [em1]Cat God[/em1]...
They haven't appeared to me during my prayers.
I heard that you were instrumental in restoring the temple.
So I thought if you came with me, the Cat God might be more inclined to answer.
Oh, that was nothing, really.
If that's all, I'm sure the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1] will give us permission.
Will you come with me now?
Alright. Please let me know when you have the time.
But we have to go during the [em1]day[/em1] to see the Black Cat God.
Understood. Then let's meet during the day.
Y-you really are... the Black Cat God.
Greetings, Black Cat God. I'm Roy, the florist from the village.
I've run the flower shop there for years... I wonder if you might remember.
Hello, Black Cat God!
If it's alright... may I take a few blossoms from your temple?
Life always demands an equal price.
If you wish to claim the promised flower, offer instead an [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1].
Huh? That doesn't even exist!
Present it among the [em1]living flowers[/em1], and make your offering.
The living flowers bloom [em1]in the heart[/em1].
Do this, and the promised flower will be yours.
Could you maybe explain that in... fewer riddles?
And just like that, gone again...
The [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1]...
If a flower like that existed, don't you think we'd have found it by now?
There might be a [em1]hidden meaning[/em1].
If we think simply...
Perhaps it means an [em1]artificial flower[/em1].
But that's just a [em1]fake flower[/em1], isn't it?
True, but is still a flower that never fades.
And since the god stressed it must be offered among the [em1]living flowers[/em1]...
Maybe it means the opposite. It's simply [em1]not alive[/em1].
Hm... that does make sense.
But even if it's an artificial flower, there are way too many kinds.
I have a book that lists the [em1]meanings of flowers[/em1].
If we study it, it might point us in the right direction.
Besides the [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1],
the so-called [em1]living flower[/em1] is likely a riddle too...
What could be the living flower blooming [em1]in the heart[/em1]... <shake>Ah!</shake>
Did something come to mind?
That [em1]brooch[/em1] on your chest! Isn't it shaped like a flower?
You're right. Ah... [em1]a flower on the heart[/em1].
But it's still not a real, living flower.
The brooch's shaped like a [em1]pansy[/em1]...
If I make a [em1]pansy bouquet[/em1], it might work.
But what if we're wrong? All this is just guesswork.
Even if we are, the Black Cat God will see the effort.
Alright. Then I'll track down what that the [em1]ever-blooming flower[/em1] might be.
Let me get my book.
I'll put this [em1]book[/em1] at my [em1]flower shop[/em1]. Feel free to check it anytime.
Ugh... Book...
N-nope! Anyway, good luck with your part!
Thank you, Ellie. Truly.
Once you're ready, come find me.
Did it work?
Yes. Thank you, Ellie. It's all thanks to you.
You know... You really are very reliable.
Reliable? Her?
Zip it, Virgil.
Haha, Ellie is more reliable than you think.
At your age, I was still completely [em1]lost[/em1].
Really? You were?
Embarrassing as it is, yes.
I relied on a few kind souls...
But until I met my teacher, I was wasting my life.
How did you meet your teacher?
I tried to steal his wallet.
What?! Seriously?
I told you, my past wasn't exactly proud.
I became a soldier because he was one. I wanted to follow him.
Oh... I thought there was some great destiny behind it.
Ellie... What does family mean to you?
My mom and dad taught me what love is.
What it feels like, how to show it.
I love them so, so much.
My teacher is that person for me.
When I was caught stealing...
He could have handed me over to the guards, but he didn't.
Instead, he told me I had quick reflexes and a strong build, and that I could choose another life.
And that's how you became a soldier.
He was strict, but always there for me.
When I struggled to fit into the regiment...
When I couldn't sleep from the pain of training...
He was always the first to offer me comfort and support.
I think I get it.
Family doesn't have to be tied by blood. Right?
Yes. To me, he is [em1]like a father[/em1].
Speaking of which, I've always wondered...
That [em1]pansy brooch[/em1] you always wear. What's the story behind it?
Ah, this? It was his gift.
He gave it to me when he retired.
Said it represents the heart I'd saved, and is a token for his son.
He wasn't a man who smiled often, but that day, he put it on me... with a shy smile.
Wow...
It's amazing how you and he became family.
And you plan to give the flower from the temple to him, right?
I hope this one reaches him.
As do I. Thank you.
Forgive me, I've gone on too long about myself.
Don't be! I'm glad I got to know you better.
Then I'm glad, too. I've enjoyed this time with you, Ellie.
Oh, here's a bouquet I made to thank you.
Oh wow, it's another pansy bouquet!
Yes. I picked the freshest, most beautiful ones, just like the ones I prepared for the Black Cat God.
By the way, Roy, remember that blue rose you showed me?
Why not display it in your shop?
Hm? Why do you ask?
I think it would look great in a bouquet.
It'd be happier among other flowers than alone.
Besides, if it has brought you luck before, you should keep it close.
True... then I'll place it [em1]near the counter[/em1], where the sun can shine over it.
I spend most of my time in the shop anyway. I'll be able to watch over it.
I can watch it all the time and keep it from wilting.
And I wish the same for you, Ellie, that happiness and good fortune are always by your side.
Support
I can always trust and depend on mom and dad.
Sure, sometimes mom stirs up trouble and dad has to fix it, but still...
Love and frustration
Sometimes, families fight over the smallest things.
Things can get hairy when conflicts arise...
Alright, let's try summoning the Black Cat God.
If I pray here...
Black Cat God! I've brought what you asked for!
Which bouquet should I give to the Cat God?
Here's the bouquet you asked for!
Huh? Why is there no response?
Seems that wasn't what the Cat God wanted.
Well... guess we'll have to try again.
I'll prepare the bouquet, and you can come back anytime.
I should go back to the [em1]flower shop[/em1] and study the [em1]tongue of flowers[/em1] again.
Is... is this wrong too?
You who control both life and death...
No flower can bloom for a hundred days.
Now, the ever-blooming flower and the living flower stand together.
You may take the promised flower.
Really? So they agreed, right?
Yes, I believe so.
Woohoo! Thank you, Black Cat God!
Thank you, Black Cat God.
Leave
Hm... maybe I should head back to the village and rethink this.
Sorry, Black Cat God. I'll return again.
What's wrong, Ellie?
I don't think this offering was the right one.
I'll prepare again.
Do you like this color?
It looks good, thanks to you.
I don't think Enite needs help with her task, but you can drop by if you're concerned.
I just picked the colors.
Making choices is the hardest part. You were a big help.
Ahem, I'm flattered.
Now that it's decorated like this, it really feels like a stage.
It surely does. Now, we just need some illumination and comfortable seats.
I've got a plan on those. Can you entrust them to me?
Sure, I just helped a little.
By the way, Enite, Arden and Arin are in charge of food preparation, right?
I wonder if it's going smoothly!
Enite is a trustworthy cook, but...
I don't know Arin well, so I can't say anything about her, but... Arden's dishes are nice I suppose?
They are... They just lack variety.
Now that it has come to my mind, I should check on them. Hang in there, Roy!
Okay, thank you, Ellie.
Wow, I'd expect nothing less from Kyla. This is a full-fledged stage.
Kyla told me that she'd finished repairing, so I was going to decorate the stage.
I heard from Kyla on my way here
that you were in two minds.
I've picked the style and locations... but not the colors.
Ah, but don't worry. After all, we've decided to let you rest this time.
Come on. It's just picking colors. I can help you with that.
But wouldn't it take up your time?
But in other words, it means I get the right to choose the color scheme for the decoration!
You can have more rights than that, since we wouldn't have had access to this place if it weren't for you.
Okay, can you choose with me then?
I'm wondering what colors the curtains and carpet should be.
Ellie, what color do you prefer?
It's refreshing and nice-looking. I like it too.
Just a minute.
I guess most people would think of that  when it comes to a stage.
Green
It suits our village well.
Welcome, guys.
I can't play any musical instrument, so I prepared some flower petals for scattering.
Wow, you're going to scatter petals as you march?
Yes, I once saw a brass band doing so.
Next up is [em1]Arden[/em1]!
But I wonder if Arden will agree to join the march.
He will! Because Arden has a warm heart!
At least... the fire he breathes is warm for sure.
A long time ago, a man lived in the village.
In a very distant village, there was a woman he loved dearly.
They often met in the forest because of fierce opposition from their parents.
Oh... Was this a forbidden love?
Sounds like everything forbidden looks good to you, huh.
Of course not! I'm just a hopeless romantic!
One day, the man was delayed by some business in the village, and the woman encountered a wild beast while waiting for him.
She was wounded and fell to her death from the cliff while trying to run away.
After the man arrived, he saw the torn clothes and blood and was filled with self-reproach for having come too late.
Evening primroses began flowering where the woman fell.
The man would climb the cliff every night at the same time to pray, until the evening primroses wilted.
When the flowers wilted, he confessed his longing for her, and jumped off the cliff.
The Cat Gods, taking pity on him, went to the place he fell from.
Rosemarys that gave off golden moonlight began flowering in that same spot thereafter.
That's so tragic...
But of all things, why did they turn into flowers?
Although flowers can't speak,
people often assign them meanings.
This part's a little [em1]crumpled[/em1].
Didn't expect you to be so engrossed in a book.
I've always been a very empathetic person, okay?
Not you, I mean Roy.
Oh, it's here.
Since we've learnt about the contents of the legend, let's ask around the village.
Maybe it was to pass this message on.
*Sticks out head trying to see the evening primroses on the cliff*
Curious Blooms Around the World
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))]
The flower's said to bloom at night.
Here we are!
It's really so close to the moon.
The man must have prayed here for a very long time...
It still sounds really tragic to me...
Since when were you so emotional?
There's something from a tragic love story that I can't describe!
Mom said she became more considerate after she met Dad.
Dad said that he began to take better care of himself.
The two in the legend could have been just as happy, right?
It's hard to say for sure when it comes to humans.
I've got to hold it carefully so I don't spoil it.
It's definitely going to be really close to the moon at night.
Wow, we can really pluck it now we've brought evening primrose with us.
Of course the legend's rooted in fact.
It smells heavenly...
What's Roy going to use it for?
Let's show it to Roy.
It's a legend from the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] about a certain flower.
I'll come by sometime to listen to you tell it.
Of course, feel free to come by anytime.
It's said that a type of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] rosemary only blooms in the [em1]spot closest to the moon[/em1].
What makes it more special is that people can only see its [em1]golden flowers[/em1] at [em1]night[/em1].
After learning of this legend, I began keeping a lookout for it whenever I went to the forest.
But it's not that easy to find.
I don't think I've seen that kind of flower.
According to the legend, you need to bring some [em1]evening primroses[/em1] to pluck the petals of the flowers.
If you can bring me some, I'll make it into a permanent [em1]decorative item[/em1] for you.
It'll be a gift in lieu of the construction fees I owe you.
I see you haven't given up trying to pay me.
Just... kidding.
How's your search for the Gold Rosemary?
I've left the [em1]Compendium of Legends[/em1] in my flower shop. Feel free to take a look anytime.
Do you wish to give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))][/em1] to Roy?
Oh yes, I just remembered something. Would you like to hear about it?
Speaking of interesting things, I just remembered something. Would you like to hear about it?
Would you like to hear about a legend?
Roy, I've brought you [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))]!
You... you really found it.
Where did you find it?
On a cliff connected to the caves.
It was really very close to the moon.
I've found the path. If you're interested, go have a look, Roy.
Yes, I've been wanting to look for it myself.
Now let me make this into a decoration for you.
One second.
Sorry to keep you waiting.
Wow, how did you do it?
I tried a method that was popular in Highlion.
I've preserved it in clean water using a special technique so it will last.
Because you got rid of the prickly vines in the village, Ellie.
I went ahead of time to get water from the lake by the Bitter Grape Tea Tree.
Awww, you're making me shy.
She just did it without thinking about anything other than legends and great adventures.
I think it's quite Ellie-ish and cool.
Though I've said it before, but thank you, Ellie.
It's all thanks to you that I could return here.
If you need any flowers or help, please let me know anytime.
Sure, take care.
Who knows if you'll find more legends?
Best of luck to you.
Standing over there reminded me of that legend and I felt so sad.
I see... so who did you find more pitiful, Ellie?
The man
The woman
He must have been very sad to only hear that the woman had passed away after so long...
Because he couldn't do anything to save her.
Is that so...
Don't you think so, Roy?
Well, at least the man could pray.
She died an unjust death, and didn't even see the person she wished to see.
It was too late when he heard.
Yes... that indeed was regrettable.
But I need to thank you, Ellie. You gave me the chance to see an item from the legends in the flesh.
Do you think the woman's situation was more pitiable, Roy?
Yes, because a dead person can't do anything.
Maybe you can ask someone familiar with the forest.
I think some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DryEveningPrimrose_Name"))][/em1] was sandwiched in the pages of the [em1]book[/em1].
Please come to the [em1]flower shop[/em1] in a bit, I'll be sure to locate the [em1]book[/em1].
Hmm, so going back to what we were discussing,
Do bring [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "GoldRosemary_Name"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DryEveningPrimrose_Name"))][/em1] with you.
Good day to you, Roy!
You've come at the perfect time. I have something for you.
Hm? What's this? Why are you giving me Gold Coins out of the blue?
I heard that you helped to rebuild the house.
This is your payment, don't think too much of it.
Though you're telling me not to overthink, this is a really generous sum!
Besides, I didn't do it for the money.
I understand, but you put a lot of effort into it...
<shake>No, no!</shake>This is still far too much!
But I put this aside for you...
If I was after money, I'd have asked you to begin with!
But you deserve it...
<shake>No thank you!!!</shake>
I'll give you this then, to thank you for stopping me from taking off my shoes on the train, Roy.
That's hardly a good proposition for you.
<shake>Just take it!</shake>
Alright then, but I'd still like to give you something to show my appreciation.
Wow, now you're just being stubborn.
Has Ellie Blueriver finally met her match?
Uh... In that case...
Oh, you lived elsewhere before coming to Wisteria, Roy?
If you know anything interesting, do let me know.
Hm... I don't know if it's interesting, but I can answer any of your questions about the forest and plants.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))]
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "Pompom_Name"))]
Cloudflower
Ask about all of them.
Have you heard of an adorable bird that lives in [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Deep"))][/em1]?
Because it's a [em1]nocturnal animal[/em1], it's always asleep in the day.
Amongst them, there's a little fellow with [em1]spots[/em1] on its rear.
It came to me because I was carrying a lantern.
Go to [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Plateau"))][/em1] and climb up the [em1]vines[/em1]. You will reach a [em1]high spot[/em1].
There's a flower that's [em1]gigantic and strange[/em1].
Because that was my first time seeing it myself, I'm not too sure what it was,
but it should be safe to take a closer look.
I often saw a [em1]bird with a flower blooming on its head[/em1] when I walked around in [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))].
It is very sensitive to movement and will fly away when approached,
but if you release it when the flower on its head is blooming, you'll be able to keep the flower.
It's said that the flower has many uses in medicine or in tea.
Oho... I've got to write this down in my [em1]notebook[/em1].
Is this your notebook?
Yes. It's handy for writing down all kinds of things.
I see. I often see witches using them... They look very useful.
W-well... I'll take a look then...
If that's the case, I will.
Let's walk around and take another look at the [em1]Plump Bird[/em1].
What's taking so long!
Have you packed everything?
Oh yes, I said I wanted to bring some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DryEveningPrimrose_Name"))][/em1].
Let's bring some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DryEveningPrimrose_Name"))][/em1].
Of course it's impossible to go empty-handed.
I think Roy said that we needed some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DryEveningPrimrose_Name"))].
Look, I brought it.
Still, thank you for your help.
Roy.
Have you delivered your speeeeecial order?
Hi, Ellie. Here's your payment.
Wow, thank you, Roy.
This is too much. All I did was collecting some materials.
No, you deserve this much.
It's nothing compared to what the Countess paid me.
Is it? Thank you then.
Speaking of which!
Roy, the Countess is actually your patron. <shake>That's amazing!</shake>
You [em1]promised[/em1] to tell me in details, right?
Details... I don't know how detailed it will be, but I'll try.
Yeah! Go ahead!
Alright. It was soon after I opened my first shop...
The Countess was the first to use my service.
As there were already many large flower shops in Highlion, my shop chiefly provided small potted plants good for home decoration.
Sounds like your shop wasn't so big, Roy?
No, but it was in a nice location.
The Countess learned about my shop by accident.
Her butler apparently bought some potted plants from my shop as gifts, and she found them satisfying.
That was how she started to frequent my shop. That's it.
I was hoping to hear gossips about the Count's family and their secret conspiracies.
For example, a detective-story-like adventure where you and the Countess worked together to find clues and solve puzzles!
There was nothing like that...
Ellie, quit the unrealistic imagination.
Roy is just an ordinary flower shop owner.
Humph! It won't hurt to be imaginative.
Sorry for letting you down.
When in Highlion, I was as busy as a bee all the time,
but there were also incidents I would remember fondly and be grateful about.
You don't plan to go back, do you?
You're needed here in the village, Roy! And we've just become friends.
Don't worry, Ellie. I don't plan to go back.
I was just recalling it briefly.
Is there anything else you'd like to know?
Hmm... Nope.
If so, take this.
You said that you wanted to see the flower basket, Ellie...
So I made another one with the same materials.
It's a few flowers short, but the overall structure is the same as the Countess's flower basket.
But you paid me just now.
That's payment from the Countess. This is payment from me.
Wow, can I really have it?
Thank you so much, Roy!
Now I feel like being a countess myself!
You were a great help. You deserve it.
Roy, just let me know whenever you need help again!
Roy, I heard that you got an order from Highlion, so I'm here to help you.
What? Oh, you saw the poster?
Yeah. I needed some help, so I put up a poster.
So! Just tell me about the situation.
The Countess, a patron of mine, placed a special order for her daughter's engagement ceremony.
<shake>The Countess?! Engagement ceremony?! Special order?!</shake>
Ellie, aren't you a bit too excited?
How can I stay calm when you mentioned three catchy keywords in one single sentence?
Ellie... I know what you're curious about. I'll tell you about it later.
You will? It's a promise then. I won't forget it.
Now, I'll tell you about the request: I hope you could gather some flowers for me.
I've got most of the flowers and materials, and can get to work, but...
This elegant flower basket needs one more material, which will be the jewel in the crown.
Namely, [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))][/em1]. I probably need 3 of them.
Is [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))][/em1] the flower growing on top of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "FlowerBird_Name"))][/em1]s?
Yes, considering the size of this flower basket I'm making, [em1]3[/em1] of them should suffice.
It's a special collected item... so I think I should leave it to a professional.
Leave it to me, Roy. I'll get them for you right away.
Thank you. Until you return, I'll be handling my unfinished work.
Do you wish to give [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1] to Roy?
Roy, I've brought you the [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1].
Ellie, great timing.
How's your work going?
It must be a deluxe flower basket since it's ordered by the Countess?
Yeah... It's for the engagement ceremony of the Count's daughter, so it necessarily is much more elegant than average flower baskets.
But Her Excellency seems to want more than elegance.
Does she? So the special order really is special.
I always do my best to deliver every single order, and haven't pondered over them too much, but...
Her Excellency said that she liked my works because she always found peace of mind on seeing those flowers.
Peace of mind?
Yup. She places one order every month, saying that my flower arrangements are different from those that only value elegance.
It feels like bragging when I say it myself... It's embarrassing.
C'mon, it's a well-deserved compliment.
<wave>You're amazing.</wave>
The Countess appreciates your abilities, Roy.
The nobles are usually demanding. It's a proof that you know your stuff!
Please stop. I'm getting really awkward.
Anyway, now that I've got all the materials, I can start working.
Is there anything else I can help with?
No, I‘m good.
I wish I can see how the Countess's flower basket looks.
I'm afraid you may not see the finished product.
I plan to finish it this midnight and have it delivered at once, so that the flowers will still be fresh.
Sigh... That's a shame.
Still, it wouldn't have been possible without your help.
A friend of Aurea will come to fetch the flower basket and bring me my payment early tomorrow morning.
So, you can come to get your payment tomorrow.
Alright, Roy. I'll get out of your way then.
However! You should tell me about the whole thing as promised!
Ellie, please collect [em1]3 [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "FlowerBird_Collect_Name"))]s[/em1] for me.
Sorry if it sounds like I'm impatient. I am not.
It's okay, Roy. I'll be back soon.
Good day to you, Roy! I heard you were selling furniture too.
Welcome to my shop, Ellie. Yes, I'm planning to sell [em1]potted plants[/em1] and other [em1]decorative plants[/em1].
Though they may not count as furniture, plants are good decorations. Placing plants in your home can really change the atmosphere.
The plants I sell don't have any theme. [em1]Each single unit[/em1] is unique.
I'll pick the fresh plants of the day to sell and my offerings will [em1]change daily[/em1].
If you would like the products offered to stay the same, please let me know. I'll sell the same things for [em1]3 days[/em1].
I'd be very grateful if you shop here often.
Ellie, I've nearly finished my part.
Could you handle the rest?
Hi, Roy!
Hello, Ellie. How may I help you today?
I'm here for something else.
I've finally made up my mind to say this: I've been worrying about you since that day.
Actually, I've wanted to apologize this whole time...
No, I am the one who should apologize, for having left you there.
It doesn't matter! And you were injured because of my reckless action.
It's okay. You just wanted to help. I understand.
I know it...
Sorry, I want to talk to you, but I need to get back to work.
What? Wait, Roy!
He's gone. He looked like his usual self, didn't he...?
He isn't as upset as we imagined. Isn't that good news?
No, that is weird. He was acting like nothing happened.
He cherishes them so much: the memories of his teacher, and the blue rose field.
He was so sad. Seeing him acting cool only worries me more.
What's there to worry about now that he's back to his usual self?
That is the problem! My sixth sense says so!
If it concerns you that badly, try to talk to him again.
But he avoided me just now. He may keep acting that way.
Shall I talk to Roy right now?
Alright, Roy's returning to the flower shop.
Once he's in the shop, he's cornered!
I must hear his true feelings this time!
I'd better come again later.
Why, you're scared?
I'm not! I should finish the tasks at hand to make time for such a serious talk.
I'll come see Roy later.
Sorry, Ellie, but I've still got work to do.
I feel like he's still avoiding me...
By "that day," do you mean the day at the [em1]blue rose field[/em1]?
Sorry, I was being inconsiderate.
And nothing about the flower shop looks out of the norm. Was I overthinking?
Wait, the [em1]blue rose[/em1] is gone. He used to cherish it so much!
Everything's so normal that it's abnormal!
Roy, let's talk!
Ellie? What do you want to talk about? If it's not urgent, I...
<shake>It's urgent! It's an emergency!!</shake>
What is it...?
Where's your blue rose?
<shake>Roy!</shake>
I've discarded it.
What? Why? It was so important to you.
Because it was a fake. There's no point in keeping it.
But it carried your cherished memories with your teacher!
Maybe I was the only one who cherished those memories.
If he really considered me family, he wouldn't have made me a soldier.
Yet like an idiot, I wore the pansy brooch he gifted me.
Roy, please, it's not like you to say such things.
And what are things it's "like me" to say?
Such ideas are just like that blue rose. They are make-believes. Paths you believe, relations you believe, and even miracles... None of them is real.
I don't think so!
They say that witches help those in their reach.
I know you're a nice person, Ellie, but you don't need to help me just because it's a witch's principle.
Wait, I'm not helping you because it's a witch's principle. I just...
That's very arrogant of you, don't you think?
No, I didn't mean to look down on you, Ellie.
We shouldn't have talked about this. We should have just chatted like usual.
I'm sorry, but please leave me for today.
W-wait, Roy! I haven't finished...
He threw me out.
I'm doing this not as a witch, but as Roy's friend.
I'm just trying to help a friend...
Don't linger on it. It might simply have been a bad time.
Where could Roy have discarded the [em1]blue rose[/em1]?
Told you not to linger on it.
I can't help it! Roy was so happy when he talked about the blue rose.
He can't have thrown away a flower that important.
What's the point of finding it when he has said he doesn't want it?
That's all the more reason to find it. Someone may have seen it.
I'll [em1]ask[/em1] the [em1]villagers[/em1] if they've seen Roy going anywhere with the blue rose!
You do take after your mother. Go ahead then.
I've never seen Roy that shaken.
If only I could do something for him...
I must do something or it's over.
I think I've asked everyone?
Basically.
Dana says that Roy was carrying [em1]a shovel and a watering can[/em1].
Rex said that Roy went [em1]into the depth of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))][/em1].
Where exactly is the depth of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))]?
Wasn't there a path that leads inside?
You mean the place we planted the blue rose field?
It's where the prickly vine core used to be. Let's go!
Wait, where's my blue rose field!
What are those white shards in the corner?
Who did it? Don't tell me it was Roy.
Wait, there's one [em1]blue rose[/em1] left.
It can be plucked, but the magic dye is permanent.
Here it is, in the bush. And the color has faded.
It may have disappeared, like it never existed.
Isn't it called the [em1]"flower of miracle and the impossible"[/em1]? No wonder it can't be found.
[em1]A shovel and a watering can[/em1]. These should be the tools Dana witnessed.
Which means this is the [em1]blue rose[/em1] that Roy took?
But why is this one still blue when others have faded?
You remember what Roy said before? About a flower field's disappearance?
Yeah, he discovered a blue rose field on the battlefield, but when he went back later, it was gone.
The disappearances could have shared the same cause, although I don't know what.
Do [em1]fields of blue roses always disappear[/em1]?
Maybe that's why they're called the [em1]flower of miracle and the impossible[/em1].
But the one Roy picked up isn't gone.
The blue rose field is gone, but [em1]this one blue rose remains.[/em1]
Perhaps [em1]Roy's feeling[/em1] has reshaped this blue rose?
What does that even mean?
Roy already knew that this flower was fake.
He could have thrown it away, but instead, he took it to the blue rose field and tried to plant it.
Roy was unwilling to let it go. Maybe that feeling of his has kept this rose.
That's just what you think.
But I want to believe it. That this blue rose has remained is a [em1]miracle[/em1] in itself, isn't it?
Alright, I'll go to [em1]Roy[/em1] again.
I have his shovel and watering can. I've got a good reason to see him!
Em, what was it again?
Let me drop a hint: the battlefield and the blue roses.
Oh, you mean the incident where he discovered a blue rose field on the battlefield, but when he went back later, it was gone?
Roy doesn't seem to be at home.
Is he away?
We'll put the shovel and watering can down and wait then.
And look around the [em1]flower shop[/em1] as well.
(sniff) I think I know that smell.
It's a food you've eaten.
It's Enite's pie! <wave>Smells like heaven~</wave>
And there's a note too?
I hope you're not hurting anywhere. Have this and cheer up.
Everyone's worried about you. Best wishes.
She baked a pie to cheer Roy up?
I hope he gets well again after eating it.
There are some letters in the box.
That's a good deal of letters, and they're all addressed to Roy?
Some look quite old. Has he kept all of them?
You aren't supposed to read someone else's letter.
I know, but these all seem to be letters of encouragement.
They may shed light on how to help Roy.
You simply want to satisfy your curiosity.
I'm really doing it for Roy's sake!
I'll take a quick glimpse.
A Letter Pressed Hard
Good sir of the flower shop, greetings!
Thank you for all those bouquets you make me each time!
My stay at the hospital would have been boring and lonely if your flowers hadn't been here to company me. I really love them!
I want to recover as soon as possible and open a flower shop just like you!
There seem to be more letters.
An Elegant-looking Letter
Mr. Roy, your flower arrangement has once again surpassed my expectations.
The flowers, wisely picked and gorgeously arranged, matched the party perfectly.
It delighted me to see people chatting cheerfully by the flowers.
If I'm not mistaken, the tongue of the main flower is "bright hope"? I'm always impressed by the silent care your works carry.
If I need to order more flowers, I'd like to order them from you again.
A Neat Letter
Mr. Roy! Thank you for the flowers you recommended last time.
They gave me the courage to confess my feelings to the girl I love.
She accepted with a smile, saying that my flowers were too pretty for her to turn me down.
Your flowers do have the power to touch people's hearts! I mean it!
Please keep enlightening me! Thank you so much!
That's all.
All the letters express gratitude for Roy.
I think he usually puts them away. Why has he dug them out?
Maybe he's going to throw them away?
That'd be a pity...
Are these all orders?
It'd be way too much work if they were all new orders.
Maybe he accepted all the orders he received?
No wonder he's been busier than usual.
Working may be his only means to take his mind off things.
I hope he won't tire himself out.
This flower has wilted.
Roy usually takes good care of every single flower. What's going on?
Flowers are very delicate.
Show the slightest sign of neglect and they will wilt.
Will it revive if I give it plenty of water?
Too much water can kill it too...
O-of course I know that!! I'm a witch!
Don't you ever try to grow flowers.
He's probably got something on his mind.
I don't think Roy is seeing it.
How much the villagers care about him, and how much the customers appreciate his service.
What can a person see when he keeps staring at the ground?
Just a dark shadow. He wants to see nothing but the shadow.
But Roy's surrounded by so many people. His teacher isn't the only one.
There's got to be something we can do for Roy.
Wait, I think I heard someone coming.
...Ellie, there you are. I was looking for you.
I was rude. I want to apologize again.
I'm terribly sorry for what happened before.
Ah, it's okay! Don't worry about it. No hard feelings at all!
I see... By the way, Ellie, what are you doing here?
I'm here to return your shovel and watering can.
Oh, I thought I lost them. Thank you for retrieving them for me.
No problem. And there's something I want to tell you, Roy!
Roy, are you sure you want to stay like this?
What do you mean by "like this"?
Everyone's worried about you, and grateful to you.
You're not imagining things. We truly feel this way. You're important to all of us.
Ellie, I used to think this way myself... about my relationship with my teacher, and the blue rose field...
But then I realized that I was mistaken, and all that remained was a sense of meaninglessness. I think I never owned anything.
To conclude, I own nothing. I'd rather face this reality than expect otherwise.
<shake>That's not true!</shake>
You know where I found the shovel and the watering can?
At the place where we appreciated the blue rose field together.
The blue rose field is gone, but one blue rose has remained.
It's the [em1]blue rose[/em1] you used to carry around, isn't it?
You could have thrown it away. Why did you plant it at that very location?
I can't seem to hide anything from you, Ellie.
It's true that I struggle to give up those feelings even now.
That's why I wandered there before I knew it. I wanted to return the rose to where the flower field used to be, if not anything else.
But the blue rose field is already gone.
That view reminded me again of the reason why it is called the [em1]flower of the impossible[/em1].
I'm ready to move on, and this matter will never trouble me again. Don't worry about me.
<shake>You are not! You're troubled in every way!!</shake>
E-Ellie?
It's not just me. Everyone can see that you're not quite your usual self!
Just be honest and say that you need help, that you are tired, and we'll all help you.
However, you always keep problems to yourself, and never ask for advice! You're tormenting yourself!
<shake>To hell with this flower of the "impossible"!</shake> The word impossible is not to be found in my dictionary!
I'll [em1]prove[/em1] that your efforts have never gone to waste! Just you wait!
Hey, Roy! Welcome!
So, what did you need me for?
Let us sit down and talk first.
What do I do, Virgil? I was so mad that I spoke without thinking.
Why the fuss? It's just how you always act.
What if my words hurt Roy?
I don't want to run away, but I'm kind of scared.
It's just normal that you don't know what's on someone else's mind.
I still don't get Aria or you, after all these years.
Hesitation gets you nowhere. Just follow your heart.
It's actually your strong suit: to act before you think.
I can be thoughtful sometimes!
But you're right. I'm not someone to sit back and do nothing.
Alright, since I've talked big, I have to prove it to him!
That's the attitude. How do you plan to prove it?
He thinks he has accumulated nothing.
So, I need to show him that, although his teacher's gone, many things and people are still around.
Roy once said that feelings could be conveyed with tongues of flowers.
Is there [em1]an intense way to communicate feelings[/em1]?
Something intuitive, something that presents feelings like fireworks!
You want the feelings to be audible and touchable?
Such as a book from which memories unfold like a hologram and ties between people are visualized!
A magic book...
Wait, I think I've seen a book like that.
We've read one together at your home.
That's it! The graduation photo album of witches — [em1]Book of Memories![/em1]
Now I remember it. I've seen Mom's Book of Memories!
Right, Aria's log.
A [em1]Book of Memories[/em1] records things a witch does and stories about people involved in a vivid fashion.
You know how to craft one?
You need [em1]an item cherished by the book owner, feelings of people close to them,[/em1]
a [em1]Book of Memories copy[/em1], and a [em1]potion[/em1] to bind them together.
No need to rush. I'll start with items easier to obtain.
Speaking of an item that Roy cherishes, it must be the [em1]blue rose[/em1].
Let's retrieve the [em1]blue rose[/em1] first.
Such a book is perfect for Roy, who thinks he has accumulated nothing.
Thank goodness it's still here!
Let me uproot it right away.
Wait, it's important to Roy. I'd better dig it out softly.
Done!
Got the [em1]blue rose[/em1].
Next up, I need to gather feelings from people close to Roy.
It won't be a problem if they are villagers of Wisteria, but what about those living elsewhere?
For villagers, I can ask [em1]Enite[/em1].
For non-villagers, I guess I'll ask [em1]Aurea[/em1].
Aurea sells Roy's products for him, which means she probably knows Roy's customers.
As for the Book of Memories copy, can't I just use an ordinary book?
There's no way an ordinary book can hold all the letters and belongings.
But you can probably buy one from a shop, since witches are not the only ones that want a Book of Memories.
In that case, I know the perfect person to go to. A [em1]sundries store owner[/em1]!
Okay, here's the to-do list.
I'll ask [em1]Enite and Aurea[/em1] to handle the letters, and then ask [em1]Alvin[/em1] if he's got a Book of Memories!
All the tasks are finished.
The letters will arrive tomorrow. Now I just need to wait.
Virgil.. Do you think Roy will take this [em1]Book of Memories[/em1]?
What's the point of worrying when you've already done all the work?
I did all the work because I didn't want to sit back.
But what if Roy doesn't want it?
What if it adds to his disappointment or rubs salt into his wound?
I wish I could read Roy's mind.
Unfortunately, there isn't a spell that magical.
Is that how Roy appears to you?
No, Roy is a soft, kind, and considerate friend to me.
That's why everyone wants to help him.
Everyone's doing their bit. I can't be idling!
I'll [em1]check the letterbox tomorrow[/em1]! The letters must have arrived by then.
I don't think this box is from anyone we're asking a letter from.
Who sent this?
For your information, you shouldn't just open a random...
Hah!
Forget about it.
It's stuffed with [em1]letters[/em1]...
Maven Ostyr. It doesn't ring a bell.
Who's it addressed to?
It's addressed to... Roy?! These are all [em1]letters to Roy[/em1]!
That's a lot of letters.
This letter is from a different person, a "Lilac Ostyr." Shall I read it?
Roy, I'm terribly sorry to inform you of my father's death.
You and my father were like family. You must be as shocked as I am.
Actually, the news may hit you much harder than me, because the time I spent by my father's side has prepared me mentally.
Nevertheless, please do forgive my father. You know how prideful he was.
He kept claiming that exchanging letters was too mushy an activity for men.
Actually, he anticipated your letters eagerly,
but instead of writing back, he just put away all the replies he wrote.
These are the replies my father wrote. I hope you could accept them.
Are these all [em1]letters from Roy's teacher[/em1]?
As I expected, he had cared about Roy this whole time.
And here's [em1]an origami blue rose[/em1].
It's awkwardly made. There are even unneeded folds.
But it somehow [em1]feels heartwarming[/em1].
Why would such a clumsy work give me this feeling?
Will Roy change his mind if I give this to him?
Who knows? He may assume that you've made this up to comfort him.
That's the hardest part when dealing with someone who won't look up from the ground. They never embrace positive thinking.
Let's add this to the [em1]Book of Memories[/em1] then. It will definitely help!
Okay, we've got all the letters from the villagers and Roy's customers as well!
And there's a [em1]potion[/em1] I need for making the book?
There seems to be one in every envelope.
The [em1]Reminiscence Potion[/em1] is ready!
Let's make the [em1]Book of Memories[/em1].
I suppose I should do it at the [em1]workbench[/em1]?
Here we go!
Let's see... Put the Book of Memories copy, the blue rose, and the letters together.
Then pour the [em1]Reminiscence Potion[/em1] on them. That's it.
It's easier than I expected.
To make the ones issued at school, there were more steps, such as accepting blessings of the stars.
Book of Memories copies offered at stores are expensive for a reason.
I'm glad I have the copy from Alvin.
Let's get started.
Lay the items here, and pour the potion...
Now I'll get it to [em1]Roy[/em1]!
I hope he'll cheer up this time.
I don't have them on me.
Roy, there you are!
Welcome, Ellie. How may I help you today?
What's wrong? Why the silence?
I didn't know Roy was so good at acting.
It may take time. You'd better finish any other task first.
Give the [em1]Book of Memories[/em1] to Roy?
I'm here to give you this.
Roy, I've got some important business.
Sorry, Ellie, but I've got another busy day ahead of me.
I'll help you with your work. Please hear me out in return.
Or I'll stay here until you finish your work!
I guess you really mean it... Alright, give me a second and I'll make some time.
I'll come again when I've finished other tasks.
Ellie, we've met again.
Roy, you haven't changed a bit.
I don't have the [em1]Book of Memories[/em1] on me. I need to fetch it.
Ellie, what's this book you gave me?
It's called the [em1]Book of Memories[/em1].
It holds the life a person has lived, the ties they've established, and the feelings of people who remember them fondly.
Roy, I said I would [em1]prove[/em1] that your efforts had never gone to waste. Remember?
And I told you that there was no need, Ellie.
No, I must do it.
It's a witch's principle to help those in her reach, but this time, I'm helping because it's you, Roy.
I'm not someone to sit back and watch.
I won't read this book even if I take it.
In fact, Ellie, I don't even dare to open it. I don't want to be hurt again.
I'm not going to let you read it alone! I'll read it with you, Roy!
Even so, I can't take it.
That stubbornness of yours does take me back to the day we first met.
I won't back down. Never.
Until you agree to read it, I'm not leaving.
Sigh, alright. You win.
Nobody beats Ellie Blueriver in stubbornness.
Great, it's decided then?
Come on, open it! This is gonna be fun!
<shake>Ellie?! What is...</shake>
Don't worry. We're still in the [em1]flower shop[/em1].
The Book of Memories is a device that displays a hologram of its content.
To return to the flower shop, you just need to close the book.
I see. It appears to have faded. This is magical.
The objects with colors are projected by the book.
Since it's your Book of Memories, the memories are represented by [em1]flowers[/em1].
And if you touch this colored flower like this...
Roy, are you watching?
Ellie, the flower is talking!
Shh. Hear him out!
You sent the flowers to cheer me up, and it really worked!
I'm well again!
Like you said, I just need to make a little effort every day.
You encouraged me to imitate the flowers and work gradually towards full bloom.
To tell you the truth, at first I thought that was a silly thing to say.
Whenever I see the flowers, my loneliness goes away, and I remember how you cheered me on. It makes me so happy.
Just want to say thank you! I want to grow up to be a bringer of hope, just like you!
Now that I'm healthy again, I'll work hard just like you!
I know that voice. It's a boy I once gave flowers to.
I told you. The book holds feelings of people close to you.
There are more flowers. Let's watch all of them together!
Keep turning the pages. There are more stories to see!
Hurry. The story isn't over yet!
Understood, keep going and I'll follow along.
But why are they presented in this way?
Because it's your book, Roy. All the feelings appear as flowers.
Mr. Roy, thank you for all the beautiful flowers you've delivered.
Whenever I see your flowers, I feel like they are quiet guests.
When a party ends, I would gaze at the flowers as I recall what happened that day, and the tongues of flowers you told me.
Flowers don't speak, but somehow I can hear them talking to me, saying, "You've done a great job."
You know what? I always feel warmth in my chest when I receive the flowers.
I hope you'll be relieved to read this letter. You'll always have my gratitude and support.
Is this from a noble?
Yes, it's a lord I met at Highlion.
He used to frequent my shop.
I'm glad my flowers brightened his days.
And I would close my eyes, thinking to myself that I'd fought through another long day.
This time, Mr. Roy, I hope I can bring you strength, like how you've kept me going.
He appreciated my flowers even when the parties were over.
The letter says he felt like the flowers were comforting him.
Mr. Roy! I'm going to marry the girl I confessed to!
I sent her those splendid flowers when I proposed.
I've never been smart or eloquent. I couldn't have reached out to her had I not received courage from you.
With hindsight, luck must have guided me into your shop that day! Coincidences are like magic, haha!
PS: Could you make the wedding bouquet for us? And the flowers for decorating the venue!
You've changed our lives. Isn't that something? Let's keep in touch!
A marriage?!
I'm very pleased too. It's great news.
Do you remember this customer?
I do. He came into the shop yelling that he wanted flowers for a lady.
He wasn't very coherent, but I could feel his profound love for her.
I'm glad he's found happiness.
You said you were ashamed of your past, and that you wanted to connect people with flowers from now on.
You can now be proud of yourself! Thanks to you, Mr. Roy, I've met the most beautiful lady ever!
It's been so long since I asked you to return and reopen the flower shop, but to me, it feels like yesterday, hehe.
Since your return, you've been looking after the village's flowers for me. It fills my heart with immeasurable gratitude and happiness.
Whenever I see those flowers, I see how much care you've put into the village.
You used to say that you loved the village because of the quietness and peace here.
Do you still find peace in living here?
I doubt that. Seeing how you're emaciated worries me so much.
Do eat properly and restore your health. Don't push yourself too hard.
I hope the village always remains a cozy and welcoming place for you.
We've long considered you part of the village. You're [em1]family to us[/em1].
Roy, you know what? After you arrived here, the flowers start to bloom, and [em1]the village looks much more colorful.[/em1]
Granny says the flowers lift her spirits.
And looking at the flowers makes me feel great too! It makes me itch to do something fun.
You've also told me interesting stories and taught me how to make flower tea,
so that I have things to do and think about even when I'm alone.
Roy, I hope loneliness doesn't get you either. I want to see the usual smile on your face.
I'll keep making flower tea for you until you get better!
I didn't know that the villagers considered me [em1]family[/em1].
I thought I was just an outsider staying temporarily.
You only got that idea because you weren't paying attention to the people around you.
Both the grandmother and the grandson are so fond of you. You just never saw that.
On to the next story! There are more.
Whenever I organize the bookshelves, I remember how we discussed the books we'd read.
You've avidly read every book I recommended to you.
When you give me feedback on the books, it sheds light
on the implications I missed when reading them myself. That's why I always look forward to such exchanges.
I hope we can have more of such delightful discussions in the future.
Please take your time to recover though. There's no need to rush.
The books and a friend willing to listen will always be here for you.
Roy, I'm not great at writing personal letters, so I'll just get to the point!
You haven't been visiting the library! <shake>Why is that!</shake>
Arin's worried about you, and to tell you the truth, so am I.
You know so much about plants, and I want to hear more of it.
I mean, you don't have to talk about them if you don't want to.
But if you ever do, you're always welcome at our place.
<shake>Are we now friends? Wahahaha!!</shake>
Letters feel so different when they are visualized.
Arin pauses a lot when she speaks, but her writing is fluent and to the point.
Rex's writing is as loud as his speech.
They are exactly the people I know them to be.
They came to me at the parade and told me that they were willing to be my [em1]friends[/em1] if I were looking for friends.
I thought the parade vibe made them say so, but...
Arin and Rex sincerely consider you a friend, Roy.
They're so worried about you.
Are they...?
I'm also [em1]Roy's friend[/em1]. If you want to know what one of Roy's friends thinks, ask another of Roy's friends!
Hahaha, I don't usually write letters, because it feels odd, but I'll try if it will help you.
Come to think of it, we've spent quite some time together since the restoration began.
I used to think you were an honest worker, but a bit too quiet.
I still find you quiet, but being by your side has turned out to feel oddly reassuring.
I'm glad you've returned right after I did, hahaha.
Feel free to talk to me about anything that bothers you! Isn't that what taverns are for?
Drop by when you've time.
I just happened to move here early.
I told you. You don't have to do anything. Your presence itself is a blessing.
How about we visit Arden's Restaurant together someday?
You don't have to drink. We can simply chat.
Kyla's glad that you moved in.
And Arden doesn't invite people over every day.
Because you're not an outsider, but [em1]a reassuring presence[/em1].
A reassuring presence...
You've been looking listless. That's not good news. I don't know what happened,
and I don't know you so well, but there's something I want to tell you.
People tend to pause when things are not going in the way they want.
There's nothing wrong with that. You should sit down and rest when you're tired.
— sounds cool, doesn't it? I've quoted it from a book! And I've been eager to say it! Hehaha!
Anyway, as long as you don't collapse.
You may not notice it, but you've got support from many people in this village.
And you can come to me too! I've got time. Come whenever you want, hehaha!
I don't usually write to anyone other than a friend,
but you've taken care of me. I don't want to see you depressed.
I've got you a little something to cheer you up.
It's super fun, teehee.
Do press the object attached to the letter.
It will give you strength, so buck up now! It's an order.
Is this the object he's talking about? Here we go.
W-was that a farting noise...?
Will Theo ever stop messing around?!
Hahaha... Sorry.
Why is he doing this for me when he hardly even knows me?
Because he cares about you, Roy. Everyone knows how kind you are.
If you're still suspicious, talk to them. I'm sure they're all willing to listen.
Pfft.
I don't want to say this, but this is probably Theo's way of [em1]comforting[/em1] people.
Look, Bjorn's also provided you with [em1]advice[/em1].
It's not like that. This is [em1]colored paper[/em1].
And the craftsmanship is very...
Poor?
I didn't say that.
You can touch it if you're curious. You may find out who the maker is.
The craftsmanship feels familiar though. It's just like...
Your stubbornness hasn't changed a bit. Told you not to write to me.
Th-that's my teacher's voice?!
All the talks about tongues of flowers and stories... I wonder where you picked up so much to say.
I would die from old age before I could read so many letters, period.
That said, if you've the mood to write letters, it must be a peaceful village.
I hope you can always live a peaceful life.
I've always hoped so — when you were dying in the blue rose field, when I took you in and you looked so nervous,
and when you were dressed in rags and forced to steal.
Whenever I interacted with you, I wondered if I had done the right thing.
I would fear that you viewed me as "a stranger calling himself father."
However, that day, I saw you lying in the blue rose field, with blood pouring out of you.
And it didn't matter to me anymore: whether we were connected, whether your blood was blue.
Whatever blood flows in you, you are [em1]my son[/em1].
My stubborn son, I'm going. Stay safe, and be happy.
Oh my, that's so resolute.
That's very typical of my teacher.
So... My teacher...
He did view me as a [em1]son[/em1]...
R-Roy! Are you alright?
Yes, but I want to stay here for a while.
I've never seen a flower so shoddy, yet so beautiful.
So, that's how my teacher had viewed me.
I hope I had bid him goodbye properly. There are words I never managed to utter, due to shyness.
I hope they'll reach him if I say them here.
I've always considered you my [em1]father[/em1].
I've looked up to your back view and aspired to be just like you.
Until I read this book, I thought my life was full of lies. Now, however, I've realized...
that I have helped someone else, and changed their lives, just like what you did for me...
I'll get all the stories ready, and tell you about them when we meet again. Until then, please wait for me.
The blue rose field we saw that day might be a fake.
But all the time we spent together, and all the memories of you, I'll never let go.
We're back.
Right, we're back in the flower shop.
How are you feeling?
Are you convinced now?
I am. This gift is too precious. I cannot repay you enough.
So many people care about me. I feel ashamed that I never noticed.
Many say that blue roses are "flowers of the impossible," but for some, they can be flowers of miracle.
That's just like you, Roy. You stay kind even when you're hurting.
You are a [em1]man of miracle[/em1], who connects people with flowers.
I'm glad to have met you, Ellie.
It's great to see you well again, Roy!
I need to spread the word about your recovery!
Everyone will rejoice!
Mr. Ostyr, are you watching over me?
Apart from you, I seem to have met another [em1]miracle[/em1].
She's a [em1]miracle so very, very wonderful[/em1].
Ellie, I'm so glad to have met you.
Is that... a blue rose field?
Ah, w-wait, Roy!
Ellie, like I said earlier, that’s something I’ve already thrown away.
I have no regrets, so there’s no need for you to look for Ellie either.
I don’t think Roy will tell me.
Someone might have seen it, so let’s ask [em1]someone else[/em1].
Indeed, this is the Wisteria Station!
Wisteria Station... Could it be...?
Hold on! You'd better see this with your own eyes!
Alright, if you say so.
You lead, I'll follow.
...Did it really have meaning…? Truly?
...Roy, is it really okay to keep going?
Yes, I would still like to see more.
Wait, don’t tell Roy yet.
I'll watch attentively.
Virgil, look! There's a [em1]box[/em1]!
How many people on earth have you asked?
A lot! Let's go have a look!
If you're seeing this, it means Ms. Witch has delivered the Book of Memories successfully.
I'll be outside, waiting to learn how your story unfolds.
I don't know what its ending will be,
but I certainly hope it's a happy one.
After all, your flowers have created sweet memories for me.
Even your flowers feel spiritless these days. You must have something on your mind.
I'm not good at speech, and I've never told you properly, but I always find your flowers heartwarming.
Once you cheered me up with a flower when my work didn't go well.
You caught me off guard by pulling out a flower that I didn't order, and you said that "it calms the mind."
I was flustered and took the flower without saying a word, but it actually meant so much to me.
I'd like to seize this opportunity to put my feelings into words.
Roy, you're much tougher than me. You can overcome any hardship you encounter.
I look forward to your return.
You've gifted Alvin and Vinch flowers?
Yes, since they are my patrons.
I sometimes give them bonus flowers that are not for sale.
Maybe they were bothered by the unasked-for flowers... They would always ask, "Why are you giving these to me?"
They may not be talkative or eloquent, but they do remember the flowers they received from you.
Your sincerity has definitely reached them. They are by no means bothered.
I can't help noticing that you've been gloomy these days.
But not knowing how to bring it up, I just watched silently.
I hope you can cheer up.
Even if you don't, feel free to visit Munchy Bakery any time, and have all the free snacks you can eat.
I hope my donuts help improve your mood. Take care.
Because I've always been grateful to you, Roy.
They say you're feeling down, Roy. I'm super worried!
I used to follow you around, but now you don't even notice me watching.
I hope you can be like before.
We all love the kind and soft Roy — me, Clala, and everyone in the village.
Hang in there! I'll always have your back!
I believe you know Clala and Dana?
I do, since we all live in Wisteria.
And I love Munchy Bakery.
They say they hope you can cheer up, and they're offering free snacks!
I guess they are just being nice to a patron. Isn't that how you run a business...?
Do you still believe so?
I'm confused...
It's good to see you well again, Roy.
I hope the Book of Memories reminds you of all the people who cherish you whenever you browse through it!
Would you like to hear a different story than last time?
Yes, anything. Even something small is fine.
Very well. Hm...
Forgive me. I'm not good at socializing, so nothing comes to mind easily.
Have you ever received help from Lisa?
Many times.
Whenever I didn't know something about plants, I'd ask her.
She was always kind in her answers.
And you never talked about anything else?
...Why?
...Nothing.
Ah! Wait. I do recall something.
It's not exactly my story, but... would you like to hear it?
Of course. Please tell me.
There used to be someone called Brad at the library.
Once, a plant he bought from me began to wilt, so he took it to Lisa.
That was the first time anyone had seen her actually [em1]angry[/em1].
Angry? Lisa?
Yes. Not furious...
But compared to her usual self, it was quite the outburst.
What did she say?
She asked Brad why he brought it to her and yelled at him to take it away.
Later, Brad came to me looking gloomy and told me the story.
So even Lisa had moments like that.
At her core, she was kind, but yes, she could show anger.
Did she ever apologize?
Lisa? No, not directly...
Hm. Actually... now that I think of it...
Not long after that, Lisa gave out plants to the villagers as gifts.
She gave Brad and me each an [em1]olive tree[/em1].
Looking back, I think that was her way of apologizing.
So, she really did feel bad.
Yes. She was a thoughtful person after all.
Neither of us realized at the time that it was her way of apologizing.
Lisa was always so amiable afterwards, and we simply forgot about it.
And come to think of it, when I asked her questions afterwards, she did seem a little uneasy.
Still, I'm glad you two made peace.
Thanks, that story helped.
Ah, and if you ever see Lisa... would you tell her something for me?
I'd like to thank her for the olive tree. And tell her both Brad and I are always grateful.
Please, if you can.
Just as I thought... the witches' graduation ceremony is far grander in scale than I imagined.
But... watching over the entire village is no easy task.
Back in the army, I stood watch as a guard... but I never had the ability to patrol an entire village.
At most, I can stand guard around you, Ellie.
To watch for threats, you'd need someone with a much [em1]broader vision[/em1]... like an explorer.
If he studied at a school in the city… he must be a very polite fellow.
I heard it’s a place where students are taught very strictly.
He must be a good kid.
It seems he’ll become a good friend to Rubrum.
Did you used to own a flower shop in Highlion?
Yes, I closed it down to come here.
Weren't you sad?
Hmm... I would be lying If I said I wasn't.
But not as sad as I was happy to be able to come back to Wisteria.
What made you sad about leaving Highlion?
There was a bakery I always went to for breakfast.
The bagels and donuts from there were delicious. I miss those.
Ah. I also miss the food I ate on the train.
Riding the train until my butt pretty much melted was terrifying, though.
But, it was a flavor that I will never forget.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Roy"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Is there a reason why you started a flower shop?
Well... Not any reason worth sharing.
Come on, at least there's a reason.
That reason really isn’t anything special.
Please, tell me.
I heard a train ticket cost the same as 300 pies. How did you get one?
I don't want to sound arrogant... But, I had a lot of customers visiting my shop.
Wow, your shop must have been popular.
Yes, I'm very thankful.
If you'd like to read [em1]Curious Blooms Around the World[/em1], feel free to drop by the flower shop anytime.
I've been leaving it out in case you need to have a look at it, Ellie.
Because it's a legend.
Why do you think the woman's situation was more pitiable, Roy?
Because a dead person... no longer has a chance.
A chance to make amends, a chance to find happiness, or a chance to meet someone...
But surely the man who was left behind was suffering too, right?
Of course, but he was alive.
He could choose between life and death.
Ellie, do you know what the rosemary means in the language of flowers?
Though it has many meanings, one of it is "resurrection."
He must have wanted to make up for it, even if that would cost his life.
Perhaps he was responsible for all the chances lost.
Actually... I was basically illiterate before I joined the army.
All I could write was my own name, and I couldn't even read shop signs.
Was that the period of wandering you talked about before?
Right. On my first day in the army, it already caused me trouble.
They asked me to write down my reason for joining...
I wasn't able to.
I only evaded punishment because a soldier beside me wrote it for me.
That was the first time I felt ashamed... and decided that I must learn to read and write.
My teacher suggested that I start from keeping a diary. I would naturally be exposed to many words if I wrote down my thoughts.
So I've been writing a diary every day.
Whoa! That means you've got everything recorded for the last few years.
Unfortunately... I lost one of the diary books. My bag was torn apart in a battle, and I lost everything in it.
It's a shame. That book contained part of your life, Roy.
It's okay. Coping with loss is also part of life.
Ellie, do you stay in touch with your family?
Well... I don't contact them that often.
When I was at school, I used to write to my parents three times a week.
Then, Dad said that Mom found it troublesome to reply to every single letter, so I wrote less.
That's impressive... I should give it a go too.
By "it," do you mean writing everything that happened in class in your letters?
No, not that. I mean, contacting people I cherish frequently.
Now that I think about it... many people have been nice to me, but I haven't expressed my gratitude properly.
I did send a letter to my teacher... but as for my comrades from the army... and the ones who helped me open this flower shop...
I'm come here without thanking them properly. I regret it very much.
It's not too late, Roy. You just need to contact them now and say it.
When you think it's too late to do something, it's actually the earliest moment to do it!
That doesn't sound quite logical...
Ellie... Your words always manage to touch and enlighten me.
I need to write all those letters right away.
Flower Shop
Legends about flowers
Diary
Connect with people
You live in Highlion?
Correct. I own a flower shop there.
Where are you going?
To meet an old friend of mine.
Wow, you must be excited.
...Correct.
You'll find nothing exciting about me, Ms. Witch.
I'm just an everyman.
I always wake up at a set time in the morning.
Handling flowers puts my mind at ease.
Army
It's a place that changed my life... though I don't have many fond memories of it.
Huh? What brought this on?
Learning how to make donuts from Enite last time was a huge help.
More than that, it taught me how to properly use an oven, which helps with making all sorts of things now.
I found Arin and Rex to be rather interesting people, surprisingly.
Interesting? Does Arin even make jokes?
Ah, it's not so much that... It's more that watching them talk just made me smile for no reason.
When Rex moved his broccoli onto Arin's plate...
She started scolding him for it. For a full hour, no less.
One hour?
I invited them over for a meal not too long ago.
Aha! He acts so tough, but he's actually a picky eater!
I suppose there's a certain charm to it.
Can I tease him about it next time?
But... I have to say, I envy them.
I don't have any memory of someone scolding me like that in my life.
And to just casually put food you don't want on someone else's plate...
Just thinking about it now makes me feel all warm inside.
Well... If you ever feel like being picky about something, you can tell me.
I appreciate that.
Not that I regret joining, of course.
There were parts I genuinely liked. The routine, for instance.
The routine? You liked that?
What? Are you surprised because you can't even imagine it?
Of course! Some days you just want to sleep in.
I enjoy relaxing too.
But I liked the certainty of knowing what each day would hold.
Today is for maintaining weapons. Tomorrow is for mountain drills.
Having every day laid out like that was... comfortable.
What else did you like about it?
Let me think...
The food was cheap, and travel was covered. Having a uniform meant I didn't need to buy clothes... things like that.
That's quite a list!
I suppose so. But the bad memories still outnumber the good. They're just... difficult to talk about.
Well... I think I'm better off not hearing them.
So you get to eat all the donuts you want now!
I-I don't just eat donuts every day.
I can't make fancy pies like Enite can, not yet. But I'm working on it.
So, what's the best thing you've made so far?
The best thing... I've been trying my hand at this flat bread, rolled thin, with tomato sauce and various toppings.
The one I made with loads of [em1]pineapple chunks[/em1] was surprisingly the most delicious.
Pineapple... on bread? That doesn't sound like it goes together.
Your mind will change once you try it. I'll make some for you next time.
Hmm... Okay, sure.
That said, I broke all my picky eating habits in the army.
If you can't eat certain things, you never know what might happen in an emergency.
Ugh~ Sounds tough.
When I was living on the streets... I only moved when I had to, and spent the rest of the time sleeping.
Those were empty, meaningless days. I regret that time, which is why I'm happy now.
I don't want to hurt... or trouble anyone anymore.
I've learned once again that it never hurts to learn new things. And I owe that chance to you, Ellie.
It's a bit embarrassing to say... but of all the things I've made, it's the first one I feel might actually be good enough to sell.
Ellie, do you enjoy traveling?
Of course! I love it!
My favorite place was the [em1]Garden of Tides[/em1] I visited before enrolling in the School for Witches.
Do you want to travel somewhere, Roy?
I think I've heard of that place. I've thought about going there myself.
Yes. Not right away, but I'm making long-term plans to go on an extended trip.
Wow. You must have a lot of places you want to see!
I have many people I want to meet. My old comrades from the army.
But... It's a promise I really want to keep.
Everyone's scattered now, and hardly any of them are in one piece... except for me. So, I figured I should be the one to visit them.
I've heard it's common for soldiers who promise to meet again never to see each other for the rest of their lives.
Wow... meeting your comrades again must be so emotional.
Ah, we do write to each other occasionally.
So, it won't be a complete surprise visit.
When the time comes for my trip, I may need to ask you to look after the shop for a little while.
Would that be alright?
Absolutely! I'll take care of every flower like it were my own.
You're the first witch I've ever had a proper conversation with, Ellie.
Huh? But you've run a flower shop in Highlion for quite a while.
Don't you get plenty of witch customers?
They were customers, so I never formed deep connections.
Of course, we exchanged pleasantries and built a certain level of familiarity.
I was mostly listening, but they told me many fascinating and fun stories.
Witches are certainly interesting beings, of course...
That's a shame. I bet they're great people once you get to know them.
Haha. I think you might be mistaken about one thing, though...
Huh? Really?
It's only because I'm close with you that I talk this much.
Honestly, there are plenty of days where I don't say a single word.
Whoa... I can't even imagine that.
But still~
I'm glad the first witch I became friends with was you, Ellie.
Not a single word?
That makes me really happy! It means you really think of me as a friend.
I always tried to keep my distance, since they were customers first.
I'm just not really a talker like you'd expected.
Any interesting stories?
I'm ready to hear and also ready to tell!
Will there be treasures in the Green Forest as well?
They say that your feet feel wobbly when you're on a boat. Does that make the sea wavy land in disguise?
I want to play a musical instrument just like Vinch and Alvin do! It's so cool!
<wave>Do-do-fa! Sol-la! Sol-fa!</wave>
Hello, Ellie. Would you like to play with me?
One, two, one, two.
There is a very, very cool hero living here.
I’ll make a huge castle.
Hello, Ellie! Meet my friend Popo.
Popo, what game are we playing today?
Granny taught me about it! Ellie, do you enjoy tea too?
Granny says that the way you store tea affects its taste.
And Ellie, eat this.
It’s a gift.
Granny pours me a cup of tea after each meal. It's warm and yummy.
Granny's cooking is always great!
Theo says I'll make an excellent wind musician.
I'll practice hard so that everyone will enjoy my performance!
Thanks for helping me get home!
That's nothing special.
Oh, [em1]Granny[/em1] wants to meet you.
Granny?
Yes! She's the [em1]village chief[/em1]!
Oh, not "is." She used to be. You can find her in the back.
Okay. I’ll go.
Oh, Ellie!
Okay, take care.
But it really looks like no one is in the village.
Yes, many of them left after the [em1]prickly vines[/em1] started growing like mad.
Now we only have Arden's and my house.
I see. You must be bored.
No. It's okay because Granny and Arden are here! There are also lots of fun things in the forest.
She was actually the village chief?
I don't know what you're talking about.
Do you happen to remember anything about the witch who was here before?
She healed me when I was sick.
I had a really bad headache but got better right away after taking the medicine.
Oh, the person at the bakery always made deliveries to the Witch's House.
She must be a big fan of bread.
The bread from the bakery is delicious! I like it too.
You will be able to eat it again.
It's a shame that they moved away. If only I could have some more.
Ellie! I see you got rid of the prickly vines!
Yeah, I got rid of them.
That’s awesome!
Then I guess Kyla will be coming back!
Yup, I'll write her a letter, and she'll be back.
I want to see Kyla soon!
When will Kyla be here?
In no time.
I'll write her a letter, and she'll be back.
I also have weird dreams from time to time.
I dream about flying in the sky, climbing trees or swimming up waterfalls...
I guess it's because you play a lot in the forest.
Then, suddenly I fall.
And wake up screaming.
That means you will have a growth spurt.
I want to become tall enough to pick leaves from tall trees.
I'm sure you will.
Right!!!
I'm good at fixing things. I fixed that chair from last time.
There’s one less leg after fixing it, though.
That's why Arden said he would help me.
Did Arden fix it?
No, I haven't seen the chair since.
Err, I'd better not leave it to Arden then.
My legs still hurt.
Wow, what's this? Is this candy?
Yeah, this candy can heal your legs.
Wow, thanks. It looks delicious.
Oh, it's good.
Ugh, this tastes awful.
It's good for you.
How're your legs now?
Well, I think they feel better.
The candy tastes awful.
Ellie, can I follow you too?
Wouldn't it be better to rest a little more?
But staying at home all the time is boring. C'mon, please!
Okay, fine. But be careful.
Okay, thanks!
It wouldn’t hurt to try. Let’s go.
Treasure map!
What about the giant prickly vine?
Oh well. We can't do much about it yet.
So, how did you get caught in the spiderweb?
I just came to the forest to play for a little bit...
But I lost track of time, and when I was finally going home... the road back was already blocked by the [em1]giant prickly vines[/em1].
I was looking for another path, when I heard the [em1]sound of a train[/em1].
Oh, it must be the one I was riding.
I went towards the train, but a [em1]strange bird[/em1] suddenly started chasing after me...
It must have been that bird, not the train.
It was that bird.
I ran desperately into the depth of the forest...
Then I found a treasure map and got caught in a spiderweb as I was trying to pick it up.
I saw a picture of a skeleton through the bushes.
I saw in a children's book that it's a sign of pirates' hidden treasures!
Shall we go check?
Is this a prickly vine fragment?
Fascinating.
Do you happen to know something about it?
No, I don't.
Oh, okay.
What color do you want the [em1]streetlamps[/em1] to glow in, Rubrum?
I’d love it if the streetlamps glowed [em1]yellow[/em1] like [em1]fireflies[/em1]!
You're going to light the streetlamps?
Yeah, I’m gonna give it a shot.
Yay, now I can play at night, too!
I wouldn’t do that if I were you.
As the maker of the streetlamps, I can tell you that they won't be as bright as before.
So you should still be careful walking around during the night.
So what color do you want the streetlamps to glow in?
I... I want them to be [em1]yellow[/em1] and flicker!
Alright, I’ll give it a go.
Ritoring?
You've never seen one?
I saw one in the woods.
I wanted to catch it, but it was too fast for me.
Let me know if you see one again.
Okay! Let me know if you find one too, Ellie!
I don’t know anything more.
Do you want to hear about the delicious tea in the forest again?
No, that’s okay.
I don't know anything other than that.
The prickly vine in the village is not so good.
Not so good?
It’s bitter, spicy and [em1]not tasty[/em1]. It also smells fishy.
You ate it?
Yes, I made tea with it.
I removed the thorns, dried the vine under the sun, and roasted it. It was much work.
Oh, I remembered. It tasted similar to [em1]that thing[/em1].
I guess you drink everything as tea.
It tasted similar to [em1]White Prickly Vine[/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1] in the forest.
Hmm, if it [em1]tastes similar[/em1], can you see it as [em1]similar breed[/em1]?
Thanks. That's probably a useful piece of intel.
There are so many delicious tea ingredients in the forest.
I like bush apple because it's sweet. And Granny says the Birdflower tea smells good.
I'll also make some delicious tea for you, Ellie.
Okay, I'll look forward to it.
You tried that too?
White Prickly Vine has a good scent.
Alright, come over for some tea next time.
Hello, Ellie. I have something I want to show you.
I made a very huge castle.
And I want to show you, Ellie…
Oh, that’s right!
Did you make it with Kyla's shovel?
Yeah... it was good for scooping up a lot of sand at a time, since it was big.
But I have to run an errand for Granny. What should I do?
Where did you make it? I’ll go see it and get the shovel too.
It's the place with the well, just leave the village and keep going straight!
You can play rock-paper-scissors on the stairs.
You can pick apples too since there are apple bushes around.
It's my favorite playground.
Where did you say you were playing at?
The place with stairs after you go straight out of the village!
Ellie! You're back from your trip?
Granny says don’t go too far out.
The wind feels good.
I wish I had more friends.
What would be cool to make?
I also want to go on an adventure once in a while. Would Granny scold me?
What would other forests look like?
Granny said she would bake me a pie once I finish my meal.
She said I should never skip meals or I'll end up suffering when I'm old!
Tick-tock tick-tock for a long time! Tick-tock tick-tock with grandpa!
The clock has stopped! My grandpa's wall clock!
Curse? What is a curse? Is it on treasures?
Hmm... A curse may ban you from saying anything other than praises for nature...
Or keep you having nightmares and uable to sleep well...
Or make you have hiccups every time you eat an apple...
*Gasp*
Did Arden get one?
Maybe. I'm investigating because I'm not sure.
Did you happen to take anything that Arden threw away?
Yes! This one! Sparkly and pretty!
A teacup with a gold coin drawn on it... That's quite materialistic.
I can't imagine Arden using this...
Arden said he was throwing it away because he no longer needed it.
Arden had thrown away many other things.
Aurea told me when she gave me candies.
I should also go to Aurea then.
Thanks, Rubrum.
This is the thing that Arden threw away. Isn’t it beautiful?
It looks like a piece of treasure hidden by pirates.
What’s that?
It's supposed to be a special silver lamp without any wicks or candles.
You've seen it somewhere?
It’s Arden’s, right?
I picked it up near the lake and I was gonna give it to him.
But I discovered a new tea leaf on the way and I completely forgot about it!
Where was it?
I made a mark, so I could find it again.
Alright. I'll find it and give it to Arden.
Since it's you, I'll let you have a look.
The round and lengthy one, right?
Uhh... It was more shriveled than lengthy.
Granny said that meant they were [em1]withered[/em1].
They can grow again with good [em1]nutrition[/em1].
I can’t just wait for it to grow.
Check the [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1]. Also, don’t forget about the [em1]Witches’ Catalogue[/em1].
Alright. By the way, do you have the [em1]tea[/em1] Arden asked for?
I'll bring it to him.
Oh, okay! Thanks!
I’ll get it to him safely.
Okay! Don’t forget to teach me how to breathe fire too!
[em1]<shake>I'm gonna breathe fire!</shake>[/em1]
Woah!!! Wow! How? How?
Arden agreed to teach me.
Me too! Me too! Teach me too! I want to breathe fire too!
I’ll learn from Arden and teach you.
Okay! Promise you’ll teach me!
I forgot to give him the tea.
What to discuss with Rubrum?
Spider
I once went to [lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Deep"))]
without telling Granny.
I've heard a strange rattling noise, said to be made by spiders.
I hate spiders.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rubrum"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
They say it used to be full of people all the time when I was younger.
I like how things are now, with Granny and Arden. And Ellie!
Playing with sand
And I made such a huuuuuuge sand castle!
I'm a sand castle artisan, heehee.
Hopscotch
Granny taught me this game.
Though Granny can't hop much, it's fun even if I play it alone so it's fine!
Granny makes great tea!
And I'm trying to make tea with all kinds of ingredients. It's really fun!
I want to keep a cat at home, but Granny wouldn't allow it.
She finds it too tiring to clean all the cat hair.
Ellie, you scribble in your book every day. Are you drawing?
Would you like to draw with me?
Vinch asks me to draw, and he's given me [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Reform_Coloritem_Name"))][/em1]!
Ellie, what's your favorite food?
Granny's apple pie!
If I bring [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s from the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Plain"))][/em1], Granny will make pies out of them!
Trains
I used to hate trains very much, you know?
Because they carry everyone away.
However, I've come to like them, because they've brought you here, Ellie.
Toy
Hmm? Any toy I want?
I don't know... I can't think of any...
Ah! I want a broom, just like the one you ride around!
May I have one?
There were many older kids in the village.
Granny says we used to play hide-and-seek all day long... but I don't quite remember.
Is it because I was too small?
Ellie, I'm really glad to have you in our village.
Witches in fairytales often do weird things, and Ellie...
Ellie also does weird things a lot.
So, Ellie indeed is a witch.
I wanted to be a village chief, just like Granny.
But Granny says that to become one... I need to eat at least another 1000 bowls of rice.
Ellie, how much is 1000 bowls of rice?
Granny
I like to sleep in Granny's arms.
And... I like pies Granny make me with the fruits I pick!
And... I like it when Granny reads stories to me. She's a great storyteller.
I wish there were more books with illustrations in the library.
Last time, Arin showed me a book called [em1]Legends of Animals[/em1], and it was really fun!
But apparently, there aren’t many books like that. Most of them are just books with words written in them...
I’ve tried it.
But I’ve never caught a fish. Freddy says I’m not strong enough.
That’s why I want to try catching [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Fish_Cantsee_Name"))][/em1], but I always miss it...
I’m drying the tea leaves instead of my grandmother.
Lately, I’ve been making tea leaves out of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MapleHerb_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
Citrus scent is trending these days, or so Aurea told me.
A good cup of tea is a synonym of happiness.
If only there were plenty of interesting things going on every day.
Are you going to the peak now?
No, I still have stuff to do.
Wait, I forgot the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))][/em1].
I suppose, since you're still young.
Yes, I've hardly ever met her.
Oh, but her hands were very warm.
Her hands?
Yes, she tended to me when I was sick and held my hand tightly.
Her hands were very warm and I was so happy that I got better very soon.
She sounds like a kind person.
Seems to be the case.
But that alone isn't going to help us find Lisa.
If you're really stumped, why not ask the [em1]Cat Gods[/em1]?
Cat Gods?
Yes. If we [em1]pray[/em1] at the [em1]temple[/em1], the Cat Gods might come to answer our prayers.
Is there a temple in the village?
Will the Gods really show themselves if we pray at the temple?
Yes! It's amazing, right? You should go try it, Ellie.
Alright, thanks for the tip. I'll give it a go.
Oh, you'll see the temple to the [em1]right[/em1] of my home.
It's gorgeous.
But a little run-down now.
Okay, I'll go look for it. Thanks.
In the [em1]day[/em1], the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1] appears, while the [em1]White Cat God[/em1] appears at [em1]night[/em1].
What's that? Is it good for brewing tea with?
No idea... So not even you have seen it?
I've seen white and pink rosemaries...
It's said to bloom [em1]in the spot closest to the moon[/em1].
Then it should be somewhere easy to get a good look at the sky!
If you're on the [em1]bridge[/em1], you will get a really clear view of the sky!
If I venture too far, I'm going to get an earful from Granny, so I don't go there a lot, but I want to.
Fade out and summon Rubrum who fades in
I think this is it, but I'd better ask Rubrum.
Villager model fades out and disappears, Rubrum fades back in normally
Oh, that's it, that's the one! [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]!
They were in really isolated spots.
It's trying to hide from the Blue Fairy after all.
Yes, if it hid here, it definitely wouldn't have been found right away.
Now that I think about it, when I was here for the first time exterminating Little Honey Pumpkins,
I wasn't expecting to settle down in the village.
If I'd known about the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))] back then, I would have kept my eyes peeled.
Are you going to say, "Not Highlion, not Highlion"?
Thankfully that wish came true without the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))].
I'm really curious about Rubrum's wish.
Since I've started searching, I may as well [em1]search for another one[/em1].
Hehe, here's another [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]!
I didn't expect to have to swim to find an apple.
Why's an apple in the middle of the lake?
Is it because fairies have wings?
Did it fly all the way here to hide from the Blue Fairy?
It's amazing if it really were granting wishes while on the run.
Do you really think that legend's true?
Didn't I learn about legends and myths in school too?
Because there are lots about powerful forces and mythical beings.
It wouldn't be that strange if one happens to live in the Green Forest.
You don't seem that dim when it comes to this.
Are you trying to say I'm dim the rest of the time?
Let's hurry and take this [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))] to Rubrum so he can make his wish come true.
You... <shake>Just wait and see</shake>, Virgil.
I found two!
We need three to get the fairy to make our wish come true...
Maybe we should get Rubrum to look for one on his own.
Now we'll finally know what Rubrum wishes for.
This is... a Blue Apple!
[em1]Follow[/em1] the Blue Apples and pay attention to your surroundings.
I need to find a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))].
Blue Apples sure look strange.
They're not just ordinary apples after all.
This is my first time seeing something like this.
What happens if we eat it up?
Maybe we'll be hexed and turn into apples.
Let's just... leave it as is then.
What's the matter? Where's all that curiosity you used to display on hearing the word hex?
I'm only interested in hexes. I don't want to get one.
Now the Blue Fairy can't bully the fairy who's turned into a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))].
Because Rubrum and I looked very hard.
My name is Rubrum.
It's the name given to me by Granny.
The name suits you well, Rubrum.
Thank you. Who gave you your name, Ellie?
My mother picked my name, saying there would be an echo when she called it. This pleased her.
Ellie~ Ellie~ She's right, it's perfect for you.
I like picking names for others too.
I even gave the [em1]doggies that appear every night[/em1] outside the village names.
Oh, really? What did you name them?
Coco, Barley, Bean and Star.
Apart from them, I've named so many constellations and flowers too.
Come name things with me sometime, Ellie.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rubrum"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Ellie, what kind of tea do you like?
Sweet tea
I like sweet tea.
I also like sweet tea.
I like bush apple tea. [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "WitchFlower_Name"))] tea is also good.
But you shouldn’t drink too much sweet tea. It will rot your teeth.
Can you resist the temptation?
No... Every time, I plan to have a sip, but end up having a lot.
So my teeth hurt a lot. You shouldn't drink too much, Ellie!
Okay. I’ll be careful.
Aromatic tea
I like tea that has a fragrant aroma.
Birdflower tea is a nice aromatic one.
Oh, the name already sounds aromatic.
While Granny pairs nothing with Birdflower tea, I have it with a slice of pie.
[em1]Granny's pies[/em1] are the icing on the tea!
Where did you learn that expression from?
Granny often says that while she's decorating her pies.
Bitter tea
I like tea that is slightly bitter.
Bitter ones don't taste good.
Bitter ones have their unique charm.
No, I don't like bitterness.
I guess you'll like the bitter grape tea then. Granny likes it.
That sounds delicious.
I've heard that there's a bitter grape wine too, and I have to grow up before I can try it.
I don't think you will like it even after you grow up, Rubrum...
Hm... Who knows? The grown-ups say that I always manage to enjoy eating things that aren't that yummy.
Don’t like tea
I don’t like tea that much.
What a pity. There are so many delicious teas!
Let's drink some tea together next time. I'll give you some delicious tea.
Oh, okay. Thanks.
I like playing in the forest.
But you must be careful when you play in the forest.
Because you might end up like this again.
Hehe...
But it's pretty fun.
I occasionally see really amazing or special things.
Besides, I can even find leaves that Granny likes to use as bookmarks!
Do you usually play in the forest?
Granny always tells me not to roam too far, so I don't go every day.
But I like to play in the forest more than other things.
Because you might end up like last time.
Ellie, you must have many friends at school.
Friends? Yeah, I do.
Really? I envy you...
But why? Rubrum, you want friends?
Yup. I want a lot of friends.
Ellie, if you have many friends, you must have played [em1]Red Light, Green Light[/em1] together.
What is "Red Light, Green Light"?
Really? You don't play it at school?
No... I haven't even heard about it.
I'll teach you then! We can play together.
I tried to play with Granny and Arden, but Granny couldn't move fast, and Arden wouldn't move at all. It was boring.
Does this game require many friends? How many people does it need?
Well... I don't know.
But Granny says the more the merrier.
How about we invite all the villagers? That's many people.
Ellie, how did you become a witch?
How... Hmm, I had the option, and I chose it?
There are many things a witch can do.
Can I be a witch too?
I want to craft potions, use magic, and talk to crows, just like you, Ellie.
Well... to be a witch...
Rubrum, speaking of the way to become a witch...
<shake>W-wait a second, Virgil!</shake>
Hm? What's wrong, Ellie?
W-well, Rubrum, you must be at least ten to enroll in the School for Witches, you know?
You're only seven now, so you need to wait. We'll talk about it when you're old enough, okay?
Really? That's a long wait...
Favorite tea
How to be a witch
I like Arden's [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))]. It's delicious.
But Granny doesn't let me eat a lot of [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))].
It’s fun to make tea.
But I don't like bitter ones.
Ambition
Ellie, I'm wondering if I should be a cook or a painter.
Ellie, I saw a Ritoring just now.
Really? Where?
In the Green Forest! This is the third time.
I saw it on my way to that place with the spiderweb.
Again? You could have gotten caught in the web for a second time, you know.
Yeah... so I didn't go that far.
And the Ritoring reassured me that the spiderweb was gone, so it was okay.
The Ritoring talked to you?
Yup, they would invite me to drop by, although <wave>oooonly</wave> occasionally.
I've never heard it before... Ritorings actually talk?
Ellie, you've never talked to a Ritoring?
No, they would drop a gift and then they were gone.
I'll ask the Ritorings to greet you next time.
What should I become?
To become a cook, I should learn from Arden; to become a painter, I should learn from Vinch, right?
And both of them find me quite talented in their field.
In that case, you could be trained in both. You're very young. You have the time for it.
But... Vinch said that I should [em1]pick and focus on one path[/em1].
That I should dedicate myself to one single skill if I want to master it. I would fail if I tried to do two things at once.
You don't have to make the decision at such a young age.
Vinch actually said that? That does put pressure on people...
If you ask me, though...
Rubrum, it's up to you.
Pick whichever one interests you the most.
Wow... Ellie, that's so cool of you.
I'll think carefully! Both feel interesting enough for me.
Really? I look forward to hearing your choice!
Are witches very different from one another?
Some witches craft potions from dawn to dusk, while others explore their days away.
Don't let anyone tell you what to be. Just be the person you yourself want to be.
Why so serious all of a sudden?
Because I truly think that's the right way to decide one's path.
Do what you want to do the most! Or you'll regret it!
Favorite things
Ellie, what do you like the most?
Yup, such as treasure.
Well, what I like the most is...
Mom and Dad?
Come on, that's not what I mean!
Name a food, a toy, or something like that.
Toy? Does Virgil count as a toy?
Meh.
But why would you ask?
Is there a toy you want?
I'm just being curious, teehee...
So that I know what to gift you!
I'm allowed to give gifts to my friends.
Well, I do love Enite's [em1]apple pies[/em1]~
But it feels cheeky to ask her for one~
If only someone could get me one of those pies!
Oh, that's what you like?
I see, teehee.
I'm sure Posy will do a great job.
Items filled with affinity?
Yes, to repair the bridge. Is there anything you can give me?
Um... I'm not too sure.
Have you ever received a gift from anyone?
A gift? Oh yes, I got this.
Wow, is this a rag doll?
Yes, her name's Posy!
Once I got injured playing in the forest.
So I couldn't go out and had to play at home. Roy made this for me.
Are you really going to give such an important doll to me?
Yes, it's alright.
Every meeting must end with a goodbye.
Where did you pick that up?
Aurea taught me.
Alright then, thank you. The bridge is going to be even stronger thanks to Posy.
Hmm... A flower that rings whenever touched,
And a pink flower that shrinks whenever receiving impact...?
Looking for them in the forest makes a fun trip!
Yeah... well... but I haven't been to other places, so I'm not sure whether they are exclusive to this place.
[em1]Someone who has been to other places[/em1] must know.
What's up? What's up?
I wish there's something fun.
Rubrum, what's the Legend of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]?
You saw the notice I put up?
Yes! Is it a special apple?
Super duper special! It's stunning!
And it helps make wishes come true too!
An apple... can make wishes come true?
Collect 3x [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))] and your wish will come true.
I did it once and my wish really came true!
I once sneaked into the school basement and opened a secret chest, but it only contained a crystal ball that showed memories.
If what you're saying is true, that's a really powerful apple.
Right! There should be [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]s growing in the Green Forest now.
But one year... two years... three years! I've only found one over three years.
So come look for it with me, Ellie.
Sure, I'm the expert when it comes to uncovering secrets and finding hidden things.
But are you looking for [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]s because you have a wish to make, Rubrum?
Uh... Yes!
What wish is that?
It's a secret. I can't reveal it before the wish comes true.
Otherwise, it won't come true.
So you've got to keep your wish to yourself too, Ellie!
Alright, alright. Let me know if you find another apple.
Let me see, where should we start? Should we start from the corners of the Green Forest?
Granny wants me to keep an eye out for [em1]Blue Apples[/em1].
[em1]Blue Apples[/em1]?
Yes! It's said that the golden apple was once a wise and kind fairy.
It was nice and helpful.
Because it was often bullied by the Blue Fairy, it secretly turned itself into an apple and hid in the forest.
But the Blue Fairy found out eventually and also turned into an apple — to deceive people.
So when you find a [em1]Blue Apple[/em1], a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))][/em1] must be nearby.
I get it, you mean that the [em1]Blue Apple[/em1]'s a clue for the hunt.
Yes! Come look for me once you've found it!
Would you like to pass [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))][/em1] to Rubrum?
Ta-dah! Look what I found, Rubrum!
Oh wow! You're amazing. I can't believe you found two!
I found one too, heehee.
Here you go, Ellie!
Huh? Didn't you find this, Rubrum?
I thought you had a wish to make.
Yes, but I'd rather give it to you, Ellie.
You've already made my wish come true.
Yes! People in the village left because of the prickly vines, you know.
And Granny kept sighing at the empty houses.
But thanks to you, the prickly vines are gone and everyone's back.
So this time, I want to make your wish come true, Ellie!
Hurry, make a wish.
Restore the village
Hm... I wish that the rest of the village can be restored soon.
So more people can return.
That's what I was wishing for too, Ellie!
So do I just hang onto the apples now?
Once you make your wish, Granny will turn them into apple pies.
Oh, [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))] pies? They must taste great!
Yeah! They're yummy. Soooooo yummy!
Oh, and, Kyla was looking for you.
Huh? Kyla? Why all of a sudden?
Hm, she must have something to tell you. I'll bring the apples back to Granny.
Ellie, you go on ahead and see [em1]Kyla[/em1]!
Riches
X marks the spot! Hidden treasure troves! I'd like to look for lots of things like that.
Treasure's great! One of my wishes is to unearth some treasure!
Health and happiness
I'd like to stay healthy forever and not fall ill. It feels awful to be sick.
And I hope happy things happen everyday!
That's right, Granny always says health's the most important and happiness is the best medicine.
Granny will make pies out of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]s.
What do we need to do to find a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))]?
It loved helping people, but was bullied by the Blue Fairy, so it secretly turned itself into an apple and hid in the forest.
So when you find a place with a [em1]Blue Apple[/em1], that's where you'll find a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))][/em1].
Bring the [em1]two [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Rubrum'sGoldenApple_Name"))] [/em1]s you've found.
Rubrum, why did you come from that way?
I was learning to play a musical instrument from Vinch!
It was so fun! Just blow it gently and it will produce various notes.
And I did the homework Vinch assigned me!
I had him check today's homework, and learned something new. I was on my way back when I saw you.
You look so excited.
Yup! My home is always filled with the aroma of food these days. I'm so glad.
And Granny agreed to let me eat more [lua(GetLocalizedString("EffectFoodCommon", "BeefBread_Name"))] at the party than usual.
Ellie, you must be looking forward to the party too!
Yes I am.
But I've just agreed to be the emcee. This task just perplexes me.
I'm not good at speech, but it would be boring if I just introduce everything plainly.
Emcee? Is that the person who tells the guests to do this and that?
Then... Emm... Well... Let's hold a [em1]parade[/em1]!
Vinch told me that in villages much larger than ours, people would carry their musical instruments into the streets and play them as they march!
Doesn't that sound super fun?
Yeah... but that may not work for our village stage, since it's so small...
Huh? Wait. The parade doesn't have to start from the stage, does it?
Rubrum, could you lend me an ear?
Wow! Cool idea, Ellie! It will be super fun!
Don't worry! I'll tell the villagers!
Leave it to me! Ellie!
Oh, it's Ellie!
Ellie!!
Vinch is a brilliant painter.
He used to take me painting.
Vinch got different colored paint, and painting with him is super fun!
But he's constantly getting lectured by Granny for his lack of sleep.
I don't have any impression of that old man.
What do you mean by eagerness?
Well... A strong desire for something, or a strong wish for something to happen?
Hmm... Just like I want the village population to increase?
Um, nothing. I've got Granny, and Arden.
How about showing them an item you want badly?
But to be specific, the item I want badly is owned by them.
I want them to know I really need that.
Hmm... In that case, show them [em1]something they like[/em1].
Something they like?
Yup. Granny once said this.
"If you want something from someone, you need to first think about [em1]what that person likes[/em1]."
Rubrum, have you seen any [em1]cats[/em1] coming to the village?
Cats?
Yeah, a cat recently came to my door.
I wonder whether it visits the village too.
Well... I don't know which cat you're talking about.
But cats do come to the village. I know some of them.
What? There are more than one cat?
Yup, some would stay by me for a while.
But they never stay for long, which is a shame.
Wow... that means you get along with some cats.
They... don't often come here, I'd say.
But we'll more likely become friends with them if we see them often, don't we?
The cats stopped visiting the village because of the prickly vines.
That's why you didn't have much chance to socialize with them, Rubrum.
Yeah. So, I'm not familiar with those cats. And the adults who are have left.
That being said... A mid-aged man seems to come from time to time to take care of the cats.
A mid-aged man?
Uh-huh. I don't know him, and he never stays for long.
I sometimes see him on my way to the temple, which is north to my home, but I've never seen his face properly.
Is that so...?
Maybe he has left something for the cats at the temple?
I don't know. I rarely play in that area.
Alright, thank you, Rubrum. I'll check it out.
Umm, that's not the case.
That's why I only see them occasionally.
Rubrum, about the mid-aged man you saw...
Hm? You met him?
But I found something else — a cat encyclopedia and a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1] half-eaten by them.
So, the man and the cats were not there, but there were traces of them.
Yup, so, here's my suggestion.
Let's find some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s and go again, shall we?
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s?
Right. There was a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1] with cat bite marks on it.
That means we can get some fresh [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s to feed the cats there.
Aww, I'm in, Ellie.
Great. Then, could you wait until I get some [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s myself? We'll go together.
Okay, I'll gather many of them too.
Give the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s to Rubrum?
Here are the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s. Shall we go now?
Okay, let's go, Ellie.
Let's get them to the cats quickly.
I'll bring [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Cranapple_Name"))][/em1]s. Just a minute.
Okay, Ellie. I've got my apples ready. We can set out once you're back.
Got it, Rubrum.
Hey, Ellie...
Hey, Rubrum. Why do you sound so down?
It's because...
I broke the toy I wanted to show you.
Is this the toy you're talking about?
Yes, that's the one...
When I first found it, there was a cat right next to it.
So I started waving it around to play with the cat.
No wonder it's called a [em1]cat toy[/em1], huh?
Yeah... But it broke very quickly.
I really wanted to show it to you...
Aw, don't worry. That kind of thing happens sometimes.
But this broken piece... What is it, exactly?
This? It was already broken like this when I found it.
Hmm, I wonder how it got broken...
Ellie, do you think you can fix it?
Sorry, Rubrum. I'm not very good at fixing things like this.
But maybe you could ask Kyla?
Kyla! You're right. Kyla could probably fix it.
Ellie, wait here! I'll go get Kyla!
Rubrum, having fun?
Ellie! Did you see Freddie?
Of course. He even asked me to say hi to you.
As for the toy I took to him, Freddie said it couldn't be fixed, so he made me a brand-new one.
Now then! Let me show you how to use the new toy. Want to see?
Yes, yes, Ellie, I want to see!
All right, watch carefully.
So, what do you think? Freddie made it sturdier than before. Now I can wave it around as much as I want without worrying.
That's great and all... but I'm smaller, and I feel like I'd still break it.
Hmm, in that case...
I'll ask Freddie to make a smaller version just for you. He did mention he'd stop by your place eventually.
Really? He can do that?
Making a Rubrum-sized toy shouldn't be a problem for him.
Freddie and Kyla are so talented. I wish I could be as skilled as them someday.
Oh, that's right! Speaking of toys, one of them was broken before.
Kyla and I fixed it together!
Yep! Kyla said it's a [em1]scratching post[/em1], and after fixing it, she even went to check on it.
So it really was something for the cats to play with.
Do you want to go take a look?
Sure, let's go!
I helped hand over the hammer and nails, you know?
Kyla said she wants me to help her again next time.
Oho, then let's have our little assistant introduce his work!
Huh? Introduce it?
Yeah, tell us how to use it.
How to use it... I don't know.
Hey, Rubrum, didn't you help make it? How can you not know?
I can't help it... Kyla and I were standing right here, so the cats didn't come near us.
Rubrum, do you remember when we fed apples to the cats together?
In front of the Cat Temple, right? Of course, I remember.
What did we do then?
Ah! So this time we should [em1]watch from a distance[/em1] as well, right?
Exactly, Rubrum.
I saw a cat nearby just now, so let's step back a bit.
Ellie, do you see the cat using it?
Yep, it went right over.
It's probably the cat's first time seeing it, but it just knew how to use it right away. Isn't that amazing?
Yeah, it must've been designed by someone who really understands cats.
Someone who knows their habits... he must know or really like cats.
Do you think it could be the same person who left the [em1]Cat Encyclopedia[/em1]?
It's possible.
If it is, maybe we could talk to him about the encyclopedia in person...
Ellie, what are you and Virgil talking about?
Ah, we were just talking about the person who left the cat encyclopedia last time.
The toys and the scratching post were probably left by him, too.
But I've never seen anyone like that around here... And nobody claims to be that person.
Someday, we'll probably meet him in the village.
And when we do, we should thank him properly.
I'd like to greet him, too!
Thanks to him, our village has scratching posts and toys for the cats now.
If we want to play with the cats, we'll need to visit the village more often.
It must be fun. I'm looking forward to it.
I can play as much as you want!
I kept practicing even after the parade, hehe.
Really? Then I’ll be able to hear another wonderful performance from Rubrum.
Do you perhaps have someone you could recommend?
Yeah, my [em1]music teacher[/em1]!
You played such a wonderful [em1]lyra performance[/em1] when you first came to the village, and again at the parade!
Whoa, it's my favorite [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
Oh, well... [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]...
[em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]? Uh-oh.
What even is this.
Oh, it's [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]! I love it!
Ellie! Are you really giving this to me?
I’m so excited! I’m going to brag about it to my grandmother.
Wow~! This is exactly what I wanted.
Is it okay if I brag about getting [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]? Hehe.
I don't need it.
I've already got a gift today.
I don’t need any!
I just found this.
I thought you might need it, Ellie, so I've brought it to you!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Rubrum"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
I've brought a gift.
I've been receiving things from you, Ellie.
It's now your turn to receive something from me.
Let's play again next time.
Ah, Ellie! You're here.
I've got something for you.
Heh, do you like it?
It took me quite some time to think of a suitable gift.
I also asked other villagers for advice.
But instead of suggesting gifts, they all told me to thank you in their place.
And I want to thank you too, Ellie!
Ellie! I have something for you.
You always give me gifts first.
I’ve only said thank you, but my grandmother says I shouldn’t just do that.
So, I’ve prepared something I think you’ll like.
Should I keep playing with you?
I really thought hard about what you’d like to receive.
Hehe. How is it? Do you like it?
Rubrum! I've retrieved the toy taken by that Gaga Bird.
Whoa, you really did. It's my toy!
I thought I would never see it again. Thank you, Ellie.
Keep it safe from now on. Don't let the Gaga Bird lay its claws on it again.
By the way, could you tell those people something on my behalf?
Those people? Who do you mean?
Enite, Arden, Kyla, and Roy.
Those who benefited from the removal of the Green Forest's prickly vines.
Alright. What should I tell them?
Tell them to gather at [lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Deep"))] when I send for them. To be specific, at the [em1]place where the prickly vine core used to be[/em1].
It's for the village's wisteria tree. Please make sure they are informed.
Oh, and Rubrum, I want you to be there too.
I shall get [lua(GetItemName("RubrumToyStolenByGaga"))].
Rubrum! There you are!
Hi, Ellie! What's up?
Do you have a moment? We can play together!
Theo's brought me some fun snacks!
You can blow them up, and it will rain snacks!
That sounds magical! I want a try!
By the way, I hope everything's fine with Theo.
Why? Has anything happened to him?
I saw him being scolded by the grown-ups the other day.
He looked quite upset back then, and I'm worried.
He was scolded?
A lot! You know Theo likes to joke around.
I heard the grown-ups talking to Granny about it.
And Granny wasn't sure what to do about it.
I see. We'd better ask around.
Now's not the right time for me. I'm going to bake bread with Roy.
Okay, I'll go to Enite on my own and ask her.
Now that you're on it, the problem will be resolved in no time.
I also get yelled at whenever I play with Theo. That's not fun.
Haha, you play with Theo a lot?
He always asks me and Dana to join him!
That's much better than playing alone!
And he knows tons of ways to play, which makes it even more fun!
That's why I don't want the grown-ups to be too hard on him.
Don't worry. It can't be very serious.
He's still a child. He should be forgiven for some innocent jokes.
That doesn't sound right. You've made a similar joke before, if I remember correctly.
That was a revenge. It doesn't count.
Anyway, I'll stop him if he's up to any mean prank.
Alright! Thank you, Ellie.
Now, shall we make the dessert we were talking about?
Oh yeah, the dessert! Count me in!
Give me a minute. I'll get prepared!
While you're preparing, I'll go to Theo.
It's been a while since Granny was that mad.
It was scary.
Rubrum, care to have an adventure?
Are you quoting Theo?
Teehee, he said it recently, when exploring the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
Theo can always find hidden paths and places of interest!
And he's found all kinds of amazing herbs and made tea out of them.
But he isn't visiting anymore. I kind of miss him.
No improvement?
No, he and Granny aren't getting along.
He would avoid her even if she called on him with her food...
It makes Granny upset. I've talked to him about it, but he told me to keep my nose out of a bigger boy's business.
That's not exactly how a bigger boy should behave.
So, I want to find some sweet herb and give it to Granny.
Theo has a sweet tooth. He would like Granny's dishes if they're topped with sweet herbs.
So that's your plan?
But just mentioning Granny seems to make Theo gloomy.
Theo must also want to be friends with Granny again.
I will find the herb, so that they can enjoy their time together, just like before! Teehee.
Alright, I'll let him know.
But I don't think Theo would like the idea. Are you sure?
Don't worry, I won't force it on him. Shall we visit Theo together later?
Okay, see you later!
I thought he would have reconciled with Enite by now.
He remained silent last time. I guess nothing will change this time.
But we should do something about it, don't you agree?
Especially since [em1]Theo seems to be less and less popular[/em1] in the village.
That concerns me too. I must talk to him properly.
[em1]Talk to Theo[/em1] during [em1]daytime[/em1] before you set out.
Oh, Ellie, look at this. It's a mushroom!
Are you hunting for mushrooms?
Yeah, they should make good tea.
You're using this as a tea ingredient as well?
Tea making is fun. Do have a taste when my tea is ready.
By the way, that scary animal is no longer around here.
The thought of running into it worried me, but fortunately, I didn't.
But weren't we here looking for it in the first place?
But it's scary...
If you're scared, take shelter behind me or Theo.
I will! Thank you, Ellie! Ah, Theo is heading north!
I guess he plans to go deeper.
In that case, I'll go in there as well.
Okay! See you later!
I'll take this mushroom back.
Theo has gotten in there. Go northward.
You shall find it there.
Hi, Rubrum!
Hi, Ellie!
Arden has sent me here.
Are you making tea?
Yeah, Granny's back's hurting, so I'm doing it in her place.
Ellie, would you like some too?
Granny says that each tea [em1]has its own effects[/em1], and that they're good for your health.
Let me know whenever you want to have some.
I'll pour you some!
I'm worried about which tea leaf to brew.
I'm making fresh flower tea.
I don't have any tea brewed yet.
Hehe, Ellie, you want some tea too, don’t you?
Come by again if you’d like some more.
That’s right! I can brew even more tea now! Aurea says that’s what it means when the [em1]stock[/em1] increases.
Since Ellie praised me, I feel like I brew tea with [em1]more care[/em1].
Come drink lots, Ellie. Heehee.
Ellie, have you noticed I’ve gotten good at brewing tea lately?
Ellie, I think I’ve gotten really good at brewing tea lately.
Ellie, I can brew tea as well as Grandma now!
Ellie, do you know when Teo is moving in?
Can’t we ask him to move in sooner?
We played tag together and also had fun with the sand~
I’ve thought of so many things we can play together. Heehee.
Cats sleep a lot.
Thank you, Rubrum. You've inspired me.
Are you up to something? Is it going to be fun?
They may sleep the days away.
When the weather is nice!
They would nestle in corners.
Fair. On fine days, we also want to nap.
Up ahead is the engine room.
Small talk is forbidden during operation.
I’m an attendant of Brightman Railroads.
My job is to ensure the passengers' comfort and safety.
Please save any inquiries regarding souvenirs at the station until after you exit the train.
We don't check the passengers' outfit.
Even if you don't check, it's inconvenient to get off if you wear lace-up boots.
There are so many different types of clothing that cause discomfort, I can't define them all.
Then, what about having a hard time taking off your shoes when you get off?
Delays occur once in a while due to their shoes, but again, it’s not regulated.
I guess there's no fine.
Isn't it a matter of harming social reputation rather than the fine?
To file a complaint, please follow the procedure.
Under Brightman Railroads regulations, we cannot accept passengers' belongings.
I heard that you need an audience when performing.
Enite says that it's important to get some fresh air occasionally.
It's... just a habit.
I'm praying. This place... Done.
I want to jump out of one single painting theme and try more themes.
I calm down once I pick up my brush.
I'm making paint with various materials. Common materials are flowers and beautiful stones, though.
Watch it, it's hard to remove from your clothes.
And Ellie, I have some leftover paint supplies.
I’ll share a little with you.
Whenever I see this tree, I feel the impulse to draw it.
And I'm feeling perfect. I think today is the day to do it.
Vinch, here are the two cypress trees you ordered.
I didn't think you'd come along. They were heavy, weren't they?
<shake>Whew, that was a piece of cake. My arms can't even feel it.</shake>
Okay. It seems like hard work, thank you.
You said before that these are also materials for making paint, right?
What kind of painting are you going to make?
I have a painting that I started a long time ago.
But before I came back to the village, I needed money… So, I couldn't focus on painting.
I want to start over with that painting.
Wow, what kind of painting is that?
It's hard to describe. You'll know when you see it.
By the way, you seem to go to Roy's flower shop often, right? You two look like you are close.
Well… I don't know if that counts as "often." I don't really know much about flowers.
But looking at flowers makes me feel happy.
Roy knows a lot about flowers and he is very gentle.
If you like a certain flower or are interested in something, he will be a good listener.
Oh, by the way. You helped me so much. I should give you something in return.
These are the paintings that I have finished, you can choose one that you like.
I hope this painting will fit well in your home.
Thank you for your help.
I'm at home [em1]anytime except at night[/em1], feel free to come over again.
Sorry, I'm not sure.
Anything you need me for?
I'll take care of my own work. You don't have to do anything.
Hello, Ellie. It's with great pleasure to see you again.
Hi, Vinch. You don't have to be so formal with me. We're friends.
Really… We're friends now...? Thank you for saying so.
Haha, it's nothing. No "thank" is needed between friends.
Yeah, you're right.
I was going to visit you, then I ran into you. I'm so happy.
Really? Anything you need me for?
Nothing important. It's just that, you're my benefactor who helped me return to the village.
I want to thank you properly.
If you're free, would you like to come to my house and have a cup of tea?
This is the tea Enite gave me. It's very fragrant.
Wow, thanks. But why are we having tea outside?
Well… it's a bit embarrassing, but my house is too messy.
And, because I paint inside all day long, my room smells like the paint. It may be irritating.
Heck. It's not that big of a deal. I don't mind.
You're actually used to this because your room is like a pigsty, right?
Hey! Stop the nonsense!
Haha. Is that hat your friend? It's amazing.
I suppose it's more like... a love-hate relationship.
Anyway, if it's just because your room is in a mess, that's fine by me. Don't worry.
That's just one of the reasons. The smell of the paint will definitely give you a headache.
Hmm, but you're right. Inviting a guest over and having tea outside is too disrespectful to the guest.
No way, it's not that serious. The wind is soothing, and I feel quite stylish.
That's right! I come out for a breather when I want to take a break.
Although… it's not very tidy outside either.
Haha, you hit the nail on the head.
You said that these paints are all made by yourself, right?
Do you really need to make your own paint?
You can buy them at the store, but they're very expensive and the color choices are limited.
And I have [em1]a painting that I must make[/em1].
You can call it a habit, or just me being stubborn... but I always make my own paint.
I'm not satisfied with the first batch of paint that I made after my arrival, and I'm thinking about making a new batch.
Ah, I understand. It is fun to choose materials and make your own things!
My, my, would you proudly call some boiling lava-like potion from hell your own thing?
Haven't you heard that failure is the mother of success?
Well, Vinch, can I help you make paint too? It looks fun.
Um, you want to try? There's really no need to.
The witches from the Witch's House are usually quite busy, right? I appreciate your kindness.
Hmm, the duty of the Witch's House is to help people.
And I'm very familiar with this place. I'll be of great help. What do you say?
Now that you've said that… please allow me to ask for a favor.
I was thinking about some materials I would need. Would you like to hear them?
I need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Bellody_Collect_Name"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Reaver_Collect_Name"))][/em1]. 3 [em1]each[/em1].
Wow, that's so interesting, I thought these were only good for making food or potions.
It's the first time I've seen someone use them in paint.
It's a lot of work, difficult, and not always successful.
But I still think that I have to keep doing it.
If you feel tired, don't force yourself. Be careful not to get hurt.
It's fine. It would've been me doing it alone.
Collecting materials is not that easy, right? Don't push yourself too hard.
You just need to tell Roy to deliver the goods.
That's all I needed. Thanks.
The quality is perfect for making paint.
Hehe, I'm really good at collecting stuff.
Yeah, you're really a professional witch.
Ah, excuse me, can I ask you for one more thing?
I asked Roy to find something else for me.
Can you tell him to deliver it to my house?
How about I go get it for you?
Please don't, it may be too heavy for you. Just give Roy the word.
Some plants for making paint.
There's only so much I can get around here, so I often request flower shop and general store for help.
Okay. I'll tell Roy when I see him.
Just go there [em1]when Roy is working at the flower shop[/em1].
You're doing me a favor, so I certainly can't be too impatient.
If this isn't Vinch, what brought you here?
Haha, Rex's shouts can be heard even from here.
Yeah, I do have a booming and appealing voice.
And it's a bit far to walk all the way to my house.
I don't want you to get injured from walking in the dark, so I've come in advance.
Ah~ you mean that old man. Um... he used to help me sell paintings.
He seems to understand art very well, or should I say he has good taste?
But he rarely talked about himself, so I don't know what kind of person he is.
Before I came to Wisteria, I often received commissions for portrait paintings.
He gives a similar vibe to the people I met back then.
Huh? What is it?
What would you like to discuss with Vinch?
The air here is so fresh, it's conducive to creativity.
Being able to come back here is really wonderful.
She's a very warm person, very kind to me. If I had good parents... would it feel like this?
But she always asks me if I've eaten every time we meet, which bothers me a bit.
He's very cute. I think about him occasionally.
Because he's so healthy, always running around... and sticking close to me, to the point where I feel a little embarrassed.
Flowers
I only realized when I grew up that each type of flower has its own meaning.
Because I often paint flowers, I always think about their corresponding meanings.
The flower I like around here... might be [em1][lua(GetItemName("Bellody_Collect"))][/em1]?
It makes me think of the flower's meaning. Was it [em1]love that never returns[/em1]?
Uh... well... drawing?
I don't really have anything that qualifies as a hobby.
Likes
You mean my taste for paintings?
I like portraits the most.
Because I can stare at someone's face for as long as I want.
Meals
Eating is troublesome. I keep forgetting to eat.
I usually satiate my hunger by painting first, and with bread when that's not enough.
It's a huge forest, but it's a shame that there are no sunflowers. I like sunflowers.
I can't grow flowers at home, because the dyes are too toxic.
But I may buy two [em1][lua(GetItemName("Sunflower_Plant_Vase"))][/em1]s and plant them in the yard.
They say the place's become more forgiving than before, but... it's still tricky for ordinary people, isn't it?
There used to be ferries travelling between the village and the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "RainbowForest_Basin"))][/em1], so it was easy to get there.
The place produces [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Reaver_Powder_Name"))][/em1], which gives paintings vivid colors.
Praying
Unlike Enite, I don't pray to the Cat Gods.
My prayers... are reserved for someone important.
Money
Painting is more costly than I expected.
I can make my own paint, but not my own brushes or canvases.
Fortunately, painting supplies are my only big expenses, so I can get by in Wisteria.
We haven't talked much, but I feel comfortable around him.
Probably because he doesn't comment on my paintings.
Ellie, I heard that you came here by train?
I believe most people come here by horse-drawn carriages, because there's no train station near the village.
But I've come on foot, because I wanted to see the scenery along the way. It's stunning.
Swimming
Do you know that the river flowing through the village is deeper than it seems?
Rubrum once fell into it.
To save him, I stepped into the river for the first time, and water actually reached my waist.
I heard that not even witches could extend their own lifespans.
I once dreamed of such magic or potions.
When I learned that they weren't a thing, I felt reassured... but also disappointed.
My favorite food... I've never thought about it.
I suppose eating is more like a burden for me?
The pies Rubrum sometimes brings are a headache for me...
Ah, please don't tell Rubrum about it.
I feel like I spend my time either praying or finishing my drawings.
It helps calm my restless mind from the whole day.
That’s why I use [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Moondelion_Powder_Name"))][/em1].
When burned like incense, it releases a soothing fragrance that calms the mind.
Blacksmith shop
Did you know that blue is a harder color to get than you'd think?
It's a rare and expensive color, so it was a burden for me to use it too.
Still, recently, thanks to Kayla, I’ve been able to ease the burden a bit.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("MoonButterfly_Water"))][/em1] can be processed and used as paint. I was told how.
Of course, it's not a perfect blue, so it's a bit disappointing.
You also look very healthy today, which is great.
Be careful not to get hurt, or I'll be very sad.
Ellie, have you been eating regularly?
Wow, the same question as Enite!
Haha. Yes, Enite asks that all the time.
So, I thought I'd give it a try too.
Though I occasionally forget when I get busy, I'm eating regularly.
How about you, Vinch?
Um... I don't really have favorite foods.
When I'm painting, I usually just have a quick meal.
So, I don't think it counts as eating regularly.
If Enite found out, she might bake pies for you every day.
Spare me, Ellie. I did tell Enite I eat on time every day.
Alright. I'll let it go this time.
But don't you ever crave sweets while painting?
Hmm... Not really...? Oh, but I do enjoy coffee.
Initially, it was to keep me awake and focused,
But I found out that brewing coffee takes a lot of time.
So, I started eating coffee beans directly, and it feels good too.
Oh? Eating raw coffee beans instead of brewing coffee?
Yes. Since you're interested, would you like to try it next time?
N-No, thank you. I can't handle bitter things... Haha.
Is that so? Then you must be more like Rubrum, preferring cocoa.
Um, you don't eat raw cocoa beans too, do you?
No, those are reserved for guests.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Vinch"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Did you become a painter because you love painting, Vinch?
Um... it's probably the only thing I can do.
Sounds like you're talking about someone else's business.
Haha, yeah. Of course, I love painting.
Isn't painting difficult?
It is... There are very few moments of true self-satisfaction.
It's just making pigments, sketching, coloring,
overlapping, outlining, and endlessly revising all day.
I can't say whether I enjoy the process, but...
As long as there's something I want to paint, I'll keep painting.
I think I can understand.
I hate attending classes, doing homework, reading...
But the process of making [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))], throwing them, finding secrets... oops,
discovering new places is really interesting.
Haha, Ellie, you're indeed a qualified witch.
Vinch, your yard must be full of paint, right?
Wouldn't it be too much of a hassle to make your own paints?
Indeed. It's a lot of work.
But compared to buying them, making them myself is much cheaper.
Mixing different materials by hand to create various colors also benefits my painting skills.
But when necessary, I do buy some paint from the store.
That's impressive... If it were me, I'd probably give up because it's too much of a hassle.
Is that so? Witch's work is similar, isn't it?
It's all about collecting materials, processing them, and making something out of them.
In that sense, what you do, Ellie, isn't much different from what I do.
Hmm, brewing potions does take quite an effort.
Hey, Vinch, have you been making your own paint since you started painting?
Not initially.
I think it was since when I left home and had something I wanted to paint...
I can't say exactly when, but it's been a long time.
Rubrum likes you a lot, Vinch.
Haha, it's probably because I can help him with painting.
Rubrum likes painting too.
His works are always a delight.
That is a factor... but Rubrum enjoys being with you even if painting isn't involved.
It's not like I'm jealous. I just find you two really close.
Well... Maybe it's because Rubrum has known me for longer than he's known you.
But of course, friendship isn't only measured by how long you've known each other.
Rubrum must like you a lot too, Ellie.
The other day, he used more than ten sheets of paper to draw you.
Really? I kind of want to see all those paintings.
Well, he said he would give you the best one. Just pretend you don't know the others exist.
Ahaha, no problem.
Ellie, is there any candy that serves as a sleep aid?
Sure. There's this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DeepSleepCandy_Name"))][/em1]. Eat it and you'll fall asleep immediately.
Shall I make some for you?
Well... Does that candy have a specified dose?
Because I don't have any other problem except for insomnia.
Well... I've never tried it myself.
I always fall asleep fast.
She's great at falling asleep. It's a rare talent.
Really? I envy you.
I only manage to fall asleep after tossing and turning for two or three hours in bed.
That's why I want to try a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DeepSleepCandy_Name"))][/em1].
It sounds like you've got severe insomnia, Vinch.
Enite says that a cup of warm tea will help you fall asleep. You can give it a go.
I already have... I've tried various other cures too, but none of them works.
Then... I wouldn't recommend [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "DeepSleepCandy_Name"))][/em1], because you gain resistance if you take too many of it.
Alright... Please let me know if you come up with any better treatment.
Why become a painter
Making paint
Insomnia
It would be nice if there were bread that could fill me up with just one bite.
I'm always the same.
Enviousness
It embarrasses me to admit it, but...
Ellie, I sometimes envy you.
Her?
Right... You're always honest about your feelings.
You always seem so confident.
I also want to behave that way... but it's quite hard for me.
Well... thanks for the compliment.
Actually, I also envy you, Vinch.
R-really?
How shall I put it~ Vinch, you're very considerate.
You always step into the other person's shoes when you speak.
I honestly admire this trait of yours!
You... you're making me shy...
Does that count as a merit?
Of course it does!
And you take good care of Rubrum.
I suppose I need to try harder... to embrace positive thinking.
Ellie... you're great at doing that.
You can see the positive side of everything.
I wish I could do that.
[lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))] exchange
You want to exchange what you have for a [lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))]?
Yeah... since it takes materials for me to make my own [lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))]...
Just bring me [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect"))][/em1] or [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "NormalCollect_Unique"))][/em1] then.
Note that different materials result in a different number of products.
Come back again.
You want to exchange what you have for a [em1][lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))][/em1]?
Did you come to see the paintings?
Ellie, thank you for taking an interest in my painting.
So I’m thinking of selling [em1]various kinds of furniture[/em1] that might interest you by increasing the [em1]stock[/em1]. Of course, most of it will still be paintings.
I’ll have everything prepared as I said by tomorrow. I look forward to your continued support.
Ah, I’ll also make some more [em1][lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))][/em1]. Lately, I’ve gotten faster at making them.
Oh, hi, Ellie. It's been a while. What's up?
Anything will do, but I draw flowers the most.
I want to paint as much as I can when I go out... because I can't paint much when at home...
That place is super creepy, right?
You've been there?
Yup, I was too scared to get in, though.
But what exactly were you scared of?
Didn't you hear that it is haunted?
Huh, haunted?
Yeah... They say that a village girl called Janifer was crushed by books in the wing and turned into a ghost.
And [em1]she can be heard crying[/em1] in the thickets near the wing at night.
R-really? Vinch, have you heard the crying yourself?
No, I'm too scared. I never get near that place at night.
Ellie, do be careful if you go to the library [em1]at night[/em1].
After all, there's a ghost crying there [em1]at night[/em1].
This sounds complicated.
I may not be able to tell by reading them, but I'm willing to try if that helps you, Ellie.
Hmm... I've never used a cane, so I have no idea.
Maybe you should find someone who [em1]uses a cane[/em1], or someone who is strict with [em1]quality of items[/em1].
I do take portrait orders, but I don't hire people to paint for me.
Besides, judging from "someone you miss," the letter seems to be for [em1]a person who's lived here for long[/em1].
All that I've packed are paintings, just so they don't get damaged. I've never worried about packaging.
Hmm... I used to run into [em1]Alvin[/em1] and [em1]Roy[/em1] a lot at the library.
Maybe you can ask them?
Give the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColourfulPotion_Name"))] to Vinch?
Vinch, is the paint ready?
Yeah, I've got the three primary colors for now.
Please get a bunch of dishes too.
The potion I've got here shall create a lot more colors.
The colors will vary depending on the amount of stirring and the number of drops you add.
Unfortunately, the colors created are totally random...
But the variety is guaranteed.
Can I give it a shot first?
My... the color really changes each time I stir it.
But there seems to be a little residue of the previous color.
Right, since the colors are random, they may blend together or leave residue.
I see... It's a pity that such a useful substance is known by only a few.
But Rex and Rubrum may find its niche status particularly attractive!
I believe they will. I'll go get them.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "ColourfulPotion_Name"))][/em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "LetsBringItem"))]
I know how to do it because I once colored my furniture at home.
However, coloring furniture is different from painting.
Since furniture is in 3-D, it's much harder to paint, and the outcome wasn't great.
That's a shame. I thought you could pick the best color, Vinch.
Ellie, you have a decerning eye for colors. You should be able to find a suitable color.
I heard that Aurea was scratching her head over a furniture customization task. Are you asking for her?
If you're going to do it, Ellie, I'll give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item",  "Reform_Coloritem_Name"))][/em1] to Aurea.
I happen to have some paint for customization to spare.
That said... I don't usually make such paint. If you want more, I may need to charge you.
No problem. You're so considerate, Vinch.
A blue rose... a blue rose... It rings a bell...
There was a time when special ingredients was used to make paint.
At least that's what I heard when I left home...
According to merchants who were acquainted with witches,
there was an otherworldly [em1]vivid blue[/em1] [em1]dye[/em1] that they used.
What was its name again... I believe it had something to do with [em1]Blue Flower[/em1].
If only I had a chance to use that. The idea fills me with regret even now.
How vivid, you ask? Those who have seen it say that it was so stunning that it almost felt [em1]alive[/em1].
[em1]Blue roses[/em1] are the rumored ingredient of that dye.
You’re looking for someone to perform?
But my skills aren’t really something to boast about…
Oh, but it sounded wonderful to me.
And you even taught Rubrum before, didn’t you?
Well, Rubrum enjoys it, so…
Still, since it’s your request, Ellie, I can’t refuse. Alright.
Ah, speaking of a performance, shouldn’t we make sure not to leave [em1]him[/em1] out?
Who was it?
The most… [em1]lively[/em1] person in the village?
He often shows off his [em1]flute playing[/em1]. If we leave him out, he’ll surely make a fuss.
Is this for me? A [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
Thank you for your [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1].
It's a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
I suppose I have room for it at home.
A [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
My house is too messy... I can't possibly find a place to put this...
Ellie, you're giving me a [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
Thank you. I appreciate it.
Ellie, did I ever mention that I like [em1][lua(GetItemName(GetNPCPresentStorageItemID()))][/em1]?
It feels great to receive something I like as a gift. Thank you.
You prepared this thinking of me, right?
I’m always grateful for how sincerely you treat me, Ellie. I’ll gladly accept it.
I've received enough.
I've already received a gift today.
It's a gift from me.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Vinch"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
We've been meeting a lot recently.
Thank you for visiting me often. I hope it isn't bothering you.
I'm really glad to see you.
Here's something for you.
I was planning to simply chat, but then it occurred to me that I could get you a gift.
You know I struggle to get along with people.
Probably because I'm mean and cowardly.
You're quite my opposite — innocent, energetic... and kind.
So, I naturally hope to befriend you.
I hope that's the right way to put it.
Here's a gift from me. I enjoy your company, Ellie.
As you know, I don't have much interest in anything other than drawing.
So, I don’t really think much about what I like... or what I avoid.
That’s why... I feel like you know me better than I do.
It must mean that you think about me even when we’re not talking, right?
I’m not sure if it’s to your taste, but... I wanted to repay that kindness, so I’ve prepared something.
I look forward to continuing to be with you.
I hope my strength helps.
You need the spirit of the craftsman?
You're looking for craftsmen to infuse a marionette with aura?
But I'm not that remarkable as a painter...
I'd be someone who needs such aura instead of someone who provides it.
But your paintings are popular, aren't they?
You receive commissions from so many. I believe that qualifies you as a craftsman.
I'm only doing it to make more money... but thank you all the same.
I may not have all the skills required for a good painter, but I have a good sense when it comes to choosing colors.
I developed this "sense of color," as it is usually called, over my years of drawing.
Would you like me to share this ability?
Sure. It will bring brilliant colors to my furniture. Thank you so much!
Vinch, do you remember the flag I carried during the parade?
That glorious red flag with golden patterns? Sure.
That's the one. Do you still have the flag?
Did you hear it from Arin?
Yup, I need it, so I'm looking for it.
Sorry. I did borrow it from Arin, but I don't currently have it.
Alvin?
Right. Go ask Alvin.
Okay, thanks.
What's so special about this flag?
Why's everyone so fond of it?
It does look pretty.
Anyway, I'll go ask [em1]Alvin[/em1].
[em1]Alvin[/em1] needed it, so I lent it to him.
A witch's graduation certificate? I've seen one before.
Once I was commissioned to draw a portrait, and my client invited me to her house.
She wanted to be portrayed holding her graduation certificate. That's how I saw one.
The witch was in the first graduating class after the School for Witches was restored.
She showed me her graduation certificate with great pride.
It was a plain, written certificate with hardly any ornament to speak of. I suppose anyone can recreate it as long as they know the written content.
She also mentioned that she managed to graduate in the first try, although I didn't quite get what she meant.
I heard that a long time ago, someone lived in the house where I used to live.
Of course, they lived there before I was born, so I don’t know what kind of person they were.
I remember there was some scribbling left behind that seemed to have been written by Bjorn when he moved in.
He must have had so many things he wanted to do. There was a whole bunch of bucket lists written down.
Oh, hi, Ellie.
Has my poster brought you here?
Could you help me gather the materials for making paint?
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("WitchFlower_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
My schedule is tight today, so I have to ask for your help.
If possible... I hope to receive them [em1]today[/em1].
Sure. Just give me a minute!
Thank you, Ellie. I'll be waiting for you.
I can't seem to find high-quality materials if I go on a gathering trip myself.
I was going to make some paint today, then I found my materials running low.
I want to explore some new paint, and it may require these materials.
I want to stock up on materials this time.
I want to make more [em1][lua(GetItemName("Reform_Coloritem"))][/em1], so I need some materials.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("SilverStarFlower_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("MapleHerb_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Bellody_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Moondelion_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("MushroomWallPlants_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("ShootingStarFlower_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("RolyPoly_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
I need 3x [em1][lua(GetItemName("CliffRoot_Collect"))][/em1]. Sorry for the trouble.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("WitchFlower_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
Vinch, I've got you the items you want.
Your efficiency never fails to impress, Ellie.
You've been a great help.
3x [lua(GetItemName("WitchFlower_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("SilverStarFlower_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("SilverStarFlower_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("MapleHerb_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("MapleHerb_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("Bellody_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("Bellody_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("Moondelion_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("Moondelion_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("MushroomWallPlants_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("MushroomWallPlants_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("ShootingStarFlower_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("ShootingStarFlower_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("RolyPoly_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("RolyPoly_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]3x [lua(GetItemName("CliffRoot_Collect"))][/em1] to Vinch?
3x [lua(GetItemName("CliffRoot_Collect"))] will do.
How can I help you?
I don’t have anything to tell you.
Hello. Where am I?
Since it's a long story, let's skip it. You'll forget it anyway.
Look, I'm sorry, but I really don't know what you're talking about at all.
It's truly amazing that your reaction is different every time even though you can't remember.
Uh, I'll probably remember this one.
I've drunk [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))].
It felt like I kept having weird dreams, so I drank it beforehand.
Wait wait, you drank what?
Is this the weird dream I've been having?
Okay. Good. I’ll do it again.
Nice to meet you, young lady.
Are you the apprentice witch Ellie Blueriver?
Uh, but I remember it all!
You're only doing this now?
You kept forgetting even if I begged you until now...
I'm not sure what's going on, but don't worry. I'll remember everything from now on.
Please tell me now.
My dignity as a god...
Who are you, and why do you appear in my dreams?
Yes... okay. I’ll tell you.
Thank you so much for saving Rubrum. And you did a great job removing the White Prickly Vine.
You reconstructed the village and brought one villager back, which is Kyla the carpenter. Well done.
You also found the prickly vine core. Now all you have to do is make [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))] one more time.
Why did the first meeting that must be dignified become like this...?
Hello, White Cat God.
Please allow me to ask something. I'm looking for a plant special for the village.
Is there any?
In that case, you'd better ask the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1].
I can't offer you anything that is alive.
Oops... Now the White Cat God is also saying things I can't understand?
Anyway, I just need to ask the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1], right? Thank you!
Ellie, you carry the scent of vine flowers.
Black Cat God gave it to me.
Isn't it great? Why come to me then?
I wish to know its meaning.
That its name already implies, no?
Just think about this place, and the name of the village, Ellie.
The flower was in bloom in the temple for a long time until destroyed by the prickly vines.
There was a time when you could smell vine flowers wherever you go in the village. The village was permeated with the flowers.
I see... So that's why the Black Cat God gave it to me.
Does that answer your question?
Yes, thank you very much! White Cat God!
Bring [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RattanPetal_Name"))][/em1].
It's been a while since I uttered these words
I am the White Cat God, the guardian deity of this village.
Ellie, I called you to this village because I have a favor to ask you.
God? A god called me to this place?
Yes, I called you to this village.
But as I was on the train, I accidentally...
Yes, the train had to stop because of the prickly vines.
And missed the train because I overslept...
Yes, you missed the train because I made you "accidentally" oversleep.
You... did?
We've also met in reality once.
Don't tell me the cat on the lake shore was...
I guided you to the Witch's House.
And I showed up in your dreams so that you'd oversleep and miss the train.
I see. No wonder I overslept.
What is the favor?
This is a very personal and selfish request.
I wanted to help this village. It is declining because of the prickly vines.
But a god without believers is powerless. I couldn't do it with my own power.
It's been too long since this abandoned Witch's House saw its last witch.
You’re the only one that I can ask, Ellie.
Let me repeat what I said in the dream that night.
Ellie, please help this village.
Yeah. And I'm still doing so.
Precisely. You reacted the same way the first time we met in your sleep.
I've lost count of how many times I've been in this dream.
Even back then, when you didn't know about Rubrum, Enite, Arden, or the village at all.
You've aided a village, its people, and a God, none of whom you've met before, without hesitation.
But why are you doing this? Why are you willing do help?
Happiness
I wish people around me can become happy.
If others are happy, I'm happy.
If anyone is unhappy, I want to make them happy.
Because that’s what makes me happy.
And, there are many in Highlion other than myself who can help.
I'm glad it was you on the train back then, Ellie.
Any witch would have done what I did.
No, Ellie. Absolutely not.
I'm so glad it's you. Thanks again.
It's not such a big deal.
Yes? Do you have any questions?
Perhaps the fact that I felt like I'd been there when I first entered the village was also...
Yes, there was a time when I showed you the village in the dream. Although you didn't remember.
And was that also the reason I felt as if I knew Enite?
I really talked a lot about Enite.
I've been watching Enite since she was born.
Enite was a real cutie as a child, you know? The serious expression and clear pronunciation when she spoke...
Oh, look at the time.
What's the time?
Time to get up.
You should wake up from the dream when it's morning.
I'm eager to see where our partnership takes us, Ellie.
Me too, White Cat God.
The path above the village... has been cleared...
So, the [em1]temple[/em1]...
Obligation
I have heard this more than enough at school.
I want to help everyone impartially.
I want to help people nearby and those in need of help.
Fun
I grew up always listening to the story of my mom’s adventure.
I really wanted to go on that kind of adventure some day.
A shining tree in the mountain! Prickly vines all over! Rare plants and animals!
For me, staying in this village seemed much more fun than going to Highlion.
Graduation
I want to become a true witch like my parent.
In order to do so, I have to finish my apprenticeship first and graduate the School for Witches.
In order to finish my apprenticeship, I must help many people at the Witch's House.
This village is full of people who need help.
No thanks.
Ellie, you really never change.
The first night we met, you jokingly refused, just to see my reaction.
I guess you experienced it already.
You've always playfully accepted requests that you can say no to.
How can I help you, Ellie?
Greetings, White Cat God!
I have a favor to ask.
May I take some of the water in the temple, please?
No?
If that's what you want, you should ask the [em1]Black Cat God[/em1] instead of me.
In that case, come [em1]pray[/em1] in [em1]daytime[/em1].
Because the Black Cat God is very fond of that place.
Oh~ So it's fine as long as the Black Cat God agrees?
My sincere gratitude, White Cat God.
If you want the water in the temple,
go ask the Black Cat God.
I've rid the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] of its prickly vine core as well!
So you have. The village is in a much better shape now.
And we are seeing some new faces.
Right, Mr. Brad isn't coming back, but we've got his friend's grandson and the grandson's friend!
That sounds like a tongue twister.
It's okay, I get what you mean. You're talking about Rex and Arin.
White Cat God, you're always in the know!
However, Lisa wasn't at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] either.
I found a [em1]tent[/em1] that Lisa might have used... Do you know anything about it?
You don't?
Ellie, why do you want to meet Lisa?
Is it only because you wonder if [em1]Lisa has caused[/em1] the [em1]prickly vines in the village[/em1], like you said before?
Well... that's one of the reasons. Besides that, I also have [em1]something that I want to tell her directly[/em1]!
I'll only tell Lisa, face to face! It's an [em1]important private matter[/em1] of Lisa's!
I can't reveal it to anyone, not even you, White Cat God!
Please tell me her whereabouts. I need to find her fast.
I think... Lisa has gone to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1].
It's also where you'll find the [em1]last prickly vine in the village[/em1].
Finally, the last one.
As for the way to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1], [em1]the kid who takes care of the village[/em1] will guide you.
Kid? You mean Rubrum?
[em1]Enite[/em1], the village chief.
Oh! I see, even Enite is a kid from the Cat God's perspective, haha.
Okay! I'll go ask Enite. Thank you for always being so helpful, White Cat God!
You want to tell me something about the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]?
No, it's nothing.
Ellie, your goal is to eliminate the prickly vines and restore the village. Is that right?
Good. Bear that in mind then.
Whatever you see at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][em1], just ignore it[/em1], and focus on removing the prickly vine core.
Huh? Al-alright...
Thank you for all your contributions to the village, Ellie.
I hope you manage to convey your message to Lisa.
Good luck then.
Welcome. How's the village restoration going?
That's exactly what I'm here for.
I believe you are aware of the giant wisteria tree in the village?
I certainly am, and the fact that it has withered.
That's right. It remains withered even though the villagers have all returned.
Is there a way to revive it?
The wisteria tree is still alive, but it's dying.
Prickly vines have damaged its roots, rendering it difficult for it to take in nutrients.
Is there a cure?
There is, but there is a problem.
Which is?
Heh, you know what? This is the sort of situation that I hate the most.
It goes back to the time when I was still tending to gardens.
Everything I painstakingly cultivated would collapse and decay one day.
And People who didn't want to see that would come to me.
I really hate it.
It's like having my imperfection exposed. That's why I've been pursuing eternity.
I pursued it throughout my life... and even after my death, I ended up returning to this place.
Yeah... I know.
My mistake has caused all of this. I need to make things right before I go.
Eternity isn't all that matters.
Some things are precious because they don't last... because they are constantly changing.
You may be correct.
[em1]Grafting[/em1] can be performed on the wisteria tree.
Grafting?
It means uniting different trees.
Roots of the village's wisteria tree are fragile. You need to plant a new wisteria tree and unite it with the old one.
That way, the old one can receive nutrients from the new one.
Really? That sounds like magic.
Wisteria trees are tough.
Here, take these seeds.
They are the fruits of my research when I first came to the village to study wisteria trees.
All I need to do is to sow them?
Right, but establishing the [em1]bond[/em1] is the key.
Bond?
It's a shared wish, just like what connects you to the village, to the villagers, and to me.
The wisteria trees you plant must share the wish of the village tree, or they won't sustain later.
I don't quite get it. What exactly shall I do?
Firstly, go to the [em1]locations where prickly vine cores used to be[/em1].
Why those places?
Because those are where you find the most vitality.
Go [em1]to each location with the villager who introduced you to it[/em1],
plant the seed together with the bond between you and the villager,
and make a wish.
What would that wish be?
To establish a bond.
Just like the one that connects you and the villagers. You need to establish a bond between the two trees.
That sounds kind of hard.
It is. Connecting trees is challenging, just like connecting people.
However, you've already established bonds between all the villagers.
I have faith in you, Ellie.
What exactly am I supposed to sow together with the seeds?
You need to discover it yourself, since you're the one sowing and making the wish.
Recall carefully everything that happened since you came here.
They are all part of you.
Understood. I'll try.
Worry not. When my help is required, I will provide it.
Come back to me when you've sown all the seeds.
We are going to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))][/em1], the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1], and the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1], where prickly vine cores used to be.
And remember to take the items that symbolize the bonds.
Let me think about the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] first.
Villagers I associate with the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))] are Enite, Rubrum, Arden... Kyla, and Roy.
What shall I plant here? What is the thing that established the [em1]bond[/em1] between me and these villagers?
That was when you'd just arrived here.
Speaking of Green Forest, all that comes to my mind is Gaga Bird...
Hmm... let's see...
I was passing the place on the train, and saw a glowing tree, and the train stopped.
I wandered the forest, found the Witch's House, spent a night there, woke up to find the train had left without me, and...
That's it! it's the [em1]letter[/em1]!
The [em1]bartender on the train wrote a letter for me[/em1].
That was how I learned about the village and why I decided to stay here.
The letter was the first item that connected me with Wisteria. Let's get it.
Is it still there?
As long as nobody has taken it.
The letter should be [em1]where the train initially stopped[/em1]. Let's search the place.
It's all because of Lisa.
Shall I help you with your exploration of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]?
Well... I do need [lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))] for crafting [lua(GetItemName("MoonTear"))].
Oh, so you do, since you need to remove the prickly vine core at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
That's not the only reason.
You probably know the other one already.
Please have a look at this.
It's Lisa's witch brooch.
I found it on the bed at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] campsite.
I believe Lisa Whitegarden died in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
Actually, Lisa Whitegarden died way before I came to the village. Is that right?
Why have you been keeping it from me?
I... I didn't know it!
Your attitude has betrayed you!
Maybe she lost it at the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]?
Lisa is an adult witch. Knowing the significance of a witch brooch, she couldn't have left her brooch lying around.
And, White Cat God, you've told me yourself that Lisa was in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))]!
What happened to Lisa? She's passed away, hasn't she?
You don't...?
I believe we've got a more important issue to take care of.
You should focus on village restoration. Stop wasting time on trivial matters.
Lisa's whereabouts isn't a trivial matter! There's something I've got to tell her...
What would that be?
I'll tell no one but Lisa herself.
Alright, give me the witch brooch and I'll look for Lisa's soul.
Soul?
Didn't you have something to tell her?
I'll look for Lisa when you're restoring the village.
Just give me the witch brooch.
And you can have [lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))].
No, thanks. I'll ask the Black Cat God for ‌[lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))].
Wai—
If you will excuse me!
I smell something suspicious!
Anyway, I can't do what the White Cat God tells me.
I've got to get ‌[lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))] from the Black Cat God.
Ellie, you're here again?
What is it this time?
Can I trade with something other than Lisa's witch brooch?
What did the Black Cat God say?
I didn't understand a word.
Something about the east being the cradle of both day and night...
I see. That explains everything...
Which means?
Give me Lisa's witch brooch, and you can have [lua(GetItemName("SacredWater_Water#Important"))].
Ellie, just forget about Lisa.
<shake>But...!</shake>
Think about the village. The villagers are suffering because of the prickly vines.
You're their only hope, Ellie.
Therefore, forget Lisa for now.
You need to care more about those around you, instead of someone... that doesn't exist.
The prickly vines are still growing, causing more damage to the village every minute.
And not all the villagers are back...
<shake>Okay!</shake>
Here's the brooch.
The villagers will be grateful.
I'm leaving then.
Uh-huh...
Have you changed your mind?
I'll come back again later.
You've rid the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] of its prickly vine core as well.
All the prickly vines are now gone.
White Cat God.
Why did you lie to me about Lisa?
I'm sorry about that, Ellie.
I did it so that you would remove the prickly vines and restore the village.
I would have helped the village even if you hadn't lie.
So you would. I know it now...
But I wasn't so sure about it at the beginning.
You were my last chance. I wanted to be on the safe side.
Please tell me the truth then.
What happened to Lisa?
Ellie, as you already know,
Lisa was here to build a garden, but she made an awful blunder during the process.
But how did she die?
B-by the way, why are you so interested in Lisa?
She has already passed away.
Because she's the former occupant of the Witch's House.
And I've heard about a letter addressed to Lisa.
Although the message in it will never be received anymore now that Lisa's gone...
Letter? What letter?
It said that Lisa's daughter gave birth to a girl.
Lisa's daughter? Dosca... has given birth to a daughter?
Right. The letter also said that Dosca wanted to name the girl Lisa.
Dosca... wanted to use the name "Lisa"... but...
Please tell her not to.
Huh? Why are you making the decision?
I-I'm not. That's what Lisa said when she was still alive...
By the way, what are you going to do about the letter?
I don't think that's for me to decide.
The best approach in my opinion is to write back and tell the truth.
I could have done something else if Lisa were still alive, but now that she's gone, I don't find it right to hide the fact forever.
Umm, maybe... maybe you could put that off for a bit longer?
Well... wouldn't it be better if you write back after the village is fully restored?
You never know what might happen after you've sent the letter.
Wisteria should be our priority.
You may have a point, but...
And it's not like the witches are anxious for a reply. You can send it later.
Well, I guess I can have Kent deliver the letter for me, since he will come when the village's restored.
Okay, I'll listen to you.
That's very considerate of you. I appreciate everything you've done.
I want to ask about Lisa.
You're still looking for Lisa?
I want to learn more about her.
And, White Cat God, you seem to be quite familiar with her.
Ellie, you're showing much concern for a deceased.
Why are you so eager to learn about Lisa?
At first, I thought Lisa was an evil witch.
I thought she created the prickly vines and destroyed the village.
I wanted to find her and ask her why she would do such a thing.
But as I found out more about her, my attitude changed.
Now, I simply wish we could chat.
I want to learn her reason for coming to Wisteria, for producing the prickly vines, to learn the life she dreamed of, and the goals she wanted to achieve...
Lisa was a fool.
A fool?
Blinded by the pursuit of her foolish dream, she paid no attention to the people around her.
Then she made a stupid mistake.
And died a stupid death.
Why would you call Lisa a fool?
She lived for her dream!
Whether she realized her dream or not, she shouldn't be called a fool!
Yes, she should. Lisa was a fool, a know-nothing, and a good-for-nothing.
But she worked hard to help the villagers.
Many villagers are grateful to her.
There were times when she annoyed a villager or two, but in general, she performed her duty as a witch.
And she developed the prickly vine she wanted.
Which destroyed the village she loved.
I don't think that was intentional.
Even so, she should be held accountable.
Right, but...
She shouldn't be deemed by a single mistake.
But in her case, the consequences will linger forever.
One can repair the damage they cause. They can apologize, and they can strive to be forgiven.
But Lisa is already gone.
She can no longer apologize to anyone, and nobody can forgive her anymore.
That's why I want to find Lisa.
Ellie, you said you wanted to chat with Lisa if you found her.
If you're only allowed to tell her one thing, what would you say?
I would tell her about...
The villagers
I would tell her what the villagers say.
Enite says thank you for keeping her company.
Roy says thank you for saving the olive tree. He's much obliged.
Arden... Arden says thank you for "you know what," although he didn't specify the favor.
I want to tell her that the villagers are doing well, and that they still miss her and remember her with gratitude.
Those kids never changed.
Lisa must have been saved many times by their kindness.
Lisa would probably have seen [em1]herself[/em1] in Ellie.
In me?
A successful version of herself, instead of the failed one.
A version of herself marching down the path she chose.
A version of herself that believes she will achieve her goal, and runs towards it.
A version of herself she never became.
And she never will become.
She would have regretted, envied, and grieved...
And she would have been so terribly grateful.
That's what Lisa would have asked me to tell you.
If she were only allowed to tell you one thing...
She would have squeezed out all her remaining strength and told you about her heartfelt gratitude.
The prickly vines
I would ask her why she created the prickly vines, and what in the world happened.
I would tell her that the prickly vines have all been removed and the village's restored.
I would tell her how I removed them.
I don't know how she thinks about the prickly vines now...
But if she's worried, I want to reassure her.
Whatever Lisa used to think, she must be regretting it.
Thanks to you, Ellie, she's been redeemed.
I would tell her about the new apprentice witch at Wisteria's Witch's House, which is me.
I want to tell her about everything I've experienced and learned, and the people I've met here.
I would start from the train ride, and go all the way to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))], the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))], and the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
I would also tell Lisa about the villagers and animals that were not around in her time.
Ellie, you certainly have a gift.
Had Lisa met you, she would have wanted to return to the Witch's House.
I need to fetch the [lua(GetItemName("PolarisPotion"))].
Hello, Lisa.
You've even taken care of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
The [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] should be quite challenging for you.
That's what I'm here for.
Yes? Is there anything I can do to help?
I want to ask you how to "plant" the future.
Heh, that's an interesting question.
I don't think I've established a strong bond with villagers brought back through the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
But I'm positive that it will become strong in the future!
Therefore, I want to plant the future "bond."
Ellie, what do you think is the [em1]power of a witch[/em1]?
Hm? Well... her magic?
It's the [em1]power of wish[/em1].
Power of wish?
For example, you would make a wish when crafting a potion.
A wish that it will cure its consumer.
But I thought everyone did that.
No, not everyone does that.
Only a few pray from the bottom of their heart.
That's why the product of a witch is far more effective than that of an ordinary human, even though they use the same recipe.
Just make a wish. Wish for a stronger bond.
Oh! I see. Then I shall sow that "wish."
Heh, smart girl.
Thank you. I'll make sure to chew on it.
I hope I can be around to see it.
Then be around and see it.
My body is long gone.
I thought I would have no regrets when the garden was finished...
But now that I've met you, I realize that I still have.
Heh, maybe I should have agreed to be a master witch.
Ellie, it's too early to be sad. Go sow your wish.
Sow your wish — a wish to establish a bond with everyone.
You can do this.
I've finished the sowing!
Great. Did you make sure they'd sprouted?
Yes, they all have.
That must have been an arduous task. Well done, Ellie.
Now, it's time for me to mind my own business.
W-wait! Are you going to do it already?
That is the plan. Why?
Could you put it off for a little bit?
We'll soon be celebrating the restoration at the village.
I think that will be a better occasion to do it.
I prefer to do it now.
<shake>W-why!</shake>
To appear in front of so many people... the idea alone sickens me...
But haven't you agreed to apologize!
I-I certainly have...
You're not fleeing again, are you?
I'm not fleeing. I'm just moving on to my next life!
Alright, alright, I know.
I'm not fleeing again. Not from my last chance.
And I've made a deal with my apprentice witch.
*takes a deep breath* Okay, let me know when the venue is ready.
I'll make sure you get the best venue possible.
It gives me a stomachache just thinking about it...
I'm so nervous already...
I suppose so...
By the way, can you give me a potion recommendation?
Potion for what?
For the celebration.
In that case... how about the Firecracker Potion?
I've used that one before. Is there anything else?
What about Meteor Fall?
Hm? You've never heard about that? It was popular among my generation when we were young.
We used to mess around with it at every festival. So, kids today are quite well-behaved.
How do you do it?
Make a Firecracker Potion, transfer it into smaller bottles, add something not in the recipe, and shake it.
Shake exactly four and a half times.
I've done that before, but wouldn't it explode if you shake it more than four times?
That's why you need to stop halfway through the fifth time.
It will make the Firecracker Potion launch higher, and fall back down like a meteor shower.
Sounds dangerous... but fun as well...!
Dilute the potion and it will be less risky.
That way, the worst consequence would be a little soot on your face.
It does require courage though, and a precise shake. Wanna try it?
Good, have a good time.
Even White Cat God is here!
Lisa is in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1].
You've restored the temple! Well done!
It's definitely easier to talk to White Cat God.
Ah, I met Black Cat God,
but I couldn't understand a word he said.
I see. Each god has their own attitude, you know.
Thankfully, it's simpler to communicate with you.
Oh, there's something I'd like to ask you.
Do you happen to know the whereabouts of Lisa Whitegarden, a witch that used to live in the Witch's House here?
Hmm... Lisa Whitegarden, is it?
Yes, White Cat God, I believe you know her?
Surely I do.
She...
She... is now in the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1]? Where's that?
It's a special forest in Wisteria.
There used to be a path connecting it to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_GreenForest"))], but it seems to be blocked at the moment.
Clear the path [em1]across the bridge in the village[/em1] and follow it to reach the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
Woah! Thank you, White Cat God. Good thing I've come to you.
I believe the Black Cat God also tried to help you.
Ah, may I ask about something else?
Is Lisa really responsible for the prickly vines in the village? If so, what's her purpose?
It would be better for Lisa herself to explain it to you.
I believe it's what she would've wanted.
Alright. Thank you very much!
It's my pleasure. And thank you for contributing to the village.
To go to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1], you must first repair the village bridge.
Okay, let's head for the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))][/em1] now.
We have to fix the bridge first.
The bridge over that river, is it?
It's a big one.
Kyla should be able to help. Let's go ask her.
White Cat God, I've removed the prickly vine core in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] as well.
Yes, I saw it. Well done. More people should return to the village now.
But I searched every corner of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] and didn't find Lisa anywhere.
After I removed the prickly vine core, I also went to Lisa's camp, but she wasn't there either.
Lisa traveled around the forest a lot, so she probably camped at many places.
Oh, and I also found Lisa's diary at the camp.
According to the diary, the prickly vines in the village were in deed caused by Lisa!
Hmm... Is that so?
Lisa probably wanted to explain it herself. She would feel sorry to hear that you discovered it yourself.
Where is she now, then?
Was she in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))] before?
Yes, she was in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
But as for where she is now... not even I have any idea.
Continue with the village restoration. I'll try looking for Lisa.
Please come to me again when you've brought all the villagers to the place where the prickly vine core was removed.
Before that, shall I repair Witch's House first?
The floor is squeaky, the bed has cracks, and the workshop is too cramped...
That house indeed is too shabby.
Then, let's repair the Witch's House before we handle the bridge.
<shake>I'm exhausted...</shake>
Nothing to say at the moment.
I have nothing to say at the moment.
