Um... hello?
(The pages rustle as if they were feeling happy. The quill flicked excitedly)
(A lengthy [em1]Terms of Use for Witches' Catalogue[/em1] appears)
(There's a space for signatures at the end of the terms)
Just sign here?
(Ellie holds the quill, and it trembles slightly, as if feeling ticklish)
(After signing, the terms disappear, and a greeting appears)
Glad to make your acquaintance.
I need new recipes to enter a new place. Can you help me with the registration?
(Jotting down Witch Association's potion sales regulations)
(There's a blank for signature at the bottom)
I've signed it.
(It says "registration completed")
(The quill sways gently from side to side, as if shy.)
Wow, this tastes awful.
What about I go to sleep now?
Now you can’t use it anymore.
The Earth is round.
Molecule
Do you think you've become smarter?
What do you mean become smarter?
The potion is definitely effective.
The ancient witch language is simple.
One [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))] and a cup of [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SacredWater_Water_Name"))].
Add the sacred water to the juice from [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))] and boil it while stirring it clockwise over low heat until it boils.
Wait, there's more writing.
Uh... was made... because it was difficult to manage with [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))]...?
I guess the medicine is wearing off.
But I still got the important information.
I can't read anymore.
But the sacred water...? Where can we get this?
You can normally get it from places like shrines, but I think you have to buy it from Diane here.
Good, since we have [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))], let's make it right away once we get the sacred water.
Um, I don't know what kind of text this is.
You learned it at school. It's the [em1]ancient witch language[/em1].
What do you think? Have you become a little smarter?
The Earth is flat.
If it is round, how can people below or on the sides of it remain standing?
That’s because the Earth is pulling the objects above it.
And the reason why such force appears is...
Don't be silly and read the note when it works.
Although I'm not sure if you've really become smart...
Let’s find the note and read what it says.
And I didn't realize that there is a [em1]recipe[/em1] that yields [em1]3 bottles[/em1] of this potion.
Alright, [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "IntUpPotion_Name"))] is ready.
I feel like I'm already smarter!
Now, I guess it's time to drink it.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RememberDreamPotion_Name"))] is ready!
Although it smells like juice from unripe grapes...
I must drink it.
Have you been very busy lately? Feels like it’s been a while since we talked.
Are you having a good day?
Oh, I actually have some leftover ingredients from my bread research today.
Consider it a thank you for always stopping by the bakery.
Would you like to try some freshly baked donuts?
Did you order something?
It just needs a little more kneading...
It's a beautiful day for a walk.
What orders do I have for tomorrow again...?
It's better to get some rest.
I'm going to try and develop a new donut flavor.
The bread is baked to perfection today. Hehe.
Stop by the bakery whenever you want.
Did you need something?
What's up?
What should I ask Clala?
Prize Drawing
It was one of the things Dana really loved when we were in the city.
I always wanted to do it someday, so I'm glad we could host a similar event for our grand opening!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Clala"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Best-selling item
Munchy Bakery's most popular item is the carrot donut.
You have to try it at least once! It's my latest invention.
Customers
I try my best to remember every customer who comes to Munchy Bakery.
My mom always said it's one of the basic rules of business, and that I shouldn't forget it no matter where I go.
Hehe, she always emphasized it.
Every time I see Vinch, I get worried because he looks so frail.
What if he collapses one day?
I wish he would eat a little more.
Cleanliness
We're making and selling food, so of course it should be clean, right?
The food that goes out to our customers must be handled with the utmost care.
The city
When I first went to the city, I was so surprised.
There were so many people, and so many bakeries.
Of course, that wouldn't stop us from being the best!
Mistakes
That's why I try hard every day not to make any.
Remember this: Whether you're good or bad at it, business is a real-world battlefield.
Just one mistake can send a shop's reputation down the drain.
Alvin seems to really like our donuts.
Whenever we have a new flavor, he's one of the first to buy it, second only after Roy.
Then he gives me his review, and it's surprisingly accurate, so it's a big help. Hehe.
Bread research
A baker should never stop researching new products.
The moment they stop, they might fall behind other bakeries.
For a long time, I only focused on work and Dana.
So I don't really have any close friends.
I used to think it didn't matter, but now I'm so happy that you and everyone else are here.
Night walks
I love walking because it clears my head.
It helps me organize my thoughts and prepare for what I need to do the next day.
If you have time, you should try a night walk too, Ellie.
W-well! I don't really have time to think about things like that right now!
I think it's still too soon for me. I'll think about it once Dana is all grown up!
I still have a lot to do.
You have to be diligent every day to survive in this world.
Hobby
Work is the most important thing, so I prefer hobbies that aren’t too demanding.
The bakery is the most important thing, right? If it gets in the way of that, then I don’t consider it a hobby.
So I think something like sewing, just enough not to get tiring, is nice.
Since coming here, I’ve enjoyed sewing with [em1][lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))][/em1].
Rubrum was even cuter when he was a baby, you know?
Of course, he’s still cute now, though.
I still remember his face, all wrapped up in a cloth with just his little face sticking out.
But now he’s grown so much that he even knows how to brew tea—amazing, isn’t it?
Who would’ve thought he’d be able to brew such delicious [em1][lua(GetItemName("Food_StaminaReduceConsume_Lv1"))][/em1]?
Roy really does seem to know a lot about all sorts of things, doesn’t he?
I went to buy flowers to decorate the shop, and I ended up hearing all sorts of things from him.
Surprisingly, I heard all sorts of things, and they were really helpful. You should definitely listen to him next time too.
Things like [em1][lua(GetItemName("WallSticky_Jelly"))][/em1] turned out to be more useful than I thought, you know?
Oh my, did I talk too much?
During the day, it feels hard to think about anything other than working at the bakery.
When I used to run the shop with my parents, I still had some time to rest.
I’m thinking of putting a comfy chair like [em1][lua(GetItemName("ThanksGiving_Chair"))][/em1] in the shop.
Wouldn’t it be nice to sit and rest, even just for a little while? What do you think?
Isn’t that a dangerous place to wander around? I don’t really want to go somewhere like that.
And you know what—have you heard of [em1][lua(GetItemName("Gboolnori_Powder"))][/em1]?
It smells really nice, but it’s poisonous, so eating it would be dangerous.
Ellie, be careful not to put it in your mouth, even by accident. Just think how dangerous a place must be if things like that are around.
I heard there were people who, tempted by the smell, tried to mix it into food. Do you know how angry that made me?
The yarn is soft, and whatever I make turns out well. You should try using it too.
Clala's Personal Story 1
Is the Munchy Bakery in Wisteria run by you, Clala?
It's actually my second shop!
The second shop?
The first location is run by my parents back in the city we lived in after we left the village.
The bakery became quite famous. Though our bakery is in a small city, people would stop by from all over.
Even from Highlion!
Wow! You mean I can eat those delicious baked goods here too?
I'm already excited!
Thank you! My dad trusts my skills so much that he put me in charge of the second location.
Besides, Dana and I are a perfect team.
When we work, we're even better than my parents at our original shop.
Wow, that's amazing!
Well, if you were in the city, you could have opened a shop in a nearby or even bigger city.
Why did you come all the way to Wisteria?
Oh, I don't mean that I don't want you here! I'm so happy that you and Dana came!
But I just thought that you and Dana could have started in a much better place.
Well, you're right. But I just like it here. That's the only reason I came.
And wouldn't it be great if Munchy Bakery's second branch became even more famous?
It could become an attraction for the village. Hehe.
Haha, the village will be even more bustling!
Please visit our bakery often.
I'll always have some delicious baked goods, prepared with all my heart!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Clala"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
Clala's Personal Story 2
Clala, are you working today too?
What's this? Are you interested in me? Asking for a girl's routine.
Of course I am! Every time I see you, you're working.
I was worried that you weren't getting enough rest.
Fine! It's no fun to tease you when you're so serious. Hehe.
No, nothing. Did you ask if I'm getting enough rest?
You don't have to worry. I may not look it, but I have a set routine.
A routine?
That's right. First, I wake up at 6 a.m. and make bread.
6 a.m.?!
Of course, I have to let the dough ferment and rest.
I usually make bread or donuts for the morning delivery first.
Once I'm done with the preparations, I leave the delivery bread to Dana and get ready to open the shop.
In the afternoon, I continue to bake bread.
Interesting fact: Here at the second branch, we sell more bread in the afternoon than in the morning.
We do local business, but we also offer delivery services.
It seems that your bakery is quite famous now, isn't it?
Yeah. At night, I clean up the shop and rest.
I usually play with Dana or research new products.
What do you think? Nothing exciting, right?
I knew that already, but I think you're working too hard, Clala.
On the contrary, I keep working because I get anxious if I rest.
If my routine falls apart, my whole day is a mess. Hehe.
But don't push yourself too hard, Clala.
What's this? You're worried about me? You're so cute, Ellie.
Don't change the subject! I'm genuinely worried about you!
Alright, thanks for saying so. Don't worry. I'm still full of energy.
What were you and Dana like when she was little?
Me and Dana?
Yeah! I was curious because you and Dana have a big age difference.
We obviously get along well.
My Dana is so cute and lovely.
She's been that way since she was born.
Since my parents were busy, I pretty much raised her myself.
Do you know what Dana's first word was? 'Sister'! Hehe.
My parents were so disappointed.
You really love Dana, Clala.
Of course, she's my only little sister.
Besides, when I decided to move here, I was originally planning on coming alone.
Yeah, but a few days before I was supposed to leave, Dana found out.
She grabbed onto my parents' legs and mine, and bawled her eyes out.
<shake>I'm going to follow you, sister! No! I want to stay with you!</shake>
She made such a scene, I tell you. Hehe, I'm happy just thinking about that.
Now that I think about it, I'm glad I took her with me. I'm content with my life here.
I bet Dana would be happy if you told her that.
You know you can't tell Dana, right? I feel so embarrassed!
Oh, come on! Dana loves you so much, and she might run around the whole village if she found out.
That's the problem! The whole village will find out!
Ellie, stop laughing and listen to me! This is just between you and me!
Ugh, I shouldn't have said anything. So embarrassing.
Clala? You look tired today.
Wh-what are you talking about? I'm still full of energy!
Look me in the eye. Are you really okay?
W-wait, can you stop staring at me like that?
Ugh, fine, I give up. I surrender!
So? Do you want to tell me what's wrong?
It's nothing. Just like you said, I'm a little tired. I've had a lot on my plate lately.
But when I try to just lie down and rest, I get very anxious. Heh.
I'm sorry for making you worry.
...Clala.
You don't have to apologize! We're friends!
If something's bothering you or if you want to talk about it, just let it all out! I'm always here for you.
That's what friends are for, right? And when I'm having a hard time, you can help me too.
Hehe, fine, you win.
I was just busier than usual. I guess that was a little hard on me.
...Yeah, it was busy just like before.
Like before? Do you mean when you were living in the city?
That's right. You catch on quick. Hehe.
It was so busy back then. We hired more people, but it still wasn't enough.
I was so exhausted because I didn't have any time for myself.
It was even hard to get out of bed because I was so tired of dealing with people every day.
That's when it happened. I got a call from Wisteria.
So you came to Wisteria instead of another city because of that call?
Yeah, that's right. This village, you know, has a lot of memories.
It's where Dana and I were born and a very special village that helped me develop my dream of becoming a baker.
It holds so many peaceful and happy memories, so that's why I came back.
I'm glad I came, more than I ever expected.
Clala? Why are you staring at me?
Ellie. I'm only going to say this once, so listen carefully.
I'm so glad I met you. Thank you for always reaching out to me.
I'm happy to see you smile, too. I really am.
Ugh! Alright! Let's get back to work.
You've made me feel better. Thank you, Ellie!
I'm a witch who helps people. You can come to me anytime!
Munchy Bakery
Schedule
I have a ton of things to do today.
I'm thinking about making a new product!
Do you have any hobbies, Ellie?
My hobbies?
Well, I like to ride my broom, observe things, and eat delicious food until I'm stuffed... That's all I can think of right now.
Why? Don't you have any hobbies, Clala? Like playing a musical instrument, reading, or drinking tea?
Hmm... I guess if I had to think of one, my hobby would be being alone and quiet.
Oh really? So your hobby is [em1]contemplation[/em1]!
I don't think that deeply about anything, though.
I just like to walk alone quietly... or sit without thinking about anything.
I always think too much. When I have free time, I try to not think about anything at all.
Then... Isn't that just resting, not a hobby?
Is it? To be honest, I don't really have any hobbies or pastimes that I enjoy.
I was curious about what other people do. Even Dana has so many hobbies.
Then why don't you try to find a hobby you can do with Dana? Like making dolls together.
I want to, but Dana and I have different preferences.
But I guess doing anything together would be good, right?
Do you have any recommendations?
Of course! I had a hobby I always wanted to do with my siblings, if I had one that is.
How about learning to dance together? It's so much fun to dance with a partner!
I don't think our heights would match...
Then how about playing with dolls? You can do role-playing together!
Is that game really meant for someone my age...?
Hmm... This is difficult! I'll think about it some more.
No, it's okay. Just thinking about picking a hobby sounds like a headache.
But thank you for doing this for me.
Do you have something on your mind?
Don't worry about me.
Munchy Bakery isn't fully ready yet. Please give us some time!
I’ll trade it.
Your order's ready! Enjoy your meal.
Come by again next time!
Please do visit us again!
Ellie, thanks for coming to our bakery so often.
Maybe it's because of you, but things seem to be running smoother. That means we can increase the [em1]stock[/em1] of our bread.
Oh, and I have the time to make a few of our donuts with [em1]extra care[/em1]. Be sure to try them!
Ellie, perfect timing.
What a delightful surprise to see you!
Ellie, I have something to tell you.
You brought a tasting voucher! Want to trade it?
I won’t trade it.
I don't understand what you mean.
Wisteria seeds are seeds of emotion...?
Do you have any idea what it means? It is said that they need the power of wishes.
Hmm... I don't know much about trees or flowers.
Could this have something to do with witches?
I've often run into puns when buying sweets or ordering items at a Witch's House.
From experience, the best way to understand these things is to think [em1]intuitively[/em1] and a bit [em1]simpler[/em1] rather than overcomplicating it.
Area you going to gather starlight?
Did Dana and Rubrum tell you about this?
Explain the situation
Interesting... Alright, I'll come along.
We'll need to be careful. There are plenty of clumsy folks who might get hurt.
I heard Kyla could use some fresh inspiration. Maybe you could talk to her?
This is the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1], right?
I... I've wanted this for so long!
...I never thought someone would actually give it to me.
I'll treasure the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1].
Oh? I mean... why would you give me something like this?
Wait, [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]? Are you really giving this to me?
S-sorry, I really don't like this one... Can you think it through next time?
...It's fine, really. I'm not that bothered.
What's your plan? This is enough.
I'll make good use of it. Th-thank you...
...I'll gladly accept it. Thanks.
Who's that? Oh, it's Ellie!
Perfect timing! I happened to have some left.
I saved it because I thought you might want it. Hehe, enjoy!
Here you are! I've been waiting for my regular guest!
I was just thinking about you.
Actually, there's something I want to give you.
Just so you know, I don't want to always be on the receiving end.
And I feel like giving something today. Hehe.
Hehe, you came again today, Ellie.
I've been thinking about you a lot lately. Funny, isn't it?
This is the time you usually arrive. And soon, you'll be off again.
I often look at you without realizing it.
Silly, isn't it? Hehe.
These feelings are new to me. I'm really glad I came to this village.
I... I owe it all to you, Ellie. So, thank you!
Here's a gift. It comes straight from my heart. Hey, keep it between us, okay?
Ellie! I want to tell you something. Do you have a moment?
Hehe, I'm surprised you've been paying so much attention to me.
Of course! Our bakery is top-notch, and you hardly ever meet a girl like me!
...But relationships require someone to take the lead.
I've only focused on Dana and work, so I never paid attention to that.
I didn't try to do anything about it.
Yeah, I'm really a boring person. Yet, you still keep coming back to me. It's a bit foolish, isn't it?
And I fell for such a fool. Hehe.
So, here. Consider this a thank-you for all the gifts you've given me so far.
...I'll never forget the gifts you gave me. Hehe.
Munchy Bakery... Ah! A witch has arrived!
Ellie, you're Ellie Blueriver, right?
Yes, that's me. Just call me Ellie.
Hehe, very well! Nice to meet you, Ellie.
Could you grab the books I borrowed from Arin at the library?
I just need to go to Arin and pick them up, right?
Exactly. I borrowed quite a few... I hope that's alright.
No problem at all. I'll go see Arin then.
By the way, is this urgent?
Sorry for asking...
But since you came to our shop... I assume you came for the donuts, right?
Ah, I just came to say hello.
Really? Then let's chat over some delicious donuts.
It's the [em1]original[/em1] Munchy Bakery's most popular item, the [em1]carrot donut[/em1].
Wow! That looks amazing. Thanks, Clala.
You like donuts too, Ellie? Good! I'll try to make you a regular here.
Haha. A lot of villagers love desserts. I bet the bakery will be quite popular.
Roy, living across the street, is crazy about donuts.
Really? You're giving me insider info already? Wait...
Huh? What are you writing?
Oh, this is my work notebook.
I record anything useful for the shop, including info on potential regulars.
Ah, like making an encyclopedia.
Exactly. Running a shop requires knowing and remembering a ton of things.
Actually, I was busy revising the schedule I wrote before coming to town.
A schedule? Do you plan your days so carefully?
Of course. You don't do this?
I usually just go with my mood.
That's just a better way of saying "no plan at all."
This hat is called Virgil. Don't even trust a single word he says.
Virgil? Nice to meet you. I guess hat can't eat donuts, right?
You can put donuts in my mouth, but I can't guarantee the aftermath.
If I don't track everything in detail, I can't function.
A magical hat... if it eats a donut, disaster... thanks.
Clala, you really write everything down, huh?
Hmm? Can't help it. If I don't, I may forget something important.
Do you have anything to do now?
Nothing right now. I planned to go get the books just after organizing my schedule.
I still have some time to talk with you, Ellie.
Wow... That's a detailed plan...
After that, I'll need to work on recipes fitting Wisteria's vibe... and analyze each villager's preferences...
I see that you're quite busy. I want to help.
No, it's fine. I plan to stay up tonight anyway, so I have enough time.
Aren't you pushing yourself too hard? You might burn out.
Hmm... I am the manager of the second branch. And the shop just opened recently, so I have to work hard.
It's alright, I'll help.
Shall I bring you the books?
No need, Ellie. I borrowed a lot of books. It will be quite heavy.
I'm stronger than I look. If it's too heavy, I can just ride my broom.
Is that so? Well...
Actually, it's fine. I won't be reading them immediately anyway.
Then I'll come back after I take care of an important matter first. Is that okay?
Of course, Ellie. It's very kind of you to offer help already.
Thanks for the help. I won't forget it.
Clala, I've brought the books. Do you want to check if they're the right ones?
Thank you, Ellie. You're so thoughtful.
It's nothing, really. I'm happy to help. Is there anything else you need?
Nothing really. I have to handle the rest myself.
Then, can I ask you a question?
A question? Of course, go ahead.
What kind of book is [em1]Miscella and the Toy House[/em1]? I feel like I've seen it before... I just can't remember clearly.
Oh my, you know Miscella's doll collection too?
Then, the name [em1]Moonlight Jonnie[/em1] must ring a bell, right?
Of course! "When the moon rises, ta-da! When the stars shine, bling-bling!"
Hehe. There was a time when every child in town sang that song.
I wasn't really into dolls myself, but they were so pretty that I remember going to the doll shop several times with Dana.
That's right. These dolls were all the rage before I entered the School for Witches.
Dana loved those dolls so much... You and Dana have something in common, huh?
This book showcases all the dolls released by Miscella's Toy House.
I see. Are you trying to find a doll for Dana?
Unfortunately... Miscella and the Toy House no longer make dolls.
The witch who ran the workshop passed away a few years ago...
Ah... that's sad.
Since I can't buy the doll for Dana, I want to make one myself.
I'm not great at making dolls, but I want to try making one since she loved those.
Moving here left her with fewer friends, and I think this could cheer her up.
Wow... That's such a wonderful idea.
Clala, is it okay if I join you on this?
Honestly, I'm [em1]pretty[/em1] interested in dolls too.
I'd love to watch and learn as you make it, if that's alright.
I'll gather the materials for you to make the doll.
I feel like I'm relying on you too much...
Don't worry! Witches are supposed to help those within their reach.
Next time, let me help you when I can. How does that sound?
Sounds great.
Good. We'll need some thread made from [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))].
But to make the thread, it needs to be lightly singed but not burned. Do you know how to do that?
Hmm... I could figure out how to prepare ingredients for potions, but...
Maybe we should ask Enite about this?
I agree. The book doesn't explain how to process the thread. Alright, I'll leave it to you.
Oh, I almost forgot to bring the [em1][lua(GetItemName("BunchBooks"))][/em1].
Clala, I've turned the [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))] into thread and brought it.
Oh my, this looks really fine. Did Enite help?
Yes! Enite knew how to make the thread and did it for me.
She also said that you can ask her for help with the doll.
That's wonderful. Thank you. Ellie, do you have a moment?
I'd like to start making the doll right now.
Really? Is it okay if I just watch?
Of course. In fact, I want you to watch closely.
I'm not an expert either, but I'll be right here watching.
Then let's follow the instructions in the book.
That's probably the best. Following the instructions reduces the chance of mistakes.
Great. First, we need to do the stitches.
The book says... that the stitches should be a bit [em1]loose[/em1].
Oh? Hmm...
Why? Did Enite say something about it?
Enite suggested sewing a bit [em1]tighter[/em1] because the thread is weak.
Then what do you think? How should we do it?
I think...
Let's follow Enite's advice.
Good. Listening to someone experienced is always wise.
Next, we need to stuff the doll with cotton.
Ah, Clala. Before I came, Dana told me that—
She had a huge, super fluffy doll back at home, right?
Ah, that doll. Dana used to hug it every night while sleeping.
She didn't want to part ways with it. She probably wants a soft doll that she could cuddle and sleep with.
Really? But... the book says it's best to stuff it moderately.
What do you think we should do?
We should make it the way Dana likes
Since it's for Dana, let's stuff it more as she would want.
I'll put in more cotton, like Dana wanted.
Now for the final step: Choosing the color for the decoration on the head.
There's an orange one here. Let's use that. Dana likes it.
She loves the orange color of the [em1]Giant Carrot[/em1].
Orange?
But [em1]Moonlight Jonnie[/em1] originally had a blue head decoration.
Shouldn't we stick to the original decoration?
That's how Dana remembers it.
You're right... It's a tough choice.
It is... There are just too many decisions to make.
Ellie, would you decide for me?
It's difficult, but I'd say...
Exactly. It's a doll for Dana, after all.
The doll turned out great!
The stitching is strong... It is denser and rougher to the touch than the original doll.
With extra stuffing, it's cuter... but the characteristic flatness is going.
The orange decoration looks nice. Dana will love it.
I think she will! It's super cute!
Right? I hope Dana likes it.
It's a bit different from the doll on the book, but... Dana should like it.
She does love dolls, after all.
Thinking about Dana being happy makes me happy too.
Exactly. I'll give it to her as a surprise gift tonight.
If I give it to her before bed, she'll probably cuddle with it.
Ellie, thank you so much for your help. You've done me a huge favor.
Hehe, I'm just glad I could help! The Moonlight Jonnie is so cute! I want one too.
Maybe next time we can make it together!
Of course. I'll be here whenever you need me.
Then I'll be off. Hope Dana loves her gift!
Virgil, what do you think? Will Dana like this doll?
Dana? I think Clala seems to care more about it than Dana does.
I'm not the only one who noticed that, huh.
Exactly. Even though it's for Dana, Clala seemed to care more about the doll.
Maybe it's because Clala really wants to give a special gift to Dana.
Or... Maybe Clala doesn't realize Dana's interest in dolls has faded.
She's just holding on to memories of playing with them at the shop before.
That's definitely possible.
Even family can't always know everything unless it's put on the table.
True... It's really a tricky situation.
I think I should write a letter to mom and dad too.
They probably wonder how I'm doing since I haven't been in touch.
Have you considered that it might be your own assumption?
Virgil~!
This [em1]Moonlight Jonnie[/em1] looks exactly like the one in my memories.
Dana will be so touched when she sees it.
It's a bit different from the original [em1]Moonlight Jonnie[/em1]... Dana will like it, I think.
The blue decoration fits perfectly. It looks just like the doll in the shop.
And with the right amount of stuffing, it has that same soft, sinking feeling when you hold it.
The seams are slightly loose, but... it retains Jonnie's signature rustic look.
Follow the instructions
Yeah, sticking with the original decoration is best.
Right. Too much stuffing might tear the doll.
I'll follow the book and stuff it moderately.
Exactly. Following the instructions is the way to go.
I forgot to bring the [em1][lua(GetItemName("SpecialYarn"))][/em1].
Clala, I have something I want to say!
Is it about making donuts?
Oh, did Theo already tell you?
Yes, he came running and said that he wants a [em1]sweet, honey-filled donut[/em1], right?
Then he said he'd go get the honey himself.
Haha, Theo always acts first when he wants to do something.
Exactly. [em1]That's both his best and worst trait.[/em1]
I actually refused him once.
Hehe, running a shop, you hear these things naturally.
I know all about the incident where he made a mess of Enite's house.
I never expected Dana or you to do the same thing, though.
I... I'm already reflecting on it.
Besides that, Theo has been running around causing mischief all over the village too.
A little prank is one thing, but [em1]lately, he's gone too far.[/em1]
So I thought maybe he's up to some prank again this time.
Not this time!
Theo said he wouldn't mess around in the kitchen.
So I decided to trust him this one time. And you're here too.
Besides, it's a [em1]honey-filled donut[/em1]. As a baker, I want to try making one too.
Thank you, Clala.
Don't get too excited yet. We don't even have the ingredients.
I want to make a honey donut with an extra sweet aroma.
There's a special ingredient I want to use from [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1]. I can't exactly ask Theo for that...
That would be hard for Theo to get. I'll do it!
Hehe, really? Then just 2x [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RolyPoly_Water_Name"))][/em1] should be enough!
Once you have everything, come over [em1]after work at night[/em1].
The kitchen will be quite busy during work hours, and I might not be able to help while at work.
That's okay
Alright, then it's a deal!
Clala said to come [em1]at night[/em1].
If I give her the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RolyPoly_Water_Name"))][/em1], she might start making it right away.
Do you want to give Clala 2 [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "RolyPoly_Water_Name"))][/em1]?
Clala, I've brought everything!
You're here! Theo's already gathered everything too.
Oh really? Where is he?
He went to gather the other kids, saying it'd be more fun if everyone joined.
He said, "It's more fun together than alone!"
Looks like Theo's about to arrive. Shall we get ready?
Yes, let's do it!
It might take a while. I'll come back once I've dealt with the things on my hand.
A blue rose? I think Dana has mentioned it before...
Really? You know where to find it?
Sorry, I didn't note it down, and I can't recall it anymore.
I guess I have to ask someone else.
By the way, how's Roy doing?
Roy is a patron of the bakery, but he seems downcast recently.
I hope he can cheer up soon. He's not usually like this.
As for the blue rose, [em1]Dana[/em1] may know something.
If it isn't Ellie. Welcome.
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("LittleMandrake_Collect"))][/em1]?
Really? I'll leave it to you, then.
Could you bring them to me [em1]today[/em1]?
My request is as stated in the poster. Is that okay for you?
I need the items for my bakery.
I'm working on a new donut recipe, and I want them as a decoration.
They're for my personal use.
I may need them for making dolls, and I hope someone could get them for me.
I don't have time to go in person, because it's a whim.
I want to make something for the kids to play together.
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("FlowerBird_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Pompom_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Uru_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Tails_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("StoneCrocodile_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Ondori_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("BubbleShot_Collect"))][/em1]?
Could you get me 2x [em1][lua(GetItemName("Rodeo_Collect"))][/em1]?
Leave it to me, Clala. I'll find them for you.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("LittleMandrake_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
Clala, I've got you the items you want.
Really!
Thank you for making the time to help me! It means so much to me!
Here's your payment.
2x [lua(GetItemName("LittleMandrake_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("FlowerBird_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("FlowerBird_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("Pompom_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("Pompom_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("Uru_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("Uru_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("Tails_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("Tails_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("StoneCrocodile_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("StoneCrocodile_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("Ondori_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("Ondori_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("BubbleShot_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("BubbleShot_Collect"))] will do.
Give [em1]2x [lua(GetItemName("Rodeo_Collect"))][/em1] to Clala?
2x [lua(GetItemName("Rodeo_Collect"))] will do.
You need something cold but tasty, right?
The donuts I make are good even when at room temperature, but there's no reason they have to be cold.
Is this a special request? May I give it a try?
I actually have a recipe for this in mind already.
Of course! I'm the one asking for it, after all.
Thanks. I'll do my best to prepare something that won't disappoint you or Arin.
I'll make donuts that are tasty even at room temperature.
This is a perfect chance to impress both you and the witches!
Wait... so you're drawing on the power of the White Cat God to save the giant wisteria tree?
And to do that, you need an item that contains my wish to become friends with the villagers?
Exactly, in short.
Will it really work?
Can an item like that actually save the tree?
Of course. Trust me.
Hmm... alright.
Ellie, I'll trust you. I was planning to be friends with the villagers.
Do you need some time to think about the item that carries your wish?
No need.
I have it on me.
Wow... What is it?
Tada, a Munchy Bakery coupon!
Capitalism at work.
To get close to someone, you need to see them more often.
This coupon carries a wish to meet them again.
That's really nice.
Of course, they'll buy some donuts too while they're in the shop.
Can I have some of those coupons too?
Of course. You can have some.
Really? Great! I'll take just a few.
You can bury these coupons.
And these are yours.
No problem! Come by often.
If you need more coupons, just say the word.
Ellie, it’s been such a long time!
I just hope every day's filled with happiness!
Hehe, I even got you a present!
Okay! Let's give our best shot today!
And let's stick together forever!
Whew, I'm so, so busy!
Today's deliveries are...
<shake>Welcome to Munchy Bakery!</shake>
Here for some bread?
I've got the day off today!
What should we do for fun?
The night breeze feels amazing!
Thanks for all your hard work today!
Bye-bye! See you again soon!
Huh? Huh?
What's going on? Tell me!
Come on, don't keep me out of it!
Do you need something from me?
Don't you have any interesting news?
What should I talk about with Dana?
Bread Delivery
I do morning bread deliveries every day!
My sister's bread fresh out of the oven is the best in the whole world!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Dana"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Clala's donuts are my absolute favorite!
Especially her carrot donuts! You have to try them, they're delicious!
Math
If it's related to numbers, leave it to me!
Clala said I was amazing at math the other day!
You'd be surprised too, Ellie! Hehe.
Running
I'm surprised how fast I can run now because of doing deliveries every day!
I might even be quicker than Roy now!
Even he was impressed! Hehe.
Rumors
I hear so many interesting stories while making deliveries!
But whenever I tell Clala, she says I shouldn't waste time on silly gossip.
But why not? It's fun!
Verbal tic
I didn't notice that, but Clala says I repeat words without realizing.
I don't think I do it that much though!
Right, right? Don't you agree, Ellie?
Parents
The village we came from was much bigger than this one!
Mom and dad run the very first Munchy Bakery there!
If you're curious about the taste, stop by our second shop here!
She's always so kind to me!
But... I wish she'd stop nagging all the time! She's not mom!
Little Sister
Sometimes I wish I had a little sister too.
In a book Clala read to me, a giant raven would bring siblings.
But it's okay now! I've got Rubrum with me!
Love Stories
Love stories are my favorite!
Every time I hear one, it feels like butterflies in my stomach! Kyaa!
Hey, Ellie... do you have someone you like? Tell meee!
Promises
Clala always says, people who break promises are bad!
And if you lie too much... your butt'll get all fluffy!
Secrets
Wanna know a secret? I've got a mole on the bottom of my foot!
Only Clala and you know that, Ellie. So it's our secret, promise?
Now, let's go grab some carrot donuts!
Keep up the good work today!
My Room
Never tried it before?
Still, I want to try it. There’s a fish I want to see.
It’s a really beautiful fish~ I once saw it in the Cloud Valley.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_Angel"))][/em1]? That was its name. I want to see it again.
Dana is all grown up now, so sleeping alone at night isn’t scary anymore.
Still, on really dark nights, it does feel inconvenient to go to the bathroom.
If I can’t see, I might trip. And if I trip, it hurts, so I thought about what to do.
Kyla says she’s good at making everything except cooking.
But I think that’s true.
Last time, she brought [em1][lua(GetItemName("StarSeaCaveRock_Special"))][/em1], you know?
But she carved it into such a wonderful sculpture. Kyla really is as amazing as an older sister.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Map", "GreenForest_Waterfall"))] sounds like such a wonderful place.
The waterfall is so big that it’s fun to play there all day long.
But... I don’t really like [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "BubbleLizard_Name"))][/em1].
[em1][lua(GetItemName("BubbleLizard_Collect"))][/em1] looks kind of unpleasant, doesn’t it? Don’t you think so, Ellie?
But you know, Grandpa Alvin said that if I hang something like [em1][lua(GetItemName("MarchenDream_Walldeco_DreamChater"))][/em1], the moonlight will shine through and I won’t trip at night.
This is the first time I’ve ever had my own room.
So I’ve been decorating it with various things.
So I’ve been busy lately carrying around the things I need to decorate my room.
But you know... If I spread [em1][lua(GetItemName("PhantomJellyfish_Jelly"))][/em1] on the wall, it’ll sparkle and look pretty... What do you think?
But Grandpa Alvin doesn’t sell it. Ellie, do you know where to get one?
You said you're the delivery girl for Munchy Bakery, right?
Yup, yup! I bring fresh bread to everyone every morning!
Clala's bread tastes best when it's just out of the oven, so timing is everything!
Isn't it tiring, though? You help in the shop during the day too.
Nope, not at all! I love running!
When I see people smile after getting their bread, it makes all the hard work worth it!
Plus, I hear so many interesting stories while making deliveries!
Interesting stories?
Uh-huh! Gossip from all around the village!
Really? I've never heard any! Like what?
Okay, here's one I heard recently...
Rex swore he saw a giant noisy bird in Green Forest!
...A giant noisy bird?
Yup! <wave>Thiiis big!</wave> It showed up screaming so loud his ears rang for days!
He said it must've swallowed a steam engine!
Oh, I think I know what bird that is.
Huh. Guess it's still lurking in Green Forest.
Every delivery comes with new stories. It's so fun!
Sometimes I even wonder...
<shake>Ah! Never mind!</shake> Anyway, I love delivering!
And Ellie, you should drop by the bakery sometime! I'll be there!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Dana"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
What do you like to do for fun, Dana?
I love playing with my friends and with my dolls!
We have <wave>sooo many</wave> dolls at home. You should come see!
That many?
Uh-huh! Clala keeps buying me more!
She even got me a really pretty one just the other day!
Are you going to play with it today?
Nah, that one's boring now.
Today I'm going on an adventure with Rubrum in Green Forest instead!
Arin taught me about tea leaves, so we're gonna pick some!
Sounds fun, but Green Forest can be dangerous. Please be careful.
Don't worry, I know!
I'm older than Rubrum, so I'll keep an eye on him!
Oh? Then I'll count on you, big sister Dana!
Hehe... Big sister... D-Dana... Ahem! That's right! <shake>Leave it to me!</shake>
I always protect my brothers and sisters!
I'll keep Luvlum safe no matter what!
Dana, you don't look too happy today. Did something happen?
Oh, hi Ellie...
<wave>It's just</wave> that Clala nagged me again!
Nagged you?
Yup, yup! She made green pepper soup this morning.
I told her I hate green peppers, but she said if I didn't finish, I couldn't go out to play!
And yesterday, she told me to keep my clothes clean while playing or else.
She's not even mom, but she nags all the time! I hate it!
<wave>Ellieee</wave>... Can't you be my sister instead?
Wh-what? Me?
You're always so nice to me!
So why can't you be my real sister?
...Sorry, Dana, but that's not something I can be.
Even if I treat you kindly, you wouldn't truly feel like I was your sister.
Clala's words might sound like nagging, but it's because she worries about you so much.
Do you really dislike Clala that much?
...N-no, not really.
I know she takes care of me since mom and dad are always busy.
I like Clala too...
That's good. Even so, I can still be your "neighborhood sister."
If you've got something you can't tell Clala, I'll be there for you anytime.
...Okay! Ellie, it's a promise!
Dana, what's your dream?
My dream? Probably a baker, right? A great baker like my sister!
So your dream is to be a baker?
...Well, um...
Remember how you said I could talk about anything?
Honestly, I'm not so sure.
I do love baking! I really do want to be a baker like Clala!
Mom, dad, and Clala are all bakers.
So I thought I should be one too.
But I also love hearing people's stories. And I really love running!
Ellie... what should I do? Am I a bad kid?
Dana, don't ignore your own heart just because of what everyone around you is doing.
Why not try things you want to do one by one?
You can start today, like you already have with the bread deliveries.
You're not a baker yet, but you're doing great work as a delivery girl.
...If I say I want to do something different, it will make Clala sad.
Not at all! Clala will support you no matter what path you choose.
R-really? She won't get mad?
Of course not! And I have your back! Don't be afraid.
...Hehe. I'm glad I told you, Ellie.
Thank you so, so much!
You really are the <shake>best sister!</shake> Just after Clala!
Delivery girl
Games
Unhappy things
Action matters more than words!
Hi, hi! It's a wonderful day today!
Ellie! What's up?
I'm boooored~
My sister sells bread!
You should go see her!
Sorry, I don't really know.
Are you going to gather starlight? Count me in! Count me in!
Roy would love to gather starlight too.
He knows stories behind constellations as well as he knows the tongue of flowers.
He must really, really love stars!
A gift?
I've always wanted this! Thank you, Ellie!
Can I really have this [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
<shake>Yay, this is the best!</shake> I'm telling everyone! Thanks, Ellie! You're the best!
A [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1] for me?
Thanks, Ellie! Hehe.
Ellie, is it a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
O-oh... T-thanks...
Ellie... Why would you give me something like this...?
I really, really hate it... That's so mean...
Huh? You're not giving me anything? But I want a gift from you...
That's enough for today! Hehe.
Ellie! Hi! I've been waiting!
Guess what? I got you something today!
Hope you like it! Hehe.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Dana"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Chipchat_Add"))]
Ellie, Ellie! Over here!
Seeing you again today makes me <wave>so happy!</wave>
I'm always happy to see you.
Okay! I'm gonna do my best today!
And to cheer you on, here's a gift! You've got this!
<shake>Hi, hi!</shake> You came again!
Hehe, I was waiting all this time for you!
I feel so happy with you around! You always listen and are always nice to me!
It feels like having another sister.
Oops, Clala might get upset if she heard that.
So shhh! It'll be our secret, okay?
Promise! Hehe.
Here, this is for you. Thanks for everything!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Dana"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
<shake>Ellie!</shake> I've been waiting forever for you!
Here! Ta-da!
Surprised? I've been wanting to give it to you all along!
You're always so nice to me, Ellie.
And I want to know more about you too!
Everything you like, everything you don't <wave>all of it!</wave>
Then I'll know so much more about you, right?
'Cause I really, really like you, Ellie!
Let's play together more often!
Dana, what's your favorite color?
Favorite color? Hmm...
And why are you asking about colors anyway?
Just curious about what everyone likes. I like blue, myself.
Really? Then I pick orange! Like a [em1]giant carrot[/em1]!
Got it. Dana's favorite is... carrot orange.
Ahaha, Ellie, you're just like my sister! You write things down!
Of course. A witch has to know what people like. It's important.
Now, what's your favorite game?
Favorite game? Hmm... that's tough...
If I had to choose, I'd say running the shop is the most fun! Then hide-and-seek and racing!
How about playing with dolls?
Dolls?
Hmm... I used to love it when I was little, but not so much now.
Playing outside is way more fun! There's so much space to run around!
Yep! And when we moved, I left all my dolls behind.
But... I really wanted to bring my [em1]big, fluffy doll[/em1]. It was too heavy and huge to carry...
That must've been disappointing.
Any more questions? Nothing else?
No, that's enough for now. Thanks for answering!
Okay! Got it!
Don't you think Dana's lost interest in dolls?
She mentioned a [em1]big, fluffy doll[/em1], so maybe not completely.
She probably just doesn't have one here that she really likes.
True. That's probably why Clala wants to make one for her little Dana.
I like orange!
Its ears were so round and soft that touching them made me feel good.
I'm so gonna get scolded by Clala...
But if I work extra hard, maybe not as much. Leave this to me!
Cloud Valley always looks so pretty!
Look, even the river's gorgeous!
Dana, do you remember what we're here to find?
Oh, right, right! That weird creature!
There's so much to see here, so I keep forgetting. Hehe.
I looked around, but I don't see it nearby.
Maybe it's deeper inside the valley?
Good idea. Let's head further in.
Nope! Not around here!
We should check deeper in.
I-I think I've seen it!
They say Roy hasn't been very energetic lately.
I was idling near his place, trying to figure out a way to cheer him up. That was when I saw it!
He went out with the rose, a shovel and a watering can!
With [em1]a shovel and a watering can[/em1]...?
Yup, that's all I know. Was he heading somewhere faraway?
Thank you, Dana! That's the clue I was looking for.
If you need anything else, just say the word!
Roy? He went somewhere with [em1]a shovel and a watering can[/em1].
Maybe you should ask someone else.
This'll be my first time at a graduation ceremony!
What should I wear? Would a white dress be okay?
You can dress normally. There's no dancing or singing involved.
Really? Aww, that's a shame...
Instead, we'll share delicious food and stories.
For real? Then I’ll prepare looots and loooots of donuts that [em1]big sis makes[/em1]!
That sounds great.
And the more, people the better, right?
Of course. The more, the merrier! It's a celebration, after all.
Then I'll bring some of my doll friends too!
Uh... I don't think there'll be space for dolls...
Really? Huh. This ceremony's kinda different from how I imagined. That's a bummer...
Sooo... to befriend a tree, I have to bury a potion and some of my things?
Pretty much.
Dana, don't you want to get closer to the villagers, too?
Of course! Absolutely!
I wanna be friends with everyone!
And how will you do that?
Umm... umm... Oh, I know!
Singing! I'll sing for them!
Singing?
Yeah! Like the song Clala and I sing while making donuts together!
...How do you bury a song?
Beats me.
I have to bury the song?
Yup. To befriend the tree, you do.
Hmm... then, then...
I'll put the song inside this bottle!
A bottle?
Uh-huh! It can keep sugar and jam from spilling.
And it can hold a song too!
Sounds good.
Sounds good?
If it can hold jam, it can hold a song. Why not?
That makes no sense.
What matters is putting your heart into it.
See, Virgil? You don't get this stuff. I'll teach you someday, little brother.
...Little brother?
For now, let's bottle up that song.
Okay, okay!
<shake>Little brother?!</shake>
Quiet, Virgil. I'm bottling the song.
Don't worry, I'm too shocked to talk anyway.
Ahem!
<wave>Knead, knead~</wave> donut dough~
<wave>Knead and pat~</wave> tasty donuts~
<shake>Sizzle, sizzle~</shake> fried donuts~
<shake>Sizzle and crackle~</shake> tasty donuts~
<wave>Sprinkle, sprinkle~ sugar snow, twinkle twinkle~ stardust glow~</wave>
Share them all, donuts we made~ <wave>Munchy Donuts~</wave>
There, all sealed in the bottle!
Wow, thanks. That song was adorable.
Right? Right? I'll sing for you again sometime!
So, Virgil, was my song amazing?
I can't deny that the song was good.
When Ellie sings, though, it makes me regret being a hat.
<shake>Hey!</shake>
I hope the tree gets healthy real soon.
I wonder where the [em1]carrot[/em1] was?
You're still thinking about that?
We found everything except the [em1]carrot[/em1].
I think it's good that we never found the [em1]carrot[/em1].
There was something off about that "legendary" [em1]carrot soup recipe[/em1].
I just realized we never checked the men's restroom.
You actually have some [em1]shame[/em1]? I thought you knew nothing but adventures.
We searched the whole school save for that place, but we never found the [em1]carrot[/em1].
That means the carrot was in the [em1]<wave>men's restroom</wave>[/em1]!
A carrot in the men's restroom? What an odd sense of humor...
I should write Jenny a letter asking her to look through the men's restroom.
Can't you ask Will instead? It's the men's restroom after all.
Nope. If that coward finds it, he'll take it to the professor bawling, like before.
Keep in mind that if it weren't for Will, you'd be in jail right now, instead of on a train.
... Ugh. I'm so bored!
It's a flashback. Flashbacks are supposed to be boring.
I see why no one else wants to ride this god-awful train. It's boring enough to drive anyone insane.
A ticket for this train costs 500 pies.
And its stop? The Witch's House in [em1]Highlion[/em1], where all roads lead to.
You're [em1]magna cum laude[/em1] at School for Witches.
Whatever! I don't care about any of that!
How did I become [em1]magna cum laude[/em1] anyway? I even sneaked into the forbidden principal's office twice!
Three times.
And I looked through the forbidden books in the hidden library in the school basement!
I still remember that horned rabbit that was as big as a house.
No wonder Will started crying.
So how on earth did I manage [em1]magna cum laude[/em1]!?
I simply didn't want to lose!
Cut it out and sit quietly. This is a [em1]train only for those who want to succeed[/em1].
The Witch's House might be dark and damp, but it's only three years of your life.
Fine, fine. Enough with the lecture.
The thought of taking off my [em1]shoes[/em1] when I got off the train alone was disturbing enough.
Shoes? For what?
We've just arrived, and you're already planning to get us into trouble?
I won't! I won't fool around the moment I get there!
I didn't know you had self-control.
Don't you know about the [em1]terrible city of rules[/em1] that is Highlion?
The first thing to do here is to take your shoes off as soon as you get off the train.
I heard that Jenny's older sister was wearing [em1]tall lace-up boots[/em1] when she first arrived at Highlion.
This is my first time hearing something like that.
See! Mom bought me new shoes as well!
Didn't Aria just mean to encourage you?
No, dad also did say that comfortable boots would be better.
That’s strange.
It's true! Ask someone else if you don't believe me.
So she almost couldn't get off because she was busy untying the boots.
It really is an abandoned Witch's House.
Taking that into consideration, it looks okay.
Although it’s not that clean.
Since the Witch's House is managed on her own.
It doesn't seem to be in a very good condition considering how dirty it is.
The bed looks quite comfortable, though?
I guess I can just sleep here.
Um, well, since the Witch's House is a [em1]public institution[/em1].
And it's better than sleeping outside.
It’s okay to sleep one night or so.
What's with that face? You slept on a nice, fluffy bed.
Yes but...
I dreamt that I was sleeping on the train.
All that effort not to sleep on the train, only to dream of just that?
You should have just slept on the train.
No, that's not it.
I slept very well, actually.
I can almost hear the [em1]sound of the train[/em1], though.
Wait... Isn't that indeed the [em1]sound of the train[/em1]?
Is it departing already?
Let's go have a look!
What on earth is that thing?
It's called the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "Gaga_Name"))][/em1]. They say it's a bit insane.
Quiet. I don't need this information now.
It's your fault for oversleeping. Don't blame the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "Gaga_Name"))][/em1].
Fine. Whatever. Just be quiet.
I wonder where the previous witch has gone.
She probably left a long, long time ago.
She can be living well somewhere in Lucerine Ortu.
This house is such a mess.
It reminds me of your room.
My room was cleaner than this.
You are right if it's the dust that you're talking about.
It's also messy [em1]in front of the desk[/em1] over there, Ellie, in case you didn't notice.
Stop bossing me around like a professor.
I finally managed to get out of school!
All done cleaning!
There's some dust over there, Ellie.
Don't leave food behind, Ellie.
I told you not to go inside the principal's office, Ellie.
You should have listened.
Oh, this is a [em1]witch elevator[/em1]!
That's why you should listen to your professors.
Let's hurry up and go down.
What if there's a scary monster?
You think so? Oh, I'm so excited!
Wow. Look at this, Virgil.
This looks like the [em1]Dispensary[/em1]. You can make [em1]potions[/em1] here as long as you've got the proper [em1]tools[/em1].
But it needs some [em1]cleaning[/em1] first.
Wow... [em1]Cleaning[/em1] again...
I know what this is! It's an [em1]Extractor[/em1]!
We used it sooooo many times at school. It was a slightly smaller one though.
It would be hard to use. Look at the [em1]glass bottle[/em1] underneath.
Oh, that's true. It's broken.
I'll need a friendly toad at least.
I’ll need to get a [em1]glass bottle[/em1] first in order to use this.
Let's look for one.
How come everything here is broken?
You can't expect to find things intact in a place so dirty and messy.
Still, the pot is fine.
You need to at least fix the extractor in order to make potions.
Alright. Let's go to the [em1]village[/em1] first.
A [em1]Roaster[/em1]? Ugh, I hate this thing.
After you put in the collected items, it's a long and anxious wait.
It's quite convenient as long as you remember to toss the collected items in before hand.
But it seems to be in bad condition?
Really? Oh, yes. There is no handle for winding the spring.
Where would I get a Roaster handle?
Still, the cauldron is fine.
We may find something in the village.
Yeah, let's go to the village first.
It's okay. The Roaster is not needed for the basic recipes.
Wow, this pot looks pretty good.
I think it was made by the "[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteriorPropTheme", "BasementBasic"))]."
And it has a very classic design.
I've only ever used the cheap pots at school. Finally, I get to use a good one!
Do you remember how to use one?
Use processed [em1]ingredients[/em1], [em1]heat[/em1] them precisely, and [em1]stir them in the right direction[/em1].
And at last!
At last! You'll end up with a proper [em1]potion[/em1].
I actually like the way Ms. Olivia speaks.
Still, the cauldron looks fine.
You’ll be able to make a potion if you have the ingredients.
The processing tools are in bad condition though.
Since there are some discarded ingredients...
Let’s make the potion we need using them for now.
Huh? This isn't a [em1]village[/em1]?
Look over there, Ellie! It's a [em1]prickly vine[/em1] this time.
And it's quite huge and thick.
What do I do with the Extractor?
First, take a look around it.
Wow, it's really big.
Too big for the "[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))]," I think.
Hm... We need [em1]another solution[/em1].
We'll have to stay at the Witch's House for a while.
Look at this, Virgil!
It's a [em1]<wave>prickly vine fragment</wave>[/em1].
It seems to have worked a little bit.
But the vines will regenerate soon.
With this, we might be able to figure out the exact [em1]<wave>species of these prickly vines</wave>[/em1].
They aren't even in the Encyclopedia. How are you going to figure that out?
Let's show the fragment to someone and ask them about it.
Oh, wouldn't a person living around here know something?
Isn’t it heavy?
It's not.
Really. Don't talk to me now.
Our village is just a little further from here!
But we cannot pass through now because of the prickly vines...
Let's go to the witch's house for now and find a way.
Sorry, you can't go beyond here.
Why did the train stop?
There is [em1]something[/em1] in the train's path.
We're trying to get rid of it.
Something's in our way? Is it a boa constrictor?
A boa constrictor? No, no. It's a strange [em1]prickly vine[/em1].
A strange prickly vine?
Yes. It wasn't there when we passed this place a little while ago, but it seems to have grown overnight.
A regular axe can't cut into it. What a headache.
We've contacted the witches, so it will be fixed in no time.
Can I take a look? I happen to be a witch myself.
But you're our passenger. It's our responsibility to make sure you're safe.
We'll take care of it, so please be patient.
Can I just take a peek...?
I'm sorry.
Is there any way I can help?
How long will this take?
All you have to do is sit tight.
Oh, geez.
If we can take care of it on our own, it shouldn't take long.
But it might take some time if it is a problem that we can't solve.
Look, Ellie! It's a [em1]quest mark[/em1]!
All I see is dust and cobwebs that we have to [em1]clean up[/em1].
Exactly what I'm talking about.
Let's find something useful while [em1]cleaning[/em1].
Good, I think it’s working properly.
Let's pass by quickly and find the core in the meantime.
Anyone there?
Is anybody there?
Seems like nobody is here.
This Witch's House may have been abandoned.
After all, even the Witch Administration can miss out things.
Alright, let's go inside!
The house is a bit messy.
We'll just stay for one day. Who cares?
That doesn't matter. Going by [em1]train[/em1] is the only way.
What's going on? It won't even budge!
It must be stronger than the secret door in the principal's office.
What are these [em1]fragments[/em1] coming out of it?
At your feet.
It's so beautiful.
Yes! It’s really really beautiful!
Rubrum, can you go to the prickly vines and wait for us there?
We'll come as soon as the potion is ready.
I'll be waiting in front of the vines.
Now we just need to collect some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))] and make [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))][/em1].
Are you okay?
Yeah... I'm okay.
Good, I got the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))].
Let's go back to Rubrum now.
Let's get rid of the weed first.
There's too much.
It would take forever to pull all this out using hands.
Take a look at the bin over there.
It might contain a potion to get rid of weed.
Wow, there really is one.
I guess the previous witch made a few of them.
Hmm... There are 3.
But that's not much.
I don't think I can get rid of them completely with these.
Well, then you'd have to use your hands.
It doesn't look like there's anything here, so let's do the front of the house later.
There’s nothing here.
Then we'll have to use another tool.
Is there another tool?
Yes, there is a wonderful tool.
Your hands.
Alright, I think that was all?
It's clean now. Good.
Now it's time to tidy up the house.
I should make [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))].
You must make [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))][/em1] before you go.
I should go check on Rubrum first.
Alright now, have some patience and stay seated.
Yeah, look outside...! Look at that mountain!
It must be hiding a cave with a tiled chamber deep within. There would be tall pillars, strange statues... and a giant door, in front of which you'll find...
Sounds like the prologue to a story where you awaken a terrible demon.
Wait, hold on! Virgil, shut up and look out the window. At the summit of the mountain.
There's a [em1]gigantic shining tree[/em1].
A [em1]<wave>gigantic shining tree</wave>[/em1]!
Why is it shining? Does it have luminous flowers? It must be beautiful up close.
Give it up. This train won't stop for two days.
Ugh... I want to get out now!
I hope we crash.
Fat chance of that happening, so just stay bored.
After all, you signed up for three years of even more boredom.
Aren't there any crocophants nearby?
What about boa constrictors?
This isn't a jungle.
Train robbers?
This isn’t the wild west. It’s a healing game, remember?
Hey, a boa constrictor!
The correct line is, "What's going on?"
There's no station here. Why are we stopping?
I'm not sure. Maybe there's something wrong with the train.
I doubt it's a boa constrictor, though.
I don't care if it's not a boa constrictor!
Please just say there's some massively critical issue... Please, please...
I’m bored...
But you just sat down.
This is torture...
Stare out the window if you're so bored.
Please...
If I should ask something, it would be about the mountain right outside there!
A critical issue, perhaps?
The train cannot continue its journey due to a [em1]critical issue[/em1]...
Attention. The train will stop until [em1]tomorrow morning[/em1], and the departure time...
Can we go outside?
...will likely be announced tomorrow. We will depart immediately if possible...
Okay, I'll be back in a bit!
In the meantime, please avoid wandering too far from the train...
I'm not sure if you remember but...
Of course I remember! The shining tree is at the [em1]peak[/em1].
No, not that.
We have to get back by [em1]tomorrow morning[/em1].
Then we should get going!
Alright, I got rid of the core.
Those annoying vines should be gone by now!
Why are there so many things blocking the path?
This must be a forest with many secrets.
Looks like a barrier made with a [em1]witch sigil[/em1].
Witch sigil? Is there a witch here?
There was or...
Do you remember how it works?
School hammered it into my head. Shouldn't be an issue, as long as it's drawn well.
Virgil, look at that!
It's grown so much.
It wasn't that big a while ago.
That must be an adult Honey Pumpkin.
We'd better get rid of it before it grows any more.
We haven't been to the place behind it. And to go there, we must get rid of it.
What? I’m not even a gardener. Why...?
Oh, I guess it can't be helped to get to the new place.
I guess I should make [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))][/em1].
Don't forget to remove the [em1]core[/em1] if you want to avoid repeating the same thing.
It's simple. I've made it once before.
By now, this much is easy.
Let's go to the new place now.
How do you feel?
<shake>What do you mean?</shake>
Your molars might fall out. Relax a bit when you speak.
I can't believe Jenny deceived me...
There's a reason why she's your friend.
Now, go back to your seat quietly and wait until we've arrived.
We still have three more days to go.
Three more days... that's as terrible as the smell of spotted shiitake mushrooms.
Ugh... gross...
a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))]!
I even went to a hidden library because I wanted to make it.
I'm so lucky to find this here!
They don't normally use a skeleton design as a symbol of luck, right?
The point is, it looks like it can blow things up.
And there's something I want to blow up.
Don't be too worked up.
Then shall we go try it right away?
I missed this feeling.
Do you plan to destroy everything on the top of getting into trouble?
Hey! What do you take me for?
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))]... Don't you feel the almighty power just from the name?
When in trouble, throw it!
Break it if you can't have it?
Sometimes it takes boldness to overcome a crisis!
Don't you think it's strange that a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))] was dropped in that secluded forest?
Someone might have hidden it thinking that it's treasure, like Rubrum.
Go! [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))]!
Or someone might have accidentally dropped it.
Accidentally dropped a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))]?
Ugh, whatever. What matters now is that I have a [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BoomPotion_Name"))].
I think the cat dropped something. What is it?
Looks like a [em1]witch chalk[/em1].
That thing you use to draw sigils?
It looks a little different from the one we were using at school...
It's just a different packaging.
This [em1]box[/em1] looks pretty useful.
I can put stuff in here when my pockets are full.
Wow, it's beautiful.
Where are those butterflies going?
Wouldn’t they go back to where they came from?
But the flower...
Oh, over there! Over there!
How’s your leg?
It still hurts a bit...
But I have to hurry up and get back to the village.
If not, Granny will scold me.
Okay. Leave it to me.
I'll get rid of that giant prickly vine.
I'll get you back to your village. Don't worry.
Oh, before that, I should treat your [em1]leg[/em1] first.
Rubrum, wait here for a moment.
We must return to the train by [em1]tomorrow morning[/em1].
The [em1]shining tree[/em1] is at the [em1]peak of the mountain[/em1], so go quickly if you want to see it.
Yeah, yeah.
Wow! It's the [em1]shining tree[/em1]! The same one we saw from the train!
Check this out, Virgil. There are a ton of butterflies on it.
You're right. The butterflies seem to be glowing.
These are [em1]Bluemoon Butterflies[/em1].
They give off a subtle moonlight.
The light from these butterflies has the same power as [em1]actual moonlight[/em1].
That's why strange things always happen in their habitat — They change the environment.
Aren't they beautiful? A [em1]giant tea tree[/em1] with [em1]butterflies glowing with moonlight[/em1].
It's not just beautiful. It can be called an amazing sight to behold.
Is this a pretty magnificent discovery?
I'll have to write a letter to the school!
Fill up the [em1]Encyclopedia[/em1] and all, right?
Just don't be late.
Let's go back the [em1]way we came up[/em1]. There might be other strange things.
Actually, those two life forms are not rare themselves.
What? You mean, although the sight is stunning, it's not special?
The fact that those two are together is the amazing part.
This is a [em1]Bitter Grape Tea Tree[/em1]. I don't think the tree is the one that's shining.
What about those two being together?
They're usually raised together artificially to get [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))][/em1] in Lucerine Ortu.
But it's uncommon for them to be together naturally like this.
Um, anyway, we did find something, right?
Oh... Wow...
Ellie? Let's go back to the train...
[em1]<shake>Look at that, Virgil!</shake>[/em1]
A shining white cat?
I've never seen anything like that before!
Ellie? We have to–
[em1]<shake>Let's go after that creature!</shake>[/em1]
Look, Virgil! There's a house!
That's a [em1]witch's house[/em1], isn't it?
It looks pretty old.
I guess we can talk to the master witch here and stay here for a while.
It doesn't look like there are people inside...
If there's no one, we might stay for a while.
Isn't it natural for an [em1]apprentice witch[/em1] to stay at a [em1]Witch's House[/em1]?
Huh? Where did the cat go?
It really is the [em1]sound of the train whistle[/em1]!
I think it's about to leave.
Let's hurry back.
I woke up just in time.
Glad I didn't sleep in.
Where's the [em1]train[/em1]?
Hahaha! Looks like that [em1]bird[/em1] was imitating [em1]train whistle sounds[/em1].
But where's the train?
It's gone to Highlion, of course.
Then what do we do now?
Let's look around [em1]the area[/em1]. We may find some clues.
Why are you so calm?
I've been through much worse with your mom.
Oh, it's a notebook.
Might be useful later.
This is a potion ingredient, isn't it?
You've used them in school countless of times.
Are witches usually this sloppy?
Sloppy or not, they're careful with their ingredients.
Then I guess the witch that lived here was really sloppy.
Or she left in a hurry.
Looks like [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1].
It's a demon that grows in gardens.
The vines grow so fast that you can never get rid of them by hand.
To remove the vines, you must find and destroy the [em1]core[/em1] hidden somewhere.
If we find the core, we can remove the vines, right?
Or just be good and return to the train.
That can’t happen.
Let's go look for the core. It must be nearby.
Since the core gives off [em1]light[/em1] when you touch the vines, you'll be able to find it.
It’s a hill.
It won’t be easy to climb.
Look over there. There are vines hanging on the hill.
I'll be able to climb that much.
That's bad news.
We're almost there.
Wow... A witch's house...
A [em1]letter[/em1]!
How nice of them to leave a letter behind.
Let's see... I think it's from the bartender on the train.
You're probably shocked to see that the train is gone.
I heard that a witch who arrived in the middle of the night got rid of the prickly vines in no time.
Unfortunately, the train couldn't wait any longer and had to leave right away.
But don't worry. The train will come back and there's a [em1]village[/em1] nearby where I used to live.
You can just spend some time there. There should be a [em1]sign[/em1] in the forest. Follow it and find the [em1]village[/em1].
When you arrive at the [em1]village[/em1], please send Enite and Arden my regards.
"Bartender"
He says there's a [em1]<wave>village</wave>[/em1], Virgil!
Are you even a little upset that we missed the train, Ellie?
There's a [em1]village[/em1] nearby!
But we didn't see one yesterday.
It was probably too dark to see. Let's look for it again.
See if there is a [em1]sign[/em1] as well.
How about [em1]cleaning[/em1] the witch's house?
We might have to stay there until we find the village.
Please try not to sound so excited. We missed the train, remember?
That place we saw earlier must be the [em1]village[/em1].
It's okay since there is a village, right?
I guess we can just wait here.
You never know what might happen.
We must get rid of the [em1]prickly vines[/em1] at the village entrance.
And check if there really is a [em1]village[/em1].
It’s the bartender’s letter. Shall I read it again?
As long as we find the village.
And clean the witch's house.
You heard me, right?
Well then. I might as well add more to the Encyclopedia now.
Great. They're stuck to the tree as expected.
Wow, there are tons of shining [em1]butterflies[/em1]!
We're going to make them all go away now, right?
I feel so bad for them all of a sudden.
It's for the tree's sake. Hurry up and throw the potion!
I'm here. Now let's hurry up and get rid of the annoying vines.
You won't suffer any loss because of me, will you...?
Don't worry about that.
I'm the one who [em1]decided[/em1] to do it. It's what I really wanted to do.
And this is my [em1]choice[/em1].
It's no a big deal.
You can come to the witch's house anytime you want.
Are you going to stay here?
Yeah, I think I'll stay here throughout my apprenticeship.
Really. Let's spend more time together, Rubrum.
Okay! Let's spend more time together, Ellie!
Hurry up and go home for now.
Your granny must be worried. I'll find you later.
Okay! See you in a bit!
Yeah~
Woohoo! The [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))][/em1] is ready!
Let's go get rid of the prickly vines now!
Woohoo! The [em1]"[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "SunlightPotion_Name"))]"[/em1] is ready!
Let's go to the tree right away!
Ellie, the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))][/em1] is...
Don't worry, I [em1]already[/em1] have the ingredients.
You already have them?
Now, let's find the [em1]"[lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))]"[/em1].
Do you really want to go [em1]now[/em1]?
Have you done [em1]everything you want to do[/em1]?
I still have stuff to do.
Stop wasting time.
If you're done, let's talk to [em1]Rubrum[/em1] and go.
There's nothing more to do!
Heehee! I'm fast, aren't I?
You made it all the way there in such a short time?
Come on, Ellie!
Witch's House~ Witch's House~
You're not really giving me a chance to catch up.
No one can catch a running child. They move like the wind.
How energetic.
Children of that age are bound to run around no matter where they are.
Was I like that too?
Oh boy, your mother was out of tricks when it came to you.
Yeah... Probably?
Can you walk?
Yup…!
Then let's go to the Witch's House together.
This should work.
I'm stuck in a spiderweb. Hehe.
My arms hurt.
Aren't you uncomfortable?
It actually feels like I'm floating. It's fun!
But I'm scared of big spiders.
I'll help you down, don't worry.
I'll help you down right away.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))][/em1] is found on [em1]cliffs[/em1].
Like this.
Wow, Virgil. There's someone stuck in the [em1]spiderweb[/em1].
I think he's lost consciousness.
Is he even alive?
I don't know... Um...
Gah!
He woke up.
Who...?
A witch?
Wow, this is my first time seeing an apprentice witch!
And it's my first time seeing a person caught in a spiderweb.
My name is [em1]Rubrum[/em1].
I live in the village with Granny.
But now I'm stuck in a big spiderweb.
He doesn't seem to understand the gravity of his situation...
A big spiderweb means there's a big spider nearby.
You be quiet!
Don't worry. You'll be fine.
I'll help you down.
You have to be careful when dealing with spiderwebs, Ellie.
It looks pretty strong. One wrong move, and you'll get stuck in it yourself.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))][/em1] works best against insects.
Just one [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))][/em1] should be enough.
I learned that [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))][/em1] grows on [em1]cliffs[/em1].
I'll bring it soon.
Yeah, come back soon.
If it is [lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MapleHerb_Name"))], I have it.
Hanging on the cobweb's too boring.
My legs are killing me. I can't walk any further.
No wonder this kid dashed around so energetically.
I'll carry you then.
I'll give you treatment at the Witch's House.
Are you okay? Are you hurt?
The spilled bottle, scribbled paper and a book... What a mess.
Just brush off the dust.
Just brushing off the dust might take a lifetime...
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))][/em1]? Looks like a [em1]recipe[/em1] for potion.
Judging from the mark, this should be a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))][/em1].
[lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "LimitedRecipe"))]s are also [em1]disposable[/em1].
I guess it belongs to the previous witch.
It reads, "a potion with the [em1]power of moon[/em1]." The ingredients are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Encyclopedia", "MoonFlower_Name"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Phoenix_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
They are all very expensive.
I'll use it someday. Let's have it ready for now.
Yup, alright.
There is also something underneath.
Where? Oh, you're right.
You mean I learned how to read these strange symbols?
Your score wasn't bad either.
I don’t remember anything.
Anyway, let's have a look first.
Um... Looks like a [em1]recipe[/em1]...
It seems like [em1]moon’s...[/em1] something...
I have no idea. I got a headache.
Take a look if you remember later.
Yeah! I should put it away and revisit it later.
This desk would be nice to use as a workbench later.
There's no use for it now, though.
Ellie, I hope you haven't forgotten.
For [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))], you need [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Phoenix_Collect_Name"))][/em1].
But there's no way we can find a phoenix around here.
We have a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "Phoenix_Collect_Name"))][/em1] right here.
You told me all about it earlier.
Oh, Ellie... That's not a good idea.
If we do that, we will not be able to get back on the [em1]train[/em1].
That means you will not make it to [em1]Highlion[/em1].
That again?
You just like it here better.
You just don't like the witch's house in Highlion.
Stop being childish. You're going to regret it later.
No, Virgil.
What I will regret is not doing this right now. I'm sure of it.
You have to be smart about this...
Ugh.
Great! I have all the ingredients now.
Ellie, you’re worse than Aria sometimes.
Oh, please. I'm nowhere near as good as my mother.
That wasn't a compliment.
Alright, now let’s make [em1]'[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "MoonOil_Name"))]'[/em1].
Quit acting like a saint!
This place seems fun to you, that's all.
Virgil, try not to say stuff that makes me sound like a bad guy, will you?
It's a [em1]<wave>Happy Ending</wave>[/em1] for all if I have fun and they're happy, isn't it?
Will the professors get angry?
"Like mother, like daughter..." That's what they'll say.
Well that's great!
It's not a compliment.
Alright! Let's head to the village now!
I think this road leads to the [em1]village[/em1], but the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1] is in the way.
Hmm... Would [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))][/em1] work?
It's a basic [em1]recipe[/em1], and the ingredients on the Dispensary floor should suffice.
Okay! Let me show you what I've got!
Let's go to the [em1]Witch's House[/em1] and figure it out.
The road is blocked.
Alright, throwing the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))] here shall fix it.
According to the [em1]sign[/em1], the [em1]village[/em1] must be this way.
But the road's blocked by the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1].
It won’t explode either.
Hehe, I thought we’d need it, so I made one in advance!
We won't be able to pass by unless we get rid of it.
This alone won't fix it, but you can get in and destroy the core when the vines are gone.
Good, use that.
I just need to get in and destroy the core when the vines are gone, right?
And also clean up.
Awesome. The [em1]<wave>"Stubborn Weed Elimination Potion"</wave>[/em1] is complete!
It's "Extermination," not Elimination.
Anyway, it's ready!
Okay. Don’t worry.
You must use it carefully since there are no more ingredients.
Let's go throw it at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1].
Why did you make this?
Do I need a reason for making a potion?
A normal person would.
It’ll be used somewhere.
Just in case.
Just because I wanted to make it
No reason.
Just because I wanted to make it.
You never know. It might be useful for something.
People normally make it when they need it.
Let's look for the village for now.
Throw it at the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1], find the [em1]vine core[/em1], and remove it.
Because [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))] is just a [em1]temporary measure[/em1].
I got it!
I missed...
Well, it happens.
I thought we’d need it, so I had one hidden.
Don’t ask how.
You'll only embarrass yourself.
Be careful this time.
Or you'll embarrass yourself a lot.
Here it goes!
Yes! I'm all done [em1]cleaning[/em1].
I think we're pretty well-equipped now.
And we can make [em1]potions[/em1] now.
First, let's go find the location of the village!
We can't stay here forever.
Let's look for the [em1]sign[/em1].
There was [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "LittleHoneyPumkin"))][/em1] in front of the village...
The [em1]"Stubborn Weed Elimination Potion"[/em1] should do it, right?
It’s a [em1]'[lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "BadGrassPotion_Name"))]'[/em1].
Alright, then let's make potions in the [em1]witch's pot[/em1].
Only half of this stuff remains, so you can't process.
You can't process properly with broken tools.
Someone left their ingredients on the floor. Let's try making with them for now.
Anyway, let's get started!
Check the recipe in the Encyclopedia.
You can probably use the ingredients you were lucky enough to find.
Let's try making some with the stuff we picked up earlier!
What do you mean why? Why not?
I asked because people usually have reasons.
This much is easy.
Then let's go back to the Little Honey Pumpkin we saw earlier.
Full of energy today as well! <shake>Hahaha!</shake>
By the way, Ellie, here's something for you!
A gift to say hello!
What else could it be? A gift, of course! Come on, take it!
Meow~ Hey kitty, kitty~ Come over here.
Where are the cats now...
Seeing them here in the restaurant brings back memories!
Come on in! Fancy a drink?
Perfect weather for a stroll today!
Oh, need some help?
I'll show it to you someday when it's completed!
Hmm... This is how it should be done.
Came to see me, have you? Hahaha!
I got plenty of time.
What should I talk about with Bjorn?
Wisteria hace changed a lot.
I do miss the old days, but it's not bad now either.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Bjorn"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
I think gifts really are wonderful
They may not convey all my feelings, but at least they give form to them!
Trains bring back memories.
Perhaps trains are an inseparable part of my life. Hahaha!
You meet them more than you think if you work at the Ministry of Railways.
Though it's really difficult to guess the age of witches simply by talking to them.
Hahaha! Arden and his meat stew have never changed. It's really reassuring!
Some things fade with time, but I want to keep this chapter in my memory.
Call on me if you ever need help!
It's nice to take it easy like this.
Books
After leaving the village by train and spending a lifetime on one, now I've returned.
It's not as bustling as the city, but quite lively for a small village.
Despite appearances, I do enjoy reading.
You should read too. Reading books is like peaking into other people's lives, something you can't really do in your everyday life.
Joke
Do I seem like someone who's bad at jokes?
Ugh... I even received a book about jokes as a gift, and it's so difficult to understand.
Do you know...?
...What's with that look of disbelief on your face? It's a true story.
Essay
I've always thought about writing an essay about my life.
I have a long history with Enite! It brings back childhood memories!
...The fear then still lingers.
Elders
I still have a long way to go.
Ellie, you're quite young. You should listen to elders more.
Stories
There are many folktales and legends in this village.
If there's a chance, I want to tell you all these stories, just like when I was a kid!
Hey, I was a boy myself. Much like the teenager named Vinch. Hahaha!
Enite is older than me, so I once carelessly called her "ma'am."
Sometimes, elders would gather in the square to share stories.
If you need some guidance, don't struggle alone. Ask for help.
Come to think of it... He really didn't seem to remember me.
I'm especially fond of philosophy and biographies. They capture the lives of great people.
My companions, and even Kyla recently, tell me not to take it too seriously.
Advice
Weakness
I don’t really like the night that much. It gets boring when I’m alone.
Since I’m always moving around, I haven’t been able to keep up with any steady hobby.
So I guess my hobby has become collecting things that can only be bought in the places I visit.
Of course, I collect books too! There are so many beautiful and fascinating ones.
I’m a bit sensitive to looking at bright light.
That’s why I try not to look at the sun either!
And I really can’t stand things like [em1][lua(GetItemName("WaterDragonfly_Jelly"))][/em1].
Those kinds of books look so beautiful when lined up in a [em1][lua(GetItemName("GoldenPearl_Bookcase"))][/em1]. Kahaha!
Even just a glance makes it feel like my vision is melting away...
My strength is that I can eat anything!
Of course, when it comes to favorites, I especially like foods full of oil.
So what I’m saying is,
I noticed the menu at Arden’s restaurant has grown... Was that thanks to your efforts, Ellie?
Anyway, [em1][lua(GetItemName("Food_ReduceFatigueUsage_Lv1"))][/em1] has become my absolute favorite dish! You must try it.
On a train, a fire would be disastrous, so things like torches are treated with extreme caution.
I’d rather get up a bit early and talk with people.
Maybe that’s why, no matter how sleepy I am, I tend to avoid foods like coffee that chase sleep away.
Food like [em1][lua(GetItemName("Food_ForceSleepFatigueShield"))][/em1] works a little too well on me.
That’s why things like [em1][lua(GetItemName("ShootingStarFlower_Collect"))][/em1] come in handy.
At night, of course, we have no choice but to use lanterns, but during the day we try to use something else whenever possible.
If you ever need just a fist-sized light, be sure to use it. This is a tip I’ve spread far and wide. Kahaha!
Just eating one of those and not being able to sleep for three days is way too hard!
Bjorn? Are you... lost in thought?
B-Bjorn?
Looks like he's deep in his own world.
Ugh, think I will give up that easily? Here goes... Ha!
<shake>Bjorn!! Can you hear me?!</shake>
No, Ellie! When have you arrived?
I've been here the whole time!
What on earth are you thinking about that's got you so focused?
Hmm... I was thinking about my face.
...Your face?
Yes. I visited Enite recently.
She looked busy, so I offered to look after Rubrum for a bit.
But then Rubrum got all teary, hiding behind Enite and saying my face is scary!
Enite sighed, saying I shouldn't do that, but I didn't do anything.
...How did you approach him, exactly?
Like this!
Rubrum! Enite's busy. I'll play with you!
Come over here. Be a good one.
...Ahh
Hmm? What's with you two?
...Does he really not get it, or is he pretending?
...Haha, well, Bjorn is huge.
Anyone would be startled if he suddenly came close with that expression.
But he has such a hearty laugh. I think it'd be fine if he approached smiling.
Hmm, like this?
<shake>Hahaha! Rubrum!! I'll play with you!</shake>
...This man knows no middle ground.
Good, from now on, this is how it'll be! <shake>Thanks for the tip, Ellie!</shake>
I'll try again with Rubrum later!
...Now that's on you!
Haha, it's much better than before. Don't worry about it!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Bjorn"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
You're retired now, right?
I heard that you were working at the Ministry of Railways...
That's right. Thirty years in the Ministry of Railways, eighteen as a train driver.
Wow, that's a long career!
Eighteen years in such a boring place... I wouldn't have lasted.
Hahaha! Most would feel the same.
But seeing the passengers' faces, full of anticipation and satisfaction...
Ah, that's when I knew it was worth it.
It sounds happy.
Why retire so early, though?
If you like the job, why didn't you keep doing it?
...Hmm, well, I figured it was time to settle down!
No particular reason. Just like that.
...Bjorn?
Anyway, it brought me to this village.
It's so relaxed here. I wander about, finding things to do.
...Wouldn't that get boring? Just roaming the village?
Not at all. It's actually fun exploring. Sometimes I even spot cats.
Ah, so that's why you were fiddling with cat toys every morning.
And with a completely serious face, no less.
What else can I do? Summoning adorable cats is serious business!
Soft little paws, sparkling eyes, and yet such prideful poses!!
<shake>How could I not fall in love!!!</shake>
You really love cats.
What about other things?
Of course! I also collect cute things!
Even when I was still driving trains, I'd gather bookmarks, badges, and other cute trinkets.
You were not going to use them, were you?
I just want to collect them. If it's cute, that's enough.
Cuteness is the most important factor.
Anyway, got some time now? <shake>I'll show you!</shake>
Wait, calm down, Bjorn!
Not now. Show me later!
Ugh. What a shame. They're so cute! I wanted to show off my collection.
But if you're busy, I understand!
Now that I'm retired, I have all the time! Come find me anytime!
You said you've lived here a long time?
Do you know stories unique to this village?
Of course. My family's native here.
Native?
Yes. I've heard many legends and folktales.
I'm amazed at the heroes in them.
Ordinary people flying through the sky, rescuing someone stranded on cliffs... I loved those stories.
...You don't actually believe all that, do you?
...Does it matter?
...Uh?
As a child, I'd sit in the square listening to adults tell stories.
My parents were famous storytellers.
Tales of cat gods, the origins of Wisteria, and heroic adventures!
Of course, each story was absurd and unbelievable. Even I could tell.
But I didn't care.
It didn't matter whether the stories were true or made-up.
Fantasy stories are always better than grim ones, right? Hahaha!
These fantasy stories can still resonate with ordinary people.
That's why they've been told from generation to generation.
...You sound really like a grown-up.
...Huh? What do you mean? I AM an adult.
Haha, never mind. I mean, I like those fantasy stories as well.
Tell me one next time.
I want to know more about this village!
Ah, of course! Next time! And bring the kids! Hahaha!
Just like my parents did, I want to share stories with you.
Ellie, do you know why I came to this village?
To settle down, right?
Hahaha! You remember the retirement story!
Yes, I felt it was time to settle down, so I did.
...And it's true. I felt it was time.
But the reason I came here goes back to a promise.
A promise?
Yes, I had to leave this village once. Because of my parents.
Leaving close friends and villagers was painful.
Even Enite, who scared me, and the indifferent Arden... Parting was hard.
So I promised them. <shake>I will come back one day! Hahaha!!</shake>
That was just a kid's promise.
Exactly! Just a small, childish promise!
But I never forgot it.
Even if everyone else did, even if it's just a trivial promise, I wanted to keep it.
Though I'm not a witch, I want to protect people as best I can.
I want to show others the beautiful scenery I saw on the train.
What I say, I keep. That's my principle.
I don't want to disappoint! Hahaha!
Wow... I could never match that.
Why compare? You have your own path to walk.
This is more like a promise to myself.
Honestly, now it feels like I was just throwing a tantrum like a kid. Hahaha!
Virgil... I think Bjorn is incredible...
Yeah... Thought he was a clueless and overly serious before.
Virgil, do you always have to ruin it with one more comment?
Hahaha! Oh, that reminds me. I made promises to you too.
I said I'd tell stories and show my cute collection.
You should see it! Paw-shaped items too! <shake>So soft and adorable!</shake>
Wait... Do those count as promises too?
That was just random remarks!
Better not make pointless promises around Bjorn next time.
True... but I'm kind of looking forward to the day when the promises are fulfilled.
Retirement
Reasons for staying in the village
It's a quiet day...
I'm thinking about what to do today.
Well, I can't remember it at all.
Is there anything I can do?
Tell me! Anything at all!
Ugh... nothing. My apologies.
Sorry, I didn't bring anything.
Take your time looking around. Hahaha.
It’s truly been a long time. I was waiting for you to come talk to me!
I didn't spend a lot of time here as a child, so I can't compare myself to those who lived here for many years.
Still, this forest was my playground, and I know it better than anyone.
If you need me, I will gladly go.
View Keywords
What? A gift for me?
Are you sure you want to give me a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
And it's something I love! Thank you so much, haha!
Oh, this is! Isn't this a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
I never imagined that I would receive this from someone one day! I'm so happy!
<shake>I'll treasure it for the rest of my life!</shake>
This... is a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]? Is this really for me?
Oh, it... it is? Th-thank you...
What... I mean... Ellie...!
D-did I hurt you or something?
Not hurt at all, hahaha!
This one alone is good enough for today!
Ellie! You must take this first!
It goes against my nature to always be on the receiving end.
Consider this my gift to you!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Bjorn"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
Look who it is! Ellie! I've been wondering when I'd see you again!
Haha, I used to wait for my friends like this when I was little.
I'm so glad we've become friends!
You must feel happy, too! Isn't it great to have so many friends?
Here, consider this a gift from a friend. You're always welcome here, so come by whenever you want.
Ellie! I'm so glad you visit so often!
To be honest, when I first came back to this village by train, I was not only excited, but also anxious.
My childhood memories led me back to this place. I knew things wouldn't be the same as they were before.
Both the village, and myself.
But even so, coming here was my own selfish desire.
Now, I can say from the bottom of my heart that coming back was the right choice.
Out of all the people I passed by in my life, I found you, my friend.
Ah, truly, I am a blessed man. Thank you for being my friend, Ellie.
Ellie, wait a moment! There's something I want to say.
I never imagined someone would show me so much kindness.
I wasn't sure if I was good enough for this.
...Ultimately, you only feel human when you laugh and talk with others.
And that, you know, is much harder than it seems.
Because you have to truly understand someone to get close to their heart.
To put it simply, you've completely bared my soul.
You're the first person I've ever opened up to like this.
So, I put some thought into it, just like you would, and prepared a proper gift.
I hope you like it. I'll work even harder, so I can be a person like you someday.
There's a way to get closer to cats?
I should hear what he has to say!
I'll go to the [em1]village[/em1] and talk to him.
Bjorn was the one who brought all the cat-related items to the village...
Bjorn! I want to befriend the cats too!
I've acquired something called a [em1]Token of Friendship[/em1] for those who are serious about their friendship with cats.
A witch I met during my time at the Ministry of Railways made them, but they only work on [em1]cats[/em1].
That's right. If your mind is made up, then give it to the cat you wish to be with.
Oh, one more thing. You can only have one cat to live with.
Indeed. But you still need to put some effort into everything once you and the cat are living together.
This is the ultimate gift to give to a cat you want to live with.
A Token of Friendship that can only be used on cats?
The closer you are, the greater the responsibility. If you keep breaking your promises, the cat may not feel the same way about you anymore.
I understand. I'll be careful when deciding which cat to give it to.
Exactly. They say that the magic in the necklace passes the user's feelings and scent to the cat.
Don't just give it to any random cat you see. They'll only accept it if they feel like they're close enough to you.
I see. It's used to show the cats your sincerity and ask them to live with you.
Likewise, the cat's thoughts will be conveyed to the user, so you'll be able to communicate with each other.
Wow... The gift has some special meanings attached, not just an ordinary gift.
I don't think we'll find it in the village.
Hohaha! Because I stroll every inch of the village every day!
Maybe you've simply overlooked it.
Hm? Bjorn, you've also noticed it?!
I didn't, but then Enite told me about it! Hohaha!
He looked the same as usual when I greeted him, so I thought I was imagining things.
But after further observation, I found that Roy often looks depressed and tired when he's alone.
If the blue rose isn't in the village, it must be somewhere outside.
Let's ask [em1]someone who often travels beyond the village[/em1]. They may know something.
I don't have a clue. Ask [em1]someone who often travels beyond the village[/em1].
Th-that can't be! I've inspected every nook and cranny of this village!
I think it's probably gone...
You don't sound quite certain, do you?!
Anyway, I've never seen it!
Where on earth is the blue rose then?
Why are you looking for it?
The blue rose is important to Roy. He says he no longer needs it, but I want it back anyway.
I see. Is that why he's been listless?
No wonder he's been zoning out a lot when watering flowers.
What a shame. I could have done something to help had he told me about his trouble.
I hope he recovers soon.
Hohaha! You're already working at it!
Ellie, thank you for visiting me. Looks like you're having a nice day.
Haha, so I am. What about you, Bjorn? How does it feel to be back at Wisteria after so long?
It feels great. It's like being back home after a short trip.
The village has changed a lot, but Enite and Arden are the same as before. Seeing them gives me a strong sense of being home.
And I want to tell you about my conversation with Enite. Care to hear it?
Sure. What did you talk about?
I told Enite that I want to help with everything that contributes to the village. She was glad to hear it, and encouraged me to do so.
So I pondered over it and made this draft. Tell me what you think.
A cat castle? It's so adorable!
Bjorn, you once left a cat encyclopedia in the village, didn't you?
How did you know? I did lose one when I passed by the village.
So that was really yours! No wonder the art styles are the same.
Oh yeah! Now I remember it. Once the train malfunctioned and had to stop.
It happened to be near Wisteria, so I walked around the villager. Since then, I've been dropping by every time the train stops near it.
Whenever I visit the place, I take care of the cats and chat with Enite. That was how I lost the encyclopedia.
Although the encyclopedia was lost, I ended up moving back, so it was a blessing in disguise.
You're so devoted to the village and cats. You've drawn such fun art for them.
It's nothing! A castle for the cats certainly deserves a meticulous design!
The cats don't even have a proper shelter. I want to provide a place for them to live together.
Really? Is this a blueprint?
How much will it cost to build such a castle in Wisteria... Before that, is it even possible at all? It looks almost as big as the village itself.
No need to worry. I've bought 50 books or so on castle building.
I plan to build as I learn, so that the cats can have a cozy home as soon as possible.
I've even made a shopping list of all the materials required.
Shall we consult Kyla before the construction begins?
Kyla is a carpenter. You should pick her brains about the castle.
Right, I forgot Kyla! We've got an expert within reach!
The villagers' anniversary, party preparations, construction of the village train station... I've got so much work to do.
But the castle is the most urgent. I need to go to Kyla.
If you're busy, I can show the blueprint to Kyla for you.
Really? That's so kind of you!
You will ask for Kyla's advice before you begin the construction, right?
Something's come up. I'll help you once I'm back!
The [em1]cat castle[/em1] will usher in a new era of even better cat welfare.
Of course! As the best carpenter, Kyla may come up with a greater castle design.
I'm counting on you, Ellie!
The conclusion seems to be "It's plain but practicable"?
Have you thought of something?
Yup! But I need to talk to Bjorn before I can tell you.
How was your talk with the villagers? Did you get any inspiration?
Yeah, I got some nice ideas from Rex and Rubrum.
What about you, Bjorn? How was the cat-watching?
Good question! I found a cat hiding in the bushes near the stage.
I didn't disturb it. I just watched silently for a while, while it remained asleep in that tight space.
It was so soundly asleep that I remained perfectly still, hardly daring to stir.
Then I looked around the place and found another one napping in a smaller bush.
I'm now convinced that cats love to sleep in tight spaces.
What do you think of my cat-watching operation? Wasn't it fruitful?
Yeah, we've arrived at the same conclusion.
So, how about we build a space based on the preferences of cats?
But tight spaces are very common... You can find them anywhere.
Not near my house though.
In that case, how about we build one beside your house? And decorate it with all the popular [em1]cat furniture[/em1].
They will visit often, and know you better.
Ellie... You must be a genius!
I'm so happy to have a genius as a friend!
Thanks to you, I now have a general idea of what I should do.
Make a new design then. And I'll gather the materials.
Getting your own materials and making your own handmade gift feels sweeter than buying a finished product.
Great idea. I've got some materials in mind. Please find them for me.
You've got all the materials already?
Perfect! Now, I can bring the [em1]cat furniture[/em1] in my mind to reality.
This size should easily fit into the spaces beside your home.
Sure. I've drawn the blueprint with every word of Kyla's in mind.
Now... time for the actual crafting.
I've waited for so long that I almost forgot how to take action!
It'll be ready [em1]within[/em1] tomorrow. Stay tuned.
Ellie, you've come at the perfect time.
Don't you want to find out if the cats will actually use it?
I'm still working on it! Give me more time.
The furniture's ready! The cats are gonna love it! I've put your materials to good use.
You're so serious about everything you do, Bjorn.
You've helped me a lot. I can't let your efforts go to waste.
You haven't seen it yet?
I've been wandering around with my eyes closed, so that we can witness the wonder together.
That's incredible, Bjorn... Let's have a look before you injure yourself.
Ellie, you see that cat? Even before this, it had been frequenting the surroundings of my house.
I can see its interest in what you've made.
But it's not coming near... Seems to be on its guard.
Shall we try to lure it? With food or toys, maybe.
Good idea! I'll wave a toy beside it to draw its attention!
Since when have you had such a toy?
I bought it before moving back. It has good durability.
Here we go.
The cat had a great time.
It's the first time I've actually seen someone cherish an item I put effort into making...
Thanks to you and Kyla, I think I've found an activity I love.
I know that feeling! It's so rewarding to see people using the items I make.
And I'm glad the result was so satisfactory for you, Bjorn.
I've also had a great time, thanks to you.
Let's work together more often, Ellie.
Sure, let me know whenever you're doing something fun or need my help.
Hmm... that didn't catch its attention.
I'll try again!
I've never actually watched a graduation ceremony, but I've transported countless witches who were attending them.
On the journey there, I could see their faces full of excitement and happiness.
But it's not easy to find the items witches use.
I don't think I can help you... I'd even introduce you to a [em1]general store run by witches[/em1] if I knew of one!
<shake>I'm really sorry!</shake>
The items they prepared for the graduation ceremony were [em1]special deliveries[/em1], so I never got the chance to even see them.
To think you were doing such a difficult thing... You truly are amazing, Ellie.
Then of course, I have to help you.
Bjorn, you want to become friends with others, right?
<shake>Haha! Of course!</shake>
That's my goal.
But to give an item, and convey the wish of becoming friends with someone... Hmm...
Can't you think of anything?
Quite the opposite. There are so many that I don't know which one to give...
Just prepare something simple.
It's going to be buried, so it's better to avoid something too valuable.
No, I can't do that.
What if the tree doesn't come back to life because my gift wasn't sincere enough? I can't have that.
Wait a minute. I have a good idea.
This is...?
It's star honey wine.
Not honey, but star honey?
The flowers that grow where a star has fallen are called star flowers. This is liquor brewed from the honey gathered from them.
In particular, this one is the finest quality, brewed on the day a shooting star fell. Hahaha!
Why make it into a wine?
Hahaha! People get close over a drink, don't they?
But some people don't drink.
Oh, you're right! I didn't think of that!
Just a moment.
Good thing I kept some of this on hand.
This is star honey drink for people who don't drink.
Of course, it's also made from the same star honey wine.
I think star honey wine would suffice. That's more than enough to convey your sincerity.
I can't do that. I also want to be friends with those who don't drink.
That makes sense. Okay, I'll keep them safe.
Hahaha! If there's anything else you need, just let me know!
If there's anything else you need, just let me know!
How did it go? I mean Kyla’s evaluation.
She gave me really good advice. Maybe Bjorn should have gone along too.
Was it that good? Hurry and tell me what advice she gave.
Kyla said that since it’s for the cats, we should start by finding out what the cats want.
So instead of building the castle first, she suggested making at least one thing the cats want.
I see… So that’s what Kyla’s advice was…
It seems there was definitely something I overlooked. Since it’s good advice, I’ll follow it.
Then what did she suggest you try making?
She didn’t say anything specific… but I do want to do something for the cats.
How about looking for something the cats might need this time?
Ellie… what you just said…
<shake>That’s… convincing!!</shake>
<shake>Ack!</shake>
Was I too loud? Sorry, I just got carried away with emotion…
Bjorn even made a codex because he wanted to treat the cats well.
So this time, let’s find out together what the cats want.
Do you mean… you’ll join me?
Of course. I’m serious about the cats too.
Bjorn, would you observe the cats? You might notice things I can’t see.
I’ll ask the villagers who like cats what might be good.
A division of roles, then. Understood. I’ll do my best, so let’s begin right away.
At least give me a signal before you shout. It feels like my ears are about to burst.
Got it, hat man.
Where have you been! It was boring without you!
What tricks should I play today?
I hate school...
Hi, Ellie! This is for you!
I took it because it looked like you, teehee.
But I don't need it. Put it to good use, teehee~
*yawning* I'm so sleepy.
Homework? It can wait until tomorrow.
You aren't here to nag me like my mom, are you?
What do you want? Just say it. I don't have forever.
Take my knife!
Why would you come at such a time of day?
Hmph, I was just working on my schedule for tomorrow!
Enite is such a great cook.
Will you finish any bitter tea for me?
What should I talk to Theo about?
Before I came to Wisteria, I thought it would be quiet and boring here.
But life here is actually better than what I imagined.
Most importantly, I'm not constantly under the watch of my parents! Teehee.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Teo"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Small"))]
Enite brings me food every day.
I also get food from other villagers who care about me.
... I'm fine.
Pranks
Playing pranks is my daily routine.
It should add some liveliness to such an eventless village.
Don't treat me like a child. I've grown up.
As you see, I can take care of myself when my parents aren't around.
Hat
I got it before I came here. It's a gift from my friends back at school.
It's my favorite at the moment!
School
Before I came here, I used to go to school.
There are days when I miss my schoolmates.
But we can always write to each other.
Tutor
Mom and Dad have hired a tutor for me so that I won't neglect my studies.
But since this village is in the middle of nowhere, it's in the form of a correspondence course.
Another day means new assignments... Sigh...
Dinner at Enite's
Enite always offers to have me over for dinner.
However close we are, that's not my home, so I don't think I should go every day.
Freedom
My parents are strict.
They yell at me for everything I do.
But while I'm here, I can do whatever I want! I love it!
I'm not sure about it.
There are a lot of things I want to do though! Teehee.
Secret base
My schoolmates and I used to have a secret base
I hope I can have one here too.
Animals
Dad once brought me a puppy.
But I prefer cats.
I want to have something sweet.
Which prank should I begin with?
Witch
There was also one witch teacher at school.
I was really excited, thinking that with a witch as a teacher, the classes would be super fun.
But it was just ordinary nature lessons, so it wasn’t fun.
Still, if we did well on tests, she would give us [em1][lua(GetItemName("WitchFairyCake"))][/em1] as a reward.
That was really great. It tasted amazing.
Why do you just sit there staring blankly at the water?
Doesn’t it look silly?
Still, I guess it would be fun to catch a funny-looking fish.
Have you seen what [em1][lua(GetItemName("Fish_NoEndure"))][/em1] looks like? It’s so ugly~
Imagine a fish like that suddenly jumping out of a drawer? <wave>It’d be so</wave> funny, right? Heehee.
I like Enite because she’s sooo much better at cooking than my mom and dad.
Especially [em1][lua(GetItemName("EniteApplePie"))][/em1]—it’s so good it could be sold.
Now that I think about it, I want to eat it again. <wave>I’ll have to ask her to make it for me.</wave>
Ellie, you’ve caught [em1][lua(GetItemName("CaveLizard_Collect"))][/em1] before too, right?
You know there’s no feeling at all when you catch one, right?
It felt so weird, <shake>I really hated it.</shake>
What kind of animal is that, anyway?
It’s just a quiet, ordinary forest, so it feels a bit lacking for an adventure.
Still, there was this one thing that was pretty nice.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("LittleMandrake_Collect"))][/em1]—I’d only ever seen it in books! But it really exists!
Isn’t it so funny how it makes that weird noise when it’s pulled out?
What brought you to Wisteria?
Well, I was told that my granny and Enite were friends.
I think they met each other soon after Enite arrived in the city?
And Mom knows Enite as well.
They thought it would be better to put me under the care of someone they knew.
Wait a second. Wasn't this place overrun by prickly vines until recently?
And you'd learned about me removing the prickly vines when you arrived?
Mom and Enite were writing to each other.
Enite told her that a great witch's arrival had brought fortune to the place and that it was now safe to live here.
Haha, that's typical for Enite.
Anyway, I like this village.
I'm glad I listened to Mom and moved here.
And I even saw something interesting the day I moved here. Teehee.
Do give me a break, will you?
I know I covered my face in flour!
And don't you continue the conversation without me!
Teehee, I bet this village will keep me entertained.
And look forward to my new pranks!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Teo"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "FavorabilityUP_Large"))]
You said that your parents are archaeologists?
Right, they would start packing whenever they learn about any newly-discovered artifacts or ruins.
As far as I know, they are quite famous in this field. They've made their way into newspapers.
My goodness! They are celebrities?
Yes, and as always, there is a high expectation for their new exploration.
They would probably have taken me with them if it weren't dangerous.
Do you wish you had gone with them?
Absolutely not! My parents are very strict.
All those talks about good manners. I can't be me when around them.
They will talk my ears off if they catch me ignoring my assignments or playing tricks.
I want to be here. When I'm here, I'm free!
I can do whatever I want and eat whatever I want.
I can take care of myself!
As long as you're doing well, it's okay, but let me know if you run into any problems.
I'll help you with all my skills.
Okay, teehee.
I won't help you with anything evil, though!
I haven't even asked.
But I'm counting on you! You'll be such a great help! Teehee.
I said "not anything evil"! You heard me?!
Where did you live before coming to Wisteria?
In a big city, although not as big as Highlion.
I had to go to school every day.
You used to go to school?
Right, although it was not a School for Witches.
Even then. Not many people can afford to go to school.
After all, my parents are renowned archaeologists.
When I was at school, I would play pranks with my friends, teehee.
We would sneak into the assistant principal's office, or sprinkle chalk dust all over the classroom.
I thought nobody would do such things except Ellie.
No, Ellie's pranks were worse.
Virgil! There were not!
Teehee, we would get a good scolding if they caught us.
If only I could see my friends. I wonder how they're doing.
Theo...
Cheer up! You have a new companion: a witch lady, stylish and capable!
Your stay here will be as fun as before!
I've been thinking about it... Do you really deserve being called a "stylish witch lady"?
A "witch baby" seems more suitable if you ask me, teehee.
Hey! I'm older than you, kid!
Unfortunately, unlike you, I'm still amid my growth spurt, teehee.
In no time, I'll be taller than you. I hope your neck won't hurt too much looking me in the eyes.
Huh, I'll make all your cookies bitter, I warn you.
Hey! That's mean! And wasteful as well!
Excuse me? Until you grow taller, I don't think I can hear you from up here.
Be louder, little guy. That way, your voice may reach me, haha!
Teehee, just you wait. I never forget an insult.
Come at me, boy. I'll teach you about the bitterness of life.
Yeah... life here can be fun, teehee.
How does it feel, living alone? Is everything alright?
Of course! Everything's perfectly fine!
Theo?
Well, we've known each other for a while...
Is anything wrong?
No, but... about that question just now...
I used to think it was fine being alone,
but solitude can scare me.
When everyone's left and I'm on my own at home...
I mean... my point is...
Thank you for keeping me company...
Sorry? What was it? I didn't catch the last part. Could you repeat yourself?
... Come closer and I'll repeat it.
*inhales*
<shake>BLAME YOURSELF FOR NOT CATCHING MY WORDS!!!</shake>
What the freak!
Teehee, you shouldn't have obeyed me.
<wave>Ugh</wave>... Hey, do you have to be so mean?!
That's just how I am, teehee.
...Theo.
What? Did that hurt your feelings? You can cry if you want.
Wait, why grab my ear...
<shake>YOU ILL-MANNERED BRAT!!!</shake>
You're deafening me!
Haha, I can hurt you back if I want. <wave>Phew, sweet revenge.</wave>
I'm gonna burst your eardrums! Where are you going! Come back!
The pot calling the kettle black...
The reason for coming to Wisteria
Previous life
Recent life
I envy you, Ellie. You're a witch.
If only I could be a witch too.
Witches can craft all the amazing things.
They can make as many [lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))] as they want.
And magical furniture that ordinary people can never make, such as super-bouncy sofas.
If I were a witch, I could have designed pranks no one would ever expect.
Happy birthday to Ellie II.
Watch your mouth. I'm not that nasty!
And for your information, witches can't use their power on pranks.
Why? It's your magic.
Witches are supposed to help those in their reach.
It's a witch's duty to help those around her.
She's not supposed to fool people with her magic.
And abusing magic can cause danger.
Tsk, that's boring.
If so, I refuse to become a witch.
You can't become one even if you want to...
Nagging
I hate being nagged at.
I don't think anyone likes that.
But my parents always nag at me.
They keep telling me to do this and not do that.
I won't grow up to be like them.
What kind of adult would you like to be then?
Someone who is understanding and kind to people?
Someone good-humored, just like my granny!
Is that how your granny's like?
Kind of. I've spent much of my life with my granny,
because as archaeologists, my parents are often away working.
Every day is fun when I'm with Granny.
She never nags at me. Instead, she joins me in every activity. Even cleaning is enjoyable if I do it with her.
You really love your granny.
She's my favorite person in the world!
I wish she were here with me...
She's not with me anymore, but I really cherish those memories with her.
What!? You're making me uncomfortable. I'm not gonna cry or anything.
Of course you aren't. You're a tough boy! Shall I give you a hug?
Eek, leave me alone!
What do you mean "eek"!
Hugging is weird! Nobody does it! There's got to be something wrong with you!
There is not! I just have a soft spot for kids being strong! That's all!
Soft spot, huh!
What game shall I play with Honey Bear? I can't wait to get started!
Looks like you're having a lovely day.
It was lovely, considering all the gloomy days I've been having.
Honey Bear has brightened my mood!
What do you like about Honey Bear?
He just caught my attention at first sight.
I felt like I could be friends with him forever! Something like that.
Besides, I know Honey Bear well.
I feel like being a big brother! I want to take care of Honey Bear.
I want to stay with him. It just so happened.
It's Honey Bear he's talking about...?
What? Is anything wrong?
I can look after you too, if you want, teehee.
It should be the other way around.
You want to live with Honey Bear like you were brothers?
It's more than that, but I'd like to be with him.
Unfortunately, we can't live together, but I can go and see him often.
You can come whenever you've got time.
I'm the party leader. You've got my permission, teehee.
Actually, it's more fun when you're included.
I also find this adventure exciting.
I've got an appointment with Enite.
Go ahead then, and I'll join you on your next adventure!
Letter
Theo, you've read all the letters?
It gave me a scare. Why would they have so much to write about?
I've read all of them, and I was drenched.
You should have read them when they arrived.
What were they about?
Just the usual stuff.
The nagging, and other things as well.
To be honest, I'm writing letters myself.
Really? I thought you didn't even want to read letters, still less writing one.
You thought wrong! I do read.
Yeah, yeah, comic books.
Comic books are decent books.
But I've been studying as well.
I often write to tell them I'm doing well.
What's with that look?
The look of relief?
You're writing letters, and you're studying.
Everyone! Theo has grown up!
Quit it! That's embarrassing!
And I'm only studying because I have found a goal.
I want to be the first help Honey Bear can get when he is ill.
It may be hard, but if I can become a d-doctor...
Theo has grown up!!
I said quit it!!
There's nothing to be ashamed of. Everyone will be proud of you.
I'm allowed to feel ashamed!
W-wait! Don't tell anyone else about it!
This is exactly how I want to spend my life!
I've got another letter.
What should today's first prank be? Teehee.
*yawning* I'm so bored.
Do you want this wooden club? Teehee.
Unfortunately, I've got nothing to sell you.
Something I don't know?
I remember everything that happened before I came here.
Give me a large candy and I'll consider it.
Who else do you remember?
Well... Returners should have more stories to tell than newcomers.
Heh, you have a gift for me?
I happen to want one of those! I'll take it!
Is it... a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]? Can I really have it?
Humph, I-I thank you then!
<wave>*humming*</wave>
A [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?
Heh, it's sweet of you. Thank you.
I didn't expect to receive a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1] from you.
If you insist, I'll take it.
A <shake>[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", presentID))][/em1]?</shake>?
Teehee, if that's how you treat me, I'll repay you with a prank!
Come on, not another gift!
One gift alone is good enough for one day.
Ellie, wait!
I don't plan to fool you. I just want to talk.
Hm... Why are you giving me all the gifts?
You've found out about all my likes and dislikes through the process.
You now know me too well.
That'll give you an upper hand when I want to fool you, teehee.
Here you are. It's a gift from me.
Th-this is what you get for giving me all the gifts...
I only give out good stuff when I'm serious. Do cherish it, teehee.
Ellie, you've come at the perfect time!
Tada! I can't be the receiver all the time. I've got something for you today.
You can cry if you want to, teehee.
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Teo"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "Chipchat_Add"))]
Ellie, come over here!
What's so fun about visiting me so often?
I've been seeing you every day.
Thanks to you, though, I've been having a good time in this village.
Here's a gift for you! Visit me as much as you want.
Hi, Ellie! I was waiting for you.
Actually, I was anxious to tell you something.
I really want to tell you this:
I actually enjoy all your visits.
I suppose I wouldn't have enjoyed my stay so much if it weren't for you.
Thanks for that! Here's a gift for you!
Teehee, sorry, that's just an empty box. Here's the real gift!
Keep your guard up! My pranks can strike anywhere and anytime!
[lua(GetLocalizedString("InteractableObject", "People_Teo"))][lua(GetLocalizedString("Choice", "AboutYou_Add"))]
If it isn't the witch hit by the flour bomb?
I'm trying hard to forget that. Don't bring it up...
Wait, what are you wearing? That's indecent!
This is how I like to dress. Live with it.
I would have dressed like this from the first day had my parents not insisted otherwise.
Now, let's get down to business. I have a favor to ask, teehee.
I hope no prank is involved.
Is prank the only thing you can associate me with?! I just want to ask if witches can change the flavor of food at will?
Flavor of food?
Yup, is there a spell for altering tastes?
What do you say? Is it a thing?
Well, there are many ways to alter food taste.
And they work differently.
Some methods change the food, while others deceive the consumer's senses.
Why are you asking that though?
Enite usually brings me food because, as you know, I currently live alone.
The problem is, none of the food is sweet.
She even brings me tea bitter to the point of tongue-numbing, claiming that it's good for children's health.
Please, I want a way to sweeten those food and drinks!
It doesn't take a potion to sweeten food.
[em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1] would work well! It's a powerful sweetener!
[em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1]? But it says "curse" in its name.
That's just a name. Don't worry about it! Have one of such candies and everything will taste sweet.
It also widens the types of sweetness you can sense, including a sweetness unique and magical!
In addition, the sweetness is so intense that only someone with a sweet tooth will enjoy it. That's what makes it a curse.
Fantastic! That's exactly what I need!
<wave>Ellie, please make me one of such candies! Pretty please with a cherry on top!</wave>
Leave it to me. I can make it in a blink.
Alright! Go ahead!
Tsk, why not? I'm not giving up!
Ellie! How long are you going to keep me waiting!
Can you get me a [em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1] now?
Another no? I'm not giving up!
At last! Beef stew!
I just need to add the candy to this stew, right?
Yeah, and you'd better crush the candy and add only a bit at a time.
If you toss the whole candy in, the sweetness will linger on your tongue for ages.
That's right. She's even experimented it on herself, just to prove the rumor.
Even water tasted sweet then. I almost missed saltiness.
That was crazy. You must be the only one who's ever used the whole candy in one go.
I was only being curious. I won't do it again. Relax.
I see... Teehee.
Hah! I'll be the second one then!
What? Hey, <shake>was that the whole candy?! Did you hear what I said?</shake>
I was wrong. You aren't the craziest person in the world.
What about food from Enite!
Oh, now that you mention it, I was supposed to use the candy on that.
But this was just testing. I'll commission more candies later.
Now, let me have a taste.
*gulps* H-how is it?
... Th-this is....
<wave>This is great! It's so sweet!</wave> Exactly how I like it!
Ellie, you should have some as well!
Let's see...
<shake>Huh? What is this! It's even sweeter than before!</shake>
Hey, don't you add anything weird to my beef stew.
It's nothing weird, Arden! This is the best beef stew I've ever had!
It's way better than the one loaded with pepper!
No way. No stew can beat mine.
How would you know when you've not even tried it? Don't you agree, Ellie?
Me? Well, it does taste better than pepper, but...
Have a try! Or I can feed you! <wave>Ahhh~</wave>
Forget it. It can't be better than my stew.
Arden, are you alright?!
W-w-water...
Wait, even water will taste sweet for Arden now...
Ugh... The water's also... sweet.
There's no way to wash the taste away now?
Arden may have a poor tolerance for sweetness, since he's only used to pepper.
But it was a small dose, so it should wear off in 1 hour.
I don't think he will last for 1 hour.
What are you talking about? It tastes much better than before!
If you offer this in your restaurant, customers will pour in from outside the village!
Right, Arden! You should order more candies from Ellie and add them to your pot tomorrow!
*grunts*
Oh? He's recovered?
Arden! Are you feeling better?
Get out... Both of you.
Arden! I haven't finished eating!
Out.
He's kicked us out!
Never mind! The effect was perfect. I love it.
Thank you, Ellie, for treating me to the utmost delicacy.
You witches are really incredible. That honestly deserved to be called magic.
Oh-ho. Ahem, brace yourself. I've always scored full marks in concoction, <wave>heh</wave>.
<wave>Long live the stylish and capable witch!</wave>
Lady Witch, could you grant me one more wish?
I want a [em1]bouncy sofa[/em1] similar to the one back at home, but even bigger and bouncier!
Similar to the one back at home?
You must love that sofa a lot.
<shake>Well,</shake> it's as soft as a cloud, and it's gigantic.
Does such a sofa really exist?
Are you lying by any chance?
I'm not! It was really big and soft.
But are you sure you want one even bigger and bouncier? Can't you make do with a sofa the same as before?
<wave>Sigh</wave>... Not even the great Lady Witch can manage this?
If it's beyond you, Ellie, it's okay. I understand, teehee.
It's not! It's just a walk in the park for me!
Ellie, he's provoking you. Are you aware of that?
I'd call it a challenge!
Just you wait, kid. I'll impress you with my unmatched witchcraft!
It's too late.
So, you're making it for me?
Teehee, I've always wanted a sofa like the one at home. I can finally have it.
Let's see... A sofa so bouncy and huge that it can almost launch you into the sky...
I'd better consult Kyla first, since it's her field of expertise.
Sure! I'll go first. Don't keep me waiting!
But the current sofa is already bouncy and nice.
My goodness, that gave me the scare.
You can be a coward.
I'm not!
Indeed! <shake>*howls*</shake> You almost wet yourself, teehee.
You'd scare anyone if you pop up from nowhere.
Right, you got me too.
You were too late, so I thought I'd play a trick on you, teehee.
Pranks are indeed the only thing I can associate you with!
Why not? It's fun! And I didn't get to do it often!
He's like an unbridled pony. It's nice to be a child once in a while, haha!
Who are you calling a child? I'm a grown-up.
Nobody would believe in that...
There, there, we should apologize for being late.
Sorry for keeping you waiting, Theo.
I-It's okay... It wasn't a long wait.
See? Ellie, that's how a grown-up should behave.
Shut up, Virgil.
Let's get down to business. What are we making?
I want a sofa larger and bouncier than the current one!
The one back at home was so bouncy that it could launch you into space, and it was large enough to fill the entire room!
W-wait a second. Aren't you asking for even more than last time?
Haha! That's an amazing sofa!
What do you want such a sofa for?
<shake>Hm, well... it's for...</shake> for me to lie on it when I take a break!
You rest better when on a familiar sofa, don't you? Teehee.
I'd say you're asking for too much.
Haha, some people just like to be dramatic.
But not even I can make a sofa bouncy enough to launch you high into the sky.
I can make one capable of launching you close to the ceiling, but that requires some [em1]special materials[/em1] and techniques.
It will take some time to finish such a sofa. Is that okay?
Yeah! That sounds nice! Go ahead!
Understood. Ellie, could you find me the materials?
[em1]2 [lua(GetItemName("FogFox_Collect"))] and 2 [lua(GetItemName("Nail_Collect"))][/em1] will provide enough bounciness.
Still, I wonder if such a sofa is necessary.
Why? You were so motivated!
I've taken the order, but the more I hear the details, the less I find it necessary.
Haha, it may not be a staple, but it can make a good housewarming gift.
It's natural for someone his age to have many desires, and he enjoys living alone.
If you say so, Kyla, I'll get you the materials.
How is it, Theo? Is this what you want?
Good job, Kyla! This looks super bouncy!
May I touch it?
You don't need my permission. It's your sofa.
Don't be too rough, though...
Now, mine...
Hm? It doesn't feel very bouncy.
What? It can't be.
It's not? Looks very bouncy to me...
Try sitting on it if you don't believe me, teehee.
Does the touch betray the appearance?
Alright! I'll check it out!
I feel kind of uneasy...
It IS bouncy! There's nothing wrong with it!
It's so bouncy that it may launch you out of it.
<shake>Ouch!</shake>
Teehee, teeheehee, hahaha! Ellie went up like a rocket!
E-Ellie! Are you alright?
I tried to stick to the requirements. Have I overdone it?
Told you. I thought we would burst out of the house.
You sometimes forget that I'm a hat.
Scared the life out of me. Good thing the quilt stopped me.
I saw it coming, so I laid the quilt there in advance, teehee.
See? Like you said, it almost launched you into the sky, teehee.
That remark must have summoned bad luck...
I wouldn't call this a sofa.
You're right. This can be dangerous.
Should I make it less bouncy?
Don't! I like it this way! It's just like the one at home!
Is this really intended for homes?
Using this at home? It's impossible.
Teehee, it's not like you can prove otherwise.
And this sofa will certainly create some fun memories. Don't you agree, Ellie?
That was easily among the top five leaps I've ever witnessed, teehee.
That wasn't fun at all!
Wait... You're right. That will be fun to recall.
Hm? Why the smile? What are you plotting...?
Give Theo the [em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1]?
Theo! I've got you the [em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1]!
Everything will taste sweet if I eat this first. Is that right?
Right. We are going to sprinkle it on Enite's cooking.
Hm? Can't I swallow it whole?
You can, if you don't mind [em1]bitterness intense[/em1] enough to numb your tongue.
Isn't it supposed to be a sweetener?!
Haha, it is, as long as you crush it and sprinkle it on your food.
Is that right? It now feels kind of unsettling...
Hey! If you don't believe me, <shake>you don't have to eat it!</shake>
<shake>O-of course I believe you!</shake> Don't take it away!
How dare you question my skills!
Okay, okay, I'm sorry.
It will make do. What shall we experiment it on first?
Hm? Are we not sprinkling it on Enite's cooking?
I've eaten that up. She will bring me more later,
but I want to test the candy on something else before Enite comes with more food. Any suggestions?
Teehee, I didn't know you were that hungry, Ellie. Your stomach was so loud.
Shut up. I've been busy. I need to grab something to eat.
Shall we go to Arden's restaurant then? That's the only establishment in the village that offers meals.
We can get food for testing and for my stomach.
It's decided then. Let's go!
[em1][lua(GetItemName("SweetCurseCandy"))][/em1] is needed.
Ah, I forgot to deliver the sofa to Theo!
It can't be helped. I should fetch the [em1]Bouncy Sofa[/em1].
Give the [em1]Bouncy Sofa[/em1] to Theo?
My sofa's ready? Already?!
Yeah, it's just a piece of cake for me.
There. See how bouncy it is.
It can launch you through the ceiling, even into the sky if you want.
That's an overstatement, however you look at it.
Yup... This is how I like it, teehee.
Let me put it in place then!
<shake>Ughaaaah</shake>! Hey, what are you doing?
Isn't it obvious! Taking my revenge!
Sorry, but it isn't over.
It isn't?
That was for launching me with the sofa. And this is for fooling around at Kyla's place!
I've read it in an old book: Tickling is the best way to discipline brats like you.
Come here, won't you?
Wait! L-leave me alone!
<shake>Capable Lady Witch! Miss Ellie! Please— I said, leave me alone!</shake>
Too late!
<shake>Ha, hahaha! Hahahaha! Hey! Give me a break!</shake>
This is hilarious. I want to keep going!
He, hahahaha! Wait, I-I surrender, hahaha!
They're just kids. Both of them.
Theo would be going too far if he comes up with worse pranks...
But I guess the current ones are fine, hahaha!
<wave>Hehehe, hehe.</wave>
Theo? You seem to be in a great mood today.
What are you holding? Is it a letter?
It's a [em1]letter from my parents[/em1]. They write to me every day.
Is that the reason for your good mood?
<shake>Are you kidding me?</shake> It's just the old nagging. I don't want it.
That's not the point. Ellie, you've come at the perfect time.
I've just received a much-anticipated delivery, teehee.
Delivery?
[em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Box[/em1], limited edition!
[em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Box[/em1]? What's that?
You're so ignorant.
It's a precious box of snacks. When used properly, the box will blow up and create a rain of snacks!
What? That sounds so fun!
But why haven't I heard of it?
Of course you haven't. It's [em1]a snack gift box designed for ordinary humans[/em1].
The box is infused with magic, allowing ordinary people to do magic with the snacks inside.
Witches don't need it because they have magic.
But that's a rare item. It should cost quite a fortune.
Right. Before I came here, Mom asked me if there was anything I wanted.
So I asked her to get me one of these limited edition [em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Boxes[/em1].
They say it can produce magical snacks, sweet and tasty! I want to give it a try!
Mom's got me a bunch of it, because she wants me to share with friends. I'm gonna get local kids to try it.
If you've got time, you can join me. What do you say?
Count me in! It's going to be fun!
Of course it is!
I'll summon the kids now.
I'll get Dana, while you get [em1]Rubrum[/em1].
The more the merrier, teehee.
Be back soon!
Come back once you've handled whatever you're doing. The more the merrier.
Ellie! Are you done with your business?
Isn't it fun making [em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Boxes[/em1]?
Theo! Rubrum will come once he's ready.
Perfect. Ellie, you've got time?
It may take long. You can't quit halfway.
Why would you ask that? I've made time for it.
Ready when you are!
Teehee, exactly what I want to hear.
The kids will soon be here. Let's get going!
Come when you're ready. I'll be waiting for you.
Ellie! You're so slow. Are you available now?
Is everyone here? Here we go.
I've never made snacks before!
I was itching to get started, so I've come early, heh.
This is going to be cool. I'm so excited!
So, what are we doing?
Wait, here are the instructions.
Alright, I've skimmed through it. I guess we simply need to add all the ingredients.
We'll find out as we proceed, teehee.
Wait, that doesn't sound reassuring. I'll have a look myself!
It's basically the same as making candies and potions.
If this is how we do it, I can manage!
I'm so excited! I've never done this before!
It feels like cooking! I'll try my best!
Now that everyone knows what to do, let's begin.
Woah! It worked?
That scared me! The explosion was different from what I imagined.
Heh, the snacks are so sweet! Yummy!
The explosion wasn't as intense as the instructions say.
<shake>Tell me about it.</shake> We did everything correctly, but that was lame.
I hope it was more violent.
I agree. It was kind of mild.
After all, it's a toy for non-witches.
If you take that into consideration, the effect was decent.
Now that you mention [em1]non-witches[/em1]!
We've got a witch here! Ellie, can't you enhance the explosion with your [em1]magic[/em1]?
I'm not sure...
Please, Ellie! Don't you want to see it yourself?
A rain of snacks falling from heaven!
Kids, you want to see it too, don't you?
I do, but Clala says I shouldn't play with my food...
It's okay. This gift box is a toy. It's how you're supposed to use it!
Would it be dangerous if we boost the explosion?
Rubrum, are you scared?
We can do it outdoor. As long as we stay away, we'll be fine!
Snacks raining from the sky! It's got to be spectacular!
Yup, I want to see it if possible.
Right?! You heard them, Ellie. They both want to see it! And you think it fun yourself!
Fine... I am curious, I'll give you that.
But we'll stop the moment I sense any sign of danger!
<wave>Bravo! Ellie, you're the best witch ever!</wave>
Quit the insincere flattery. I'll see what I can do.
What potion or candy shall I use?
Firstly, the instructions say that the explosion is a result of [em1]heat and pressure combined[/em1].
Maybe I can [em1]heat it a bit more or press harder[/em1]?
I must warn you in advance: [em1]Potions are forbidden[/em1] for safety concerns.
I know. And speaking of [em1]candies that can produce heat and pressure[/em1]...
We do have a candy with similar effects...
One single type won't suffice. I need [em1]one candy that produces heat, and another candy that creates pressure[/em1].
There's nothing we can do when Ellie's gathering the materials. Let's come back another [em1]day[/em1]!
We'll get scolded again if we don't go home before late.
We'll leave it to you, Ellie! Teehee.
Oops, I messed up.
But it happens, and we can always try again.
[em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WarmComfortCandy_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HeavyPressCandy_Name"))][/em1] should do the trick?
It's too late to summon them.
I'll go see Theo with [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WarmComfortCandy_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HeavyPressCandy_Name"))][/em1] in [em1]daytime[/em1].
It's [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WarmComfortCandy_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HeavyPressCandy_Name"))][/em1].
Give [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WarmComfortCandy_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HeavyPressCandy_Name"))][/em1] to Theo?
<wave>At last, Lady Witch!</wave> Are those the candies in question?
Right, they are [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "WarmComfortCandy_Name"))] and [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HeavyPressCandy_Name"))][/em1]!
You just need to put them in the box for them to produce heat and pressure.
Then, BOOM! We'll get the [em1]explosion[/em1] we want.
Teehee, I'd expect no less of Ellie the greatest witch!
Humph, flattery will get you nowhere!
Get the kids, and we'll get rolling!
I've got business. I'll come back later.
Get the [em1]candies[/em1] and [em1]go to Theo during daytime[/em1]!
We just need to put both candies in the box?
Right, and even part of them will do.
<wave>Alright, I'm on it, heh~</wave>
If you crush the candies first, they will melt faster in the box.
<wave>Marvelous!</wave> It's slightly burnt, but it's good nevertheless!
Eek! Wh-what was that!
That's an excellent explosion!
Theo, try the snacks! They are great!
Thanks to you! You've made this view possible!
Right, it's so beautiful!
I hope the others were here to see it too.
I agree. It's a shame we were the only audience.
Teehee.
What's the big deal? We can show them from now on!
You're worrying me. What are you trying to do?
There's nothing to worry about. It's easy.
I'll place a [em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Box[/em1] in front of a villager's door.
And then...?
Ellie, you give me the [em1]sign[/em1], and I'll press the doorbell.
When the villager opens the door, BANG! They will see the spectacular sight we saw.
It's just a minor scare. Not even Dana fell down. They'll be fine.
A-are you doing it to Clala as well?
It's not like that, but Clala will be very mad if she finds out I'm involved in such a scheme.
And, haven't you recently been scolded for your pranks?
You may be getting yourself into more trouble.
Where on earth did you learn that?
It's okay. This is just a [em1]lighthearted joke[/em1], and the explosion is splendid!
Even Dana was able to handle such a small scare, teehee.
<wave>Come on, let's do it.</wave> Ellie, they'll enjoy it.
Where's that confidence coming from...
Why wouldn't they? It's just a pleasant surprise.
Sigh... Alright. It wasn't as risky as I imagined. As long as we do it outdoor.
Are we really doing it?
We shouldn't keep such a wonderful view to ourselves, and being surprised is fun, isn't it?
It is, and that's the usual naughty Ellie.
Let's go then!
While we're on it, Rubrum and Dana should keep watch for any passer-by heading this way.
H-hahaha! Dana, you overreacted!
Stop making fun of me! That was really scary.
Bahaha, you aren't as brave as you appear!
Dana, are you alright?
It's just a slight sprain, and we made it!
<shake>So we did! It was exactly what I wanted!</shake>
Heh, it was funny.
But you do find it fun, don't you? I saw you laughing.
Dana, don't tell me you want to be the only one scared. As long as Clala doesn't find out, we're good.
I do want to see others scared, but...
Alright, we'll start from [em1]Bjorn's home[/em1], since it's the closest from here.
I'll repeat the plan once more.
I'll place a [em1]Witch's Party Snack Gift Box[/em1] at the target's doorstep.
Rubrum and Dana will keep watch for passers-by.
If the coast's clear, Ellie will give me the [em1]signal[/em1].
I'll toss the candies in and press the doorbell! That's it!
But isn't Clala's bakery the closest?
... We'll save Clala for last.
I played a prank on Clala not long ago, and she nagged at me.
Even the memory of it gives me a headache! How could anyone babble non-stop for 3 hours straight?
Not even Mom does that!
If she catches me this time, I bet she will tie me to a chair and nag at me for a whole day!
That's why we'll save her for last...
My sister does like to lecture people...
Still, he doesn't find "cancelling the prank" an option. Alright, we'll start with Bjorn.
By the way, don't put the box too close to the door.
I know, I know. Lady Witch's word is my command, teehee.
You have a glib tongue.
I-I'm getting stage fright!
I feel nervous too!
Teehee, that's the essence of pranks. Let's go!
Ellie, I'm done!
What the— What is this! Snacks are falling from the sky!
<shake>Teehee, teeheehee, hahaha.</shake>
<shake>Heh, hahaha!</shake> We caught Bjorn off guard!
I've seen it once, but I'm still impressed this time! Heh.
I told you that it was gonna be easy! Now, let's get to the next house before we're exposed!
We'll show it to as many as possible, teehee.
Ellie! You saw that? Everyone's surprised!
What if my sister finds out... My heart is still racing.
That was more fun than I imagined!
Rex loved it. He was running about and picking the box up to inspect it.
Arin gaped at the falling snacks before she caught some midair and put them in her mouth!
Vinch jumped and looked around repeated, teehee.
I told you that it was gonna be fun!
Yeah, so far, so good!
The next is [em1]Enite's house[/em1]?
Heh, I hope Granny will like this view too!
And Roy's also at our place today.
Right, he said he and Enite were making something.
If so, we'll treat him to this fantastic view as well, teehee.
Ellie, ready here.
<shake>Roy!! Enite!!</shake>
<shake>G-Granny!</shake>
... <shake>H-hm?</shake>
Go check on them! See if they're injured!
There was an explosion in the house!
<shake>What are you doing!</shake>
Do you realize how dangerous that was!
I'm sorry. It was an accident...
D-don't be mad at me... I won't do it again... *sobbing*
I should have known it. Clala will kill me if she finds out.
Enite, could you keep it from my sister?
I should have stopped them...
I know how naughty Theo is, but I didn't expect the other kids to play along.
I'm ashamed.
But why did you take the box inside?
I thought it was my parcel, the materials I ordered.
But there were some [em1]strange noises[/em1] when I picked it up.
Thank goodness I told Enite to take cover.
Luckily, no, but it was close.
You may think it funny, but you could have caused serious injuries.
Right... I'm sorry, Enite. I'm glad you weren't hurt.
And you, Theo, this is nothing to laugh off!
The villagers have been complaining about your [em1]pranks[/em1]. You know that?
I know how lonely and tiresome living alone can be. I thought you were just seeking attention.
I trusted you...
And you've let me down, a lot.
I must talk to your parents about this.
Don't go away when you've cleaned the mess, understood?
Theo, I think you should apologize first.
Looks like he's had his moment of reckoning. How about we [em1]clean the mess[/em1] together?
We can't leave the place the way it is.
I'll do my best...
It's finally finished...
Thank you, everyone. Help yourself to some tea.
And have some sweet bread too.
It's a well-earned treat, now that everything's spotless.
But don't you play such pranks again. You could have injured people.
I'll keep it in mind.
Wait, has anyone seen Theo?
What? He's gone?!
Now that I think about it, I don't think he was there during the cleaning.
What? How dare he sneak away when we were scrubbing and polishing!
I shouldn't have played with Theo! He's always like this!
Don't be too hard on Theo. He doesn't mean bad.
But we'd better make sure he's safe. Ellie, could you go search for him?
I guess it can't be helped, and I'm kind of worried too.
I'll have a word with him if I find him.
Thank you. I'll leave it to you.
Alright, let's look for Theo.
If only there were some [em1]traces[/em1].
Don't you see the stuff littering the ground?
What's this? It's [em1]sticky[/em1].
Is this [em1]candy dust[/em1]?
I see. Theo was right beside the Witch's Party Snack Gift Boxes.
Maybe that's why he got candy dust on him.
We may find him if we follow the [em1]trace[/em1]!
I believe there's a candy that helps with cleaning.
You should be reflecting on your mistake!
Quit the nonsense and go on with the scrubbing.
Fine, I'm the one who caused this. This is what I get.
And the sofa's a mess too. This will take forever!
Theo has a spare sofa at his place. They won't notice if I switch the two.
Don't be ridiculous.
Just kidding. I hardly even clean my own room.
Alright, we're almost there.
I think it's almost over. Everyone, come here.
Theo! There you are!
<shake>H-huh?</shake> Ellie?
Who told you I was here?!
My keen observation and deduction.
You don't sound impressed. So, why are you here?
You shouldn't have fled amid the cleaning. We had to do your part as well.
But you can come back now, since Enite and Roy have cooled down.
They will forgive you as long as you apologize properly.
Why should I apologize?
I wanted to share a splendid view with them. That's all.
It was just a lighthearted joke, and you all enjoyed it.
They shouldn't have taken an unidentified object into the house.
But we were the ones who placed it there.
It's always like this. I get scolded for everything I do.
Everyone tells me about how I've "let them down," when I've never asked for their expectations...
They never let me do what I really want to do.
Enite is as nice as Granny, so I thought she'd be different...
But she turns out to be just like every other adult!
I didn't do anything wrong.
You may have a point, but you've got a worrying look.
Both Enite and Roy are unhurt.
Everyone's worried about you, Theo.
Who are you to say that?
Theo, there's something on your face.
Hm? What are you doing?
<shake>Hey! W-wait!</shake> What was that? Why are your hands so sticky!
I had no choice but to get my hands dirty when looking for you.
Then I saw a face perfect for wiping my hands on it, so I couldn't help!
Eek, now my face is all sticky. Do you have to ruin the mood?
I was being serious.
What's it to me?
I was the one who did the cleaning and searched for the fleeing kid.
Is it your place to complain when you've caused me so much trouble?
Okay, fine, that's great of you, but...
What I want to say is... hmm...
You could have simply said "thank you."
Why would I? I was going to ask you if you'd drunk some strange potion! You're giving me goosebumps by being so nice.
Okay, okay, you're welcome.
<shake>Ugh, just leave me alone!</shake>
But... I do feel better than I did just now.
Thanks to me?
Never!
Anyway, leave me for now. I'll go back, after I've reflected on the whole thing.
Bye, Ellie. See you later.
Hi, Ellie! You always look as busy as a bee.
You seem to be in a good mood. What happened?
I've been getting along with [em1]Honey Bear[/em1]!
He's just told me about a spot where I could get a lot of honey!
I don't really know Honey Bear, since he's been living in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
Exactly what I was going to say: Honey Bear's never stepped out of the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))]!
That's why I want to take him to a new place.
They say you've been to somewhere called the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1]?
Wait, you aren't going there, are you?
Arin said that a [em1]sweet herb[/em1] can be found in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))].
And it so happens that our party is embarking on a [em1]new adventure[/em1]. That can be our next destination, teehee.
But it's dark in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))], and the passages are confusing. It's dangerous.
Right, Ellie has fallen off a cliff in there.
The others won't allow it.
How about you join us? You've been there before. You can guide us.
You're the [em1]guest member[/em1] of our party.
Well, if we stick to places I've been to...
Exactly, we'll be fine if you've got our back. Do be our guide, <wave>Lady Witch~</wave>
I'm also interested in this sweet herb. I'm going.
It's decided then!
You tell [em1]Rubrum[/em1], and I'll fetch Dana.
If you're ready, [em1]come to me during daytime,[/em1] teehee.
Tsk, we can't go to the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))] without you!
We can't go without you.
Meh...
I'll be waiting for you! Keep that in mind!
Ellie! Are you ready? Can we go now?
What?! Are we putting it off again? Hurry up!
Are you ready this time?
Yes! Are we after the sweet herb?
Yeah, I hope it won't turn out to be disappointing.
Don't cross the bridge before you come to it. Off to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1]!
Lady Witch, everyone's here except you!
I'll be done in no time, I promise!
Be quick, will you? I'm tired of waiting.
Theo, I've got something to tell you.
That sounds ominous...
Have you not reconciled with Enite yet?
You can't run away from it forever.
<wave>I</wave>, I know it! It's none of your business.
Theo... Is it something you can't talk to ME about? Do you not trust me?
Th-that's not the point.
I just feel uncomfortable whenever I see Enite.
You feel uncomfortable whenever you see Enite? But you were not like this before.
Ever since the snack box prank, whenever I see Enite, I've felt like she's gonna scold me again, which makes me uneasy...
You're still lingering on that? Just apologize to her and you'll be fine. No big deal!
It may be no big deal for you, but not for me...!
Why? You just need to say sorry.
Saying sorry makes me feel like I'm the only villain.
Like it was my fault. Like I'm responsible for everything.
I know I've caused trouble, but it's so hard to say the word...
I didn't mean to put Enite in harm's way, or make her house a mess.
Will you do nothing then?
And it's too late now. My parents already know it.
Their interference has extended to how I dress. I don't even want to open their letters anymore.
So, that's why your letterbox is stuffed with unopened letters.
Right. I'm only telling you about it. Don't tell anyone else.
You think everyone will hate you for it?
Humph, they can hate me for all I care. I'll always have you and Honey Bear by my side.
What if Honey Bear and I disappear? Every relationship can change.
Talk to Enite. You need to face it.
If it scares you, I can go with you.
You're hurting my feelings... but I'll think about it.
Alright, [em1]I'll meet you after the adventure![/em1]
Alright, alright. The kids are coming. Can we go now?
Oops, sorry, I don't think it's the right time for me.
What? Were you here just to upset me?
But we can't go without you. Do take care of whatever you're doing fast.
We can't go on an adventure so late at night.
I shall [em1]go to Theo during the day[/em1].
But it really was your fault.
Members of the adventure party, welcome to the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_StarSeaCave"))][/em1]!
Did you see all those murals on our way here? They speak of so many interesting stories!
I'll tell Clala about them!
I-I'm kind of scared. What if a g-ghost turns up?
I've seen this before. It looks like a real night sky, as if being among a sea of stars!
Watch your steps though. There are many cliffs.
Especially Theo. I saw you startling Rubrum on our way here!
I didn't do that. He was <wave>sooo</wave> scared, so I helped him unwind.
Fine, but don't do that again, or we're heading back already.
Alright, alright, I won't! What a spoilsport.
Anyway, according to what you said, we should be quite close now...
Wait a minute. Let me check my memo.
Characteristics... [em1]It looks like jelly. The color is light pink[/em1].
But it's said to have firm roots, [em1]making it hard for a single person to uproot[/em1].
We can first split up to search. If anyone finds one, we'll pull it together.
Don't. You. Ever. Wander off.
Behave, or I won't take you on an adventure again!
Fine... You were right. This place really is a dark maze.
If you forget the characteristics, come to me and I'll repeat them.
Those stars look so real. I feel like I'm exploring the sky.
I don't actually enjoy nighttime, but I [em1]like stars[/em1].
You do? Why?
When night falls, sounds fade away, as if I were left alone in the world.
But if I look up, I'll always see stars twinkling up there.
Stars never abandon me. That's why I like them.
It would be awesome if this place is home to not only stars, but also [em1]sweet herbs[/em1], heh.
Are you urging me? Don't worry! I'm searching!
Do you remember the characteristics?
[em1]It looks like soft jelly. The color is light pink[/em1].
Leave this area to me. You can look somewhere else.
You want me to repeat the characteristics?
It's not here. Look somewhere else.
I've never seen a cave so amazing!
Look, there are strange flames over there!
And the murals on our way here were fascinating too!
It's a shame I only had enough time for a glimpse.
Dana, we're here for sweet herbs, remember?
I can't help it. Everything here is new to me!
Alright, you can look around, but keep my words in mind.
"Stay where Ellie can see me. Don't wander off. Be careful." Right?
Heh, I didn't forget them, and I'm keeping an eye out for sweet herbs!
Leave this area to me! You can search somewhere else.
Okay, I'm counting on you, Dana!
Heh, I'll tell Clala about today's adventure when I go home!
Ellie? I'll be searching this area. Look somewhere else!
Rubrum, you're with Honey Bear?
Heh, Theo told me that I could stay with Honey Bear if I was afraid.
And that I could call out for him if anything happened.
Are you still afraid?
I am, but Honey Bear's with me, and the others are around too.
I'll do my best to help Granny and Theo!
Honey Bear and I have searched this place. There is no sweet herb.
I see. It isn't here either.
No, but we haven't checked out everywhere.
That herb may make delicious tea as well...
But we need to find it first.
I'll look around here! Ellie, you can check another area.
Rubrum, besides Theo, you can call out for me too if you're scared.
Got it! Thank you, Ellie. I'll be fine.
I've spotted some interesting herbs and mushrooms. It's getting exciting, heh.
Glad to hear that. I'll leave this area to you then. See you!
This seems to match Theo's description.
I don't think this looks anything like [em1]soft jelly[/em1].
Maybe you're right. We'll look elsewhere.
I thought this was the plant Theo wanted.
But the color is different...
Our target should be [em1]light pink[/em1].
No luck. We'll look elsewhere.
It’s a piece that fell off. Did someone drop it?
Maybe it was dropped by one of the animals nearby?
Looks like it doesn’t have an owner… Guess I’ll take it
<wave>Hehe~ Finders keepers~</wave>
Oh, there’s one here too?
<wave>Teehee~ This one’s mine too~</wave>
Yeah, yeah. Just don’t forget why we came here.
Look at this plant!
[em1]It looks like soft jelly, and it's light pink.[/em1] This must be the one!
Okay, let's pull it out.
I've been thinking: You're so good at finding things.
After all, I'm a witch. I'm used to it.
But my strength alone isn't enough.
Shall [em1]we[/em1] pull it together?
That's what I'm saying! It may be easy when we're united. Everyone line up behind Ellie and help out!
Can [em1]we[/em1] make it? Isn't it super firm?
It may be firm for one person, but not for a crowd.
One, two! Done!
Who was it that [em1]jerked[/em1] from behind?
Honey Bear joined us at the last moment!
What did I say? Strength lies in solidarity! So, this is the sweet herb.
Does it taste sweet if I eat it raw? Let's find out. Ah~
<shake>Wait!</shake> Granny said that you shouldn't mess with an unidentified herb!
To be on the safe side, we should ask Arin or Enite.
Theo, you heard this from Arin, didn't you?
To be precise... I heard Arin talking to Rex about it.
You [em1]eavesdropped[/em1] on her?
What do you expect me to do? Arin and I are not on speaking terms.
Is it because of your pranks?
You naughty kid.
Ellie...? Where's the herb?
The herb? Didn't we leave it on the side after uprooting it?
Got you? I was just kidding. I wouldn't really eat it, heh.
Have you forgotten the time when Honey Bear ate the donut? He could have followed your bad examples!
<shake>Wait!</shake> I haven't finished! Don't you eat it!
<shake>Wh-What do we do?! Make him spit it out?</shake>
He has swallowed it.
He looks fine... Or rather, he looks like he enjoyed it?
<shake>Honey Bear!</shake> You mustn't eat random things on the ground!
It was probably sweet. Look, Honey Bear likes it.
Anyway, let's wrap up for today. I'll consult [em1]Arin[/em1].
It could have been just a sweet herb.
Leave it to me and go back to the village, alright?
Alright... See you later.
Okay, we just need to check Honey Bear's condition.
It may be fine.
Right! Honey Bear will be fine! I'll have a look.
Did you hear any strange noise...?
You aren't imagining things.
I believe it's coming from Honey Bear's way.
I believe this place abounds with Cleansing Herbs...
Do we have to search every nook and cranny?
Don't you have Enite's memo? There should be a description in it.
I'll check. The herb should be somewhere around here.
Yippee, I did it! The victory's mine!
Congrats. You've finally found it.
Good, we've got the Cleansing Herb.
I’ve already got the Cheongyeon Herb.
If the memo is correct, it should be around here...
These herbs all look the same. What do I do?
What does the memo say? Read it carefully.
A [em1]potion[/em1] may help.
I can’t tell which one is the Glowtwig Bloom.
Check the memo. There might be a [em1]potion[/em1] you need to use.
Don’t waste your potions blindly. Go closer and check the [em1]flower[/em1] first.
Well, potions are precious after all. Let’s use them carefully.
It really is glowing! I can see it now that we're in the dark!
It [em1]absorbs light[/em1], just like the Darkness Potion.
But unlike the Darkness Potion, it doesn't work when the light is too intense.
This is curious. Nature is full of wonders.
It actually glows even when in the Darkness Potion.
Doesn't the Darkness Potion absorb light? Why's the flower still glowing?
In that case, I suppose their light-absorbing natures conflicted with and offset one another.
Anyway, I've got the flower, and I'm taking it with me.
This will do the trick, right?
I didn't expect the ingredients to be so hard to gather.
Antidotes are inherently hard to craft.
And every poison requires a different cure.
Some don't even have a cure. You're lucky to have encountered a curable one.
Right, I hope this will cure him.
Theo said that he was also hunting for ingredients. I'll [em1]go find him.[/em1]
Theo, there you are! I've found you at last.
Ellie! I've gathered every ingredient I can find here, but I'm still missing a few types.
I wonder if these will suffice...
Don't worry. I've got some substitutes, although they may not be as effective.
You look like your usual self though.
I'm told that fretting won't help.
It's very considerate of you to have got substitutes. Honey Bear will be fine, right?
Let's hope so. We just need to craft the antidote.
Hurry up then! You've got the time?
Of course I'll do this. But where are we crafting it?
What about in front of my house? I've got a campfire set up. My pot may be small, but it's usable.
You've got everything ready in advance. Okay, let's do it there.
Not yet? Alright, but come as soon as you've got time.
Honey Bear seems to be suffering. It really distresses me...
At last! Do you have time now?
I forgot to bring [em1][lua(GetItemName("GlowtwigBloom"))][/em1] and [em1][lua(GetItemName("BlueMistHerb"))][/em1]. I’ll go grab them right away.
Theo, are you telling me... that this is the pot you've prepared?
S-so what? It's the biggest pot I have!
But... the recipe says it requires a large pot and a big fire.
Would it be better if I use my witch's pot?
Well, witch's pots are for magical concoctions.
Since this antidote doesn't require magic to craft, maybe an ordinary pot is more suitable.
When it comes to medicine, dosage is the key.
The recipe says that a witch's pot may change the antidote's effect.
Although it may reduce effectiveness, the antidote can be made in a smaller pot.
Well... I wonder if it will work. We don't have all the ingredients, and the pot is small.
And I've never made an antidote. I don't feel so sure.
I suppose making an antidote is just like cooking.
As long as you follow the recipe. The steps are not complicated.
Give it a try, Ellie! I'll do whatever I can to help.
I-I made it? I think that was a success?
<shake>You did?</shake> Great, thank heaven! Honey Bear will be saved, right?
We can't be sure yet, but at least we have an antidote!
By the way, will Honey Bear drink this?
Emm, it's medicine, so it's probably super bitter?
<shake>Eww</shake>! It's [em1]as bitter as hell[/em1]! I've never tasted anything this awful!
You tried it?
I have to find out, but I'll never do it again. *pukes*
That said, I saw it coming, and I'm prepared!
When I was sick, Granny and my parents used to do this.
It will work! Honey Bear is in safe hands!
So he is! Let's go to him now. I hope he gets well soon.
I expected this. This is why I prepared more ingredients than we could use.
Same here. Failure is not an option this time. We must save Honey Bear!
I'm warning you: That's junk. You mustn't use it.
Honey Bear! I've got you the medicine. Take it. Have a little sip.
Maybe he knows it's bitter?
Honey Bear, you won't get better if you don't take the medicine.
It can't be helped. Last resort.
Huh? He won't take it.
[em1]You mixed the antidote with porridge?[/em1]
Yup, that's what my family does when I'm sick.
I can't handle bitter food either. This is how they trick me into eating it.
The [em1]antidote is bitter[/em1], but it may help to wash it down with porridge.
Alright, let's give it a shot.
Finally. He ate it all.
He had a grimace all through the process.
I don't think the porridge concealed the bitterness.
It's just a camouflage. It's better than taking the antidote the way it is.
Sorry I deceived you, but this is the only way for you to get better.
I've told you that you should take care of yourself when nobody's there to look out for you.
Don't eat random things from the ground, you fool.
Sorry, I shouldn't be babbling when you're sick. Have some rest. I'll be here for you.
... Ellie, the antidote should have kicked in?
Yeah. He looks better than before, but not completely...
He still has some poison in him.
<shake>What? Wh-what now?</shake> Will he ever recover?
It's my fault...
I let Honey Bear out of my sight...
I was carried away by the new environment, and I neglected him... What do I do, Ellie?
<shake>What do I do?</shake> What if Honey Bear ends up dying because of my carelessness?
C-calm down! Honey Bear will be fine. L-let's figure this out...
There can be another way. As long as we make a proper antidote...
<shake>That's impossible!</shake> You heard Alvin. The [em1]ingredients are hard to find[/em1]!
And they're rare not just in this village, but in other places as well! I've searched every place possible myself!
Of course it's hard if you want to do it all by yourself.
But everyone hates me. I'm not that oblivious.
And Enite will never forgive me... *sobs*
Why isn't Honey Bear recovering?
Honey Bear is going to die. I killed him with my foolishness...
The others may [em1]help[/em1].
But how exactly are they going to help?
Most importantly, they won't be willing to. Not for me
How about we cask [em1]Enite[/em1] to [em1]post a request for help on the bulletin[/em1]?
The place is frequented by villagers. Someone may happen to have the ingredients we need.
Think about our [em1]sweet herb[/em1] hunting!
Had I gone alone, I couldn't have gotten the herb.
You don't seem to be your usual self either.
I... I'll admit it. It was incredibly ineffective.
...Honey Bear? What are you doing?
"Hang in there?" Are you cheering me on?
You're the one who's sick.
Why are you worrying about me?
And you only became sick because I wasn't watching...
Ellie, I'm going. [em1]I want to see Enite.[/em1]
Theo!
Are you sure? What if nobody's willing to help?
I know I'm being selfish.
They don't have to forgive me, but I must try.
I can't just sit here and regret. I must take action! I'm Honey Bear's friend!
I'll go with you then. We'll do this together.
I'll always have your back.
Yup! Let's go.
My, hello, Ellie!
Come on in!
What's up? Is the antidote finished?
Thanks to you, Enite!
But it wasn't that effective. Probably because I didn't have all the required ingredients.
You're working so hard for Honey Bear.
Hm? Who is that...?
Em, h-hi... I...
Enite, I...
I know that I'm a pain in the ass in this village.
Everyone hates me for my pranks.
I almost injured you the last time.
I know I'm shameless, and that I am beyond redemption.
You don't have to forgive me, but could you help me one last time?
I don't want my friend to suffer. Please...
Theo, you can do this!
I, I'm really sorry for what I did before!
Of course I'll forgive you.
And I'll certainly help you, heh.
Why? I almost injured you with my prank!
Because you've apologized for it from the bottom of your heart, heh.
To apologize is much more difficult than one might think.
It requires a great deal of courage.
It requires the person to view themselves objectively, and view the other party objectively.
Even more so when your visit was a decision you made yourself.
I appreciate the sincere apology.
That aside, how exactly may I help you?
Th-thank you so much... *sobbing*
Since Theo isn't able to speak at the moment, I'll talk in his stead.
We need a proper antidote because the makeshift one didn't work, but we lack the ingredients.
We want to ask the [em1]villagers for help[/em1].
Could you post a request for help on the [em1]bulletin[/em1] for us? Someone may be able to help us.
That's easy. It will be out immediately. Rest assured, heh.
I'll do whatever I can!
Thank you both.
Alright, that's everything within our power at the moment.
Let's go back for now. You should have some rest.
Ellie, will Honey Bear be alright?
He isn't in immediate danger. It's not much, but the makeshift antidote is doing its work.
Once we gather all the ingredients, we can make a proper antidote, which will heal Honey Bear!
Alright... See you again [em1]tomorrow during the day[/em1].
Theo, you look worn out. Are you okay?
Of course I am. Don't worry about me. I'm perfectly fine.
Pfffft, but your eyes are badly swollen from all the crying.
<shake>Th-there was no crying!</shake> I got dirt in my eye!
Don't you tell anyone that I cried.
Well... I'll consider it.
... Ellie, what do we do now?
Everything we still lack is hard to come by.
And the villagers may not help.
Shall we go to the fountain to check it out? There may be someone at the bulletin.
It's too late for a meeting.
We shall [em1]meet Theo during the day[/em1].
It usually takes [em1]at least one day[/em1] for people to notice any new poster on the bulletin board.
[em1]I shall go to Theo during the day tomorrow[/em1].
Nobody is here...
M-maybe we are too early!
Why the long face?
Heh, just to say hello and cheer you up.
Because... I feel so powerless.
I'm ready to do anything if it's for Honey Bear.
But all I can do now is to stand idling. It makes me anxious.
Yo, boy, depression isn't for you.
A-Arden? Why are you here?
And what's that giant pot for?
Enite said that you needed a large pot and a big fire.
Hahaha, I believe that's what you call a large pot. I helped make it!
I've brought my tools in case you need anything else. Just say it.
I didn't plan to come. I'm leaving once I've done my bit.
I've only come because Enite and Rubrum won't leave me alone.
Thank you for being willing to help, but we don't have the ingredients.
Are we the first to arrive? Hahaha! There's nothing to worry about then!
Theo! I've brought everyone, hehe!
<shake>AHAHA!</shake> I thought I was late!
You've got the fireworks to blame.
I know we don't gather often and you want to celebrate,
but fireworks are not needed in making antidotes.
Yeah, I know.
Are you guys here to help me...?
Haha! Why not? You posted for help and ingredients yourself.
And you even knocked on every door to apologize and ask for help.
Theo knocked on every door to apologize?!
<shake>EXACTLY!</shake> It's known throughout the village!
Everyone was young and childish once.
But people grow up. They mature. You have matured.
I helped spread the message!
Theo can be childish and annoying.
But we are friends! And you don't turn your back on a friend in distress, heh.
I like Theo! Playing with Theo is much more fun than playing alone!
I followed Theo around yesterday and helped him with the pleading!
I'm impressed! You've been working hard!
And, Bjorn and Vinch were up the whole night looking for ingredients!
Hey, Rubrum! You don't have to reveal that!
And we couldn't have found the ingredients by ourselves.
<shake>LONG STORY SHORT!</shake> Arin taught us about the ingredients!
The search was supposed to be hard, but Arin sped things up with her extensive knowledge!
It wasn't just me... Alvin helped too... I was not much help...
I simply inspired you. You applied the knowledge to practice, and that's what mattered.
They were both a great help.
Thanks to their input, I managed to get the ingredients from an acquaintance in the area.
Guys! I can't believe you're all helping out!
To err is human. Even more so when the human is a kid.
If we approach the kid with kindness, we can guide him in the right direction.
I was there myself.
I'm glad to be able to offer help now.
And to be honest, I didn't expect Theo to apologize so sincerely.
Theo, you visited Roy too?
He did, and I simply couldn't refuse him when he was so desperate.
Ellie, you said that we just needed to help...
Your words... have brought me insight.
The old me would have refrained from asking for help... and would have made no difference.
Hm? Arin, why are you staring at me?
Heh... Theo visited the library too...
He was so desperate... that I decided to do everything within my power... even if I couldn't find the ingredients.
I can't find those ingredients either, being just an ordinary baker.
But I've got some [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))] for our patient.
Delicious food gives you strength, doesn't it?
Why are you doing all of this for me?
I thought you hated me. I thought you would never forgive me...
Why? How could this be?
Because we've accepted you as our fellow villager since quite some time ago.
You may be a troublemaker at times,
but you've added vitality to the village.
I want you to stay in the village!
You've made the village a more lively place.
My grandfather used to say that children should play as much as they want!
And you've apologized with all your heart!
Well... After visiting Enite, I've been thinking.
I should apologize to everyone, since I caused trouble to more than just Enite...
You could have dodged the subject, but you've chosen to face it.
I decided to help after seeing you apologize.
Guys...
I told you. It's not just me and Honey Bear.
Everyone cherishes you, Theo.
Boohoohoo~!
Theo?!
Thank you so very very much...!
But you just cried yesterday. At this rate, your eyes are never gonna recover.
Let's make the antidote!
I can't help it... I never imagined this.
Okay, hold your tears back! We've got all the ingredients.
Will this save Honey Bear?
Sure! This antidote carries everyone's love!
Now, take it to him, as well as my best regards.
Right, leave the cleaning up to us, hahaha!
Theo, go ahead!
Honey Bear! Try this one! It's the real antidote!
He must know it's bitter. He isn't touching it.
Come on, Honey Bear, take it! Or you won't get better!
We deceived him the last time. He won't be deceived again.
Please, Honey Bear! You've got to take your medicine!
If you insist...
You swallowed it?!
<shake>*coughs* That was awful!</shake>
But it will cure you! See? Honey Bear!
It's bitter, but it takes the pain away. I promise!
Are you healed?
Great! Honey Bear! Thank goodness!
I-I was so worried! Don't ever eat random things again!
I'm glad the antidote worked.
Now that I think about it, we've got the [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))][/em1] from Clala.
Here. It's a reward for being good.
Pffft, hahaha! Honey Bear looks very grateful!
Hey, you smudged my face again. Heh, take this!
How dare! You asked for this. Ha!
Teeheehee! Your face is a mess too.
Eek, it's all sticky!
Ellie, you've been working hard as well. That's a gift from Honey Bear.
We ended up smudging each other's faces.
But a happy ending is the best.
Haha! What are you murmuring about?
Nothing!
By the way, Ellie, that's not all the repayment you're getting from me, you know.
Hm...? What? Don't tell me... Hey, wait!
Ugh, you naughty brat.
Why do you keep smudging my face with honey?!
Blame yourself for pouring a whole jar of honey on Theo's head.
That was meant to be a reward.
Says who?
Despite the face smudging, it was such a satisfying day.
Theo should be on his way back?
Or, is he going to spread the news about Honey Bear's recovery first?
Find it out yourself if you're curious.
Okay, I will!
Hi, Ellie! You're back!
What the heck! What's with your clothes!
What? Heh, is there anything different from before?
What do you mean "anything"! Everything's different! You look so neat and handsome!
That's what he wore the first time you met.
It's just that I've decided to approach my life more seriously, heh.
Actually, after I thanked everyone, Enite told me something on my way back.
My parents also helped with the ingredient hunting.
Your parents?
Right, so I went through all the letters in my letterbox.
You mean that hill of letters?
After that, I suddenly realized that the nagging was a demonstration of their love for me.
Speaking of which, I've seen them at work.
They are always occupied, exploring, studying, and researching late into the night.
Despite that, they actually carved out time for me.
Hard as it must have been, they helped me gather the ingredients without me knowing it.
Did that reassure you?
Yup! After I left school and my friends, I thought I was going to spend a lonely life.
But my parents and the villages have been caring for me this whole time.
And you as well. I wouldn't have noticed it if you weren't here.
Wait, it's out of character for you to be so sincere. What are you plotting?
Ugh, do you have to ruin the mood?
I should be the one saying that, haha!
My life sucks these days.
You're holding another [em1]letter[/em1]. Is it from your parents again?
Wait, why crumple it up? Have you even read it?
Humph, there's nothing new to read about. Just the old nagging from the very beginning!
"Behave when you're away from home." "Have you done your homework?" Blah blah blah.
And they're scolding me for abusing the Witch's Party Snack Gift Box.
Why would I want to read these?
Leave me alone. I'm gonna throw it away.
But it's a [em1]letter from your parents[/em1]. It's disrespectful not to keep it.
Why must I keep a letter full of babbling!
They never have anything nice to say to me, huh...
They'd better not write at all. That way, I won't have to check my letterbox.
And the villagers aren't having any sense of humor. Dana keeps yelling at me for what I did before.
In short, nothing good is happening to me.
Wait, there's something good. During my adventure, I ran into a [em1]fantastic beast[/em1]!
A [em1]fantastic beast[/em1]?
Exactly. Since my pranks aren't working out, I've been on [em1]explorations[/em1] with the kids.
And I found something fun. Heh, I can tell you more if you're curious.
But you need to do me a [em1]favor[/em1]! It's very simple!
Deal. I do wonder what you found.
But your favor has to be reasonable!
Heh, relax. I said it's very simple.
Well, as you know, Enite has been cooking meals for me.
I've finished the food, but I still have the utensil at my place.
Could you return it for me?
Why me? Can't you do it yourself?
I hate the trouble. That's all.
Come on, do you want to hear the tale or not? Go ahead, heh.
Fine, if it's just delivering a [em1]bowl[/em1]. Be right back.
Tsk, lazybones! I won't tell you the story!
Ellie? What's it? Your curiosity has gotten the better of you?
I'll tell you everything as long as you do me the favor.
You fought with Dana as well?
Yeah, but the lass is quick to forget.
Ellie, I got you some ingredients!
Well, well, didn't expect you to do your bit.
I've gathered all the honey I can find, heh.
That's quite a lot. I'm impressed.
But we really need some to spare, in case our first attempt fails.
All the basic ingredients are here, and we've refined the recipe.
The name's decided too. I'm calling it [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))][/em1], because it uses a lot of honey.
Clala has so much fun making the test version of [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))][/em1]!
Nothing motivates her more than new items! Hehe.
Dana, shush!
I was just a little excited, because it's been a while since I developed a new item.
Most importantly, my recipes can't fail, can they?
Thank you for your help, Clala!
I've never made a dessert before!
Heh, a brand-new donut! I can't wait to try it!
That said, Rubrum, aren't you scared, being away from your home so late at night? I'm fine only because it's my own home.
I'm okay! Theo and Clala are with me!
You can say that again! You owe that rare experience to me.
Can we start working on it?
Will it work...? I'm not a great baker.
No, you aren't. You are a great blaster.
Let's not be too creative this time.
I will be more careful since there are other people around.
Heh, I didn't think you were a terrible cook, Ellie.
Try not to get us poisoned with your final product.
Hey, I'm not that bad!
Haha, don't worry. Even the best bakers were beginners, and I have your back.
It's similar to potion crafting. You just need to [em1]stick to the recipe[/em1].
How can you possibly fail when the amount of every ingredient is clearly stated?
If it really overwhelms you, just shout "Master Theo! Have mercy on me!" and it's not like I can't lend a hand.
I'd rather ask Clala.
You should behave when we're cooking, do you hear me?
Especially Theo. You are not to fool around in my bakery.
Humph, fine! Granny always says that a kitchen is a dangerous place.
Alright, I'll trust you for this one time. Ellie, please keep an eye on the kids.
Alright, let's get rolling.
ou at least know how to knead the dough, right? Hehe.
The donut collapsed...
No success? It's okay. We can practice more.
We've still got ingredients. Would you like to try again?
Say "Master Theo! Have Mercy on me!" if you need help.
No, thanks.
Fine, I'll help anyway, heh.
D-does this count as a success?
I actually baked something that looks edible!
Whoa, it looks delicious!
You should attribute half of it to me. I did much of the work, teehee.
You were a better cook than I thought.
I can do it if I want to, and it was an easy recipe to begin with. No trial and error was needed.
Theo adjusted the baking ratios for me, heh. Check out my donut.
Rubrum did a good job too, haha.
What about the taste? Is it good?
R-right, the taste is the most important factor.
Both the smell and the taste are sweet. It's exactly the kind of food I like!
What? You've already tried some?
Honestly, I'm a gourmet when it comes to sweets and desserts, teehee.
I have a discerning palate for them.
I want to have some too!
Don't you eat them all! Save some for me!
I'll dig in too...
Whoa, it's good! So sweet and aromatic!
Seems that everyone's doing well already. Good thing we succeeded before we ran out of ingredients.
Nothing is as satisfying as cooking the first meal on your own, ahem.
Dad would be amazed if he found out that I've made donuts!
It's so good. I want a second one.
Sorry, but there's no more for you, teehee.
How come! There are still plenty left, and I've only had one!
Because there will be none left for Honey Bear if you eat them at this rate.
I didn't eat that much!
As a bigger girl, you naturally have a larger appetite. You can easily wolf down all of them even if you claim to want only <wave>"a second one."</wave>
<shake>That's mean! I've only had a single bite! You little brat!</shake>
<shake>Who are you calling little!</shake>
Who else could it be? Aren't you younger than me?
Quit it, will you?
Ellie was the one who started it!
Blame yourself for being mean!
I need to have a word with you two if you don't stop fighting...
<shake>Huh?</shake> Wait! Is it going to be another lecture?
Alright, alright, I'll shut up. I don't need a whole day of lecturing.
Same here...
I packed the donuts while you were quarreling!
Thank you, Rubrum. We can now deliver them to Honey Bear.
Are we really visiting that [em1]scary animal[/em1]?
It almost scared my life out of me the last time...
It would be boring if I go alone.
Who am I going to boast to if you guys aren't around? Come on!
Just run away like last time if you sense danger.
Shall I go along?
What, Ellie, you're coming with us? Alright then, your presence will be reassuring for the kids.
I'll make an exception and make you our [em1]guest member[/em1]! Teehee.
In that case, I'm going!
Me too! It's less frightening if I'm with a crowd!
It's decided then?
It's too late today. Let's go with the kids [em1]during the day[/em1].
[em1]During the day[/em1]?
Rubrum and Dana are going too. They will be scolded if they go out at night.
It's been a long day. [em1]Come to me during daytime[/em1], teehee!
I had a great time today, hah. Be careful on your way back.
I think the dough’s about right like this.
Yeah, the oven looks about right too. Now I just need to shape it and bake~
Theo wants us to meet him [em1]during the day[/em1].
Hi there, Ellie! We've been waiting for you!
Dana and Rubrum are ready to go.
What about you? Is now a good time?
No problem, ready when you are!
We were getting impatient. We almost left without you.
No way! We're going together!
We are, but not when you're so slow. You should arrive as early as I do.
Don't expect me to cover you if you fall down when we're running for our lives.
That said, you can probably handle a bit of falling when you're so thick-skinned, teehee.
If you dare leave without me, I'll get my revenge like last time.
Do it if you can. Let's go!
What? What's keeping you? A mountain of boxes to unpack after moving?
I just have all kinds of work to do! I'm not a loafer!
All kinds of work, huh? Whatever, we don't have forever!
Stop rushing me! I'll be here once I'm done.
Teehee, so you should. Hurry up!
Hmm, it should be around here...
Is it the wrong place? This is weird...
I can't recall it.
You forgot the location?
It should be somewhere near here. Does any of you remember?
No idea... I was running for my life.
So was I. I almost got lost had Theo not found me.
Hide behind me if you're too scared. Don't wander off.
We can't afford to get lost around here.
Shall we split up and look around?
Alright, let's [em1]search the surroundings of this spot[/em1].
If you find Honey Bear or his habitat, stay away and get everyone, got it?
Got it. See you later!
Is this a lump of honey?
Did someone drop it here?
I do know an animal that loves honey.
It could be the Honey Bear we're after.
Great, I think it likes honey.
I'll take the honey lump with me.
Since it's ownerless, I'll claim it.
That's quite thrifty of you.
One should cherish food and resources.
If there's a lump of honey, Honey Bear should be around. Theo was probably right.
We might have walked past him without noticing.
Right, you can retrace your path.
Theo? What are you doing here?
I was wondering if I should examine the area from the top of a tree.
But that's a tall tree. It's dangerous!
I'm the best tree climber among my peers, teehee.
I have to be fast at escaping, or I'll get caught for my pranks.
I've climbed trees taller than this one.
It's just a walk in a tree.
Why would you claim trees? You're not a monkey.
Monkey?
Monkeys are known for climbing trees. And have you heard of this saying?
"Even a monkey can fall from a tree.‌"
It means you can fail even in a field you're great at.
If you fall from this tree, you'll get a huge bump on your head, ahaha.
I'm not going to make such a mistake, teehee.
I'll go up there. You can search somewhere else.
Or you can go deeper into the woods.
Alright, I will.
What? I need to warm up before I climb a tree.
Leave this area to me and look elsewhere.
Go check the depth.
Found it! Now I remember! This is the place!
Good thing he still lives here.
Right, I'm glad he does. Let's get the kids.
Ellie, I've found it!
But the bear isn't here.
Maybe he's just away for a little while. On a honey hunting trip or so.
If so, this is a perfect opportunity, teehee.
How about we look around the dwelling when the owner is away?
But what if Honey Bear comes back?
Exactly! He may jump at us this time!
I can keep watch for you.
I've seen him before. You, on the other hand, should take this opportunity to know Honey Bear better.
Everyone simply check what's close to you.
I've looked at this place from afar. It's piled with random stuff.
The kids have been examining the place carefully. They've probably found something.
Who shall I ask?
I've found a [em1]letter[/em1].
It says about moving. They've probably abandoned Honey Bear.
Did you read the whole letter?
Humph, I don't need to. All adults are alike.
But they may have their reasons. Try to step into their shoes.
Honey Bear used to be close to a certain girl, who had to move away.
Honey Bear found a doll she had left behind. He likes it too, so he isn't throwing it away.
Look at the stuff again with that in mind.
Oh, she wanted to take Honey Bear with her, but she wasn't able to.
If so, the other stuff may also be belongings she failed to take with her!
Honey Bear has collected them one by one!
Is this the girl and Honey Bear in this painting? What are they holding?
The letter mentioned a doll. This could be the doll.
I see. I believe they used to play house together.
Right, it's just like what you say!
If that's true... is Honey Bear still waiting for his friend? All alone?
It must be lonely. If Granny is gone, I'd be very sad too...
I know! It'd be the same for me if I lose Clala!
And we have our parents, who often check on us by writing letters...
But he may not have anyone to care for him.
Nevertheless, Honey Bear is being strong. He had a good time when I retrieved the doll for him.
Is he really having a good time?
Maybe he simply knows no better life because he's on his own.
And solitude must be even harder to endure if you once had company...
I believe that deep down, Honey Bear feels lonely. He's just putting up a happy front because dwelling on his loneliness hurts.
Hm? Ellie, did you hear something?
I think I heard someone [em1]humming[/em1]...
I'll ask the other kids too.
Heh, I found a [em1]painting[/em1]!
I think it's a family portrait. It has daddy, mommy, and two kids in it!
Honey Bear was actually a daddy! Heh.
Dana‌
It's mostly [em1]random stuff[/em1]. Here's a pretty doll.
But it's the only thing notable.
Has Honey Bear abandoned the place? Maybe he's left it to the doll.
<shake>It's him! It's him! The bear!</shake>
Ellie! Come quickly!
Calm down, kids! He was quite docile the last time we met.
A-are you serious?! He may be docile, but he's larger than you!
Seriously! Ellie!
My goodness, Theo, you gave me a scare.
You should have come fast!
Ugh, wait... He's bigger than I thought...
Theo, it's really fine. He won't hurt us... probably.
You won't, right? Hello, do you remember me? I retrieved your doll for you.
What do you mean by "probably"? And why are you greeting him?! Stay away!
Because I'm not perfectly sure... Wait a second.
You're not trembling, are you?
<shake>O-o-of course I'm not trembling!</shake>
I-I-I'm just concerned!
I'm the leader of this party! I'm responsible for everyone's safety!
Pffft... I didn't know you were that responsible!
Shut up! I certainly am! And why can you stay so collected!
You're way too close to the animal...
<shake>Hahaha</shake>, Theo, your face is so funny.
What the— Where's the [em1]honey[/em1] coming from!
It's all over my face.
Anyway... Everything ended well, except my face.
Hahaha! Theo, look at your big smile.
I think he enjoys our [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))][/em1]s.
And he has a huge appetite. I hardly got to eat any.
Your dwelling is a mess. You'll injure yourself if you don't clean it.
And eat properly! You should take care of yourself when nobody's there to look out for you.
I've got friends, if not family, but you're literally on your own...
Sigh... Come to think of it, Honey Bear, you shouldn't eat so many desserts in one go.
Wh-what are you doing! Didn't you enjoy the donuts?!
That's how [em1]Honey Bear says thanks[/em1].
Who would express gratitude by smudging people's faces with honey?!
And he's not the first to do this. Ellie did it too. Do you guys have something against my face? It's so sticky now...
Theo, are you alright?
Haha! Theo, you've got honey all over your face!
I think it wanted you to quit nagging.
I wasn't nagging! You know nothing about real nagging!
Heh, Theo, you sound like Clala!
Like how she always says, "What am I going to do with you?"
You remind me of my granny too.
What? How so! I was just telling him to take care of himself.
What on earth am I defending myself for...
Why? What's the matter with that?
It's just normal that you become talkative when you worry about someone.
What's with that look? It's creepy.
Hehe, I won't say it out loud.
Your eyes are saying it already.
But... is he going to lead such a life forever? When will his family come back?
Wait, how about you come to [em1]my house[/em1]?
That was a great adventure! I've made a new friend!
I'll visit him again with even more donuts!
The same donut as before?
Yeah, I've noted down Clala's recipe.
Speaking of which... You hardly ate any.
Huh? Now? But it's night already.
Night is the ideal time.
Don't worry about it. See you!
Honey Bear real love the donuts. He actually ate all of them.
... Oh! It just occurred to me. I've got something to tell you, teehee.
Come here [em1]at night[/em1] if you've got time.
Now that we mention Honey Bear, thank you for what happened just now.
When Honey Bear approached us, you shielded me with your body, didn't you?
And you did it while trembling, pffft.
It wasn't because of fear! I was thrilled to see him!
And it wasn't like I had a choice.
If you're injured, we'll be banned from adventures and get lectured.
Alright, alright. I've got your point.
I had fun too, although I do wish I had more [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))] to eat.
It can't be helped, but we can make more of them one day.
<shake>Wh-why are you here?</shake> I told you to come [em1]at night[/em1]!
Why does it have to be [em1]at night[/em1]?
B-because we are more likely to be seen during the day...
S-stop asking questions! Leave me, and come back [em1]at night[/em1]! Shoo!
I wonder why Theo reacted like that.
There's nothing I can do. I'll just come back [em1]at night[/em1].
Well... I just wanted to give you this. It's a leftover.
Is it... a [em1][lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))][/em1]?
I thought they were all gone.
Well... I found it at the bottom of the bag.
Really? But it feels warm, as if freshly out of the oven...
And you smell like bread — slightly burned bread.
<shake>Y-you're mistaken!</shake> It's just a leftover!
Because of me, you didn't get much to eat back at Dana's.
And I couldn't have found Honey Bear's habitat or become friends with him had it not been for you.
Just think of it as a [em1]gift[/em1] from the party leader!
Be sure to savor it. It's the only good one.
That's all. Let's hang out again, Ellie!
I don't think it's this way.
Ellie! What are you doing at this time of day? Are you lost? Teehee.
Theo, you aren't visiting Enite anymore?
Why? Did Enite talk to you about it?
Humph, I just don't feel like going.
If you plan to lecture me like the others do, I'm leaving.
Sigh... You just won't listen.
Fine, let's talk about the [em1]adventure[/em1] you mentioned before. How's that?
Rubrum said that you saw a [em1]horrible monster[/em1].
It wasn't horrible! It was just a [em1]weird-looking animal[/em1].
If Rubrum and Dana weren't that scared, I would have had a closer look.
In the end, I ordered a retreat, because the party leader has to be considerate of his members.
But I want to go again and find out more about the animal...
You're making me curious. A [em1]weird-looking animel[/em1]...
What species was it?
Hm? Just a large and weird-looking animal. That's all.
That's not what I'm asking about. Is it hard to describe?
Make your [em1]question[/em1] more specific.
So that we can narrow down the candidates.
Good idea!
What shall I ask about?
I only caught a glimpse from afar, but it was [em1]huge[/em1]. Certainly bigger than you. Maybe around Arden's size.
Hm, [em1]bigger[/em1] than me...
I need to ask for more information.
An animal that matches all three descriptions.
You've seen it before. Try to recall it.
[em1]A large animal that has legs and makes adorable noises[/em1]...
Could it be a Gaga Bird?
Do you remember the first time you met a Gaga Bird?
Did its noises sound adorable to you?
Not really. I'll try again.
Now I remember! It's a [em1]Honey Bear[/em1]!
Honey Bear?
Right! It's a honey enthusiast found in the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Common", "Common_Theme_RainbowForest"))].
So that's what he's called! If he likes honey, he can have a sweet tooth just like I do.
I wish I could meet him again!
Go visit him then. He'll be glad if you get him a [em1]gift[/em1].
You're right. I can get him some desserts with honey added to them!
Why don't we ask Enite? Enite makes pies and cakes!
Maybe not Enite... What about the bakery!
We can go to [em1]Dana's home, the bakery[/em1].
Dana's big sis is a baker, which means she's a professional dessert maker.
But Clala is probably too busy for this.
We can make our own desserts then!
Huh? That... will be kind of hard...
Ellie once cooked herself a burned meal and insisted on eating it.
Hey! Don't give me away!
It's okay. I can cook.
You can...?
Yup, I learned it from Granny, because my parents are too busy to cook for me.
I can coach you if you aren't sure about yourself, teehee.
You've prepared the Witch's Party Snack Gift Boxes, and we can consult the baker.
Come on! <shake>Let's do it! Let's do it! Let's do it!</shake>
Ahhhh! Shut up! I'll do it, okay?
Great, I'll tell Clala. Find me at [em1]Clala[/em1]'s place!
Starwhale
Could it be a Starwhale?
Wake up. Starwhales don't have legs.
Noises
It makes [em1]adorable noises[/em1] despite being large.
When approached by other animals, it would greet them cheerfully with cute cries!
[em1]Cute cries[/em1]...
It was as mobile as we are. It had [em1]legs[/em1].
An animal with [em1]legs[/em1]...
Why? You've been here all on your own this whole time.
She may never come. She may have forgotten you.
Maybe he believes she will come back. That's why he's still here.
If he stays, she can find him when she's back.
That's so stubborn... You're such a fool...
If she never comes back, he's literally abandoned.
What about this? You can join my [em1]party[/em1]!
Join the party?
Right, you can stay with us before the child comes back.
Even if she does come back, we'll make her regret not coming back earlier, because we'll have created so many happy memories together!
If you have to wait, wait while you play with us!
I insist on being your friend. You have no right to refuse! Teehee.
Hm...? Who was that?
Don't look at me! It wasn't me!
Me neither.
I would never make that sound on such an occasion!
If so... It was Honey Bear?
He can be hungry.
What are we waiting for? Theo, we have food on us!
You mean the [lua(GetLocalizedString("Item", "HoneyDonut_Name"))]s?
Honey Bear! You like sweet food, don't you?
I planned to eat all of it, but since I've taken a liking to you,
I'll make an exception and share some with you. Try it!
This is how you eat it! Hold the donut with your hands, and bite down.
It won't budge...
[em1]It's hard for a single person to uproot[/em1], remember?
I need to get everyone.
Theo, is that you? What are you doing here?
<shake>E-Ellie!</shake> Help! Help Honey Bear!
I was worried about Honey Bear, so I came to check on him.
Then I found him out cold.
He feels as hot as flames! Arin was right after all!
That herb was indeed [em1]poisonous[/em1].
<shake>P-poisonous?</shake> I-is Honey Bear going to die?
It isn't necessarily fatal.
But by the look of his condition, he needs an [em1]antidote[/em1].
Arin said she would look into it. I'll go ask her.
I'm going too!
Honey Bear, hang in there!
I hope this isn't too bad.
I should have gotten Ellie to help me.
No, she's gonna make me a laughingstock.
Em, but it's the first time I've ever written a [em1]letter[/em1].
Umm... Mom, Dad,
During my stay in this village, I've realized something.
I've been feeling lonely this whole time.
I've been hungry for attention, and I can have it if I play pranks.
As a result, I've been messing around, and seeking my favorite desserts.
I call myself a grown-up when I'm actually the most childish one.
And I, irresponsibly, run away from my mistakes.
<wave>Phew!</wave> It feels so good now that I've figured everything out. I was such a fool. Why didn't I realize it earlier! Teehee.
Mom, Dad, you don't need to worry about me anymore.
I can now handle bitter food, study hard, and look after myself.
Until we meet again, I wish you success in your work.
Thank you for sending me here. I'm glad to have met everyone at Wisteria.
I don't plan to get along with the villagers.
Why not? Be nice to people!
Why should I befriend everyone?
I don't mind taking them with me during an adventure though, as long as they behave, teehee.
That's so arrogant of you.
It's the same for you, Ellie. Make a good impression on me if you want to be part of my party.
You'd better reconsider your attitude, heh.
You enjoy your life here, right?
Of course! I can do whatever I want while I'm here!
But your parents may take you away if they learn that you're causing trouble.
And Enite knows your parents.
How dare you threaten me with that...!
That's not a threat. That's a fair negotiation.
Tsk, fine.
A gift from someone who sincerely wants to be your friend. Go ahead and open it.
You've actually got a gift for me? I didn't expect that from your barbs.
<shake>Ahhh! What is this!</shake>
Ahaha! A <wave>surprise</wave> from me!
And you call yourself sincere?
I've a potion to craft! Leave me alone!
It eases the tension on a first meeting, teehee.
I don't want any awkward silence.
This won't help you leave a good impression.
It's better than awkwardness.
Nevertheless... I'll take this token of "sincerity."
Just you wait.
Take your revenge if you can.
Haven't I already given it to you?
Teehee, a seed of wish? Ellie, you're too naive.
Are you mocking me!?
I'm not, teehee. I called you naive because you are naive.
Find a kid that loves [em1]fairy tales[/em1] if you believe in such things.
I'm past believing in such childish nonsense.
Jeez, Theo's letterbox is full to the brim!
It's all [em1]letters from his parents[/em1].
Why does he leave them here...
Here's a letter.
From his parents?
No, wait, it's a letter from Theo to his parents!
For your information, reading someone else's letter without permission is a crime.
I know. I'm just relieved to know that he's writing to them.
Theo's relationship with his parents has improved! Yahoo!
This letter is crumpled...
I suppose I can peek into it if it's discarded?
Shall I read it?
Are you doing your homework? Or cleaning your room? We hope you're eating more than just snacks.
We've read the letter from Ms. Enite.
She said that you were poorly dressed, and messing around all the time.
We've told you repeatedly that you should watch your manners all the time.
Cause no more trouble to others, and take responsibility for your actions.
How are you doing in Wisteria? Sorry we are always away.
Much as we want to write more, we must go back to work now.
Take good care of yourself, and stay healthy.
We hope to hear from you one day.
Much Love, Mom and Dad.
Graduation? You mean a fake ceremony for getting books?
Ellie, what's so great about schools?
You actually want to experience graduation twice, teehee.
By the way, if you want [em1]more[/em1] fireworks, just let me know!
Why are you so happy when we've got so much work to do...?
There's no need!
No neeeed?
Alvin's recently stocked his sundries store with a bunch of new stuff that can probably make incredible fireworks, teehee.
