Act 3: A Wisteria-Scented Letter
I planned to use potions set aside for the event, just like before, but...
Since the event is organized by the Administration, I can't afford to let anything go wrong.
Use the quill pen to draw and gather information, then use the right potion to obtain gathered materials.
I actually want to stick to this place only.
There's no request at the moment.
It's very kind of you.
I just wanted to eat more, so I started copying what I’d seen over her shoulder. I suppose that’s how it all began
Have you ever had any steak?
I've got you one of the streaks I roasted.
It will give you strength.
If you craft and deliver well, you will get the chance to deliver more advanced potions and in larger quantity. I look forward to your good work.
Virgil, [em1]something weird and squashy[/em1] is trying to eat my letter.
Are my eyes playing tricks on me?
You have my words: They aren't.
Which means... there's indeed a squashy thingy eating my [em1]letter[/eml]?
At least that's what I see.
<shake>You thief! Leave my letter alone!</shake>
Huh? Wait, that's me?!
It transformed?!
But it's not moving.
It's an opening then! Let's catch it!
How did it assume my appearance?
And the blobs it ejected maintain their shape even if I touch them...
And they make my hands sticky.
Well, it looked different from its usual form, but I guess I recognize it.
You do?
Something that transforms, shoots blobs when fleeing,
gathers items, and has a squashy body. Only one creature meets all these descriptions.
You've learned about it at school. You should know it.
I-is it a [em1]Mimic Jelly[/em1]?!
But [em1]Mimic Jellies[/em1] are an endangered species illegal to collect.
If it was a Mimic Jelly, my letter is lost for good.
I don't think that's the case. There's no rule against taking a Mimic Jelly's collection.
Once a Mimic Jelly gets an item, it carries the item around forever.
We should make it throw the items up. It's good for the Mimic Jelly too.
That's interesting. I shall lend it a hand then.
Read the [em1]letter[/em1] first.
Hi, Ellie! It's Rubrum writing.
You've helped me a lot lately! So I'm writing this letter to thank you!
You've treated my injuries, taken me back to the village, and brought me lots of good luck ever since!
In return, I've baked you a [em1]pie[/em1]. It's not much, but hope you like it!
PS: Do tell me if the pie was good when you've had it!
Wow, it's a letter from Rubrum!
He wants to know wheter the pie was good. He's so adorable.
Pay him a visit later.
I will. Where's the pie then? The pie Rubrum gifted me...
...Virgil, is it just me, or is there no pie?
You've had my words. Your eyes are functioning normally.
If the pie's missing, I can only think of one explanation.
It's not my letter that the Mimic Jelly has taken. It's my [em1]pie[/em1]?!
<shake>Wh-what do I do?!</shake>
One way to get a Mimic Jelly's collection is to pop its blobs.
But I tried with my hands and failed.
Just approach a blob [em1]on your broom[/em1] and break it.
What? Why a [em1]broom[/em1] all of a sudden? Will that work?
The magic in brooms is said to be effective against those blobs.
The mechanics I don't understand, though.
Come on, so you are also clueless.
I do know how to break the blobs.
Right, right, you're amazing.
